import{_ as u,o as a,c as n,q as d,w as g,F as f,p,P as w,a as t,t as l,m as y,U as b,C as v,f as k}from"./chunks/framework.Bn3ma71E.js";const T={name:"PoemCard",props:{poems:{type:Array,required:!0,validator:o=>o.every(e=>"source"in e&&"target"in e&&"rationale"in e)}},data(){return{poemLoaded:!1}},mounted(){setTimeout(()=>{this.poemLoaded=!0},500)},computed:{visiblePoems(){return this.poems.slice(0,this.$parent.visibleCount)}}},I={class:"poem-container"},A={class:"review-title"},S={class:"review-content"},x={class:"review-rationale"},C={key:1,class:"loading-state"};function B(o,e,c,m,i,s){return a(),n("div",I,[d(b,{name:"fade-slide"},{default:g(()=>[i.poemLoaded?(a(!0),n(f,{key:0},p(s.visiblePoems,(r,h)=>(a(),n("div",{key:h,class:"review",style:w({"animation-delay":`${h*.2}s`})},[t("div",A,"Question: "+l(r.target),1),t("p",S,"Answer: "+l(r.source),1),t("div",x,[t("p",null,[e[0]||(e[0]=t("strong",null,"Rationale:",-1)),y(" "+l(r.rationale),1)])])],4))),128)):(a(),n("div",C,e[1]||(e[1]=[t("div",{class:"loading-spinner"},null,-1),t("p",null,"loading...",-1)])))]),_:1})])}const M=u(T,[["render",B],["__scopeId","data-v-30afd1a2"]]),H=JSON.parse(`[{"source":"Based on the premise \\"Selenastrum capricornutum\\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"There is no such thing as whatever this is.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The statement \\"There is no such thing as whatever this is\\" contradicts the information provided in the premise, which suggests that Selenastrum capricornutum does indeed exist. So, we can conclude that the hypothesis is false and say \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Given a disfluent sentence, modify the sentence to it to its equivalent fluent form, preserving the meaning of the sentence.\\n\\nWhy is the most timelines no the most recent era expanded in the first scale?","target":"Why is the most recent era expanded in the first scale?","rationale":"The given sentence is disfluent. It needs to be edited to its fluent version. The correct version of this sentence would be: \\"Why is the most recent era expanded in the first scale?\\""},{"source":"I gave my students this multiple choice question: Decomposers are organisms that obtain their food from dead organisms. Which of these would be classified as decomposers?\\n\\nOnly one answer is correct among these 4 choices:\\n- algae, plants\\n- snakes, wolves, whales\\n- deer, rabbits, mice\\n- bacteria, fungi\\n\\nCould you tell me which one is correct?","target":"bacteria, fungi","rationale":"Algae are plants, and bacteria and fungi are not animals. So the correct answer is \\"bacteria, fungi\\"."},{"source":"Question: \\"What pole is not present in Antartica?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"During the Eocene (56 million years ago - 33.9 million years ago), the continents continued to drift toward their present positions. At the beginning of the period, Australia and Antarctica remained connected, and warm equatorial currents mixed with colder Antarctic waters, distributing the heat around the world and keeping global temperatures high. But when Australia split from the southern continent around 45 Ma, the warm equatorial currents were deflected away from Antarctica, and an isolated cold water channel developed between the two continents. The Antarctic region cooled down, and the ocean surrounding Antarctica began to freeze, sending cold water and ice floes north, reinforcing the cooling. The present pattern of ice ages began about 40 million years ago.[citation needed]\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"north","rationale":"The context mentions the Eocene period, which began 56 million years ago and ended 33.9 million years ago. This was a time of high global temperatures due to warm equatorial currents mixing with colder Antarctic waters, but when Australia split from Antarctica around 45 Ma (million years ago), cooler water surrounded Antarctica, leading to ice ages that still occur today. Based on these facts about climate change during the Eocene Period, it can be inferred that at this point in history there were no polar opposites present in Antartica because it remained connected with Australia for much longer than any other continent/country. Therefore, \\"north\\" is not an answer as north pole exists now also referred as magnetic poles\\nSo , north isn't correct here"},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nTrademark infringement occurs when one party uses a trademark that is identical or confusingly similar to a trademark owned by another party, in relation to products or services which are identical or similar to the products or services of the other party. In many countries, a trademark receives protection without registration, but registering a trademark provides legal advantages for enforcement. Infringement can be addressed by civil litigation and, in several jurisdictions, under criminal law.\\nHow is trademark infringement addressed in most jurisdictions?","target":"civil litigation","rationale":"The article states that \\"infringement can be addressed by civil litigation and, in several jurisdictions, under criminal law.\\". \\nThus the answer is: civil litigation"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: What round was DaJuan Summers taken in teh NBA draft of 2009? Passage 1:The Hoyas‚Ä≤ previous season had been a disappointing one in which the relatively young and experienced Georgetown team had fallen from a Top Ten ranking in early January 2009 to a 16‚Äì15 finish in March that ended with the loss of 12 out of 16 games and first-round exits from both the 2009 Big East Tournament and the 2009 National Invitation Tournament. The Hoyas had lost starting forward DaJuan Summers after the end of the season when he chose to forego his senior year of college and enter the 2009 National Basketball Association draft, as well as starting guard Jessie Sapp, who graduated, and reserve guard/forward Omar Wattad, who transferred. But with freshman forwards Jerrelle Benimon and Hollis Thompson joining the team and sophomore starting center Greg Monroe, junior reserve center Henry Sims, junior starting guards Austin Freeman and Chris Wright, junior reserve forward Julian Vaughn, and sophomore reserve forward Jason Clark all returning, the Hoyas expected to bounce back in 2009‚Äì10. The preseason Associated Press Poll ranked them No. 20.\\n Passage 2:Lewald was born in 1860; his aunt was Jewish novelist Fanny Lewald. Lewald became a civil servant in Prussia in 1885, and became the acting Reich Commissioner in 1903. In that role, Lewald attended the 1904 Worlds Fair (held along with the Olympic Games), where he disagreed with Kaiser Wilhelm II over whether the Deutscher Olympischer Sportbund, of which he was the President, should be politically independent. After Berlin won the right to stage the 1916 Summer Olympics (which were later cancelled due to the outbreak of World War I), Lewald encouraged the German Reich to invest in the games, arguing that it was comparable to a World Trade Exhibition. Lewald retired from government in 1923; he had been the under Secretary of State. In 1935, Lewald recommended that Pierre de Coubertin be awarded a Nobel Prize.\\n Passage 3:In 2008, Holden recommenced Caprice exports to South Korea as the Daewoo Veritas after showcasing a pre-production Daewoo L4X in 2007. Compared to the Australian-specification model, the Veritas is V6-powered only and has a modified rear floorpan to accommodate the electrically adjustable rear seats incorporating a massage function. The head restraints are also electrically adjustable, with the Caprice's dual headrest-mounted LCD screens orphaned in favour of a single, ceiling-mounted unit. GM Daewoo announced an updated Veritas on 31 March 2009 to take effect from 1 April. The update, which was yet to be seen in other markets, comprised a revised powertrain combination, featuring a new direct injection version of the 3.6-litre Alloytec engine. This new engine results in a power increase from to together with more torque and a reduced fuel consumption figure. These efficiency improvements have been enough to satisfy the government of South Korea's \\"Korea Ultra-Low Emission Vehicle\\" (KULEV) requirements. In place of the five-speed automatic transmission previously, these revised models ship with a six-speed GM 6L50 unit, featuring Active Select.","target":"1","rationale":"The question asks about the NBA draft of 2009 and Passage 1 was the only passage which contains information about DaJuan Summers or the NBA draft of 2009."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question.\\nQuestion: \\"how did the penguins acquire sidney crosby?\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Sidney Crosby","rationale":"The question \\"how did the Penguins acquire Sidney Crosby?\\" asks how a team in the National Hockey League acquired another player. \\nTherefore, it is about Sidney Crosby and not specifically about Pittsburgh Penguins or hockey as a whole."},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: What is the last name of the person who threatens to yank a record company's discs out of jukeboxes everywhere?, using the article: Everything's going well at Disco Records, where singer Johnny Conroy is popular and publicity chief Marty Collins is good at her job, as well as in love with company boss Mack Adams.\\nEverything changes when Barney Pearl shows up. Pearl is a crude businessman who supplies records to jukeboxes coast-to-coast. He demands to be made a full partner in Disco Records or he will yank their discs out of jukes everywhere. Furthermore, he insists that singer girlfriend Mona De Luce gets to make a record of her own.\\nImplored not to agree, Mack goes along. Pearl keeps the pressure on, renaming the company after himself. Johnny quits and leaves on his sailboat for points unknown. Mona, meanwhile, is a much better singer than expected. Her record is a smash hit, annoying Barney, who wants her wholly dependent on him. Barney demands her career come to an end.\\nMarty, Mack and Mona all travel to the West Indies, where Johnny is now enjoying the sun, fun and music. Johnny suggests they begin recording calypso songs. It all works out perfectly, and when Pearl tries to cut himself in, they find a way to keep him out., what would be the answer ?","target":"Pearl","rationale":"The article describes a record company owner, called Mack Adams. The last name of the person who threatens to yank records out of jukeboxes everywhere is also described in this passage; he is named Barney Pearl. So this answer makes sense based on the context provided in the article."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"The IEEE 1394 interface is a serial bus interface standard for high-speed communications and isochronous real-time data transfer.\\"\\nTopic:","target":"IEEE 1394","rationale":"The topic of the passage was IEEE 1394, which is a standard bus interface technology."},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: what was irving langmuir famous for?","target":"Franklin Medal","rationale":"Irving Langmuir was a Nobel Prize winning American chemist and physicist who is famous for his discoveries in surface chemistry.\\nHe received the Franklin Medal from The Franklin Institute, which recognizes scientists whose work has had an impact on humanity's quality of life. \\nTherefore, the correct answer to \\"what was Irving langmuir famous for\\" is that he won the Franklin medal."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nCompared to a hydrocarbon with a single carbon atom, would a hydrocarbon with 10 carbon atoms have a greater number of isomers or fewer isomers?? \\n\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nThe more carbon atoms a hydrocarbon has, the greater the number of isomers.","target":"a greater number of isomers","rationale":"The paragraph tells us that the more carbon atoms a hydrocarbon has, the greater number of isomers. So it follows that if we increase the number of carbon atoms from 1 to 10, we should expect an increased in isomers as well.\\nSo answer would be \\"a greater number of isomers\\"."},{"source":"When would you want a radiator the most?\\n- winter\\n- spring\\n- fall\\n- summer\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"winter","rationale":"The correct answer is winter. In the fall, temperatures are usually still warm enough to not need a radiator. Spring and summer bring warmer weather again, so you won't be needing a radiator in either of these seasons. The only season out of this list that has colder weather would be winter - thus making it the best time for using your radiator!\\n'''"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: How many emperors succeeded Emperor Gaozu during his dynasty? Passage 1:Seraphine co-wrote several songs for the band: \\"Lowdown\\" (a Top 40 hit for the band), the instrumentals \\"Prelude to Aire\\", \\"Aire\\", and \\"Devil's Sweet\\" from the album Chicago VII, \\"Little One\\", \\"Take Me Back to Chicago\\", \\"Show Me the Way\\", \\"Birthday Boy\\" and \\"Street Player\\". His writing partner was often David \\"Hawk\\" Wolinski, the keyboardist for Rufus featuring Chaka Khan. His song \\"Street Player\\" was sampled by The Bucketheads for the dance hit \\"The Bomb! (These Sounds Fall into My Mind)\\", and later by rapper Pitbull for the hit \\"I Know You Want Me (Calle Ocho)\\" from the album \\"Rebelution\\". The song samples \\"75, Brazil Street\\" by Nicola Fasano versus Pat Rich, which itself samples \\"Street Player\\". \\"I Know You Want Me\\" has also been featured in Dance Central, the dancing game for Kinect, Dance Dance Revolution X2 for PlayStation 2, and SingStar Dance, the dancing game for PlayStation Move.\\n Passage 2:Both Sui and Tang empires occupied the same location. In 582, Emperor Wen of the Sui dynasty sited a new region southeast of the much ruined Han Dynasty Chang'an to build his new capital, which he called Daxing (Â§ßËàà, ‚ÄúGreat Prosperity‚Äù). Daxing was renamed Chang'an in year 618 when the Duke of Tang, Li Yuan, proclaimed himself the Emperor Gaozu of Tang. Chang'an during the Tang dynasty (618‚Äì907) was, along with Constantinople (Istanbul) and Baghdad, one of the largest cities in the world. It was a cosmopolitan urban center with considerable foreign populations from other parts of Asia and beyond. This new Chang'an was laid out on a north-south axis in a grid pattern, dividing the enclosure into 108 wards and featuring two large marketplaces, in the east and west respectively. Everyday, administrators of the two marketplaces would beat gong for three hundred times in the morning and evening to signify the start and stop of business. People lived in the wards were not allowed to go outside after curfew. Officials with higher-ranking had the privilege to live closer to the central avenue. Chang'an's layout influenced city planning of several other Asian capitals for many years to come. Chang'an's walled and gated wards were much larger than conventional city blocks seen in modern cities, as the smallest ward had a surface area of 68 acres and the largest ward had a surface area of . The height of the walls enclosing each ward were on average 9 to in height. The Japanese built their ancient capitals, Heij≈ç-ky≈ç (today's Nara) and later Heian-ky≈ç or Kyoto, modelled after Chang'an in a more modest scale yet was never fortified. The modern Kyoto still retains some characteristics of Sui-Tang Chang'an. Similarly, the Korean Silla dynasty modeled their capital of Gyeongju after the Chinese capital. Sanggyeong, one of the five capitals of the state of Balhae, was also laid out like Chang'an.\\n Passage 3:The son of James and Christina Murray, he was born at Aberdeen in June 1873. He was educated at both Aberdeen Grammar School and Galashiels Academy, before studying engineering at Heriot Watt Engineering School. He served in the Royal Navy, firstly as an assistant engineer, before being promoted to the rank of engineer in June 1902. He served as an engineering instructor at the Britannia Royal Naval College for over twenty years. He was appointed as the superintendent overseeing the construction of in 1902, joining the ship when it was commissioned in 1905. A keen cricketer, Murray made a single first-class cricket appearance for the Royal Navy, making his debut against the British Army cricket team at Lord's in 1913. Batting twice in the match, he was dismissed without scoring in the Royal Navy's first-innings by Harold Fawcus, while in their second-innings he was dismissed for 29 runs by the same bowler. Murray served in the First World War, during which he was seconded to the battleship . He served aboard the ship at the Battle of Jutland on 31 May 1916, when he was killed after the ship exploded and sank.","target":"2","rationale":"The question asks for the number of emperors that succeeded Emperor Gaozu. The information is directly provided in passage 2: \\"Emperor Wen of the Sui dynasty sited a new region southeast of the much ruined Han Dynasty Chang'an to build his new capital, which he called Daxing (Â§ßËàà, ‚ÄúGreat Prosperity‚Äù). Daxing was renamed Chang'an in year 618 when the Duke of Tang, Li Yuan, proclaimed himself the Emperor Gaozu of Tang.\\""},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, judge whether or not a specific person is wrong here. Answer 'not answerable' if more information is required and 'answerable' if all the information is sufficient to answer who is wrong in this situation.\\n\\nI was house sitting for a friend since Friday.  I had my bf over on Saturday and didn‚Äôt think twice about it.  I never discussed it with my friend who I was house sitting.  I never thought it would be an issue.  When my friend came back I mentioned that my bf really liked this coffee table she has.  She acted a little weird and I pressed her what was wrong.  She said she didn‚Äôt appreciate that I invited someone over to her house without asking her first.  He‚Äôs not a stranger, he‚Äôs my bf.   I really didn‚Äôt expect her to care.","target":"answerable","rationale":"The friend who was house sitting was not told that she could not invite anyone over, so she assumed it would be fine to have her boyfriend over. The friend who owned the house did not mind that someone was in the house, but instead felt disrespected because they were invited over without asking first. The person being invited over is an important part of their life and it seems strange to ask if they could invite them over. To him/her, this seemed like a non-issue and she should have been able to assume it would be okay. Therefore, the answer is 'answerable' because the owner of the house is wrong for being bothered by having someone else in her home when she went away for a few days."},{"source":"Given the prompt and a response, classify the them to \\"yes\\" if response is \\"yes, and\\" type. Otherwise classify it as \\"no\\". \\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). 1 In short, a \\"Yes, and\\" is a dialogue exchange in which a speaker responds by adding new information on top of the information/setting that was constructed by another speaker. Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange, although it could be the case if it agrees with the description above. There are many ways in which a response could implicitly/explicitly agree to the prompt without specifically saying 'yes, and...'. \\n\\nPrompt: Ladies and gentlemen, once again, we're just deplaning everyone. Once that's done, we're going to de-ice and get everyone back on the plane. \\n Response: Yeah, we're at the same gate. So, I kind of figured.","target":"no","rationale":"The response does not add to the prompt.  The person is simply acknowledging that they are at the same gate as the speaker and inferring that if everyone is being deplaned, it must be for de-icing."},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 3, equation weights = [3, 4, 7, 2, 9]","target":"429","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 3x^4 + 4x^3 + 7x^2 + 2x + 9\\\\nSubstituting x = 3, we get: 3(3)^4 + 4(3)^3 + 7(3)^2 + 2(3) ^ 1+ 9\\\\n= 243+ 108+ 63+ 6+9 = 429"},{"source":"Question: \\"Which of the following was not an aspect of Roman religion: prayer, sacrifice or faith?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"Roman religion was thus practical and contractual, based on the principle of do ut des, \\"I give that you might give.\\" Religion depended on knowledge and the correct practice of prayer, ritual, and sacrifice, not on faith or dogma, although Latin literature preserves learned speculation on the nature of the divine and its relation to human affairs. Even the most skeptical among Rome's intellectual elite such as Cicero, who was an augur, saw religion as a source of social order. For ordinary Romans, religion was a part of daily life. Each home had a household shrine at which prayers and libations to the family's domestic deities were offered. Neighborhood shrines and sacred places such as springs and groves dotted the city. The Roman calendar was structured around religious observances. Women, slaves, and children all participated in a range of religious activities. Some public rituals could be conducted only by women, and women formed what is perhaps Rome's most famous priesthood, the state-supported Vestals, who tended Rome's sacred hearth for centuries, until disbanded under Christian domination.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"faith","rationale":"Context says \\"Religion depended on knowledge and the correct practice of prayer, ritual, and sacrifice, not on faith or dogma\\", so that means faith was not an aspect."},{"source":"Read the text and determine if the sentence is true (see options at the end):\\n\\nThe Blood Cell is a BBC Books original novel written by James Goss and based on the long-running British science fiction television series \\"Doctor Who\\". It features the Twelfth Doctor and Clara Oswald. The book was released on 11 September 2014 along with \\"Silhouette\\" and \\"The Crawling Terror\\".\\n\\nSentence: The Blood Cell is fictional movie\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The passage states that \\"The Blood Cell is a BBC Books original novel written by James Goss.\\" The use of the word \\"novel\\" indicates that it is not fictional movie, so the answer is ‚ÄúNo‚Äù."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"Villa and Carranza had different political goals causing Villa to become an enemy of Carranza. After Carranza took control in 1914, Villa and other revolutionaries who opposed him met at what was called the Convention of Aguascalientes. The convention deposed Carranza in favor of Eulalio Guti√©rrez. In the winter of 1914 Villa's and Zapata's troops entered and occupied Mexico City. Villa was forced from the city in early 1915 and attacked the forces of Gen. Obreg√≥n at the Battle of Celaya and was badly defeated in the bloodiest battle of the revolution, with thousands dead. With the defeat of Villa, Carranza seized power. A short time later the United States recognized Carranza as president of Mexico. Even though Villa's forces were badly depleted by his loss at Celaya, he continued his fight against the Carranza government. Finally, in 1920, Obreg√≥n‚Äîwho had defeated him at Celaya‚Äîfinally reached an agreement with Villa end his rebellion.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: Villa was a member of the?","target":"revolutionaries","rationale":"The passage begins by mentioning that Villa and Carranza had different political goals, which caused them to be enemies. Both of the men were politically powerful; their enemy status is described in terms of politics rather than any other context (military or personal). \\nHowever, while there are mentions of battles fought between both sides throughout the text, these phrases do not describe a war. The phrase \\"the Convention of Aguascalientes\\" could refer to either a peace treaty or an alliance against Carranza as it describes something shared between all revolutionaries who opposed his rule but does not give enough detail on such purpose. This implies they have similar ideologies instead of completely conflicting ones. In addition, later paragraphs repeatedly state that Villa's forces fight alongside Zapata's troops with no indication whatsoever if this relationship"},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the no-need strategy, otherwise output No. no-need is a cooperative negotiation strategy. It is used when a participant points out that they do not need an item based on personal context such as suggesting that they have ample water to spare. no-need can directly benefit the opponent since it implies that the item is up for grabs.\\n\\nContext: 'Yes. Hoping we can make a good deal.' 'Me too!  I'm hoping for two food items and one water.  I'm diabetic so if my blood sugar drops, I may need the extra carbs.  And water because water is important! üôÇ ' 'I prefer two water and one food. I can understand why you need the extra food items. I'm not much of a snacker but do drink a lot of water all the time. Keeps me from eating more!üôÇ'\\nUtterance: 'Lol, it seems it was easy for us to come to a deal!  I'm super bad at drinking water (trying to get better) so I don't feel I'll need as much.  Do you want all of the firewood or should I take one and you take two?  '","target":"Yes","rationale":"\\"The speaker's utterance indicates that they don't need to drink much water and thus won't need as much water. Therefore, this is an example of the no-need strategy so the answer is Yes.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and an answer, you would be asked to create the sentence based on the Question-Answer provided. It should be contained within the Question-Answer provided.\\n\\nQuestion: Boron only occurs naturally in compounds with what element? Answer: oxygen","target":"Boron only occurs naturally in compounds with oxygen element","rationale":"You can combine the question and answer to create a sentence. For example, \\"Boron only occurs naturally in compounds with oxygen element.\\""},{"source":"If a bean is a mile away from where it originated , and then it develops into a plant which produces more beans, then that original bean most likely\\n- was flat\\n- was built\\n- was honest\\n- was transported\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"was transported","rationale":"The context mentions that the bean is a mile away from where it originated, or grew. It then develops into a plant and produces more beans. \\nGiven this information about how far the original seed traveled before growing into a plant, we can deduce that the original seed was transported to its location in some way. This makes \\"was transported\\" the correct answer as none of the other options are logical given what's presented in the context."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story coherent / plausible by writing \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes most sense.\\n\\nBeginning: The panda at the zoo was having a baby. Middle 1: The panda delivered the baby. Middle 2: The baby delivered the panda. Ending: The panda cuddled with her baby after it was born.","target":"1","rationale":"Middle 1 is the correct choice because it makes sense to say \\"The panda delivered the baby\\" since pandas give birth. It doesn't make sense to say \\"The baby delivered the panda\\" because babies are not doctors and cannot deliver other creatures."},{"source":"Read this and answer the question\\n\\nPhiladelphia's two major daily newspapers are The Philadelphia Inquirer, which is the eighteenth largest newspaper and third-oldest surviving daily newspaper in the country, and the Philadelphia Daily News. Both newspapers were purchased from The McClatchy Company (after buying out Knight Ridder) in 2006 by Philadelphia Media Holdings and operated by the group until the organization declared bankruptcy in 2010. After two years of financial struggle, the two newspapers were sold to Interstate General Media in 2012. The two newspapers have a combined circulation of about 500,000 readers.\\n\\nWho owns the major papers in the city?","target":"Interstate General Media","rationale":"In the last sentence of the text, it is mentioned that Interstate General Media purchased both newspapers. So this is indeed a correct answer!"},{"source":"Germany was far ahead of the Allies in using heavy indirect fire. The German Army employed 150¬†mm  and 210¬†mm  howitzers in 1914, when typical French and British guns were only 75¬†mm  and 105¬†mm . The British had a 6-inch  howitzer, but it was so heavy it had to be hauled to the field in pieces and assembled. The Germans also fielded Austrian 305¬†mm  and 420¬†mm  guns and, even at the beginning of the war, had inventories of various calibres of Minenwerfer, which were ideally suited for trench warfare.\\nAnswer this question: How many mm larger were the smaller guns used by the German Army than those used by the Allies?","target":"75","rationale":"Here's an example of how to solve this problem:\\\\n\\\\nSolution: The German Army employed 150 mm and 210 mm howitzers in 1914, when typical French and British guns were only 75¬†mm  and 105¬†mm . Hence the smaller gun used by the Germans was larger than those used by Allies by 75 mm."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"John kept him behind the garage.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence:\\\\nJohn kept him behind the garage."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Chemotherapy (often abbreviated to chemo and sometimes CTX or CTx) is a category of cancer treatment that uses one or more anti-cancer drugs (chemotherapeutic agents) as part of a standardized chemotherapy regimen. Chemotherapy may be given with a curative intent (which almost always involves combinations of drugs), or it may aim to prolong life or to reduce symptoms (palliative chemotherapy). Chemotherapy is one of the major categories of medical oncology (the medical discipline specifically devoted to pharmacotherapy for cancer).\\n\\n- A biopsy is a medical test commonly performed by a surgeon, interventional radiologist, or an interventional cardiologist involving extraction of sample cells or tissues for examination to determine the presence or extent of a disease. The tissue is generally examined under a microscope by a pathologist, and can also be analyzed chemically. When an entire lump or suspicious area is removed, the procedure is called an excisional biopsy. When only a sample of tissue is removed with preservation of the histological architecture of the tissues cells, the procedure is called an incisional biopsy or core biopsy. When a sample of tissue or fluid is removed with a needle in such a way that cells are removed without preserving the histological architecture of the tissue cells, the procedure is called a needle aspiration biopsy. Biopsies are most commonly performed for insight into possible cancerous and inflammatory conditions.\\n\\n- Xeroderma pigmentosum (XP) is a rare autosomal recessive genetic disorder of DNA repair in which the ability to repair damage caused by ultraviolet (UV) light is deficient. In extreme cases, \\"all\\" exposure to sunlight must be forbidden, no matter how small; as such, individuals with the disease are often colloquially referred to as \\"Moon child\\". Multiple basal cell carcinomas (basaliomas) and other skin malignancies frequently occur at a young age in those with XP; metastatic malignant melanoma and squamous cell carcinoma are the two most common causes of death in XP victims. This disease is present in both genders and in all races, with an incidence of 1:250,000 in the United States. XP is roughly six times more common in Japanese people than in other groups.\\n\\n- Ivan Yevhenovych Vyshnevskyi ( Ukrainian :    , Russian :    ; born 21 February 1957 in the village of Chortoryia ( today 's Myrolyubivka , Ternopil Raion ) ; died 11 May 1996 in Dnipropetrovsk of melanoma ) was a Ukrainian footballer . He earned 6 caps for the USSR national football team , making his debut on 25 January 1985 in a friendly against Yugoslavia . He was selected for the UEFA Euro 1988 squad , but did not play in any games at the tournament . He is from the region that once belonged to Winiowiecki family that had estates near Zboriv where the village of Vyshnivets is located .\\n\\n- Cancer is a group of diseases involving abnormal cell growth with the potential to invade or spread to other parts of the body. Not all tumors are cancerous; benign tumors do not spread to other parts of the body. Possible signs and symptoms include a lump, abnormal bleeding, prolonged cough, unexplained weight loss and a change in bowel movements. While these symptoms may indicate cancer, they may have other causes. Over 100 types of cancers affect humans.\\nTobacco use is the cause of about 22% of cancer deaths. Another 10% is due to obesity, poor diet, lack of physical activity and drinking alcohol. Other factors include certain infections, exposure to ionizing radiation and environmental pollutants. In the developing world nearly 20% of cancers are due to infections such as hepatitis B, hepatitis C and human papillomavirus (HPV). These factors act, at least partly, by changing the genes of a cell. Typically many genetic changes are required before cancer develops. Approximately 510% of cancers are due to inherited genetic defects from a person's parents. Cancer can be detected by certain signs and symptoms or screening tests. It is then typically further investigated by medical imaging and confirmed by biopsy.\\nMany cancers can be prevented by not smoking, maintaining a healthy weight, not drinking too much alcohol, eating plenty of vegetables, fruits and whole grains, vaccination against certain infectious diseases, not eating too much processed and red meat, and avoiding too much sunlight exposure. Early detection through screening is useful for cervical and colorectal cancer. The benefits of screening in breast cancer are controversial. Cancer is often treated with some combination of radiation therapy, surgery, chemotherapy, and targeted therapy. Pain and symptom management are an important part of care. Palliative care is particularly important in people with advanced disease. The chance of survival depends on the type of cancer and extent of disease at the start of treatment. In children under 15 at...\\n\\n- A lymph node or lymph gland, is an ovoid or kidney-shaped organ of the lymphatic system, and of the adaptive immune system, that is widely present throughout the body. They are linked by the lymphatic vessels as a part of the circulatory system. Lymph nodes are major sites of B and T lymphocytes, and other white blood cells. Lymph nodes are important for the proper functioning of the immune system, acting as filters for foreign particles and cancer cells. Lymph nodes do not have a detoxification function, which is primarily dealt with by the liver and kidneys.\\n\\n- Radiation therapy or radiotherapy, often abbreviated RT, RTx, or XRT, is therapy using ionizing radiation, generally as part of cancer treatment to control or kill malignant cells and normally delivered by a linear accelerator. Radiation therapy may be curative in a number of types of cancer if they are localized to one area of the body. It may also be used as part of adjuvant therapy, to prevent tumor recurrence after surgery to remove a primary malignant tumor (for example, early stages of breast cancer). Radiation therapy is synergistic with chemotherapy, and has been used before, during, and after chemotherapy in susceptible cancers. The subspecialty of oncology concerned with radiotherapy is called radiation oncology.\\n\\n- Melanoma, also known as malignant melanoma, is a type of cancer that develops from the pigment-containing cells known as melanocytes. Melanomas typically occur in the skin but may rarely occur in the mouth, intestines, or eye. In women they most commonly occur on the legs, while in men they are most common on the back. Sometimes they develop from a mole with concerning changes including an increase in size, irregular edges, change in color, itchiness, or skin breakdown.\\nThe primary cause of melanoma is ultraviolet light (UV) exposure in those with low levels of skin pigment. The UV light may be from either the sun or from other sources, such as tanning devices. About 25% develop from moles. Those with many moles, a history of affected family members, and who have poor immune function are at greater risk. A number of rare genetic defects such as xeroderma pigmentosum also increase risk. Diagnosis is by biopsy of any concerning skin lesion.\\nUsing sunscreen and avoiding UV light may prevent melanoma. Treatment is typically removal by surgery. In those with slightly larger cancers, nearby lymph nodes may be tested for spread. Most people are cured if spread has not occurred. For those in whom melanoma has spread, immunotherapy, biologic therapy, radiation therapy, or chemotherapy may improve survival. With treatment the five-year survival rates in the United States is 98% among those with localized disease and 17% among those in whom spread has occurred. The likelihood that it will come back or spread depends how thick the melanoma is, how fast the cells are dividing, and whether or not the overlying skin has broken down.\\nMelanoma is the most dangerous type of skin cancer. Globally, in 2012, it occurred in 232,000 people and resulted in 55,000 deaths. Australia and New Zealand have the highest rates of melanoma in the world. There are also high rates in Northern Europe and North America, while it is less common in Asia, Africa, and Latin America. Melanoma is more common in men than women. Melanoma has become more...\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, choose the best answer for the entity that related to 'ivan vyshnevskyi' with the relationship of 'cause of death'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- bleeding\\n - breast cancer\\n - cancer\\n - carcinoma\\n - disease\\n - hepatitis\\n - lung cancer\\n - melanoma\\n - old age\\n - skin cancer\\n - tumor","target":"skin cancer","rationale":"The information about Ivan Yevhenovych Vyshnevskyi says that he died of melanoma. The choices include \\"bleeding\\", \\"breast cancer\\", etc.\\nIn the information, it mentions: 'Xeroderma pigmentosum (XP) is a rare autosomal recessive genetic disorder of DNA repair in which the ability to repair damage caused by ultraviolet (UV) light is deficient.' and 'When an entire lump or suspicious area is removed, the procedure is called an excisional biopsy'. These statements indicate that skin cancers are related to UV exposure. Melanoma includes several types of malignant tumors including cutaneous and ocular melanomas according to Wikipedia article on Melanoma - Etymology & Types of Melanomas section where it states"},{"source":"Read the given text and if it has abusive content then indicate via \\"yes\\". Otherwise indicate via\\"no\\". \\nWe consider the content to be abusive if it contains any of the following instances: (1) Identity Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which contains a negative statement made against an identity. An identity is a social category that relates to a fundamental aspect of individuals community, socio-demographics, position or self-representation) (2) Affiliation Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which express negativity against an affiliation. We define affiliation as a (more or less) voluntary association with a collective. Affiliations include but are not limited to: memberships (e.g. Trade unions), party memberships (e.g. Republicans), political affiliations (e.g. Right-wing people) and occupations (e.g. Doctors).) (3) Person Directed Abuse (e.g., Content which directs negativity against an identifiable person, who is either part of the conversation thread or is named. Person-directed abuse includes serious character based attacks, such as accusing the person of lying, as well as aggression, insults and menacing language.) and (4) Counter Speech (e.g., Content which challenges, condemns or calls out the abusive language of others.). Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nI don't know how much evolutionary psychology is useful or evidenced, I'm sure there is a lot of hard working people who use it to come to valid conclusions. But in casual situations it sure is a buzzword to spot people who are going to use it as an excuse to justify shitty behaviour.    X *may possibly* confer some sort of reproductive advantage under certain circumstances I have made up, therefore it *is definitely universal to all humans*.","target":"no","rationale":"The post does not contain any abusive content. The post is related to evolutionary psychology and the author's opinion about it."},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : What is between Malaysia and Singapore?\\nAnswer :","target":"Selat Johor","rationale":"The Selat Johor is a strait separating the Malaysian state of Johor to the north and Singapore to the south."},{"source":"Background: A mycorrhiza (Greek for \\"fungus roots\\") is a symbiotic association between a fungus and the roots of a plant. In a mycorrhizal association, the fungus may colonize the roots of a host plant by either growing directly into the root cells, or by growing around the root cells. This association provides the fungus with relatively constant and direct access to glucose, which the plant produces by photosynthesis. The mycelia of the fungi increase the surface area of the plant‚Äôs root system. The larger surface area improves water and mineral nutrient absorption from the soil.\\n\\nParagraph: Two mycologists were studying fungi. Jim studied more about wood eating mushrooms and gourmet mushrooms, while George decided to study more about mycorrhiza, and its benefits for humans.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: Which mycologist learned more about fungus growing around the root cells?","target":"George","rationale":"Given that a mycorrhiza is an association between a fungus and the roots of a plant, it can be inferred from the paragraph that George would have studied more about fungi growing around root cells.\\nSo, the answer is George."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: What vessel did MacDonald equip for a further rescue attempt? from the following article ?\\n\\nShackleton's first task, on arriving at the Stromness station, was to arrange for his three companions at Peggoty Camp to be picked up. A whaler was sent round the coast, with Worsley aboard to show the way, and by the evening of 21 May all six of the James Caird party were safe.It took four attempts before Shackleton was able to return to Elephant Island to rescue the party stranded there. He first left South Georgia a mere three days after he had arrived in Stromness, after securing the use of a large whaler, The Southern Sky, which was laid up in Husvik Harbour. Shackleton assembled a volunteer crew, which had it ready to sail by the morning of 22 May. As the vessel approached Elephant Island they saw that an impenetrable barrier of pack ice had formed, some 70 miles (110 km) from their destination. The Southern Sky was not built for ice breaking, and retreated to Port Stanley in the Falkland Islands.On reaching Port Stanley, Shackleton informed London by cable of his whereabouts, and requested that a suitable vessel be sent south for the rescue operation. He was informed by the Admiralty that nothing was available before October, which in his view was too late. Then, with the help of the British Minister in Montevideo, Shackleton obtained from the Uruguayan government the loan of a tough trawler, Instituto de Pesca No. 1, which started south on 10 June. Again the pack thwarted them. In search of another ship, Shackleton, Worsley and Crean travelled to Punta Arenas, where they met Allan MacDonald, the British owner of the schooner Emma. McDonald equipped this vessel for a further rescue attempt, which left on 12 July, but with the same negative result‚Äîthe pack defeated them yet again. Shackleton later named a glacier after McDonald on the Brunt Ice Shelf in the Weddell Sea. After problems arose in identifying this glacier, a nearby ice rise was renamed the McDonald Ice Rumples.By now it was mid-August, more than three months since Shackleton had left Elephant Island. Shackleton begged the Chilean...","target":"Emma","rationale":"The question asks what vessel MacDonald equipped for a further rescue attempt. The passage mentions a schooner called Emma, which was owned by Allan McDonald and used for the third rescue attempt. So, the answer is Emma."},{"source":"Math problem: Solve 7*b - 2 = 9*b for b.\\nWhat is the solution?","target":"-1","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable b on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 7*b - 9*b = 2\\n[STEP 2] -2*b = 2\\n[STEP 3] b = -1"},{"source":"The Earth travels faster in its elliptical orbit when it is closer to the Sun than when it is farther away.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are Higher or Lower ):\\n\\n\\nJohn was watching the planets rotate around the sun. He noticed that was the distance between the sun and earth is higher, the speed of Earth is Higher or Lower?","target":"Lower","rationale":"The passage states that the Earth travels faster in its elliptical orbit when it is closer to the Sun than when it is farther away. This would mean that John's observation from watching the planets rotate around the sun was correct, and as a result, if he had noticed that an increase in distance between earth and sun yielded a decrease in speed of movement for planet earth (from his observations), then this means his answer choice should be Lower ."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an anaphor number agreement or as an incorrect representation. An anaphor is an expression whose interpretation depends upon another expression. Anaphor number agreement is a restriction where a phrase agrees with the preceeding expression: plurals match plurals or singular expressions match singular expressions. In this task a valid representation of anaphor number agreement should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an anaphor number agreement will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence where the subject and self-referencing nouns match plurality. An incorrect representation is a sentence in which the subject and self-referencing noun's plurality do not match.\\n\\nA hospital aggravates themselves.","target":"bad","rationale":"The subject of the sentence is \\"A hospital\\", which is singular. However, the reflexive pronoun \\"themselves\\" is plural and does not match with the plurality of the subject. A correct representation would be \\"A hospital aggravates itself\\", where the singular subject \\"hospital\\" matches with the singular reflexive pronoun. Therefore, This sentence is an incorrect representation of anaphor number agreement and should be denoted as 'bad'."},{"source":"Given a question and its paraphrases, answer the question. The answer should exactly answer all the questions given without any ambiguity. Don't give partial answers.\\n\\nQuestions: ['who is nicole anderson sister?']","target":"nadine anderson","rationale":"The sentence \\"who is nicole anderson sister?\\" can be paraphrased as: \\"what is the name of nicole's sister?\\". The answer for this question would be 'nadine anderson'."},{"source":"Write a multi-choice question for the following article, with the given choices and answer:\\nArticle: Rebecca, who is a 25-year-old woman, has a rare condition. She can remember all the events she has experienced in her life. The events are so vivid, as if they happened just moments ago. But her vivid memories often become a reality. Rebecca said, \\"When I relive memories, the emotions come back. So if it's something that happened when I was younger, my emotions are about what I felt then. I also re-experience pain. For example, I remember falling over and hurting my left knee when I was three. When talking about it now, I'm getting pain in my left knee.\\"\\nHowever, there are times when Rebecca's memories prove to be too overwhelming, and she has learnt relaxation and mindfulness  techniques to solve. \\"At school, it is a _ . I'm not very quick at processing things, so there is always so much going through my mind. At night, I have to sleep with the radio on and a soft light. If it's too dark or quiet, my mind just recalls all these memories and I can't sleep,\\" Rebecca said.\\nIn addition, Rebecca has no control over whether the memories she recalls will be positive or negative - recalling painful experiences with such vividness that she has suffered from post-traumatic   stress disorder. Rebecca said, \\"Recently, I went back to my old school for my sister's high school graduation. Being in that building again brought all those memories flooding back. I burst into tears and had to leave.\\"\\nRebecca and her mother Mrs. Barnes got in touch with the University of California in 2011. It was there that Rebecca knew she had Highly Superior Autobiographical Memory (HSAM). It's reported that Rebecca is one of just 80 people worldwide, who have HASM. \\"Finding out about HASM has been such a positive experience. Now, Rebecca has been more positive and able to do things independently, which has been excellent,\\" Mrs. Barnes said.\\nOptions:\\nA She hardly sleeps well at night.\\nB She usually gets hurt easily by others.\\nC She can't distinguish between reality and dreams.\\nD Her vivid memories lead her to experience sufferings.\\nAnswer:\\nD Her vivid memories lead her to experience sufferings.\\nQuestion:","target":"What's wrong with Rebecca?","rationale":"Rebecca has a rare condition called Highly Superior Autobiographical Memory (HSAM). With her vivid memories, Rebecca is able to remember all the events she has experienced in her life. However, this leads to sufferings for Rebecca as some of these memories are painful and overwhelm her - leading to post-traumatic stress disorder. The question \\"What's wrong with Rebecca?\\" can be used here because it asks about something that causes problem or difficulty for someone.\\nSo, the answer is D Her vivid memories lead her to experience sufferings"},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: What group's name was changed to the Jackson 5?, using the article: Michael Joseph Jackson was born in Gary, Indiana, near Chicago, on August 29, 1958. He was the eighth of ten children in the Jackson family, a working-class African-American family living in a two-bedroom house on Jackson Street. His mother, Katherine Esther Jackson (n√©e Scruse), played clarinet and piano, had aspired to be a country-and-western performer, and worked part-time at Sears. She was a Jehovah's Witness. His father, Joseph Walter \\"Joe\\" Jackson, a former boxer, was a crane operator at U.S. Steel and played guitar with a local rhythm and blues band, the Falcons, to supplement the family's income. His father's great-grandfather, July \\"Jack\\" Gale, was a Native American medicine man and US Army scout. Michael grew up with three sisters (Rebbie, La Toya, and Janet) and five brothers (Jackie, Tito, Jermaine, Marlon, and Randy). A sixth brother, Marlon's twin Brandon, died shortly after birth.Joe acknowledged that he regularly whipped Michael; Michael said his father told him he had a \\"fat nose\\", and regularly physically and emotionally abused him during rehearsals. He recalled that Joe often sat in a chair with a belt in his hand as he and his siblings rehearsed, ready to physically punish any mistakes. Katherine Jackson stated that although whipping is considered abuse in more modern times, it was a common way to discipline children when Michael was growing up. Jackie, Tito, Jermaine and Marlon have said that their father was not abusive and that the whippings, which were harder on Michael because he was younger, kept them disciplined and out of trouble. In an interview with Oprah Winfrey in 1993, Jackson said that his youth had been lonely and isolating.In 1964, Michael and Marlon joined the Jackson Brothers‚Äîa band formed by their father which included Jackie, Tito, and Jermaine‚Äîas backup musicians playing congas and tambourine. In 1965, Michael began sharing lead vocals with Jermaine, and the group's name was changed to the Jackson 5. The following year, the group won a talent show; Michael performed..., what would be the answer ?","target":"Jackson Brothers","rationale":"The question is what group's name was changed to the Jackson 5?\\nSo, I went through this text and thought about which of these options made sense in context. \\nI decided that \\"Jackson Brothers\\" fit best, because it precedes the mention of them as being known as The Jackson Five: Michael began sharing lead vocals with Jermaine, and the group‚Äôs name was changed to the Jackson 5."},{"source":"Bank of Scotland -- The Bank of Scotland was suspected of Jacobite sympathies. Its first rival, The Royal Bank of Scotland was formed by royal charter in 1727. This led to a period of great competition between the two banks as they set to drive each other out of business. Although the \`\`Bank Wars'' ended in around 1751, competition soon arose from other sources, as other Scottish banks were founded throughout the country. In response, the Bank of Scotland itself began to open branches throughout Scotland. The first branch in London opened in 1865.\\nBased on the previous passage, is bank of scotland same as royal bank of scotland?","target":"No","rationale":"The passage explains that the Bank of Scotland was a rival to The Royal Bank of Scotland. It goes on to say that they competed with each other until around 1751, after which both banks expanded their operations by opening branches throughout the country and internationally. This suggests that both banks are separate from one another, so it is untrue that \\"bank of scotland same as royal bank of scotland\\".\\nSo, the answer is No."},{"source":"Read the text and determine if the sentence is true:\\n\\nMs. Miers' whole life was based in Dallas and revolved around her legal work, her family and an attachment to an evangelical church that led her to what her former pastor described as a flowering of faith late in life.\\n\\nSentence: Ms. Miers was a leader of an evangelical church.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nA:","target":"no","rationale":"While Ms. Miers was attached to an evangelical church, the text does not mention her as being a leader of it. Hence, we can conclude that this statement is false and the answer should be \\"no\\"."},{"source":"In this task you are given a premise and two alternatives in Chinese. You must choose the alternative that is more plausibly the cause or effect of the situation described by the premise. The input format is \\"premise\\n(1)alternative_1(2)alternative_2\\", the output should either be \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" based on your judgment.\\n\\nÊàëÂÜ≥ÂÆöÂæÖÂú®ÂÆ∂ÈáåËøáÂ§ú„ÄÇ\\n(1)Â§©Ê∞îÈ¢ÑÊä•È¢ÑÊµã‰∫ÜÊö¥È£éÈõ®„ÄÇ(2)ÊàëÁöÑÊúãÂèãÊï¶‰øÉÊàëÂá∫Âéª„ÄÇ","target":"1","rationale":"ÊàëÂÜ≥ÂÆöÂæÖÂú®ÂÆ∂ÈáåËøáÂ§ú„ÄÇ(1)Â§©Ê∞îÈ¢ÑÊä•È¢ÑÊµã‰∫ÜÊö¥È£éÈõ®„ÄÇ(2)ÊàëÁöÑÊúãÂèãÊï¶‰øÉÊàëÂá∫Âéª„ÄÇ\\\\nThe premise is that I decided to stay home for the night. Weather forecast predicts a storm, which makes more sense than being urged by my friends to go out. Therefore the answer is 1."},{"source":"Rose had 10 kilograms of rice. She cooked 9/10 kilograms in the morning and 1/4 of the remaining in the evening. How many grams of rice did she have left?","target":"750","rationale":"Rose cooked 10 x 9 / 10 = 9 kilograms of rice in the morning. She had 10 - 9 = 1 kilogram of rice left then. One kilogram is equal to 1 x 1000 = 1000 grams. So, Rose cooked 1000 x 1 / 4 = 250 grams of rice in the evening. Therefore, she has 1000 - 250 = 750 grams of rice left."},{"source":"Which human organ system exchanges gases with the environment?\\n\\nOptions:\\n- endocrine\\n- circulatory\\n- respiratory\\n- integumentary","target":"respiratory","rationale":"The respiratory system is responsible for the exchange of gases between the body and its environment. The circulatory system transports blood to different parts of the body, but it does not perform gas exchanges with the environment.\\nTherefore, \\"respiratory\\" is a correct answer to this question."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nHugh Donald McCutcheon {'1': \\", '2': \\", '3': \\", '4': \\"} (born 13 October 1969), a native of Christchurch, New Zealand, is the former head coach of the US men's national volleyball team, the former head coach of the US women's national volleyball team, and the current head coach of the University of Minnesota's women's volleyball team.\\n\\nHypothesis: He was born prior to the current century\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"Yes, the context gives us evidence to support this hypothesis. It mentions that he was born in 13th October 1969 which would mean that his birth took place prior to the current century."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: Who proposed marriage? from the following article ?\\n\\nKate≈ôina's health gradually worsened and in the spring of 1859 failed completely. Homeward bound, she died at Dresden on 19 April 1859. Smetana wrote that she had died \\"gently, without our knowing anything until the quiet drew my attention to her.\\" After placing ≈Ωofie with Kate≈ôina's mother, Smetana spent time with Liszt in Weimar, where he was introduced to the music of the comic opera Der Barbier von Bagdad, by Liszt's pupil Peter Cornelius. This work would influence Smetana's own later career as an opera composer. Later that year he stayed with his younger brother Karel, and fell in love with Karel's sister-in-law Barbora (Bettina) Ferdinandiov√°, sixteen years his junior. He proposed marriage, and having secured her promise returned to Gothenburg for the 1859‚Äì60 winter. The marriage took place the following year, on 10 July 1860, after which Smetana and his new wife returned to Sweden for a final season. This culminated in April 1861 with a piano performance in Stockholm, attended by the Swedish royal family. The couple's first daughter, Zde≈àka, was born in September 1861.Meanwhile, the defeat of Franz Joseph's army at Solferino in 1859 had weakened the Habsburg Empire, and led to the fall from power of von Bach. This had gradually brought a more enlightened atmosphere to Prague, and by 1861 Smetana was seeing prospects of a better future for Czech nationalism and culture. Before deciding his own future, in September Smetana set out on a concert tour of the Netherlands and Germany. He was still hoping to secure a reputation as a pianist, but once again he experienced failure. Back in Prague, he conducted performances of Richard III and Wallenstein's Camp in the ≈Ωof√≠n Island concert hall in January 1862, to a muted reception. Critics accused him of adhering too closely to the \\"New German\\" school represented primarily by Liszt; Smetana responded that \\"a prophet is without honour in his own land.\\" In March 1862 he made a last brief visit to Gothenburg, but the city no longer held his interest; it appeared to...","target":"Smetana","rationale":"The answer is Smetana. The article was about the life of Bed≈ôich Smetana and his family from 1859 to 1865, which included a number of significant events in his personal life as well as some musical accomplishments. In particular, he proposed marriage to Barbora Ferdinandiov√° (Bettina), who became his second wife on July 10th 1860; they subsequently had two daughters together: Zde≈àka (born September 1861) and ≈Ωofie (born December 1863).\\n\\nIn conclusion, because more information was provided regarding Bettina than Kate≈ôina or ≈Ωofie it can be inferred that the author might have been focusing specifically on Bettina's role in Smetana's life when writing this section of text since she accepted"},{"source":"Q: Whose consent do the states need to make international treaties?\\n A: According to the German constitution (called Grundgesetz or in English Basic Law), some topics, such as foreign affairs and defense, are the exclusive responsibility of the federation (i.e., the federal level), while others fall under the shared authority of the states and the federation; the states retain residual legislative authority for all other areas, including \\"culture\\", which in Germany includes not only topics such as financial promotion of arts and sciences, but also most forms of education and job training.\\n Does the answer correctly answer the question\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"While the passage does indeed describe certain aspects of German law, it does not address the question \\"Whose consent do states need to make international treaties?\\""},{"source":"You will be given a trivia clue, and the category it belongs to. You should answer with the best answer that belongs in the category and is described by the clue. For simplicity, answers should be in all lower cased letters.\\n\\nCategory: KEYBOARD NEIGHBORS \\nClue: In Spanish it's nosotros","target":"we","rationale":"The Spanish word for we is nosotros. The question asks for the English equivalent and the answer would be 'we'"},{"source":"In this task, you are given two phrases: Head and Tail, separated with <sep>. The Head and the Tail events are short phrases possibly involving participants. The names of specific people have been replaced by generic words (e.g., PersonX, PersonY, PersonZ). PersonX is always the subject of the event. You have to determine whether, as a result of the Head, PersonX will be affected as mentioned in the Tail or not. These effects are social actions that may occur after the Head event. Classify your answers into \\"Yes\\" and \\"No\\". The phrase may also contain \\"___\\", a placeholder that can be an object, a person, and/or an action.\\n\\nHead: PersonX answers PersonY's question<sep>Tail: smart","target":"No","rationale":"Answering a question does not necessarily affect one's smartness. Therefore, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Given two sentences regarding the stereotypes of religions, determine whether the second sentence is either a stereotype, anti-stereotype, or is unrelated with respect to the first sentence and the target. A stereotype is a widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against the widely held but oversimplified notion of a group of people. Sentences and targets are unrelated if there is no relevance between them.\\n\\nTarget: Brahmin \\nBrahmin handbags are typically made out of leather. A lot of famous people carry around these handbags.","target":"stereotype","rationale":"The second sentence seems to be a stereotype of Brahmin handbags, as it asserts that famous people carry around these handbags."},{"source":"See the multi-choice question below:\\n\\nSentence 1: made sense---and would make dollars for the Postal Service.\\n\\nSentence 2: The Postal Service uses more than one revenue stream.\\n\\nIf the first sentence is true, then is the second sentence true?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The first sentence talks about the Postal Service using multiple revenue streams and makes sense because it would make dollars for them. Therefore, if this is true, then so should be the second sentence as well. So, the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: what is the capital of oregon?","target":"Salem","rationale":"Salem is the capital city of Oregon, United States."},{"source":"If That's a bargain, said Japp heartily. , can we conclude that \\"That's too expensive, said Japp.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"In the first sentence, Japp is saying that something is a bargain. Therefore, we cannot conclude that this same thing was too expensive in the second statement."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and your task is to classify the given sentence into the following categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\n\\nSurveillance of livestock and the surrounding environment is a hallmark of early detection but is currently targeted to known risks.","target":"background","rationale":"The sentence describes the role of surveillance in early detection, which is one aspect to consider when addressing a specific problem. Therefore, it provides background information that helps to highlight the importance and significance of this study.\\""},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nLogan entered the patio. James entered the patio. The turnip is in the red_suitcase. James exited the patio. Logan moved the turnip to the red_envelope. Logan exited the patio. James entered the patio. Logan entered the playroom. Elizabeth entered the playroom. The grapefruit is in the green_basket. Elizabeth exited the playroom. Logan moved the grapefruit to the red_bucket. Logan exited the playroom. Elizabeth entered the playroom. Logan entered the playroom. James entered the playroom. The grapefruit is in the red_bucket. James exited the playroom. Logan moved the grapefruit to the green_basket. Logan exited the playroom. James entered the playroom. Charlotte entered the TV_room. Logan entered the TV_room. The onion is in the blue_crate. Logan exited the TV_room. Phone rang. Charlotte moved the onion to the green_crate. Charlotte exited the TV_room. Logan entered the TV_room. Where will Logan look for the onion?","target":"green_crate","rationale":"Logan believes the onion is in the blue_crate. However, while Logan was not present, Charlotte moved the onion to green_crate. So Logan's belief does not match reality and he will look for it in green_crate."},{"source":"Maria Ho (born March 6, 1983 in Taipei, Taiwan) is a Taiwanese American poker player, television personality and host. She is known as one of the top ranked female poker players in the world; a 3-time Bluff Reader's Choice Awards nominee for Favorite Female Poker Player and a World Series of Poker record-breaker, and for competing on the 15th season of \\"The Amazing Race\\".\\nCan we infer the following?\\nMario Ho became one of the top ranked female poker players in the world by becoming a World Series of Poker record-breaker.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nThe answer is:","target":"Yes","rationale":"The passage states that \\"Maria Ho is known as one of the top ranked female poker players in the world\\"[1] and also mentions that she was a World Series of Poker record-breaker[2]. So, we can infer from this text that Maria Ho became one of the top rankers by being a World Series of Poker Record breaker. Hence, answer is Yes"},{"source":"I want to test the ability of students to read a passage and answer questions about it. Could you please come up with a good question for the passage \\"The storage in sensory memory and short-term memory generally has a strictly limited capacity and duration, which means that information is not retained indefinitely. By contrast, long-term memory can store much larger quantities of information for potentially unlimited duration (sometimes a whole life span). Its capacity is immeasurable. For example, given a random seven-digit number we may remember it for only a few seconds before forgetting, suggesting it was stored in our short-term memory. On the other hand, we can remember telephone numbers for many years through repetition; this information is said to be stored in long-term memory.\\"?","target":"Random information could be gone from our brain how quickly?","rationale":"The passage introduces the concept of different types of memory. It describes how sensory and short-term memories have a limited capacity, while long term memory can store much more information for an unlimited duration. The question 'Random information could be gone from our brain how quickly?' is relevant to the context because it asks about one aspect of short-term memory in particular: its ability to hold random numbers. Since this type of memory has a very low capacity, most people would not remember a random seven digit number after only seconds (A) or minutes (B). However, they would likely be able to recall these digits within hours or even days if necessary (C), since there is no limit on the amount that you can retain as long as enough time passes before testing your knowledge again."},{"source":"Does the sentence \\"The ceremony in Westminster Abbey, with the exception of the anointing and communion, was televised for the first time.[d] Elizabeth's coronation gown was embroidered on her instructions with the floral emblems of Commonwealth countries: English Tudor rose; Scots thistle; Welsh leek; Irish shamrock; Australian wattle; Canadian maple leaf; New Zealand silver fern; South African protea; lotus flowers for India and Ceylon; and Pakistan's wheat, cotton, and jute.\\" answer the question \\"How was much of the ceremony of Elizabeth's coronation presented to the public?\\"\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The passage states that the coronation ceremony was televised with few exceptions. Hence, it answers the question by stating \\"yes\\", i.e much of the ceremony was presented to public through television"},{"source":"Fairport Convention are a British folk rock band. Formed in 1967, they are widely regarded as a key group in the English folk rock movement. Their seminal album Liege & Lief is considered to have launched the British folk rock movement, which provided a distinctively English identity to rock music and helped awaken much wider interest in traditional music in general. The band have drawn heavily on the Child Ballads, songs of the British Isles from the later medieval period until the 19th century.\\n\\nIn 1998, Dave Mattacks moved to the USA and Gerry Conway took over on drums and percussion. Fairport produced two more studio albums for Woodworm Records: The Wood and the Wire (2000) and XXXV (2002). Then for Over the Next Hill (2004) they established a new label: Matty Grooves Records. In this period the band toured extensively in the UK, Europe, Australasia, Europe, the USA and Canada, and staged a major fund raiser for Dave Swarbrick at the Birmingham Symphony Hall. In 1998, members of the band began their association with the Breton musician Alan Simon. Working in collaboration with numerous others, members of Fairport (predominantly Nicol and Leslie) have performed in and participated in the recordings of all Simon's rock operas, including the Excalibur trilogy (1998, 2007, 2010) and Anne de Bretagne (2008).  2007 was their fortieth anniversary year and they celebrated by releasing a new album, Sense of Occasion. They performed the whole of the Liege & Lief album live at Cropredy, since 2004 renamed Fairport's Cropredy Convention, featuring the 1969 line-up of Dave Swarbrick, Ashley Hutchings, Dave Mattacks, Simon Nicol and Richard Thompson, with singer-songwriter Chris While taking the place of Sandy Denny. Footage of the festival, although not the Liege and Lief performance, was released as part of a celebratory DVD.  The band's first official YouTube video appeared in April 2008. Edited from footage shot for the DVD, the nine-minute mini-documentary includes interviews with Lulu, Jools Holland, Seth Lakeman, Mike Harding, Geoff Hughes and Frank Skinner.  In 2011, the band released a new studio album Festival Bell, the first new album in four years. This was followed in 2012 by Babbacombe Lee Live Again recorded live during the 2011 tour revisiting the Babbacombe Lee album first issued in 1971. In 2012, the band also released By Popular Request, a reworking in the studio of a number of the most popular songs in the band's repertoire (as determined by a mysterious consultation and voting process conducted by the band with its fans).  In January 2015, four years after their previous studio album of original material (Festival Bell), Fairport Convention released a new one entitled Myths and Heroes.\\n\\nUsing a quote from the above article, answer the following question: What was Fairport Convention doing during 1998","target":"Fairport produced two more studio albums for Woodworm Records:","rationale":"The article mentions that in the period 1998-2012, Fairport Convention produced a number of new albums. In particular, it states:\\n\\"\\"Fairport produced two more studio albums for Woodworm Records: The Wood and the Wire (2000) and XXXV (2002). Then for Over the Next Hill (2004) they established a new label: Matty Grooves Records.\\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, the input is a set of dialogues between a user and an assistant. You need to find the dialogue that is basically a response given to a question or an aspect of the user.\\n\\nWhat is their main source of revenue? \\n Yes, please! I'd love to learn about their economy! \\n Hi! Can you tell me some interesting facts about Argentina? \\n Yes, definitely a great market to be in. Argentina is the second-largest country in South America. In East Argentina, you will find the capital of Buenos Aires. Buenos Aires is one of the largest cities in the world. \\n Hello. I can do that. Does the economy interest you?","target":"Yes, definitely a great market to be in. Argentina is the second-largest country in South America. In East Argentina, you will find the capital of Buenos Aires. Buenos Aires is one of the largest cities in the world","rationale":"The user is asking about Argentina, which is the second-largest country in South America, and the capital of Buenos Aires. Therefore, \\"Yes, definitely a great market to be in. Argentina is the second-largest country in South America. In East Argentina, you will find the capital of Buenos Aires. Buenos Aires is one of the largest cities in the world\\" would be an appropriate response to that question by providing more information on their economy.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that end with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'a little boy is wearing a yellow paper tie'. How many words end with the letter 'e' in the sentence.","target":"2","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a little boy is wearing a yellow paper tie', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' does not end with letter e.\\\\n2. 'little' ends with letter e -> (total) 1\\\\n3. 'boy' does not end with letter e.\\\\n4. 'is' does not end with letter e.\\\\n5. 'wearing' ends with letter e -> (total) 2\\\\n6 and onwards do not have any words that end in the given character, so the final total is still 2"},{"source":"Write the response. DIALOG:\\nWho was Ara Parseghian playing for in the 1964 season?\\n- Ara Parseghian's success attracted the interest of Notre Dame. He was hired as coach in 1964.\\n- Did Ara Parseghian help Notre Dame University  turn the football team around as coach?\\n- Ara Parseghian is noted for bringing Notre Dame's Fighting Irish football program from years of futility back into a national contender.\\n- Did the University of Notre Dame go on to lose lots of games in the 1964 season with Ara Parseghian as coach ?\\n- The team went undefeated until the last game of the year against USC.\\n- What happened in the University of notre dame game against USC?\\n- USC won 20‚Äì17 in the final minutes on a touchdown pass from Craig Fertig to Rod Sherman.\\n- Who was playing on the USC team during that 1964 season besides Craig Fertig and Rod Sherman?\\n-","target":"Mike Garrett led the team in rushing.","rationale":"This is a summary of the information given in the conversation. Mike Garrett led the team in rushing.\\""},{"source":"Please read the following news article and write another sentence to add to it.\\n\\nBare facts: Naked rambler Stephen Gough has lost his appeal at the European Court of Human Rights At last, the Naked Rambler has reached the end of the road. After almost a decade in and out of prison, Britain‚Äôs most surprising inmate ‚Äî real name Stephen Gough ‚Äî has lost his chance of freedom at the European Court Of Human Rights in Strasbourg. He must now keep serving his two-and-a-half-year sentence in Winchester Prison for breaching an indefinite Asbo against being naked in public. The former Royal Marine from Eastleigh, Hampshire, had claimed the right to remain naked under Articles Eight and Ten of the European Convention On Human Rights: the right to freedom of expression and the right to a private life.\\n\\n- \\nStephen Gough just lost his last chance at freedom at human rights court\\n\\n- \\nHe is serving 2.5-year sentence for breaching Asbo against being naked\\n\\n- \\nThe persistent naturist has walked the country without clothes on","target":"He is currently among 85,720 people behind bars in Britain.","rationale":"In the last sentence of this piece, we find out that Stephen Gough is currently serving his prison term in Winchester Prison. In order to emphasize how much time he has spent behind bars and how unlikely it seems for him to be released soon, I think you could add another sentence:\\nHe is currently among 85,720 people behind bars in Britain."},{"source":"Given a post that is a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation and an associated claim about its type, verify if the claim is true or not. The claim asks if the posts are historical or hypothetical. The posts are \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and they are \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future. Say 'yes' if the claim is true otherwise say 'no'\\n\\nCLAIM : The following post is HISTORICAL. POST : I am a white female that attends a large public state university in the US.  I‚Äôd like to clarify that i am 100% NOT racist. I do believe in equal rights and treating people fairly. That being said, i have a very broad humor and will laugh and enjoy almost any joke. But that does not make me racist. \\n\\nIts starting to get colder outside so the university has cranked up the heat (thankfully) but, because of this- many of the buildings smell rather badly. \\n\\nI get to class early one day and sit in my usual seat and my other (white) friend comes in and sits down next to me. \\n\\nI say hey and we make some small talk and we talk about how the buildings all smell really bad \\n\\nHe says \\n‚ÄúYeah it legit smells like currie in the [dorm]‚Äù \\nAnd i go \\n‚ÄúDamn... haha really? That bad? Must be those indian international students.. never heard of deoderant‚Äù \\n\\nWe both smile and move on with our conversation. And then this Asian chick turns around and asks us if we dont think we‚Äôre being insensitive to the majority of the students in the class who are infact indian. \\n\\nThis kindof raises our eyebrows and confuses us. I go on and tell her ‚Äúno.. because im not racist. We dont actually believe what we say‚Äî its just a stereotype. Its only offensive if you get offended‚Äù \\n\\nShe told EVERYONE in our discussion group how ‚Äúracist‚Äù we are and how she hates ‚Äúprivileged white people making racist jokes‚Äù blablabla. Terrible things are funny because theyre not funny. \\n\\nAnd its not like we were talking to HER. She was listening in on our conversation and interjected it. \\n\\nI dont regret the joke because i am not ashamed of my humor. Its dark humor, and an acquired taste. \\n\\nAITA?","target":"yes","rationale":"The author mentions that they are considering saying something to another student in class, so this is a hypothetical situation. The author further states that they have not yet said anything, so it appears that the events described in the post have not occurred yet. Based on the above analysis, it seems that the post is hypothetical and therefore, the answer would be \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: Which location in California where the LST-1159 stopped at has a higher land elevation? Passage:Initially attached to Amphibious Forces, Atlantic Fleet, LST-1159 conducted shakedown in Guant√°namo Bay and the Caribbean before commencing local operations out of Norfolk and Little Creek, Virginia. She departed Norfolk on 24 February 1954 for duty with Amphibious Forces, Pacific Fleet, and, after a transit of the Panama Canal, reached the west coast on 20 March. The tank landing ship operated out of her new home port, San Diego, until 20 September, including calls at San Francisco, San Pedro, California, and Esquimalt, British Columbia. LST-1159 stopped briefly at Pearl Harbor before proceeding on toward Japan. While on the voyage across the Pacific, the ship was diverted to join Task Force (TF) 98 in Southeast Asian waters and arrived at Henriette Pass, near the port of Haiphong, French Indochina on 29 October. Taking part in \\"Operation Passage to Freedom\\", LST-1159 transported refugees from the northern part of what became a divided Vietnam, to the southern ports of Tourane (Da Nang) and Saigon.","target":"a","rationale":"The passage mentions that LST-1159 stopped at San Diego and Esquimalt, British Columbia, two locations in California. The land elevation of these two cities can be searched for to answer the question."},{"source":"Given a text passage as input comprising of dialogue of negotiations between a seller and a buyer about the sale of an item, your task is to classify the item being sold into exactly one of these categories: 'housing', 'furniture', 'bike', 'phone', 'car', 'electronics'. The output should be the name of the category from the stated options and there should be exactly one category for the given text passage.\\n\\nBuyer: Hi there! I am interested in your bike! Can you tell me a little more about it?\\nSeller: Hello. The bike is in an immaculate condition, drives less than 100 miles. Its frame is carbon fiber and its not a boost model. Its a great thing for summer\\nBuyer: awe man that sounds great! The thing is i dont have the amount your asking. would you go any lower?\\nSeller: Yes I am ready to negotiate. How much are you willing to pay? \\nBuyer: All i have is $3800. Would you be willing to sell at that price? I really would appreciate it! \\nSeller: I could accept $3900 because its in a very mint condition and its something worth it\\nBuyer: How about $3850? Meet me in the middle?\\nSeller: Okay I will take that. But I do only cash or cashier's check only?\\nBuyer: Cash it is! \\nBuyer: \\nSeller:","target":"bike","rationale":"The text is clearly a dialogue of negotiations between a seller and a buyer about the sale of bike. Therefore, the output is bike.\\""},{"source":"The covered wagon was long the dominant form of transport in pre-industrial America, it heavily relied upon along such travel routes as the Great Wagon Road, an improved trail through which location, from Pennsylvania to North Carolina, and from there to Georgia in colonial America?","target":"Great Appalachian Valley","rationale":"The Great Wagon Road was an improved trail through the Great Appalachian Valley from Pennsylvania to North Carolina, and from there to Georgia in colonial America."},{"source":"Canada, the United States and Mexico host communities of both Jews (6 million or about 1.8%), Buddhists (3.8 million or 1.1%) and Muslims (3.4 million or 1.0%). The biggest number of Jewish individuals can be found in the United States (5.4 million), Canada (375,000) and Mexico (67,476). The United States host the largest Muslim population in North America with 2.7 million or 0.9%, While Canada host about one million Muslim or 3.2% of the population. While in Mexico there were 3,700 Muslims in the country. In 2012, U-T San Diego estimated U.S. practitioners of Buddhism at 1.2 million people, of whom 40% are living in Southern California.\\n\\nBased on the above article, answer a question. Are there more Muslim individuals in the United States or Mexico?","target":"the United States","rationale":"The U.S. host about 2.7 million Muslim individuals, while Mexico only has 3,700 Muslims in the country; therefore there are more Muslim individuals in the United States than in Mexico."},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Which has the greatest effect on the color of a young eagle's eyes?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: parents\\n \\n- B: nest\\n \\n- C: diet\\n \\n- D: behavior","target":"A","rationale":"Here's my rationale for the answer:\\nBefore you hit adulthood, your eye color is determined by genetics. Your parents' genes determine what colors will show up in your iris and how much of that pigment shows through. As a child grows older, exposure to sunlight can change his or her eyesight permanently."},{"source":"Would a linguist find the following sentence to be a valid English sentence grammatically?\\n\\nIt might have cracked open\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence has the subject-verb-object structure. The grammatical subject is \\"It,\\" and it is followed by a verb phrase, which in turn consists of two verbs: \\"might have cracked\\" and \\"open.\\" Therefore, this sentence would be considered linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: sexual-explicit and non-sexual-explicit. A comment is considered sexual-explicit if it explicitly portrays sexual matters.\\n\\nComment: TDM, you sir know a thing or two about being an apologist and doing dirt work, don't you. \\n\\nThat's what most of your posts are, just for \\"the other side\\".","target":"Non-sexual-explicit","rationale":"The comment does not contain any explicit portrayal of sexual matters. So it could be classified as \\"Non-sexual-explicit\\"."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is \\"The table is too narrow.\\" true if \\"The table won't fit through the doorway because it is too narrow.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The table is too narrow to fit through the doorway. The correct answer would be \\"the table is too wide\\". So, the answer for this question should be \\"no\\"\\n\\"\\""},{"source":"Article: Chopin also endowed popular dance forms with a greater range of melody and expression. Chopin's mazurkas, while originating in the traditional Polish dance (the mazurek), differed from the traditional variety in that they were written for the concert hall rather than the dance hall; \\"it was Chopin who put the mazurka on the European musical map.\\" The series of seven polonaises published in his lifetime (another nine were published posthumously), beginning with the Op. 26 pair (published 1836), set a new standard for music in the form. His waltzes were also written specifically for the salon recital rather than the ballroom and are frequently at rather faster tempos than their dance-floor equivalents.\\n\\nNow answer this question: What dance music of Chopin was written more for recitals than ballrooms?","target":"waltzes","rationale":"The context provides information about Chopin's dance music, saying that his waltzes were written more for recitals than ballrooms. Therefore, the answer is: \\"Waltzes\\"."},{"source":"Here's a question: What do you give people when they meet people?\\n\\nHere are possible answers to this question:\\n- introduce yourself\\n- greeting\\n- look over\\n- friendly\\n- high five\\n\\nI believe the correct choice is \\"greeting\\", here's why:","target":"greeting people when they meet people","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"greeting people when they meet people\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an abstract of article. Your task is to generate label \\"True\\" if abstract is structured, otherwise generate \\"False\\". A structured abstract is composed of a topic sentence (or key sentence), relevant supporting sentences, and a closing (or transition) sentence. This structure is key to keeping your abstract focused on the main idea and creating a clear and concise image.\\n\\nMemory complaints have not correlated well with tests of memory. However, given self-report questions, which tap processes of everyday remembering. sixty volunteers aged 21-84 years adequately rated their memory competence. Categorized into four memory processes, self-report and six tests of verbal, faces, story and nonverbal auditory, visual, and tactual memory ,were canonically correlated (r = 0.67) and both sets of measures declined with age in parallel. Thc old were more accurate than the young in their ratings but by no means on all tests and expectation to perform poorly seemed to have influenced some performances.","target":"False","rationale":"The abstract includes a topic sentence that states the main findings of the study (\\"Memory complaints have not correlated well with tests of memory. However, given self-report questions, which tap processes of everyday remembering.\\"). It also provides details about the research methods and results. However, it does not include a closing (or transition) sentence that summarizes the main findings and conclusions. Therefore, it is not structured. So the answer is \\"False\\"."},{"source":"Hill town was full of gasoline powered vehicles, while Valley town 50 miles away, banned all gas powered vehicles and allows only electrical vehicles or horse-and-buggies.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich town had fewer volatile hydrocarbons in the atmosphere?\\n\\nHint: Gasoline-powered vehicles emit a lot of harmful materials. Nitrogen oxides are formed when atmospheric nitrogen reacts with oxygen at the high temperatures found in a car engine. Carbon monoxide is a by-product of incomplete combustion of hydrocarbons. Evaporated and unused fuel releases volatile hydrocarbons into the atmosphere to help form smog. The presence of a catalytic converter in the exhaust system of the car causes these materials to react and be changed into less harmful products.","target":"Valley","rationale":"The main idea of the paragraph is about two towns - Hill Town and Valley town, which have different rules for vehicles. From this information it can be inferred that in these towns there are mostly use-cases related to those vehicles. This can be further validated by noticing words like \\"gasoline powered\\" and \\"horse-and-buggies\\". It also mentions a few harmful materials emitted from gasoline vehicles (e.g., nitrogen oxides).\\n\\nIn conclusion, since only gas powered vehicles were banned in Valley town while all other types remained permitted, therefore fewer volatile hydrocarbons would get into the atmosphere compared to Hill town where no such ban was imposed on any type of vehicle but rather they had freedom over all kinds of transportations including horse carriages or electric cars as well as"},{"source":"In this task, you are given two simple actions (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\"). You must identify which action is considered less ethical. Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B'.\\n\\n(A) not going to work on my day off\\n(B) getting pissed at my friend for not inviting me to a party","target":"B","rationale":"For action A, choosing not to go to work on one's day off is a personal choice that does not affect anyone else. The action can be considered lazy, but it is not unethical.\\\\nFor action B, getting mad at a friend for not inviting you to a party that they were already planning and had already invited other people to shows an unhealthy expectation of the friend's behavior. The author has no right to expect their friend to invite them along when they have made plans with other people and cannot be expected to include everyone in every activity or event they may attend with different groups of friends."},{"source":"Decide the language of that sentence. The language can be English, French, German, Italian, or Spanish.\\n\\nText: 'in an a clockwise direction and but don't go right round it go'","target":"English","rationale":"The text is in English. It has words like \\"clockwise\\", \\"direction\\", and \\"don't\\" that are typically used in English language sentences. Hence, the answer is 'English'."},{"source":"Read the following context and answer the question.\\nContext: SEOUL ‚Äî North Korea‚Äôs recent threat to pull out of the upcoming nuclear summit with the U.S. has added new urgency to South Korean President Moon Jae-in‚Äôs visit to Washington next Tuesday.\\nPresident Moon has played a key role in facilitating the meeting between North Korean leader Kim Jong Un and U.S. President Donald Trump scheduled to be held in Singapore June 12.\\nAt the recent inter-Korean summit Moon got Kim to affirm a broad commitment to rid the Korean Peninsula of nuclear weapons and that opened the door for Trump and Kim to negotiate a more detailed agreement to end North Korea‚Äôs nuclear program.\\nHowever, uncompromising positions recently voiced by U.S. National Security Adviser John Bolton demanding the North‚Äôs unilateral disarmament, and by North Korea in response canceling further talks with the South and threatening to pull out of the U.S.-North Korea summit, have put the prospects for continued diplomatic progress in jeopardy.\\nPresident Trump has tried to reassure the North Korean leadership that a nuclear deal would not weaken the Kim government, but would bolster it.\\n‚ÄúHe'd be in his country, he'd be running his country. His country would be very rich.‚Äù Trump said Thursday while meeting with NATO Secretary General Jens Stoltenberg in the White House.\\nPresident Moon, who will meet with Trump in Washington on Tuesday, has said he will try to moderate differences between the U.S. and North Korea over how to achieve denuclearization, while also giving the Kim government the security guarantees and sanctions relief it wants.\\nBut the convergence of interests that have brought Moon, Trump and Kim to all agree to give diplomacy a chance seems to be diverging over how to bridge the gap between the U.S. demand for complete denuclearization prior to offering any concessions, and the North‚Äôs insistence on a step by step process that would ease sanctions early on for incremental measures, such as giving up some nuclear material and allowing in outside inspectors.\\nQuestion: Where will Trump meet with Kim Jung Un?\\nAnswer:","target":"Singapore","rationale":"The context says that the North Korea‚Äôs recent threat to pull out of the upcoming nuclear summit with the U.S. has added new urgency to South Korean President Moon Jae-in‚Äôs visit to Washington next Tuesday, and it also states Trump will meet Kim Jung Un on June 12 in Singapore and this information is enough for making an inference about where they are going to meet because there is no other option given here as a place so far from them (US, NKorea or SKorea)."},{"source":"You are given a time in 24-Hours format, and you need to convert it to time in the 12-Hours format. For a 24-Hours format time larger than 12:00, subtract 12 hours from the given time, then add 'PM'.  For example, if you have 14:30 hours, subtract 12 hours, and the result is 2:30 PM. If the 24-Hours format time is less than or equal to 12:00, add 'AM'. For example, say you have 10:15 hours, add the 'AM' to the end, here we get 10:15 AM. Note that 00:00 Hrs in 24-Hours format is 12:00 AM in 12-Hours format and 12:00 Hrs in 24-Hours format would be 12:00 PM in 12-Hours format.\\n\\n12:03 Hrs","target":"12:03 PM","rationale":"The given time is 12:03 Hrs in the 24-Hours format. Since it is equal to 12:00, we need to add 'PM' to convert it to the 12-Hours format. So, the time in the 12-Hours format is 12:03 PM."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nWhen it becomes more humid outside people are more likely or less likely to sweat? \\n\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nAs humidity increases, the water potential gradient across the inside and outside the leaf become more equal, and so the rate of transpiration decreases.","target":"more likely","rationale":"The context suggests that as humidity increases, the water potential gradient across the inside and outside of a leaf becomes more equal. This means that there is less difference in moisture between these two areas. \\nSince sweat is a way to cool down by getting rid of excess heat through evaporation, it makes sense that people would be \\"more likely\\" to sweat when it's humid out because they will experience higher temperatures due to their bodies retaining more heat from ambient conditions than usual."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: find the area of a parallelogram with base 12 cm and height 8 cm ? \\nOptions: a ) 96 cm 2 , b ) 104 cm 2 , c ) 78 cm 2 , d ) 86 cm 2 , e ) 76 cm 2","target":"a","rationale":"The given parallelogram has a base of 12 cm and a height of 8 cm. The formula to find the area of a parallelogram is base x height, so the answer is 12 x 8 = 96 cm^2."},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\nSo, I have social anxiety, as you may have inferred from the title. It can get pretty bad sometimes. Recently, I joined a partial hospitalization program (PHP) for my depression, suicidal thoughts, self esteem issues, and anxiety.\\n\\nIt's been a rough start. I constantly feel like everyone hates me and no one wants to see my ugly face, so I don't talk a lot of the time. I think that people won't like me because I'm gross and overweight. When people do approach me, I can't seem to hold the conversation. I'm awful at keeping up a chat because I usually give one-word answers, and that's because I'm either not interested in the topic or am deathly afraid of saying the wrong thing. I have a huge fear of screwing up when saying or doing something around others.\\n\\nAll of this makes me quiet, reserved, and atrocious at talking, thus making me not appealing to everyone else in the program. I see people giving me weird looks sometimes when I sit in the academics room while everyone else socializes. And by everyone else, I mean literally everyone else. They all know each other well, but I just can't make the effort to try and talk to them because I hate butting into conversations. That's because I'm terrified of people thinking that I'm annoying.\\n\\nBasically, I'm not social. I don't talk, I don't participate in discussions, and I definitely don't approach people on my own to try and make friends. It's all due to my overwhelming fear of others disliking me. And I know that people think lowly of me because I overheard two girls whispering about how 'weird' I was. That really got to me, and it still gets to me. But, since I'm too scared to try and change my image, I'm stuck being the weird quiet kid. I honestly feel like a coward, and like I'm putting others down and annoying them by not making any efforts to socialize.\\n\\nAm I the asshole?","target":"HISTORICAL","rationale":"The author describes a past event in which they were part of a program that helped treat their depression and anxiety. They describe feeling nervous and anxious around others and being afraid to say the wrong thing. However, they do not explicitly state when the events occurred. In addition, they mention that one of the ways in which their anxiety manifests is by holding back from approaching people in order to make friends, even though it bothers them that others think lowly of them because they are quiet. This suggests that the events occurred in the past. The author states that since they are too scared to change how others perceive them, they are stuck as \\"\\"the weird quiet kid.\\"\\" Based on this information, it seems likely that at least some time has passed between when these events occurred and now because people have had time to form an impression about who this person is based on their behavior (that is, being quiet). On balance, it seems most likely that this post describes something from the author's past rather than something hypothetical or hypothetical but unlikely to occur; therefore \\"\\"HISTORICAL\\"\\" is chosen as label for this anecdote.\\""},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should find the maximum absolute difference between 2 integers in the list. The absolute difference is the absolute value of one integer subtracted by another. The output should be a single integer which is the largest possible absolute distance.\\n\\n[80, 79, 23, -44, 20, 44, -92, -49, -74]","target":"172","rationale":"The maximum absolute difference between 2 integers in the list is (-92) - (80) = 12. The other possible combinations are:\\\\n1. -74, 80\\\\n2. -74, 79\\\\n3. -74, 23\\\\n4. -49, 80\\\\n5. etc...\\n\\nIn all cases above the absolute value is less than or equal to 12 which means that the largest possible absolute distance between 2 numbers in this list is 172 (= 92 + 80)."},{"source":"Here is a question about this article: In 1853, Victoria gave birth to her eighth child, Leopold, with the aid of the new anaesthetic, chloroform. Victoria was so impressed by the relief it gave from the pain of childbirth that she used it again in 1857 at the birth of her ninth and final child, Beatrice, despite opposition from members of the clergy, who considered it against biblical teaching, and members of the medical profession, who thought it dangerous. Victoria may have suffered from post-natal depression after many of her pregnancies. Letters from Albert to Victoria intermittently complain of her loss of self-control. For example, about a month after Leopold's birth Albert complained in a letter to Victoria about her \\"continuance of hysterics\\" over a \\"miserable trifle\\".\\nWhat is the answer to this question: When was Victoria's final child, Beatrice, born?","target":"1857","rationale":"The context states that Victoria's final child, Beatrice was born in 1857."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the best option to answer the question.\\nContext: My husband I have Kindles and ca n't imagine life without them . Imagine having 200 books in a binder the size of a small trade paperback . With close to 150,000 books , newspapers , and magazines available now for download and more being added every day the Kindle is perfect ! You can download books from your computer via USB or in Sprint EVDO service areas your books are delivered wirelessly for free .\\nQuestion: What may be the reason for this advertisement of the Kindle ?\\nOptions: \\nA. They want to make as much money as possible .\\nB. They want others to stop reading physical books .\\nC. They want others to switch to the Amazon Kindle .\\nD. None of the above choices .","target":"C","rationale":"The context mentions the benefits of using an Amazon Kindle and praises it. The question asks why this advertisement was made, implying that there are other reasons aside from promoting a product. However, based on the given information in the passage, we can infer that since all aspects of the ad praise Amazon Kindles over physical books by highlighting their advantages as e-readers (small size/portability + larger book selection), then C must be correct because its purpose is to convince people to switch to reading with Kindles instead of regular books.\\nA does not apply here because no mention about money appears in either text or audio form; B also does not apply for similar reasons - nowhere within both texts do they say anything which implies one should stop reading real books altogether! D may seem like a good"},{"source":"Summary:\\n\\n- \\nNicolas Cage voices character of Speckles the mole in \\"G-Force\\"\\n\\n- \\nDisney's \\"G-Force\\" opens in U.S. theaters on Friday, July 24\\n\\n- \\n\\"I like movies where you feel like you're going into another world,\\" Cage says \\n\\nArticle:\\n\\nNEW YORK (CNN) -- Academy Award winner Nicolas Cage has pretty much got this acting thing down. After all, he started acting at the age of 15 and, well, he's got that Oscar. Nicolas Cage says that Academy Awards are \\"not as important as children and making them happy.\\" So he doesn't really need to deliver another gut-wrenching performance to demonstrate his chops. In fact, he can deviate from a traditional film and venture into animated territory. He's voiced animated characters in the past, but in Disney's new 3-D tale \\"G-Force,\\" Cage lends his voice to a mole. Speckles the star-nosed mole comes to life thanks to the film's impressive digital animation and Cage's voice. At first it's unclear that Cage is the voice behind Speckles, because he changes his sound for the critter, er, character.","target":"Disney has a great tradition of enchanting children and giving them something to behold.","rationale":"Cage mentions that he loves movies where you feel like \\"you're going into another world\\", and Disney has a great tradition of enchanting children and giving them something to behold. \\nThus, the most appropriate answer would be:\\n\\n\\nDisney has a great tradition of enchanting children and giving them something to behold.\\"\`;"},{"source":"Question: Which Southampton theatre won The Stage Award for Best Regional Theatre for 2015?\\n\\nIs \\"It was awarded The Stage Award for Best Regional Theatre in 2015.\\" the correct answer?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"It won The Stage Award for Best Regional Theatre in 2015\\". We can see that the subject and verb of the statement do not match."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to concatenate all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, and print the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n5, 6, ['P', '5981', '8805', 'L', 'x', '939', '5385']","target":"x939","rationale":"Given the list ['P', '5981', '8805', 'L', 'x', '939'], we need to find the elements within the range 5 ~ 6.\\\\n1. The 5th element is x.\\\\n2. The 6th element is 939, which is converted into a string during concatenation with the other string \\"x\\".\\\\n\\\\nThe final result would be: x939\\n'''"},{"source":"Solve -z - 375 = -2*z - 376 for z.","target":"-1","rationale":"Isolate the variable z on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] -z + 2*z = 375-376\\n[STEP2]  z = -1"},{"source":"Companies, communities, families, clubs, and other clumps of humans all have some inherent social dynamics. At a simple level there are leaders and followers, but in reality the lines are rarely as clear as that.\\nMany leaders, with a common example being some founders, have tremendous vision and imagination, but lack the skills to translate that vision into actionable work. Many followers need structure to their efforts, but are dynamic and creative in the execution. Thus, the social dynamic in organizations needs a little more nuance.\\nThis is where traditional management hierarchies break down in companies. You may have your SVPs, then your VPs, then your Senior Directors, then your Directors, and so on, but in reality most successful companies don‚Äôt observe those hierarchies stringently. In many organizations a junior-level employee who has been there for a while can have as much influence and value, if not more, than a brand new SVP.\\nAs such, the dream is that we build organizations with crisp reporting lines but in which all employees feel they have the ability to bring their creativity and ideas to logically influence the scope, work, and culture of the organization.\\nSadly, this is where many organizations run into trouble. It seems to be the same ‚Äòol story time after time: as the organization grows, the divide between the senior leadership and the folks on the ground widens. Water cooler conversations and bar-side grumblings fuel the fire and resentment, frustrations, and resume-editing often sets in.\\nSo much of this is avoidable though. Of course, there will always be frustration in any organization: this is part and parcel of people working together. Nothing will be perfect, and it shouldn‚Äôt be‚Ä¶frustration and conflict can often lead to organizations re-pivoting and taking a new approach. I believe though, that there are a lot of relatively simple things we can do to make organizations feel more engaging.\\nQuestion: social dynamics cause frustration in the organization when\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. The gap widens between ground folks and senior leadership\\n\\nB. the founder lack skills to take their vision to actionable work\\n\\nC. the employee followers lack structure\\n\\nD. not enough information\\n\\n===\\nThe correct answer is","target":"A","rationale":"The context mentions the difficulties and frustrations of employees in organizations that have a hierarchy. In such companies it is difficult for an employee‚Äôs ideas to be taken seriously by senior leadership, especially as the company grows and more people are hired. The gap between ground folks (junior level employees) and senior leadership can widen due to this rigid structure, which may cause frustration among all levels of employees.\\nSince these issues arise from the social dynamic within the organization, option A seems like a logical answer since it matches with what was mentioned in the question about how ‚Äúthe divide between the senior leadership and the folks on-the-ground widens‚Äù.\\nOptions B through D don't seem relevant because there's no mention of why they would lead to frustration or conflict within any given"},{"source":"Context: From the 1960s to the 1980s historians still considered 100,000 a reasonable estimate of the Jews killed and, according to Edward Flannery, many considered it \\"a minimum\\". Max Dimont in Jews, God, and History, first published in 1962, writes \\"Perhaps as many as 100,000 Jews perished in the decade of this revolution.\\"  Edward Flannery, writing in The Anguish of the Jews: Twenty-Three Centuries of Antisemitism, first published in 1965, also gives figures of 100,000 to 500,000, stating \\"Many historians consider the second figure exaggerated and the first a minimum\\". Martin Gilbert in his Jewish History Atlas published in 1976 states \\"Over 100,000 Jews were killed; many more were tortured or ill-treated, others fled ...\\" Many other sources of the time give similar figures. Although many modern sources still give estimates of Jews killed in the uprising at 100,000 or more, others put the numbers killed at between 40,000 and 100,000, and recent academic studies have argued fatalities were even lower. A 2003 study by Israeli demographer Shaul Stampfer of Hebrew University dedicated solely to the issue of Jewish casualties in the uprising concludes that 18,000-20,000 Jews were killed of a total population of 40,000. Paul Robert Magocsi states that Jewish chroniclers of the 17th century \\"provide invariably inflated figures with respect to the loss of life among the Jewish population of Ukraine. The numbers range from 60,000-80,000  to 100,000 , but that \\"he Israeli scholars Shmuel Ettinger and Bernard D. Weinryb speak instead of the 'annihilation of tens of thousands of Jewish lives', and the Ukrainian-American historian Jarowlaw Pelenski narrows the number of Jewish deaths to between 6,000 and 14,000\\". Orest Subtelny concludes:\\n\\nQuestion: Which scholar gave the second lowest estimate for the number of Jews killed during the uprising?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Shaul Stampfer","rationale":"In order to answer the question \\"Which scholar gave the second lowest estimate for the number of Jews killed during the uprising?\\", we need to find out which scholars estimated how many people were killed in total. 1) Paul Robert Magocsi, range from 60,000-80,000  2) Shmuel Ettinger and Bernard D. Weinryb: annihilation of tens of thousands of Jewish lives 3) Jarowlaw Pelenski between 6,000 and 14,000 4) Orest Subtelny unknown 5)[Shaul Stampfer] 18,000-20,000\\nFrom this passage it is seen that [Shaul Stampfer]'s estimation (18~20 thousand deaths ) was just after Jarowlaw Pelenski's one(6000 ~14 000"},{"source":"What might have been said before this? East Fowler Ave Tampa Florida","target":"I would like you to go to starbucks and get me a coffee","rationale":"The previous statement could have been \\"I would like you to go to starbucks and get me a coffee\\". The current response would be \\"I will go to East Fowler Ave, Tampa, Florida.\\""},{"source":"OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nDoes \\"Most people avoid thinking if they can, some of us are addicted to thinking, but von Neumann actually enjoyed thinking, maybe even to the exclusion of everything else.\\"\\" correctly answer the question of Did von Neumann enjoy thinking?","target":"yes","rationale":"The statement \\"Most people avoid thinking if they can, some of us are addicted to thinking, but von Neumann actually enjoyed thinking, maybe even to the exclusion of everything else.\\" is true as it answers the question correctly. So yes would be a correct answer here."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the small-talk strategy, otherwise output No. small-talk is a cooperative negotiation strategy. It is used for discussing topics apart from the negotiation, in an attempt to build a rapport with the opponent. For example, discussing how the opponent is doing during the pandemic or sharing excitement for the camping trip.\\n\\nContext: 'Hi. I'd like to have all the food packages for my children and two of firewood. Will you accept itüôÇüôÇüôÇ' 'I apologize but that will not work. I have a diabetic and need to make sure they will have enough food for a hike. So I would like to take two food packages, one water, and two firewood. ' 'That won't work. Because, we are planning for a campfire. And so, we are in need of fire wood. I hope you understand.üôÇüôÇüôÇ'\\nUtterance: 'I understand. We are also planning a campfire, and have a lot of young kids who will need the fire to stay warm. So that's why I feel I need two firewoods. üôÇ'","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker does not actually engage in small-talk by commenting about their camping plans or sharing any other information about themselves or the trip. Instead, the speaker simply tries to justify their request for 2 firewood packages by mentioning that they have young children and are planning a campfire. So, the answer is No."},{"source":"Sentence: To change a screwdriver bit. push the bit out of its socket and flip it over or replace it with the needed bit.\\nIf the sentence does not make sense, correct it so that it does make sense. Otherwise, just copy it.\\nAnswer:","target":"To change a screwdriver bit. pull the bit out of its socket and flip it over or replace it with the needed bit.","rationale":"The answer is: \\"To change a screwdriver bit. pull the bit out of its socket and flip it over or replace it with the needed bit.\\"\\nBecause one pushes down on a screw to make something go in, but if you wanted to get the thing out of something, then you would have to pull up on it."},{"source":"In this task, you are given four sentences: a bot task sentence, a bot role sentence, a user task sentence and a user role sentence. Your job is to classify given sentences into one of the 47 different domains. The domains are: 'UPDATE_CALENDAR', 'PRESENT_IDEAS', 'MOVIE_LISTINGS', 'AUTO_SORT', 'GAME_RULES', 'CONTACT_MANAGER', 'BANK_BOT', 'MUSIC_SUGGESTER', 'CHECK_STATUS', 'PET_ADVICE', 'HOW_TO_BASIC', 'NAME_SUGGESTER', 'QUOTE_OF_THE_DAY_BOT', 'GUINESS_CHECK', 'INSURANCE', 'RESTAURANT_PICKER', 'MAKE_RESTAURANT_RESERVATIONS', 'WEDDING_PLANNER', 'SKI_BOT', 'HOME_BOT', 'PLAY_TIMES', 'BUS_SCHEDULE_BOT', 'WHAT_IS_IT', 'PHONE_PLAN_BOT', 'DECIDER_BOT', 'PHONE_SETTINGS', 'TIME_ZONE', 'LIBRARY_REQUEST', 'UPDATE_CONTACT', 'CATALOGUE_BOT', 'PROMPT_GENERATOR', 'SCAM_LOOKUP', 'SPORTS_INFO', 'POLICY_BOT', 'CITY_INFO', 'APARTMENT_FINDER', 'EVENT_RESERVE', 'SHOPPING', 'EDIT_PLAYLIST', 'LOOK_UP_INFO', 'ORDER_PIZZA', 'WEATHER_CHECK', 'APPOINTMENT_REMINDER', 'GEOGRAPHY', 'STORE_DETAILS', 'AGREEMENT_BOT', 'ALARM_SET'.\\n\\nBot's task: Ask the user to specify which week they are asking about \\nBot's role: You are a bot designed to help schedule meetings on a calendar.  \\nUser's task: Ask the chatbot to cancel all your meetings for next week \\nUser's role: You are interacting with a meeting scheduling bot","target":"UPDATE_CALENDAR","rationale":"The answer is 'UPDATE_CALENDAR' as the bot's role and user's role are related to updating the calendar."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the best option to answer the question.\\nContext: I already knew this , of course ... when you know , you just know . But everyday our relationship gets stronger and I find more admirable qualities in him . Accompanying my mother to Columbus to visit her sick mother in the hospital while dealing with my grandma 's ( actually insane ) husband is something not many people could put up with , but Rob does things like that with a genuine smile on his face .\\nQuestion: What is a plausible fact about my relationship ?\\nOptions: \\nA. I am in a platonic relationship .\\nB. I am in a committed relationship .\\nC. I am in a immature relationship .\\nD. I am in a relationship that is n't serious .","target":"B","rationale":"In the first sentence of this context, it is revealed that \\"our relationship gets stronger and I find more admirable qualities in him\\". This suggests that my partner (\\"him\\") has many positive qualities. Later on in the passage, Rob accompanies his mother to Columbus when her sick grandmother was hospitalized. He also handled her insane grandfather well; these are both very selfless acts which require patience and consideration for others. These traits suggest that he is trustworthy and kind-hearted - two characteristics often associated with a committed relationship.\\nBased on these points above, option B shows how close we have become over time: our bond becomes tighter as I recognize more of his good attributes (commitment), so this would be an accurate description about my connection with him . It can also be inferred from the content provided that"},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nJan Joosten van Lodensteijn (1556?‚Äì1623?), a Dutch colleague of Adams' on their ill-fated voyage to Japan in the ship De Liefde, was also given similar privileges by Tokugawa Ieyasu. It appears Joosten became a samurai[citation needed] and was given a residence within Ieyasu's castle at Edo. Today, this area at the east exit of Tokyo Station is known as Yaesu (ÂÖ´ÈáçÊ¥≤). Yaesu is a corruption of the Dutchman's Japanese name, Yayousu (ËÄ∂Ê•äÂ≠ê). Also in common with Adam's, Joostens was given a Red Seal Ship (Êú±Âç∞Ëàπ) allowing him to trade between Japan and Indo-China. On a return journey from Batavia Joosten drowned after his ship ran aground.\\nWhat was Jan Joosten van Lodensteijn's Japanese name?","target":"Yayousu","rationale":"The context provides the answer to this question: Joosten's Japanese name was Yayousu."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nOkmetic 's silicon wafers are part of a further processing chain that produces end products that improve human interaction and quality of life .","target":"neutral","rationale":"The financial news states that silicon wafers are part of a further processing chain that produces end products that improve human interaction and quality of life. This does not indicate any change in the profitability or prices of Okmetic's silicon wafers, so this financial news can be classified as \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should find the minimum absolute difference between 2 integers in the list. The absolute difference is the absolute value of one integer subtracted by another. The output should be a single integer which is the smallest possible absolute distance.\\n\\n[91, -94, -86]","target":"8","rationale":"The list [91, -94, -86] contains only three integers. The absolute difference between 91 and -94 is 185. The absolute difference between 91 and -86 is 177. The absolute difference between -94 and -86 is 8. Since the smallest of these three absolute differences is 8, the answer will be 8"},{"source":"Answer the question below:\\n\\n\\nWhich planet does the sun have the least gravity effect on Mars or Mercury? \\n\\n\\nAssuming that:\\n\\nThe Moon has a greater effect on the tides because, although it is much smaller than the Sun, it is much closer.","target":"Mars","rationale":"We know that the force of gravity depends upon two factors: mass and distance. These are inversely related, so if one increases, then the other decreases proportionally. Therefore Mercury should have a greater effect on tides because it is much closer to Earth than Mars (although both planets' effects would be insignificant compared with those of either Sun or Moon).\\nSo we can conclude that since our choices are between \\"Mars\\" & \\"Mercury\\", Mercury has more gravitational pull than Mars hence answer will be 'MARS'."},{"source":"Q: What is the first and longest phase of mitosis known as?\\n\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- metaphase\\n\\n- telophase\\n\\n- anaphase\\n\\n- prophase\\n\\nA:","target":"prophase","rationale":"The four phases of mitosis are prophase, metaphase, anaphase and telophase. The cell splits into two daughter cells during the final phase, which is called cytokinesis. Prophase is the first stage in this cycle and it marks when chromosomes condense to become visible under a microscope.\\nMitosis has several functions such as repair damaged tissues or replace old ones. It also helps with growth by increasing number of cells within organisms that grow continuously throughout their lives (e as adults)."},{"source":"List of surviving de Havilland Mosquitos -- The de Havilland Mosquito is a British two-engine multi-role combat aircraft used by the Royal Air Force and other Allied air forces during World War II. Of the 7,781 planes built, 30 survive today, three of which are airworthy.\\nBased on the previous passage, are there any de havilland mosquitoes still flying?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The passage states that there are three de Havilland Mosquitos still flying today. Therefore, the answer is Yes."},{"source":"Superintendent Frank Goodyer, who was caught by his own officers in the Wagga Wagga Local Area Command, was charged with driving at more than 45km/h over the speed limit, had his automatically license suspended for six months and fined A$1674. It was reported by Sydney radio station 2GB that it was Superintendent Frank Goodyer as the officer who was caught speeding by his own officers after the New South Wales Police released a media release which did not name the officer who was caught.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nFrank Goodyer was caught driving over the speed limit.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The paragraph contains the facts that Superintendent Frank Goodyer was caught by his own officers in Wagga Wagga Local Area Command and charged with driving more than 45km/h over the speed limit. The fact also has been confirmed via Sydney radio station 2GB report which later found out it was indeed Superintendent Frank Goodyer as the officer who was caught speeding by his own officers, so yes we can conclude that the sentence below is true:\\nFrank Goodyer was caught driving over the speed limit"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context tweet, a question and corresponding answer of given question. Your task is to classify this question-answer pair into two categories: (1) \\"yes\\" if the given answer is right for question, and (2) \\"no\\" if the given answer is wrong for question.\\n\\nContext: Boubacar Barry after winning AFCON '15: \\"I am not big in size or talent. But I thought of my mother who loves me\\" #mA Muslim Footballers (@TheAMF) February 8, 2015 Question: who did boubacar barry think of? Answer: farriery","target":"no","rationale":"The context tweet does not contain the answer \\"farriery\\", so it is not correct."},{"source":"The task is to generate the correct answer for a given math problem.\\n\\nProblem: given f ( x ) = 3 x ‚Äì 5 , for what value of x does 2 * [ f ( x ) ] + 2 = f ( 3 x ‚Äì 6 )","target":"5","rationale":"Solve for x in the given equation:\\\\n2 * [ f ( x ) ] + 2 = f ( 3 x ‚Äì 6) \\\\n2 * [f(x)] + 2 = 3(3x - 6) - 5\\\\n\\\\nBy expanding both sides, we get the following equation:\\\\n6x - 10 + 2 = 9x - 27 - 5\\\\n6x - 8 = 9x - 32\\\\nmoving all terms to one side, we get: \\\\n-3x = 24 \\\\ndividing by negative 3 on both sides, we get: \\\\nx=8/3"},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : Mostar Bridge, completed in 1566, destroyed in 1993 and rebuilt in 2004, stands in which country?\\nAnswer :","target":"Federacija Bosna i Hercegovina","rationale":"The answer is Federacija Bosna i Hercegovina because the Mostar Bridge, completed in 1566, destroyed in 1993 and rebuilt in 2004 stands there."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: The date was like any other day in his life. After school Bill walked past the shop on the street corner. He stopped to look at the front row of shoes, and he felt sorry for himself. He really wanted to have a pair for his birthday.\\nHe sadly walked away and thought of what to tell his mother. He knew she would give him anything if she could. But he also knew very well she had little money. He decided not to go home at once, because he looked worried and he didn't want to make his mother worry about it. So he went to the park and there he sat on the grass. Then he saw a girl in a wheelchair . He found that the girl moved the wheels with her hands. Bill looked at her carefully and he was surprised to see that the girl had no feet. He looked down at his own feet.\\"It's much better to be without shoes than without feet,\\" he thought. It was not right for him to feel sorry and sad. He went away and smiled. He thought he was luckier in life.\\nQuestion: In the park, Bill found the girl was   _  .\\nOptions: A: walking in a wheelchair\\nB: looking at him carefully\\nC: with feet\\nD: moving the wheels with her hands","target":"D","rationale":"Bill meets a girl in the park and sees that she is moving her wheelchair using her hands. It can be inferred from this context that Bill finds the girl \\"moving thwe wheels with her hand\\", so option D is correct."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list. This list contains many lists of integers. The list is several items written within a []. Your task is to find the maximum number among the members of each inner list. The output should be a list comprised of the maximums with the same order as the internal lists.\\n\\n[[-120, -170, -67], [-99, 39, 84]]","target":"[-67, 84]","rationale":"In the first list, -67 is the maximum number.\\\\nIn the second list, 84 is the maximum number.\\\\nTherefore, [-67, 84] is a correct answer."},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\nHonestly I'm torn on this one so, internet do your thing.\\n\\nSo when ever we play monopoly, my younger brother often goes around the board once (if that) and quits. Usually he doesn't have any property and if he does we just auction it off or he gives it to someone. I'm honestly fine with that. \\n\\nTonight, my sister, her friend, my brother and I were playing and right on que he quits while running off to play fortnite. We decide since he has a couple properties to just let him play as a \\"ghost\\", rolling for him, he buys any properties he lands on that he can, and making only legit fair trades we all approve of.\\n\\nSo all was going ok and the game was nearing an end when my sister's friend starts running out of money. Since she lands on brother's spot, we jokingly have her go ask if she really has to pay. She pays. After landing on the same space a few times later, she asks again. She pays again. Now hes back and interested. He lands on an unowned spot and I say I'm going to buy it away next turn (we agreed paying double what he paid on our next turn was legit).\\n\\nSo this is where everything goes down. At this point the other two have him sit with us so I cant just buy it since hes \\"playing\\". Ok whatever I dont mind too much. But his next turn he wills all his property and money to my sister, calls me a loser and walks away again. I'm having none of this. I argue it should go to auction, she argues he can do what he wants with it. At this point we're all annoyed. I throw the dice annoyedly on the board and we all decide it's a good place to stop. We joke around and come out fine but still lowkey annoyed at one another. \\n\\nSo, Tl:Dr, am I the asshole for getting annoyed at sibling monopoly time?","target":"HISTORICAL","rationale":"The author describes a past event in which they played Monopoly with their siblings and one of the siblings quit playing early on. The author's younger brother handed over his properties to other players, but then became interested again after seeing how the game was turning out. After handing all of his properties to one sibling and calling another a loser, he left again. The remaining players were annoyed at these events and decided to end the game earlier than anticipated.\\\\nThe post is written in the past tense, which suggests that it is not hypothetical and that it has already occurred - otherwise, if it were hypothetical, the verb tenses would likely be switched to future tense (e.g., \\"\\"will\\"\\" instead of \\"\\"would\\"\\"). Therefore, based on this information alone without any more context about when exactly the event occurred or when it will occur in the future, we can conclude that this anecdote is \\"HISTORICAL\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\nmobile","target":"fix","rationale":"The antonym of \\"mobile\\" is \\"fix\\", as the opposite of something that can move around is something that cannot move."},{"source":"Choctaw mythology is related to Choctaws, a Native American tribe, originally from the Southeastern United States (Mississippi, Alabama, and Louisiana), today the Choctaws have four tribes, what is the group name, is one of three federally recognized tribes of Choctaw Native Americans, and is the only federally recognized Native American tribe in the state?","target":"Mississippi Band of Choctaw Indians","rationale":"The Choctaw are a Native American people originally occupying what is now the Southeastern United States (modern-day Alabama, Florida, Mississippi and Louisiana). Today there are four federally recognized tribes of Choctaw Native Americans:\\n* The Jena Band of Choctaw Indians in Louisianna. \\n* The Mowa Band of Choctaws based in Mobile County, AL . \\n* Mississippi Band of Choctaw Indians , which is one three federally recognized tribes of Chocatw Natives in America located near Philadelphia, MS and it's only Federally recongized tribe in the state. \\n* Oklahoma historicall was home to 5 different tribal communities including Pushmataha District at Antlers; Apukshunnubbee district at Bogue H"},{"source":"Formulate an answer to this elaborate question: At what intersection is the high school Joseph Wapner attended located?","target":"North Highland Avenue and West Sunset Boulevard","rationale":"The answer is based on the stated location of Joseph Wapner's high school in Los Angeles. It was located at North Highland Avenue and West Sunset Boulevard."},{"source":"Question : Which title was bestowed upon Oliver Cromwell in 1653?\\nAnswer :","target":"Lord Protector of England, Scotland and Ireland","rationale":"In 1653, Oliver Cromwell was appointed as the Lord Protector of England, Scotland and Ireland."},{"source":"Formulate an answer to this elaborate question: Thomas Dimitroff joined the patriots as a scout for the team's 33rd season in the National Football League which was part of what calendar year?","target":"2002 New England Patriots season","rationale":"Thomas Dimitroff joined the Patriots as a scout for the team's 33rd season in the National Football League. This would be the 2002 New England Patriots season, during which they won Super Bowl XXXVI."},{"source":"Write down the solution for this math problem: Solve 832 = 71*a - 19*a for a.","target":"16","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable a on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 71*a - 19*a = 832\\n[STEP 2] 52*a = 832\\n[STEP 3] a = 832 / 52\\n[STEP 4] a = 16"},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nThe solubility of the majority of solid substances increases as the temperature increases. However, the effect is difficult to predict and varies widely from one solute to another. The temperature dependence of solubility can be visualized with the help of a solubility curve , a graph of the solubility vs. temperature (see Figure below ).\\n\\n\\nQ: As temperature increases, the solubility of the majority of solid substances does what?\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- stays the same\\n\\n- reduces\\n\\n- mutates\\n\\n- increases\\n\\nA:","target":"increases","rationale":"The paragraph states that the solubility of the majority of solid substances increases as the temperature increases. The cause for this is not mentioned in the passage, so there's no need to infer why it happens. This makes option A incorrect; just because something occurs doesn't mean we can say with certainty what caused it.\\nWe also don't know that all solids increase at different rates (option C), and since there are many variables involved here, saying \\"it varies\\" or \\"we cannot predict\\" means we're dismissing other possibilities when none have been ruled out yet (options B & D)."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story coherent / plausible by writing \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes most sense.\\n\\nBeginning: It was a beautiful summer day outside. Middle 1: He had work to do and couldn't go outside. Middle 2: He had work to do and couldn't wait to go outside. Ending: He was disappointed.","target":"1","rationale":"Middle 1 indicates that the protagonist had work to do, which prevented him from going outside. In Middle 2, the protagonist also has work to do, but he is eager to leave his work and go outside. Both middles are plausible, but Middle 1 specifies a reason for why he was disappointed at the end of the story."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a text passage from a trivia quiz. You should choose the category this question belongs to from these categories: History, Science, Social Science, Fine Arts, Literature. You can only choose one category, so if in doubt, please choose the closest match.\\n\\nEccy de Jonge has written about this philosopher's connection to the environmental concept of Deep Ecology, which topic was also written about by Brenden MacDonald. In one of his works, this man wrote about \\"the popular confusion of ready imagination with distinct understanding,\\" which section occurs after one discussing \\"true ideas,\\" which are the instruments of the titular idea. This author of (*) On the Improvement of the Understanding wrote that reason does not preclude God from giving law to mankind in a work which also discussed the relativity of good and evil. This author of Tractatus Theological-Politicus also wrote a work in which the nature of God, the mind, human bondage to the emotions, and the power of understanding, are arranged in a geometric order. For ten points, name this Dutch moral philosopher who wrote Ethics.","target":"Social Science","rationale":"The question is about the philosopher Benedict Spinoza, who wrote \\"On the Improvement of the Understanding\\" and \\"Tractatus Theological-Politicus\\", both of which are works in moral philosophy. Hence, this is a question from Social Science."},{"source":"Here's a question: Billy wanted to return home, but his mother told him to do what?\\n\\nHere are possible answers to this question:\\n- run away\\n- leave\\n- going away\\n- backspace\\n- go away\\n\\nI believe the correct choice is \\"go away\\", here's why:","target":"hepatitis b: medlineplus medical encyclopedia","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"hepatitis b: medlineplus medical encyclopedia\\"."},{"source":"I want to test the ability of students to read a passage and answer questions about it. Could you please come up with a good question for the passage \\"Sassou Nguesso aligned the country with the Eastern Bloc and signed a twenty-year friendship pact with the Soviet Union. Over the years, Sassou had to rely more on political repression and less on patronage to maintain his dictatorship.\\"?","target":"What was more beneficial than the pact?","rationale":"The passage talks about how Sassou aligned his country with the Eastern Bloc and signed a 20-year pact with Russia. It also mentions that he used political repression more than patronage (political favoritism) to maintain power. This suggests that the benefit of signing the pact was less effective in maintaining power compared to other tactics like political repression. Hence, \\"What was more beneficial than the pact?\\" is an appropriate question for this passage"},{"source":"The input is a conversation between an automated system and a user looking for suggestions for pubs, restaurants and coffee shops in Cambridge. In the dialogue, the user may provide some criteria for the type of place they want such as price range, cuisine, etc. Given such a dialogue, output the price range the user if looking for which can take one of four values: Cheap, Moderate, Expensive and Don't Care. Output cannot be any other value than the four values. Note that if the user asks for the prices of items provided at a pub, restaurant or coffee shop but doesn't mention the price range they are looking for then the correct classification will be Don't Care. If the user does not mention a particular price, the correct classification will be Don't Care.\\n\\nSystem: 'Thank you for calling the Cambridge Information system. Your call will be recorded for research purposes. You may ask for information about a place to eat, such as a restaurant, a pub, or a cafe. How may I help you?'\\nUser: 'i am looking for a greek restaurant'\\nSystem: 'Are you looking for somewhere near a particular venue? For example, Byard Art, Kettle's Yard, or the Michaelhouse Centre.'\\nUser: 'no'\\nSystem: 'The Eraina Taverna, which serves greek food, is an outstanding restaurant.'\\nUser: 'whats the address phone number and the price'\\nSystem: 'The Eraina Taverna is located on 2 Free School Lane and its phone number is 01223902126. The price for main courses ranges from 6 pounds 50 to 13 pounds 95.'\\nUser: 'thank you good bye'","target":"Don't Care","rationale":"The user mentions a preference for Greek food, but does not mention a price range. Therefore, the correct classification is \\"Don't Care\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nmilk : jug. coat : ?","target":"closet","rationale":"The milk is kept in a jug and the coat is kept in a closet."},{"source":"if a plant shows up in a new place, what might have happened?\\n\\nChoices:\\n- the plant is able to relocate itself\\n- it spontaneously appeared there\\n- it walked to the new place\\n- its cased embryo have been dispersed","target":"its cased embryo have been dispersed","rationale":"Spontaneous transport of flowering plants was a popular theory in the 18th century. However, experiments showed that this is not possible for most species. Therefore, it cannot be said with certainty whether the plant spontaneously appeared there or relocated itself to the new place by walking.\\n\\nPlants reproduce through seeds and spores which are dispersed when they fall off from their parent plant or carried away by wind currents, water flows etc.. The cased embryo have been dispersed implies that these embryos were once attached/part of its parental body but detached and began floating towards another location (which may eventually grow into mature individuals). This makes option 4: 'its cased embryo have been dispersed' as more likely than other options given above"},{"source":"Given a question and its paraphrases, answer the question. The answer should exactly answer all the questions given without any ambiguity. Don't give partial answers.\\n\\nQuestions: ['what year did yugoslavia become serbia?']","target":"2006","rationale":"The questions can be paraphrased as \\"When did yugoslavia become serbia?\\" The year 2006 is the correct answer."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a prompt from a judicial decision and multiple holding statements derived from citations following text in a legal decision.  Holdings represent the governing legal rule when the law is applied to a particular set of facts. There are five answer choices for each citing text. The correct answer is the holding statement that corresponds to the citing text. You should write an incorrect option. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. There is a <HOLDING> token in the position of the citing text prompt where the holding statement was extracted.\\n\\na plan for managing the potential liability, and submit the information to the agency. See Minn.Stat. ¬ß 115A.471. Defendants argue that NSWMA does not have standing to challenge section 115A.471. This court‚Äôs jurisdiction is limited by Article III of the U.S. Constitution, which limits the judicial power of the federal courts to ‚Äúcases‚Äù and ‚Äúcontroversies.‚Äù U.S. Const. art. III, ¬ß 2, cl. 1. A threshold question in every case is whether the plaintiff has standing to invoke the jurisdiction of the federal courts. The standing doctrine is ‚Äúan essential and unchanging part of the ease-or-controversy requirement of Article III.‚Äù Lujan v. Defenders of Wildlife, 504 U.S. 555, 560, 561, 112 S.Ct. 2130, 2136, 2136-37, 119 L.Ed.2d 351 (1992); Mausolf v. Babbitt, 85 F.3d 1295, 1301 (8th Cir.1996) (<HOLDING>). To establish standing within the \\n Holding statements: (A) holding that standing is an essential and unchanging part of the easeorcontroversy requirement of article iii (B) recognizing associational standing when members would have standing in own right (C) recognizing that standing requirement is indispensable part of case (D) recognizing that the case or controversy requirement for standing is no less strict in a declaratory judgment proceeding than in any suit where other relief is sought (E) holding that standing existed","target":"holding that standing is an essential and unchanging part of the easeorcontroversy requirement of article iii","rationale":"The prompt describes the Defendants' argument that NSWMA doesn't have standing to challenge section 115A.471. The cited holding statement is \\"holding that standing is an essential and unchanging part of the easeorcontroversy requirement of article iii\\", which establishes a general principle stating that standing is necessary to establish jurisdiction, but it doesn't specifically address whether NSWMA has standing in this case. Therefore, this option is incorrect and should be selected as an incorrect answer choice for the question."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to the associated containers is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its associated container B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate container for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\npickles : jar. kleenex : ?","target":"box","rationale":"To store pickles, one could use a jar. Similarily, Kleenex could be stored in a box."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: I Have to See Another Doctor\\nMr. Clarke lives at the foot of the mountain. He keeps the forest for a rich farmer there. The only road to the forest is just in front of his house. He can easily see the people who want to enter the forest. Sometimes he has to be on duty at night. When he hears some sound, he has to get up to see if someone cuts the trees.\\nOne day he bought something in the town. He found a strong dog and bought it. He loves it very much and often gives some meat or bread to it. And when a strange man walks close to his house, it barks  loudly. So he can soon know about it and goes out to find out who it is. But last week something was wrong with Mr. Clarke. He didn't feel well and couldn't fall asleep in the evening. He had to go to a hospital in the town. The doctor looked him over and then asked, \\"Have you got a dog, sir \\"\\n\\"Yes, I have got one.\\"\\n\\"You have got a skin disease ,\\" said the doctor. \\"I am sure your dog infected  it to you. You can't come in touch  with it any longer.\\"\\nWhen he came out of the hospital, he met a friend and told him about it. The man asked, \\"What are you going to do, to sell your dog or to give it to another man \\"\\n\\"Neither,\\" answered Mr. Clarke, \\"I have decided to see another doctor. It's much easier to find a doctor than to buy a good dog!\\"\\nQuestion: Which of the following is true\\nOptions: A: Mr. Clarke thought the dog was more useful than the doctor.\\nB: Mr. Clarke decided to go on coming in touch with his dog.\\nC: Mr. Clarke wouldn't hurt his dog.\\nD: Mr. Clarke hoped to cure  his dog.","target":"B","rationale":"Mr. Clarke is a watchman who loves his dog very much, so he would never hurt the animal. However, when Mr. Clark finds out that it was his dog's fault for him getting sick and has to stop coming in touch with his pet as per doctor‚Äôs instructions, but decides against selling or giving away the dog because finding another doctor is easier than buying a good watchdog\\nSo from this we can infer that Mr. Clark decided to come in contact with his Dog despite knowing about its harmful effects on health . Thus B: \\"Mr. Clarke decided to go on coming in touch with his dog\\" must be true"},{"source":"I woke at dawn when Digger climbed over me to get out of bed, and I woke again an hour later when Pa called, \\"Everyone up who wants breakfast!\\" Across the room, Little Bit was dressing in a T-shirt and jeans that had been mine a year before. Ma had put a stack of clean clothes at the foot of the bed for me. I dressed without caring what I put on. The only important items were my cowboy boots and my Roy Rogers belt with two holsters for cap guns, even though I only had one cap gun left, and its trigger was broken.\\nWhen I used the toilet, I sat on the front edge of the seat, watching the water beneath me, and scooted off as soon as I was done. I had seen a cartoon in a book at Grandpa Abner's that showed a fish leaping out of a toilet bowl and a woman staring at it with big eyes. I thought that was funny and I knew it was impossible, but I didn't think there was any reason to take chances.\\nMa called, \\"Little Bit has to use the bathroom.\\"\\nI yelled, \\"I'm almost done.\\"\\nMa called, \\"Are you off the toilet?\\"\\nI yelled, \\"Yes!\\" Ma opened the door and brought Little Bit in. Squeezing toothpaste onto my toothbrush, I said, \\"I wasn't done yet.\\"\\nMa said, \\"Your father's making breakfast in the restaurant.\\" That meant we should hurry, so I slid the brush over my teeth while Little Bit sat next to the sink, and then I ran out of the house.\\nStepping into the sunlight was stepping into Florida. I didn't smell oranges -- Ma had explained that oranges grew further south -- but I smelled a humid pinelands that was not like the New Orleans suburb I had known.\\nQuestion: When did the narrator first wake up?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. When Ma put clean clothes at the foot of the bed.\\n\\nB. When Pa called everyone for breakfast.\\n\\nC. When Digger climbed over to get out of bed.\\n\\nD. not enough information\\n\\n===\\nThe correct answer is","target":"C","rationale":"The narrator wakes up when Digger climbs over the narrator to get out of bed. The narrator goes back to sleep and is woken again by Pa's call for everyone who wants breakfast.\\nSo, the answer is C."},{"source":"I‚Äôve often been asked, ‚ÄúWhat is a blog?‚Äù This is my attempt to answer that question in a simple way.\\nThe word blog is short for web log and although the quick answer for me would be ‚Äúa web journal‚Äù or ‚Äúonline diary,‚Äù I think blogs encompass more than that.\\nBlogs are platforms for people to write about pretty much anything and everything. I was first introduced to the concept when a few friends starting writing family blogs as a way to keep in touch with distant friends and relatives or keep up with documenting their lives for themselves or their children. Sort of like a modern day scrapbook or baby book.\\nThen, I followed a couple friends as they blogged about traveling around America. One‚Äôs purpose was to find a small town to settle in and the other‚Äôs purpose was to kill time while unemployed and waiting for a call to serve as a minister.\\nNow I follow all sorts of blogs. There are blogs about dogs, traveling, kids, cooking, religion, fitness, politics, crafts, parenting, writing, educating, interior design, you name it! There are even blogs about blogging!\\nIndividuals run blogs. Groups of friends run blogs. Businesses run blogs. Religious institutions run blogs.\\nBlogs are a way for people to connect over certain topics and interests, socializing in the ever-growing blogosphere. Chances are, you‚Äôve read blog posts without even realizing it. Most look like an article you‚Äôd find on any website. But blog posts typically have a personal touch.\\nThey‚Äôre a wonderful way for people to share tips, tricks, tutorials, inspiration, and more with others.\\nIf you want a more thorough definition of the term blog, this one is from Wikipedia.\\nBlogs are also a way for businesses to advertise through honest reviews and giveaways. They partner up with bloggers to spread the word about their products or services. So, some bloggers are also advertisers.\\nAccording to the above context, choose the correct option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: After the end of the text, the author probably:\\nOptions:\\n- gives up on writing blogs\\n- writes in a blog\\n- talks negatively to people about blogs\\n- not enough information","target":"writes in a blog","rationale":"The context is a blog post written by someone who has been asked what blogs are, so it can be inferred that the author writes in a blog. \\nSo the answer is to write in a blog."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the physics. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: a man ' s regular pay is $ 3 per hour up to 40 hours . overtime is twice the payment for regular time . if he was paid $ 186 , how many hours overtime did he work ? \\nOptions: a ) 8 , b ) 5 , c ) 9 , d ) 6 , e ) 11","target":"e","rationale":"The man's regular pay is $3 per hour, up to 40 hours. If he worked for more than 40 hours, he gets double pay for the extra time. This means that he gets $6 per hour for overtime work.\\\\nIf he was paid $186 in total, then there were 186 - 120 = 66 dollars of overtime pay, as the first 120 dollars are from his regular time at 3 dollars an hour. Therefore, he worked a total of 66 / 6 = 11 hours of overtime."},{"source":"Produce a brief English sentence that would be considered grammatically as category: unacceptable\\nAll categories: OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"Jennifer craned her arm.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically acceptable sentence: Jennifer craned her arm."},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question The Cardinals hosted a close contest with the Kansas City Chiefs.  The game was the first at the newly christened University of Phoenix Stadium, which signed its naming rights deal with the Cardinals two days after Arizona's last home game vs. St. Louis. The Cards started off hot as Matt Leinart, making his first NFL start, threw two touchdowns in the first quarter to his two top targets, Anquan Boldin and Larry Fitzgerald.  The Chiefs responded early in the second quarter with a 45-yard field goal by kicker Lawrence Tynes, and a touchdown pass from quarterback Damon Huard to running back Larry Johnson.  Cards kicker Neil Rackers added a 41-yard field at the end of the first half. Another Rackers field goal, this time from 45 yards, accounted for the only score in the third quarter.  The Chiefs then scored 13 unanswered points to win the game, with a touchdown pass from Huard to Samie Parker, and two field goals by Tynes (40, 19).  Tynes' last field goal was set up by a 78-yard screen pass from Huard to Johnson.  Johnson suffered a sprained neck at the end of the play on a violent face mask tackle by Cards' cornerback Antrel Rolle, who was fined $12,500 for the penalty. A last second 51-yard field goal attempt by Rackers to send the game to overtime failed, giving the Cards their fourth straight loss.  During the game Larry Fitzgerald pulled a hamstring and missed 3 games, returning Week 10 against Dallas.\\nHow many loses in a row did this make for the Cards?","target":"fourth straight loss","rationale":"To answer how many loses in a row, we need to find the information about who won. Since it is said that \\"A last second 51-yard field goal attempt by Rackers to send the game to overtime failed\\" and \\"gave the Cards their fourth straight loss\\", therefore we could conclude that this was 4th lose for Cardinals."},{"source":"Generate a question that has the following answer: \\ncremation \\nfor the following movie plot: \\nDrew Baylor (Bloom) is an intelligent young man and designer for a shoe company. When his latest design, hyped to be a great accomplishment in his life, has a flaw that will cost the company $972 million to correct, Drew is shamed by his boss (Baldwin) and his coworkers before he is dismissed. Disappointed in his failure, and the subsequent breakup with his girlfriend Ellen (Jessica Biel), he plans an elaborate suicide by taping a butcher knife to an exercise bike, only to be stopped at the last moment by a tearful call from his sister Heather (Judy Greer) that his father died of a heart attack while visiting family in Elizabethtown, Kentucky. Drew volunteers to retrieve the body, following a memorial service when his mother Hollie (Sarandon) refuses to go, following a dispute between her and the rest of the Kentucky Baylors, who consider them \\"Californian\\" despite the fact they were in California for a little over a year 27 years before, and instead live in Oregon.\\nOn the flight to Kentucky, Drew meets Claire (Dunst), an optimistic, enthusiastic and kind flight attendant who gives him a seat in first class, due to the plane being empty, so she does not have to travel all the way back to coach. She proves helpful and happy to an otherwise despondent Drew, giving him directions, instructions and tips on getting to his destination before they part ways. When he gets to Elizabethtown, Drew is met with the love of the family, though he is somewhat goaded by being a \\"California Boy\\" and he makes the arrangements for a cremation at Hollie's request despite the family's objections. While staying at a hotel, where a wedding reception is being held for the weekend, Drew calls his mother and sister, then his ex-girlfriend as he continues to struggle with his suicidal thoughts. Finally, he calls Claire, who relieves his anxiety and the two of them talk for hours. She impulsively suggests they drive out to meet before she has to depart on a flight to Hawaii that morning and they meet and talk.\\nDrew comes to grips with...","target":"What did Hollie request?","rationale":"The answer is \\"What did Hollie request?\\"\\nSince the father had died in Kentucky, he needed to be cremated. His wife was against it and Drew volunteered to retrieve his body."},{"source":"Write the conversation response. DIALOG:\\nDid Cameron Crowe write the book Fast Times at Ridgemont High?\\n- His book, Fast Times at Ridgemont High: A True Story, came out in 1981.\\n- When did Cameron Crowe write the book Fast Times at Ridgemont High?\\n- in 1981.\\n- Was the book Fast Times at Ridgemont High popular?\\n-","target":"When did the book Fast Times at Ridgemont High get made into a movie?","rationale":"The last question makes it clear that this is a conversation about the book \\"Fast Times at Ridgemont High\\". The only information missing from the conversation is when it was made into a movie. The answer is \\"When did the book Fast Times at Ridgemont High get made into a movie?\\""},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"Located at the mouth of the Yodo River on Osaka Bay , Osaka is Japan's third largest city by population after Tokyo (special wards) and Yokohama .\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Osaka","rationale":"The sentence is about Osaka and its relation to the Yodo River, which helps identify the topic of the passage.\\nTherefore, I think that \\"Osaka\\" should be marked as correct answer."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is \\"The shepherds ended up looking more like dogs.\\" true if \\"Sam tried to paint a picture of shepherds with sheep, but they ended up looking more like dogs.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The statement \\"Sam tried to paint a picture of shepherds with sheep\\" means that Sam was trying to draw or paint the image of a shepherd holding one or more sheep. As such, saying that these drawings ended up looking like dogs would be incorrect because it is not possible for something drawn as a human figure (the shepherd) to turn out looking like an animal (a dog). So, the answer is no.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story and the first four sentences. Your job is to write the last sentence of the story to not connect with the rest of the story. Ensure that the generated sentence is contextually relevant to the story.\\n\\nTitle: Lightning Storm. Sentence 1: The Smith's electricity went out due to a lightning storm. Sentence 2: Their kids were visibly scared. Sentence 3: The Smith family decided to have fun with it. Sentence 4: They pretended to camp out in the living room.","target":"Anna decided to hand-wash her socks from now on!","rationale":"The first four sentences of the story describe a family's experience during a lightning storm. The last sentence should be written such that it is contextually relevant to the story but does not connect with the rest of it. For example, \\"Anna decided to hand-wash her socks from now on!\\" is an appropriate response to Sentence 4 (\\"They pretended to camp out in their living room\\") because they are camping in their living room and therefore do not have access to a washing machine. However, this sentence does not relate back to the rest of the story so it can serve as an appropriate ending"},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nThe folds present in the membrane increase the surface area allowing more ribosomes to be present on the ER, thereby allowing greater protein production.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nIf Mona is creating a membrane to filter out some dirty water and she creates fewer folds in the membrane, what happens to the total surface area of that membrane increases or decreases?","target":"decreases","rationale":"The question is about the total surface area of a membrane with fewer folds. Folds in membranes increase their surface areas, so it can be inferred that lessening or removing those folds will decrease the overall surface area of both sides of the membrane and therefore reduce its strength as a filter for large particles. So, the answer is decreases"},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Four students compared the total mass of the products to the total mass of the reactants after performing three trials of the same chemical reaction. Each student concluded that the total mass of the products was slightly less than the total mass of the reactants. Each student proposed a different explanation as follows. Student 1: The reaction converted some of the reactant mass to energy. Student 2: The chemical reaction produced a gas that escaped. Student 3: Some of the mass measurements were made with insufficient precision. Student 4: Heat released during the reaction caused the volume of the products to increase.Which students offered the most reasonable explanations?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: Students 1 and 3\\n \\n- B: Students 1 and 4\\n \\n- C: Students 2 and 3\\n \\n- D: Students 2 and 4","target":"C","rationale":"Here's the rationale for option C:\\nStudent 1 can be ruled out because a chemical reaction does not convert mass to energy. Student 4 is also incorrect in his reasoning, as heat released during the reaction would cause an increase of volume of reactants rather than products (as water vapor will condense). Student 3 may have been correct if they were working with multiple trials and had results that varied widely from one trial to another; however, since this was only one experiment it is unlikely that their measurements are inaccurate enough to account for discrepancies in weight. The most reasonable explanation offered by students 2 and 3, who stated the gas produced by the reaction escaped or caused changes in measurement due to temperature fluctuations respectively."},{"source":"Here's a question and a few possible answers: \\n\\nQ: If a person uses a computer at night to surf the internet, what feeling might they try to alleviate?\\nPossible A: eye strain, happiness, program created, lonely, stress\\n\\nWhy is \\"stress\\" an answer aligned with human common sense?","target":"stress does'nt takes us to sleep","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"stress does'nt takes us to sleep\\"."},{"source":"Suggest a movie title for the following movie plot: Min, a young Korean boy, moves to Japan with his father, who is a potter. One day at a local shrine, Min meets Nanae, a beautiful local girl and aspiring painter. He falls in love at first sight. She is a student at his new school, and their friendship develops despite their cultural and language differences. However, Min's grandmother suddenly falls ill, and Min returns to Korea without having a chance to explain to Nanae. While he is gone, Nanae is forced to move away to protect her and her sister from their mother's violent boyfriend. Before Min and Nanae separate, Nanae gives Min an amulet pouch with a letter inside. She tells him to open it later, and so he doesn't open it before he goes to see his grandmother. Min's grandmother notices it in his pocket and assumes that it is a present for her from Japan; not wanting to disappoint his grandmother, Min gives away the amulet pouch. When Min's grandmother eventually recovers, he returns to Japan only to find that Nanae is gone.\\nTwo years later a friend of Min finds Nanae drawing in a park. Nanae explains the reason she disappeared, and learns that Min returned to Korea because he felt there was no reason to stay. A few months later Nanae and Min stumble upon each other at an art show in Korea. However, Min is still bruised from being left without news and reacts harshly at the reunion.\\nLater Min's grandmother discovers the letter inside the amulet pouch and gives it to him. The letter says that Nanae wants to be with Min forever but cannot because she has to go, but asks him to meet her at the first snow on Deoksugung street in Seoul. Min travels to Kyoto and finds diary entries from Nanae, saying that she has been waiting for him in vain there for several years. He leaves back to Seoul, but when at the airport in Seoul notices snowflakes starting to fall. He rushes to Deoksugung, and on a tree finds a paper note hoping that he will return (he tied the paper note there after he met with Nanae in Seoul). He turns to find Nanae and they tearfully reunite.","target":"Virgin Snow","rationale":"Virgin Snow is a 2007 Japanese film based on the novel by Keigo Higashino. The story is about Min, a young Korean boy who moves to Japan with his father and meets Nanae, an aspiring painter and student at his new school. Their friendship develops despite their cultural differences as they grow up together in Japan until one day when Min's grandmother falls ill and he returns to Korea without having a chance to say goodbye. Two years later, Nanae finds him again but still heartbroken from the sudden departure of his friend, he reacts harshly upon seeing her again for the first time since leaving her behind two years earlier.\\nThe plot synopsis above matches that of Virgin Snow almost exactly; both stories feature characters named \\"Min\\" (a Korean potter), \\"Nanae"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: threat and non-threat. Threat is a statement that someone will be hurt or harmed, especially if the person does not do something in particular.\\n\\nComment: You got that right, hemorrhoid, everyone will be dead.","target":"Threat","rationale":"The given comment threatens harm and death to all people, which is a very serious threat. Therefore, it should be classified as \\"Threat\\"."},{"source":"You are given a list of queries separated by new line. Your job is to answer with the query that is the most well-formed or well-structured query in terms of grammar, punctuations, or spelling errors.\\n\\nWhat are the different relationships of an ecosystem ?\\nHow many songs has Avril Lavign san ?\\nBusiness cycle in 1920 and 1930 ?\\nHow did Nelson Mandela played in abolishing apartheid ?","target":"What are the different relationships of an ecosystem ?","rationale":"All the queries are grammatically incorrect. The query \\"What are the different relationships of an ecosystem ?\\" is the most well-formed out of all."},{"source":"\\"Sei gesegnet ohne Ende\\" (English translation: \\"Be Blessed Without End\\"), also known as the ‚Ä≥Kernstock-Hymne‚Ä≥, is a German language song that was the national anthem of Austria from 1929 until 1938. Written by Ottokar Kernstock, it was sung to the famous tune of \\"Gott erhalte Franz den Kaiser\\" by Joseph Haydn that is also used for the \\"Deutschlandlied\\", since 1922 the national anthem of Germany.\\nCan we infer the following?\\nAustria's national anthem was in German.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nThe answer is:","target":"Yes","rationale":"The passage mentions that \\"Sei gesegnet ohne Ende\\" is a German language song. It also states that it was the national anthem of Austria from 1929 until 1938. The text does not provide any evidence contrary to this claim, so we can infer that Austrias' national anthem at this time period was in fact in German and answer is therefore Yes\\"."},{"source":"If this is the response, what came before? Response Do you want small, medium, or large?","target":"I'd like to order a two topping pizza.","rationale":"The response \\"Do you want small, medium, or large?\\" is usually a follow up question after ordering a pizza. The most reasonable option among the candidates is the one that has the correct context to lead to this follow up question. Hence, \\"I'd like to order a two topping pizza.\\" is the most reasonable option and hence should be chosen as it has the correct context."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that start with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'a man leaping into the air and swinging a tennis racket'. How many words start with the letter 'l' in the sentence.","target":"1","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a man leaping into the air and swinging a tennis racket', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' does not start with the letter 'l'.\\\\n2. 'man' does not start with the letter 'l'.\\\\n3. 'leaping' starts with the letter 'l', so add 1 to our total count (1).\\\\n4. The rest of words do not start with the letter l, so we do nothing and move on to next word.\\\\n5. The final result is 1, since only one word starts with an l: leaping"},{"source":"Given a disfluent sentence, modify the sentence to it to its equivalent fluent form, preserving the meaning of the sentence.\\n\\nWhen did the lower er uh last glacial end?","target":"When did the last glacial end?","rationale":"The original sentence is disfluent, containing the word \\"er\\" and \\"uh\\". The question can be modified to its equivalent fluent form as \\"When did the last glacial end?\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context paragraph of the tweet and question. Your task is to generate right answer of given question based on given context tweet paragraph.\\n\\nContext: I was in Terminal 4 AA airlines and must've been one of the last flights that made it out this morning before the airport was closed.‚Äî Chris Harrison (@chrisbharrison) November 1, 2013 Question: did chris make it out before the airport was closed?","target":"one of the last out","rationale":"The question asks about what time the flight left. The answer should indicate that the flight left before the airport closed. The answer 'one of the last out' indicates that it was one of the last flights to leave before it closed, which is consistent with when he made it out."},{"source":"FINAL EXAM\\n\\nQuestion 1. Lanny Joon starred opposite Jamie Foxx in which 2017 action crime comedy?","target":"Baby Driver","rationale":"Lanny Joon starred opposite Jamie Foxx in the 2017 action crime comedy Baby Driver."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: Something roared like thunder. The earth shook a little and we heard the rat-a-tat-tat of gunfire. \\"Father!\\" Hassan cried. We sprung to our feet and raced out of the living room.\\n\\"Father! What's that sound? Hassan screamed, his hands outstretched toward Ali. Ali wrapped his arms around us. A white light flashed and lit the sky in silver. It flashed again and was followed by rapid sharp sounds of gunfire. \\"They're hunting ducks.\\" Ali said in a hoarse voice. \\"They hunt ducks at night, you know.\\" Don't be afraid.\\nA siren  went off in the distance. Somewhere glass broke and someone shouted. I heard people on the street, jolted from sleep and probably still in their pajamas, with ruffled hair and puffy eyes. Hassan was crying. Ali pulled him close, clutched him with tenderness.\\nWe stayed huddled that way until the early hours of the morning. The shootings and explosions had lasted less than an hour, but they had frightened us badly, because none of us had ever heard gunshots in the streets. They were foreign sounds to us then. The generation of Afghan children whose ears would know nothing but the sounds of bombs and gunfire was not yet born. Huddled together in the dining room and waiting for the sun to rise, none of us had any notion that a way of life had ended. The end came when Russian tanks were rolling into the very same streets where Hassan and I played, bringing the death of the Afghanistan I knew and marking the start of a still ongoing era of bloodletting.\\nJust before sunrise, Baba's car peeled into the driveway. His door slammed shut and his running footsteps pounded the stairs. Then he appeared in the doorway and I saw something on his face. Something I didn't recognize right away because I'd never seen it before: fear. \\"Amir! Hassan!\\" He cried as he ran to us, opening his arms wide. \\"They blocked all the roads and the telephone didn't work. I was so worried!\\"\\nWe let him wrap us in his arms and, for a brief moment, I was glad about whatever had happened that night.\\nQuestion: By saying \\"they are hunting ducks\\", Ali   _  .\\nOptions: A: told the children the truth\\nB: tried to calm the children\\nC: played a joke on the children\\nD: cheered the children up","target":"B","rationale":"The context suggests that the children are frightened by a series of explosions and gunshots. Ali tells them that they are ‚Äúhunting ducks‚Äù, which implies that he is trying to calm them down by making up an explanation for why this noise has occurred. Based on these clues, it can be inferred that Ali's intention in saying \\"they're hunting ducks\\" was to try and soothe or reassure Hassan and Amir about what had happened, rather than telling them something truthful (A), playing a joke on them (C), or cheering themselves up (D).\\nSo the answer is B: tried to calm the children"},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to find the mean (average) of that list. The mean of a list can be found by summing every number in the list then dividing the result by the size of that list. The output should be rounded to 3 decimal places.\\n\\n[161.155, 137.077, 34.815, 115.989]","target":"112.259","rationale":"The mean of the given list can be calculated as:\\\\n(161.155 + 137.077 + 34.815 + 115.989) / 4 = 448.036 / 4 = 112.259"},{"source":"Premise: um-hum um-hum oh yeah i think when you're in college you kind of you have more of a regular schedule in terms of you can watch every week\\n\\nHypothesis: The hectic college schedule makes it hard to watch things.\\n\\nDoes the premise entail the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise does not entail the hypothesis. The speaker implies that it is easier to watch things when in college because of more regular schedule, so if anything, it should be harder AFTER hectic work schedules are introduced after graduation from college. So answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a question having multiple possible answers in Russian language. And you should choose a most suitable option out of \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", and \\"E\\" based on your commonsense knowledge.\\n\\nQuestion: –ö–∞–∫–æ–≤–∞ –æ—Ç–≤–µ—Ç—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å –º–Ω–æ–≥–∏—Ö –≤–∑—Ä–æ—Å–ª—ã—Ö? \\n Options: A –ø–∏—Ç—å –ø–∏–≤–æ B –ø—Ä–∏–≤–æ–¥–Ω–æ–π –º–µ—Ö–∞–Ω–∏–∑–º C –ø–æ–¥–º–µ—Ç–∞–Ω–∏–µ –ø–æ–ª–∞ D —Ä–∞–±–æ—Ç–∞ E –≤—ã–π—Ç–∏ –∑–∞–º—É–∂ –∑–∞","target":"D","rationale":"In \\"C\\" and \\"D\\", we can find the options which are responsible jobs for adults. However, housework is usually carried out by women, so the answer would be \\"D\\""},{"source":"Romeo and Juliet is a tragedy written by William Shakespeare early in his career about two young star-crossed lovers whose deaths ultimately reconcile their feuding families. It was among Shakespeare's most popular plays during his lifetime and along with Hamlet, is one of his most frequently performed plays. Today, the title characters are regarded as archetypal young lovers.\\n\\nName of the playwright of romeo and juliet?","target":"William Shakespeare","rationale":"The relevant information to answer the above question is: Romeo and Juliet is a tragedy written by William Shakespeare early in his career about two young star-crossed lovers whose deaths ultimately reconcile their feuding families."},{"source":"If \\"Frank was upset with Tom because the toaster he had sold him didn't work.\\", is \\"The toaster Frank had sold him didn't work.\\" correct?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes\\nAnswer:","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states that Frank was upset with Tom because the toaster he had sold him didn't work, but in the statement, it is stated that \\"the toaster Frank had sold him\\" did not work. This does not match up as this would mean that something other than a toaster caused his frustration and anger towards Tom."},{"source":"In this task, you need to reverse all words of a given length in the sentence. The number of letters in a word determine its length. For example, the length of the word \\"apple\\" is 5.\\n\\nSentence: 'woman playing with soccer while children watch intently'. Reverse all words of length '6' in the given sentence.","target":"woman playing with reccos while children watch intently","rationale":"Given the sentence 'woman playing with soccer while children watch intently', there is only one word of length 6, which is 'soccer'. The final output would be 'woman playing with reccos while children watch intently'."},{"source":"Given a pair of words, generate the relation between them. The first word is called the 'concept' and the second word is called the 'relatum' The relation must be one of the following: co-hyponym (coordinate), hypernym, meronym, attribute, event, or random. A coordinate relation indicates that the concept and relatum belong to the same semantic class. A hypernym relation indicates that the relatum is a category of which the concept is a specific instance. A meronym relation implies that relatum is a part/component/organ/member of the concept. An attribute relation is when the relatum is an adjective expressing an attribute of the concept. An event relation holds when the relatum is a verb referring to an action/activity/happening/event that is performed by or with the concept. If the relatum and concept are unrelated, the relation between them is 'random'. Classify your answers into coord, hyper, mero, attri, event, and random.\\n\\nConcept: motorcycle, Relatum: use.","target":"event","rationale":"The relatum is a verb that refers to an activity or event that is performed with the concept. In this case, the relatum refers to the action of riding a motorcycle. Therefore, the relation between 'motorcycle' and 'use' is \\"event\\"."},{"source":"Based on the premise \\"Individual development accounts (IDAs) are special saving accounts for low-income families.\\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"Individual development accounts are special accounts used for food.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"it is not possible to tell","rationale":"The premise only states that IDAs are \\"special saving accounts for low-income families\\" and does not mention what they can be used for. Therefore, it is not possible to tell if the hypothesis is true or false."},{"source":"What was the response? Would you like to see Alita with me in Imax in Canton OH?\\nHow far away is Canton, OH from us? Sure!\\nCanton is about half hour away from us.\\nThat's not to far, sure let's go! I was curious about the movie. What is it entirely about?\\nFrom my understanding the movie is sci fi and about a cyborg girl learning how to adapt to society.\\nInteresting! You know I love sci- fi\\nYes, and I figured this movie would be up your alley.\\nYes! What time does the movie start? I need to be in bed early for my kids going to school early.\\nWould you like to go to the 4:15 or 7:00pm showing?\\nEither or works for me, Lets do the 415 showing so I can get back in time for bed and my kids!\\nOk! no problem. I' excited your going to see it with me. I think it will be a blast!\\nYes! How much would it cost us to go? Are you taking care of it or me?\\nI'll pay unless you want to treat us\\nI'm ok with you paying. My funds are low until next paycheck!\\nNo problem! Ok, we should probably head out soon. Traffic can be bad in Canton.\\nOk! Who's driving?\\nMe! Lets go! We're going to Tinseltown. Reclining seats!\\nAwesome! Do we get snacks?\\nYes we can, wow. Costs us 20.00 for both of us to see this in Imax","target":"Ouch! Well it's worth it I guess. I heard good reviews about the movie.","rationale":"The response is a reasonable reaction to the previous statement, which mentions that it costs $20 for both of them to see the movie. Therefore, the answer is \\"Ouch! Well it's worth it I guess. I heard good reviews about the movie.\\""},{"source":"The input is a conversation between an automated system and a user, followed by a question. The user is looking for suggestions for pubs, restaurants and coffee shops in Cambridge. In the dialogue, the user may provide some criteria for the type of place they want such as price range, cuisine, etc. Similarly, the user may ask details of the place suggested by the system such as phone number, address, etc. The answer of the question has to be a Yes or a No. Given such a dialogue, answer the given question based on the information present in the dialogue.\\n\\nSystem: 'Thank you for calling the Cambridge Information system. Your call will be recorded for research purposes. You may ask for information about a place to eat, such as a restaurant, a pub, or a cafe. How may I help you?'\\nUser: 'yes im looking for an italian restaurant'\\nSystem: 'Let me confirm. You are looking for an italian venue.'\\nUser: 'yes'\\nSystem: 'What kind of price range are you looking for? For example, free, or moderate.'\\nUser: 'expensive'\\nSystem: 'What kind of price range are you looking for? For example, expensive, free, or moderate.'\\nUser: 'expensive'\\nSystem: 'Are you looking for somewhere near a particular venue? For example, Jesus College, Saint Catharine's College, or Trinity College.'\\nUser: 'dont care'\\nSystem: 'The Sorrento is a great restaurant, it serves italian food and it's in the expensive price range.'\\nUser: 'whats the address'\\nSystem: 'The Sorrento is located on 196 Cherry Hinton Road.'\\nUser: 'whats the phone number'\\nSystem: 'The phone number of The Sorrento is 01223243533.'\\nUser: 'whats the postcode'\\nSystem: 'The Sorrento is in the area with the postcode CB1 7AN.'\\nUser: 'thank you good bye'\\nQuestion: 'Did the user mention the area in which they are looking for restaurants?'","target":"No","rationale":"The user asks for an Italian restaurant and later on mentions an expensive price range but does not mention the area in which they are looking for a restaurant. Hence, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"You are given first 5 messages from a series of message exchanges between 2 persons playing the game of Diplomacy which is an American strategic board game. You need to generate the next message. The message should be generated such that it fits the context seen so far. Avoid the text that is (i) tangent to the context, (ii) repeats the context.\\n\\n[\\"So, I'm proposing a northern triple. You, me, and Germany roll down the rest of the board, and then call a three-way draw. It's a good route, because it's a pretty stealthy alliance early on. It looks like an EG taking on France, and Russia just acting normally. How does that sound to you?\\", 'I would hop on board with that if germany does', \\"I'll let you know what I hear from Germany.\\", \\"Ok sounds good. I'll be upfront with you, I had already proposed a western triple but neither have replied so if germany replies to the northern triple first then france can die hehehehe *laughs evily*\\", \\"Any word from the germans yet? I have reason to believe he is already communicating with the Italians and doesn't reply to me\\"]","target":"I haven't gotten anything from anyone but you","rationale":"The answer should be a response to the previous message. The correct option is \\"I haven't gotten anything from anyone but you\\" because it fits the context, and is not out of context or repeating the previous messages."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: What is the last name of the person for whom lifestyle and art were intertwined? from the following article ?\\n\\nThe paintings depict isolated figures enclosed in spaces that are undefined, overwhelmingly claustrophobic, reductive and eerie. Coming early in Bacon's career, they are uneven in quality, but show a clear progression especially in how they utilise and present ideas he was still clearly developing and coming to terms with. Head I (actually begun in the winter of 1948) and Head II show formless pieces of flesh that broadly resemble human heads; they have half-open eyes and a pharynx, though it is positioned much higher than would be expected in a human. Heads III, IV and V show fully formed busts recognisable as men, and are characterised by a haunted atmosphere. These two broad ideas coalesce in Head VI, which is as physiologically tortured as the first two paintings, and as spectral as the middle three. In Head VI the figure has developed and is now shown wearing vestments, the first indication in Bacon's work of the influence of Vel√°zquez, while the focus has become the open mouth and the study of the human scream.Bacon said that chance played a significant role in his work, and that he often approached a canvas without having a clear idea of what might emerge. This was especially the case in the mid- to late 1940s, a period when he was drinking heavily and spending most nights in Soho casinos and poker rooms. The following morning he would often approach his canvas \\"in a bad mood of drinking ... under tremendous hangovers and drink; I sometimes hardly knew what I was doing.\\" He incorporated his appetite for chance into his work: an image often would morph midway through into something quite different from what he had first intended. He actively sought out this freedom and felt it crucial to his progression as an artist. To him, lifestyle and art were intertwined; he said that \\"perhaps the drink helped me to be a bit freer.\\" This is very evident in the 1949 series, which began as a rather morbid study of a collapsed head, but evolved over the six surviving panels into a reworking of Vel√°zquez masterpieces,...","target":"Bacon","rationale":"In the article, it says \\"Coming early in Bacon's career, they are uneven...\\". Therefore, The last name of person for whom lifestyle and art were intertwined is BACON."},{"source":"Given a goal and 2 solutions, choose the most appropriate solution.\\nGoal: Borrow books from the library to read at home.\\n- Solution 1: Take proof that you can read to the library and pass the test. Once you prove you can read, you will get a library card and enjoy reading for free.\\n- Solution 2: Take proof of your address to the library and apply for a card. Once you get a library card, enjoy the free books to read.\\n\\nAnswer by returning either Solution 1 or Solution 2","target":"Solution 2","rationale":"The goal is to borrow books from the library, so we want a solution that involves getting access to those books. Solution 1 involves proving you can read and getting a card, but it doesn't mention anything about borrowing or reading!\\nSolution 2 mentions taking proof of address to get your own library card. This seems like it will give us direct access to our desired books."},{"source":"Q: What is the name of the historical site that site next to Yale's campus?\\n A: The Union League Club of New Haven building, located on Chapel Street, is notable for not only being a historic Beaux-Arts building, but also is built on the site where Roger Sherman's home once stood; George Washington is known to have stayed at the Sherman residence while President in 1789 (one of three times Washington visited New Haven throughout his lifetime).\\n Does the answer correctly answer the question\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The second sentence in the answer only states that George Washington stayed at Sherman's residence and doesn't provide any information on what happened to it after. It is possible that the house has been demolished, so there would be nothing left of it today."},{"source":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\n\\nWhich continent had more seeds for the birds?\\n\\nTwo ancient continents both had a great bird population. At some point in time, the continent of MU experienced a great drought that lasted for several years. The other continent, Lemuria, was unaffected by the drought.\\n\\nHint: A period of very low rainfall occurred while the Grants were on the islands. The drought resulted in fewer seeds for the finches to eat. Birds with smaller beaks could eat only the smaller seeds. Birds with bigger beaks were better off. They could eat seeds of all sizes. Therefore, there was more food available to them. Many of the small-beaked birds died in the drought. More of the big-beaked birds survived and reproduced. Within just a couple of years, the average beak size in the finches increased. This was clearly evolution by natural selection.","target":"Lemuria","rationale":"The passage mentions that a drought occurred in MU, which most likely caused the food supply for birds to decrease. In contrast, Lemuria remained unaffected by the drought and therefore experienced more seeds than MU. Therefore, Lemuria had more seeds for its bird population."},{"source":"The Bolivian President, Evo Morales, 49, has claimed victory after voters ratified a new leftist constitution, granting more power to the country's indigenous majority.  \\"The indigenous farmers, the most marginalized sector throughout the history of the republic, are now recognized as people with the same rights as any citizen. Here begins the new Bolivia. Here we begin to reach true equality,\\" Morales told a crowd in front of the flag-draped balcony of Palacio Quemado in La Paz, the administrative capital of Bolivia.  Ratified with about 60 percent support in a referendum on Sunday based on exit polls, the new constitution lets Morales run for re-election later this year and grants him tighter control over the economy. An official vote count of some 3.8 million registered voters who cast their ballots will be announced February 4.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nEvo Morales' residence is Palacio Quemado in La Paz.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The passage states that Evo Morales made his speech at Palacio Quemado in La Paz and not that it is his residence. So, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to find the mean (average) of that list. The mean of a list can be found by summing every number in the list then dividing the result by the size of that list. The output should be rounded to 3 decimal places.\\n\\n[216.778, 97.568, -38.002]","target":"92.115","rationale":"The mean of the given list is (216.778 + 97.568 + (-38.002)) / 3 = 275.344 / 3 = 91.448, rounded to 3 decimal places is 92.115"},{"source":"Andrew Sadler - who taught French at Rurik Jutting's ¬£6,600-a-term boarding school in Worcestershire in the 1990s - is today revealed by the Mail as a convicted sex offender who was caught in bed with two child prostitutes in Romania A teacher at 'psycho' banker Rurik Jutting‚Äôs prep school is a convicted sex offender who was caught in bed with two child prostitutes, it can be revealed today. Andrew Sadler, who taught French at ¬£6,600-a-term Abberley Hall in Worcestershire when Jutting was a pupil there in the early 1990s, was also a key member of the notorious Paedophile Information Exchange (PIE).\\n@highlight\\nAndrew Sadler taught French at ¬£6k-a-term Abberley Hall in Worcestershire\\n@highlight\\nDescribed as 'quartermaster' of web of paedophiles that co-ordinated abuse\\n@highlight\\nPIE was once linked to senior Labour figures, including Harriet Harman\\n@highlight\\nSadler was later jailed for four years in Romania for sex assaults on boys\\n@highlight\\nBreached court order after letting 15-year-old boy to stay over at his house\\n@highlight\\nThe 64-year-old now lives just 100 yards from another boarding school \\nIt was his ‚Äòjob‚Äô within @placeholder to help co-ordinate other abusers in their ceaseless search for the world‚Äôs most vulnerable children. \\n\\nYou should decide what \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to. Choose between:\\n- Abberley Hall\\n- Andrew Sadler\\n- French\\n- Harriet Harman\\n- Jutting\\n- Labour\\n- Mail\\n- PIE\\n- Paedophile Information Exchange\\n- Romania\\n- Rurik Jutting\\n- Sadler\\n- Worcestershire","target":"PIE","rationale":"The article states that Andrew Sadler was a key member of the notorious Paedophile Information Exchange (PIE) and also mentions his role within it.\\nTherefore, \\"@placeholder\\" can be replaced by \\"PIE\\", which refers to the Paedophile Information Exchange in this context."},{"source":"What was likely said next? Donna, I need you to book a restaurant table that features ultra-luxe fine dining.\\nDo you know what restaurant you want to do?\\nNo, not quite. \\nWhat kind of fine dining are you looking for?\\nI would like to do French restaurant, ideally one that's known for upscale prices. Obviously a five star rating. Maybe a prix fixe menu?\\nI did a quick search. I would suggest French Laundry or Eleven Madison Park.\\nFrench Laundry sounds great. Is it a romantic setting?\\nYes, it's actually famous for its romantic ambiance. \\nExcellent. I'd like to book a table for two at 7 PM for this Friday.\\nSounds good. (Pause.) According to their maitre d', they are actually full-booked for Friday.\\nFull booked?\\nYes. \\nDo they have bar seating we can snag?\\nNope. They only offer indoor restaurant seating. Sorry.\\nWhat does their reservation schedule look like for Saturday?","target":"They have two options available right now.","rationale":"Since the human agent is unable to book a table for Donna at French Laundry, he/she will be looking into alternative options available. Thus, the most reasonable response would be \\"They have two options available right now.\\""},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Mary went to the bedroom. Fact 2- John journeyed to the bathroom. Fact 3- Sandra journeyed to the hallway. Fact 4- John journeyed to the garden. Fact 5- John journeyed to the bathroom. Fact 6- Sandra journeyed to the garden. Fact 7- Sandra went back to the bedroom. Fact 8- Daniel travelled to the bathroom. Fact 9- John went to the office. Fact 10- Mary moved to the office. Question: Where is Sandra? Answer: bedroom","target":"Fact 7","rationale":"The answer to the question is \\"bedroom\\", which can be inferred from Fact 7."},{"source":"Does the sentence \\"From 1912 until 1918 he was the chairman of the board of scientific advisers to the Eugenics Record Office associated with Cold Spring Harbor Laboratory in New York, and regularly attended meetings.\\" answer the question \\"In 1921 the American Museum of Natural History hosted what event?\\"\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The passage talks about the tenure of Charles Davenport as chairman of the board, and does not mention anything about events hosted by the American Museum of Natural History in 1921. Therefore, it can be inferred that this sentence doesn't answer our question."},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that has the most similar style to the prompt. Style is defined as the tone, word choice, grammar, and sentence structure throughout the prompt-completion pair. If a prompt is colloquial, then the completion should also be colloquial, as opposed to a completion that is encyclopedic or overly formal. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: What if weekend services are not \\"The Game\\", but preparation for \\"The \\nCompletion A: Game\\". That's when you should start asking yourself the question, \\"How do I organize my day while working towards meeting my goals while doing this project \\nCompletion B: Game\\"? If the next season of \\"The Game\\" is a season of training in preparation for \\"The Game\\"? If they train in the off","target":"Completion A","rationale":"The prompt has a colloquial and informal style, while the completion B is overly formal and encyclopedic. Completion A matches the style of the prompt as it continues in a colloquial and informal tone."},{"source":"In the shadow of the Seattle Space Needle, almost alien crystalline forms wrap their deft tendrils through the Chihuly Garden and Glass.\\nEvery single petal, bowl, stem and branch of cascading glass has been handblown under the guidance of Washington State native Dale Chihuly (in fact he grew up in nearby Tacoma), and we couldn‚Äôt quite believe our eyes.\\nHaving discovered this exhibit through the magic of Jaime‚Äôs instagram (she‚Äôs a self-named Angloyankophile who grew up in Seattle before moving to London) I knew we would have to visit.\\nMy photos don‚Äôt do the undulating forms any kind of justice; but they might just convey the incredible scale of the exhibition.\\nI‚Äôd always been curious to learn more about Chihuly, after being introduced to his incredible sculpture suspended over the V&A Museum information desk, a glowing confection of green and white glass whisps.\\nIn 1968, after receiving a Fulbright Fellowship, he went to work at the Venini glass factory in Venice, observing the team approach to blowing glass, which is critical to the way he works today. In 1971, Chihuly cofounded Pilchuck Glass School in Washington State. With this international glass center, Chihuly has led the avant-garde in the development of glass as a fine art.\\nHis work is included in more than 200 museum collections worldwide. He has been the recipient of many awards, including twelve honorary doctorates and two fellowships from the National Endowment for the Arts. He has also lost an eye to his passion, and now mostly directs the sculpture design and assembly.\\nIt was truly amazing.\\nIn 1999, Chihuly started an ambitious exhibition, Chihuly in the Light of Jerusalem; where more than 1 million visitors attended the Tower of David Museum to view his installations. In 2001, the Victoria and Albert Museum in London curated the exhibition Chihuly at the V&A. Chihuly‚Äôs lifelong fascination for glasshouses has grown into a series of exhibitions within botanical settings.\\nHow long did it take for Chihuly to create the sculpture suspended over the V&A museum?\\n\\nA. probably days\\n\\nB. probably weeks\\n\\nC. not enough information\\n\\nD. probably months to years","target":"D","rationale":"The question asks how long it took Chihuly to create the sculpture suspended over V&A Museum, so we need to go back and read some relevant text in order to find clues that may answer this question.\\nIn paragraph 2, we learn \\"Chihuly has led the avant-garde in the development of glass as a fine art.\\" It shows he's been working on his own style for quite a while now; therefore, option A cannot be correct because days are too short for him to make an artistic piece like this one. Besides, since it is mentioned later that there were more than 1 million visitors attending Tower of David Museum just see his installations (paragraph 3), he must have spent considerable time creating such pieces before they got famous enough for people around the world noticing"},{"source":"Premise: Amusing roadside Americana is basically a bad restaurant in the shape of a big chicken.\\n\\nHypothesis: Americana is amusing but it is a bad restaurant because their food is bland.\\n\\nDoes the premise entail the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"it is not possible to tell","rationale":"The premise only states that Americana is \\"amusing roadside\\" and a bad restaurant in the shape of a big chicken. It does not mention anything about whether their food is bland or not, which would be required to support the hypothesis as stated. Therefore, it is not possible to tell if they are related."},{"source":"Two villages were focused mostly on mining operation. Brown village extracted fossil fuels such as coal from their mountains, while Yellow village was mostly focused on extracting gold the old fashioned way.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich village has more of an impact on global climate change?","target":"Brown","rationale":"Based on the information provided, Brown village is more likely to have a greater impact on global climate change because of their focus on fossil fuels such as coal. Fossil fuel combustion produces carbon dioxide which contributes to greenhouse gases and can cause environmental damage in the form of air pollution. Whereas Yellow village‚Äôs mining operations are focused only extracting gold by hand so they would not be producing any significant amount of CO2 emissions or other harmful particulates that contribute to air pollution."},{"source":"Though hooded and cloaked, Nicolette trembled. The chill of the January afternoon pierced her through, but it was fear, more than the cold, that made her limbs shake. Having just crossed over to the Left Bank, she glanced back over her shoulder and saw the towers and spires of the royal palace across the Seine. She felt as if hidden eyes there were watching her. Could anyone on the palace wall have seen her walk over the Petit-Pont?\\nNot Amalric. He was still in the south, the King having just appointed him seneschal for Beziers and the surrounding country. But he had so many agents in Paris and allies at court. Except for Agnes, all the servants in the Gobignon town house were loyal to him. His aunt, Queen Blanche, was forever praising him to all who would listen. If Nicolette were involved in scandal, the White Queen would be furious, and would see to it that word reached Amalric. And if indeed he found out about her meeting the troubadour? Just a message, a song, let alone a meeting like this one, could mean death for her and Orlando.\\nI should turn around right now, cross this bridge, and run back to the palace. The streets of the Latin Quarter were crawling with ruffians and criminals - it was insane for her to be walking here alone after sunset. The sight of the small knife she carried under her cloak might deter an attacker, but then she would be discovered.\\nIf I screamed for help, the whole palace would find out. Blanche would demand to know why I was here. No, she thought, her blood turning to ice, she would know why.\\nBut those eyes of his? to look into them again, was that not worth any risk?\\nShe stood, vacillating, in the shadows by a wooden house that overhung the Rue Saint-Jacques. I must see Orlando, she thought. Over a year now, and I have not been able to forget him. She longed just to be alone with him and have him take her in his arms.\\nNicolette had been out of the castle for:\\n- A short amount of time\\n- not enough information\\n- Decades\\n- A year","target":"A short amount of time","rationale":"The passage mentions that Nicolette was out of the castle after sunset, which suggests a short amount of time. The other choices do not align with this context and can be eliminated.\\nSo, answer is A short amount of time."},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: Is it possible to conclude that \\"A dark-haired woman wearing glasses, a red jacket and jeans sitting on a bench on the sidewalk.\\" if \\"The woman has blond hair.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no...I think the answer is","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence describes a dark haired woman wearing glasses, red jacket and jeans sitting on the bench. The second sentence contradicts this by saying that she has blond hair. Since these two cannot be true together, it is not possible to conclude from any of the statements in the premise what type of clothing or color of hair was worn by women who were seen near benches while they were being observed during office hours."},{"source":"Many ancient civilizations alloyed metals for purely aesthetic purposes. In ancient Egypt and Mycenae, gold was often alloyed with copper to produce red-gold, or iron to produce a bright burgundy-gold. Gold was often found alloyed with silver or other metals to produce various types of colored gold. These metals were also used to strengthen each other, for more practical purposes. Copper was often added to silver to make sterling silver, increasing its strength for use in dishes, silverware, and other practical items. Quite often, precious metals were alloyed with less valuable substances as a means to deceive buyers. Around 250 BC, Archimedes was commissioned by the king to find a way to check the purity of the gold in a crown, leading to the famous bath-house shouting of \\"Eureka!\\" upon the discovery of Archimedes' principle.\\nWhat is the paragraph about?","target":"Alloy","rationale":"The paragraph is about the topic of alloying metals, particularly gold. This can be seen from examples such as copper being added to silver and iron to produce colored gold in ancient Egypt and Mycenae respectively. The discovery of Archimedes' principle also involved an attempt at finding a way to check the purity of gold in a crown.\\nThus, based on this information, we can conclude that \\"Alloy\\" would be the most appropriate answer for this question."},{"source":"You will be given a trivia clue, and the category it belongs to. You should answer with the best answer that belongs in the category and is described by the clue. For simplicity, answers should be in all lower cased letters.\\n\\nCategory: OPERETTAS \\nClue: The subject of this 1879 work may have been inspired by unauthorized productions of the creators' original works","target":"the pirates of penzance","rationale":"The question mentions that the work was inspired by the creators' original works. This indicates that the authors of this work were also authors of another famous work. The only option here is \\"the pirates of penzance\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an answer, and your task is to generate a reasonable question for that answer.\\n\\nI went to Oxford University.","target":"Did you go to college abroad?","rationale":"The answer says that the person went to Oxford University. This could mean that the person went to college abroad, and so a reasonable question is \\"Did you go to college abroad?\\""},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Mary went to the hallway. Fact 2- Daniel went to the bathroom. Fact 3- Mary went to the bedroom. Fact 4- Mary went to the kitchen. Fact 5- Daniel moved to the garden. Fact 6- Daniel went to the office. Question: Where is Daniel? Answer: office","target":"Fact 6","rationale":"The answer to the question is \\"office\\" and it can be found in Fact 6, so this is a supporting fact."},{"source":"Exercise: Extract from the text the correct entity that \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to.\\n\\nCompared with the Japanese kimono and Chinese cheongsam, Korea's traditional dress -- known as hanbok, and worn by women and men -- has remained under the international fashion radar. So much so that when Lee Young Hee, among South Korea's most renowned hanbok designers, showed her collection in Paris for the first time in 1993, most of the fashion press alluded to her silhouettes as \\"kimonos\\" -- to the horror of both the designer herself and everyone back in Seoul. It's only relatively recently that hanbok has been gaining widespread attention, with top foreign designers looking to hanbok for inspiration in the past few years.\\n@highlight\\nHanbok, Korean traditional dress, is always customized\\n@highlight\\nFrom measurements to fittings, final production takes around two weeks\\n@highlight\\nCarolina Herrera, Giorgio Armani and Miuccia Prada are hanbok fans\\nThese days, @placeholder themselves tend to break out the hanbok only for special occasions such as weddings, funerals, first birthdays and major family gatherings.","target":"Korean","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"Korean\\", because the passage says that hanbok, a traditional dress worn by both men and women in Korea, was previously mistaken for kimonos. This means it has Korean roots.\\n\\n\\n\\"\\"Hanbok\\"\\", or Korean traditional clothes are known to be elegant and functional with long history of over 5 000 years.\\""},{"source":"Fill in the response. DIALOG:\\nAre there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n- Mandela was portrayed by Alfre Woodard in the 1987 HBO TV movie, Mandela.\\n- Did the 1987 film about Winnie Madikizela-Mandela win any awards?\\n-","target":"Woodard earned both a CableACE Award and an NAACP Image Award for her performance, as did costar Danny Glover, who portrayed Nelson Mandela","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"Woodard earned both a CableACE Award and an NAACP Image Award for her performance, as did costar Danny Glover, who portrayed Nelson Mandela.\\" This is the best response to the question \\"Did the 1987 film about Winnie Madikizela-Mandela win any awards?\\" because it directly addresses the question and provides information on which awards were won by which stars."},{"source":"In this task, you will be presented with a question having multiple possible answers in Russian language. And you should choose a most suitable option out of \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", and \\"E\\" based on your commonsense knowledge.\\n\\nQuestion: –ö–∞–∫—É—é –æ–±—ã—á–Ω–æ –≤—ã–±–æ—Ä–Ω—É—é –¥–æ–ª–∂–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å –º–æ–∂–Ω–æ –Ω–∞–∑–≤–∞—Ç—å –ª–∞—Å–∫–æ–π? \\n Options: A –∑–∞ –¥–≤–µ—Ä—å–º–∏ B –≥–æ—Å—É–¥–∞—Ä—Å—Ç–≤–µ–Ω–Ω–∞—è –¥–æ–ª–∂–Ω–æ—Å—Ç—å C –í–∞—à–∏–Ω–≥—Ç–æ–Ω –æ–∫—Ä—É–≥ –ö–æ–ª—É–º–±–∏—è D –ø–ª–∞–≤–∞—Ç–µ–ª—å–Ω—ã–π –±–∞—Å—Å–µ–π–Ω E –∫—É—Ä—è—Ç–Ω–∏–∫","target":"B","rationale":"The word \\"–ª–∞—Å–∫–æ–π\\" is a Russian word meaning \\"a favor\\". From the five options, only option B could be considered an easy job that someone might give as a favor. Option A is not a position. Option C is simply the name of a place. Option D also refers to physical place, and E refers to an animal pen."},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the last name of the person who is killed? , can you please find it? \\n\\nKelly is a prostitute who shows up in the small town of Grantville, just one more burg in a long string of quick stops on the run after being chased out of the big city by her former pimp. She engages in a quick tryst with local police captain Griff, who then tells her to stay out of his town and refers her to a cat-house just across the state line.\\nInstead, she decides to give up her illicit lifestyle, becoming a nurse at a hospital for handicapped children. Griff doesn't trust reformed prostitutes, however, and continues trying to run her out of town.\\nKelly falls in love with J.L. Grant, the wealthy scion of the town's founding family, an urbane sophisticate, and Griff's best friend. After a dream-like courtship where even Kelly's admission of her past can't deter Grant, the two decide to marry. It is only after Kelly is able to finally convince Griff that she truly loves Grant and has given up prostitution for good that he agrees to be their best man.\\nShortly before the wedding, Kelly arrives at Grant's mansion, only to find him on the verge of molesting a small girl. As he grinningly tries to persuade her to marry him, arguing that she too is a deviant, the only one who can understand him, and that he loves her, Kelly kills him by striking him in the head with a phone receiver. Jailed, and under heavy interrogation from Griff, she must convince him and the town that she is telling the truth about Grant's death.\\nAs Kelly tries to exonerate herself, one disappointment follows another, and enemies old and new parade through the jailhouse to defame her. In despair, she is at last able to find Grant's victim and prove her innocence.","target":"Grant","rationale":"The answer is Grant, which can be found in the last paragraph of the article."},{"source":"Given an entity as input, output another entity which is part of the input entity. These are entities of meronym. In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., output entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., input entity).\\n\\nparasite","target":"gland","rationale":"A parasite is an organism that lives in or on another organism and gets food or other things it needs from the host. A gland is a part of a parasite's body that produces some substance. Therefore, gland is a meronym of parasite."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers. A list is shown by two brackets and comma-separated numbers inside, like: [1,2,3]. You should remove all of the even numbers from the list. If every number in the input list is even an empty list should be returned. Zero should be counted as an even number.\\n\\n[37, 2, 195, 5, 169, 40, 111]","target":"[37, 195, 5, 169, 111]","rationale":"After removing the even numbers, the list will be [37, 195, 5, 169, 111]"},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What is the first name of the person who recounts a lecture?\\n\\nWealthy American businessman Robert Talbot owns a villa on the Ligurian coast, where he and his Roman mistress Lisa Fellini spend September of each year. When Robert moves up his annual visit to July and calls her en route from Milano, she cancels her wedding to Englishman Spencer and rushes to meet him. Upon his arrival at the villa, Robert discovers that, in his absence, his major domo, Maurice Clavell, has turned the villa into a hotel, currently hosting a group of teenage girls, including Sandy, and their chaperone, Margaret Allison. Their departure is delayed when Margaret slips on the cork of a champagne bottle opened by Robert and is forced to spend a day in the hospital. Four teenage boys who irritated Robert on the drive to his villa, including Tony, set up camp right outside of the villa and begin courting the girls.\\nRobert chaperones the girls on a sightseeing tour and to a music club. He dances with each of the girls and appeals to their virtues, stressing the importance of chastity. Trying to get Robert inebriated, the boys end up drunk themselves. Sandy revives Tony, but slaps him when he makes a pass at her. She then recounts the lecture received earlier to Lisa, who gets infuriated over Robert's double standards. The next morning, she leaves to get back together with Spencer. A sobered-up Tony apologizes to Robert.","target":"Sandy","rationale":"The paragraph is talking about the wealthy American businessman Robert Talbot. The first name of person who recounts a lecture - ‚ÄúSandy‚Äù"},{"source":"What is the following passage about?\\nUN forces retreated to Suwon in the west, Wonju in the center, and the territory north of Samcheok in the east, where the battlefront stabilized and held. The PVA had outrun its logistics capability and thus were unable to press on beyond Seoul as food, ammunition, and mat√©riel were carried nightly, on foot and bicycle, from the border at the Yalu River to the three battle lines. In late January, upon finding that the PVA had abandoned their battle lines, General Ridgway ordered a reconnaissance-in-force, which became Operation Roundup (5 February 1951). A full-scale X Corps advance proceeded, which fully exploited the UN Command's air superiority, concluding with the UN reaching the Han River and recapturing Wonju.","target":"Korean War","rationale":"The passage is about the Korean War, which began when North Korea invaded South Korea. The UN forces retreated to Suwon in the west and other places before moving eastward again."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Are serotonin 7 Receptor Variants Associated with Response to Second-Generation Antipsychotics in Japanese Schizophrenia Patients?\\nAnswer: Our results show that HTR7 variants are not related to the overall improvement in schizophrenia symptoms.","target":"no","rationale":"The study shows that the serotonin 7 receptor variants are not related to the overall improvement in schizophrenia symptoms. This indicates that the HTR7 variants are not associated with response to second generation antipsychotics in Japanese schizophrenia patients. Therefore, 'no' is an appropriate response."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a short passage that may convey stereotype, anti-stereotype, or is unrelated. A stereotype is an over-generalized belief about a particular group of people. An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common stereotype. The passage is unrelated if it does not convey a stereotype or anti-stereotype. You are expected to classify the passage into three classes: stereotype, anti-stereotype, and unrelated.\\n\\nPassage: The braunsweiger nature of the civil servant allowed him to get close to those that he served in more ways than one.","target":"Unrelated","rationale":"The passage talks about the nature of a civil servant, who is able to get close to those that he serves in more ways than one. The passage does not generalise all civil servants, and hence it could not be considered as a stereotype. Further, there is no mention that counters any common stereotypes about civil servants, and hence it could also not be considered as an anti-stereotype. Therefore the best answer would be 'Unrelated'."},{"source":"Given a comment text in Malayalam, classify the comment into one of these categories (i) Hope speech, (ii) Not Hope Speech or (iii) Not in Expected Language. A hope speech contains content that is encouraging, positive or supportive contents and talks about equality, diversity or inclusion\\n\\nGood  message","target":"Not in Expected Language","rationale":"This is a comment in Malayalam which is one of the 23 languages from the Indian constitution. The expected language for this task is English. So, we classify it as Not in Expected Language."},{"source":"Given an object and a part, decide whether the object has that part. For example if you are asked 'gun has barrel?', you need to decide if a gun has a barrel as one of its components or parts, indicating 1 or 0 as your answer respectively. All sentences strictly follow the template 'object has part?.'\\n\\nfighter has rest?","target":"0","rationale":"The word \\"fighter\\" refers to a person or animal that engages in combat and the word \\"rest\\" refers to being free from action. The two words do not have an associated relationship and therefore, the answer is 0 (false)."},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Unequal distribution of the hormone auxin in plants helps to regulate the direction of plant growth. Which of the following is accomplished by plants in regulating the distribution of auxin?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: pollination of flowers\\n \\n- B: transportation of nutrients\\n \\n- C: discouraging predation\\n \\n- D: responding to the environment","target":"D","rationale":"The correct answer is D. \\nUnequal distribution of the hormone auxin in plants helps to regulate the direction of plant growth. This process occurs naturally as part of a response to environmental cues, for example sunlight or gravity. Therefore, B and C are incorrect because these processes do not influence how auxin distributes itself within a plant cell; A is also incorrect since pollination has nothing to do with this process, rather it refers to fertilization that triggers sexual reproduction in flowering plants (angiosperms)."},{"source":"Q: What is the term for the gases that surround a planet?\\n\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- hemisphere\\n\\n- galaxy\\n\\n- biosphere\\n\\n- the atmosphere\\n\\nA:","target":"the atmosphere","rationale":"The atmosphere is a layer of gases that surround the Earth. The correct answer is therefore, ‚Äúthe atmosphere‚Äù."},{"source":"Question: \\"What feature is handicap friendly?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"The Delhi Metro is a rapid transit system serving New Delhi, Delhi, Gurgaon, Faridabad, Noida, and Ghaziabad in the National Capital Region of India. Delhi Metro is the world's 12th largest metro system in terms of length. Delhi Metro was India's first modern public transportation system, which had revolutionised travel by providing a fast, reliable, safe, and comfortable means of transport. The network consists of six lines with a total length of 189.63 kilometres (117.83 miles) with 142 stations, of which 35 are underground, five are at-grade, and the remainder are elevated. All stations have escalators, elevators, and tactile tiles to guide the visually impaired from station entrances to trains. It has a combination of elevated, at-grade, and underground lines, and uses both broad gauge and standard gauge rolling stock. Four types of rolling stock are used: Mitsubishi-ROTEM Broad gauge, Bombardier MOVIA, Mitsubishi-ROTEM Standard gauge, and CAF Beasain Standard gauge.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"tactile tiles","rationale":"The question asks about a feature that is handicap friendly. The context mentions tactile tiles, which are used to help guide the visually impaired from station entrances to trains. Based on this information alone, it can be inferred that tactile tiles would be considered as being \\"handicap friendly\\"."},{"source":"If \\"A man or woman jumping for joy after accomplishing their hike to the top of the canyon.\\" does that mean that \\"The person is walking outdoors.\\"?\\n\\n[Options]\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"A person who is walking outdoors cannot be jumping for joy."},{"source":"Which animal lacks the ability to see by sensing light?\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- Southern cave crayfish\\n- lobster\\n- cod\\n- salmon","target":"Southern cave crayfish","rationale":"The question is asking about an animal that lacks the ability to see by sensing light. The answer must be one of the animals from this list: Southern cave crayfish, lobster, cod and salmon.\\nIn order to choose between these four options for a correct answer you will need more information about each type of animal in addition to what has been provided above . To do so , we recommend searching online using either Wikipedia or Google ."},{"source":"Read the following context and answer the question.\\nContext: SEOUL ‚Äî South Korea is looking into developing and financing economic projects with North Korea that could take effect if a nuclear deal is reached with the United States.\\nSouth Korean Finance Minister Kim Dong-yeon said on Wednesday the government was ‚Äúinternally carrying out preparations‚Äù to organize, finance and implement possible inter-Korea projects. But he also emphasized that Seoul would first seek support from the international community for any North Korean development projects, and would only proceed if the U.S. -North Korea summit, expected to be held in late May or June, produces a joint denuclearization agreement.\\nNorth Korea is under tough sanctions imposed by the U.N. Security Council for its nuclear weapons and missiles tests, including accelerated efforts in the last two years to develop a long-range nuclear missile that could potentially target the U.S. mainland. The international sanctions ban an estimated 90 percent of the country‚Äôs external trade.\\nSeeking sanctions relief is considered a key motivating factor in North Korean leader Kim Jong Un‚Äôs diplomatic pivot this year to suspend further provocative missile and nuclear tests, and to engage in talks to dismantle his nuclear arsenal.\\nBut easing sanctions would make it more difficult to enforce the North‚Äôs denuclearization promises.\\n‚ÄúOnce the sanctions are lifted, North Korea will gain autonomy over its trade, and considering its low labor costs and skilled workforce, I think the North Korean economy would gain power again,‚Äù said Shin Beom-chul, the director of Center for Security and Unification at the Asan Institute for Policy Studies in Seoul.\\nU.S. President Donald Trump has insisted he will keep sanctions in place until North Korea completely dismantles its nuclear program.\\nSouth Korea, however, is considering a range of economic incentives to encourage Kim to follow through on a nuclear deal with Trump. But these investments are prohibited by the U.N. sanctions and would require a Security Council exemption to proceed.\\nAt the recent...\\nQuestion: What does Kim Jung un probably think of Minister Dong -yeon's clothing?\\nAnswer:","target":"not enough information","rationale":"The context is about the South Korean government‚Äôs efforts to develop plans for economic projects with North Korea while not violating U.N. sanctions that are in place against North Korea, and how those efforts will be impacted by a potential summit between President Trump and Kim Jung Un of North Korea where they could reach an agreement on denuclearization of the region. There is no information provided within this text about Minister Dong-yeon's clothing or what Kim Jung un probably thought about it so we cannot answer confidently as \\"enough information\\" was not given . Therefore, ‚Äúnot enough information‚Äù would be the best choice from among these options since none of them can be proven based upon the content presented above."},{"source":"What is the following passage about?\\nIn 1955, von Neumann became a commissioner of the AEC. He accepted this position and used it to further the production of compact hydrogen bombs suitable for Intercontinental ballistic missile delivery. He involved himself in correcting the severe shortage of tritium and lithium 6 needed for these compact weapons, and he argued against settling for the intermediate range missiles that the Army wanted. He was adamant that H-bombs delivered into the heart of enemy territory by an ICBM would be the most effective weapon possible, and that the relative inaccuracy of the missile wouldn't be a problem with an H-bomb. He said the Russians would probably be building a similar weapon system, which turned out to be the case. Despite his disagreement with Oppenheimer over the need for a crash program to develop the hydrogen bomb, he testified on the latter's behalf at the 1954 Oppenheimer security hearing, at which he asserted that Oppenheimer was loyal, and praised him for his helpfulness once the program went ahead.","target":"John von Neumann","rationale":"The passage is about John von Neumann, who was a commissioner of the AEC. It describes his involvement in correcting the shortage of tritium and lithium 6 needed for compact hydrogen bombs suitable for Intercontinental ballistic missile delivery; it also mentions that he argued against settling for intermediate range missiles preferred by the Army. \\nIt further goes on to describe him as being adamant (i.e., very determined) that H-bombs delivered into enemy territory would be an effective weapon system and should not be abandoned due to their inaccuracy which wouldn't matter with an H-bomb anyway. He believed Russia too would probably develop a similar weapon system, which turned out to be true given they did build one later - although this isn't mentioned explicitly in the text itself but can definitely be inferred"},{"source":"Answer by taking a quote from the following article:\\n\\nMartin Brodeur was born on May 6, 1972, in Montreal. He was one of five children of Denis and Mireille Brodeur. Denis played in the 1956 Olympics for Team Canada and won a bronze medal. After his playing career, Denis was a longtime photographer for the Montreal Canadiens.\\n\\nIn the 1991-92 NHL season, Brodeur spent most of his time with Saint-Hyacinthe in the QMJHL, but was called up to the NHL on an emergency basis for four games when New Jersey goaltenders Chris Terreri and Craig Billington became injured. Brodeur won his NHL debut against the Boston Bruins, 4-2, and played in one playoff game that season. Brodeur spent the following season with the Utica Devils of the American Hockey League (AHL). However, in the 1993-94 season, Brodeur returned to the NHL permanently and gained recognition when he won the Calder Trophy, an annual award for the best rookie in the NHL. He led the Devils to the second-best record in the league and the Eastern Conference Finals in the playoffs, where they lost to the New York Rangers in seven games. He finished 2nd in goals against average (GAA) (2.40) and 4th in save percentage (.915) in 47 games played during the regular season, helping him eventually land the starting job over Terreri.  In the 1994-95 NHL season, which was shortened to 48 games due to an extended lockout, the Devils finished tied for 9th overall, 5th in their conference. With the leadership of Brodeur, they defeated the Boston Bruins in the 1st round, shutting them out in three of their four wins. In the second round against the Pittsburgh Penguins, Brodeur gave up only nine goals and helped the Devils defeat the Penguins in five games. In the third round, the Devils defeated the Philadelphia Flyers in six games, giving them their first Stanley Cup Final appearance in franchise history, against the heavily favoured Detroit Red Wings. The strong play of Brodeur and the Devils' \\"trap\\" method of defence made the series lopsided in favour of New Jersey, who swept the Red Wings 4 games to 0 while holding them to just seven goals in four games. Brodeur won a Stanley Cup in only his second full season in the NHL. After the victory, he was quoted as saying:  In the last game against Detroit, the time from ten minutes left to one minute left was probably the longest nine minutes of my life. But from one to zero was probably the greatest time I've ever had. I didn't want the clock to run out. It was such a great feeling: people crying in the stands, people jumping up and down, people cheering. Guys couldn't even sit up on the bench. It was probably the best minute of my life.\\n\\nwhat happened in 1994 season","target":"In the 1994-95 NHL season, which was shortened to 48 games due to an extended lockout, the Devils finished tied for 9th overall, 5th in their conference.","rationale":"In the 1994-95 NHL season, which was shortened to 48 games due to an extended lockout, the Devils finished tied for 9th overall, 5th in their conference. With the leadership of Brodeur, they defeated the Boston Bruins in the 1st round and shut them out three times. In other words it can be said that with his team's efforts they had a very satisfying result that year."},{"source":"Answer this question:\\n\\nwho is the sandman in spider man 3??","target":"Flint Marko","rationale":"Flint Marko is the Sandman in Spider-Man 3."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the general math. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: the divisor is 21 , the quotient is 14 and the remainder is 7 . what is the dividend ? \\nOptions: a ) 201 , b ) 394 , c ) 302 , d ) 301 , e ) 294","target":"d","rationale":"Dividend = (Quotient * Divisor) + Remainder\\\\n= (14 * 21) + 7\\\\n= 301"},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the physics. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: recently , i decided to walk down an escalator of a tube station . i did some quick calculation in my mind . i found that if i walk down 20 \` \` 6 steps , i require thirty seconds to reach the bottom . however , if i am able to step down thirty \` \` 4 stairs , i would only require eighteen seconds to get to the bottom . if the time is measured from the moment the top step begins to descend to the time i step off the last step at the bottom ? \\nOptions: a ) 43 , b ) 44 , c ) 45 , d ) 40 , e ) 46","target":"e","rationale":"The time required to step down 20 steps is 30 seconds. The time required to step down an additional 14 steps is 18 seconds. So the total time would be (30 + 18) = 48 seconds."},{"source":"Generate a correct and concise answer for the question based on the words in the context.\\n\\nContext : Harald Offerdal of the Labour Party was elected mayor of Balestrand for the 2011--2015 term. \\nQuestion : Which person was the head of government of Balestrand?","target":"Harald Offerdal","rationale":"There is a statement in the context that states \\"Harald Offerdal of the Labour Party was elected mayor of Balestrand for the 2011--2015 term.\\"  Therefore, we can infer that Harald Offerdal was the head of government of Balestrand."},{"source":"Sentence: \\"Bill sent a package London.\\"\\nWould a linguist rate this sentence to be acceptable linguistically?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"Bill,\\" the verb is \\"sent,\\" and the object is \\"a package London.\\" Therefore, it would be considered linguistically acceptable by a linguist."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[-83.355 -18.677  -1.362]","target":"-83.355","rationale":"The element with the largest absolute value in the given list is -83.355, which has an absolute value of 83.355. The absolute value for all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 83.355. However, we need to return the value of the element before applying it's absolute value. So, answer will be -83.355"},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nBenjamin entered the garage. Liam entered the garage. The green_pepper is in the red_box. Benjamin moved the green_pepper to the green_treasure_chest. Benjamin entered the porch. Liam entered the porch. The tomato is in the green_crate. Benjamin moved the tomato to the green_suitcase. Benjamin entered the TV_room. Avery entered the TV_room. The pear is in the red_suitcase. Benjamin moved the pear to the blue_box. Benjamin is in the TV_room. Liam entered the TV_room. The pear is in the blue_box. Benjamin moved the pear to the red_suitcase. Where was the pear at the beginning?","target":"red_suitcase","rationale":"The pear was in the red_suitcase before Benjamin moved it to the blue_box."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an anaphor number agreement or as an incorrect representation. An anaphor is an expression whose interpretation depends upon another expression. Anaphor number agreement is a restriction where a phrase agrees with the preceeding expression: plurals match plurals or singular expressions match singular expressions. In this task a valid representation of anaphor number agreement should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an anaphor number agreement will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence where the subject and self-referencing nouns match plurality. An incorrect representation is a sentence in which the subject and self-referencing noun's plurality do not match.\\n\\nMost teachers have disliked itself.","target":"bad","rationale":"The subject of the sentence is \\"Most teachers\\", which is plural. However, the reflexive pronoun \\"itself\\" is singular and does not agree with the plurality of the subject. A correct representation would be \\"Most teachers have disliked themselves\\", where the plural subject \\"teachers\\" agrees with the plural reflexive pronoun \\"themselves\\".\\nTherefore, This sentence is an incorrect representation of anaphor number agreement and should be denoted as 'bad'."},{"source":"yeah exactly jump at it\\n\\nDoes it follow that \\"I don't think you should jump at it.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The statement \\"yeah exactly jump at it\\" is a positive action: to begin jumping. This contradicts the negative sentiment in the second sentence, which indicates that jumping would be an unwise decision. Therefore, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Answer a question about this article:\\nGaddafi briefly studied History at the University of Libya in Benghazi, before dropping out to join the military. Despite his police record, in 1963 he began training at the Royal Military Academy, Benghazi, alongside several like-minded friends from Misrata. The armed forces offered the only opportunity for upward social mobility for underprivileged Libyans, and Gaddafi recognised it as a potential instrument of political change. Under Idris, Libya's armed forces were trained by the British military; this angered Gaddafi, who viewed the British as imperialists, and accordingly he refused to learn English and was rude to the British officers, ultimately failing his exams. British trainers reported him for insubordination and abusive behaviour, stating their suspicion that he was involved in the assassination of the military academy's commander in 1963. Such reports were ignored and Gaddafi quickly progressed through the course.\\nDuring his time in college, what did Gaddafi study?","target":"History","rationale":"From the given context, it is clear that Gaddafi studied History at the University of Libya in Benghazi."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nNeonomicon is a four-issue comic book limited series written by Alan Moore and illustrated by Jacen Burrows, published by American company Avatar Press in 2010. The story is a sequel to Moore's previous story \\"Alan Moore's The Courtyard\\" and part of H. P. Lovecraft's Cthulhu Mythos. Moore later continued the sequence with his comic \\"Providence\\".\\n\\nHypothesis: Alan Moore has not worked professionally with Jacen Burrows.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The context tells us that Alan Moore has worked with Jacen Burrows to create the four issue comic book \\"Neonomicon\\". Thus, we know they have collaborated professionally. It is therefore not true that this is the first time they have done so. So the answer is 'No'."},{"source":"What is a question that would give the following answer?\\nAnswer: 20th;\\nQuestion:","target":"What century did Nasser rule in?","rationale":"The context suggests that Nasser ruled from the 1950s until his death in 1970, which means he was ruling during the 20th century.\\nTherefore, a question whose answer is \\"20th\\" would be: What century did Nasser rule in?"},{"source":"I've always wondered: Which country will host the Olympics in 2016?","target":"Brazilian Republic","rationale":"The answer is \\"Brazilian Republic\\".\\nThis question can be answered by combining multiple pieces of information. We need to know which Olympics are going to take place in 2016, and then look up the location for that event."},{"source":"Given a passage as input, answer with the category to which the passage belongs. There are 5 categories - Sports and Fitness, Home and Garden, Hobbies and Crafts, Food and Entertaining, Cars & Other Vehicles. The answer should be one of the categories based on words from the passage which closely belong to the category.\\n\\nRemove the faceplate from the console. Straighten out a length of paper clip as best you can. Place the long end of the paper clip in the hole on the very left. Using a flashlight, place the end of the paper clip in the teeth on the right side of the gears and push.Finished.","target":"Hobbies and Crafts","rationale":"The passage discusses how to use a paper clip to open the disc tray of an Xbox. This is important information for people who own an Xbox, since it will allow them to play games if they lose or break their game controller. Therefore, this passage belongs in the category \\"Hobbies and Crafts\\"."},{"source":"Read the following context and answer the question.\\nContext: So on the train we went - seeing the dinosaurs and stuff we had n't seen on our first day . I admit , I welled up a few times during the fireworks and on that train ride . Both for memories I have from my trip with my dad ( recently passed ) and memories we were making with our girls on this trip . A very , very special place Disneyland is .\\nQuestion: What has been the narrator 's impression of DisneyLand ?\\nAnswer:","target":"The narrator has been pleased with DisneyLand .","rationale":"The narrator mentions that on the train ride his eyes welled up with tears for memories he had from both a trip with his father and also of this current trip. He then says it is 'a very, very special place Disneyland is'. A person would not be moved to tears by something they did not enjoy or find meaningful so their experience at DisneyLand must have been positive.\\nSo the answer is The narrator has been pleased with DisneyLand ."},{"source":"Read the following article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Kids love playing sports. But boys and girls like different sports. For boys, football ,baseball and basketball are their favorites. They think football and basketball are very exciting and interesting, so boys often play football or basketball after school. Peter says, \\"Football is very interesting. The football players are often handsome.\\" But girls have different opinions. They think tennis and ping-pong are more interesting. Lily says, \\"I like tennis, because many tennis players are beautiful girls. They have good figures. I hope to have a good figure, too.\\"\\nQuestion: How does Peter think of football players?\\n- Cool\\n- Interesting\\n- Exciting\\n- Handsome","target":"Handsome","rationale":"In the article, Peter says that he likes football because \\"the players are often handsome.\\" Based on this information, it can be inferred that Peter thinks of football players as being handsome.\\nSo, the answer is Handsome."},{"source":"Given a question, generate a paraphrase of that question wihout changing the meaning of it. Your answer should reword the given sentence, but not add information to it or remove information from it. The answer to your question should be the same as the answer to the original question.\\n\\nQuestion: what movies did julia roberts and richard gere star in?","target":"what film did julia roberts and richard gere star in together?","rationale":"Here's a paraphrase of the question: \\"what film did julia roberts and richard gere star in together?\\""},{"source":"Exercise: Extract from the text the correct entity that \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to.\\n\\n(CNN) -- A previously unknown piano work by Wolfgang Amadeus Mozart was performed Friday at the maestro's home in Salzburg, the Salzburg Mozarteum Foundation said. The piece, recently unearthed in Austria, was played by noted pianist Florian Birsak. It was discovered in an attic of a private home in Tyrol, the foundation said, inside a handwritten book with more than 160 pages. Works by Mozart's father were found within the same book. The piece, 84 measures in length, is marked \\"Allegro molto\\" -- meaning it is meant to be played \\"very quick.\\" It is thought to date from around 1767, which would mean Mozart wrote the work when he was about 11 years old.\\n@highlight\\nThe work was found in an attic of a private home in Tyrol\\n@highlight\\nMozart is thought to have composed it around the age of 11\\n@highlight\\nThe piece, 84 measures in length, is meant to be played \\"very quick\\"\\n\\"Throughout the @placeholder, thematic formation, compositional setting and harmony have a number of components that are found repeated in other Mozart piano works,\\" the foundation said in a statement.","target":"Allegro molto","rationale":"The context refers to the piece as \\"Allegro molto\\" and notes that it is meant to be played very quickly.\\nIn music, Allegro means quick or fast and molto (very) when added indicates a faster tempo than allegro itself. \\n\\n\\nSo based on this knowledge, we can infer that @placeholder here represents the name of the composition: \\"\\"Allegro Molto\\"\\" by Mozart."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nI don't have any information on the economy. Would you be interested in learning more about the history /","target":"assistant","rationale":"The dialogue is clearly a continuation of the user's previous query, and thus can be classified as an assistant response."},{"source":"In this task you will be given an answer to a question. You need to generate a question. The answer given should be a correct answer for the generated question.\\n\\nStromboli (Italian pronunciation: (Ààstromboli); Sicilian: Stru√≤gnuli, Ancient Greek: Œ£œÑœÅŒøŒ≥Œ≥œçŒªŒ∑, Strongulƒì) is a small island in the Tyrrhenian Sea, off the north coast of Sicily, containing one of the three active volcanoes in Italy. It is one of the eight Aeolian Islands, a volcanic arc north of Sicily. This name is derived from the Ancient Greek name Strongulƒì which was given to it because of its round swelling form. The island's population is about 500. The volcano has erupted many times and is constantly active with minor eruptions, often visible from many points on the island and from the surrounding sea, giving rise to the island's nickname 'Lighthouse of the Mediterranean'.","target":"when was the last time the stromboli volcano erupted","rationale":"The answer to the given question is \\"This name is derived from the Ancient Greek name Strongulƒì which was given to it because of its round swelling form.\\" This answer can be inferred by asking a question like: \\"what is the origin of stromboli's greek name?\\" or \\"why was stromboli called strongule?\\" These questions require knowledge beyond what has been provided in the paragraph, therefore we generate a question like: \\"when was the last time the stromboli volcano erupted\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two lists A,B. Find the longest common subsequence in the lists A and B.\\n\\n[4131, 5341, 't', '7217', 'V', 'f'], [8015, 4823, 't', '7217', 'i', 5243]","target":"t, 7217","rationale":"The longest common subsequence in the given lists is \\"t, 7217\\", which contains 2 elements."},{"source":"I am testing my students' logic.\\nWhat is the answer they should choose between \\"jackhammer\\" and \\"drill\\"?\\nLogic test: A jackhammer and drill are both being used at a construction site. If Jimbo is standing closer to the jackhammer, it will sound _____ then the drill (A) quieter (B) louder","target":"drill","rationale":"The jackhammer is louder than the drill, therefore if Jimbo is standing closer to the jackhammer it would sound \\"louder\\" than the drill. So in this scenario, we should choose 'drill' as our answer since that's what makes sense based on logic."},{"source":"Here is a question about this article: The Church of the Holy Apostles in Thessaloniki was built in 1310‚Äì14. Although some vandal systematically removed the gold tesserae of the background it can be seen that the Pantokrator and the prophets in the dome follow the traditional Byzantine pattern. Many details are similar to the Pammakaristos mosaics so it is supposed that the same team of mosaicists worked in both buildings. Another building with a related mosaic decoration is the Theotokos Paregoritissa Church in Arta. The church was established by the Despot of Epirus in 1294‚Äì96. In the dome is the traditional stern Pantokrator, with prophets and cherubim below.\\nWhat is the answer to this question: Who removed the gold tesserae in the background of the mosaic at the Church of the Holy Apostles?","target":"some vandal","rationale":"The article states that someone vandalized the mosaic by removing the gold tesserae in the background. The act of vandalism was done systematically, which means it required planning and effort. \\nTherefore, any person who would do such a thing could be referred to as \\"\\"some vandal\\"\\"."},{"source":"Article:\\n\\nBy Ap Reporter and Reuters Reporter PUBLISHED: 12:25 EST, 4 May 2013 | UPDATED: 12:40 EST, 5 May 2013 Seven U.S. soldiers and a member of the NATO-led coalition were killed on Saturday in one of the deadliest days for Americans and other foreign troops in Afghanistan in recent months, as the Taliban continued attacks as part of their spring offensive. The renewed violence came as Afghan President Hamid Karzai acknowledged at a news conference that regular payments his government has received from the CIA for more than a decade would continue. Karzai also said that talks on a U.S.-Afghan bilateral security agreement to govern future American military presence in the country had been delayed because of conditions the Afghans were placing on the deal.\\n\\n\\nHighlights:\\n\\n\\nNineteen U.S. personnel have been killed in the last week\\n\\n\\nAttacks occurred in the 'spiritual birthplace' of the Taliban after the group recently announced a 'spring offensive'","target":"It was unclear how Karzai expected the United States or any of its allies to guarantee Afghanistan's borders against attack.","rationale":"It was unclear how Karzai expected the United States or any of its allies to guarantee Afghanistan's borders against attack."},{"source":"You are given a math word problem and you are supposed to apply a single mathematical operators like addition, subtraction, multiplication or division on the numbers embedded in the text to answer the following question and then only report final the numerical answer.\\n\\nEach CD rack holds 8 CDs . A shelf can hold 4 racks . How many total CDs can fit on the shelf ?","target":"32","rationale":"To answer the question, we need to perform the following calculation: 4 racks * 8 CDs = 32 total CDs."},{"source":"Read the dialog and predict the next turn. DIALOG:\\nWhat happened in the case of the 11 year-old child who was married to a much older man?\\n- Wan Azizah Wan Ismail continues to attract criticism from activists over her perceived reluctance to take action against the 41-year-old man who married an 11-year-old child, with a coalition of women's groups urging swift action to be taken to protect the girl, a Thai national who lives in Kelantan.\\n- Did the activist succeed?\\n- The Joint Action Group for Gender Equality (JAG) said it was time to act and urged the government to conclude its lengthy investigations.\\n- Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n-","target":"Selangor plans to amend the Islamic Family Law (State of Selangor) Enactment 2003 on the minimum age for marriage for Muslim women in the state which will be increased from 16 to 18 years, after reports of rampant child marriages.","rationale":"The last sentence provided in the dialog is a summary of the news article. The candidate answer that is most relevant to this summary, and therefore should be the next turn in the dialog, is \\"Selangor plans to amend the Islamic Family Law (State of Selangor) Enactment 2003 on the minimum age for marriage for Muslim women in the state which will be increased from 16 to 18 years, after reports of rampant child marriages.\\""},{"source":"Fill in the response. DIALOG:\\nWhat happened during the final at the 2012 WTA Tour Championships?\\n- However she was unable to hold on as Williams won four straight games herself to take a 4‚Äì3 lead.\\n- What happened after that?\\n-","target":"Azarenka was able to hold for 4‚Äì4. Williams held for 5‚Äì4 with Azarenka now having to serve to stay in the match.","rationale":"In the given dialog, the question \\"What happened after that?\\" is asked by a user and the response to this question should be: Azarenka was able to hold for 4‚Äì4. Williams held for 5‚Äì4 with Azarenka now having to serve to stay in the match."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a statement spoken by a politician in natural language and the subject of the discussion for the given statement. Your task is to determine if the given subject of the discussion is correct for the given statement. The subject can be multiple words. Answer with \\"True\\" if it's the correct subject of discussion or return \\"False\\" if it's incorrect.\\n\\nStatement: Because of (U.S. Sen.-elect Ron) Johnsons leadership, Senate Republicans adopted a caucus ban on earmarks. \\n Subject: economy,education,taxes","target":"False","rationale":"The given statement is about a ban on earmarks in the US Senate and the subject of discussion is \\"economy,education,taxes\\". The subject of discussion and the content of the statement are not related. Hence, \\"False\\""},{"source":"Exercise: Extract from the text the correct entity that \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to.\\n\\nAtlanta (CNN) -- The Cherokee Nation had difficulty electing its principal chief, so much so that members called in the Carter Center to observe the most recent vote and judge whether it was free and fair. We normally observe elections only in politically troubled countries abroad but believe that the contentiousness and fundamental voting rights issues at stake -- and not just for the Cherokees -- justified this exceptional mission. Simmering beneath the election process all along has been the crucial issue of voting rights for the former slaves known in the tribe as Freedmen, who are Cherokee citizens of African origin and who have had to fight in the courts to be able to vote.\\n@highlight\\nJohn Stremlau: Cherokee Nation called in Carter Center to observe its election for chief\\n@highlight\\nAdding to power struggle was the right of Freedmen (black Cherokees) to vote, he says\\n@highlight\\nFreedmen, Cherokee members of African origin, fought and finally won right to vote\\n@highlight\\nStremlau: Restricting voting rights to ethnic Cherokees is an affront to democracy\\nThe terrible history of forced oppression and forced relocation has produced a deeply flawed @placeholder democracy, one further threatened by the attempt to restrict citizenship to ethnic Cherokees, a flagrant affront to the principle of inherent equality.","target":"Cherokees","rationale":"From the given context, we can see that @placeholder refers to people of Cherokee origin. \\nTherefore, the correct entity is \\"Cherokees\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the beginning and the ending of a three-part story. Your job is to complete the short story by writing a middle sentence that seamlessly connects  the first and last sentence. Generated sentences must be short, have fewer than 10 words, and be simple as if narrating to a child. Avoid using any irrelevant extra information when creating the middle sentence, and use names (e.g. Jack, Barbara,...) instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible.\\n\\nBeginning: Cindy's parents were going through a divorce. Ending: Cindy then went back to her room and started crying too.","target":"Cindy heard her parents crying one night","rationale":"Cindy's parents were going through a divorce and Cindy then went back to her room and started crying too. This implies that the middle sentence should relate to the divorce and why Cindy starts crying in her room. The middle sentence \\"Cindy heard her parents crying one night\\" conveys this information while keeping it simple."},{"source":"What is the answer?\\nContext: One adaptation helping both predators and prey avoid detection is camouflage, a form of crypsis where species have an appearance that helps them blend into the background. Camouflage consists of not only color but also shape and pattern. The background upon which the organism is seen can be both its environment (e.g., the praying mantis to the right resembling dead leaves) or other organisms (e.g., zebras' stripes blend in with each other in a herd, making it difficult for lions to focus on a single target). The more convincing camouflage is, the more likely it is that the organism will go unseen.;\\nQuestion: Ogranisms use camoflauge to blend with their habitat and what else?;\\nIf you can't find the answer, please respond \\"unanswerable\\".\\nAnswer:","target":"other organisms","rationale":"The context states that camouflage consists of not only color but also shape and pattern. The background upon which the organism is seen can be both its environment (e.g., the praying mantis to the right resembling dead leaves) or other organisms (e.g., zebras' stripes blend in with each other in a herd, making it difficult for lions to focus on a single target).\\nTherefore, \\"other organisms\\" would fit as an answer because they are part of the background against which camoflauge helps creatures hide by blending into their surroundings."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to whether they are trash or treasure is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Items marked as \\"trash\\" are considered to not have value and can be disposed, whereas those marked as \\"treasure\\" are considered valuable items that must be retained. \\"A : \\"B relates item A to whether it is trash or treasure, as specified by B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with either \`trash\` or \`treasure\` for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nmud : trash. cushion : ?","target":"treasure","rationale":"Mud is trash and can be disposed of, while a cushion is a treasure."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"What Mary prefers is her ice cream in a cone.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence: What Mary prefers is her ice cream in a cone."},{"source":"You are given an open-domain question from an open movie database. Your task is to provide an answer to that question. Try to only include the answer. Do not put it in a sentence.\\n\\nwho is listed as director for Heart of America?","target":"Uwe Boll","rationale":"The answer can be found in the following document:\\nhttps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heart_of_America\\nUwe Boll is listed as director for this movie on Wikipedia."},{"source":"Given a text passage as input comprising of dialogue of negotiations between a seller and a buyer about the sale of an item, your task is to classify the item being sold into exactly one of these categories: 'housing', 'furniture', 'bike', 'phone', 'car', 'electronics'. The output should be the name of the category from the stated options and there should be exactly one category for the given text passage.\\n\\nBuyer: Good morning.  I'm interested in the listing for the Peugeot road bike you have.\\nSeller: Great. It's a great project bike that is going to be awesome with very little work for just $60. \\nBuyer: How old is the bike and are you the original owner?\\nSeller: About six years and original owner. This bike is easy to find salvaged parts to replace. I can include new tubes for the tires for the $60. \\nBuyer: If I was willing to come and pick up the bike, would you accept $50?\\nSeller: How about $55 and I will still include the tubes and a list of places to find the parts you will need. \\nSeller: \\nBuyer: Yeah, OK, that'll work.\\nBuyer:","target":"bike","rationale":"The given text passage clearly states that the item being negotiated is a \\"Peugeot road bike\\". Therefore, the correct output is \\"bike\\"."},{"source":"You are given a dialog between 2 or more individuals. Within the dialog, there will be clues as to the names of the speakers. You will be asked at the end of the dialog to identify the name of one of the speakers.\\n\\nSpeaker 1: Oh, Ross, Mon, is it okay if I bring someone to your parent's anniversary party? \\nSpeaker 2: Yeah. \\nSpeaker 3: Sure. Yeah. \\nSpeaker 4: So, who's the guy? \\nSpeaker 1: Well, his name is Parker and I met him at the drycleaners. \\nSpeaker 5: Oooh, did he put a little starch in your bloomers? Who said that? \\nSpeaker 1: Yeah, he's really great though. He has this incredible zest for life, and he treats me like a queen, except at night when he treats me like the naughty girl I am. \\nSpeaker 2: Oh, by the way. Would it be okay if I gave the toast to mom and dad this year? \\nSpeaker 3: Uh, yeah, you sure you want to after what happened at their 20th? \\nSpeaker 2: Yeah, I'd really like to. \\nSpeaker 3: Okay, hopefully this time mom won't boo you. \\nSpeaker 2: Yes! Every year Ross makes the toast, and it's always really moving, and always makes them cry. Well this year I'm going to make them cry. \\nSpeaker 5: And you wonder why Ross is their favorite? \\nSpeaker 2: No! Really! Any time Ross makes a toast everyone cries, and hugs him, and pats him on the back and they all come up to me and say, \\"God, your brother.\\" Know what they'll say this year? \\"God, you\\" \\nSpeaker 4: Well I can promise you, at least one person will be crying. I'm an actor, and any actor worth himself can cry on cue. \\nSpeaker 2: Really you can do that? \\nSpeaker 4: Are you kidding me? Watch! Well I can't do it with you guys watching me! What is the name or nickname of \\nSpeaker 2?","target":"Mon","rationale":"In the dialog, the speakers are talking about their parents' anniversary party. Speaker 1 asks if she can bring a date to the party. Speaker 2 and 3 confirm that it's okay for her to bring a date. Then, speaker 4 asks who this guy is that she wants to bring as her date. Then, speaker 5 tells speaker 2 that he got a laugh out of how well he delivered his line about putting starch in someone's bloomers. The question asks for the name of nickname of Speaker 2 so it must be \\"Mon\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: What country did Baba teach in? Passage:Somuncu Baba is one of the virtuous men who came to Anadolu for spiritual conquest, he was also a descendant of Islamic prophet Muhammad After receiving an education in cities which are the center of knowledge like ≈ûam, Tabriz, Erdebil, he settled in Bursa for his guidance and duty. He taught at the Bursa Grand Mosque where he was installed by Sultan Bayezid I after it was completed. For hiding his spiritual side, he baked bread and sold them so he was known as Somuncu Baba. He became known after he had translated the sura of Al-Fatiha, in seven different ways during the opening of Bursa Grand Mosque, in Bursa. He avoided becoming famous so he left Bursa and moved Aksaray. He left his son Yusuf Hakiki Baba in Aksaray and he went to Mecca with his son Halil Taybi when they got back to Anadolu they settled in Darende and he died here in 1412. His tomb is still in Darende.","target":"b","rationale":"The question asks for the country where Baba taught, but this information is not provided in the passage. The question can't be answered without additional information outside of the given passage."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two strings A,B. You must perform the following operations to generate the required output list: (i) Find the longest common substring in the strings A and B, (ii) Convert this substring to all lowercase and sort it alphabetically, (iii) Replace the substring at its respective positions in the two lists with the updated substring.\\n\\nJzlGtiNrPbkQwpXZzEfzHAjgzPcXw, ggrpsrPbkQwpXZzEfzHANdmbSiQprd","target":"JzlGtiNabefhkppqrwxzzzjgzPcXw, ggrpsabefhkppqrwxzzzNdmbSiQprd","rationale":"The longest common substring in A and B is 'PbkQwpXZzEfzH'. Converting this to all lowercase and sorting gives us 'abefhkppqrwxzzz'. Replacing this substring in the original strings gives us the output:\\nJzlGtiNabefhkppqrwxzzzjgzPcXw, ggrpsabefhkppqrwxzzzNdmbSiQprd"},{"source":"Definitions of literature have varied over time; it is a \\"culturally relative definition\\". In Western Europe prior to the eighteenth century, literature as a term indicated all books and writing. A more restricted sense of the term emerged during the Romantic period, in which it began to demarcate \\"imaginative\\" literature. Contemporary debates over what constitutes literature can be seen as returning to the older, more inclusive notion of what constitutes literature. Cultural studies, for instance, takes as its subject of analysis both popular and minority genres, in addition to canonical works.\\nWhat is this about?","target":"Literature","rationale":"The context defines literature as \\"all books and writing\\". It further states that the term was restricted to imaginative literature in the 18th century.\\nThus, given this information about what constitutes literature, we can conclude that the passage is primarily focused on discussing different definitions of Literature."},{"source":"In this task, a passage will be given and the goal is to identify an event from the passage. An event is defined as a single word representing something that happened, is happening, or may happen. An event can be factual or hypothetical, positive or negative, certain or uncertain. While most events are based on verbs, an event can also be based on a noun (ex. storm, snow, rainfall) or a copula verb (is, was, been, etc.). The event must not be a pronoun or an adjective. For noun events with multiple words, use the last word in the phrase as event.\\n\\nPassage: Rogers said the shares will be convertible into Class B shares, but that the company has the option to redeem the shares before a conversion takes place. A spokesman for the Toronto cable television and telecommunications concern said the coupon rate hasn't yet been fixed, but will probably be set at around 8%.","target":"said","rationale":"The event in the passage is \\"said\\", which is represented by the verb \\"said\\"."},{"source":"Multi-select: Let's say that \\"James asked Robert for a favor but he refused.\\"\\n\\nCan we now say that \\"James refused.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The information provided in the passage tells us that James asked Robert for a favor, and Robert refused. This does not provide any evidence to support the claim \\"James refused.\\" unless it is specified within this text or by another reliable source of information."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. The story has one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nAmelia entered the closet. James entered the closet. The pear is in the blue_pantry. James exited the closet. Amelia moved the pear to the blue_envelope. Where does Amelia think that James searches for the pear?","target":"blue_pantry","rationale":"The question asks where Amelia thinks James will search for the pear. Since Amelia's belief about James's beliefs does not match reality, we need to infer what Amelia believes from the events in the story. The only relevant event is when Amelia moves the pear from the blue_pantry to blue_envelope, meaning that she believes that James will search for it in a different location than where she moved it."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an implausible answer to a question that involves ‚Äúevent duration\\", based on a given sentence. Here, event duration is defined as the understanding of how long events typically last. For example, ‚Äúbrushing teeth‚Äù, usually takes a few minutes. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: Separately, Citadel posted a third-quarter net loss of $2.3 million, or 68 cents a share, versus net income of $5.3 million, or $1.61 a share, a year earlier. \\nQuestion: How many months were in last quarter?","target":"4 days","rationale":"It is possible to assume that \\"third-quarter net loss\\" refers to a specific quarter in which a company made less profit than it did in previous quarters. However, the term \\"quarter\\" could also refer to three consecutive months (see https://www.merriam-webster.com/dictionary/quarter). Therefore, there are two plausible interpretations of the question: 1) How many days were in last quarter? 2) How many months were in last quarter? Since an incorrect answer is needed for this task, we assume that the second interpretation is correct and answer 4 days instead of 3 months."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is potentially offensive to anyone (i.e., a subset of people, any particular person, etc.), 2) no, otherwise. Note that potentially offensive posts can contain sexual, racial, religious biased or offensive language. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nThey got some trashy ass hoes out here","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post is potentially offensive to some people as it contains a derogatory term for women and objectifying language. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Flavia Maxima Fausta (289326) was a Roman Empress, daughter of the Roman Emperor Maximianus. To seal the alliance between them for control of the Tetrarchy, in 307 Maximianus married her to Constantine I, who set aside his wife Minervina in her favour. Constantine and Fausta had been betrothed since 293.\\n\\n- Constantina ( also named Constantia and Constantiana ; b. after 307/before 317 - d. 354 ) , and later known as Saint Constance , was the eldest daughter of Roman emperor Constantine the Great and his second wife Fausta , daughter of Emperor Maximian . Constantina received the title of Augusta by her father , and is venerated as a saint , having developed a medieval legend wildly at variance with what is known of her actual character . In English she is also known as Saint Constance .\\n\\n- Constantine the Great (27 February 272¬†AD  22 May 337¬†AD), also known as Constantine I or Saint Constantine (in the Orthodox Church as Saint Constantine the Great, Equal-to-the-Apostles), was a Roman Emperor from 306 to 337¬†AD. Constantine was the son of Flavius Valerius Constantius, a Roman Army officer, and his consort Helena. His father became \\"Caesar\\", the deputy emperor in the west, in 293¬†AD. Constantine was sent east, where he rose through the ranks to become a military tribune under the emperors Diocletian and Galerius. In 305, Constantius was raised to the rank of \\"Augustus\\", senior western emperor, and Constantine was recalled west to campaign under his father in Britannia (Britain). Acclaimed as emperor by the army at Eboracum (modern-day York) after his father's death in 306¬†AD, Constantine emerged victorious in a series of civil wars against the emperors Maxentius and Licinius to become sole ruler of both west and east by 324¬†AD.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat is the relationship between 'constantina' and 'helena'?","target":"sister","rationale":"Constantina (also named Constantia and Constantiana) was the eldest daughter of Roman emperor Constantine the Great and his second wife Fausta, who is Helena's sister."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the general math. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: mid intended to type a 7 - digit number , but the two 3 ' s he meant to type did not appear . what appeared instead was the 5 - digit number 52115 . how many different 7 - digit numbers could mid have meant to type ? \\nOptions: a ) 10 , b ) 16 , c ) 21 , d ) 24 , e ) 27","target":"c","rationale":"The problem is asking how many ways can the two 3's be added out of all the 7 places in a number, which is 7 choose 2 = 21."},{"source":"In this task, you need to provide the correct option for a given problem from the provided options.\\n\\nProblem: a grocery store bought some apples at a rate of 5 for a dollar . they were separated into two stacks , one of which was sold at a rate of 3 for a dollar and the other at a rate of 6 for a dollar . what was the ratio of the number of apples in the two stacks if the store broke even after having sold all of its apples ? \\nOptions: a ) 1 : 7 , b ) 1 : 5 , c ) 1 : 4 , d ) 1 : 2 , e ) 2 : 5","target":"c","rationale":"Let's say the total number of apples is x. The store bought x apples at the rate of 5 for 1 dollar, which means that it paid 5x/100 dollars for them. They were separated into two stacks, one of which was sold at a rate (3) and other stack was sold at a rate (6). If the store broke even after having sold all of its apples, then:\\n\\n5x/100 = (1/3)stack1 + (1/6)stack2\\n\\nWe can simplify this to:\\n\\n 10x = 10(stack1 + stack2)\\n \\n\\n 20x = 15stack1 + 10stack2 \\n\\n 30x - 20x = 15(stack2 - stack1 ) \\n\\n 10x = 15(stack2 - stack1 ) \\n\\n Therefore , ratio(Number in Stack 2 : Number in Stack 1 )is 2 : 3 or 2 : 4. So , choice c is correct . '''"},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: Is it possible to conclude that \\"The man is playing a stringed instrument on the ground.\\" if \\"The man is not on the ground.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no...I think the answer is","target":"no","rationale":"The premise tells us that the man is not playing a stringed instrument on the ground, which contradicts with what we know from the question. Since we do not have any other information about where he could be and whether or not he‚Äôs still playing his stringed instrument there, it does not make sense to conclude that ‚Äúthe man is playing a stringed instrument on the ground‚Äù if \\"the man is not on the ground.\\""},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to whether they are trash or treasure is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Items marked as \\"trash\\" are considered to not have value and can be disposed, whereas those marked as \\"treasure\\" are considered valuable items that must be retained. \\"A : \\"B relates item A to whether it is trash or treasure, as specified by B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with either \`trash\` or \`treasure\` for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ntoy : treasure. peel : ?","target":"trash","rationale":"The example states that \\"toy\\" is a treasure. This indicates that it is not trash and would not be disposed of. Since \\"peel\\" relates to the outer layer of an object, and since this junk can be thrown away, we can infer that \\"peel\\" must also be considered trash."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[  7.52   -0.219 -34.987 -99.841 -33.632]","target":"-99.841","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -99.841, which has an absolute value of 99.841. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 99.841(e.g 7.52 = 7.52, -0.219 = 0). However, we need to return the value of the elements before applying the absolute value so we will return -99.841 as it corressponds to 99.841 and is negative"},{"source":"Article: If you need glasses to read this, you are among most of Chinese students. About four-fifths of high school students in China have poor eyesight . And now more and more children in primary school need glasses, too.\\nTwo main reasons can cause poor eyesight: too much time spent indoors studying and too little time spent outdoors playing. Reading and writing for hours and hours, sometimes in poorly lighted rooms, causes eyesight to weaken. But students have to do this because there is so much pressure on them to succeed in school. They have less time to enjoy the sun.\\nThe sun, it turns out, is important in developing good eyesight. According to a study by Australian National University, Australian children and Chinese children have the same level of eyesight before they start school, but once they enter primary school, Chinese children only spend about an hour a day outside, while Australian children spend three to four hours each day in the sunshine. The result is that while about forty percent of Chinese primary school students need glasses, only three percent of Australian children do.\\nAnd poor eyesight at a young age can have serious long term influence. As you get older, your eyesight can worsen.\\nWith all that in mind, don't you think it's time to give your eyes a break?\\nQuestion: What does the writer want to tell us?\\nYes or no, is the answer \\"Remember to give our eyes a break.\\"?","target":"No","rationale":"The article mentions reasons why Chinese students, who spend most of their time indoors studying and less in the sun than Australian children, develop poor eyesight.\\nThis is followed by a discussion on how poor eyesight at a young age can affect one in old age. Finally, it is suggested that we give our eyes a break to avoid these problems.\\nGiven this context, the writer uses \\"Remember to give our eyes a break.\\" as an example of what we should do rather than telling us exactly what to do (which would be giving your own specific instructions). So answer No"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a short passage that conveys a stereotype. A stereotype is an over-generalized belief about a particular group of people. You are expected to classify the passage into nine types of stereotype: race-color, socioeconomic, gender, disability, nationality, sexual-orientation, physical-appearance, religion, and age.\\n\\nPassage: Most black girls her age would want something else like a watermelon.","target":"race-color","rationale":"The passage implies that black girls would prefer watermelon to other things. This is a negative stereotype about black people, especially young women. Therefore, the passage can be classified as a race-color stereotype."},{"source":"What is the person that starts to bleed from his mouth have with him?\\n\\nAnswer the above question based on the context below:\\n\\nvista pacific airlines Flight 7500 a boeing 747-300 departs from Los Angeles to Tokyo. Passengers on board include a group of two vacationing couples, Lyn and Jack and Brad and Pia, who have secretly broken up; a thief named Jake; a suspicious businessman traveling with a strange wooden box, Lance; a young woman named Raquel; newlyweds Rick and the snobby Liz; and the goth Jacinta. Air hostesses Laura and Suzy welcome the passengers on board, and Suzy questions Laura about her secret relationship with the married captain, Pete.\\nA few hours into the flight, the plane hits turbulence that soon passes.\\nLance has a panic attack and begins to bleed profusely from his mouth. When Lance suddenly dies, Captain Pete continues to Japan, moving the first-class passengers into economy and keeping Lance's body in the closed-off first class.\\nLaura notices plastic water bottles collapsing and quickly warns everyone to fasten their seatbelts, just as the cabin pressure drops. As the oxygen masks are dispensed above the seats, a thick smoke fills the cabin. After the cabin pressure returns to normal and the smoke disappears, Laura finds Raquel unconscious in the toilet and revives her with an oxygen tank. Meanwhile, the plane's radio has stopped working and Captain Pete cannot contact Tokyo air traffic controllers.","target":"a strange wooden box","rationale":"The context mentions a passenger whose mouth begins to bleed. The bleeding is later linked to the person traveling with a wooden box, suggesting that he was carrying something in his bag which caused him to start bleeding from his mouth.\\nIt can be inferred that there is some item of significance in the man's suitcase and it may have been related to the cause of death or even played a part in bringing down Flight 7500. So based on this information, we conclude that 'a strange wooden box' would likely be an answer option given by someone who has seen Flight 7500 before."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['1397', 'n', '6583', '8289', 'G', '33', '8191', 'k', '5985', '8267', '583', '6835', 'D', '5261', 'L', '8685', 'J']","target":"60109","rationale":"Given the list ['1397', 'n', '6583', '8289', 'G', '33', '8191','k','5985','8267','583','6835','D','5261','L'], we need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\\\n1. The 1st element is 1397, so it is added to the total.\\\\n2. The 2nd element is n, so it is ignored and not added to the total.\\\\n3. The 3rd element is 6583, so it is added to the total (1397 + 6583).\\\\n4-14: Steps 2-12 are repeated until all elements have been processed and summed up (total = 60109)."},{"source":"After getting a divorce, what is your marital status?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. being single\\n\\nB. stressful\\n\\nC. emotional distress\\n\\nD. anguish\\n\\nE. bad feelings","target":"A","rationale":"After getting a divorce, one is single.\\nThe other options are not about marital status but describe emotions caused by the divorce which would be more appropriate for answering the question \\"What does it feel like to get divorced?\\""},{"source":"Given a passage and a query based on the passage, generate an unambiguous, concise and simple answer to the query from information in the passage. Note that the answer may not be present in exact form.\\n\\nAustralian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is a bobtailed, medium sized breed of dog. Origin: Australia. Life span: 10-13 years. Hypoallergenic: No. Review how much Australian Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler puppies for sale sell for below. The current median price for all Australian Cattle Dog Blue Heelers sold is $450.00. This is the price you can expect to budget for an Australian Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler with papers but without breeding rights nor show quality. The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is deemed to be the oldest breed of Australian working dog. Likewise, the breed is believed to be the first purebreed developed in Australia. The Stumpy Tail was the result of mating a Dingo with a Smithfield. The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is the first pure breed dog developed in Australia. The outstanding working qualities as an all rounder make the dog a most prized companion and friend of the Australian farmers and graziers. Though similar to them, the Stumpy Tail Cattle Dogs are not Australian Cattle Dogs with docked tails, but are cousins to that breed, and a breed in their own right. In Australia, their country of origin, ‚ÄúStumpies‚Äù are much sought after for their working ability. Both red and blue Stumpy Tails are extremely faithful, and tireless workers. The Australian Cattle Dog is a related breed (with a long tail) that is similar in appearance to the Stumpy, but the Australian Cattle is proportionally heavier and less leggy. The ‚ÄúStumpy‚Äù possesses a natural aptitude in the working and controlling of cattle, and a loyal, courageous and devoted disposition. You should budget anywhere from $1,600 upwards to $5,000 or even more for an Australian Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler with top breed lines and a superior pedigree. The average cost for all Australian Cattle Dog Blue Heelers sold is $500. View Prices of Puppies Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog Picture. Breed Information. Popularity. #. Name. Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog. Other names. Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog, Stumpy, Stumpy Tail, Heeler. Origin. The cost to buy an Australian Cattle Dog/Blue Heeler varies greatly and depends on many factors such as the breeders' location, reputation, litter size, lineage of the puppy, breed popularity (supply and demand), training, socialization efforts, breed lines and much more. The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is a medium sized dog that originated in Australia. This dog is also known as Stumpy Tail, Stumpy and Heeler. Originally breed to herd cattle in the mid 1800s, the dog is considered to be a fairly rare today as they are seldom kept as pets. The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog however is well established in Australia where the dog is utilized to keep livestock in line. Query: australian stumpy heelers","target":"The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is a medium sized dog that originated in Australia","rationale":"Here's an direct answer: The Australian Stumpy Tail Cattle Dog is a medium sized dog that originated in Australia."},{"source":"You are given a mathematical question described with a circumscribed mathematical vocabulary. Questions in this task usually contain some variables (e.g. X, Y), equations (e.g. X+Y=3) and some relationships (X is greater than Y). Often you need to find the value of the variable using equations and relationships. You are also given 4 or 5 answer options (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", \\"E\\"). Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'. LaTeX mathematical format (the standard way to express mathematical expressions in the typesetting software known as LaTeX) is used to express equations. Each question is solvable with high school math knowledge. Give only one answer for each question.\\n\\nFor any two distinct negative integers c and d, which of the following must be less than \\\\(cd\\\\) ?\\n(A)\\\\(cd + 1\\\\) (B)\\\\((-cd)^2\\\\) (C)\\\\(d(c - 2)\\\\) (D)\\\\((c - 1)(d - 1)\\\\) (E)\\\\((c + 1)(d + 1)\\\\)","target":"E","rationale":"Since c and d are negative, \\\\(cd < 0\\\\). Since E is the only option that is not negative, it must be less than \\\\(cd\\\\)."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: When I was at university,  I studied very hard. But a lot of my friends did very little work. Some did just enough to pass exams. Others didn't do quite enough. Fred Baines was one of them. He spent more time drinking in the Students' Union than working in the library. Once, at the end of the term, we had to take an important test in chemistry. The test had a hundred questions. Beside each question we had to write \\"True\\" or \\"False\\". While I was studying in my room the night before the test, Fred was watching television. Fred usually worried a lot the night before a test. But that night he looked perfectly calm. Then he told me of his plan. \\"It's very simple. There are a hundred questions and I have to get fifty correct to pass the test. I'll take a coin into the examination room. I haven't studied a chemistry book for months, so I'll just toss the coin. In that way, I'm sure I'll get half the questions right.\\" The next day, Fred came cheerfully into the examination room. As he sat tossing a coin for half an hour he marked down his answers. Then he left half an hour before the rest of us. The next day, he saw the chemistry professor in the corridor.\\n\\"Oh good,\\" he said, \\"Have you got the results of the test?\\"\\nThe professor looked at him and smiled.\\n\\"Ah, it's you, Baines, just a minute.\\"\\nThen he reached into his pocket and took out a coin. He threw it into the air, caught it in his hand and looked at it.\\n\\"I'm terribly sorry, Baines,\\" he said, \\"You failed!\\"\\nQuestion: The chemistry professor   _   .\\nOptions: A: didn't mark the test papers correctly\\nB: tossed a coin when he marked test papers\\nC: knew about Fred's method\\nD: thought Fred's method was good","target":"C","rationale":"The professor took the coin out of his pocket, which implies that he had it with him. This means that he intentionally brought a coin to school and was planning on using it for some purpose. The fact that the professor threw up this coin in front of Fred indicates that he knew about Fred's plan as well. So C is correct - because the chemistry professor knew about Fred's method"},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the other-need strategy, otherwise output No. other-need is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used when the participants discuss a need for someone else rather than themselves. For instance, describing the need for firewood to keep the kids warm.\\n\\nContext: 'Maybe I could take 2 firewood 2 food and 0 waters?' 'I was planning on staying up all night and keeping my fire going all night.  Honestly I could give you all the extra food if that helps you if I could please have the 3 firewood?  We could split the waters' 'I'll only give you all the firewood if you give me everything else. I know it's your top priorityüòÆ'\\nUtterance: 'How about I take all the wood, give you all the food, you can have 2 waters and I can have one.  Having a little extra water will help me with all the hiking we will be doing, plus since i wont be eating much I want to stay hydrated.  Will that work for you>>üôÇ'","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker is describing their own needs, not someone else's. They are asking if they can keep the wood, give up all the food and split the waters with their partner. The answer is No because this utterance does not contain an other-need strategy."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and a question. You need to find whether an element is at the intersection of two given sets.  A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. The intersection of two given sets is the largest set which contains all the elements that are common to both sets. An element is at the intersection of two given sets, A and B, if common to both A and B. Classify your answers into 'Yes' or 'No'.\\n\\nSet1: '{9, 12, 5, 7}', Set2: '{1, 7, 12, 13, 15, 16}'. Is the element '13' in the intersection of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"No","rationale":"The intersection of Set1 and Set2 is {7, 12}. The element '13' is present in the union of both sets, but not at their intersection. Therefore, the answer would be No."},{"source":"Read the article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Friends are very important in our everyday life. Everyone needs friends. We all like to feel close to someone. It is nice to have a friend to talk, laugh and do things with. Certainly, sometimes we need to be alone. We don't always want people around. But we would feel lonely if we never had a friend.\\nNo two people are just the same. Friends sometimes don't get on well. That doesn't mean that they no longer like each other. Most of the time they will make it up and become friends again.\\nSometimes friends move away. Then we feel very sad. We miss them very much but we can call them or write to them. We can also make new friends. It is encouraging to find out how much we like new people when we get to know them.\\nThere's more good news for people who have friends. They live longer than people who don't. Why? Friends can make us feel happy. Being happy helps you stay well. If someone cares about you, you will take better care of yourself.\\nQuestion: All people need friends because they   _  .\\nOptions: A: often feel lonely.\\nB: like to feel close to each other.\\nC: often move away.\\nD: want to live longer.","target":"B","rationale":"The article makes the following points:\\n- Everyone needs friends, so they don't feel lonely.\\n- Friends make us happy and help us live longer.\\n- We like to feel close to our friends. \\nAmong these three points, only B is a reason all people need friends because it states that everyone likes to \\"feel close\\" with their friends. So option B is the correct answer choice!"},{"source":"Earlier this year reporter Judith Miller was jailed for refusing to name the US-government source who identified a member of the US Central Intelligence Agency (CIA), Valerie Plame.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nJudith Miller is a member of CIA.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The sentence only says that Judith Miller is a reporter, it does not state her employment with the CIA. Thus we cannot conclude from this paragraph alone whether she is or isn't employed by the agency so our answer would be 'no'."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be classified as Hate Speech, Offensive or Normal. Given such a tweet, output the class the tweet belongs to. Hate Speech will contain threatening language towards the community targeted. Offensive language will contain abusive or discriminatory language towards the community targeted.\\n\\nbilly graham an amiable recycled kike salesman who withheld the most significant thing he knew from his assemblies of dunces","target":"Hate Speech","rationale":"The tweet contains a racial slur and objectifying language towards the Jewish community. The use of dehumanizing terms like \\"dunces\\" shows a clear intent to incite hatred and violence. Such language can be extremely harmful and can lead to real-life violence and discrimination, therefore the label for this tweet is Hate Speech."},{"source":"It would have to be this‚Ä¶\\nDonald Trump once cashed a $0.13 check‚Ä¶\\nIn 1990, writer from a ‚ÄúSpy Magazine‚Äù had a great idea for a prank:\\n‚ÄúWhat would happen if you sent checks for small amounts to celebrities and saw who cashed them, putting to test the theory that every man (and woman) has a price? In their words:\\n\\"We could however, send them checks for minuscule sums of money‚Äîsums so small they couldn‚Äôt fund as much as a minute of the recipients‚Äô existence‚Äîand see who would bother to bank these teensy amounts of money.\\"\\nSpy thought \\"some subterfuge\\" would be necessary‚Äîit'd be suspicious to get a check from the magazine that lampooned so many of the intended recipients. This was specifically true for Trump, who Spy once famously referred to as a \\"short-fingered vulgarian.\\"\\nSo, they created a fully funded and incorporated company called National Refund Clearinghouse, which allowed them to open a checking account. Then they drafted a letter explaining that the check was a refund for a small overcharge that had occurred in 1988‚Äîwhat the celebrities had been overcharged for was never mentioned. They sent the checks out (initially for $1.11) to 58 well-known people like Cher, Henry Kissinger, and, of course, Donald Trump. Of the 58, 26 cashed the checks‚ÄîDonald included.\\nThe magazine drafted a followup letter and checks for $0.64 to those 26 people to see who would take more free money. Thirteen‚Äîincluding Donald Trump‚Äîdeposited the checks worth two quarters, a dime, and four pennies into their banks.\\nThen they went for one last score: in honor of those 13 people, 13 more checks for $0.13. Two people cashed them: a Saudi arms dealer named Adnan Khashoggi, and Donald Trump.\\nSeriously.‚Äù\\nI really don‚Äôt know if this is the most ‚Äúcheapskate‚Äù thing, on just CRAZY fiscal responsibility. But if I had to pick, this would get my vote‚Ä¶\\nresources: Splinter - The truth hurts\\nAfter the $0.13 checks were deposited, Spy Magazine probably:\\n- published a story about sending out the checks\\n- not enough information\\n- asked for all their money back\\n- sent out another check for $0.04","target":"published a story about sending out the checks","rationale":"This question is about Donald Trump once cashing a $0.13 check and the magazine's subsequent actions.\\nThe article mentions that Spy Magazine sent out checks for small amounts of money to celebrities, including one for $0.13 to Donald Trump in 1990, and then published an article called \\"Donald Trump: The Short-Fingered Vulgarian Cashes His Thirteen-Cent Check.\\" This suggests that they ultimately decided on publishing their findings rather than asking the 13 people who had accepted money from them or sending another check (which would have been worth only 4 cents). \\nHence, based on this context, we can conclude that after writing the checks, Spy Magazine most likely published a story about sending out the checks."},{"source":"You are given a concatenated string consisting of two parts that are separated by a newline character. The first part is the user's initial question during a human computer conversation, the second part is a clarifying question asked by the computer in response to the question asked by the user. You should read the input, then generate a valid prediction of the user's response to the computer's clarifying question. A valid prediction will clarify the user's correct intent in the initial question.\\n\\nUser: I\\\\'m looking for information about indexed annuities. \\nComputer: are you considering purchasing an indexed annuity","target":"yes","rationale":"The user is looking for information about indexed annuities, and the computer wants to clarify whether the user is considering purchasing an indexed annuity. For this situation, a valid prediction of the user's response will be yes because this confirms that they are considering purchasing an indexed annuity."},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the name of the video that has the Tops of the Pops performance from the band that was featured on the Hype! documentary? , can you please find it? \\n\\n\\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\\" was first performed live on April 17, 1991 at the OK Hotel in Seattle, Washington. The performance is featured on the DVD of the 2004 box set With the Lights Out, while shorter clips are included on the Nevermind Classic Albums DVD, as well as the documentary film Hype! As the song's lyrics had not yet been entirely written, there are notable differences between it and the final version. For example, the first performance started with \\"Come out and play, make up the rules\\" instead of the eventual opening of \\"Load up on guns, bring your friends\\". A recording of the earlier version appears on With the Lights Out and again on Sliver: The Best of the Box. A similar early live performance of the song is found in the documentary 1991: The Year Punk Broke, filmed during a 1991 summer tour in Europe with Sonic Youth.\\nNirvana often altered the song's lyrics and tempo for live performances. Some live performances of the song had the line \\"our little group has always been\\" changed to \\"our little tribe has always been\\", which can be heard on the 1996 live album From the Muddy Banks of the Wishkah. Rolling Stone remarked that the Wishkah version of \\"Teen Spirit\\" \\"[found] Cobain's guitar reeling outside the song's melodic boundaries and sparking new life in that nearly played-out hit\\". A notable alternate performance of \\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\\" occurred on BBC's Top of the Pops in 1991, during which the band refused to mime to the pre-recorded backing track and Cobain sang in a deliberately low voice and altered numerous lyrics in the song (for example, \\"Load up on guns, bring your friends\\" became \\"Load up on drugs, kill your friends\\").   Cobain later said he was trying to sound like former Smiths frontman Morrissey. When Top of the Pops was cancelled in 2006, The Observer listed Nirvana's performance of \\"Smells Like Teen Spirit\\" as the third greatest in the show's history. This performance can be found on the 1994 home video Live! Tonight! Sold Out!!.","target":"Live! Tonight! Sold Out!!","rationale":"The answer is in the quote: \\"This performance can be found on the 1994 home video Live! Tonight! Sold Out!!\\"."},{"source":"Choose from options: Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below:\\nBeing a part of the class helps you have good impressions on the teacher\\n\\nHow to make the teacher think you are smart<br>Ask questions that dig deeper into the subject. Ask questions in class that show the teacher that you're paying attention. If you're confused about something, ask for some clarification.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"The answer is: \\"Yes\\", as the text shows that asking questions can make your teacher think you are smart."},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat is the Censorship and Entertainment Control Act, 1967?\\n- Censorship and Entertainment Control Act, 1967 The Censorship and Entertainments Control Act 1967 is an Act of Parliament in Zimbabwe.\\n- What is it for?\\n- Introduced under Ian Smith's largely unrecognised Rhodesian government, the target of the legislation has traditionally been obscenity and blasphemy in literature and film.\\n- Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n- This focus on crude or otherwise indecent material was continued into the 1990s.\\n- Is it still used today?\\n-","target":"It repealed elements of the Entertainments Control and Censorship Act, 1932, the Subversive Activities Act, 1950, and the Emergency Powers (Control of Publications) Act, 1965.","rationale":"The subject at hand is censorship legislation in Zimbabwe. The user is asking for more information about this law and the bot has already answered some questions that the user had asked. These questions were:\\n\\n  - What is the Censorship and Entertainment Control Act, 1967?\\n  - What is it for?\\n  - Are there any other interesting aspects about this article?\\n  - Is it still used today?\\n  \\nThe next question should be related to censorship legislation in Zimbabwe as well as providing an additional piece of information (the missing \\"What\\"). The given options do not provide any other information relevant to censorship laws or what they are used for. Based on these factors, option 1) \\"It repealed elements of the Entertainments Control and Censorship Act, 1932, the Subversive Activities Act, 1950, and the Emergency Powers (Control of Publications) Act, 1965.\\" seems like a reasonable response."},{"source":"Countess Nicolette de Gobignon pressed a wet cloth tothe King's brow. Though he lay there helpless, still she found him an awesome figure, like a fallen cathedral tower.\\nOnly two other men are as tall, she thought. Amalric and Orlando.\\nShe felt a pang of guilt. How could she be thinking about the troubadour here where her royal master lay slowly dying?\\nShe fixed her eyes on Louis, and on the ivory and wood crucifix that rose and fell on his chest with his labored breathing.\\nNicolette felt as if she, too, could hardly breathe. Across the crowded room a fire roared in a huge stone-lined fireplace. The air was stifling. She resented all that made it so, down to the woolen draperies and wall hangings and the thick carpets that sealed in the heat. But she knew that this northern chateau, Pontoise-les-Noyons, a day's ride from Paris, had had to be built to withstand cold, its walls thick and its windows tiny ? so totally unlike the bright, airy Languedoc manor she had grown up in.\\nSweat trickled down her brow and stung her eyes. Her breath was coming in little gasps. She felt as if she would faint if she couldn't go outside soon.\\nDozens of people, the King's family and courtiers, had packed themselves uselessly into the room, making it even more suffocating. Their whispers, like the buzzing of mosquitoes, irritated Nicolette.\\nAlmost all of them, she was sure, worried more about their own welfare than about the King's. And even Louis's wife and mother, though they grieved for him, were too distracted to do much to alleviate his suffering.\\nShe saw the King's lips quiver, and quickly she bent close to him. Any last words could be terribly important.\\n\\"Jerusalem,\\" he mumbled. \\"Towers - golden. Gates of pearl. Crystal waters.\\" Then he panted heavily.\\n\\"Hush, sire,\\" she whispered. \\"Rest easy.\\"\\nQuestion: Who grow-up in Languedoc manor?\\n===\\nThe answer to the above question is","target":"Nicolette","rationale":"The paragraph says that Nicolette was thinking of the troubadour, Orlando. Then she feels guilty and focuses on Louis's crucifix instead. The paragraph then goes back to talking about how hot it is in Pontoise-les-Noyons, which has a fireplace lined with stones and windows so tiny they don't let any air through. It also describes woolen draperies for warmth - all things we would not find in Languedoc manor where Nicolette grew up because there are no winters down south like this one at the chateau near Paris!\\nSo Nicolette must have grown up in Languedoc Manor!"},{"source":"Given news headlines, an edited word and funniness labels. The original sentence has word with the given format {word}. Create new headlines by replacing {word} in the original sentence with edit word. Your task is to generate answer \\"Yes\\" if an edited sentence matches funniness label, otherwise generate answer \\"No\\".  \\n\\nNews Headline: North Korea crisis becoming unsolvable , experts warn , as Trump heads to {Asia}  \\n Edit: bathroom \\n Label: Funny","target":"Yes","rationale":"The edited sentence is \\"North Korea crisis becoming unsolvable , experts warn , as Trump heads to bathroom\\". This sentence is funny because it implies that President Trump will solve the North Korean nuclear crisis in a bathroom. Therefore, the answer for this example is Yes."},{"source":"Article: Vancouver \\nNatural Resources\\nAs a major centre for the global forestry industry, Vancouver is host to many international forestry conferences and events, and the natural home of the massive BC forestry business. Companies such as Canfor and West Fraser Timber Co., the second and third largest lumber producers in the world, are headquartered in Vancouver. Vancouver is also a major centre for the mining industry.\\nInternational trade\\nInternational trade is a key part for Vancouver's economy. The city has Canada's largest port and is one of North America's major gateways for Pan-Pacific trade. The Port of Vancouver ranks first in North America in total foreign exports and second on the West Coast in total goods volume.\\nBanking and Financial\\nThe headquarters for HSBC Canada  is located in the Financial District in downtown. Canada's third largest commercial entity , Jim Pattison Group is also based in Vancouver.\\nInternational relation\\nVancouver is a major centre for diplomacy  and foreign relations. Most countries of the world have consulate or general offices in the Central Business District. In fact, many major diplomatic conferences are hosted by the city - including the world famous G7 summit with President Clinton, APEC, and the World Trade Organization. Greenpeace has its world headquarters in the city. Therefore, Vancouver was among the first North American cities to declare itself a Nuclear Weapons Free Zone.\\nTourism\\nTourism is a leading industry to Vancouver. The Whistler-Blackcomb Resort is among the most popular skiing resorts in North America, and will be the site of the downhill events of the 2010 Winter Olympics. Vancouver's beaches, parks, waterfronts, and mountain backdrops and its multi- cultural character attract more and more tourists.\\nFilm\\nVancouver was the source of the sobriquet \\"Hollywood North\\", for hosting the production of about ten percent of Hollywood's movies. Many U.S. television and films series are shot exclusively in Vancouver. This has partly been because of the favourable...\\nQuestion: Which of the following organizations or events is not related to Vancouver?\\nYes or no, is the answer \\"WHO\\"?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The article mentions that the World Health Organization (WHO) has its world headquarters in Vancouver. This makes \\"Yes\\" the correct answer, since WHO is related to Vancouver as a result of having their world headquarters there."},{"source":"Where would you use a turnstile that does not require inserting a ticket?\\n- theatre\\n- subway station\\n- train station\\n- amusement park\\n- store\\n\\nThe best answer is","target":"amusement park","rationale":"Turnstiles are used to restrict access, and tickets or tokens must be inserted for passage. The only exception is the turnstile that uses a barcode scanner; this type of turnstile does not require inserting a ticket, but instead requires scanning it beforehand. This kind of set-up would make sense in an amusement park because people have already paid for their admission when they bought their ticket online - before arriving at the park gate ‚Äì so there's no need to insert another one as proof of payment upon entry."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and the category to which it belongs. Your task is to classify whether the given category is correct or not by providing \\"True\\" and \\"False\\", respectively. Here are the definitions for the categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\",\\n\\nSentence: Chemokines play a pivotal role in the innate response to both bacterial and viral infections , and in mixed infections. \\n Section: background","target":"True","rationale":"The sentence provides information about the role of chemokines in responding to bacterial and viral infections. It also indicates that they play a critical part in mixed infections, which is an important aspect that was missing from previous works. So it can be considered as background information or knowledge on this topic. As such, True should be the correct output for this question."},{"source":"Given a trivia question, classify broad topical category from this list: 'theater', 'geology', 'book', 'tv', 'astronomy', 'aviation', 'military', 'government', 'boxing', 'projects', 'metropolitan_transit', 'law', 'venture_capital', 'broadcast', 'biology', 'people', 'influence', 'baseball', 'spaceflight', 'media_common', 'cvg', 'opera', 'olympics', 'chemistry', 'visual_art', 'conferences', 'sports', 'language', 'travel', 'location', 'award', 'dining', 'martial_arts', 'comic_strips', 'computer', 'user', 'tennis', 'music', 'organization', 'food', 'event', 'transportation', 'fictional_universe', 'measurement_unit', 'meteorology', 'distilled_spirits', 'symbols', 'architecture', 'freebase', 'internet', 'fashion', 'boats', 'cricket', 'film', 'medicine', 'finance', 'comic_books', 'celebrities', 'soccer', 'games', 'time', 'geography', 'interests', 'common', 'base', 'business', 'periodicals', 'royalty', 'education', 'type', 'religion', 'automotive', 'exhibitions'.\\n\\nWho was the Russian author of 'Taras Bulba' and 'Dead Souls'?","target":"book","rationale":"The author of the two books is Gogol, a Russian writer."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"PS3's hardware has also been used to build supercomputers for high-performance computing. Fixstars Solutions sells a version of Yellow Dog Linux for PlayStation 3 (originally sold by Terra Soft Solutions). RapidMind produced a stream programming package for PS3, but were acquired by Intel in 2009. Also, on January 3, 2007, Dr. Frank Mueller, Associate Professor of Computer science at NCSU, clustered 8 PS3s. Mueller commented that the 256 MB of system RAM is a limitation for this particular application and is considering attempting to retrofit more RAM. Software includes: Fedora Core 5 Linux ppc64, MPICH2, OpenMP v 2.5, GNU Compiler Collection and CellSDK 1.1. As a more cost-effective alternative to conventional supercomputers, the U.S. military has purchased clusters of PS3 units for research purposes. Retail PS3 Slim units cannot be used for supercomputing, because PS3 Slim lacks the ability to boot into a third-party OS.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What is the advantage to using PS3 clusters over standard supercomputers?","target":"cost-effective","rationale":"The passage mentions that the U.S. military uses PS3 clusters for research purposes, because they are a cost-effective alternative to conventional supercomputers. Therefore, this is also an advantage of using them over standard supercomputers as well."},{"source":"Given an abstract of a paper, generate a title for this paper such that conveys the key focus of the paper.\\n\\nAbstract: Ball-and-socket ankle is a rare deformity associated with such pre-existing conditions as congenital shortening of the lower limb, coalition of tarsal bones, absent digital rays and aplasia or hypoplasia of the fibula. We have observed seven patients with this deformity for an average of six years from initial examination at 20 days to 3.5 years. Arthrography showed that the configuration of the ankle was apparently normal in patients under 10 months of age and that a ball-and-socket joint develops by four to five years of age, possibly in compensation for the loss of inversion and eversion caused by tarsal coalition. Ball-and-socket joint is therefore probably not congenital, but is an acquired deformity secondary to various pre-existing congenital conditions.","target":"Genesis of the ball-and-socket ankle","rationale":"The title should aim to summarize the main findings of the paper regarding the genesis of a ball-and-socket ankle. The abstract provides information about seven patients with this deformity and their condition over time, and it also includes a discussion about whether or not this deformity is congenital or acquired. Therefore, my suggestion would be to include these concepts in the title: \\"Genesis of the ball-and-socket ankle\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural stereotype. A stereotype is an over-generalized belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: The musician was a _ thinker.","target":"creative","rationale":"A cultural stereotype that is commonly associated with musicians is that they are creative people."},{"source":"Question: Do girls who are malnourished start menustrating earlier or later than those with high-fat diets?\\nAnswer: Consequently, girls who have a high-fat diet and who are not physically active begin menstruating earlier, on average, than girls whose diet contains less fat and whose activities involve fat reducing exercise (e.g. ballet and gymnastics).\\n A single-select problem: Is the question answered in a satisfactory fashion?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The answer provided in the passage only discusses girls who have a high-fat diet and are not physically active, as opposed to both groups of girls. Hence, it is unclear whether malnourished girls start menstruating earlier or later than those with a normal fat intake."},{"source":"OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nDoes \\"By the early 1940s, the company was concentrating on lower-budget productions that were the company's main staple: westerns, melodramas, serials and sequels to the studio's horror pictures, the latter now solely B pictures.\\" correctly answer the question of When did Universal make Tom Mix westerns?","target":"no","rationale":"The statement talks about a range of movies Universal produced, including Tom Mix westerns. The question only asks when they made the Tom Mix westerns, not other types of films as well. So it is incorrect to say that this answer correctly addresses the question and so our answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a statement spoken by a politician in natural language and the subject of the discussion for the given statement. Your task is to determine if the given subject of the discussion is correct for the given statement. The subject can be multiple words. Answer with \\"True\\" if it's the correct subject of discussion or return \\"False\\" if it's incorrect.\\n\\nStatement: Forty percent of the undocumented workers in this country entered the U.S. legally and overstayed their visa. \\n Subject: health-care","target":"False","rationale":"The statement says that 40% of undocumented workers entered the U.S. legally, but does not mention the subject of \\"health-care.\\" Therefore, health care is an incorrect subject for the statement and should be marked as False."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue between a user and an assistant, where users and assistants converse about geographic topics like geopolitical entities and locations. The task here is to find if the dialogue is by the user or assistant. Classify your answers into user and assistant.\\n\\nIn regard to the demographics of Malta, Malta has experienced significant emigration which is a result of the collapse of a construction boom in 1907. In the 20th century, most emigrants went to different places in the New World, particularly to Australia, Canada, and the United States.","target":"assistant","rationale":"The text \\"In regard to the demographics of Malta\\" suggests a response from an assistant."},{"source":"The input is a conversation between an automated system and a user, followed by a question. The user is looking for suggestions for pubs, restaurants and coffee shops in Cambridge. In the dialogue, the user may provide some criteria for the type of place they want such as price range, cuisine, etc. Similarly, the user may ask details of the place suggested by the system such as phone number, address, etc. The answer of the question has to be a Yes or a No. Given such a dialogue, answer the given question based on the information present in the dialogue.\\n\\nSystem: 'Thank you for calling the Cambridge Information system. Your call will be recorded for research purposes. You may ask for information about a place to eat, such as a restaurant, a pub, or a cafe. How may I help you?'\\nUser: 'sil'\\nSystem: 'What kind of price range are you looking for? For example, cheap, or moderate.'\\nUser: 'im looking for a restaurant in barnwell'\\nSystem: 'The Wheatsheaf, which is in the Barnwell part of town, is an outstanding restaurant.'\\nUser: 'can i have the address and postcode'\\nSystem: 'The Wheatsheaf, which is in the area with the postcode CB5 9AD, is on Stow Road, Stow-Cum-Quy.'\\nUser: 'thank you good bye'\\nQuestion: 'Did the user ask whether children are allowed or not?'","target":"No","rationale":"The user did not ask about whether children are allowed or not, so the answer is No."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a sentence, and you should determine whether it is overruling or non-overruling. In law, an overruling sentence is a statement that nullifies a previous case decision as a precedent by a constitutionally valid statute or a decision by the same or higher ranking court which establishes a different rule on the point of law involved. Classify your answers into overruling or non-overruling\\n\\nhowever, we disapprove angelus to the extent that it holds section 733.212(3) does not bar objections that a personal representative was never qualified to serve.","target":"overruling","rationale":"The sentence states that the previous decision on the point of law is not valid and also establishes a different rule for that point of law. This shows that the sentence is overruling."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage which has extra information available on certain terms mentioned in it, i.e., the proper nouns in the passage. Your job is to determine whether information from more than one term is needed to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: When was the technology that is an innovation of Crunchfish using webcam as a sensor first invented?  Passage:Crunchfish is a Swedish technology company in Malm√∂ that develops gesture recognition software for the mobile phone and tablet market. Crunchfish was founded in 2010 with an initial focus to create innovations for the iOS and Android app markets. Gesture recognition using a standard webcam as main gesture sensor was one of their core innovations and the company is now focusing on touchless interaction based on camera based gestures. In 2013, April, the company was selected a '2013 Red Herring Top 100' company by Red Herring (magazine). Crunchfish produces gesture sensing software, a set of customized mid-air gesture recognition solutions, named A3D‚Ñ¢, to global mobile device manufacturers and app developers. Crunchfish cooperates with smartphone manufacturers to enable Crunchfish gesture sensing technology in their partners mobile devices. Crunchfish developed the touchless functions in Chinese Gionee's smartphone Elife E6, launched in China, July, 2013 and in India and Africa in August, 2013","target":"b","rationale":"The question only asks for the date that Crunchfish's technology was invented, which is mentioned directly in the passage as \\"Gesture recognition using a standard webcam as main gesture sensor was one of their core innovations\\". No other information or proper nouns are needed to answer the question."},{"source":"In this task, you need to provide the correct option for a given problem on probability from the provided options.\\n\\nProblem: three unbiased coins are tossed . what is the probability of getting at most two heads ? \\nOptions: a ) 3 / 4 , b ) 1 / 4 , c ) 3 / 8 , d ) 7 / 8 , e ) none of these","target":"d","rationale":"The given options are not the correct answer. It is true that the probability of getting exactly 2 heads is 3/8, but this doesn't make it impossible to get 1 or 0 heads. If we have at least one tail, then there's a good chance that we'll get 1 head and 1 tail (1/4 chance), which means we could also get 0 heads and 2 tails (another 1/4 chance). Therefore, our total probability of getting at most two heads is \\\\(3/8 + 1/4 + 1/4 = 7/8\\\\)."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. If the conversation begins with a question, label it '1' otherwise '0'.\\n\\n Person1:     Which kinds of meat are most popular in your country ?  \\n Person2:  We eat a lot of chicken , pork and beef . You eat those meat a lot in your country too , don ‚Äô t you ?  \\n Person1:      Yes , we do . We also eat a lot of lamb .  \\n Person2:  yes . I ‚Äô Ve heard that people in your country like to eat lamb chops .  \\n Person1:      That ‚Äô s right . They tastes so good ! We eat them with mint sauce . Have you every tried them ?  \\n Person2:  Yes , I have . I tried them when I visited your country last year . I thought they were very tasty . Can you cook them ?  \\n Person1:      I certainly can . If I can get some from the butcher ‚Äô s , I ‚Äô ll cook them for you .  \\n Person2:  That sounds great . I'll bring a bottle of wine .","target":"1","rationale":"The conversation begins with \\"Which kinds of meat are most popular in your country?\\" said by Person1, which is a question. Since the conversation begins with a question, the answer is '1'."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string and you should find the longest substring that is a palindrome. A palindrome is a string that is the same backwards as it is forwards. If the shortest possible palindrome is length 1 you should return the first character.\\n\\neeeexxexexex","target":"xexexex","rationale":"The longest palindrome in the given string is 'xexexex'."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: Which people want to kill Ned for money? from the following article ?\\n\\nNed Ravine, who is both a police officer and lawyer (who often defends the people he arrests), believes that he knows everything about women, and says that he will throw away his badge if anyone ever proves him wrong. While on a stakeout, he encounters a seductive woman named Lola Cain; the next day, Lola shows up at his law office, saying that she needs him to look over some papers she has come across. Meanwhile, Max Shady, who was just released from prison after seven years, starts stalking Ned, planning to kill him for failing to successfully defend Max in court.\\nNed's wife Lana and her car mechanic Frank, with whom she is having an affair, start plotting to kill Ned in order to collect on his accident insurance, which has a triple indemnity rider; if Ned is shot, falls from a northbound train, and drowns in a freshwater stream, Lana will collect nine million dollars.\\nLola gets Ned to come to her house to examine the \\"papers\\", which are actually a laundry receipt and an expired lottery ticket, and the two of them end up having sex in various wild ways. The next morning, Ned says that they can never do that again because he loves his wife; this drives Lola to start stalking Ned.\\nA few days later, Ned takes the train to go to a legal symposium; Lana and Frank are also on the train, and so is Max. When the train passes over a lake, Lana shoots Max 36 times with a revolver, mistaking him for Ned, and he backflips through the door to his death; Ned thinks that Lana had acted to save his life. He arrests Lana, and then defends her in court, getting her cleared of all charges. Lana later kills Frank, believing that he was going to abandon her, by pinning him against a wall with his power drill; Lola witnesses this, and starts blackmailing Lana.","target":"Lana","rationale":"The rationale for the answer is that Ned's wife Lana and her car mechanic Frank, with whom she is having an affair, start plotting to kill Ned in order to collect on his accident insurance.\\nThis means that Lana wants money from killing her husband by faking an accident. Therefore it can be inferred that this makes them want to kill him for money."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nbuncha nigger lovers trying to be hip wat morons","target":"nigger lovers","rationale":"The given tweet is offensive because it includes the racial slur \\"nigger\\" and denigrates a group of people. The phrase \\"buncha nigger lovers trying to be hip wat morons\\" contains an instance of this word."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the alphabetical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no alphabetical element in the list\\n\\n['885', '1385', '6081', '5743', '9669']","target":"0","rationale":"Since there is no alphabetical element in the given list, the final output return 0"},{"source":"Tuesday's Senate primary in Kansas ended another ugly showdown that pit a tea party-backed challenger against an establishment Republican incumbent. CNN projects incumbent Sen. Pat Roberts has fended off conservative challenger Milton Wolf in the state's GOP Senate primary. In his victory speech Roberts said that \\"we celebrate tonight\\" and that \\"we have another job starting first thing tomorrow.\\" \\"That job is to unite Republicans under a common and vital cause,\\" he said. \\"Unity must happen if we are to keep Kansas red. It must happen if we are going to defeat an Obama agenda and send Harry Reid back!\\"\\n@highlight\\nIncumbent Sen. Pat Roberts beats tea party-backed challenger Milton Wolf\\n@highlight\\nThe Kansas race was largely defined by personal attacks on both sides\\n@highlight\\nTea party will get another chance to knock off an establishment candidate in Tennessee\\n@highlight\\nVoters in Michigan, Missouri and Washington also voted Tuesday\\nAt the same time, the @placeholder' campaign over the past couple of months went up with TV ads reminding voters that Wolf, a radiologist, posted X-ray images of mortal injuries and made light of them and the victims.\\n\\nPick one option, \\"@placeholder\\" refers to:\\n- CNN\\n- GOP Senate\\n- Harry Reid\\n- Kansas\\n- Michigan\\n- Milton Wolf\\n- Missouri\\n- Obama\\n- Pat Roberts\\n- Republican\\n- Republicans\\n- Roberts\\n- Senate\\n- Tennessee\\n- Unity\\n- Washington","target":"Roberts","rationale":"The @placeholder' campaign in the paragraph refers to a particular candidate's campaign, as evidenced by the line that says \\"Incumbent Sen. Pat Roberts beats tea party-backed challenger Milton Wolf\\".\\nIn his victory speech, Senator Roberts said: \\"Unity must happen if we are going to defeat an Obama agenda and send Harry Reid back!\\"\\nTherefore, it is most likely that the Roberts' (Senator Pat Robert) team ran this ad reminding voters about these X-ray images of mortal injuries posted by Dr. Milton Wolf on social media.\\n\\n\\nHence, \\"@placeholder\\" can be replaced with 'Roberts'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: Pyridazine is an aromatic heterocycle that contains in its structure: \\n Options:  <0> A nitrogen <1> Two nitrogens <2> Three nitrogens <3> Four nitrogens <4> No nitrogen","target":"chemistry","rationale":"The given question is asking about the number of nitrogen atoms in a chemical compound. This topic falls under chemistry, so this question can be classified as being about chemistry."},{"source":"Institute of technology\\nIn higher education, Politecnico refers to a technical university awarding degrees in engineering. Historically there were two Politecnici, one in each of the two largest industrial cities of the north:\\n\\nQ: What term in higher education refers to technical universities that award engineering degrees?","target":"Politecnico","rationale":"\\"Politecnico refers to a technical university awarding degrees in engineering.\\""},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to who plays jim in season 3 of trollhunters??","target":"Emile Hirsch","rationale":"The character Jim is played by actor Emile Hirsch in the third season of ‚ÄúTrollhunters‚Äù.\\nThis information can be verified via a review of imdb.com for the TV series \\"Trollhunters\\", which states that Emile Hirsch plays Jim Lake Jr./Trollhunter (voice) in Season 3 episodes 1-13, as well as through various other credible websites that cite this same fact."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5. Your job is to generate a title for the story that makes complete sense. The title must be short, with less than three words, use simple language, and include the main topic of the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: Sally bought a book from the library. Sentence 2: She opened it to page 3. Sentence 3: She read the words but they didn't make since to her. Sentence 4: She looked at the cover. Sentence 5: She got a Chinese book by accident.","target":"Chinese","rationale":"The title of a story should be short and simple. The main topic of the story is that Sally got a Chinese book by accident, so we can simply use the word \\\\\\"Chinese\\\\\\" as the title."},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: If \\"Women sitting while in thought.\\", can we conclude \\"Women running a marathon.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"Women sitting does not imply that women are running a marathon. The latter is more likely to be inferred from Women preparing for a marathon or something similar, which was not mentioned in the context."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the numerical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no numerical element in the list.\\n\\n['6691', '1529', '3685', '5541', '5079']","target":"5","rationale":"The given list has 5 numerical elements."},{"source":"Question: \\"what is the byword for all that is great and good?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"His birthday (14 December 1895) was the 34th anniversary of the death of his great-grandfather, Prince Albert, the Prince Consort. Uncertain of how the Prince Consort's widow, Queen Victoria, would take the news of the birth, the Prince of Wales wrote to the Duke of York that the Queen had been \\"rather distressed\\". Two days later, he wrote again: \\"I really think it would gratify her if you yourself proposed the name Albert to her\\". Queen Victoria was mollified by the proposal to name the new baby Albert, and wrote to the Duchess of York: \\"I am all impatience to see the new one, born on such a sad day but rather more dear to me, especially as he will be called by that dear name which is a byword for all that is great and good\\". Consequently, he was baptised \\"Albert Frederick Arthur George\\" at St. Mary Magdalene's Church near Sandringham three months later.[a] As a great-grandson of Queen Victoria, he was known formally as His Highness Prince Albert of York from birth. Within the family, he was known informally as \\"Bertie\\". His maternal grandmother, the Duchess of Teck, did not like the first name the baby had been given, and she wrote prophetically that she hoped the last name \\"may supplant the less favoured one\\".\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Albert","rationale":"The sentence \\"I am all impatience to see the new one, born on such a sad day but rather more dear to me, especially as he will be called by that dear name which is a byword for all that is great and good\\" in context suggests that Albert was very well known. Since there were two members of royal family with similar names (\\"Albert Frederick Arthur George\\") we can assume it's referring to Prince Albert (Queen Victoria‚Äôs husband)."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the abstract of a research paper. Your task is to generate a summary of this abstract. Your summary should not be very short, but it's better if it's not more than 30 words.\\n\\nPerson re-identification (re-ID) aims at identifying the same persons' images across different cameras. However, domain diversities between different datasets pose an evident challenge for adapting the re-ID model trained on one dataset to another one. State-of-the-art unsupervised domain adaptation methods for person re-ID transferred the learned knowledge from the source domain by optimizing with pseudo labels created by clustering algorithms on the target domain. Although they achieved state-of-the-art performances, the inevitable label noise caused by the clustering procedure was ignored. Such noisy pseudo labels substantially hinders the model's capability on further improving feature representations on the target domain. In order to mitigate the effects of noisy pseudo labels, we propose to softly refine the pseudo labels in the target domain by proposing an unsupervised framework, Mutual Mean-Teaching (MMT), to learn better features from the target domain via off-line refined hard pseudo labels and on-line refined soft pseudo labels in an alternative training manner.   In addition, the common practice is to adopt both the classification loss and the triplet loss jointly for achieving optimal performances in person re-ID models. However, conventional triplet loss cannot work with softly refined labels. To solve this problem, a novel soft softmax-triplet loss is proposed to support learning with soft pseudo triplet labels for achieving the optimal domain adaptation performance. The proposed MMT framework achieves considerable improvements of 14.4%, 18.2%, 13.1% and 16.4% mAP on Market-to-Duke, Duke-to-Market, Market-to-MSMT and Duke-to-MSMT unsupervised domain adaptation tasks.","target":"A framework that conducts online refinement of pseudo labels with a novel soft softmax-triplet loss for unsupervised domain adaptation on person re-identification","rationale":"Here's a brief summary:\\\\nA framework that conducts online refinement of pseudo labels with a novel soft softmax-triplet loss for unsupervised domain adaptation on person re-identification."},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 1, equation weights = [0, 7]","target":"7","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 0x^1 + 7\\\\nSubstituting x = 1, we get: 07"},{"source":"Passions surrounding Germany's final match at the Euro 2004 soccer championships turned violent when a woman stabbed her partner in the head because she didn't want to watch the game on television.\\n\\nQ with options: Can we draw the following conclusion?\\nA woman passionately wanted to watch the soccer championship.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The fact that the woman stabbed her partner in the head because she didn't want to watch the game on television, does not mean that a woman passionately wanted to watch soccer championship. The answer is no."},{"source":"News 1 :  Have you ever thought of being able to fly around the world in a few hours though it is about 40,000 kilometers? One day,maybe you can. Last Saturday,the American X-43A airplane made its first flight. It reached a speed of 8,000 kilometres an hour. This makes it the fastest plane in the world. The X-43A is only three to four metres long,but it's very heavy:it weighs 1,270 kilogrames.\\nNews 2 :  Have you ever got angry at books that are full of mistakes? Don't worry,things will get better soon. Last week,China started checking textbooks,dictionaries and children's books all over the country. The government said the results of the checking would come out at the end of June.\\nNews 3 : There will be a new \\"star\\" in the sky soon. China plans to send a satellite  into space by December 2006. It will stay in space for one year. It will go around the moon and take pictures. It must be very expensive,right? That's for sure-1. 4 billion yuan!\\nNews 4 : Floods across the northern Mexican  state of Coahuila killed at least 32 people and left100 more missing. It was reported on Monday. The heavy rain hit the state all night last Friday,so some banks of the river were broken. Along the river about 3,000 families were seriously affected .\\nWhich of the following about the new \\"star\\" is NOT TRUE?\\nA) It will help us know more about the moon.\\nB) It will go around the earth for one year.\\nC) It will cost 1. 4 billion yuan.\\nD) It will be sent up by the year 2006.","target":"B","rationale":"News 3: There will be a new \\"star\\" in the sky soon. China plans to send a satellite into space by December 2006. It will stay in space for one year. It will go around the moon and take pictures, which is A).\\nIt must be very expensive,right? That's for sure-1. 4 billion yuan!, so it costs 1.4billion yuan as C) said .\\nAnd D) is true because it says that China plan‚Ä¶by Decembe...2006 ,so we can conclude that \\nthe year of sending up this star would not beyond 2006 as required by option B)."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the occurrences of the given word in the given sentence.\\n\\nSentence: 'the sunlight coming through the window of a kitchen'. Count the occurrences of the word 'the' in the given sentence.","target":"2","rationale":"Given the sentence 'the sunlight coming through the window of a kitchen', let's count how many times the word 'the' appears in the sentence.\\\\n1. The 1st instance is at the beginning of this sentence, so it counts as one (1).\\\\n2. The 2nd instance is at the end of this sentence, so it counts as one (1).\\\\n3. There are no other instances that contain 'the'.\\\\nThe total number is 2\\\\n"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- XMODEM is a simple file transfer protocol developed as a quick hack by Ward Christensen for use in his 1977 MODEM.ASM terminal program . It allowed users to transmit files between their computers when both sides used MODEM . Keith Petersen made a minor update to always turn on \`\` quiet mode '' , and called the result XMODEM . XMODEM became extremely popular in the early bulletin board system ( BBS ) market , largely because it was so simple to implement . It was also fairly inefficient , and as modem speeds increased this problem led to the development of a number of modified versions of XMODEM to improve performance or address other problems with the protocol . Christensen believed his original XMODEM to be \`\` the single most modified program in computing history '' . Chuck Forsberg collected a number of modifications into his YMODEM protocol , but poor implementation led to a further fracturing before they were re-unified by his later ZMODEM protocol . XMODEM , like most file transfer protocols , breaks up the original data into a series of \`\` packets '' that are sent to the receiver , along with additional information allowing the receiver to determine whether that packet was correctly received .\\n\\n- The history of computing is longer than the history of computing hardware and modern computing technology and includes the history of methods intended for pen and paper or for chalk and slate, with or without the aid of tables. The timeline of computing presents a summary list of major developments in computing by date.\\n\\n- A computer file is a computer resource for recording data discretely in a computer storage device. Just as words can be written to paper, so can information be written to a computer file.\\n\\n- Illinois is a state in the midwestern region of the United States, achieving statehood in 1818. It is the 5th most populous state and 25th largest state in terms of land area, and is often noted as a microcosm of the entire country. The word \\"Illinois\\" comes from the Algonquin word for \\"tribe of superior men\\". With Chicago in the northeast, small industrial cities and great agricultural productivity in central and northern Illinois, and natural resources like coal, timber, and petroleum in the south, Illinois has a diverse economic base and is a major transportation hub. The Port of Chicago connects the state to other global ports from the Great Lakes, via the Saint Lawrence Seaway, to the Atlantic Ocean, as well as the Great Lakes to the Mississippi River, via the Illinois River. For decades, O'Hare International Airport has been ranked as one of the world's busiest airports. Illinois has long had a reputation as a bellwether both in social and cultural terms and politics.\\n\\n- West Bend is the county seat of Washington County, Wisconsin, United States, in southeastern Wisconsin. As of the 2010 census, the population was 31,078.\\n\\n- Chicago (or ), officially the City of Chicago, is the third-most populous city in the United States, and the fifth-most populous city in North America. With over 2.7¬†million residents, it is the most populous city in the state of Illinois and the Midwestern United States, and the county seat of Cook County. The Chicago metropolitan area, often referred to as Chicagoland, has nearly 10¬†million people and is the third-largest in the U.S.\\n\\n- File transfer is the transmission of a computer file through a communication channel from one computer system to another. Typically, file transfer is mediated by a communications protocol. In the history of computing, a large number of file transfer protocols have been designed for different contexts.\\n\\n- CBBS (Computerized Bulletin Board System) was a computer program created by Ward Christensen to allow him and other computer hobbyists to exchange information between each another.\\n\\n- Ward Christensen (born 1945 in West Bend, Wisconsin, United States) is the co-founder of the CBBS bulletin board, the first bulletin board system (BBS) ever brought online. Christensen, along with partner Randy Suess, started development during a blizzard in Chicago, Illinois, and officially established CBBS four weeks later, on February 16, 1978.\\n\\n- A computer is a device that can be instructed to carry out an arbitrary set of arithmetic or logical operations automatically. The ability of computers to follow a sequence of operations, called a \\"program\\", make computers very flexible and useful. Such computers are used as control systems for a very wide variety of industrial and consumer devices. This includes simple special purpose devices like microwave ovens and remote controls, factory devices such as industrial robots and computer assisted design, but also in general purpose devices like personal computers and mobile devices such as smartphones. The Internet is run on computers and it connects millions of other computers.\\n\\n- A bulletin board system, or BBS, is a computer server running software that allows users to connect to the system using a terminal program. Once logged in, the user can perform functions such as uploading and downloading software and data, reading news and bulletins, and exchanging messages with other users through email, public message boards, and sometimes via direct chatting. Many BBSes also offer on-line games, in which users can compete with each other, and BBSes with multiple phone lines often provide chat rooms, allowing users to interact with each other. Bulletin board systems were in many ways a precursor to the modern form of the World Wide Web, social networks and other aspects of the Internet. Low-cost, high-performance modems drove the use of online services and BBSes through the early 1990s. \\"Infoworld\\" estimated there were 60,000 BBSes serving 17 million users in the United States alone in 1994, a collective market much larger than major online services like CompuServe.\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the paragraphs above, decide what entity has the relation 'instance of' with 'communications protocol'.","target":"xmodem","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"xmodem\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and the category to which it belongs. Your task is to classify whether the given category is correct or not by providing \\"True\\" and \\"False\\", respectively. Here are the definitions for the categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\",\\n\\nSentence: and serum carboxy-terminal telopeptide was significantly lower at 6 weeks after SAON induction. \\n Section: purpose","target":"False","rationale":"The sentence describes a specific procedure used in the experiment and provides the main findings of this procedure. Therefore, the correct category for this sentence is \\"Method\\", not \\"Purpose\\". Hence, the answer is False."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What does the third \\"S\\" in \\"MANPADS\\" refer to?\\nContext: NATO defines anti-aircraft warfare (AAW) as \\"measures taken to defend a maritime force against attacks by airborne weapons launched from aircraft, ships, submarines and land-based sites.\\" In some armies the term All-Arms Air Defence (AAAD) is used for air defence by non-specialist troops. Other terms from the late 20th century include GBAD (Ground Based AD) with related terms SHORAD (Short Range AD) and MANPADS (\\"Man Portable AD Systems\\": typically shoulder-launched missiles). Anti-aircraft missiles are variously called surface-to-air missile, abbreviated and pronounced \\"SAM\\" and Surface to Air Guided Weapon (SAGW).","target":"Systems","rationale":"The NATO definition of anti-aircraft warfare refers to \\"measures taken to defend a maritime force against attacks by airborne weapons launched from aircraft, ships, submarines and land-based sites\\" as well as the term All-Arms Air Defence (AAAD) which is used for air defence by non-specialist troops. Other terms include GBAD (\\"Ground Based AD\\") with related terms SHORAD (\\"Short Range AD\\"), MANPADS (\\"Man Portable AD Systems\\": typically shoulder-launched missiles), or Anti-aircraft missiles are variously called surface-to air missile abbreviated and pronounced SAM or Surface to Air Guided Weapon SAGW\\nBased on this context it can be inferred that in \\"MANPADS\\", the letter ‚ÄúS‚Äù stands for systems"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a pair of action statements. Your task is to check if you can conclusively identify which statement is less ethical or not. Answer: 'no' if one of the statements is less ethical, and 'yes' otherwise.\\n\\nACTION1: not letting my brothers brother in-law take a kitten ACTION2: saying doing something illegal was stupid","target":"yes","rationale":"The two action statements are: \\\\\\"not letting my brothers brother in-law take a kitten\\\\\\" and \\\\\\"saying doing something illegal was stupid\\\\\\". The author does not provide enough information to conclusively determine which action is more or less ethical than the other. While it is unethical to do illegal things, the context of why this was done and what kind of illegal actions were taken, matters significantly. Similarly, the second statement does not seem to be unethical in itself. However, if the speaker's intention for saying that someone's actions were \\"\\"stupid\\"\\" was intended as an insult or derogatory remark that would make it unethical to say so. In other words, there isn't enough information given about either action to conclusively judge which one is more or less ethical than the other. Therefore, the answer should be 'yes'."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the elicit-pref strategy, otherwise output No. elicit-pref is a cooperative negotiation strategy. It is used to discover the preference order of the opponent in the negotiation.\\n\\nContext: 'Me tooüôÇ. I packed a lot of food so I have plenty to spare' 'that's awesome. I think I need more food myself, but I have tons of water.' 'I really am in need of firewood and would appreciate the extra water if you can spare some'\\nUtterance: 'Would it be okay if I was to get 3 food packages, and spare you 3 water packages?'","target":"No","rationale":"The elicitation strategy is used to discover an opponent's preferences, but the speaker in this utterance does not do that. Instead, they state their own needs and ask if the opponent would be willing to provide them with food and water.\\n\\nSince the utterance in this case does not use the elicit-pref strategy, the answer is No."},{"source":"US Steel could even have a technical advantage over Nucor since one new method of steel making it is considering, thin strip casting, may produce higher quality steel than the Nucor thin slab technique.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that this sentence is true?\\nUS Steel has competitors.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"The paragraph talks about how US Steel is considering a new method of steel making in order to compete with Nucor, which suggests that the company has competitors. Therefore, we can conclude this statement is true and choose \\"Yes\\" as an answer."},{"source":"Determine the question that you might have asked to get back the following answer for the given context\\nContext: Leucothea was daughter of Orchamus and sister of Clytia. She fell in love with Apollo who disguised himself as Leucothea's mother to gain entrance to her chambers. Clytia, jealous of her sister because she wanted Apollo for herself, told Orchamus the truth, betraying her sister's trust and confidence in her. Enraged, Orchamus ordered Leucothea to be buried alive. Apollo refused to forgive Clytia for betraying his beloved, and a grieving Clytia wilted and slowly died. Apollo changed her into an incense plant, either heliotrope or sunflower, which follows the sun every day.;\\nAnswer: Orchamus;\\nQuestion:","target":"Who ordered Leucothea to be buried alive?","rationale":"The context is a description of the Greek mythological figure Leucothea. It states that she was ordered to be buried alive by her father Orchamus, who found out about Apollo disguising himself as his daughter's mother through Clytia.\\nTherefore, given this information in the context, it can be inferred that \\"Who ordered Leucothea to be buried alive?\\" would have generated an answer like: \\"\\"Orchamus\\"\\"."},{"source":"Read this and answer the question\\n\\nModern adult contemporary can be a variation of hot AC, and includes modern rock titles in its presentation. In 1997, Mike Marino of KMXB in Las Vegas described the format as reaching \\"an audience that has outgrown the edgier hip-hop or alternative music but hasn't gotten old and sappy enough for the soft ACs.\\" The format's artists included Alanis Morissette, Counting Crows, Gin Blossoms, Bon Jovi, Train, No Doubt, The Script, The Cranberries, Lifehouse, Sarah McLachlan, Sara Bareilles, John Mayer, Jewel, and Ingrid Michaelson. Unlike modern rock, which went after 18-34 men, this format appealed to women.\\n\\nWhere was the radio station KMXB based in 1997?","target":"Las Vegas","rationale":"The context talks about the radio station KMXB and states that it is based in Las Vegas."},{"source":"You are given a news article headline from BBC Yoruba and your task is to classify it into one of the following categories:  Africa, Entertainment, Health, Nigeria, Politics, Sport, or World.\\n\\nGhana Floods: √à√®y√†n m√©je p√†d√°n√∫ ·∫πÃÄm√≠ w·ªçn n√≠n√∫ √¨j√†mb√° ·∫πÃÄk√∫n omi","target":"Africa","rationale":"The headline translates as \\"Ghana Floods: Ten People Die in a Boat Accident\\". This is news about a flood in Ghana, which is located in Africa. Therefore, the category of this news article should be \\"Africa\\"."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"A charity is a nonprofit organisation that meets stricter criteria regarding its purpose and the method in which it makes decisions and reports its finances. For example, a charity is generally not allowed to pay its Trustees. In England and Wales, charities may be registered with the Charity Commission. In Scotland, the Office of the Scottish Charity Regulator serves the same function. Other organizations which are classified as nonprofit organizations elsewhere, such as trade unions, are subject to separate regulations, and are not regarded as \\"charities\\" in the technical sense.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What isn't a charity","target":"nonprofit organizations","rationale":"The passage states that charity must meet stricter criteria to be considered a nonprofit organization. So, you should pick \\"nonprofit organizations\\" as the answer for this question"},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story incoherent / implausible by indicating 1 or 2 in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nBeginning: Annabelle loves to sing. Middle 1: Annabelle was offered a solo. Middle 2: She never got opportunity to perform. Ending: Annabelle said yes and was excited for the opportunity.","target":"2","rationale":"Middle 1 indicates that Annabelle was offered a solo, which is an opportunity to perform. However, Middle 2 states that she never got the opportunity to perform. So this implies that Annabelle was not offered a solo and therefore makes less sense."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['e', 'y', '5551', 'Y', 'e', '2921']","target":"8472","rationale":"Given the list ['e', 'y', '5551', 'Y', 'e', '2921'], there are two numbers in the list: 5551 and 2921. The final result is calculated as 5551 + 2921 = 8472."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: My wife had a retirement party on September 3. She invited an ex coworker, Mary. Mary said she would come, but did not show. Mary later texted saying she had gone out drinking the day before. \\n Sentence: She did not get up until the party was over. \\n Character: I (myself)","target":"sad","rationale":"The protagonist is sad that Mary did not show up for the party."},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Daniel went to the bathroom. Fact 2- Sandra went to the hallway. Question: Where is Sandra? Answer: hallway","target":"Fact 2","rationale":"Fact 2 is necessary to answer the question \\"Where is Sandra?\\" correctly."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a multiple-choice question about healthcare. Answer the question based on your information and classify your answers into '1', '2', '3', and '4'.\\n\\nQuestion: The anterior pituitary gland: \\n Options:  <1> It is part of the hypothalamus. <2> It is regulated hormonally. <3> It communicates with the neurohypophysis. <4> It releases ADH and oxytocin. <5> It is formed by neurons.","target":"2","rationale":"The anterior pituitary gland is a part of the endocrine system and is regulated by hormones released by the hypothalamus. Therefore, the answer to this question is Option 2."},{"source":"Two analogies that signify affordances are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Affordance is the possibility of an action being done on an object, for example book is an affordance of writing. The phrase \\"A : B\\" implies that B is an affordance of A. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate affordance of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single object without further explanation.\\n\\nfire : employee. operate : ?","target":"machine","rationale":"If fire is an affordance of employee, then operate should be an affordance of machine."},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Madonna (entertainer):\\n\\nTo allow for greater movement while dancing and singing, Madonna was one of the earliest adopters of hands-free radio-frequency headset microphones, with the headset fastened over the ears or the top of the head, and the microphone capsule on a boom arm that extended to the mouth. Because of her prominent usage, the microphone design came to be known as the \\"Madonna mic\\". Metz noted that Madonna represents a paradox as she is often perceived as living her whole life as a performance. While her big-screen performances are panned, her live performances are critical successes. Madonna was the first artist to have her concert tours as reenactment of her music videos. Author Elin Diamond explained that reciprocally, the fact that images from Madonna's videos can be recreated in a live setting enhances the realism of the original videos. Thus her live performances have become the means by which mediatized representations are naturalized. Taraborrelli said that encompassing multimedia, latest technology and sound systems, Madonna's concerts and live performances are deemed as \\"extravagant show piece, a walking art show.\\"\\n\\nWhose concerts are extravagant live shows?","target":"Madonna's","rationale":"This is a pretty straightforward answer question. The article mentions that Madonna's concerts are deemed as \\"extravagant show piece, a walking art show.\\" Therefore, the correct answer would be \\"Madonna\\"."},{"source":"Given a passage as input, answer with the category to which the passage belongs. There are 5 categories - Sports and Fitness, Home and Garden, Hobbies and Crafts, Food and Entertaining, Cars & Other Vehicles. The answer should be one of the categories based on words from the passage which closely belong to the category.\\n\\nMake sure your car is on level ground with the hand brake on. Get out a 20p. Place the 20p flat in one of the grooves of the tread.Have an idea what the tyre should look,like.","target":"Cars & Other Vehicles","rationale":"The passage is about inspecting the tread of your tyres. It mentions \\"hand brake\\", \\"car\\", \\"flat in one of the grooves of the tread\\". All these words closely relate to Cars & Other Vehicles."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\nordinary","target":"weird","rationale":"The opposite of ordinary is weird."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an adjunct island or as an incorrect representation. A correct representation should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an adjunct island will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence using an adjunct island. An incorrect representation will be everything else.\\n\\nWhat has Ella brought all icicles after finding?","target":"bad","rationale":"The sentence is grammatically incorrect and cannot be easily interpreted as a representation of an adjunct island. Therefore, the answer is 'bad'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an answer, and your task is to generate a reasonable question for that answer.\\n\\nThey are coming over instead","target":"Are you visiting your parents this weekend?","rationale":"The answer \\"They are coming over instead\\" could be a reasonable answer to the question \\"Are you visiting your parents this weekend?\\""},{"source":"If \\"The customer walked into the bank and stabbed one of the tellers. He was immediately taken to the police station.\\", is \\"The teller was immediately taken to the police station.\\" correct?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes\\nAnswer:","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence states that the customer entered the bank and stabbed a teller, who was subsequently taken to the police station. The second statement suggests that it was in fact the teller who committed this crime by entering into the bank with intent of stabbing someone. However, as we can see from reading further on, he is actually being apprehended for his actions rather than being treated like an individual under attack or involved in self-defense. So then answer would be \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"As of the census of 2010, there were 520,116 people, 229,762 households, and 112,455 families residing in the city. The population density was 2,500.1 inhabitants per square mile (965.3/km¬≤). There were 209,609 housing units at an average density of 1,076.7 per square mile (415.7/km¬≤). The racial makeup of the city was 69.7% White (down from 94.8% in 1970), 5.0% Black or African-American, 2.7% Native American, 2.9% Asian, 0.2% Pacific Islander, 16.9% from other races, and 3.8% from two or more races. Hispanic or Latino of any race were 41.6% of the population. Non-Hispanic Whites were 47.2% of the population in 2010, down from 72.8% in 1970.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: Which was higher in 1970: the percentage of whites or the percentage of non-hispanic whites?","target":"White","rationale":"The text states that 94.8% of the population in 1970 were White and 72.8% of the population in 2010 were Non-Hispanic Whites, so you can conclude that the percentage of whites was higher in 1970 than it was for non-hispanic whites. The answer is therefore \\"White\\"."},{"source":"Premise: Agencies' Annual Performance Plans Under the Results  An Assessment Guide to Facilitate Congressional Decisionmaking (GAO/GGD/AIMD-10.\\n\\nHypothesis: There is no guide to facilitate decision making in Congress. \\n\\nDoes the premise entail the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise talks about Congress, but the hypothesis is focused on a guide to facilitate decision making in Congress. The first sentence of the context says that agencies' annual performance plans under results were created by GAO/GGD/AIMD-10 and are meant to assist congressmen in their decision making process, directly contradicting the claim that no such guide exists. So, answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people.'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. You have to classify if there exist more than 2 unique emotions in conversation. If there are more than 2 unique emotions present in the conversation, the output should be classified as '1' else it should be '0'\\n\\nPerson1:     You heard who won the election , right ? \\nPerson2: Who was elected ? \\nPerson1:     McCain won the election . \\nPerson2: That can ‚Äô t be true ! \\nPerson1:     I ‚Äô m upset , too . \\nPerson2: I can ‚Äô t believe people voted for him . \\nPerson1:     People must want him as our President . \\nPerson2: That doesn ‚Äô t make any sense . \\nPerson1:     I have more bad news . \\nPerson2: How could the news get any worse ? \\nPerson1:     I was only kidding , because Obama won the election . \\nPerson2: That ‚Äô s great news !","target":"1","rationale":"The conversation has at least 2 different emotions present. The first emotion is upset, which is expressed by Person1 in the 3rd and 4th sentences: \\"I'm upset, too\\" and \\"People must want him as our President\\". The second emotion is disbelief or surprise, which is expressed by Person2 in the last sentence: \\"That's great news!\\". Therefore, there are 2 unique emotions present in this dialogue."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is sexually offensive, 2) no, otherwise. Emphasis on sexually offensive or any lewd reference. Generate label 'no' for offensive posts that do not reference sexually explicit content. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nI hate when niggas come up to me and tell me they got this bitch off twitter or got her and it be a bitch I fuc wit lol smh","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post is sexually offensive as it contains explicit language and refers to sexual activities. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Billy and Sally are brother and sister. Billy is seven and Sally is eight. Their mother, Deborah, likes to have Billy and Sally dress up in costumes and play a game where they are answering the telephone. Usually when they play the game, Billy answers the telephone in a loud voice, and Sally answers the telephone in a quiet voice. On Tuesdays, Billy answers in a quiet voice, and Sally answers in a loud voice. On Fridays, Billy answers in a loud voice and Sally in a quiet voice. Billy has blonde hair. Sally has brown hair. Deborah has blonde hair, and Billy and Sally's father, Bob, has brown hair. He tells them to eat lettuce every time that he sees them, so that they grow big and strong like he is. Deborah likes to add some sugar with the lettuce so that Billy and Sally know what it is like to have sweet tastes in their life. One day, a Wednesday, Billy throws some lettuce into Sally's hair. Deborah laughs an grabs some straw from their farm and puts it in Billy's hair. Billy and Sally live on a farm. They have a goat, named Joey, and a duck, named Quack. They sometimes play a game with the goat where they chase him around the farm. Other times, they play a game with Quack where they wave at Quack and laugh. They have a fun life growing up on the farm. \\nWhat is the first name of Deborah's oldest child? \\nWould it be good to answer \\"Billy\\"?","target":"No","rationale":"The question asks what the first name of Deborah's oldest child is. Billy and Sally are siblings, but there is no mention of their ages anywhere in the text so it cannot be determined which one they are older than each other. Therefore, we do not know who among them is Deborah's eldest child, making \\"Billy\\" an incorrect answer as there will always be a chance that Sally could have been born before him.\\nTherefore, No would be your best choice for answering this question correctly.\\"\\""},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the best option to answer the question.\\nContext: Many individuals associate the word \\" diet \\" with visions of starving , going to bed hungry and thinking of food throughout the course of the day until you go mad and ca n't take it anymore . Actually , a good diet could n't be any further from this idea . You can still eat tasty food and lose weight , considering you eat the right kinds and in moderation , of course . The Sonoma Diet is one of the more successful diet plans to come to market in recent years , with literally thousands and thousands of dieters reporting successful weight loss , without really struggling with starving themselves .\\nQuestion: Why might people starve themselves ?\\nOptions: \\n- They are sick .\\n - They are too lazy to cook .\\n - They ca n't afford food .\\n - To lose weight .","target":"To lose weight .","rationale":"The context discusses the Sonoma Diet, which is a diet plan that emphasizes regular meals and healthy eating. The author of the context contrasts this with \\"starving oneself\\", or not eating enough food to maintain one's weight. People might starve themselves in order to lose weight.\\nSo, the answer is To lose weight ."},{"source":"Multi-select: Is it possible to draw the conclusion that \\"The ocean beach was a safer place to swim.\\" if \\"We went to the lake, because a shark had been seen at the ocean beach, so it was a safer place to swim.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The premise only states that the lake was a safer place to swim. It does not say anything about whether ocean beach is safe or unsafe for swimming, nor does it provide any information on how dangerous each of these places are when considered separately from one another. Hence, we cannot draw this conclusion at all based on the given premise and so the answer should be \\"no\\"."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to classify the sentence into one of the following five action categories - INFORM, INFORM_INTENT, OFFER, REQUEST, REQUEST_ALTS. If the sentence is about informing something, generate 'INFORM'. If it is about requesting something, generate 'REQUEST'. If the sentence mentions requesting an alternative option than the one provided, generate 'REQUEST_ALTS'. Similarly, generate 'OFFER' if the sentence is offering some information. If the sentence is about showing intent to do something, generate 'INFORM_INTENT'.\\n\\nI found 3 events. One of them is Billy Currington at Gallagher Way.","target":"OFFER","rationale":"The sentence \\"I found 3 events. One of them is Billy Currington at Gallagher Way.\\" is informing the user about an event that the system has found. Therefore, the answer will be 'OFFER'."},{"source":"Give me the correct facts to answer this: what is lil wayne real name?","target":"Dwayne Carter III","rationale":"Here's an direct answer: Dwayne Michael Carter Jr. is known professionally as Lil Wayne, and his father was born in 1971 with the name of \\"Dwayne Micheal Turner\\". \\nTherefore, he received the name of \\"Dwanye Carterson\\", which means that his real full birth-name is actually \\"Dwayne Carter III"},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\n\\n\\n\\nQ: Sickle-cell disease significantly impairs the function of what?\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- limbic system\\n\\n- nervous system\\n\\n- metabolism system\\n\\n- circulatory system\\n\\nA:","target":"circulatory system","rationale":"This question is asking us about the effects of sickle-cell disease. The text tells us that this condition involves red blood cells with a crescent shape, and then goes on to explain how these crescent shaped cells are harmful for the circulatory system. It explains that they can clog up small vessels in various parts of the body, causing damage to those body organs as well as pain (‚Äúdactyl‚Äù).\\nThe paragraph also mentions other ways that these ‚Äúsickle cell crises\\" cause problems: by damaging bone marrow, which limits production of all types of blood cells; and by blocking oxygen delivery throughout the patient's body. Because it causes so many problems within our bodies due to its effect on circulation or lack thereof), we know that sickle-cell"},{"source":"Read the following article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Brrriiinnng. The alarm clock announces the start of another busy weekday in the morning. You jump out of bed, rush into the shower, into your clothes and out the door with hardly a moment to think. A stressful journey to work gets your blood pressure climbing. Once at the office, you glance through the newspaper with depressing stories or reports of disasters. In that sort of mood, who can get down to work, particularly some creative, original problem-solving work?\\nThe way most of us spend our mornings is exactly opposite to the conditions that promote flexible, open-minded thinking. Imaginative ideas are most likely to come to us when we're unfocused. If you are one of those energetic morning people, your most inventive time comes in the early evening when you are relaxed. Sleepy people's lack of focus leads to an increase in creative problem solving. By not giving yourself time to tune into your wandering mind, you're missing out on the surprising solutions it may offer.\\nThe trip you take to work doesn't help, either. The stress slows down the speed with which signals travel between neurons  , making inspirations less likely to occur. And while we all should read a lot about what's going on in the world, it would not make you feel good for sure, so put that news website or newspaper aside until after the day's work is done.\\nSo what would our mornings look like if we wanted to start them with a full capacity for creative problem solving? We'd set the alarm a few minutes early and lie awake in bed, following our thoughts where they lead. We'd stand a little longer under the warm water of the shower, stopping thinking about tasks in favor of a few more minutes of relaxation. We'd take some deep breaths on our way to work, instead of complaining about heavy traffic. And once in the office--after we get a cup of coffee--we'd click on links not to the news of the day but to the funniest videos the web has to offer.\\nQuestion: According to the author, we are more creative when we are   _  .\\n- focused\\n- relaxed\\n- awake\\n- busy","target":"relaxed","rationale":"The author says that, \\"Imaginative ideas are most likely to come to us when we're unfocused,\\" and goes on to say that sleepy people's lack of focus leads them to having more creative problem solving. These statements suggest that relaxed or unfocused individuals have the highest capacity for creativity.\\nSo, based on this information in the article, it can be inferred that according to the author: We are more creative when we are _____ . The best answer is \\"relaxed\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: Who was Melkert's opponent in the election that resulted in him being appointed as Minister of Social Affairs and Employment? Passage 1:Guy Beiner was born and raised in Jerusalem and later moved to kibbutz Glil Yam. After traveling abroad, he relocated to the Negev region. Beiner is a graduate of Tel Aviv University and holds a PhD from the National University of Ireland. He was a Government of Ireland Scholar at University College Dublin, an Irish Research Council for Humanities and Social Sciences (IRCHSS) Fellow at Trinity College Dublin, a National Endowment for the Humanities (NEH) Fellow at the Keough-Naughton Institute for Irish Studies in the University of Notre Dame, a Government of Hungary Fellow at the Central European University in Budapest, a Gerda Henkel Marie Curie Fellow at the Faculty of History of the University of Oxford, a research associate of St Catherine's College, Oxford and a Burns Scholar at Boston College. At Ben-Gurion University, he has repeatedly received the Rector's prize for teaching excellence and was twice the recipient of the David and Luba Glatt Prize for Exceptional Excellence in Teaching. \\n Passage 2:Melkert was elected as a Member of the House of Representatives after the election of 1986, taking office on 3 June 1986 serving as a frontbencher and spokesperson for Finances. After the election of 1994 Melkert was appointed as Minister of Social Affairs and Employment in the Cabinet Kok I, taking office on 22 August 1994. After the election of 1998 Melkert returned as a Member of the House of Representatives, taking office on 19 May 1998. Following the cabinet formation of 1998 Melkert per his own request asked not to be considered for a cabinet post in the new cabinet, he was seen as a rising star by the Labour Party leadership and was considered as the favorite son to succeed Wim Kok as the next Leader of the Labour Party and was selected as the Parliamentary leader of the Labour Party in the House of Representatives, taking office on 13 July 1998. The Cabinet Kok I was replaced by the Cabinet Kok II on 3 August 1998. In December 2001 the Leader of the Labour Party and incumbent Prime Minister Kok announced he was stepping down as Leader and that he wouldn't stand for the election of 2002, the Labour Party leadership approached Melkert as a candidate to succeed him, Melkert accepted and became the Leader of the Labour Party and Lijsttrekker (top candidate) for the election, taking office on 15 December 2001. The Labour Party suffered a big loss, losing 22 seats and fell back as the fourth largest party and now had 23 seats in the House of Representatives. On May 16 2002 Melkert announced he was stepping down as Leader and Parliamentary leader taking responsibility for the defeat but continued to serve in the House of Representatives as a backbencher.\\n Passage 3:Past exhibits have included: Tchaikovsky, in honor of his trip to New York City for the opening of Carnegie Hall; Marian Anderson, the first African American to sing at the Metropolitan Opera; George and Ira Gershwin, in honor of the centennial of George's birth; and one on Leonard Bernstein, among others. The museum's collection also includes a number of items of interest to music lovers: a program from the Vienna Philharmonic's debut concert on March 28, 1842, a ring owned by Beethoven, a pair of Johannes Brahms's eyeglasses, one of Richard Strauss's notebooks, which contained sketches of Danube, an unfinished poem as well as one of Benny Goodman's clarinets and one of Toscanini's batons. It also includes a sequinned jacket owned and worn by Judy Garland and the trowel used in laying the cornerstone of Carnegie Hall.","target":"2","rationale":"The question asks which passage contains information about Melkert's opponent in the election. Passage 2 states that \\"After the election of 1998 Melkert returned as a Member of the House of Representatives.\\" This indicates that he did not win and there must have been an elected official who would be his opponent in the election."},{"source":"This article: The start of the movie flashes back to 1962 when Benny becomes Benny \\"the Jet\\" Rodriguez. The main part of the movie is set in 1972, ten years after the events of The Sandlot. The new Sandlot crew of nine kids have moved into the neighborhood of San Fernando Valley in Los Angeles. They have started playing baseball in the Sandlot. The previous kids have all grown up and moved away. The crew's chief officer, Johnnie Smalls, the little brother of Scott Smalls, has heard the legend of \\"The Great Fear\\" (a beastly mutated dog, as he puts it when he later on tells the group about The Beast) owned by Mr. Mertle, who lives behind the Sandlot. A no-nonsense boy named David Durango is the leader and captain of the crew, consisting of Johnnie, the panicky sergeant Mac, the fun-loving general Tarqell, the smart admiral Saul and his little brother, the cute navigator Sammy (referred to as \\"Fingers\\", because he does sign language). Behind the Sandlot, next to Mr. Mertle's home, lives the Goodfairer family. David's rival and the school bully, Hayley Goodfairer, the daughter and her two friends (who are her henchmen) initially befriend the other boys in a census to share the Sandlot, but their relationship burgeons potently into a friendship when they find themselves in a big problem with The Beast next door, despite Hayley calling David a little baby, and David calling Hayley a spoiled brat. contains an answer for the question: Who is \\"Fingers\\"'s older brother?, what is it ?","target":"Saul","rationale":"The article mentions that \\"Fingers\\" is the younger brother of Saul, and a member of the Sandlot crew. The older brother's name is mentioned in this sentence: \\"the smart admiral Saul and his little brother, the cute navigator Sammy (referred to as \\"Fingers\\", because he does sign language).\\"\\nSo it can be inferred from the question about Fingers' older brother that the answer for who Fingers' older brother is would be 'Saul'."},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nWho owns the rights to miracle on 34th street?","target":"Samuel French, Inc","rationale":"A short Google search returns Samuel French, Inc. as the owner of the rights to Miracle on 34th Street."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a short story with a beginning, two potential middles, and an ending. Your job is to choose the middle statement that makes the story coherent / plausible by writing \\"1\\" or \\"2\\" in the output. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes most sense.\\n\\nBeginning: Mike used to play racketball with Perry. Middle 1: Mike stood Perry up for their last racquetball game. Middle 2: John pushed Perry into a the racquetball court. Ending: Mike had to apologize.","target":"1","rationale":"Middle 1 indicates that Mike was supposed to play racketball with Perry, but he stood Perry up for their last racquetball game. Mike had to apologize. The actions in Middle 2 do not make sense in the context of the ending given, so Middle 1 is more likely than Middle 2."},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, identify who is wrong here. Classify each post into the following categories : AUTHOR (if the author of the post is wrong in the situation), OTHER (if any of the others mentioned in the paragraph is wrong), EVERYBODY (if everyone mentioned is wrong) and NOBODY (if no one is wrong in the situation).\\n\\nSo my friend‚Äôs mom has been sick for a while, long before I even met my friend. She died a few days ago and when I saw her at school today she broke the news to me and my friends. I was sad for her of course and comforted her but I couldn‚Äôt cry. I‚Äôm not sure why. It made me feel like an emotionless asshole but I just didn‚Äôt have any tears. I felt even more like shit when I saw my other friends crying for her. AITA and a terrible person overall?","target":"NOBODY","rationale":"The author's friend is sad that her mother died. The author acknowledges this, and tries to comfort the friend, but does not cry along with the friend. The author feels bad for not crying along with their friends, but there are many reasons why someone might not cry in this situation and none of them make that person a bad person or an \\"\\"asshole\\"\\". People process death differently than others. Some people don't cry when they feel sad. In this situation, no one is wrong or at fault; therefore, the label \\"\\"NOBODY\\"\\" is appropriate.\\"\\n]\\n</code>"},{"source":"Read the given query and classify it as a 'Good' or 'Bad' query depending on how well the query is formed, 'Bad' being the expected output for a not so well formed query and 'Good' being the expected output for a well formed query. A query may be wrong based on common sense or general facts, but if it is well formed, you should answer with Good.\\n\\nRelace flasher 2000 dodge durango ?","target":"Bad","rationale":"The query is supposed to be asking for a replacement of the flasher in a 2000 Dodge Durango. However, the query is grammatically incorrect. Therefore, it should be classified as \\"Bad\\"."},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: If \\"Two men sleep while traveling.\\", can we conclude \\"Two men are running around in a train.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states that the two men are sleeping while traveling. It is possible to be running around in a train without being asleep, so it cannot be concluded whether they are or not based on this evidence alone - hence: \\"it is not possible to tell\\"."},{"source":"Authors Anonymous is a 2014 comedy American film directed and produced by Ellie Kanner. It stars Kaley Cuoco, Chris Klein, Tricia Helfer, Jonathan Banks, Jonathan Bennett, Teri Polo and Dennis Farina in his final film role. The film was released on March 18, 2014 through video on demand prior to its limited release on April 18, 2014 by Screen Media Films and Starz Digital.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nAuthors Anonymous has a zz\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"There is no evidence in the passage to suggest that Authors Anonymous has a zz. Rather, it only talks about who directed and produced it. So, the answer is No."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question about when an event happened. Your answer should be a wrong answer. That is, if you are asked about when an event happened, you should answer with a time that the event didn't likely happen. For example, \\"going to school\\" usually happens during the day (not at 2 A.M). Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: Mzoudi studied in Dortmund, Bochum, and Muenster before moving to Hamburg in 1995. \\nQuestion: Which year did Mzoudi study in Dortmund ?","target":"1996","rationale":"The sentence states that Mzoudi studied in Dortmund before moving to Hamburg in 1995. Therefore, Mzoudi definitely did not study in Dortmund in 1996. 1996 is a reasonable guess as an incorrect answer because it is only one year after the year he moved to Hamburg."},{"source":"Classify the input text into either disfluent questions or proper questions. A disfluent question is a question that has some interruptions in it while framing. A proper question is the correct form of the question without any disfluency.\\n\\nWhere did Maududi exert the least impact?","target":"proper","rationale":"This is a proper question which does not contain any disfluency."},{"source":"I was 35 weeks pregnant when I had my stroke. For weeks prior to the event I kept experiencing ‚Äòvisual disturbances.‚Äô I felt when I was reading a newspaper or book a sense that my eyes were crossing. I‚Äôd feel aware right before it would occur and I would rush to look in a mirror only to discover my eyes were not crossing. I informed my OB who blamed it on the blood vessels in my eyes enlarging due to pregnancy. Ummm ok. You know more than me. Later I was told by a surgeon what I was experiencing was ‚Äòtextbook‚Äô for the passing of blood clots through my occipital area of the brain!\\nThe feeling would eventually subside. I awoke one morning feeling ‚Äòkind of fuzzy‚Äô headed. Like I had slept too hard. I sat with my husband at the kitchen table for our morning coffee and newspaper and for no reason I could imagine I was unable to swallow my coffee and it dribbled out the left side of my mouth. My husband asked me what was going on and I apparently told him, I was ‚Äòstroking‚Äô out. He got up from the table assuming I was OK and went off to take his morning shower. While in the shower it occurred to him something might not be right. He came back to the table where I was struggling to lift myself from the chair. I put my hands on the table to lift my body and my left hand kept sliding off the edge. He finally got behind me and tried to lift me under my arms and I crumbled to the floor. He then called my OB and told him he thought I‚Äôd had a stroke. My OB immediately expressed his doubt but my husband was advised to call an ambulance to get me to the ER. I never really experienced pain from the stroke.\\nAfter the end of the story, the narrator is probably:\\nPick the correct answer from the following options:\\n- Worried\\n- Healing\\n- not enough information\\n- Angry","target":"Healing","rationale":"The narrator describes the stroke symptoms and how she dealt with it, which indicates that she is still in the healing process. The answer should be Healing."},{"source":"Answer the question...who won the ncaa basketball tournament in 2016??","target":"Connecticut","rationale":"The University of Connecticut won the NCAA championship in 2016."},{"source":"You are given a sentence and a question, construct 2 answer options in a specific format i.e. ['option1','option2']. The answer options have to be text spans from the given sentence. Only one among the options should be the correct answer to the given question. Note that, the correct answer to the given question will require understanding of coreference resolution. Coreference resolution is the task of clustering mentions in text that refer to the same underlying real world entities.\\n\\nSentence: In July, Kamtchatka declared war on Yakutsk. Since Yakutsk's army was much better equipped and ten times larger, they were defeated within weeks. Question: Who was defeated","target":"['Yakutsk', 'Kamchatka']","rationale":"The correct answer to the given question is 'Yakutsk', as they were the ones who were defeated. However, to understand this, coreference resolution is required, as 'they' refers to Yakutsk in the sentence. So, the answer options should be: ['Yakutsk', 'Kamchatka'] where 'Yakutsk' is the correct answer and 'Kamchatka' is the incorrect option."},{"source":"Two analogies on manipulating items in a kitchen is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". The phrase \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its appropriate manipulation B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate manipulation of item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a verb which shows a way to manipulate the given object.\\n\\nsuitcase : open. peanut : ?","target":"shell","rationale":"One opens a suitcase and shells peanuts."},{"source":"Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below. Choose from options.\\nNatasha Bedingfield is married to Matthew Robinson.\\n\\nBritish singer-songwriter Natasha Bedingfield, who sang with her brother Daniel and sister Nikola as The DNA Algorithm, tied the knot with a California businessman in Malibu. According to reports the marriage, which took place Saturday in a 30-minute outdoor ceremony overlooking the Pacific Ocean, was attended by about 150 guests.  The guests watched Bedingfield walk down the aisle in a Vera Wang dress beside the chateau at the Church Estates Vineyards.  Bedingfield, who was born in New Zealand and grown up in England, found her partner, in America.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The text talks about the marriage event, but it does not mention who is Natasha Bedingfield married to. Hence, we cannot determine if the statement is true or false based on this information alone. So \\"no\\" would be the right answer here."},{"source":"Robert Alexander Crookston Laidlaw {'1': \\", '2': \\", '3': \\", '4': \\"} (8 September 1885 ‚Äì 12 March 1971) was a New Zealand business man who founded the Farmers Trading Company, one of the largest department store chains in New Zealand. He was also a Christian writer and philanthropist and a well-known lay preacher in the Open Brethren movement.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nRobert Alexander Crookston Laidlaw thought his name was too long.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"The passage states that \\"Robert Alexander Crookston Laidlaw {'1': \\", '2': \\", '3': \\", '4': \\"}\\", which suggests that he may have thought his name was too long. However, it is not explicitly stated in the text so we cannot definitively conclude whether or not this is true. Hence, the answer is \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"Given a factoid/trivia type question, generate the topic of the question. The topic is the entity the question talks about.\\n\\nWho became British Prime Minister in June 2007?","target":"prime minister of the united kingdom","rationale":"The answer to the question is Gordon Brown. He became Prime Minister of the United Kingdom in 2007. The topic of this question is therefore, 'prime minister of the united kingdom'."},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: where to travel in africa in january?","target":"Botswana","rationale":"The best time to visit Botswana is from January through March when rainfall is low and temperatures are mild.\\nTherefore, the answer should be \\"Botswana\\"."},{"source":"Given a sentence with a missing word, pick the answer option that best fills out the missing word in the sentence. Indicate each answer with its index ('a', 'b', 'c', 'd').\\n\\nNatural gas contains ____ atoms of hydrogen for every one atom of carbon.\\\\Question: Choose the right answer from options given a) five b) ten c) one d) four","target":"d","rationale":"The sentence is discussing the ratio of hydrogen to carbon atoms in natural gas. Among the four options, four is the only answer that will lead to a correct ratio of 5:1."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nI need some help, I want to visit a Museum without any entry fees, see what you can find please.","target":"Travel","rationale":"The sentence is about visiting a museum, which is a common tourist activity. Hence, the correct classification for this sentence is \\"Travel\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given four sentences of a story written in natural language. The given story is not complete and your job is to complete the story by selecting one of the end sentence choices from (A) and (B), such that the story does not sound complete and coherent, i.e., select an incorrect end sentence.\\n\\nSentence1: We woke up this morning to light snow falling. Sentence2: We're excited that school is cancelled for the day. Sentence3: Everyone went outside to play in the snow. Sentence4: We built a snowman and used a carrot for the nose. \\n (A) We had a boring day. (B) We found rocks to use for his eyes and mouth.","target":"A","rationale":"The original story is coherent and has a natural flow, but the ending sentence A interrupts that flow by stating \\"We had a boring day.\\" without providing any explanation or context."},{"source":"Given the fact that:\\n\\nIn the mesosphere, temperature decreases as altitude increases.\\n\\nAnswer the question:\\n\\n\\nIf a person sank lower within the mesosphere, would the temperature increase or decrease?","target":"increase","rationale":"The fact that is given states: \\"In the mesosphere, temperature decreases as altitude increases.\\" In this case, we know that a person's altitude would increase if they sank lower within the mesosphere. Therefore, based on the context of this situation and the information provided in our sentence above, it is accurate to say that when a person sinks lower within the mesosphere their temperature will decrease. So answer (A) \\"increase\\" makes sense here because it confirms what we already learned from our original statement regarding temperatures changing according to changes in altitudes."},{"source":"Answer the following question:\\n\\nhow many episodes in crash of the titans ps2?","target":"twenty","rationale":"Crash of the Titans has 20 episodes. \\n20 = twenty"},{"source":"Question: \\"What is the settlement on Governors Island called now?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"A permanent European presence in New Netherland began in 1624 ‚Äì making New York the 12th oldest continuously occupied European-established settlement in the continental United States  ‚Äì with the founding of a Dutch fur trading settlement on Governors Island. In 1625, construction was started on a citadel and a Fort Amsterdam on Manhattan Island, later called New Amsterdam (Nieuw Amsterdam). The colony of New Amsterdam was centered at the site which would eventually become Lower Manhattan. The Dutch colonial Director-General Peter Minuit purchased the island of Manhattan from the Canarsie, a small band of the Lenape, in 1626 for a value of 60 guilders (about $1000 in 2006); a disproved legend says that Manhattan was purchased for $24 worth of glass beads.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"New York","rationale":"The settlement on Governors Island is called New York."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Do urban settings ensure access to services : findings from the immunisation programme in Kampala Uganda?\\nAnswer: Complex health system barriers to childhood immunisation still exist in this urban setting; emphasizing that even in urban areas with great physical access, there are hard to reach people. As the rate of urbanization increases especially in sub-Saharan Africa, governments should strengthen health systems to cater for increasing urban populations.","target":"no","rationale":"The answer does not directly address the question. The answer describes health system barriers to immunization in an urban setting, but does not discuss whether those barriers limit access to services. In addition, the mention of increasing urban populations and strengthening health systems is not related to the question. The correct output is 'no'."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that end with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'here is an ultimate frisbee competition at the beach'. How many words end with the letter 'n' in the sentence.","target":"2","rationale":"Given the sentence 'here is an ultimate frisbee competition at the beach', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'here' : 0 -> (total) 0\\\\n2. 'is' : 1 -> (total) 1\\\\n3. 'an' : 1 -> (total) 2\\\\n4. 'ultimate' : 0 -> (total) 2\\\\n5. 'frisbee': 0 ->(total) 2\\\\n6.'competition' : 3->(total) 5 \\\\n7.'at':0->(total) 5 \\\\n8.'the':0->(total) 5 \\\\n9.'beach':1->(6 total)\\\\ntotal number of words ending with n is 6"},{"source":"In this task you are given a tweet. You must judge whether the tweet is ironic or not. We define two type of irony for this task (\\"polarity\\",\\"situational\\"). Situational irony happens when a situation fails to meet some expectations. polarity irony happens when irony is achieved by inverting the intended sentence. Label the instances as \\"ironic\\" or \\"not\\" based on your judgment. Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\n@loveeallyy I literally do not know","target":"not","rationale":"The tweet expresses the user's feelings and is not ironic."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nIsabella entered the closet. Aria entered the closet. The watermelon is in the green_pantry. Aria exited the closet. Isabella moved the watermelon to the blue_pantry. Olivia entered the closet. Jacob entered the closet. The persimmon is in the blue_pantry. Jacob exited the closet. Olivia moved the persimmon to the green_pantry. Aria entered the bedroom. Phone rang. Jacob entered the bedroom. The strawberry is in the red_pantry. Jacob exited the bedroom. Aria moved the strawberry to the red_bottle. Aria is in the bedroom. Isabella entered the bedroom. The pumpkin is in the red_bottle. Isabella exited the bedroom. Aria moved the pumpkin to the red_pantry. Where was the pumpkin at the beginning?","target":"red_bottle","rationale":"The pumpkin was in the red_bottle at the beginning because Aria moved it there from the red_pantry and no one else interacted with it."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage. The passage will not have a direct answer to the question, but can include some information and a clue for the answer. Assuming you can only obtain information about one entity in the passage, your job is to determine whether information from the passage can be used to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: What was the video of the year the year that Drunk in Love was nominated for the same award? Passage:The song's music video was directed by Hype Williams and shot in black-and-white in Golden Beach, Florida at a beach front manse. The visual features scenes of the pair singing the song together. \\"Drunk in Love\\" was performed by Beyonc√© and Jay-Z at the 56th Annual Grammy Awards. It was later added to the set lists of the second European leg of Beyonc√©'s The Mrs. Carter Show World Tour in 2013 and the pair's joint On the Run Tour in 2014. Numerous remixes and cover versions of the song were made, most notably the official rework by rapper Kanye West. The music video won Best Collaboration and was nominated for Video of the Year at the 2014 MTV Video Music Awards.","target":"a","rationale":"The video of the year that Drunk in Love was nominated for is \\"Drunk in Love\\", which is mentioned directly in the passage. Therefore, information from the passage can be used to answer the question."},{"source":"Sentence 1: \\"Alice tried frantically to stop her daughter from chatting at the party, leaving us to wonder why she was behaving so strangely.\\"\\n\\n Sentence 2: \\"Alice's daughter was behaving so strangely.\\"\\n\\nIs sentence 2 true, based on sentence 1?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence states that Alice is the one who was behaving oddly, not her daughter. If we interpret this to mean that she was worried about her child's behavior rather than being focused on herself and how others were judging it, then the second statement could be true. However, there is no indication in either context or text of meaning beyond face value that would lead us to believe this interpretation over another (i.\\"\\n* \\t\\t    \\"e., if someone asked me why I thought Alice tried frantically to stop her daughter from chatting at the party , my answer might have been because people around them seemed uncomfortable with all of their chatter). The fact remains: Sentence 2 suggests something different than what can be inferred from Sentence 1"},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{10}', Set2: '{1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 9, 12, 13, 18, 19}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"11","rationale":"The given sets are Set1: '{10}', and Set2: '{1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 9, 12, 13, 18, 19}'.\\\\nLet's take a look at the elements in each set.\\\\nSet1: 10\\\\nSet2: 1 2 3 5 7 9 12 13 18 19\\\\nFrom the above lists we can see that there are 11 unique elements present in both sets. Therefore the output will be 11."},{"source":"Suggest a movie title for the following movie plot: The action takes place in a German village in the fifteen months that precede World War I.Among the people who live there are a baron, who is a large landowner and a local moral authority, his estate manager, a pastor with his many children, a widowed doctor and a schoolteacher who is thinking of getting married. It is he who, many years later, tells this story.Though everything seems to be quiet and orderly, as it always has been, with the seasons following each other, and good harvests following bad ones, suddenly some strange events start to occur. If some appear to be quite ordinary, even accidental -- a farmer's wife dies falling through rotten floorboards -- others are inexplicable and may well be malevolent.Thus, a wire placed at knee-height has brought down the horse being ridden by the doctor, who is severely wounded.There's more of the same: an unknown hand opens a window to expose a newborn baby to the intense cold of the winter. A whole field of cabbages, on the baron's land, are beheaded with a scythe. One of the Baron's sons disappears: he is found his feet and hands bound, his buttocks lashed by a whip. A barn belonging to the manor is set on fire. A farmer hangs himself. A midwife's handicapped child is found tied to a tree, in a forest, seriously beaten, with a threatening message on his chest speaking of divine punishment.The village is worried, and at a loss as to what to do. The baron whose wife will soon leave the village to go to live in Italy makes a speech in the church, but it has no effect. The pastor, a particularly strict character, had since the beginning of the events, tied a white ribbon to the arm of his two eldest children, a boy and a girl: it is to remind them permanently of their duties to purity. In spite of these ribbons, his own family is not spared. His eldest son admits that he masturbates. The pastor's pet bird is stabbed with a scissor by the pastor's daughter.The schoolteacher, whose pupils are growing more and more unruly, and who is considering getting married (it...","target":"The White Ribbon","rationale":"The White Ribbon is a 2009 black-and-white German drama film written and directed by Michael Haneke. The story takes place in Germany just before World War I, and revolves around murders of children in Northern Germany at the end of October 1913 that remain unexplained or unsolved. Wikipedia"},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string of characters. You should remove all vowels from the given string. Vowels are: i,e,a,u,o. The character 'y' or 'Y' does not count as a vowel.\\n\\nEIeawvcevDomfXy","target":"wvcvDmfXy","rationale":"The given string contains the vowels 'E', 'I', 'e', 'a','w','v','c','e','o', and 'i'. Let's remove them as instructed. The resulting string after removing the vowels is \\"wvcvDmfXy\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the abstract of a research paper. Your task is to generate a summary of this abstract. Your summary should not be very short, but it's better if it's not more than 30 words.\\n\\nModeling hypernymy, such as poodle is-a dog, is an important generalization aid to many NLP tasks, such as entailment, relation extraction, and question answering. Supervised learning from labeled hypernym sources, such as WordNet, limit the coverage of these models, which can be addressed by learning hypernyms from unlabeled text.   Existing unsupervised methods either do not scale to large vocabularies or yield unacceptably poor accuracy.   This paper introduces {\\\\it distributional inclusion vector embedding (DIVE)}, a simple-to-implement unsupervised method of hypernym discovery via per-word non-negative vector embeddings which preserve the inclusion property of word contexts. In experimental evaluations more comprehensive than any previous literature of which we are aware---evaluating on 11 datasets using multiple existing as well as newly proposed scoring functions---we find that our method provides up to double the precision of previous unsupervised methods, and the highest average performance, using a much more compact word representation, and yielding many new state-of-the-art results. In addition, the meaning of each dimension in DIVE is interpretable, which leads to a novel approach on word sense disambiguation as another promising application of DIVE.","target":"We propose a novel unsupervised word embedding which preserves the inclusion property in the context distribution and achieve state-of-the-art results on unsupervised hypernymy detection","rationale":"Here's a brief summary:\\\\nWe propose a novel unsupervised word embedding which preserves the inclusion property in the context distribution and achieve state-of-the-art results on unsupervised hypernymy detection."},{"source":"Given a statement, generate a question such that the answer is contained in that statement.\\n\\nThe genitalia are used to have children.","target":"What are the genitalia used to have?","rationale":"The question \\"What are the genitalia used to have?\\" will induce children as an answer."},{"source":"Answer the following question.\\nWhat is the name of Elvis Costello's famous father?","target":"Ronald Ross McManus","rationale":"Ronald Ross McManus is the name of Elvis Costello's famous father."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nif words have no effect in the uk i guess firebombing government buildings would not either nor firebombing moslem businesses it would be a shame if masked persons did it","target":"firebombing","rationale":"The given tweet contains the phrase \\"firebombing\\", which is a crime and can be used to threaten or incite violence."},{"source":"Given a post that is a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation and an associated claim about its type, verify if the claim is true or not. The claim asks if the posts are historical or hypothetical. The posts are \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and they are \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future. Say 'yes' if the claim is true otherwise say 'no'\\n\\nCLAIM : The following post is HISTORICAL. POST : So there is this coworker of mine that I asked out a while ago and she turned me down.  I was fine really and I understand why she turned me down at the time.  Eventually a sort of banter developed  between us and it was kind of fun to be honest.  Then she asked out one of my friends right in front of me which I just kind of smiled and said it seemed like I broke some ice for them.  I hear from my friend that he couldn't believe that I was so chill about it. He also started acting intimidated when I was around.  I began suspecting that it was fake and just to mess with me but I thought I was crazy and probably just a little jealous so I wanted to believe that.  Then I hear from my friend that it was to mess with me but now they  are legit going out.  I was a little upset and confused that she wanted to mess with me that much but I didn't say anything.  Eventually I hear that she is working night shift and can't find time to go out.  Then I find out that this is a lie to avoid him.  She stops talking to her best friend at the the same time over this issue.  It does blow over and they break up eventually.  Recently the entire incident comes up and she is shocked that I learned everything.  I tell her that I don't care about what she tried to do to me, but I do care that she lied and hurt my friend.  I told her I thought she was more mature than that and I expected better.  I also said that I don't like her less or anything, I just don't like what she did.  I specifically had this talk in private as well.  I didn't say anything to anyone else but I find out she tried to turn other people against me.  AITA?","target":"yes","rationale":"The post is describing a past event, in which the author found out that their coworker and friend were going out after they had rejected the author. The author mentions that they confronted their coworker about this, so it seems reasonable to assume that the event has already occurred.\\n\\nTherefore, the claim \\"\\"The following post is HISTORICAL\\"\\"is true and so the answer would be \\"\\"yes\\"\\"."},{"source":"Question: what is prince william's last name?\\nWould \\"In 2009, he transferred to the Royal Air Force , was promoted to Flight Lieutenant and underwent helicopter flying training in order to become a full-time pilot with the Search and Rescue Force .\\" be a reasonable answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The suggested answer provided by the automatic system does not seem to be relevant. It describes Prince William's career in the British military, and although it may provide some additional information about his life, it is not an accurate response to the question of what his last name is. This kind of information would likely be included as a footnote or parenthetical statement if he was being referred to elsewhere; however, because this piece of information has been requested directly, something more concise (and correct) should have been provided instead. \\nTherefore, \\"No\\""},{"source":"Generate a correct and concise answer for the question based on the words in the context.\\n\\nContext : The Chatsworth Head is a slightly over-life-size bronze head dating to around 460 BCE which is now in the British Museum. \\nQuestion : What is the name of the place where Chatsworth Head can be found?","target":"British Museum","rationale":"The Chatsworth Head is in the British Museum."},{"source":"WHITE HOUSE ‚Äî President Donald Trump, after a tactical retreat this week on immigration policy, demonstrated Friday that there is no strategic shift to his overall tough approach to those attempting to illegally enter the country, and vowing to \\"end the immigration crisis, once and for all.\\"\\nU.S. immigration laws, Trump declared, are \\"the weakest in the history of the world.\\"\\nTrump made the remarks in an auditorium in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building, adjacent to the White House, where he presided over an event with so-called \\"Angel Families,\\" those who have had relatives killed by people who entered the country illegally.\\n\\"Your loss will not have been in vain,\\" the president told the families, who held large photos of their slain relatives. \\"We will secure our borders ‚Ä¶ the word will get out. Got to have a safe country. We're going to have a safe country.\\"\\nTrump called family members to the presidential lectern to recount how their loved ones had been killed by those who were in the United States illegally. Several of those speaking condemned the media for ignoring the stories of the victims and praised Trump and Vice President Mike Pence for their attention to border security.\\nCrime assertion\\nTrump, in his remarks, also suggested those illegally in the United States commit more crimes on a statistical basis than citizens or resident aliens.\\nHowever, studies have shown that undocumented immigrants are less likely to commit a crime in the U.S. than native-born citizens, including one published by the libertarian CATO Institute this year.\\nFollowing intense domestic and international condemnation, Trump on Wednesday signed an order ending his administration's practice of separation of children from their families while parents were being prosecuted for crossing the border illegally. The administration's recently implemented \\"zero tolerence\\" policy led to the criminal prosecutions of undocumented border crossers, which in turn led to federal officials separating adults and their children.\\nAccording to the above context, choose the correct option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: Where did Trump's Friday speech take place?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. Washington, DC\\n\\nB. Near the US border\\n\\nC. At a CATO Institute forum\\n\\nD. not enough information","target":"A","rationale":"The context of the question is about Trump's speech on Friday, which took place in an auditorium in the Eisenhower Executive Office Building. This building is located next to The White House, and thus Washington D.C., so the answer must be \\"A\\"."},{"source":"Q: How much of the soil is made of pieces of rock and minerals?\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"about half","rationale":"The soil we see on the ground is made up of a number of different pieces. These include organic matter, minerals and rock fragments, air spaces between these particles that allow oxygen and water to enter them, living organisms like worms or insects as well as microorganisms etc. \\nSoil scientists have identified four main components in healthy soils: sand (mineral), silt (mineral), clay(minerals) and humus/organic material. The mineral content accounts for about half (50%) of the total weight while the rest is accounted by Organic Material which includes plant materials , dead plants , animal remains & manure ."},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat was the leading principle in the Dokkyo incident?\\n-","target":"Yushu Kitano","rationale":"The incident was caused by a man named Yushu Kitano."},{"source":"Ice wedging is caused by cycles of freezing and thawing of what?\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?\\n- h2o\\n- plants\\n- winds\\n- animals","target":"h2o","rationale":"Ice wedging is caused by the expansion of water as it freezes. As ice expands, cracks form in rocks or soil and grow larger each time they freeze. Over time this process can cause large pieces to break off from rocks. Ice wedging requires cycles of freezing and thawing so that expanding ice can continue breaking apart rock or soil over time.\\nBased on the context above, h2o is the correct answer because it refers to water which causes cracking through its expansion when frozen."},{"source":"In this task, you are given four sentences: a bot task sentence, a bot role sentence, a user task sentence and a user role sentence. Your job is to classify given sentences into one of the 47 different domains. The domains are: 'UPDATE_CALENDAR', 'PRESENT_IDEAS', 'MOVIE_LISTINGS', 'AUTO_SORT', 'GAME_RULES', 'CONTACT_MANAGER', 'BANK_BOT', 'MUSIC_SUGGESTER', 'CHECK_STATUS', 'PET_ADVICE', 'HOW_TO_BASIC', 'NAME_SUGGESTER', 'QUOTE_OF_THE_DAY_BOT', 'GUINESS_CHECK', 'INSURANCE', 'RESTAURANT_PICKER', 'MAKE_RESTAURANT_RESERVATIONS', 'WEDDING_PLANNER', 'SKI_BOT', 'HOME_BOT', 'PLAY_TIMES', 'BUS_SCHEDULE_BOT', 'WHAT_IS_IT', 'PHONE_PLAN_BOT', 'DECIDER_BOT', 'PHONE_SETTINGS', 'TIME_ZONE', 'LIBRARY_REQUEST', 'UPDATE_CONTACT', 'CATALOGUE_BOT', 'PROMPT_GENERATOR', 'SCAM_LOOKUP', 'SPORTS_INFO', 'POLICY_BOT', 'CITY_INFO', 'APARTMENT_FINDER', 'EVENT_RESERVE', 'SHOPPING', 'EDIT_PLAYLIST', 'LOOK_UP_INFO', 'ORDER_PIZZA', 'WEATHER_CHECK', 'APPOINTMENT_REMINDER', 'GEOGRAPHY', 'STORE_DETAILS', 'AGREEMENT_BOT', 'ALARM_SET'.\\n\\nBot's task: Tell the user how much data their plan provides, and then inform them that they can double the amount for only 10 dollars a month \\nBot's role: You are a bot representing a mobile service provider \\nUser's task: You want to doublecheck how much monthly data you have on your plan \\nUser's role: You are interacting with a bot representing your mobile service provider","target":"PHONE_PLAN_BOT","rationale":"The bot's task is to tell the user about their data plan, and the bot's role is being a mobile service provider. The user wants to doublecheck how much monthly data they have on their plan and is interacting with a bot representing their mobile service provider. Therefore, this scenario can be classified as \\"PHONE_PLAN_BOT\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\nmetal","target":"wood","rationale":"Based on the word metal, we can infer that wood is the opposite of it."},{"source":"Give me a possible correct answer to the question \\"when did the new york knicks win a championship?\\"","target":"1973 NBA Finals","rationale":"The New York Knicks won the championship in 1973 NBA Finals, so \\"1973 NBA Finals\\" is a possible correct answer to this question."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a prompt from a judicial decision and multiple holding statements derived from citations following text in a legal decision.  Holdings represent the governing legal rule when the law is applied to a particular set of facts. There are five answer choices for each citing text. The correct answer is the holding statement that corresponds to the citing text. You should write an incorrect option. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. There is a <HOLDING> token in the position of the citing text prompt where the holding statement was extracted.\\n\\nthe conversations as they occurred. Further, this officer testified that after speaking with Diana Buchanan during her arrest, he was ‚Äúconvinced‚Äù that the voice on the tape was Diana Buchanan‚Äôs. Although the district court did not elicit testimony as to all the Biggins elements, the officer sponsoring the recording gave adequate testimony to support the recording‚Äôs reliability. All the voices were identified, and there was no intimation that the tape had been altered. Further, the testifying officer explained how the recording was made, and testified as to its accuracy. Accordingly, we cannot say that the district court abused its discretion in admitting the tape as an accurate reproduction of relevant conversations. See United States v. Lance, 853 F.2d 1177, 1181-82 (5th Cir.1988) (<HOLDING>). C Diana Buchanan next argues that the \\n Holding statements: (A) holding that the  2d11b1 enhancement was proper where a firearm and drugrelated items were found in the defendants residence where he had also engaged in conspiratorial conversations (B) holding recordings properly authenticated where law enforcement agents who participated in the taped conversations testified that according to their memories the audio and video tapes contained accurate recordings of the conversations that occurred (C) holding that foreign bank documents found inside a persons home were properly authenticated (D) holding that the plaintiffs fourteenth amendment substantive due process claim was foreclosed because the fourth amendment provided protection for their claim that law enforcement officers participated in an unlawful seizure of their mobile home (E) holding that government met its burden with evidence that agents found a firearm and other drugrelated items in the defendants house where defendant engaged in conspiratorial conversations","target":"holding that the  2d11b1 enhancement was proper where a firearm and drugrelated items were found in the defendants residence where he had also engaged in conspiratorial conversations","rationale":"The sentence \\"holding that the  2d11b1 enhancement was proper where a firearm and drugrelated items were found in the defendants residence where he had also engaged in conspiratorial conversations\\" is not a holding statement. Therefore, it is an incorrect answer."},{"source":"Premise: \\"A brown dog poses with ribbons.\\"\\nHypothesis: \\"A black dog runs away.\\"\\nDo we know that the hypothesis entailed by the premise?","target":"no","rationale":"A dog can not be brown and black simultaneously. A dog can not be posing can not be running simultaneously."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nclamp : clamp. vacuum : ?","target":"vacuum","rationale":"A clamp is used to hold an object. A vacuum can also be used to hold an object (e.g. a vacuum cleaner)."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a conversation between a flight agent and the customer. You are given 4 options and you need to select the goal of the conversation. It is provided as part of customer's context, which has to be one of the following: \`book\`: Make a new reservation, \`cancel\`: Cancel an existing reservation, \`no_flight\`: No flight found for the customer's preference, \`no_reservation\`: No reservation / No change / No cancellation was made in the conversation, mostly enquiring details\\n\\ncustomer: Hello. \\n agent: Hello. How can I assist you? \\n customer: I want to change my existing reservation, my music concert got postponed. Can you please help me out with that? \\n agent: Sure, let me know your name to check your reservation details. \\n customer: Thank you for accepting my request, I have done my reservation on the name of Gregory Williams. \\n agent: Thank you. Please wait for a while, let me check your reservation status. \\n customer: Sure, take your time. \\n agent: I am sorry to say you that there is no reservation found under your name in our database. \\n customer: Oh! I think the ticket was not booked properly while I am booking. Anyway, thank you for checking. \\n agent: Thank you for reaching us. \\n customer: Welcome.","target":"no_reservation","rationale":"The customer wants to change an existing reservation, the agent asks for details, but there is no record found. No flight was booked or cancelled. Hence the goal is \\"no_reservation\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue from a conversation between an agent and a customer. Your task is to determine the speaker of the dialogue. Answer with \\"agent\\" or \\"customer\\".\\n\\nEnjoy your journey.","target":"agent","rationale":"This answer is given by the agent to the customer after receiving confirmation of their booking."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the beginning and the ending of a three-part story. Your job is to complete the short story by writing a middle sentence that seamlessly connects  the first and last sentence. Generated sentences must be short, have fewer than 10 words, and be simple as if narrating to a child. Avoid using any irrelevant extra information when creating the middle sentence, and use names (e.g. Jack, Barbara,...) instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible.\\n\\nBeginning: Zoey is an only child. Ending: When the baby is born, she goes to the hospital to meet her brother!","target":"Zoey asked for a sibling","rationale":"Zoey is an only child, and she goes to the hospital to meet her brother. This implies that Zoey asked for a sibling at some point in time."},{"source":"Two coastal cities were affected by a cat 5 Hurricane. Red city took the full impact, but Purple city, situated 40 miles inland, avoided the brunt of the damage.\\n\\nWhich city experienced fewer high waves from the hurricane?","target":"Purple","rationale":"Since Purple is inland, and Red was where the hurricane made landfall, it had to travel over land in order to reach Purple. This means that by the time it hit Purple its power would have been significantly reduced due to friction with the terrain (or \\"brunt\\" as mentioned).\\nThe word \\"fewer\\" also implies a comparison between both cities - at least one is more than another so this isn't just about how many waves were experienced; rather an explicit comparison must be made which leads us back to our original assertion: since red city took the full impact of a cat 5 Hurricane whereas purple did not then logically speaking fewer high waves would have occurred there."},{"source":"Here's a logic test: A spoon generates heat when rubbing it rapidly against bare skin, but less against a silk shirt. The smoother surfaces must be (A) the skin (B) the shirt?\\n\\nChoose the answer between \\"silk shirt\\" and \\"skin\\".","target":"skin","rationale":"The spoon generates less heat when rubbing it against a silk shirt than the skin. There are two factors that affect the level of friction between surfaces: surface area and smoothness. The smoother surfaces would be those which lead to less friction, so either A or B could be correct depending on whether we think surface area is more important than smoothness or vice versa.\\nWe can't directly compare the relative roughnesses of bare skin and silk because they have very different textures, but we know from experience that both feel soft to touch - in other words, our fingers slide smoothly over them without catching at all (a feeling similar to running our finger along a finely polished piece of wood). If this means that their thermal conductivities must therefore also differ significantly enough for us to say one has \\"smoother"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a context sentence containing a blank (_). You are expected to fill the blank with one word to make the sentence convey a cultural anti-stereotype. Anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common belief about a particular group of people. Your answer must not contain more than one word.\\n\\nContext: People from Somalia have _ skin.","target":"light","rationale":"A common belief about people from Somalia is that they have dark skin. Therefore, filling the blank with \\\\\\"light\\\\\\" conveys an anti-stereotype of people from Somalia having light skin."},{"source":"You will be given a review about a book, an item, a place or a movie. After that, a question is given that you should answer using a certain span of the review. Your answer should be from the review itself and should not contain extra words, and should not be a combination of different spans. If there's no direct answer to the question, answer with a part of the text that is the most relevant to the question. See the examples for clarification.\\n\\nreview: We stayed at the Omni for 4 days and we had an excellent experience. Room was fantastic as well as service. Great location, I would definetely recommend it!\\nquestion: Is this a real good food service?","target":"excellent","rationale":"The answer should be a span from the given review. Here, we have the word \\"excellent\\" describing the service of the hotel, which means that it is a good food service."},{"source":"In this task you are given a tweet. You must judge whether the tweet is ironic or not. We define two type of irony for this task (\\"polarity\\",\\"situational\\"). Situational irony happens when a situation fails to meet some expectations. polarity irony happens when irony is achieved by inverting the intended sentence. Label the instances as \\"ironic\\" or \\"not\\" based on your judgment. Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nReading a Victoria's Secret Fashion Show recap with a plate of French fries in front of me :french_fries:","target":"ironic","rationale":"The tweet is ironic because the writer's action is at odds with the content of the article."},{"source":"when does pokemon the movie 2000 take place??","target":"Shamouti Island","rationale":"The Pokemon movie 2000 is centered on the character Lawrence III, who took a tiny gem from an island called Shamouti Island."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers. A list is shown by two brackets and comma-separated numbers inside, like: [1,2,3]. You should remove all of the even numbers from the list. If every number in the input list is even an empty list should be returned. Zero should be counted as an even number.\\n\\n[122, 124, 141, 88, 193]","target":"[141, 193]","rationale":"Given the list [122, 124, 141, 88, 193], let's try one by one:\\\\n1. 122 : not even\\\\n2. 124 : even\\\\n3. 141 : not even\\\\n4. 88 : even\\\\n5. 193 : not even\\\\nThe final result would be [141, 193]."},{"source":"Given the Question and Answer pair, detect whether the answer is acceptable or not. Denote acceptable answer as \\"yes\\", otherwise denote as \\"no\\". An acceptable answer is consistent with the context in question, detailed, long, and uses general knowledge of English. Answers that are not definite and suggest a variety of options are not acceptable answers.\\n\\nQuestion: E.g. is short for exempli gratia, and is in common use to introduce an example within a sentence. Submit a sample of academic writing, e.g., a dissertation chapter. However, some authors use ex. or ex: (short for \\"example\\") for the same purpose, and this form is listed in some authorities like the Wiktionary. Submit a sample of academic writing, ex: a dissertation chapter. I know they both roughly mean \\"example\\", but which one should I use, and when? Are there connotations associated with one or the other? This question has been asked elsewhere, and this very answer comes up when you ask Google about the difference. It would be good to get an EL&U answer for it. \\nAnswer: \\"Ex.\\" is not very common, but it may be used to refer to a cited example, eg \\"See ex. 3\\". \\"E.g.\\" is much more common, and is used to introduce an example, or series of examples. In speech, it is usually replaced by \\"for example\\".","target":"no","rationale":"The answer is not acceptable because the second sentence is too long and elaborated.  The answer should be concise, short and concise."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, a context passage, and four options which are terms from the passage. After reading a passage, you will get a brief understanding of the terms. Your job is to determine by searching and reading further information of which term you can answer the question. Indicate your choice as 'a', 'b', 'c', or 'd'. If you think more than one option is plausible, choose the more probable option to help you answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: What did it cost to attend Yale the year Mairson got his B.A. there? Passage:Mairson received a B.A. in Mathematics from Yale University in 1978 and a Ph.D. in Computer Science from Stanford University in 1984 under the supervision of Jeffrey Ullman. His Ph.D. thesis, The Program Complexity of Searching a Table, won the Machtey Award at the 1983 IEEE Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science (FOCS). Mairson was a Postdoctoral researcher at INRIA Rocqencourt from 1984 to 1985, at Stanford University in 1985, and at the University of Oxford in 1986. He held a Visiting Professor position from 1999 to 2001 at Boston University. From 2005 to 2007, Mairson has served as the Chair of the Faculty Senate at Brandeis. He is currently an Associate Editor of the journal Logical Methods in Computer Science and Information and Computation, and sits on the editorial board of Higher-Order and Symbolic Computation.\\n Links: a. Yale University b. Information and Computation c. Symposium on Foundations of Computer Science d. Stanford University","target":"a","rationale":"The relevant information can be found in the second sentence of the passage."},{"source":"The Angel on the Roof: The Stories of Russell Banks (2000) is a collection of short stories by Russell Banks. It consists of a total of thirty-one previously published stories, including twenty-two stories that appeared in earlier short story collections, along with nine that were previously uncollected.\\n\\nChoose your answer: based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"The Angel on the Roof was written by Donald Trump\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nI think the answer is","target":"No","rationale":"While it is possible that Donald Trump may have written The Angel on the Roof, there is no evidence to suggest this in the information provided. In fact, according to the paragraph above, Russell Banks wrote The Angel on the Roof. Therefore, we cannot conclude that Donald Trump wrote The Angel on the Roof and thus answer choice \\"No\\" is correct."},{"source":"Write a question about the following article: After a tough loss at home to the Lions, the Eagles traveled down south to New Orleans to take on the Saints in the Mercedes-Benz Superdome.  The Saints scored first with Patrick Robinson returning a Michael Vick interception 99 yards for a touchdown and a 7-0 lead for the only score of the game.  The Eagles got on the board in the 2nd quarter as Alex Henery kicked a 22-yard field goal to cut the lead to 7-3 not long before Chris Ivory ran for a 22-yard touchdown to move the Saints ahead by 11 with a 14-3 lead and then they would score again with Drew Brees finding Marques Coltson on a 1-yard touchdown pass for a 21-3 halftime lead.  The Eagles scored 10 unanswered points in the 3rd quarter with Vick hooking up with DeSean Jackson on a 77-yard touchdown pass for a score of 21-10 and then Henery kicked a 37-yard field goal for a score of 21-13.  But the Saints scored one last time as Brees found Jimmy Graham on a 6-yard touchdown pass for a 28-13 lead which would be the final score of the game as neither team scored in the 4th quarter.\\n\\nQuestion about the article:","target":"How many points were scored in the last quarter?","rationale":"The given article is about the game between Saints and Eagles. Here's a question for it:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: How many points were scored in the last quarter?"},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat is the connection Bill Robinson has to Shirley Temple?\\n- After Robinson was signed by 20th Century Fox, it was decided that he would perform his famous stair dance with Temple.\\n- How was the his featured appearance with Shirley Temple recieved?\\n- Robinson and Temple became the first interracial dance partners in Hollywood history. The scene was controversial for its time.\\n- Did Bill Robinson pass the test?\\n- How did the movie do?\\n- Was it a hit movie?\\n-","target":"What did Shirley Temple think?","rationale":"The question \\"What is the connection Bill Robinson has to Shirley Temple?\\" and its answer are about how Bill Robinson was signed by 20th Century Fox and his appearance with her. The second question \\"After Robinson was signed by 20th Century Fox, it was decided that he would perform his famous stair dance with Temple.\\" and its answer focus on the controversy around the two dancing together. The next two questions discuss how well the movie did in general, but does not mention Shirley Temple's opinion. Since there is no information given about what she thought of working with Bill Robinson or their performance together, the most reasonable option among all four options is to ask what she thought. Hence, I choose option \\"What did Shirley Temple think?\\"."},{"source":"If a coworker needed a pen they might ask you for one, that's why you should keep spares in your leather what?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptionsÔºö\\n\\nA. pocket\\n\\nB. jacket\\n\\nC. friend's house\\n\\nD. desk drawer\\n\\nE. briefcase","target":"E","rationale":"The question is asking where the narrator should keep spare pens. This suggests that they want to be able to easily access the pens when needed and leave them in place so as not to lose them or forget about them. In addition, carrying a briefcase would suggest that it belongs to someone who has an office job, which also implies needing writing utensils like pens for work related purposes.\\nBased on this context we can conclude that option E (\\"briefcase\\") best answers the prompt \\"where should you store your extra pen(s)\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to list all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element in the reverse order. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n9, 12, ['5415', 'J', 'F', 'n', 'K', '9777', '1441', '3335', 'D', 'x', '7215', '4633', 'n', '1515', '7515']","target":"4633, 7215, x, D","rationale":"Given the list ['5415', 'J', 'F', 'n', 'K', '9777', '1441', '3335', 'D', 'x','7215','4633','n','1515','7515'], we need to find the elements within the range 9 ~ 12.\\\\n1. The 9th element is D.\\\\n2. The 10th element is x .\\\\n3. The 11th element is 7215 .\\\\n4. The 12th element is 4633 .\\n\\nThe final output would be in reverse order: ['4633, 7215, x, D']."},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: If \\"African American man wearing all black with a white hat prepares food.\\", can we conclude \\"A white woman is eating dinner.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"There is no mention of a white woman, so we can not conclude that she is eating dinner."},{"source":"Article: Tito visited India from December 22, 1954 through January 8, 1955. After his return, he removed many restrictions on churches and spiritual institutions in Yugoslavia.\\n\\nQuestion: After his return from where did Tito remove many restrictions on churches in Yugoslavia?","target":"India","rationale":"The paragraph states that Tito visited India from December 22, 1954 to January 8, 1955. The context also mentions that after his return, he removed many restrictions on churches in Yugoslavia.\\nHence it can be inferred that the answer is \\"India\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: threat and non-threat. Threat is a statement that someone will be hurt or harmed, especially if the person does not do something in particular.\\n\\nComment: Fixed it for ya:\\n\\"Doubters need only read the laudatory assessments in the progressive left wing foreign media.\\"\\n\\nUnder Harper, Canada's was seen as one of the to countries in the world to live, by any measure.   \\nPandering to the Muslim voting block in the corrupt UN has not enhanced our reputation with our key allies such a the USA, GB, or Israel.  Selling arms Saudi Arabia and adopting the divisive M-103 probably enhances our reputation with those countries who subjugate their people, will not allow women to drive, behead convicts, and throw gays off buildings.","target":"Threat","rationale":"The text contains a statement that one of the countries in the world might be hurt or harmed due to some political changes. Thus, it can be classified into \\"Threat\\" category."},{"source":"Question: \\"what is the last era mentioned?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"During the 16th and 17th centuries slave traders began to raid the region as part of the expansion of the Saharan and Nile River slave routes. Their captives were slaved and shipped to the Mediterranean coast, Europe, Arabia, the Western Hemisphere, or to the slave ports and factories along the West and North Africa or South the Ubanqui and Congo rivers. In the mid 19th century, the Bobangi people became major slave traders and sold their captives to the Americas using the Ubangi river to reach the coast. During the 18th century Bandia-Nzakara peoples established the Bangassou Kingdom along the Ubangi River.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"18th century","rationale":"The last era mentioned is the 18th century, as this refers to events that took place during the 1700s."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the alphabetical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no alphabetical element in the list\\n\\n['x', 'T', '9569', '8577', 'b', 'm', '2535', '2219', 'Z', '9887', 'e', '7345', '3423', '9671', 'C', '9035', '9679', '9507', 'E', 'F', '4213', '5811', 'E', 'H', '743', 'c', 'r']","target":"13","rationale":"Given the list ['x', 'T', '9569', '8577', 'b', 'm', '2535', '2219, Z, 9887, e, 7345, 3423, 9671 C 9035 9577 ,9507 E F 4213 5811 E H 743 c r'], let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. The 1st element is x -> (total) 1\\\\n2. The 2nd element is T -> (total) 2\\\\n3. The 5th element is b -> (total) 3\\\\n4. The 6th element is m -> (total) 4\\\\n5. The 11th element is e -> (total) 5\\\\n6. The 15th element is C -> (total) 6\\\\n7. The 18th elements are 950 and E->(totlal:8)\\\\nelements 19~23 all alphabets(5)\\\\nelement 24 alphabet(1)\\\\ntotal=13"},{"source":"The organisation reports that it has recently seen a significant rise in the number of complaints and some of these involve modem connections being redirected, unbeknown to the users.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nComplaints arose in the organisation about users who redirect their modem connections.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The text does not specify the nature of complaints, and it is possible that these could be unrelated to any redirection. So no inference can be made about users redirecting their modem connections from this sentence."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nPhone rang. Aria entered the patio. Emily entered the patio. The persimmon is in the red_bucket. Emily exited the patio. Phone rang. Aria moved the persimmon to the red_treasure_chest. Phone rang. Aria exited the patio. Emily entered the patio. Jayden entered the patio. Aria entered the patio. The pumpkin is in the red_treasure_chest. Phone rang. Aria exited the patio. Jayden moved the pumpkin to the red_bucket. Jayden exited the patio. Aria entered the patio. Aria entered the closet. Emily entered the closet. The strawberry is in the green_basket. Emily exited the closet. Aria moved the strawberry to the green_pantry. Aria exited the closet. Emily entered the closet. Aria entered the bathroom. Logan entered the bathroom. The green_pepper is in the green_box. Logan exited the bathroom. Aria moved the green_pepper to the red_crate. Aria exited the bathroom. Logan entered the bathroom. Where was the green_pepper at the beginning?","target":"green_box","rationale":"The green_pepper is in the green_box at the beginning of the story."},{"source":"I've always wondered: Which religion has holy books called the Vedas?","target":"Hindu culture","rationale":"The Vedas are a collection of texts which form the oldest layer of Sanskrit literature and one of the earliest literary records in India. The Hindu culture recognizes them as \\"the first, most sacred scriptures\\".\\nTherefore, it can be concluded that Hindus consider their holy books to be called 'Vedas', so this is a reasonable answer for the question: Which religion has holy books called the Vedas?\\n\\n\\nHow do you feel about giving feedback on how well our model performed (in terms crowd-sourcing cost)? This will help us better understand when we should use these models and when we shouldn't.  Please rate each example based on your confidence that the machine generated response was correct - if any doubt at all select wrong; if 100% sure select right. If unsure please just"},{"source":"The Marlan Sea and the Jowal Sea are two bodies of water currently being studied by scientists at the Hamford Research Complex. The goal of the study is to find out which sea would be a better choice to support the construction of an experimental underwater laboratory. The employees first begin by analyzing the surrounding regions of the two seas. They discover that the Marlan Sea has many rivers flowing into it. The vast majority of these rivers are located near farms that grow crops to sell to the local cities. The Jowal Sea is surrounded by mostly uninhabited land. The rivers that flow into it have almost no human civilizations near them and instead are surrounded by flat plains and some forests.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nIs the chance of a dead zone higher or lower in the Jowal Sea?","target":"lower","rationale":"A dead zone is an area of water with very little or no oxygen. This occurs when there are large amounts of nutrients coming from land and flowing into the sea, allowing for rapid algae growth; these algae then die off and decompose in the sea, consuming all available oxygen. In this case, since more farms surround rivers near the Marlan Sea than those around Jowal Sea‚Äôs rivers, it can be inferred that a higher chance exists for nutrients to run-off from farm fields surrounding Marlan Sea than Jowal Sea. Thus we conclude that chances of a dead zone forming in Jowal Seas would be lower because fewer people live around its rivers compared to the Marlan Seas' river banks (and thus less nutrient runoff).\\nSo based on previously stated conditions above"},{"source":"San Fernando Valley -- Nearly two-thirds of the valley's land area is part of the city of Los Angeles. The other incorporated cities in the valley are Glendale, Burbank, San Fernando, Hidden Hills, Agoura Hills, and Calabasas. \\nQuestion: is glendale part of the san fernando valley\\nAnswer:","target":"Yes","rationale":"The context mentioned that San Fernando Valley is nearly two-thirds of the valley's land area are part of Los Angeles. The other incorporated cities in the valley are Glendale, Burbank, San Fernando, Hidden Hills and Agoura Hills. From this information we can conclude that \\"Glendale\\" is a city within or near to the \\"San Fernando Valley\\". Hence, it will be correct to answer as Yes"},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Based on the sentence \\"A small dog chases a white ball on the grass\\", is the sentence \\"A dog is outside\\" a true sentence?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The sentence \\"A dog is outside\\" can be inferred from the given premise. So, the answer is yes."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\na i sleep i dream of you & amp me when i wake ita 's you ia 'll see i let you fly free like bird but i know you would come back home a i sleep the day away i know ita 's you i pray when i wake ita 's you ia 'll say ia 'll see you the next day a i sleep i dream of you & amp me my heart skip a bet be love shine through so that everyone can see we stand a one with open arm your voice mellows me out thata 's how i sleep & x85 but to know you be a blessing from above to be with you be a bless a lone for you to have me be a blessing from god this be the love that shin through it all & x85 love erica r","target":"high","rationale":"The kid is in high school."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nthey must be a big minority in d.c. seeing <number> voted for the devil bitch üòà","target":"devil bitch","rationale":"The output phrase should be \\"devil bitch\\" because it is offensive, specifically sexist. The tweet also implies that a large number of people in the district voted for someone they consider to be an evil woman. This could potentially insult or offend some women as well as political groups of any affiliation.\\"\\n]] } ]] ) end"},{"source":"Farting while not at home may cause you to experience what?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptions:\\n- make noise\\n- will smell bad smell\\n- making noise\\n- public disapproval\\n- odour","target":"public disapproval","rationale":"The question asks us to choose an option which describes the condition when we fart while not at home. The most suitable answer would be \\"public disapproval\\". This is because, in a public place or outside of your house people are likely to disapprove if you break wind."},{"source":"In mathematics, the absolute value of a number is the non-negative value of that number, without regarding its sign. For example, the absolute value of -2 is 2, and the absolute value of 5 is 5. In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to return the element with highest absolute value. If a negative and positive element have the same absolute value you should return the positive element. The absolute value for negative numbers can be found by multiplying them by -1. After finding the element with the maximum absolute value you should return the value of that element before you applied the absolute value.\\n\\n[-36.475 -81.963  41.238]","target":"-81.963","rationale":"The element with the highest absolute value in the given list is -81.963, which has an absolute value of 81.963. The absolute value of all other numbers in the list is less than or equal to 81.963. However, we need to return the value of the element before applying the absolute value, so the answer is -81.963"},{"source":"Given a question and its paraphrases, answer the question. The answer should exactly answer all the questions given without any ambiguity. Don't give partial answers.\\n\\nQuestions: ['in what year did lady jane grey marry guildford dudley?']","target":"1553","rationale":"Jane Grey married Guildford Dudley in 1553."},{"source":"The statistician looked at the attribute but wanted more information, what did he want?\\n\\nA. calculus\\n\\nB. description\\n\\nC. formulas\\n\\nD. sentence where described\\n\\nE. array\\n\\nThe best answer is","target":"B","rationale":"The passage describes a statistician who is attempting to determine the probability of winning at dice games. After looking at an attribute, he wants more information about that attribute in order to make his calculations, so B (description) is the best answer for this question."},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that is the least toxic with respect to continuing the prompt. Toxicity is defined as a rude, disrespectful, or unreasonable statement that is likely to make you leave a discussion. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: In NCAAB, Texas A&M Elston Turner scores 40 points in an 83-71 \\nCompletion A: victory over Colorado on Friday, March 17, 2016. (Photo: Mark D. Wilson, KXAN-TV)More than three \\nCompletion B: win over Colorado State. The Rebels trailed at the half after a 23-6 shooting night, but ended up taking a 41-29 lead after th","target":"Completion A","rationale":"Completion B is more toxic because it seems to be a comment about an ongoing basketball game, and the commenter is making a disrespectful statement towards the other team. Completion A is less toxic because it simply provides information about the game, and does not make any disrespectful comments."},{"source":"Have you ever been to the world's smallest bookstore?\\nThe World's Smallest Bookstore,whose official name is just these three words,sits quietly about 100 miles northeast of Toronto.\\nThe bookstore is about 10 feet by 10 feet,so it is easy to imagine how tiny it really is.The bookstore is open 24 hours a day.Inside the bookstore are various books,especially literary books and classic authors' works.So if you are looking for something less popular,you may get a bit disappointed there.\\nAnother special feature of this bookstore is that each book only costs three dollars.All the expenses are paid on the honor system,which means buyers should make a note of what they've bought and leave their money by themselves.So the tools of the trade in this bookstore are quite simple: pens,papers,light bulbs and a label-maker.\\nIn order to catch passers-by's attention,the billboards of the bookstore are several times bigger than the store itself.With these large eye-catchers,many people are willing to stop by and have a visit.\\nWhat's the passage mainly about?\\nA) The world's smallest bookstore.\\nB) A strange way of selling books.\\nC) The popular books nowadays.\\nD) The popular bookstores in the world.","target":"A","rationale":"The passage is mainly about the world's smallest bookstore, which sits quietly in Toronto. Various books are sold there and each book only costs three dollars. The tools of the trade in this store are pens, papers, light bulbs and a label-maker. In order to catch passers-by's attention, large billboards have been put up around it.\\nSo A) The world‚Äôs smallest bookstore can be considered as the answer here"},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that contain the given letter\\n\\nSentence: 'a guy is standing around with some sheep in the background'. How many words contain the letter 'l' in the sentence.","target":"0","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a guy is standing around with some sheep in the background', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' : 0 -> (total) 0\\\\n2. 'guy' : 1 -> (total) 1\\\\n3. 'is' : 0 -> (total) 1\\\\n4. 'standing' : 1-> (total) 2\\\\n5. 'around' : 2-> (total) 4 \\\\n6.'with':0 ->(total) 4 \\\\n7.'some':0  ->(tatal) 4 \\\\nsheep:0  --> total=4   in:1   background:1    total=6\\n\\nThe final total number is 6"},{"source":"Given a question and its paraphrases, answer the question. The answer should exactly answer all the questions given without any ambiguity. Don't give partial answers.\\n\\nQuestions: ['when was the planet mercury first discovered?']","target":"-0264","rationale":"The planet Mercury was discovered in -0264."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and the category to which it belongs. Your task is to classify whether the given category is correct or not by providing \\"True\\" and \\"False\\", respectively. Here are the definitions for the categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\",\\n\\nSentence: One strain ( A/shanghai/1 / 2013 ) contained the R294K substitution in the neuraminidase ( NA ) gene , indicating resistance to oseltamivir. \\n Section: background","target":"True","rationale":"The sentence provides background information about the mutations in H7N9 influenza viruses and their potential to develop drug resistance. This information is important for discussing the significance of the study and its relevance to previous research. Therefore, the correct category for this sentence is \\"Background\\". Hence, the answer is True.\\"\\""},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"With the initial investment of ¬£4,200, the new trial force of the Thames River Police began with about 50 men charged with policing 33,000 workers in the river trades, of whom Colquhoun claimed 11,000 were known criminals and \\"on the game.\\" The force was a success after its first year, and his men had \\"established their worth by saving ¬£122,000 worth of cargo and by the rescuing of several lives.\\" Word of this success spread quickly, and the government passed the Marine Police Bill on 28 July 1800, transforming it from a private to public police agency; now the oldest police force in the world. Colquhoun published a book on the experiment, The Commerce and Policing of the River Thames. It found receptive audiences far outside London, and inspired similar forces in other cities, notably, New York City, Dublin, and Sydney.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What historical achievement did the force accomplish?","target":"oldest police force in the world","rationale":"The passage describes the establishment of a force to police the River Thames, and claims that this is \\"the oldest police force in the world.\\" The question asks for an historical achievement. Therefore, we can infer that it refers to something done by or related to the force mentioned. In other words, it's asking us what makes this particular group distinct from all others? What set them apart historically?\\n\\nThe answer appears directly within the text: they were 'oldest police force in the world'."},{"source":"Coming off their bye week, the Chiefs went home for a Week 7 duel with the undefeated Tennessee Titans. In the first quarter, Kansas City trailed early as Titans kicker Rob Bironas got a 49-yard field goal, along with RB LenDale White getting a 6-yard TD run. In the second quarter, Tennessee increased its lead with White getting a 2-yard TD run. In the third quarter, the Chiefs continued to struggle as Bironas got a 46-yard field goal. In the fourth quarter, the Titans began to put the game out of reach as White got an 80-yard TD run. Kansas City would finally get on the board as kicker Nick Novak got a 26-yard field goal. Tennessee would seal the win as RB Chris Johnson got a 66-yard TD run. The Chiefs would end the game with QB Tyler Thigpen getting a 14-yard TD run. During the game starting QB Brodie Croyle (9/10 for 63&#160;yards) suffered a sprained knee in the second quarter. Also, veteran QB Damon Huard (9/16 for 96&#160;yards) later left the game in the fourth with an injured thumb. Both would be placed on injured reserve, ending their seasons. To help Tyler Thigpen prepare for the game against the Jets, the Chiefs implemented the spread offense to help Thigpen and the rest of the younger players play to the best of their abilities, and also following the absence of RB Larry Johnson due to suspension. The Chiefs made a huge gamble by doing so, as most in the NFL believe that a spread offense cannot work in professional football, and also head coach Herman Edwards was traditionally in favor of more conservative, run-oriented game plans. Prior to the Chiefs implementing the spread offense, Thigpen had been playing erratically with the Chiefs, and he suddenly became poised and effective running the new offense.\\n\\nWhich team scored the most in the third quarter?","target":"Titans","rationale":"In the third quarter, Titans scored 3 points with Bironas' 46-yard field goal. So it is clear that Titans scored the most in the third quarter."},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: How does a tiger get stripes?\\nPossibilities:\\n- from its environment\\n- from its food\\n- from its offspring\\n- from its parents","target":"from its parents","rationale":"The correct answer is option d: from its parents\\nTigers get stripes through their genes; they are born with them. In this case, the tiger gets it's stripes from its parents through genetics."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWho did Chick Corea work with on duets?\\n- Gary Burton\\n- Were the albums with duets of chick Corea and Gary Burton successful?\\n- The New Crystal Silence was issued in 2008 and won a Grammy Award in 2009.\\n- Did Chick Corea perform with any other artists besides Gary Burton?\\n- B√©la Fleck\\n- Was there another collaborator with Chick Corea besides Bela Fleck?\\n- Hancock\\n- What style were the Hancock duets with Chick Corea performed in?\\n-","target":"These concerts were presented in elegant settings with both pianists dressed formally and performing on Yamaha concert grand pianos.","rationale":"The answer is \\"These concerts were presented in elegant settings with both pianists dressed formally and performing on Yamaha concert grand pianos.\\" because it is the only one that makes sense. The first two options give information about Chick Corea and Gary Burton, but the question asks who else did Chick Corea perform with. The third option \\"Did Chick Corea perform with any other artists besides Gary Burton?\\" does not make sense because it is a yes/no question and does not provide an answer to the previous question (who did he work with). Option 3: \\"Was there another collaborator with Chick Corea besides Bela Fleck?\\" also doesn't make sense because it's another yes/no question, and doesn't provide an answer to who else he worked with. Option 4: \\"Hancock\\" also doesn't make sense, as this was not part of a conversation; option 1 was the reply to option 3 (\\"Were there albums of duets between chick corea and gary burton successful\\"). Therefore, all of these options do not provide information or answers related to how they were performed or styled; hence we can conclude that they are wrong. The only remaining one which provides some information related to how they were performed is option 2: These concerts were presented in elegant settings with both pianists dressed formally and performing on Yamaha concert grand pianos.\\", which must be correct.\\""},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nSay Anything is a board game designed by Dominic Crapuchettes and Satish Pillalamarri. It was released by North Star Games in 2008 as a follow up to the award-winning Wits & Wagers. Say Anything is very similar to Wits & Wagers except players answer open-ended subjective questions instead of trivia questions. The goal of Say Anything is to get people talking about interesting things and laughing.\\n\\nHypothesis: Say Anything had more sales than Wits & Wagers.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"Say Anything is a follow up to the award-winning Wits & Wagers, but it does not mean that Say Anything had more sales than Wits & Wagers. It's impossible for us to tell from this context whether or not Say Anything had better sale figures than its predecessor. So the answer should be \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and determine if the hypothesis is true. Select from options at the end:\\n\\nHubble is helping astronomers precisely calculate the age of the universe by providing accurate distances to galaxies, an important prerequisite for calculating age. Hubble measures the distances to neighboring galaxies by finding accurate \\"milepost markers,\\" a special class of pulsating star called Cepheid variables. These, in turn, are being used to calibrate more remote milepost markers.\\n\\nHypothesis: Hubble discovers black holes.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nThe answer is","target":"no","rationale":"The paragraph talks about how Hubble is helping astronomers precisely calculate the age of the universe by providing accurate distances to galaxies. However, it does not mention anything about black holes. Hence, we can say that this hypothesis is false."},{"source":"Answer the question...who was robin in the original batman series??","target":"Burt Ward","rationale":"The answer is Burt Ward, who played Robin in the original Batman series."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a string S and a character c separated by a comma. You need to check if the character c is present in S or not. Return 1 if it is present, else return 0.\\n\\nONpJcCzUjhaFncmAgLlFShxi, e","target":"0","rationale":"The given character e is not present in the string. Hence, the answer is 0."},{"source":"Given two entities as input, classify as \\"yes\\" if second entity is the part of the first entity. Otherwise classify them as \\"no\\". These are entities of meronym In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., second entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., first entity).\\n\\nEntity 1: viper \\n Entity 2: pollen cone","target":"no","rationale":"The second entity, \\"pollen cone\\", is not a part of the first entity, \\"viper\\". A pollen cone refers to a male reproductive structure in seed plants (angiosperms and gymnosperms). On the other hand, viper is an animal. Therefore, these two entities are unrelated."},{"source":"In this task, you need to provide the correct option for a given problem on probability from the provided options.\\n\\nProblem: from a pack of cards , two cards are drawn one after the other , with replacement . what is the probability that the first card is a black card and the second card is a king or queen ? \\nOptions: a ) 1 / 52 , b ) 1 / 13 , c ) 1 / 26 , d ) 3 / 26 , e ) 17 / 26","target":"b","rationale":"The probability of drawing a black card from the pack is 26/52. The probability of replacing it and then drawing a king or queen is 2/52. The joint probability of both these events occurring is (26/52) x (2/52) = 1/13 as required."},{"source":"Answer the following question:\\n\\nwho was the first us president to be nominated at a large party convention?","target":"Andrew Jackson","rationale":"Andrew Jackson was the first US president to be nominated at a large party convention, in 1832."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nnew french president spokesman is an ethnomasochist and a nigger lover","target":"ethnomasochist","rationale":"The use of the word ethnomasochist is offensive and derogatory towards other ethnic groups."},{"source":"Given a goal and 2 solutions, choose the most appropriate solution.\\nGoal: Fix blurry smartphone camera lens.\\n- Solution 1: Put scotch tape over lens.\\n- Solution 2: Put duct tape over lens.\\n\\nAnswer by returning either Solution 1 or Solution 2","target":"Solution 1","rationale":"A smartphone camera lens can become blurry due to accumulation of dirt and dust. In this case, putting scotch tape over the lens would remove any debris from its surface without damaging it, which is why it's a better solution than using duct tape that could scratch or damage the glass on your phone. So Solution 1 is better in this scenario."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nMia entered the patio. Ella entered the patio. The asparagus is in the red_drawer. Mia moved the asparagus to the green_box. Ella is in the patio. Jackson entered the patio. The corn is in the green_box. Ella moved the corn to the red_drawer. Liam entered the laundry. Jackson entered the laundry. The carrot is in the green_bottle. Liam moved the carrot to the green_pantry. Mia entered the playroom. Jackson entered the playroom. The tomato is in the blue_cupboard. Mia moved the tomato to the red_treasure_chest. Where is the tomato really?","target":"red_treasure_chest","rationale":"The tomato is in the red_treasure_chest because Mia moved the tomato to the red_treasure_chest."},{"source":"Which entity is this text about?\\n\\nRobert Ervin Howard (January 22, 1906 - June 11, 1936) was an American author who wrote pulp fiction in a diverse range of genres. He is well known for his character Conan the Barbarian and is regarded as the father of the sword and sorcery subgenre. Howard was born and raised in Texas. He spent most of his life in the town of Cross Plains, with some time spent in nearby Brownwood.\\n\\nHoward was born January 22, 1906 in Peaster, Texas, the only son of a traveling country physician, Dr. Isaac Mordecai Howard, and his wife, Hester Jane Ervin Howard. His early life was spent wandering through a variety of Texas cowtowns and boomtowns: Dark Valley (1906), Seminole (1908), Bronte (1909), Poteet (1910), Oran (1912), Wichita Falls (1913), Bagwell (1913), Cross Cut (1915), and Burkett (1917).  During Howard's youth his parents' relationship began to break down. The Howard family had problems with money which may have been exacerbated by Isaac Howard investing in get-rich-quick schemes. Hester Howard, meanwhile, came to believe that she had married below herself. Soon the pair were actively fighting. Hester did not want Isaac to have anything to do with their son. She had a particularly strong influence on her son's intellectual growth. She had spent her early years helping a variety of sick relatives, contracting tuberculosis in the process. She instilled in her son a deep love of poetry and literature, recited verse daily and supported him unceasingly in his efforts to write.  Other experiences would later seep into his prose. Although he loved reading and learning, he found school to be confining and began to hate having anyone in authority over him. Experiences watching and confronting bullies revealed the omnipresence of evil and enemies in the world, and taught him the value of physical strength and violence. Being the son of the local doctor gave Howard frequent exposure to the effects of injury and violence, due to accidents on farms and oil fields combined with the massive increase in crime that came with the oil boom. Firsthand tales of gunfights, lynchings, feuds, and Indian raids developed his distinctly Texan, hardboiled outlook on the world. Sports, especially boxing, became a passionate preoccupation. At the time, boxing was the most popular sport in the country, with a cultural influence far in excess of what it is today. James J. Jeffries, Jack Johnson, Bob Fitzsimmons, and later Jack Dempsey were the names that inspired during those years, and he grew up a lover of all contests of violent, masculine struggle.\\n\\nEntity:","target":"Robert E. Howard","rationale":"It can be inferred from the text that Robert E. Howard was an American author known for his characters of Conan and sword & sorcery fiction stories. The text also states he grew up in Texas, had a tough childhood, took interest in boxing and literature which contributed to his work later on in life. \\nTherefore it is clear the entity described here is: \\"Robert E. Howard\\""},{"source":"Here's a complex question that requires someone to reason about the input, can you answer it?\\nOne Day in Your Life is a compilation of Michael Jackson's mid-1970s recordings from when he was aged 15 and 16, the other songs were taken from which popular American family music group, formed in 1964, under the name the Jackson Brothers?","target":"The Jackson 5","rationale":"The answer is based on the information that One Day in Your Life was a compilation of Michael Jackson's mid-1970s recordings from when he was aged 15 and 16, with the other songs taken from The Jackons 5. \\nTherefore, the answer should be \\"The Jackson 5\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the abstract of a research paper. Your task is to generate a summary of this abstract. Your summary should not be very short, but it's better if it's not more than 30 words.\\n\\nNeural networks (NNs) are able to perform tasks that rely on compositional structure even though they lack obvious mechanisms for representing this structure. To analyze the internal representations that enable such success, we propose ROLE, a technique that detects whether these representations implicitly encode symbolic structure. ROLE learns to approximate the representations of a target encoder E by learning a symbolic constituent structure and an embedding of that structure into E‚Äôs representational vector space. The constituents of the approximating symbol structure are defined by structural positions ‚Äî roles ‚Äî that can be filled by symbols. We show that when E is constructed to explicitly embed a particular type of structure (e.g., string or tree), ROLE successfully extracts the ground-truth roles defining that structure. We then analyze a seq2seq network trained to perform a more complex compositional task (SCAN), where there is no ground truth role scheme available. For this model, ROLE successfully discovers an interpretable symbolic structure that the model implicitly uses to perform the SCAN task, providing a comprehensive account of the link between the representations and the behavior of a notoriously hard-to-interpret type of model. We verify the causal importance of the discovered symbolic structure by showing that, when we systematically manipulate hidden embeddings based on this symbolic structure, the model‚Äôs output is also changed in the way predicted by our analysis. Finally, we use ROLE to explore whether popular sentence embedding models are capturing compositional structure and find evidence that they are not; we conclude by discussing how insights from ROLE can be used to impart new inductive biases that will improve the compositional abilities of such models.","target":"We introduce a new analysis technique that discovers interpretable compositional structure in notoriously hard-to-interpret recurrent neural networks","rationale":"Here's a brief summary:\\\\nWe introduce a new analysis technique that discovers interpretable compositional structure in notoriously hard-to-interpret recurrent neural networks."},{"source":"Given a paragraph and a claim, classify it this way: If the claim contradicts the evidence present in the paragraph, classify the claim as '0'. If the claim has multiple supporting *AND* contradicting evidences, classify the claim as '1'. If the claim has supporting evidence and the paragraph is in overall favor of the claim, then classify the claim as '2'.\\n\\nParagraph: In a TV message on Monday evening watched by more than 27 million people, Prime Minister Boris Johnson ordered people to stay at home, told nearly all shops to close and banned social gatherings including weddings and baptisms. However, public transport in London was busy during the morning rush hour and the streets were far from deserted amid confusion over the government‚Äôs advice to workers. The death toll from coronavirus in the United Kingdom has jumped by 87 to a total of 422 - the biggest daily increase since the crisis began. Meanwhile, the economic devastation was underscored by a survey that suggested the economy was shrinking at a record pace, faster than during the 2008-09 financial crisis. The unprecedented peacetime restrictions announced by Johnson, which will last at least three weeks, are intended to stop the state-run National Health Service (NHS), which suffers from staff shortages at the best of times, being overwhelmed. ‚ÄúThese measures are not advice, they are rules and will be enforced, including by the police,‚Äù health minister Matt Hancock told parliament. At a news conference later, Hancock announced plans to open a temporary hospital next week at the Excel Centre, a huge venue in east London normally used for trade fairs and similar events. ‚ÄúWith the help of the military and with NHS clinicians we will make sure that we have the capacity that we need so that everyone can get the support they need,‚Äù he said. British Transport Police said 500 officers will be deployed to train stations across the country to remind the public of the government‚Äôs advice to travel only when essential. Hancock called for 250,000 volunteers to help the NHS with tasks such as delivering medicines from pharmacies, driving patients to and from hospital appointments and phoning people isolating at home to check up on them. ‚ÄúIf you are well and able to do so safely, I would urge you to sign up today to help the most vulnerable people in our communities as an NHS Volunteer Responder,‚Äù Hancock said. He also said the government had bought 3.5 million coronavirus antibody tests so that people who suspect they have had the virus would be able to find out for sure. Despite the message for people to stay at home, some roads were still busy and utility workmen and others were still mingling close together. Social media images showed the capital‚Äôs underground trains were packed with passengers closer than the 2-metre (6-foot) recommended distance apart and the government said ‚Äúappropriate‚Äù construction work should continue. ‚ÄúThe government needs to urgently provide clearer guidance on who should be working and who shouldn‚Äôt,‚Äù said Rebecca Long-Bailey, the opposition Labour Party‚Äôs business policy chief. ‚ÄúNo one should be asked to work if they are not providing an essential function in this crisis.‚Äù  Under the curbs on movement, people should leave their homes only for very limited reasons such as going to supermarkets for vital supplies or for exercise once a day. Police, who will be able to issue fines of 30 pounds ($35), will now be able to break up gatherings of more than two people. A snap YouGov poll found that 93 percent of Britons supported the measures but were split on whether fines would be a sufficient deterrent. Supermarkets, where shelves have been stripped bare by  panic-buying in recent days, said they had begun limiting the number of shoppers in stores at any one time, erecting barriers outside, and installing screens at checkouts to protect staff. Last week, the government announced billions of pounds of help for businesses and said it would help to pay the wages of employees, giving grants to cover 80% of a worker‚Äôs salary if they were kept on as staff. But critics said it did not provide support for the self-employed, who total about 5 million in Britain compared to roughly 28 million employees, meaning they either had to keep working or risk losing all income. Finance minister Rishi Sunak told parliament the government was working on measures to help self-employed people, but said these had to be practical and fair. Claim: UK calls for 250,000 volunteers as virus deaths surge.","target":"2","rationale":"The claim that the UK has called for 250,000 volunteers as virus deaths surge is supported by the paragraph. The paragraph states that health minister Matt Hancock has called for 250,000 volunteers to help the NHS with tasks such as delivering medicines from pharmacies and driving patients to and from hospital appointments. The paragraph also indicates that Matt Hancock made this call at a news conference; therefore, it can be inferred that he made this call publicly.  In addition, despite stating unfavorable effects of the virus on London's public transport system and economy, the overall tone of the paragraph remains in favor of Matt Hancock's actions against coronavirus. Hence, based on all these evidence given in support of the statement along with its overall positive sentiment towards his actions against coronavirus, we conclude that this statement is true (class 2)."},{"source":"Produce a brief English sentence that would be considered grammatically as category: unacceptable\\nAll categories: OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"the boy likes themselves.","rationale":"Here's an example of an unacceptable English sentence: the boy likes themselves."},{"source":"Suggest a movie title for the following movie plot: The story is set in 1959 and is told with only a few brief snatches of dialogue, much of it in Gaelic. A down-on-his-luck illusionist (known by his stage name, \\"Tatischeff\\") watches his popularity and employment in Paris dry up. He packs his meager belongings and props, including an ill-tempered white rabbit, and moves to London. There he finds himself as the irrelevant act following a popular rock band. Despite his wounded pride, he adopts a nothing-to-lose attitude and continues plying his trade at yet smaller gatherings in bars, caf√É¬©s, and private parties.\\nHe accepts the invitation of a drunken party patron, taking a long, slow journey to a remote Scottish island (Iona in the Inner Hebrides). The small village's pub has only recently been wired for electricity, and he and his rabbit are appreciated for a time. Living modestly in a room above the pub, the illusionist encounters a young girl named Alice who is captivated by his otherworldly abilities and kind gestures, including a gift of new red shoes. Competition from more modern forms of entertainment follow the illusionist even to this idyll, and he soon moves on.\\nAlice believes the downtrodden performer possesses genuine supernatural powers, and follows him to Edinburgh, where he performs at a modest, out-of-the-way theater. They book a room in a rundown guest house favored by other fading performers (a trio of acrobats, a clown, and a ventriloquist). The illusionist sleeps on a small couch and the girl keeps busy by cleaning and cooking food that she shares with the neighbors. The girl's affections even tame the rabbit, but the illusionist's increasingly meager wages, lavished on a series of gifts for Alice, lead him to pawn off his magic kit and secretly take on more demeaning jobs. The other traditional performers become similarly depressed and destitute.\\nUnable to muster the courage to tell his starry-eyed admirer the truth about his fading trade, the illusionist continues giving until he has nothing more to offer. Alice meanwhile discovers the...","target":"The Illusionist","rationale":"The plot and description provided in the question describe a 2006 movie called \\"The Illusionist\\"."},{"source":"Premise: A digger waits patiently as a worker inspects the pipe.\\n\\nHypothesis: A digger is nervous\\n\\n.Choose the correct answer: Given the premise, can we conclude the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"it is not possible to tell","rationale":"The premise describes a worker inspecting the pipe while being watched by a digger. Given this, it is not possible to tell whether or not the digger was nervous based on only this information alone."},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: what number times ( 1 ‚ÅÑ 6 ) ^ 2 will give the value of 6 ^ 3 ?\\nOptions: a. 6, b. 36, c. 216, d. 1296, e. 7776","target":"e","rationale":"The given problem is asking what number times (1/6)^2 equals 6^3. To solve the problem, we can use the following steps:\\\\n1. The answer to 6^3 is equal to 216\\\\n2. Divide the answer by (1/6)^2 = 36\\\\n3. The final answer should be 216 / 36 = 6"},{"source":"Math Problem\\nSolve 34*f + 14 - 116 = 0 for f.","target":"3","rationale":"To solve for f, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with:\\n34*f + 14 - 116 = 0\\nSubtracting 14 from both sides: 34*f - 102 = 0 Adding 102 to both sides: 34*f = 102 Dividing by 34: f=102/34 Simplifying fractional exponent and combining like terms gives us:\\\\n\\\\nTherefore, the solution is 3."},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 5, equation weights = [1, 7, 2]","target":"62","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 1x^2 + 7x + 2\\\\nSubstituting x = 5, we get: 1(5)^2 + 7(5) + 2 = 25 + 35 + 2 = 62"},{"source":"Give me a possible correct answer to the question \\"where do most of the people live in japan?\\"","target":"Tokyo","rationale":"Most people live in Tokyo, Osaka, and Nagoya."},{"source":"EXAM\\n1. Answer by yes or no.\\n\\nDocument: Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport -- Reagan National has United States immigration and customs facilities only for business jet traffic; the only scheduled international flights allowed to land at the airport are those from airports with U.S. Customs and Border Protection preclearance facilities. Other international passenger flights must use Washington Dulles International Airport or Baltimore--Washington International Airport.\\nQuestion: is dulles airport the same as reagan airport?","target":"No","rationale":"The document mentions that Dulles Airport is a place for international passenger flights. It does not mention Reagan airport in this context, so the answer to whether or not they are the same cannot be inferred from this passage and should thusly be No"},{"source":"In this task you are given a tweet that contains some form of irony. You must classify the type of irony the tweet has. Label the tweets (\\"polarity\\",\\"situational\\",\\"other\\") based on the irony they have. Situational irony happens when a situation fails to meet some expectations, Label these instances as \\"situational\\". polarity irony happens when irony is achieved by inverting the intended sentence, Label these instances as \\"polarity\\". There are other kinds of ironies that are neither polarity nor situational, Label these instances as \\"other\\". Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\n@TODAYshow Joel Olstein, a man who hardly ever mentions Jesus in his sermons,  is going to talk about the meaning of Christmas?","target":"situational","rationale":"The irony in this tweet is situational because the speaker expects Joel Olstein to mention Jesus, but the situation actually does not meet that expectation."},{"source":"In today's world, so many people like traveling around the world. Traveling abroad can be expensive, but there are some ways of visiting Britain cheaply. So we hope  we can give you some good ideas.\\nIf you don't go there in the busy months--July and August, your visit may be cheaper. There will be fewer visitors. The weather in Britain can be pleasant from April to the end of September. Of course  you can go there in winter, but it is often dark by 4 pm. Many places, such as large houses and castles are closed in winter. However, if you are interested in museums, art galleries  or theaters, winter may be the good time to visit.\\nIf you are a student, it is a good idea to apply for   an International Student Identify Card. With the card, you can save a lot of money. You can get the card from your local  student travel office, and you can also call (44)08708 413224 to get it. To get the card, you need to show that you are a student, get a passport photo, and pay for a little money.\\nA student without an International Student Identify Card may  _  .\\nA) get a little money.\\nB) watch TV at home.\\nC) spend more money.\\nD) save a lot of money.","target":"C","rationale":"The article mentions that the International Student Identify Card is helpful for saving money, so a student without this card would not be able to save as much. Therefore, they will spend more than students with the card. So we can say that C) \\"spend more money\\" is correct answer"},{"source":"I gave my students this multiple choice question: Which of these is an example of liquid water?\\n\\nOnly one answer is correct among these 4 choices:\\n- Frost\\n- Ice\\n- Rain\\n- Steam\\n\\nCould you tell me which one is correct?","target":"Rain","rationale":"The answer is Rain because it's an example of liquid water; the others are not."},{"source":"Katy participated in a summer reading program at her local library. She read 8 books in June, twice as many in July and three fewer in August than she did in July. How many books did Katy read during the summer?","target":"37","rationale":"Katy read twice as many books in July as she did in June, so she read 2 * 8 = 16 books in July. She read three fewer books in August than she did in July, so she read 16 - 3 = 13 books in August. So, including June, she read 8 + 16 + 13 = 37 books total."},{"source":"The task is to generate text based of an event. For the given event, there will be a person who does the action in the event (usually PersonX). Your task is to write that persons emotional reaction to the event, i.e. how that person feels after doing the action.\\n\\nPersonX digs up dirt","target":"accomplished","rationale":"When a person digs up dirt, they feel accomplished, as if they have achieved something."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question.\\nQuestion: \\"when monopoly came out?\\"\\nTopic:","target":"History of the board game Monopoly","rationale":"This question is asking when the board game Monopoly was first introduced.\\nTherefore, this question's topic is \\"History of the board game Monopoly\\"."},{"source":"Given the fact that:\\n\\nRicher nations use far more energy resources, especially fossil fuels, than poorer nations do.\\n\\nAnswer the question:\\n\\n\\nSuzie is studying different countries and the amount of energy sources they use. She finds that South Africa is poorer than the United States. Therefore, South Africa or the United States uses less energy sources?","target":"South Africa","rationale":"In this example, the fact that is given states \\"Richer nations use far more energy resources, especially fossil fuels, than poorer nations do.\\" Given this information and Suzie's findings in her study we can infer that South Africa likely uses less energy sources because it is a poorer nation."},{"source":"Adverse drug reactions are appreciably harmful or unpleasant reactions resulting from an intervention related to the use of medical products, which predicts hazard from future administration and warrants prevention or specific treatment, or alteration of the dosage regimen, or withdrawal of the product. Given medical case reports extracted from MEDLINE, the task is to classify whether the case report mentions the presence of any adverse drug reaction. Classify your answers into non-adverse drug event and adverse drug event.\\n\\nRESULTS: Seven patients showed marked visual field constriction with some sparing of the temporal visual field.","target":"non-adverse drug event","rationale":"An adverse drug reaction is an appreciably harmful or unpleasant reaction resulting from the administration of a drug. The case report does not mention any such event, so the answer is \\"non-adverse drug event\\"."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the other-need strategy, otherwise output No. other-need is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used when the participants discuss a need for someone else rather than themselves. For instance, describing the need for firewood to keep the kids warm.\\n\\nContext: 'I would like to ask for 3 firewood, 1 water and 0 food. I will be in an area where no extra wood will be available and I need the wood to cook all the food that I will already have.'\\nUtterance: 'I understand where you're coming from but I'm afraid that is not acceptable.  My family's comfort is my top priority and I will be needing at least 2 firewoods to make sure they are kept warm.  I would also request some extra water. '","target":"Yes","rationale":"In the given example, the speaker describes their need for firewood to keep their family warm. The speaker also states that other-need is their top priority. Hence, this is an example of an utterance containing the other-need strategy and therefore, the answer is 'Yes'."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to when was from little things big things grow written??","target":"1991","rationale":"From Little Things Big Things Grow was written in 1991 by Paul Kelly and Kev Carmody."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the abstract of a research paper. Your task is to generate a summary of this abstract. Your summary should not be very short, but it's better if it's not more than 30 words.\\n\\nLanguage modeling tasks, in which words are predicted on the basis of a local context, have been very effective for learning word embeddings and context dependent representations of phrases. Motivated by the observation that efforts to code\\n world knowledge into machine readable knowledge bases tend to be entity-centric,\\n we investigate the use of a fill-in-the-blank task to learn context independent representations of entities from the contexts in which those entities were mentioned.\\n We show that large scale training of neural models allows us to learn extremely high fidelity entity typing information, which we demonstrate with few-shot reconstruction of Wikipedia categories. Our learning approach is powerful enough\\n to encode specialized topics such as Giro d‚ÄôItalia cyclists.","target":"We learn entity representations that can reconstruct Wikipedia categories with just a few exemplars","rationale":"Here's a brief summary:\\\\nWe learn entity representations that can reconstruct Wikipedia categories with just a few exemplars."},{"source":"A Student's Song of Heidelberg (German:Ein Burschenlied aus Heidelberg) is a 1930 German musical film directed by Karl Hartl and starring Hans Brausewetter, Betty Bird and Willi Forst. It marked Hartl's directoral debut. The film is in the tradition of the nostalgic Old Heidelberg.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nHans Brausewetter is a well known actor.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"\\"Hans Brausewetter is a well known actor\\" cannot be concluded from the given text. We can gather that he was an important member of cast, but we don't know if many people saw this film and became aware of him. So \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Heat, light, and sound are all different forms of energy. Sentence 2: Assess the sources and forms of energy (heat, light, electricity, mechanical motions and sound).","target":"entails","rationale":"The premise describes several different forms of energy, including heat, light and sound. The hypothesis states that these three types of energy are all \\"different forms of energy\\". Therefore, the premise supports the claim made in the hypothesis because it provides additional information about specific examples (heat, light and sound) related to this claim. As a result, Statement 2 entails or implies Statement 1."},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question Kuroda Nagamasa  was a daimy≈ç during the late Azuchi-Momoyama and early Edo periods. He was the son of Kuroda Kanbei, Toyotomi Hideyoshi's chief strategist and adviser. His child-hood name was Shojumaru . In 1577, when Nagamasa was a small child, his father was tried and sentenced as a spy by Oda Nobunaga. Nagamasa was kidnapped and nearly killed as a hostage. With the help of Yamauchi Kazutoyo and his wife, Takenaka Hanbei ended up rescuing him. After Oda Nobunaga was killed in Honn≈ç-ji incident of 1582, Nagamasa served Toyotomi Hideyoshi with his father and participated in the invasion of the Ch≈´goku region. Nagamasa also participated in the first Korean campaign , commanding the Third Division of 5000 men during the first invasion 1592-1593. In the second part of the campaign  he held command in The Army of the Right. He took part in the Battle of Sekigahara in the year 1600 serving under Tokugawa Ieyasu. His men killed Shima Sakon, securing victory for the Eastern army. As a reward for his service at Sekigahara, Tokugawa granted Nagamasa Chikuzen  - 520.000 koku - in exchange for his previous fief Nakatsu, Buzen.Later he participated in the Osaka Castle campaigns.\\nWhich did Nagamasa take part in first, The Osaka Castle campaigns or the Battle of Sekigahara?","target":"Battle of Sekigahara","rationale":"Nagamasa took part in the Battle of Sekigahara first, because it was mentioned that he participated in this battle before taking part in The Osaka Castle campaigns."},{"source":"What is the answer?\\nContext: The first Dominican site in England was at Oxford, in the parishes of St. Edward and St. Adelaide. The friars built an oratory to the Blessed Virgin Mary and by 1265, the brethren, in keeping with their devotion to study, began erecting a school. Actually, the Dominican brothers likely began a school immediately after their arrival, as priories were legally schools. Information about the schools of the English Province is limited, but a few facts are known. Much of the information available is taken from visitation records. The \\"visitation\\" was a section of the province through which visitors to each priory could describe the state of its religious life and its studies to the next chapter. There were four such visits in England and Wales‚ÄîOxford, London, Cambridge and York. All Dominican students were required to learn grammar, old and new logic, natural philosophy and theology. Of all of the curricular areas, however, theology was the most important. This is not surprising when one remembers Dominic's zeal for it.;\\nQuestion: What was the most important subject that all Benedictine students had to learn?;\\nAnswer:","target":"Answer not in context","rationale":"The question asks the most important subject that all Benedictine students had to learn. However, there is no mention of \\"Benedictine\\" or even any other religious order in the context except for Dominican friars.\\nTherefore, we can conclude that this answer is not available from reading the given paragraph and select: Answer not in context"},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What is an archaic view that held women back?\\nContext: As the Tokugawa period progressed more value became placed on education, and the education of females beginning at a young age became important to families and society as a whole. Marriage criteria began to weigh intelligence and education as desirable attributes in a wife, right along with physical attractiveness. Though many of the texts written for women during the Tokugawa period only pertained to how a woman could become a successful wife and household manager, there were those that undertook the challenge of learning to read, and also tackled philosophical and literary classics. Nearly all women of the samurai class were literate by the end of the Tokugawa period.","target":"how a woman could become a successful wife and household manager","rationale":"The question asks for an archaic view that held women back, which refers to a way of thinking about something in the past. The context discusses how much value was placed on education during the Tokugawa period and how important it was for families to educate their daughters from a young age. It also highlights some texts written for women at this time which focused on different topics including teaching them \\"how a woman could become a successful wife and household manager\\". However, there were other texts that encouraged literacy and challenged the idea that girls should not read philosophical or literary classics. Although many girls learned these skills by the end of this era, before they did so they were prevented from reading anything but books pertaining to being wives and house managers.\\nSo, based on all this information we can infer that an outdated"},{"source":"Question: He always tried to shop local, he didn't like to support what kind of product?\\nOptions:\\n- homegrown\\n- foreign\\n- national\\n- far away\\n- worldwide\\n\\nThe answer is \\"foreign\\" because","target":"foreign | definition of foreign at dictionary.com","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"foreign | definition of foreign at dictionary.com\\"."},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: Who is the cynical bridesmaid's cousin? ?\\n\\nAnnie Walker is a single woman in her mid-thirties, living in Milwaukee. Following the failure of her bakery due to the recession, her boyfriend left her, and she lost her savings, forcing her to take a job as a sales clerk in a jewelry store and share an apartment with an English immigrant roommate Gil and his sister Brynn. Her business failure was so painful that she has given up baking entirely. Annie has a no-strings-attached sexual relationship with the self-absorbed Ted, but she hopes for something more from him. Her best friend, Lillian, is virtually her only source of happiness.\\nLillian becomes engaged and asks Annie to be her maid of honor. At the engagement party, Annie meets Lillian's bridesmaids: cynical, worldly, long-married cousin Rita; na√Øve and idealistic newlywed friend from work Becca; the groom's decidedly unfiltered sister Megan; and Helen, the rich, beautiful, and elite wife of the groom's boss. Helen and Annie, who are jealous of each other's friendship with Lillian, take an instant dislike to each other, but Lillian persuades them to spend time together.","target":"Lillian","rationale":"The cynical bridesmaid's cousin is Lillian, the bride to be."},{"source":"Answer the question below:\\n\\n\\nIf a muscle is exercised, it will become bigger or smaller? \\n\\n\\nAssuming that:\\n\\nMuscles that are exercised are bigger and stronger than muscles that are not exercised.","target":"bigger","rationale":"Muscles that are exercised regularly will become larger than muscles that are not. So the answer is bigger.\\"\\n*/"},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string of characters. You should remove all vowels from the given string. Vowels are: i,e,a,u,o. The character 'y' or 'Y' does not count as a vowel.\\n\\nhvTIeFITIINC","target":"hvTFTNC","rationale":"The given string contains the vowels 'i', 'e', and 'I', which should be removed according to the instructions. The resulting string after removing the vowels is 'hvTFTNC'."},{"source":"In the county, the population was spread out with 23.5% under the age of 18, 7.8% from 18 to 24, 28.5% from 25 to 44, 25.9% from 45 to 64, and 14.2% who were 65 years of age or older.  The median age was 40 years. For every 100 females, there were 93.8 males.  For every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 90.5 males.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"What age group has the highest percentage of the population in the county?","rationale":"Here's a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: What age group has the highest percentage of the population in the county?"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the numerical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no numerical element in the list.\\n\\n['X', 'Z', 'b', 'b', 'Z', 'z', 'B', '8889', 'y', 'o', 'y', 'n', '8881', '7023', 'r', 'X', '7139', 'k', 'X', 'j', 'B', 'z', '8033', '8225', 'P', 'U', 'i', 's', '6455', 'N', 'M', 'i', 'l', '9275', 'T', 'v', '2199', '7517', 'n', '6065']","target":"11","rationale":"Given the list ['X', 'Z', 'b', 'b', 'Z', 'z', 'B', '8889',  ... ,'n'], we need to find all numerical elements.\\\\n1. There's a numerical element 8889 at 8th index.\\\\n2. There's a numerical element 8871 at 12th index.\\\\n3. The 13rd element is numeric: 7023.\\\\n4. The 14rd element is numeric: 7139, and so on...\\n\\nThe final count of all the numerical elements in the given list is 11 (8 + 1 + 2 = 11)."},{"source":"Reagan announced he had Alzheimer's disease, an incurable brain affliction.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nReagan died of pneumonia complicated by Alzheimer's disease\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The paragraph states that Reagan announced he had Alzheimer's disease. However, it does not mention whether the former president eventually died of this incurable brain affliction or not. As such, there is no basis to conclude that \\"Reagan died of pneumonia complicated by Alzheimer's disease\\" is true."},{"source":"Thursday morning when I went to put my walking shoes on by the front door , I noticed several ants crawling around on the floor . Where did those come from ? I never had ants in here before . Since then I have been finding ants on the living room floor , and now in the kitchen .\\nWhat 's a possible reason there were ants crawling around on the floor ?\\nA. None of the above choices .\\nB. Because there was some food spilled or left out .\\nC. Because the writer never had ants in there before .\\nD. Because it was Thursday morning .","target":"B","rationale":"Ants are attracted to food, sugar and water. Spilled or left out food can attract ants into a house through cracks in the wall or other entrances. Since this is the case, B: Because there was some food spilled or left out would be a possible reason why there were ants on the floor where they had not been before.\\nTherefore, choice B is correct and A-D are incorrect answers for this question."},{"source":"You are given two sentences. You have to find if there is entailment or agreement of the Hypothesis by the Premise. From the given pair of sentences, you should identify if there is enough information in the Premise to support the claim made in the Hypothesis. The Premise may not exactly be the same as Hypothesis. Your task is to return 'entails' if the premise supports hypothesis else return 'neutral'.\\n\\nPremise: For humans, most skin cancers are associated with exposure to ultraviolet radiation. \\n Hypothesis: Exposure to ultraviolet radiation can increase the amount of pigment in the skin and make it appear darker.","target":"neutral","rationale":"The premise provides information about the relationship between exposure to ultraviolet radiation and skin cancer in humans. It does not provide any information about the effects that exposure to ultraviolet radiation has on skin pigmentation or its appearance. Therefore, there is no direct connection between the premise and the hypothesis, and the premise does not provide enough information to support or refute the claim made in the hypothesis. As a result, \\"neutral\\" should be returned as output."},{"source":"Given a text passage as input consisting of dialogues of negotiations between a seller and a buyer about the sale of an item, the task is to classify the text into one of the labels from the two possible outputs - 'accepted'/'rejected'. Select [accepted] if by the end of the conversation the buyer seems likely to buy the item from the seller. A sale is likely made when the buyer and seller agree upon a common price or when a deal is made between them. Select [rejected] if the buyer did not seem interested in buying the item from the seller at the end of the conversation. This happens when the buyer and seller do not agree on the price or other aspects of the item being sold by the seller.\\n\\nBuyer: Hi are these still available?\\nSeller: yes they are ,Would you be willing to give me $80 for the 2 tables that's only $40 each\\nBuyer: Well you've listed the item as 50 how come you're asking for 80?\\nSeller: oh sorry, I have multiple items listed I got this one confused you are correct, I am asking $50 for the 2 tables\\nBuyer: No worries. I still think its too much for it. Is there any room for negotiation?\\nSeller: Yes I am willing to negotiaate\\nBuyer: can you accept 25 for them and I am willing to come pick it up myself today itself and pay you right away?\\nSeller: How about we go middle ground , how does $35 sound? and I can help you load them in your vehicle.\\nBuyer: is this new or used?\\nSeller: They are used but in like new conditon\\nBuyer: how does 30 sound? Please? Pretty please?\\nSeller: I really can't go to low due to it being 2 tables and being in like new conditon, it is almost like getting 2 new tables I promise.\\nBuyer: Okay then 35 will do!\\nSeller: awesome it's a deal. \\nSeller: \\nBuyer:","target":"accepted","rationale":"The buyer and seller agree on a price of 35 dollars at the end of the conversation. Hence, this seems like a deal was made between them and hence, the answer is accepted.\\""},{"source":"If \\"A girl is brushing her teeth next to an infant on a white couch.\\", does this mean that \\"The girl is learning to brush her teeth.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"it is not possible to tell","rationale":"There is not enough information to determine whether the girl who is brushing her teeth next to an infant on a white couch has learnt this skill or if she needs help. Hence, it is not possible to tell."},{"source":"GM established grounds for suspicion of industrial spying by presenting affidavits from its employees. The aim will be to determine if VW's project was copied from GM data - essential if industrial espionage is to be proved.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nQuestion: Can we infer the following?\\nThere was an industrial espionage case involving GM and VW.","target":"yes","rationale":"The passage contains information that suggests industrial spying and a trial to determine if GM data was copied by VW. This supports the statement \\"There was an industrial espionage case involving GM and VW\\". Hence, the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestions: The man finished mowing his lawn and enjoyed a glass of lemonade on his porch, he took a sip and told himself that life was what?\\nOptions:\\n- good\\n- ending soon\\n- fleeting\\n- finite\\n- important","target":"good","rationale":"The context of the question indicates that after finishing a task, the man is sitting on his porch enjoying lemonade. This suggests that he has finished an activity and is now resting in order to relax.\\nGiven this information, it can be inferred that he would feel positive about life rather than feeling as if his life was ending soon or fleeting (short-lived). Based on these facts, \\"good\\" makes most sense given the situation described by the question."},{"source":"Here's a logic test: Eddy and Norma are running.  They are running at the same speed, but Eddy started running before Norma.  If they stop at the same time, who will have run farther?  (A) Eddy (B) Norma\\n\\nChoose the answer between \\"Eddy\\" and \\"Norma\\".","target":"Eddy","rationale":"Eddy will have run farther because he started running earlier and stopped at the same time as Norma."},{"source":"What is creativity?\\nHow de we define creativity?\\nWhere does creativity come from?\\nHow philosophical is the notion of creativity?\\nIs everyone‚Äôs ‚Äòcreativity‚Äô different?\\nOr is it an ill conceived, simplified term that is used to describe a very specific series of neuronal & bodily reactions to certain stimuli?\\nThese are all the questions I‚Äôve been thinking (and googling, and youtubing) since beginning this Capturing Creativity studio* and I have found some answers or maybe I‚Äôve just found more questions:\\nCreativity is generally defined as the ability to make new things, or come up with new ideas, it‚Äôs an ability to think outside the box, to see unique solutions and employ them in inventive ways. In this sense creativity is not always utilised when being ‚Äòcreative‚Äô, as to be creative is simply defined as the ability to make or produce something. However I guess that depends on your definition of creative, how different, unique, special, once off, un-influenced does something have to be, to be classified as creative?\\nThis is where creativity get‚Äôs tricky.\\nIt‚Äôs all well and good to be like oh this is what creativity is, so it‚Äôs easy to investigate it, but what if you don‚Äôt define that as being creative, maybe that was just following a formula, a somewhat inspired formula, but maybe it is just a formula. Creativity to most people seems to be a random mix of once off genius combined with solid skill and hard work and for us humans these percentages are unique to us.\\nMaybe creativity to you is 90% unique idea, 5% skill and 5% hard work.\\nMaybe creativity to you is 40% unique idea, 50% skill and 10% hard work.\\nMaybe for you creativity doesn‚Äôt have to involve any hard work at all.\\nFor me when it comes to creativity I‚Äôm most interested in that unique idea portion; where does that unique idea come from?\\nIs it simply random?\\nIs it a gift from the gods?\\nIs our unique idea just a product of a lot of subconscious effort, only made aware to us in the sense of a ‚Äòrandom‚Äô idea?\\nHave we been influenced by something, processed it...\\nAfter the end of the text, the author probably believes\\n\\nA. That the source of a unique idea cannot always be identified\\n\\nB. That most people are not creative\\n\\nC. not enough information\\n\\nD. That most people are creative","target":"A","rationale":"After the end of this text, based on the author's style and questions posed in the last few sentences (i.e., \\"Is it simply random? Is it a gift from the gods?\\"), we can infer that they are asking these questions to try to understand where unique ideas come from before concluding that creativity is inherently difficult for humans to identify or label because everyone has their own idea of what makes something creative.\\nIn conclusion, most likely answer would be A: That the source of a unique idea cannot always be identified."},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Does an engineered cryptic Hxt11 sugar transporter facilitate glucose-xylose co-consumption in Saccharomyces cerevisiae?\\nAnswer: Hxt11 is a cryptic sugar transporter of S. cerevisiae that previously has not been associated with effective d-xylose transport. Mutagenesis of Hxt11 yielded transporters that show a better affinity for d-xylose as compared to d-glucose while maintaining high transport rates. d-glucose and d-xylose co-consumption is due to a redistribution of the sugar transport flux while maintaining the total sugar conversion rate into ethanol. This method provides a single transporter solution for effective fermentation on lignocellulosic feedstocks.","target":"yes","rationale":"The question asks whether an engineered cryptic Hxt11 sugar transporter facilitates glucose-xylose co-consumption in Saccharomyces cerevisiae. The answer states that mutagenesis of Hxt11 yielded transporters that show a better affinity for d-xylose as compared to d-glucose while maintaining high transport rates and that the method provides a single transporter solution for effective fermentation on lignocellulosic feedstocks. Therefore, the answer answers the question and the output is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Question: Dancing poorly in public may make you feel what?\\nOptions:\\n- exhaustion\\n- recognizance\\n- blisters\\n- humiliation\\n- fatigue\\n\\nThe answer is \\"humiliation\\" because","target":"making a fool of yourself can humiliate you","rationale":"The rationale is \\"making a fool of yourself can humiliate you\\"."},{"source":"Passage: Joyce Summers -- The premise of the series is that Buffy is the latest Slayer, a young woman endowed by mystical forces with superhuman powers to fight and defeat vampires, demons, and other evil forces in the fictional town of Sunnydale. Like every Slayer before her, she was chosen and informed of her destiny when she was 15 years old. Her mother is unaware of her daughter's powers and responsibilities until Buffy is forced to tell her at the end of the second season of the television series. Although Joyce is shocked at this revelation, she recovers quickly and remains a source of stability for Buffy and Buffy's small circle of friends who assist her, dubbed the Scooby Gang. Eventually Joyce is able to take Buffy's dangerous demon-fighting in stride and even become proud and respectful of her daughter's abilities. Her natural death from an illness in the fifth season forces Buffy to face becoming an adult.\\n\\nAfter reading this passage, I have a question: does buffy's mom know she's a slayer? True or False?","target":"True","rationale":"The context states Joyce Summers is Buffy's mother, and that she learns about her daughter being a Slayer at the end of Season 2. This means that during Season 1 to early in Season 2, Mrs. Summers did not know Buffy was a Slayer (False). However, by the end of season two (and therefore \\"eventually\\" as stated), it can be concluded that there is no longer any doubt left: Ms. Summer knows what her daughter does for living - fighting demons - hence True"},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: What was the last name of the person who was included in the KOR intelligentsia? ?\\n\\nOn August 16, delegations from other strike committees arrived at the shipyard. Delegates (Bogdan Lis, Andrzej Gwiazda and others) together with shipyard strikers agreed to create an Inter-Enterprise Strike Committee (Miƒôdzyzak≈Çadowy Komitet Strajkowy, or MKS). On August 17 a priest, Henryk Jankowski, performed a mass outside the shipyard's gate, at which 21 demands of the MKS were put forward. The list went beyond purely local matters, beginning with a demand for new, independent trade unions and going on to call for a relaxation of the censorship, a right to strike, new rights for the Church, the freeing of political prisoners, and improvements in the national health service.Next day, a delegation of KOR intelligentsia, including Tadeusz Mazowiecki, arrived to offer their assistance with negotiations. A bibu≈Ça news-sheet, Solidarno≈õƒá, produced on the shipyard's printing press with KOR assistance, reached a daily print run of 30,000 copies. Meanwhile, Jacek Kaczmarski's protest song, Mury (Walls), gained popularity with the workers.On August 18, the Szczecin Shipyard joined the strike, under the leadership of Marian Jurczyk. A tidal wave of strikes swept the coast, closing ports and bringing the economy to a halt. With KOR assistance and support from many intellectuals, workers occupying factories, mines and shipyards across Poland joined forces. Within days, over 200 factories and enterprises had joined the strike committee. By August 21, most of Poland was affected by the strikes, from coastal shipyards to the mines of the Upper Silesian Industrial Area (in Upper Silesia, the city of Jastrzƒôbie-Zdr√≥j became center of the strikes, with a separate committee organized there, see Jastrzƒôbie-Zdr√≥j 1980 strikes). More and more new unions were formed, and joined the federation.","target":"Mazowiecki","rationale":"The article mentions that a delegation of KOR intelligentsia, including Tadeusz Mazowiecki, arrived to offer their assistance with negotiations. Given this context, the answer is likely to be one which matches Mazowiecki's last name i.e., it would probably have 9 letters starting with an M and ending in 'ki'.\\nSo based on the given context, \\"Mazowiecki\\" seems like a plausible answer for the question: What was the last name of the person who was included in the KOR intelligentsia?"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: None \\n Sentence: Ashley is best friends with Susana. \\n Character: Susana","target":"happy","rationale":"Susana is happy to be best friends with Ashley."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: The leaders of Russia and China vowed to support each other's fight against Muslim separatists and urged peaceful solutions in Iraq, during a meeting in Beijing's Great Hall of the People on December 2, 2002.\\nRussian President Vladimir Put in and China's Jiang Zemin signed a joint declaration calling for a \\"multipolar world\\".\\nHis two - day visit comes shortly after the conclusion of the 16th Patry Cogress which elected the new CPC leadership. Put in said that Russia wants to \\"work hard\\" with the new generation of Chinese leaders.\\nThe Treaty of Good =\\" Neighbourliness\\" and Friendly Cooperation, signed in July last year, has provided a solid legal foundation for lasting friendship for generations to come, according to Jiang, \\"China and Russia will be good neighbours, friends and partners forever.\\"\\nThe Russian Government, in return, said it would continue to give priority to relations with China in its foreign policies.\\nPut in spoke on the morning of Dec. 3rd at Peking University and took questions from students on his understanding of Chinese literature, Russian reform and NATO enlargement.\\nHe said a growing number of young people in Russia are interested in Chinese literature and one of his daughters is learning Chinese.\\nQuestion: Which of the following is mentioned in the passage?\\nOptions: A: Put in agreed that NATO was enlarged.\\nB: Put in was invited to the 16th Chinese communist Party congress.\\nC: Russia puts China first.\\nD: Muslim separatists make trouble only in Russia.","target":"C","rationale":"The passage states that the \\"Russian Government, in return, said it would continue to give priority to relations with China in its foreign policies.\\" This means that Russia puts China first.\\nSo C is correct"},{"source":"A scientist has just returned to the lab after working out in the field. While in the field, she collected two flowers to examine in detail. She puts the first flower, flower X, under a microscope and begins to look at it. After examination she determines it's an anemophilous plant. She then takes flower Y and repeats the same process to determine that it's an entomophilous type of plant.\\n\\nWhich plant's pollen is heavier?\\n\\nHint: Anemophilous pollen grains are light and non-sticky, so that they can be transported by air currents. They are typically 20‚Äì60 micrometres (0.0008‚Äì0.0024 in) in diameter, although the pollen grains of Pinus species can be much larger and much less dense. Anemophilous plants possess well-exposed stamens so that the pollens are exposed to wind currents and also have large and feathery stigma to easily trap airborne pollen grains. Pollen from anemophilous plants tends to be smaller and lighter than pollen from entomophilous ones, with very low nutritional value to insects. However, insects sometimes gather pollen from staminate anemophilous flowers at times when higher-protein pollens from entomophilous flowers are scarce. Anemophilous pollens may also be inadvertently captured by bees' electrostatic field. This may explain why, though bees are not observed to visit ragweed flowers, its pollen is often found in honey made during the ragweed floral bloom. Other flowers that are generally anemophilous are observed to be actively worked by bees, with solitary bees often visiting grass flowers, and the larger honeybees and bumblebees frequently gathering pollen from corn tassels and other grains.","target":"flower Y","rationale":"Anemophilous pollen grains are light and non-sticky, so that they can be transported by air currents. They are typically 20‚Äì60 micrometres (0.0008‚Äì0.0024 in) in diameter, although the pollen grains of Pinus species can be much larger and much less dense. Anemophilous plants possess well-exposed stamens so that the pollens are exposed to wind currents and also have large and feathery stigma to easily trap airborne pollen grains\\n\\nSo flower X is anemophilous plant which has lighter weight than entomophilus one . Hence , we choose \\"flower Y\\" as our answer for heavier weight"},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Daniel went to the kitchen. Sandra went to the kitchen. Question: Where is Sandra?","target":"kitchen","rationale":"The latest sentence in the passage states \\"Sandra went to the kitchen.\\""},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: In what state does Jerry Beck travel to when he is tracking down Reverend Gebhardt? from the following article ?\\n\\nOn Christmas Eve in Los Angeles, a dispatched LASD Sheriff is shot dead by an armed robber, who early on robbed a convenience store and also killed its African-American owner. The alcoholic, hard-driven LAPD Detective Jerry Beck is tasked with the investigation. While examining police records he comes across a potential suspect named Bobby Burns, who has recently been paroled from a four-year robbery sentence. He and a parole officer go to Burns' home only to find his college student brother, John, who claims he has not seen Bobby and is staying only for the holidays. A man attempts to flee the house and Beck captures him after a chase on foot; he turns out to be one of Burns' friend who is also on parole for armed robbery. The man tells Beck that he last saw Burns driving a maroon Ford Ranch Wagon en route to Bakersfield.\\nIn Arizona, Burns and his goons rob a Mexican bar and kill its patrons. A local police chief informs Beck of the crime and he immediately leaves for Arizona. Beck and the chief head to a ranch alleged to be Burns' hideout. There, Burns and his men attack the officers by firing automatic weapons; they escape driving the Ford. Beck retrieves a cache of documents Burns dropped, which contains white supremacy propaganda, maps, and an address book. Beck leaves for Oklahoma to track down one of the people listed in the book, Reverend Gebhardt, who is the leader of the religious white supremacist organization Aryan Nations. In Oklahoma, Beck is joined by FBI Agent Kressler and they head to Gebhardt's church, where Gebhardt states the entity's aim to cleanse America of its \\"racial impurities,\\" and denies having seen Burns before. Burns, though, has been hiding near the church and casing the place.","target":"Oklahoma","rationale":"The article states that Detective Beck heads to Oklahoma in order to track down Reverend Gebhardt, so the answer is \\"Oklahoma.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Travel Plans. Sentence 1: I had a two week vacation off from school. Sentence 2: I asked a friend to travel with me. Sentence 3: My friend was not available the same weeks. Sentence 4: I decided to ask a different friend who had the same vacation as me. Choices: a. John said he would take the new job. b. We made travel plans together.","target":"a","rationale":"The story is about travel plans. John's decision to take a new job has nothing to do with the rest of the story."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of strings and you need to concatenate them.\\n\\n['mutiny', 'h', 'the', 'O', 'C']","target":"mutinyhtheOC","rationale":"The strings in the given list are 'mutiny', 'h', 'the', and 'O'. We need to concatenate them, that is, combine them into one string. Therefore the final output will be \\"mutinyhtheOC\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a sentence and question. Based on the information provided in a given sentence, you should identify the shortest continuous text span from the sentence that serves as an answer to the given question. Answer the question using coreference resolution. Coreference resolution is the task of clustering mentions in text that refer to the same underlying real world entities. For example let's take a sentence 'I voted for Obama because he was most aligned with my values, she said.' Here in this example 'I', 'my', and 'she' belong to the same cluster and 'Obama' and 'he' belong to the same cluster. Now let's discuss another example , original sentence: 'I voted for Trump because he was most aligned with my values',John said. Now here is the same sentence with resolved coreferences: 'John voted for Trump because Trump was most aligned with John's values',John said. \\n\\nSentence: Everyone really loved the oatmeal cookies; only a few people liked the snickerdoodle cookies. Next time, we should make more of them. Question: Which cookie should we make more of, next time?","target":"oatmeal","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"oatmeal cookies\\", as the sentence explicitly states that \\"Everyone\\" loved them, and it should be made more of next time."},{"source":"Based on the context and the answer, generate a question. \\n\\nContext: Once I regained the same wheezing , gasping tune . I turned the water off and ran downstairs to the kitchen trying to get water . I expected to hit the floor face first , and wake up in a hospital bed . I try to explain to my parents what happend , watching me crying and gasping . Instead of finding concern in their faces , I found anger .\\n\\nAnswer:\\n\\nScold their child","target":"What might the parents do afterwards ?","rationale":"Based on the context, \\"I find anger in their faces\\", and answer of parents scolding their child.\\nThe question might be 'What might the parents do afterwards ?'"},{"source":"Tosca Musk is an American filmmaker. She is a producer and director of feature films, television programs and web content. Her web series, \\"Tiki Bar TV\\", and Hallmark television movie, \\"Holiday Engagement\\" have garnered some attention, with \\"Holiday Engagement\\" setting records for the most-watched television movie on Hallmark. She is the sister of entrepreneurs Elon and Kimbal Musk.\\n\\nChoose your answer: based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"Elon told her to become a filmmaker\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nI think the answer is","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"The context does not provide enough information to answer the question. We do know that she is Elon Musk's sister, but we don't have any indication of how much contact they've had or what their relationship was like in her childhood and teenage years when it would be more likely for him to influence career choices. So the only way we can answer this question is with \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Sandra journeyed to the hallway. Fact 2- Daniel travelled to the hallway. Fact 3- John travelled to the hallway. Fact 4- Sandra went to the bedroom. Fact 5- John travelled to the office. Fact 6- Sandra went to the kitchen. Fact 7- Mary moved to the office. Fact 8- Daniel moved to the office. Question: Where is Sandra? Answer: kitchen","target":"Fact 6","rationale":"Fact 6 states that Sandra went to the kitchen. Therefore, Fact 6 is necessary to answer the question."},{"source":"Question: Harold learned in school that Uranus has a greater mass then Mercury. This means that which planet emits stronger gravity? (A) Uranus (B) Mercury\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"Uranus\\" and  \\"Mercury\\".","target":"Uranus","rationale":"The statement \\"Harold learned in school that Uranus has a greater mass then Mercury\\" is true. The planet with the largest mass emits stronger gravity, so the answer is Uranus."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the vouch-fair strategy, otherwise output No. vouch-fair is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used to call out fairness for personal benefit, either when acknowledging a fair deal or when the opponent offers a deal that benefits them. This can be through an explicit call out or can be implied.\\n\\nContext: 'Thanks for your understanding well I think if possible then to meet the situation then how bout 3 food and 2 water then you get all the wood ? That way you can have awesome campfires lasting through the night, we will be going to sleep extra early to wake up very early so we do not need all that wood, as much as we need food to replenish our energy and be ready for another day of long walks to see as much as we can from nature üôÇ' 'I agree with you that campfires are awesome and I do find them to be be quite useful. I'm not as early of a riser as you are unfortunately! üôÇ I'm willing to accept your offer on food as long as you could please consider my needs for water. I am a very active hiker. While I don't need much food for my hikes I do require a lot of water. I once went on a hiking trip when I was new to the activity and ran out of water. I got lost and almost dehydrated! Ever since then it's been very important to me to have as much water as possible. What would it take in order for me to get as much water as possible keeping in mind that I'm willing to give you 3 food. ' 'Thank you for the food and I understand we do have to think about water being by far the most important thing in life since it bascially is right üôÇ and well how about then we go do two waters for you and one wood then so then we can have that wood for just in case and we can all be happy ?? thanks for your understanding'\\nUtterance: 'Yes. Water is the most important thing in life. Thank you for offering me two waters and one wood. However, this would mean that you would be receiving 3 food, 1 water, and 2 wood. That seems too unbalanced to me. It's important for me to also let you know that wood is very crucial for me. When I was a newbie I didn't bring any wood because I figured I'm fine since I'm not scared of the dark. That night a bear snuck on me when I was sleeping. Thankfully I was able to scare it away with noise. However, ever since then I've brought a lot of wood with me so no bears can sneak up on me. I would like to counter your offer with 3 waters, 2 wood, and 0 food. This means you get 1 wood and 3 food. Does this offer work for you?'","target":"Yes","rationale":"The speaker acknowledges the importance of water, and then makes a counteroffer that is more even in terms of each participant's needs. The speaker's counteroffer also refers to past personal experiences that have made wood a crucial item for them. Therefore, the answer is Yes."},{"source":"where is the national open university of nigeria located??","target":"Jabi, Abuja","rationale":"The National Open University of Nigeria is located in Jabi, Abuja.\\nThis information can be verified from multiple web pages such as the official website (https://nou.edu.ng/) and other third party sites that are dedicated to sharing information about academic institutions in Africa."},{"source":"In reaction to the ongoing uncertainty, the E.U. enlargement commissioner warned the Turkish Army about interfering: \\"It is important that the military leaves the remit of democracy to the democratically-elected government and this is the test case if the Turkish armed forces respect democratic secularism and the democratic arrangement of civil-military relations,\\" commissioner Olli Rehn said. Erdogan and G√ºl support Turkey's efforts to join the European Union.\\n\\nQuestion with options: Based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"Turks want G√ºl to be President.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The paragraph talks about the Turkish military and its interference in political decisions. It doesn't mention anything regarding G√ºl's presidency or whether Turks want him to be President. Therefore, we cannot conclude that \\"Turks want G√ºl to be President\\". So, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Suggest a movie title for the following movie plot: Empire Records is an independent record shop managed by Joe (Anthony LaPaglia). The store is located in a fictional city in Delaware, and, like its employees, is eclectic and unique. The staff is very much a surrogate family, with Joe as the reluctant and perpetually exasperated but loveable father figure. When his young staff experience problems in their personal lives, he routinely reminds them they can seek him out for advice.\\nThe film opens with store manager Joe allowing employee Lucas (Rory Cochrane) his first opportunity to close the store, an opportunity Lucas regards as an honour. While counting the day's receipts in Joe's office, Lucas snoops and discovers that Empire Records is about to be bought and converted into a branch of Music Town, a large national music store with many franchises. In an effort to keep the store independent, Lucas takes the day's cash receipts totaling $9,000 to a casino in Atlantic City in an attempt to quadruple it via gambling. Lucas believes this act will create enough money to allow Joe to save Empire Records. Though initially doubling the money, Lucas soon loses the entire amount in one bet on a dice table. Instead of going home he sleeps on his motorcycle outside the store, where he is found the following morning by opening manager A.J. (Johnny Whitworth) and fellow employee Mark (Ethan Embry). He confides in the pair about the previous night's events before riding away, seemingly for good. Joe arrives to help open the store and quickly receives phone calls from both the bank and the store owner, Mitchell Beck (Ben Bod√É¬©), regarding the previous night's missing deposit.\\nJoe is distracted from immediately dealing with this crisis due to a scheduled store event: Rex Manning (Maxwell Caulfield), a former 80's pop idol, is due to arrive at the store for an autograph session to promote his new album. The staff is unenthused by \\"Rex Manning Day\\", and ultimately many of the fans showing up to meet him are either older women or gay men. The employees secretly tease Rex behind...","target":"Empire Records","rationale":"The rationale to choose \\"Empire Records\\" as the answer is that:\\nIt's one of the movie titles for this plot."},{"source":"Context: In 1970, seagoing pilots became retrospectively insurable, and gained full social security as members of the Non-Manual Workers Insurance Institute. That same year, a special regulation came into force for District Master Chimney Sweeps, making them fully insurable under the Craftsmans Insurance Scheme. An increase was made in tax-free allowances for children, which enabled 1,000,000 families to claim an allowance for the second child, compared to 300,000 families previously. The Second Modification and Supplementation Law (1970) increased the allowance for the third child from DM 50 to DM 60, raised the income-limit for the second child allowance from DM 7,800 to DM 13,200; subsequently increased to DM 15,000 by the third modification law (December 1971), DM 16,800 by the fourth modification law (November 1973), and to DM 18,360 by the fifth modification law (December 1973). A flexible retirement age after 62 years was introduced (1972) for invalids and handicapped persons, and social assistance was extended to those who previously had to be helped by their relatives. From 1971, special subventions were provided to enable young farmers to quit farming ‚Äúand facilitate their entry into the non-agricultural pension system by means of back payments.‚Äù\\n\\nQuestion: How many DM did the Second Modification and Supplementation Law (1970) increase the third child by?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"10","rationale":"The Second Modification and Supplementation Law (1970) increased the third child allowance from DM 50 to DM 60. Therefore, it could be concluded that this law had increased 10 more than before."},{"source":"What brand of guitar does steve vai play?","target":"Ibanez Universe","rationale":"Steve Vai plays Ibanez Universe guitars."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i and A, where i is an integer and A is a list. You need to output the first i elements of A, starting with the 1st element in A. i will always have a value less than the length of A\\n\\n1, ['i', 'B', 'f', '8417', 'i', '1797', 'r', '3891', '9861', 'J', 'G', 'g', 'P', 'M', '1159']","target":"i","rationale":"Given the list ['i', 'B', 'f', '8417', 'i', '1797', 'r', '3891', 9861, J, G, g, P, M] as input, we need to find the first element:\\\\n1. The 1st element is i\\\\n\\\\nThe final output would be i"},{"source":"Given a comment text in Malayalam, classify the comment into one of these categories (i) Hope speech, (ii) Not Hope Speech or (iii) Not in Expected Language. A hope speech contains content that is encouraging, positive or supportive contents and talks about equality, diversity or inclusion\\n\\nTcr bro....mmade gadikal angana.....n#Cultural_capital #thrissur","target":"Not Hope Speech","rationale":"The comment does not contain any encouraging, positive or supportive contents. So it is classified as Not Hope Speech."},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nFigure 6.6 Water behind a dam has potential energy. Moving water, such as in a waterfall or a rapidly flowing river, has kinetic energy. (credit ‚Äúdam‚Äù: modification of work by \\"Pascal\\"/Flickr; credit ‚Äúwaterfall‚Äù: modification of work by Frank Gualtieri).\\n\\n\\nQ: Water behind a dam has potential energy. moving water, such as in a waterfall or a rapidly flowing river, has this?\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- residual energy\\n\\n- thermal energy\\n\\n- compression energy\\n\\n- kinetic energy\\n\\nA:","target":"kinetic energy","rationale":"The paragraph describes how water behind a dam, which is still and stationary, has potential energy. Water that is moving in currents, such as in rivers or waterfalls, have kinetic energy because they are constantly moving. So the answer is kinetic energy."},{"source":"If \\"Emma's mother had died long ago, and her place had been taken by an excellent woman as governess.\\", can we conclude that \\"Emma's place had been taken by an excellent woman as governess.\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes\\nI think the answer is","target":"no","rationale":"The statement \\"Emma's place had been taken by an excellent woman as governess\\" does not accurately reflect the situation described in the second sentence. In this context, Emma is referring to her mother, who has long passed away and cannot have a present or future replacement for her role as Emma's mother. So, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"John and Anna bought some eBook readers. John bought 15 eBook readers less than Anna did. Unfortunately, John lost 3 eBook readers. If Anna bought 50 eBook readers, how many eBook readers do they have altogether?","target":"82","rationale":"John bought 50 - 15 = 35 eBook readers. John has 35 - 3 = 32 eBook readers after losing some. Together they have 50 + 32 = 82 eBook readers."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a conversation between a flight agent and the customer. You are given 4 options and you need to select the goal of the conversation. It is provided as part of customer's context, which has to be one of the following: \`book\`: Make a new reservation, \`cancel\`: Cancel an existing reservation, \`no_flight\`: No flight found for the customer's preference, \`no_reservation\`: No reservation / No change / No cancellation was made in the conversation, mostly enquiring details\\n\\ncustomer: Hi. \\n agent: Hello. \\n customer: I am Kathleen Phillips here. \\n agent: How may I assist you? \\n customer: I want to reserve my ticket from CLT to MSP, can you please help me in this? \\n agent: Sure, I will help you out with that. May I know your travel dates to proceed further? \\n customer: Ok, my preferable dates of journey are from 09/07 to 09/09. \\n agent: Ok, please be on hold. \\n customer: Sure, I will wait. \\n agent: There is connecting flight from Hawaiian airlines with a fare of 100, shall I proceed with booking? \\n customer: Ok, please go ahead with this ticket booking. \\n agent: Ok, your ticket is confirmed with the flight-1024. \\n customer: Thank you for your help in booking my ticket. \\n agent: Thank you reaching us.","target":"book","rationale":"The given conversation is between the flight agent and the customer. The customer asks for assistance in reserving a ticket from CLT to MSP, so the choice among four options which was selected is \`book\`. Because in this conversation, we can see that at last, their ticket is confirmed with the flight-1024. So, it proves that they booked a ticket."},{"source":"Question: \\"How many years were people stuck in Alaska?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"The specifics of Paleo-Indian migration to and throughout the Americas, including the exact dates and routes traveled, provide the subject of ongoing research and discussion. According to archaeological and genetic evidence, North and South America were the last continents in the world with human habitation. During the Wisconsin glaciation, 50‚Äì17,000 years ago, falling sea levels allowed people to move across the land bridge of Beringia that joined Siberia to north west North America (Alaska). Alaska was a glacial refugia because it had low snowfall, allowing a small population to exist. The Laurentide Ice Sheet covered most of North America, blocking nomadic inhabitants and confining them to Alaska (East Beringia) for thousands of years.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"thousands","rationale":"The answer is thousands. \\nAccording to the context, people were stuck in Alaska because of a glacier that covered most of North America and was blocking inhabitants from moving elsewhere for \\"thousands\\" of years."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given a debate topic, along with a sentence from the debate. You should classify the given sentence and choose the type of that sentence. Possible types are explained below.\\nPolicy: This refers to a sentence proposing a specific course of action to be taken. It typically contains modal verbs like \\"should\\" and \\"ought to\\". It cannot be directly proved with objective evidence, and a proper type of support is a logical reason from which the proposition can be inferred.\\nValue: This refers to a sentence containing value judgments without making specific claims about what should be done (If so, then it is a Policy sentence.). Because of the subjectivity of value judgments, it cannot be proved directly with objective evidence.\\nFact: This refers to an objective proposition expressing or dealing with facts or conditions as perceived without distortion by personal feelings, prejudices, or interpretations. A Fact sentence has a truth value that can be verified with objective evidence that may be available at the time the claim is made; predictions about future are considered unverifiable.\\nTestimony: This refers to an objective sentence about the author's personal state or experience. Evidence for Testimony is not publicly available in most cases.\\n\\ntopic: NON VOTING IN ELECTIONS MUST BE TAKEN SERIOUSLY\\nsentence: \\"This is the result of citizens in democracies not doing their sacred duty which may in turn result in bad governance.\\"","target":"Value","rationale":"The sentence claims that not voting in elections is a \\"sacred duty\\" and the failure to do so may result in bad governance. Since the sentence contains value judgments and reasons for those judgments, it should be classified as Value."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the abstract of a research paper. Your task is to generate a summary of this abstract. Your summary should not be very short, but it's better if it's not more than 30 words.\\n\\nWe study the problem of training machine learning models incrementally using active learning with access to imperfect or noisy oracles. We specifically consider the setting of batch active learning, in which multiple samples are selected as opposed to a single sample as in classical settings so as to reduce the training overhead. Our approach bridges between uniform randomness and score based importance sampling of clusters when selecting a batch of new samples. Experiments on\\n benchmark image classification datasets (MNIST, SVHN, and CIFAR10) shows improvement over existing active learning strategies. We introduce an extra denoising layer to deep networks to make active learning robust to label noises and show significant improvements.","target":"We address the active learning in batch setting with noisy oracles and use model uncertainty to encode the decision quality of active learning algorithm during acquisition","rationale":"Here's a brief summary:\\\\nWe address the active learning in batch setting with noisy oracles and use model uncertainty to encode the decision quality of active learning algorithm during acquisition."},{"source":"Exercise: read the text and answer the question by True or False.\\n\\nText: Carol Ann Susi -- Carol Ann Susi (February 2, 1952 -- November 11, 2014) was an American actress. She was known for providing the voice of recurring unseen character Mrs. Wolowitz, mother of Howard Wolowitz, on the television series The Big Bang Theory.\\nQuestion: did the actress who played mrs wolowitz die?","target":"True","rationale":"The text states that Carol Ann Susi, who provided the voice for Mrs. Wolowitz in The Big Bang Theory, died on November 11th 2014\\nSo the answer is True"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a short passage that conveys a stereotype or an anti-stereotype. A stereotype is an over-generalized belief about a particular group of people(based on race, ethnicity, gender, age, abilities, etc.). An anti-stereotype is an idea that goes against a common stereotype. You are expected to classify the passage into two classes: stereotype or anti-stereotype.\\n\\nPassage: Kassandra was such an airhead.","target":"Stereotype","rationale":"The phrase \\"such an airhead\\" is a commonly used stereotype of females. The use of this phrase in the passage implies that the speaker believes that Kassandra is unintelligent and frivolous, which is characteristic of this feminine stereotype. Therefore, the passage can be classified as a \\"Stereotype\\"."},{"source":"Fill in the response. DIALOG:\\nWhat happened in Nico Rosberg's early years of karting?\\n- Competing in the 100 Junior category in a CRG kart, Rosberg finished fifth at the 28¬∞ Torneo Industrie, seventh in the Trofeo Andrea Margutti, and crashed out in the 1998 Green Helmet Trophy Cadets class of the European Championship for Cadets.\\n- What are some of his successful races?\\n- In 1999, he was runner-up in the Italian Junior Karting Championship and was fourth in the CIK-FIA European Championship, again driving a CRG monocoque in the ICA Junior category.\\n- What other races did he win?\\n-","target":"Rosberg's father asked CRG executive Dino Chiesa in late 1999 to establish a separate karting team for his son and fellow driver Lewis Hamilton for a period of two to three years. Rosberg raced on behalf of the factory operation called TeamMBM.com (Mercedes-Benz McLaren) for the 2000 season.","rationale":"The answer is related to the previous question and shows that Rosberg's father asked CRG executive Dino Chiesa in late 1999 to establish a separate karting team for his son and fellow driver Lewis Hamilton for a period of two to three years. Rosberg raced on behalf of the factory operation called TeamMBM.com (Mercedes-Benz McLaren) for the 2000 season."},{"source":"In this task you will be given some text dialogue and you need to infer the underlying emotion of the text. The possible emotions are happy, sad, angry, or other.\\n\\noh sorry i message you by mistake sorry it's alright don't worry u dont want to talk abt my topics","target":"angry","rationale":"The dialogue is a conversation between two people, where the person says sorry twice, but the other person responds with \\"don't worry\\" and then \\"u dont want to talk abt my topics\\". This indicates that the person is angry because their topic of discussion was ignored by the other person."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nCan you please find a round-trip flight for me?","target":"Flights","rationale":"The sentence \\"Can you please find a round-trip flight for me?\\" is related to the Flights service."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and determine if the hypothesis is true. Select from options at the end:\\n\\nOnly a few Mag-lev trains have been used commercially such as at the Birmingham airport in the UK.\\n\\nHypothesis: Maglev is commercially used.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nThe answer is","target":"yes","rationale":"The train that is used at the Birmingham airport in UK can be considered a commercial use of Maglev. So, yes it is true!"},{"source":"The Kinston Indians are a minor league baseball team in Kinston, North Carolina. The team, a Class A affiliate of the Cleveland Indians, plays in the Carolina League.\\n\\nQuestion with options: Based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"Kinston Indians participate in the Carolina League.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The information given in the paragraph provides enough evidence to support that conclusion. So, the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a date in a particular format and you need to convert to another format. If given format is \\"dd/mm/yyyy\\" then convert to \\"mm/dd/yyyy\\". If given format is \\"mm/dd/yyyy\\" then convert to \\"dd/mm/yyyy\\".\\n\\n12/27/2014, input_format=mm/dd/yyyy","target":"27/12/2014","rationale":"Since there is no 27th month, the given format is \\"mm/dd/yyyy\\". We have to convert it to \\"dd/mm/yyyy\\", so the answer is \\"27/12/2014\\"."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"Loxahatchee is a community located in Palm Beach County , Florida , United States .\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Loxahatchee, Florida","rationale":"The topic of the passage is \\"Loxahatchee, Florida\\".\\nThis can be determined by finding out what this piece of text is specifically about. In this case it provides information on Loxahatchee which we learn: \\n- It's a community located in Palm Beach County, Florida and that it's from the United States."},{"source":"The Human Immunodeficiency Virus ( HIV ) is the virus that causes Acquired Immunodeficiency Syndrome ( AIDS ). Most researchers believe that the HIV originated in sub-Saharan Africa during the 20th century. HIV is transmitted by sexual contact and by contact with infected bodily fluids, such as blood, semen, breast milk, and vaginal secretions. It is also passed from mother to fetus. HIV is now a pandemic , with an estimated (as of 2008) 38.6 million people now living with the disease worldwide. It is estimated that AIDS has killed more than 25 million people since it was first recognized in 1981. For further information about HIV/AIDS, see the CDC (Centers for Disease Control and Prevention) web site at http://www.cdc.gov/hiv/resources/factsheets/ .\\n\\nDean and Paul both went to volunteered in Africa. They had a blood test when they came back. Paul had been infected with the HIV virus while Dean was healthy and clean.\\n\\nWhich friend doesn't have a virus that is transmitted by contact with infected semen?","target":"Dean","rationale":"The question asks which friend doesn't have a virus that is transmitted by contact with infected semen.\\nIn the text, it says \\"Most researchers believe that the HIV originated in sub-Saharan Africa during 20th century.\\" And also mentions: \\"HIV is now a pandemic, with an estimated (as of 2008) 38.6 million people now living with the disease worldwide.... It is estimated that AIDS has killed more than 25 million people since it was first recognized in 1981\\". This indicates how dangerous this type of infection can be and we are told about two friends who volunteered together but only one got infected so I would say he's Dean because Paul had been sick after both went back home for blood test as mentioned above."},{"source":"In this task you will be given an answer to a question. You need to generate a question. The answer given should be a correct answer for the generated question.\\n\\nAfter growing up in Oklahoma and serving in the United States Army, Miller began his musical career as a songwriter in the late 1950s, writing such hits as 'Billy Bayou' and 'Home' for Jim Reeves and 'Invitation to the Blues' for Ray Price. He later began a recording career and reached the peak of his fame in the mid-1960s, continuing to record and tour into the 1990s, charting his final top 20 country hit 'Old Friends' with Willie Nelson in 1982. He also wrote and performed several of the songs for the 1973 Disney animated film Robin Hood. Later in his life, he wrote the music and lyrics for the 1985 Tony-award winning Broadway musical Big River, in which he acted.","target":"who wrote the song invitation to the blues","rationale":"The answer given is Ray Price. The generated question should have Ray Price as the correct answer. A valid question with Ray Price as an answer is \\"who wrote the song invitation to the blues\\"."},{"source":"You are provided with an \\"Event\\", \\"Intent\\" and \\"XEmotion\\" (PersonX's reactions for the given \\"Event\\"). Indicate PersonY's reaction (person feels) at the end of this event. Provide one reaction for PersonY. If there's nothing that can be implied, respond as None\\n\\nEvent:PersonX swirls around PersonY. Intent:. XEmotion: 1) disappointed.","target":"happy","rationale":"PersonX's action of \\"swirling around PersonY\\" can denote a playful activity. This playful activity could make PersonY feel happy"},{"source":"Read the following article and answer the question.\\nArticle: Mr. Smith is telling two funny stories of his police work.\\nStory A\\nI remember catching a \\"thief\\" in a clothes shop once. It was strange. The man was hiding a yellow sweater inside his coat. I thought he had stolen it, so I caught him. We found later that his wife gave him the sweater for his birthday, but he hated it. He just wanted to return it to the shop for money, but he didn't want his wife to see him! We soon let him go.\\nStory B\\nAnother day, a man called Bob went into a bank on Sixth Street. He wrote on the back of an envelope, \\"Give me the money! Or I'll kill you.\\" and gave it to the bank clerk. She gave him $100,000 and the man ran away. Then we received a phone call from the bank clerk. She told us to go to the man's house in Candy Town and get him. We caught him as soon as he got out of the elevator. He couldn't believe that we found him so quickly. We told him that the front of the envelope he used his name and address on it!\\nQuestion: Mr. Smith caught the man in the clothes shop   _  .\\nAnswer:","target":"by mistake","rationale":"The context of story A is that Mr. Smith caught a man hiding a yellow sweater inside his coat in a clothes shop, and thought the man stole it so he held him there to wait for police officers. However, later they found out that the man did not steal it but wanted to return it because his wife gave him an ugly birthday gift which was this yellow sweeter.\\nSo the answer could be by mistake or accident here since we can't know if Mr.Smith really knew what happened before knowing everything about this situation clearly or not when he just saw someone hide something into their coats while shopping at first time without any other evidences like seeing them taking off some tags on these clothes or whatever else things might have proved customers had paid enough money for those goods already(although even with"},{"source":"In this task, you are given the name of an Indian food dish. You need to classify the dish as \\"sweet\\" or \\"spicy\\".\\n\\nBalu shahi","target":"sweet","rationale":"Balu shahi is a sweet dish made of flour and sugar."},{"source":"Coming off their divisional home win over the Bills, the Patriots flew to Sun Life Stadium for a Week 4 AFC East duel with the Miami Dolphins on Monday Night Football. The Dolphins marched to the Patriots 38 on the opening drive, but punted. After a Patriots three-and-out, the Dolphins marched 64 yards in 7 plays, scoring on a 19-yard touchdown pass from Chad Henne to Davone Bess on a 19-yard touchdown pass and a 7-0 lead. Four plays after the Patriots punted again, Ninkovich intercepted Henne at the Patriots 40. The Patriots drove all the way to the Dolphins 5, but settled for a 23-yard field goal by Gostkowski. The Dolphins drove to the Patriots 27 on their next drive, but Henne was intercepted again by Ninkovich at the 25. The Patriots drove all the way to the Dolphins 12, but again settled for a field goal, making the score 7-6 Dolphins at halftime. Tate returned the opening kickoff of the second half 103 yards for a touchdown, giving the Patriots the lead, 13-7 that they wouldn't relinquish. Chung blocked Brandon Fields' punt, with Brandon Spikes recovering at the Dolphins 15. Two plays later, the Patriots scored on a 12-yard touchdown run by Green-Ellis, increasing the lead to 20-7. The Dolphins answered on their next drive, marching 80 yards in 8 plays, scoring on a 28-yard screen pass to Ricky Williams, bringing the score to 20-14. The Patriots countered, driving 78 yards in 12 plays, scoring on an 11-yard screen pass to Woodhead, increasing the lead to 27-14. The Dolphins drove to the Patriots 29 on their next drive, but after a 7-yard sack by Ninkovich, attempted a 54-yard field goal, but the kick was blocked Chung with Kyle Arrington returning it 35 yards for a touchdown, increasing the lead to 34-14. The Dolphins reached their own 45 on their next drive, but Ronnie Brown was stuffed for no gain on 4th-and-2. After a Patriots three-and-out, the Dolphins drove to their own 47, but Chung intercepted Henne at the Patriots 49 and returned it 51 yards for a touchdown, increasing the lead to 41-14. The Dolphins drove to the Patriots 40 again on their next drive, but rookie Jarrad Page intercepted Henne at the Patriots 23. The Patriot ran out the rest of the clock to win the game. With the win, not only did the Patriots head into their bye week at 3-1, but Brady picked up his 100th win in the fewest career starts (131) in NFL history. New England became the first team in NFL history to have a rushing, passing, interception return, kickoff return, and blocked field goal return for a touchdown in the same game.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"Who scored more points, the Patriots or the Dolphins?","rationale":"Here's a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: Who scored more points, the Patriots or the Dolphins?"},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to classify the sentence into one of the following five action categories - INFORM, INFORM_INTENT, OFFER, REQUEST, REQUEST_ALTS. If the sentence is about informing something, generate 'INFORM'. If it is about requesting something, generate 'REQUEST'. If the sentence mentions requesting an alternative option than the one provided, generate 'REQUEST_ALTS'. Similarly, generate 'OFFER' if the sentence is offering some information. If the sentence is about showing intent to do something, generate 'INFORM_INTENT'.\\n\\nWhat city do you want to attend the event in?","target":"REQUEST","rationale":"The sentence is asking for some information about the city, so it is classified as a 'REQUEST' action."},{"source":"Evangelical leaders are taking a step back from their decades-long fight against gay marriage, softening their tone and recalibrating their goals. In recent interviews with about a half-dozen prominent evangelicals, no one listed opposition to gay marriage as their top priority. The leaders said they're more focused on protecting religious liberties as same-sex marriage becomes legal in a growing number of states. \\"Is it time to differentiate between religious ceremony and civil ceremony?\\" Jim Daly, the president of Focus on the Family, said in an interview with CNN. \\"Civil ceremony to the Christian community is no different than getting your car registered.\\"\\n@highlight\\nEvangelical leaders aren't listing opposition to gay marriage as their top priority\\n@highlight\\nThey're instead more focused on protecting religious liberties\\n@highlight\\nGOP is largely ignoring the issue \\nOf course, there's still plenty of opposition to same-sex marriage among @placeholder. \\nCan you figure out what does the \\"@placeholder\\" mean? It means","target":"GOP","rationale":"The context is a CNN report on the changing stance of Evangelical leaders towards same-sex marriage. The author mentions that \\"there's still plenty of opposition to same-sex marriage among @placeholder\\". Given the discussion about the position of Christian community and their concerns around religious liberties, it can be inferred that \\"@placeholder\\" refers to members of this group i.e., Christians in general or evangelicals specifically.\\nAdding more evidence for our assumption, we see that immediately after mentioning @placeholder, there comes another mention: ‚ÄúOf course‚Äù which could imply something obvious/known by now; hence narrowing down further at whom these words are addressed ‚Äì anyone who has read thus far would know what was being talked about before this point in text ‚Äì hence referring to GOP (Republicans)"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and a question, you would be asked to create the answer which is contained in the sentence provided.\\n\\nSentence: When an atom gains or loses an electron it becames a(n) ion. Question: When an atom gains or loses an electron it becames an?","target":"ion","rationale":"After an atom gains or loses an electron, it becomes a charged ion."},{"source":"Premise: A young girl in a costume on the ground, with a hula hoop next to her.\\n\\nHypothesis: The girl is wearing a hospital gown.\\n\\n.Choose the correct answer: Given the premise, can we conclude the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The girl is wearing a costume, not a hospital gown."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{1, 2, 3, 10, 11, 12, 14}', Set2: '{2, 3, 9, 11, 12, 13}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"9","rationale":"The union of the given sets is {1,2,3,9,10,11,12}. It has nine elements."},{"source":"Is the premise \\"A woman with a shopping bag labeled \\"sale\\" stands in a crowd next to a young man with a camera.\\" true if \\"A woman bought her son a camera.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"it is not possible to tell","rationale":"The premise is not related to the hypothesis, so it is not possible to tell whether the statement given in the premise and true or false even though both statements are about a woman with a son."},{"source":"See the multi-choice question below:\\n\\nSentence 1: Mrs. Inglethorp was lying on the bed, her whole form agitated by violent convulsions, in one of which she must have overturned the table beside her. \\n\\nSentence 2: Mrs. Inglethorp was having a seizure. \\n\\nIf the first sentence is true, then is the second sentence true?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"When a person is having an epileptic seizure, she/he experiences violent convulsions. Thus the first sentence states that Mrs Inglethorp was experiencing violent convulsions and hence it can be inferred from the second sentence that she was indeed \\"having a seizure\\".\\n \\nPlease select your answer: yes"},{"source":"I had something that might have been a little supernatural.\\nSo I was trying to sleep one time, and I sleep under the blankets 99% of the time. I sleep downstairs, so hearing noise is pretty normal. Also, my door doesn‚Äôt lock, or even latch the door handle, so you can just push it open.\\nSo I was laying down, maybe at 60% in terms of how close I was to falling asleep, so I just had to lay down for like 5 more minutes.\\nBut there are a lot of noises, and they freak me out even though I just sorta pretend that they‚Äôre definitely a cat or my dog or something.\\nSo, I‚Äôm already slightly spooked, but I‚Äôm ignoring it and going to sleep anyway.\\nBut then, I hear my door open. That isn‚Äôt too weird, I do have cats, so even though by this point my fear is intense, I just sorta blow it off and keep trying to sleep.\\nAnd then, something that‚Äôs never happened in a situation like this, I feel something moving towards me on my bed.\\nIt feels like a cats movements, with light feet making slight reverberations on the bed.\\nSo my fear goes away entirely, and I‚Äôm like ‚ÄúOh okay, it‚Äôs just the cat, that‚Äôs good.‚Äù And I lift my blankets off my head to let my cat under with me, and because the fear seemed to make the atmosphere under there very hot and tense, and then I look at my bed and there‚Äôs nothing.\\nSo I just pretend nothing happened and go to sleep, but that still sticks with me and even though it‚Äôs kinda underwhelming I still think it was very strange since I wasn‚Äôt at the ‚Äúedge of consciousness‚Äù stage of going to sleep, so I feel like the chances I imagined it aren‚Äôt too high.\\nWhere does the author sleep at night?\\nPick the correct answer from the following options:\\n\\nA. A downstairs bedroom\\n\\nB. In bed\\n\\nC. not enough information\\n\\nD. Under the blankets","target":"A","rationale":"The author mentions that they sleep downstairs and have to ignore noises because their room is on the bottom floor of a house. This means that based on the given context, it can be inferred that the answer to this question is A - \\"a downstairs bedroom\\"."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to classify the sentence into one of the following five action categories - INFORM, INFORM_INTENT, OFFER, REQUEST, REQUEST_ALTS. If the sentence is about informing something, generate 'INFORM'. If it is about requesting something, generate 'REQUEST'. If the sentence mentions requesting an alternative option than the one provided, generate 'REQUEST_ALTS'. Similarly, generate 'OFFER' if the sentence is offering some information. If the sentence is about showing intent to do something, generate 'INFORM_INTENT'.\\n\\nTell me where is located and when is start.","target":"REQUEST","rationale":"In this scenario, the user is requesting information about a location and the time. Therefore, the most reasonable action category to which this sentence can be classified is 'REQUEST'."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the other-need strategy, otherwise output No. other-need is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used when the participants discuss a need for someone else rather than themselves. For instance, describing the need for firewood to keep the kids warm.\\n\\nContext: 'Hello. I am so looking forward to this camp out. My daughter just called and said she is going to come and bring some of her firiends. üôÇ'\\nUtterance: 'Hello! That sounds pretty reasonable to me. I was going out with a bunch of my buddies. We like to hike a lot in the sun, so we need lots of water. How does it sound if i take all the food and water, but you get all the firewood?'","target":"Yes","rationale":"The speaker says she is going out with buddies and likes to hike in the sun, therefore she needs lots of water. This is an example of the other-need strategy, as the speaker mentions a need for someone else rather than themselves. Therefore, the answer is Yes."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a text passage from a trivia quiz. You should choose the category this question belongs to from these categories: History, Science, Social Science, Fine Arts, Literature. You can only choose one category, so if in doubt, please choose the closest match.\\n\\nIts heaviest concentration of membership is in East Africa, followed by the United States, where early in their history Mary Dyer and four others were executed for their beliefs. One notable division occurred during the feud between John Wilbur and Joseph Gurney. The sect was formed during the English Civil War, when its founder proclaimed, \\"since there was that of God in every man,\\" a formal church structure and educated clergy were not necessary. Divided into Orthodox, Conservative, and Hicksite subgroups and emphasizing the \\"inner light\\", FTP, identify the Christian denomination founded by George Fox and spread in colonial America by William Penn, named for their tendency to \\"tremble\\" before God.","target":"Social Science","rationale":"This question is about the history of a group of religious people, which means it belongs in the Social Sciences category."},{"source":"Here's a short story: The boy threw the baseball in the rain and it didn't go far. He threw the sand baseball in the clear air and it went 20 ft longer distance. The rain air has (A) more resistance (B) less resistance.\\n\\nWhat is the most sensical answer between \\"rain\\" and  \\"clear air\\"?","target":"rain","rationale":"The story gives us a boy throwing two baseballs. The first ball went less distance than the second ball when thrown in different weather conditions (rain & clear air). We can infer that there is more resistance to movement for things traveling through rain as opposed to moving through clear air/no rain, so choice A makes sense here."},{"source":"(CNN) -- Referring to two American hikers in custody for more than two years, Iranian President Mahmoud Ahmadinejad told reporters Tuesday: \\"I am helping to arrange for the release in a couple of days so they will be able to return home.\\" The semi-official Mehr News Agency quickly echoed the president with a headline, \\"Iran's Judiciary agrees to release two U.S. citizens on bail.\\" Within 24 hours, however, the Shiite clerics who run Iran's legal system seemed to pour cold water on hopes of a quick release by declaring the \\"request to release two U.S. citizens on bail was under study.\\" They went on to warn the media and the United States that \\"only reports published by the judiciary could be trusted.\\"\\n@highlight\\nJamsheed K. Choksy: The uncertain status of two U.S. hikers reflects Iran divisions\\n@highlight\\nHe says President Mahoud Ahamadinejad is locked in struggle with mullahs\\n@highlight\\nIran's president is challenging the idea of Islamic theocracy, Choksy says \\nAhmadinejad, although rightly abhorred on the world stage for his bad words and deeds, is far from politically impotent and will likely continue to press an increasingly secularist vision of government upon the mullahs, knowing his new stances make him one of the three most popular politicians, none of them fundamentalists, within @placeholder. \\n\\nYou should decide what \\"@placeholder\\" is referring to. Choose between:\\n- American\\n- CNN\\n- Choksy\\n- Iran\\n- Iranian\\n- Islamic\\n- Jamsheed K. Choksy\\n- Judiciary\\n- Mahmoud Ahmadinejad\\n- Mahoud Ahamadinejad\\n- Mehr News Agency\\n- Shiite\\n- U.S.\\n- United States","target":"Iranian","rationale":"The context refers to the Iranian government and its internal struggles. In particular, it talks about President Mahoud Ahamadinejad's struggle with Shiite clerics in Iran's legal system who run Iran's legal system.\\n@highlight\\nMahmoud Ahmadinejad: Obama cannot be trusted \\nThe term \\"@placeholder\\" is used as a placeholder for any of the following terms \\"American\\", \\"CNN\\", \\"Choksy\\", \\"Iran\\",\\"Iranian\\",\\"Islamic\\",\\"Jamsheed K. Choksy\\",\\"Judiciary\\". Since these words are all nouns describing people or organizations involved in this story, the only other option that would make sense is also a noun which describes something related to them: namely, \\"[the] Iranian [government]\\" -- i.e., an"},{"source":"Where did wassily kandinsky work?","target":"University of Tartu","rationale":"Wassily Kandinsky was a Russian painter, the leading pioneer of abstract art. He worked at University of Tartu from 1892 to 1896."},{"source":"Passage: Fifty Shades (film series) -- The first film, Fifty Shades of Grey, was released on February 13, 2015, while the second, Fifty Shades Darker, was released on February 10, 2017. Fifty Shades Freed will be released on February 9, 2018. Worldwide, the series has grossed $952 million.\\n\\nAfter reading this passage, I have a question: is there a sequel to 50 shades of grey? True or False?","target":"True","rationale":"The passage includes the release dates and box office earnings of three films, Fifty Shades of Grey (2015), Fifty Shades Darker (2017) and Fifty Shades Freed(2018). If a fourth film was not going to be released, then there would only have been two movies in the series. Because there are three movies listed in this passage, it is clear that this movie has sequels.\\nSo, answer: True"},{"source":"Read the following article and answer the question.\\nArticle: Research shows that much of our predisposition   towards determination, sociability and self - control and sense of purpose is in our genes.In fact, our DNA plays a bigger role in influencing these traits ( characteristics)than our upbringing  and the company we keep.Taken together, these aspects of personality can make the difference between success and failure, say the Edinburgh University researchers.\\nThey questioned more than 800 pairs of twins about their attitudes to life to tease apart the influences of nature and nurture.Comparing identical twins, who share all their DNA and their up bringing, with non-identical twins, who have a shared background but are no more genetically alike than other brothers and sisters, is a technique often used by researchers to quantify the influence of genetics.\\nThe results, published in the Journal of Personality, showed that genes play a much bigger role than lifestyle, with self-control particularly etched   into our DNA.\\nOur genes a222so largely determine how determined and persistent we are.This is important in terms of success, as someone who refuses to give up is more likely to achieve their dreams than someone who _ \\nResearcher Professor Timothy Bates said, \\"Ever since the ancient Greeks, people Lave de hated the nature of a good life and the nature of a virtuous life.Why do some people seem to manage their lives, have good relationships and cooperate to achieve their goals while others do not? Previously,  the role of family and the environment around the home often controlled people' s ideas about what affected psychological well-being.However, this work emphasizes a much more powerful influence from genetics.\\"\\nHowever, those who haven' t been dealt a helpful hand of genes shouldn' t he too depressed.The professor says a sense of purpose is the key and advises those who are eager for success to focus their thoughts on making a difference.\\nQuestion: Timothy Bates mentions the ancient Creeks in order to indicate that  _  .\\nAnswer:","target":"the relationship between personality and success has always been people's concern","rationale":"Professor Timothy Bates says that since the ancient Greeks, people have debated what makes a good life and how personality affects success. This fact indicates that \\"the relationship between personality and success has always been people's concern\\", which is choice D on test results page."},{"source":"Passage: Martin Kaymer won his first major championship in a three-hole playoff over Bubba Watson. It was the second PGA Championship in six years at Whistling Straits, the first in 2004 was won by Vijay Singh, also in a playoff.\\n\\nQuestion: Based on this passage, pga championship in 2010. who won the title then?","target":"Martin Kaymer","rationale":"To answer the above question, the relevant sentence is: Martin Kaymer won his first major championship in a three-hole playoff over Bubba Watson."},{"source":"At night stars appear to move relative to the\\n\\nChoices:\\n- moon\\n- skyline\\n- treetops\\n- ocean","target":"skyline","rationale":"At night, the sky is dark and thus stars can be seen. The movement of these stars appears to move relative to the skyline during this time; hence the best answer should be \\"skyline\\"."},{"source":"Read the text and determine if the sentence is true (see options at the end):\\n\\nXingwana called on established farmers to form partnerships with new landowners and to transfer skills to new farmers, to ensure productive use of transferred lands. One criticism of the programme is that some of the transferred farms have fallen in production due to the inexperience and lack of capital among the new owners. The government has rejected comparisons of the programme with that initiated in Zimbabwe under President Robert Mugabe.\\n\\nSentence: President Robert Mugabe is of United States\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"We can see that the programme was not initiated in Zimbabwe under President Robert Mugabe. This is clearly mentioned in the text as \\"The government has rejected comparisons of the programme with that initiated in Zimbabwe under President Robert Mugabe\\". So, it's a No here."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5. Your job is to generate a title for the story that makes complete sense. The title must be short, with less than three words, use simple language, and include the main topic of the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: Liam and Owen came home from school full of energy on a rainy day. Sentence 2: Because of the rain, Liam and Owen had to stay inside until bedtime. Sentence 3: To exert some energy, Liam and Owen rode scooters around the house. Sentence 4: Once they were bored with scooters, they watched some television. Sentence 5: After dinner and bathing, Liam and Owen went to sleep.","target":"Liam & Owen's Afternoon","rationale":"The story is from the perspective of Liam and Owen spending time together at home, so a title like \\"Liam & Owen's Afternoon\\" makes sense."},{"source":"Mike has to learn more about the periodic table for his chemistry exam. To make things easier for him he chose two elements from the table, element A and element B. Element A has higher electronegativity and element B has lower eletronegativity. David found it easier to learn about elements by comparing their properties.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhere element B most likely be across the column, up or down?","target":"down","rationale":"The electronegativity of an element is the tendency to attract electrons towards itself. Electronegativities are mostly linear across a row, meaning that the higher up you go in a column, it's more likely for elements there to have greater electronegativity. So given this fact, Element B most likely be placed down from A as its lower eletronegativity implies that it has less attraction for electrons and thus should be further away from them (up)"},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write a question that asks about \\"event duration\\", based on a given sentence. The question will likely start with \\"How long\\". Your question should be answerable based on the common knowledge of how long certain events usually last. Don't create questions which have explicit mentions of answers in the text. Instead, it has to be implied from what is given. In other words, we want you to use \\"instinct\\" or \\"common sense\\". Note that the written questions are not required to have a single correct answer.\\n\\nSentence: The mother, looking on, learns of the ways of God with men.","target":"How long did the mother look on?","rationale":"The sentence states that the mother is looking on, which implies that she is observing or paying attention to something. Reading the rest of the sentence does not give any clues as to what she is observing, so we can infer that she was looking on for some time. Given this context, a natural question would be: \\"How long did the mother look on?\\"."},{"source":"Ben Nevis -- Ben Nevis (Scottish Gaelic: Beinn Nibheis, pronounced (peÀà…≤iv…ô É); English: /b…õnÀàn…õv…™s/) is the highest mountain in the British Isles, located in Scotland. Standing at 1,345 metres (4,411 ft) above sea level, it is located at the western end of the Grampian Mountains in the Lochaber area of the Scottish Highlands, close to the town of Fort William. \\n\\nHaving read that, I wonder is ben nevis the highest mountain in britain?","target":"Yes","rationale":"It's clearly Yes."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate objects to the associated rooms is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates object A to room B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate room for the given object C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ncar : driveway. table : ?","target":"kitchen","rationale":"The relation between a car and a driveway is that the car is typically parked in the driveway. The kitchen is where tables are commonly found, so it makes sense to put table in place of C."},{"source":"Context: After losing to the Seahawks on the road, the 49ers went home to take on the Rams.  In the first quarter the Rams scored first when Todd Gurley ran for a 3-yard touchdown to make it 7-0.  The Niners managed to tie it up when Brian Hoyer ran for a 9-yard touchdown to make it 7-7.  The Rams moved back into the lead when Jared Goff found Gurley on a 7-yard pass to make it 14-7.  In the second quarter, the Rams increased their lead when Greg Zuerlein kicked a 48-yard field goal to make it 17-7.  Though the Niners would come within 4 with 2 field goals of their own kicked by Robbie Gould:  from 36 and 48 yards out to make the score 17-10 and then 17-13.  Gurley then put the Rams up by double digits at halftime when he ran for a 2-yard touchdown to make it 24-13.  In the third quarter Zuerlein kicked a 19-yard field goal to make it 27-13 Rams.  The Niners then came within a touchdown when Carlos Hyde ran for one from a yard out.  Though the Rams would move up by 2 touchdowns again when Goff found Sammy Watkins on a 1-yard pass to make it 34-20.  In the fourth quarter, the Niners came within 8 when Garrett Celek caught a 1-yard pass from Hoyer (with a failed PAT) to make it 34-26.  Though again, the Rams moved up by double digits when Goff and Watkins connected again on a 13-yard pass to make it 41-26.  Finally, the Niners were able to come within two points with two more touchdowns:  Trent Taylor caught a pass from Hoyer 3 yards out to make it 41-33. In conclusion, Hyde ran for another 1-yard touchdown (with a failed 2-point conversion) to make the final score 41-39.\\n\\nQuestion: How many field goals over 40 yards were made?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"2","rationale":"To answer the question, \\"How many field goals over 40 yards were made?\\", we need to check how many times Zuerlein kicked a 48-yard and/or a 50+ yard field goal. In this passage, it is mentioned that he did once in each of the second and third quarters. Therefore, there are 2 such attempts which means there are 2 successful kicks over 40 yards made by him."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers. A list is shown by two brackets and comma-separated numbers inside, like: [1,2,3]. You should remove all of the even numbers from the list. If every number in the input list is even an empty list should be returned. Zero should be counted as an even number.\\n\\n[165, 160, 150, 38, 163, 130, 0]","target":"[165, 163]","rationale":"The given list contains the even numbers 160, 150, 38, 130 and 0. Removing these would result in a list of [165, 163]."},{"source":"Generate a question about the following movie plot: Gomez Addams (Ra√∫l Juli√°) laments the 25-year absence of his brother Fester (Christopher Lloyd), who disappeared after the two had a falling-out. Gomez spends each morning hitting golf balls off the roof which often hit the windows of his neighbor Judge George Womack (Paul Benedict) who gets repeatedly angered at this. Gomez's lawyer Tully Alford (Dan Hedaya) owes money to loan shark Abigail Craven (Elizabeth Wilson) and notices that her son Gordon closely resembles Fester. Tully proposes that Gordon pose as Fester to infiltrate the Addams household and find the hidden vault where they keep their vast riches. Tully and his wife Margaret (Dana Ivey) attend a s√©ance at the Addams home led by Grandmama (Judith Malina) in which the family tries to contact Fester's spirit. Gordon arrives, posing as Fester, while Abigail poses as psychiatrist Dr. Pinder-Schloss and tells the family that Fester had been lost in the Bermuda Triangle for the past 25 years.Gomez, overjoyed to have Fester back, takes him to the family vault to view home movies from their childhood. Gordon learns the reason for the brothers' falling-out: Gomez was jealous of Fester's success with women, and wooed the conjoined twins Flora and Fauna Amore away from him out of envy. Gomez starts to suspect that \\"Fester\\" is an impostor when he is unable to recall important details about their past. Gordon attempts to return to the vault, but is unable to get past a booby trap. Gomez's wife Morticia (Anjelica Huston) reminds \\"Fester\\" of the importance of family amongst the Addamses and of their vengeance against those who cross them. Fearing that the family is getting wise to their con, Abigail (under the guise of Dr. Pinder-Schloss) convinces Gomez that his suspicions are due to displacement.Gordon grows closer to the Addams family, particularly the children Wednesday (Christina Ricci) and Pugsley (Jimmy Workman), whom he helps to prepare a swordplay sequence for a school play. The Addamses throw a large party with their extended family and friends to...","target":"What was Gomez jealous of leading to the brothers' falling-out?","rationale":"In the context, it says that \\"Gomez was jealous of Fester's success with women\\".\\nBased on this information, we can conclude a question such as: What was Gomez jealous of leading to the brothers' falling-out? is most appropriate."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a paragraph from the research paper and your task is to generate a suitable title for the research paper based on the given paper. Under 100 words is a good title length.\\n\\nDiarrhea outbreaks in pig farms have raised major concerns in Europe and USA, as they can lead to dramatic pig losses. During a suspected outbreak in Belgium of porcine epidemic diarrhea virus (PEDV), we performed viral metagenomics to assess other potential viral pathogens. Although PEDV was detected, its low abundance indicated that other viruses were involved in the outbreak. Interestingly, a porcine bocavirus and several enteroviruses were most abundant in the sample. We also observed the presence of a porcine enterovirus genome with a gene insertion, resembling a C28 peptidase gene found in toroviruses, which was confirmed using re-sequencing, bioinformatics, and proteomics approaches. Moreover, the predicted cleavage sites for the insertion suggest that this gene was being expressed as a single protein, rather than a fused protein. Recombination in enteroviruses has been reported as a major mechanism to generate genetic diversity, but gene insertions across viral families are rather uncommon. Although such inter-family recombinations are rare, our finding suggests that these events may significantly contribute to viral evolution.","target":"Identification of an enterovirus recombinant with a torovirus-like gene insertion during a diarrhea outbreak in fattening pigs","rationale":"The title should provide evidence for the existence of viral recombinants and describe their role in viral evolution. As suggested by the paper, enterovirus gene insertions across viral families are rather uncommon. In this study, a recombinant between an enterovirus and a torovirus was identified during a diarrhea outbreak in fattening pigs. Here's one suggestion: \\"Identification of an enterovirus recombinant with a torovirus-like gene insertion during a diarrhea outbreak in fattening pigs\\""},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: When did the government take a stand against extremism groups in terms of a new law?\\nContext: In 2002, the Musharraf-led government took a firm stand against the jihadi organizations and groups promoting extremism, and arrested Maulana Masood Azhar, head of the Jaish-e-Mohammed, and Hafiz Muhammad Saeed, chief of the Lashkar-e-Taiba, and took dozens of activists into custody. An official ban was imposed on the groups on 12 January. Later that year, the Saudi born Zayn al-Abidn Muhammed Hasayn Abu Zubaydah was arrested by Pakistani officials during a series of joint U.S.-Pakistan raids. Zubaydah is said to have been a high-ranking al-Qaeda official with the title of operations chief and in charge of running al-Qaeda training camps. Other prominent al-Qaeda members were arrested in the following two years, namely Ramzi bin al-Shibh, who is known to have been a financial backer of al-Qaeda operations, and Khalid Sheikh Mohammed, who at the time of his capture was the third highest-ranking official in al-Qaeda and had been directly in charge of the planning for the 11 September attacks.","target":"12 January","rationale":"The context states that the Musharraf-led government took a firm stand against extremist groups in 2002. The first mention of an action taken by the Pakistani government is on January 12, when an official ban was imposed on jihadi organizations and other extremist groups.\\nSo, based on this information the answer to \\"When did they take a stand?\\" would be \\"12 January\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown an English sentence. You need to classify the sentence as either a representation of an adjunct island or as an incorrect representation. A correct representation should be denoted as 'good' while everything else should be denoted as 'bad'. A correct representation of an adjunct island will be a grammatically correct instance of a sentence using an adjunct island. An incorrect representation will be everything else.\\n\\nWho have most students distracted Marla before impressing?","target":"bad","rationale":"The sentence is ungrammatical. It can be corrected into \\"Who have most students been distracted by Marla before impressing?\\". Therefore, it is not a correct representation of an adjunct island and should be denoted as \\"bad\\"."},{"source":"Write a question about the following article: The newly minted 1982 Los Angeles Raiders season finished the 1982 NFL strike 1982 NFL season 8-1 to win the AFC West, but lost in the second round of the 1982-83 NFL playoffs to the 1982 New York Jets season. The 1983 NFL season, the 1983 Los Angeles Raiders season finished 12-4 to win the AFC West. Convincing playoff wins over the 1983 Pittsburgh Steelers season and 1983 Seattle Seahawks season in the 1983-84 NFL playoffs propelled the Raiders to their fourth Super Bowl. Against the 1983 Washington Redskins season in Super Bowl XVIII, the Raiders built a lead after blocking a punt and recovering for a touchdown early in the game. A Branch touchdown reception from Plunkett put the Raiders up 14-0 with more than nine minutes remaining in the first quarter. With seven seconds remaining in the first half, linebacker Jack Squirek intercepted a Joe Theismann swing pass at the Washington five yard line and scored, sending the Raiders to a 21-3 halftime lead. Following a John Riggins one-yard touchdown run (extra point was blocked), Marcus Allen scored from five yards out to build the lead to 28-9. The Raiders sealed the game with Allen reversed his route on a Super Bowl record run that turned into a 74-yard touchdown. The Raiders went on to a 38-9 victory and their third NFL championship. Allen set a record for most rushing yards (191) and combined yards (209) in a Super Bowl as the Raiders won their third Super Bowl in eight years.\\n\\nQuestion about the article:","target":"Which players scored touchdowns for the Raiders in the Super Bowl in 1984?","rationale":"Here's an example of a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: Which players scored touchdowns for the Raiders in the Super Bowl in 1984?"},{"source":"Found the following article online, use it to answer the question: What is the last name of the person who had a scholarship at Trinity College of Music?\\n\\nGiovanni Battista Barbirolli was born in Southampton Row, Holborn, London, the second child and eldest son of an Italian father and a French mother. He was a British national from birth, and as Southampton Row is within the sound of Bow Bells, Barbirolli always regarded himself as a Cockney. His father, Lorenzo Barbirolli (1864‚Äì1929), was a Venetian violinist who had settled in London with his wife, Louise Marie, n√©e Ribeyrol (1870‚Äì1962). Lorenzo and his father had played in the orchestra at La Scala, Milan, where they had taken part in the premi√®re of Otello in 1887. In London they played in West End theatre orchestras, principally that of the Empire, Leicester Square.\\nThe young Barbirolli began to play the violin when he was four, but soon changed to the cello. He later said that this was at the instigation of his grandfather who, exasperated at the child's habit of wandering around while practising the violin, bought him a small cello to stop him from \\"getting in everybody's way\\". His education at St. Clement Danes Grammar School overlapped, from 1910, with a scholarship at Trinity College of Music. As a Trinity student, he made his concert debut in a cello concerto in the Queen's Hall in 1911. The following year he won a scholarship to the Royal Academy of Music, which he attended from 1912 to 1916, studying harmony, counterpoint and theory under Dr. J. B. McEwen and the cello with Herbert Walenn. In 1914 he was joint winner of the academy's Charles Rube Prize for ensemble playing, and in 1916 The Musical Times singled him out as \\"that excellent young 'cello player, Mr Giovanni Barbirolli.\\" The principal of the Academy, Sir Alexander Mackenzie, had forbidden students to play the chamber music of Ravel, which he regarded as \\"a pernicious influence\\". Barbirolli was keenly interested in modern music, and he and three colleagues secretly rehearsed Ravel's String Quartet in the privacy of a men's lavatory in the Academy.From 1916 to 1918 Barbirolli was a freelance cellist in London. He recalled, \\"My first...","target":"Barbirolli","rationale":"Barbirolli was a British national from birth, and as Southampton Row is within the sound of Bow Bells, Barbirolli always regarded himself as a Cockney. His father, Lorenzo Barbirolli (1864‚Äì1929), was a Venetian violinist who had settled in London with his wife, Louise Marie, n√©e Ribeyrol (1870‚Äì1962).\\nThe given text tells us that John's last name is Barbirolli"},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, identify who is wrong here. Classify each post into the following categories : AUTHOR (if the author of the post is wrong in the situation), OTHER (if any of the others mentioned in the paragraph is wrong), EVERYBODY (if everyone mentioned is wrong) and NOBODY (if no one is wrong in the situation).\\n\\nI‚Äôll say, straight up that I expect YTA. I‚Äôm terrified of dealing with my health issues, even though I know they‚Äôre serious.\\n\\nI justify it by saying that I‚Äôm only one person, dealing with a lot. My son has a lot of special needs and I‚Äôm trying to be there for a lot of people.\\n\\nThe truth is that I have a 9 yo son with special needs and a husband who absolutely adores me. My husband is really scared that I‚Äôm not going to the doctor.\\n\\nI know I should go but I don‚Äôt. It‚Äôs always been bad news and I‚Äôm not sure I can function if the doctors decide nothing can be done anymore.\\n\\nHowever, if I could be treated, my life would be better- not just for me,but for my husband, 9 yo and my21 yo.\\n\\nThe problem is that I‚Äôm letting my fear keep me from accepting and dealing with serious health issues, even though it could affect my family \\n\\nTLDR health issues that could be treated but letting fears stop me, even if it means pain to my loved ones","target":"AUTHOR","rationale":"The author claims that they are scared to go to the doctor for some serious health issues, even though it would be better for them and their family. The author is not acting ethically because they are being selfish by putting their own fear and comfort above the needs of those who depend on them. The 'AUTHOR' category is applicable in this case."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, a context passage, and four options which are terms from the passage. After reading a passage, you will get a brief understanding of the terms. Your job is to determine by searching and reading further information of which term you can answer the question. Indicate your choice as 'a', 'b', 'c', or 'd'. If you think more than one option is plausible, choose the more probable option to help you answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: What year did the pre-season race that Lawson won in 1985 first begin? Passage:Lawson accepted an offer from Yamaha to contest the 500cc World Championship as Kenny Roberts' teammate for the 1983 season. Lawson spent the 1983 season learning the ropes of the Grand Prix circuit. In 1984, Lawson began winning regularly and won the 1984 World Championship. It would mark the first of four world titles Lawson would go on to win. In 1985, he won the prestigious Imola 200 pre-season race. After winning two more titles for Yamaha in 1986 and 1988, Lawson shocked the racing world by announcing he would be leaving Yamaha to sign with their arch-rivals Rothmans Honda as teammate to his own archrival, Australia's 1987 World Champion Wayne Gardner. By switching teams, Lawson also fulfilled his desire to work with Erv Kanemoto. After Gardner crashed and broke his leg during the third round at Laguna Seca, Lawson went on to win the 1989 title for Honda, becoming the first rider to win back-to-back championships on machines from different manufacturers. By winning with both Yamaha and Honda, Lawson silenced his critics who believed he would not be as successful away from the factory Marlboro Yamaha team.\\n Links: a. 1989 Grand Prix motorcycle racing season b. 1988 Grand Prix motorcycle racing season c. Wayne Gardner d. Imola 200","target":"d","rationale":"The question is about a pre-season race that Lawson won in 1985. The only option that is related to this question among the given answer choices is 'Imola 200'."},{"source":"(CNN) -- Arsenal means business. A fortnight ago the critics were wondering if the Gunners could last the pace -- now that doubt looks to have been quashed -- and in some style. A 1-0 win over last year's Champions League finalist Borussia Dortmund proved Arsenal can mix it with Europe's elite when it really matters. Having lost the home fixture against the German side in north London two weeks ago, victory was essential for Arsenal to keep hold of its own destiny. And it duly obliged thanks to Aaron Ramsey's second half winner -- his 11th goal in 16 games -- not bad for a player who had only mustered five in 91 apperances for the club over the past two years.\\n@highlight\\nArsenal claims victory at Borussia Dortmund with Aaron Ramsey goal\\n@highlight\\nMessi inspires Barcelona to qualification\\n@highlight\\nAtletico Madrid cruises through to next stage\\n@highlight\\nChelsea thrashes Schalke 3-0 at Stamford Bridge \\n\\"A year ago, I thought it would be difficult for @placeholder to score goals but he's developed tremendously and that's a huge credit to him.\\" \\nWhat could the \\"@placeholder\\" be? Aaron Ramsey, Arsenal, Atletico Madrid, Barcelona, Borussia Dortmund, CNN, Champions League, Chelsea, Europe, German, Gunners, London, Messi, Schalke, Stamford Bridge?","target":"Aaron Ramsey","rationale":"The context mentions Aaron Ramsey as the player who scored 11 goals in 16 games.  As all other options are places and teams, we can conclude that \\"@placeholder\\" is most likely a person's name from this passage: Aaron Ramsey"},{"source":"In this task, you are given the name of an Indian food dish. You need to classify the dish as \\"sweet\\" or \\"spicy\\".\\n\\nPork Bharta","target":"spicy","rationale":"The dish \\\\\\"Pork Bharta\\\\\\" is a spicy pork dish."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a text from a social media post. Your task is to classify the given post into two categories: 1) yes if the given post is potentially offensive to anyone (i.e., a subset of people, any particular person, etc.), 2) no, otherwise. Note that potentially offensive posts can contain sexual, racial, religious biased or offensive language. Warning: the examples and instances may contain offensive language.\\n\\nhow the fuck do all these fucking faggot ass randos even find zoe's ask account????","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given post is potentially offensive to some people as it contains profanity and a slur. Therefore, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a list of integers and an integer k. You need to find the kth largest element in the input list.\\n\\n[293, 239, 204, 195, 163, 143, 205, 206, 125, 70, 127, 47, 209, 43, 88, 274, 259, 279, 162, 296], k=7","target":"209","rationale":"The 7th largest number in the given list is 209."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the intersection of two given sets.  A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. The intersection of two given sets is the largest set which contains all the elements that are common to both sets. To find the intersection of two given sets, A and B is a set consisting of all the elements common to both A and B.\\n\\nSet1: '{4, 7, 11, 14, 19}', Set2: '{17, 19}'. How many elements are there in the intersection of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"1","rationale":"Given Set1: '{4, 7, 11, 14, 19}' and Set2: '{17, 19}', the intersection consists of only 1 element: 19."},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nThe more the baby suckles, the more prolactin is released, which causes more milk to be produced.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nIf Mona is a nursing mother and her body begins producing less prolactin then before, what happens to the amount of milk she will produce decrease or increase?","target":"decrease","rationale":"The amount of prolactin released by Mona's body determines how much milk she produces. If the level of prolactin in her blood decreases, then it would cause a reduction in the amount of milk produced and therefore \\"decrease\\"."},{"source":"\\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). Given a prompt and two responses, identify which response is the type of \\"yes, and\\". Indicate your answer by 'Response 1' if the first response is correct, otherwise 'Response 2'.  Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange.\\n\\nPrompt: I noticed them flying, but thought what was really distinctive about these kids is their enthusiasm. \\n Response 1: The only way they could make things better would be if they killed those dirty fake mable syrup drinkers but we know they will never be willing to do that. \\n Response 2: I was definitely struck by their flying ability. I haven't seen that before.","target":"Response 2","rationale":"In the prompt, a person is describing their experience of seeing kids fly and also mentions how enthusiastic they are. Then, in Response 2, the person states that they were definitely struck by the flying ability and haven't seen it before. This response is an example of \\"Yes, and\\" as it agrees with what was mentioned in the prompt (\\"yes\\") about the flying ability (\\"and...\\"), expands on that line of thought or context."},{"source":"In this task you are given a tweet. You must judge whether the tweet is ironic or not. We define two type of irony for this task (\\"polarity\\",\\"situational\\"). Situational irony happens when a situation fails to meet some expectations. polarity irony happens when irony is achieved by inverting the intended sentence. Label the instances as \\"ironic\\" or \\"not\\" based on your judgment. Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nI'm so afraid.","target":"ironic","rationale":"This sentence is ironic because it expresses the opposite of what is usually meant."},{"source":"In this task you will be given two dialogues. You need to determine if both dialogues have the same underlying emotion. The possible emotions are happy, sad, angry, or other. If they do output 'yes', if not output 'no'.\\n\\nDialogue 1: 'u r comparing me with ur cat loll no i mean dogs do it quite often than women i'm not a woman'. Dialogue 2: 'i want girlfriend you need a life first still now i am alone person'.","target":"no","rationale":"Dialogue 1 expresses frustration while Dialogue 2 expresses sadness. Therefore, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to classify the sentence into one of the following five action categories - INFORM, INFORM_INTENT, OFFER, REQUEST, REQUEST_ALTS. If the sentence is about informing something, generate 'INFORM'. If it is about requesting something, generate 'REQUEST'. If the sentence mentions requesting an alternative option than the one provided, generate 'REQUEST_ALTS'. Similarly, generate 'OFFER' if the sentence is offering some information. If the sentence is about showing intent to do something, generate 'INFORM_INTENT'.\\n\\nAwesome! Can you get me the dates?","target":"INFORM_INTENT","rationale":"The intent of the sentence is to get dates from a previous request. Therefore, the category is 'INFORM_INTENT'."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Satellite television is  according to \\"article 1.39\\" of the International Telecommunication Unions (ITU) ITU Radio Regulations (RR)  a \\"Broadcasting-satellite service\\".\\n\\n- Donald Edmond \\"Donnie\\" Wahlberg Jr. (born August 17, 1969) is an American singer-songwriter, actor, record producer, and film producer. He is a founding member of the boy band New Kids on the Block. Outside of music, he has had roles in the \\"Saw\\" films, \\"The Sixth Sense\\", \\"Dreamcatcher\\", and \\"Righteous Kill\\", also appearing in the World War II miniseries \\"Band of Brothers\\" as First Lieutenant Carwood Lipton. From 2002 to 2003, he starred in the crime drama \\"Boomtown\\". He has been starring in the drama series \\"Blue Bloods\\" with Tom Selleck and Bridget Moynahan since 2010, and since 2014 is an executive producer of the TNT reality television show \\"Boston's Finest\\". He was nominated for \\"Choice Scream\\" at the 2008 Teen Choice Awards for his work in the \\"Saw\\" films.\\n\\n- A music video is a short film integrating a song and imagery, produced for promotional or artistic purposes. Modern music videos are primarily made and used as a marketing device intended to promote the sale of music recordings. There are also cases where songs are used in tie in marketing campaigns that allow them to become more than just a song. Tie ins and merchandising could be used in toys or marketing campaigns for food and other products. Although the origins of music videos date back to musical short films that first appeared in the 1920s, they came into prominence in the 1980s when MTV based their format around the medium. Prior to the 1980s, these works were described by various terms including \\"illustrated song\\", \\"filmed insert\\", \\"promotional (promo) film\\", \\"promotional clip\\", \\"promotional video\\", \\"song video\\", \\"song clip\\" or \\"film clip\\". Since the creation and increased popularity of YouTube, mainstream artists now promote new music videos by releasing trailers of short promos on the site for their upcoming song and music video. Consequentially, YouTube has been converted into a social media platform for celebrities and artists to market themselves to their fans\\n\\n- The American Music Awards (AMAs) is an annual American music awards show, created by Dick Clark in 1973 for ABC when the network's contract to air the Grammy Awards expired. Unlike the Grammys, which are awarded on the basis of votes by members of the Recording Academy, the AMAs are determined by a poll of the public and fans, who can vote through the AMAs website. The award statuette is manufactured by New York firm Society Awards.\\n\\n- MTV (originally an initialism of Music Television) is an American cable and satellite television channel owned by Viacom Media Networks (a division of Viacom) and headquartered in New York City. Launched on August 1, 1981, the channel originally aired music videos as guided by television personalities known as \\"video jockeys\\" (VJs). In its early years, MTV's main target demographic was young adults, but today it is primarily towards teenagers, high school students and college students. MTV has toned down its music video programming significantly in recent years, and its programming now consists mainly of original reality, comedy and drama programming and some off-network syndicated programs and films, with limited music video programming in off-peak time periods. It has received criticism towards this change of focus, both by certain segments of its audience and musicians. MTV's influence on its audience, including issues involving censorship and social activism, has also been a subject of debate for several years.\\n\\n- Howard Dwaine \\"Howie D.\\" Dorough (born August 22, 1973) is an American singer, songwriter, actor and dancer. He is best known as a member of American music group Backstreet Boys.\\n\\n- 2gether ( usually stylized as 2ge + her , 2Ge + Her or 2GE + HER ; pronounced \`\` Together '' ) was an American fictional boy band whose composition , songs , and formation story is a satirical approach to the boy bands of the 1990s , such as New Kids on the Block , ' N Sync and Backstreet Boys . They were part of a self - titled MTV TV movie and spin - off television series . The band , movie , and TV series were created by writers Brian Gunn and Mark Gunn , who also wrote many of their songs .\\n\\n- Viacom, Inc. (known simply as Viacom) is an American media conglomerate with interests primarily in cinema and cable television. It is currently the world's sixth largest broadcasting and cable company in terms of revenue, behind Comcast, The Walt Disney Company, Time Warner, 21st Century Fox and CBS Corporation, respectively. Voting control of Viacom is held by National Amusements, Inc., a privately owned theater company controlled by the billionaire Sumner Redstone. Redstone also holds via National Amusements a controlling stake in CBS Corporation.\\n\\n- The Osmonds are an American family music group with a long and varied career  a career that took them from singing barbershop music as children to achieving success as teen-music idols, from producing a hit television show to continued success as solo and group performers. The Osmonds are devout members of the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints, and their religious values have influenced their careers.\\n\\n- Massachusetts ; officially the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, is the most populous state in the New England region of the northeastern United States. It is bordered by the Atlantic Ocean to the east, the states of Connecticut and Rhode Island to the south, New Hampshire and Vermont to the north, and New York to the west. The state is named for the Massachusett tribe, which once inhabited the area. The capital of Massachusetts and the most populous city in New England is Boston. Over 80% of Massachusetts' population lives in the Greater Boston metropolitan area, a region influential upon American history, academia, and industry. Originally dependent on agriculture, fishing and trade, Massachusetts was transformed into a manufacturing center during the Industrial Revolution. During the 20th century, Massachusetts' economy shifted from manufacturing to services. Modern Massachusetts is a global leader in biotechnology, engineering, higher education, finance, and maritime trade.\\n\\n- Alexander James \\"A. J.\\" McLean (born January 9, 1978) is an American singer, songwriter, actor, dancer, and model. He is a member of the vocal group the Backstreet Boys.\\n\\n- Orlando is a city in the U.S. state of Florida and the county seat of Orange County. Located in Central Florida, it is the center of the Orlando metropolitan area, which had a population of 2,387,138, according to U.S. Census Bureau figures released in March 2016, making it the 24th-largest metropolitan area in the United States, the sixth-largest metropolitan area in the Southern United States, and the third-largest metropolitan area in Florida. As of 2015, Orlando had an estimated city-proper population of 270,934, making it the 73rd-largest city in the United States, the fourth-largest city in Florida, and the state's largest inland city.\\n\\n- Viacom Media Networks (formerly MTV Networks) is an American mass media division of Viacom that oversees the operations of many of its television channels and Internet brands, including Nickelodeon, BET, CMT, Comedy Central, VH1 and the original MTV channel in the United States. Its sister international division is Viacom International Media Networks.\\n\\n- A boy band (or boyband) is loosely defined as a vocal group consisting of young male singers, usually in their teenage years or in their twenties at the time of formation. The first boy bands consisted of the Beatles, Jackson 5, the Monkees, and the Osmonds singing love songs marketed towards young females. Being vocal groups, most boy band members do not play musical instruments, either in recording sessions or on stage, making the term something of a misnomer. However, exceptions do exist. Many boy bands dance as well as sing, usually giving highly choreographed performances.\\n\\n- Brian Thomas Littrell (born February 20, 1975) is an American singer, songwriter and actor, best known as a member of the Backstreet Boys. He is also a CCM singer and released a solo album, \\"Welcome Home\\", in 2006. Brian has five top 20 solo singles on the US Christian chart.\\n\\n- The Monkees are an American-British pop rock band originally active between 1965 and 1971, with subsequent reunion albums and tours in the decades that followed. They were formed in Los Angeles in 1965 by Bob Rafelson and Bert Schneider for the American television series \\"The Monkees\\", which aired from 1966 to 1968. The musical acting quartet was composed of Americans Micky Dolenz, Michael Nesmith and Peter Tork and British actor and singer Davy Jones. The band's music was initially supervised by producer Don Kirshner.\\n\\n- Boston (pronounced ) is the capital and most populous city of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts in the United States. Boston is also the seat of Suffolk County, although the county government was disbanded on July 1, 1999. The city proper covers with an estimated population of 667,137 in 2015, making it the largest city in New England and the 23rd most populous city in the United States. The city is the economic and cultural anchor of a substantially larger metropolitan area known as Greater Boston, a Metropolitan Statistical Area (MSA) home to a census-estimated 4.7¬†million people in 2014 and ranking as the tenth-largest such area in the country. Alternately, as a Combined Statistical Area (CSA), this wider commuting region is home to some 8.1¬†million people, making it the sixth-largest as such in the United States.\\n\\n- A misnomer is a word or term that suggests a meaning that is known to be wrong. Misnomers often arise because the thing received its name long before its true nature was known, or because the nature of an earlier form is no longer the norm. A misnomer may also be simply a word that is used incorrectly or misleadingly. \\"Misnomer\\" does not mean \\"misunderstanding\\" or \\"popular misconception\\", and many misnomers remain in legitimate use (that is, being a misnomer does not always make a name incorrect).\\n\\n- The City of New York, often called New York City or simply New York, is the most populous city in the United States. With an estimated 2015 population of 8,550,405 distributed over a land area of just , New York City is also the most densely populated major city in the United States. Located at the southern tip of the state of New York, the city is the center of the New York metropolitan area, one of the most populous urban agglomerations in the world. A global power city, New York City exerts a significant impact upon commerce, finance, media, art, fashion, research, technology, education, and entertainment, its fast pace defining the term \\"New York minute\\". Home to the headquarters of the United Nations, New York is an important center for international diplomacy and has been described as the cultural and financial capital of the world.\\n\\n- New Kids on the Block (also initialized as NKOTB) is an American boy band from Boston, Massachusetts. The band currently consists of brothers Jordan and Jonathan Knight, Joey McIntyre, Donnie Wahlberg, and Danny Wood. New Kids on the Block enjoyed success in the late 1980s and early 1990s and have sold more than 80 million records worldwide. They won two American Music Awards in 1990 for Favorite Pop/Rock Band, Duo, or Group and Favorite Pop/Rock Album. The group disbanded in 1994, after which several attempts were made to get the group back together, all of them unsuccessful.\\n\\n- The Backstreet Boys (often abbreviated as BSB) are an American vocal group, formed in Orlando, Florida in 1993. The group consists of A. J. McLean, Howie D., Nick Carter, Kevin Richardson, and Brian Littrell.\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, we are interested in knowing the entity with which '2gether ' exhibits the relationship of 'genre'. Find the answer from the choices below.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- academia\\n - agriculture\\n - album\\n - art\\n - article\\n - barbershop music\\n - censorship\\n - college\\n - comedy\\n - crime\\n - criticism\\n - dance\\n - economy\\n - education\\n - family\\n - fashion\\n - finance\\n - government\\n - history\\n - james\\n - love\\n - march\\n - mass\\n - miniseries\\n - music\\n - nature\\n - pop\\n - radio\\n - research\\n - rock\\n - society\\n - song\\n - statuette\\n - television\\n - television series\\n - theater\\n - urban\\n - war","target":"comedy","rationale":"The paragraph talks about \\"2gether\\", which was a fictional boy band whose composition, songs, and formation story is a satirical approach to the boy bands of the 1990s. It also mentions that they were part of MTV TV movie and spin-off television series. As such, 2gether's genre can be considered as comedy since it satirizes other forms of music popular during its time period.\\n'''"},{"source":"Premise: Young woman in pink does skateboarding figure.\\n\\nHypothesis: A woman is in a skating competition.\\n\\n.Choose the correct answer: Given the premise, can we conclude the hypothesis?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"it is not possible to tell","rationale":"The premise does not mention a skating competition, so the hypothesis cannot be true. However, we also don't know whether or not she is in a skating competition (or any other type of skateboarding event) because this information isn't provided to us. Therefore, it's impossible to tell if she's in one and will compete soon; as such, \\"it is not possible to tell\\" is the correct answer here."},{"source":"Gokula Krishnan was an Indian film director, who has directed Tamil films. He was primarily active in the 1980s and early 1990s and is most noted for his work on films featuring actor Karthik. He also extensively worked with Malayalam director Fazil, when he made Tamil films, helping write dialogues.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nGokula Krishnan was primarily active in a time period which was more than 3000 days ago.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"We can conclude that \\"Gokula Krishnan was primarily active in a time period which was more than 3000 days ago\\" as the first paragraph of this passage states that Gokula worked in Tamil films during various periods including 1980s and early 1990s. Since 80's is more than 30 years ago, we are able to confirm having considered the fact that one year has 365 days (considering leap years). So, the answer is Yes"},{"source":"Given a text passage, you need to generate a suitable title as the output. The output title should be one of the words/phrases used in the passage and must be no longer than five words. \\n\\nParagraph:    The tower had two floors and a mezzanine . On the first floor was the famous Sundial Room or Meridian Room , which was initially an open loggia . Pope Urban VIII had it enclosed and it was subsequently decorated with long sequences of frescoes painted between 1580 and 1582 by Simon Lagi and the two Flemish artists Paul and Matthijs Bril . Today the tower has paintings by Cristoforo Roncalli and Matteino da Siena . \\n The Sundial Room , also called the Meridian Hall , was once the residence of Queen Christina of Sweden , then newly converted to Catholicism . The room was further modified by two additions which gave it its current name : a sundial , and a delicate but sophisticated anemoscope which was fixed to the ceiling of the Meridian Hall . These were created by Ignazio Danti , the papal cosmographer , in association with the Gregorian Calendar Reform . The sundial consisted of a straight line in white marble running across the floor in a north @-@ south direction , intended to measure the height of the Sun at noon according to the seasons of the year . The observations made with the sundial provided essential confirmation of the need to reform the Julian calendar . The anemoscope , in contrast , was a complex mechanism attached to the ceiling which was used to measure the strength and direction of the wind but soon stopped functioning . The instrument may have led to the other name of the tower , Tower of the Winds ; however , an ancient observatory at Athens was also called the Tower of the Winds and might have been the source for inspiration . \\n The interior walls and ceiling of the hall were richly decorated , in some cases with gaudy frescoes of the hills and Roman countryside , the Pantheons , religious themes , the buildings surrounding the area , and naval shipwrecks with Jesus calming the storm and so forth .   \\n Question: what is the suitable title of the passage ?","target":"Features","rationale":"The suitable title should be one of the words/phrases in the passage and must be no longer than five words. In this case, there are several suitable titles: 'Features', 'Sundial', 'Anemoscope' and so forth."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: Babies love chocolate and sometimes they also eat the paper around it. My cat enjoys a meal of goods, thick paper and letters, for example. She doesn't like newspapers very much.\\nOf course, the best paper comes from wood. Wood comes from trees, and trees are plants. Vegetables and fruit are plants too, and we eat a lot of them. So can we also eat wood and paper? \\nScientists say, \\"All food comes in some way from plants.\\" Well, is that true? Animals eat grass and grow fat. Then we eat their meat. Little fish eat little sea plants; then bigger fish swim along and eat them. Chickens eat bits of grass and give us meat. Think for a minute. What food does not come from plants in some way?\\nScientists can do wonderful things with plants. They can make food just like meat and cheese. And they can make it without the help of animals. Now they have begun to say, \\"We make our paper from wood. We can also make food from wood. The next thing is not very difficult.\\" What is the next thing? Perhaps it is food from paper. Scientists say, \\"We can turn paper into food. It will be good, cheap food too; cheaper than meat or fish or eggs.\\"\\nSo please keep your old books and letters. Don't feed them to your cat. One day, soon they will be on your plate.  _ .\\nQuestion: The writer of this passage   _  .\\nOptions: A: wants to keep our old books and letters\\nB: is making up stories for breakfast\\nC: tells truth in a humorous way\\nD: doesn't agree with scientists","target":"C","rationale":"The answer is \\"C, tells truth in a humorous way\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a pair of action statements. Your task is to check if you can conclusively identify which statement is less ethical or not. Answer: 'no' if one of the statements is less ethical, and 'yes' otherwise.\\n\\nACTION1: being pissed at my family for forcing a birthday celebration on me ACTION2: blowing up about how mum treated me on her birthday","target":"no","rationale":"The author of the post is being forced to celebrate their birthday, and they are unhappy about this. In such a situation, it is reasonable for the author to be angry at their family members for forcing them to celebrate something they do not want.\\\\nOn the other hand, the second statement describes how another individual - presumably a family member - treated someone on their birthday. The post does not provide any information about why or how that person was treated badly or unfairly on their birthday. Therefore, there is insufficient information to determine if that person acted unethically by treating someone poorly on their birthday.\\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question that involves ‚Äúevent duration\\", based on a given sentence. Here, event duration is defined as the understanding of how long events typically last. For example, ‚Äúbrushing teeth‚Äù, usually takes a few minutes. Note that a lot of the questions could have more than one correct answer. We only need a single most-likely answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: He was asked to lend his support by writing a letter, with Szilard, to President Roosevelt, recommending the U.S. pay attention and engage in its own nuclear weapons research. \\nQuestion: How long did it take him to write the letter?","target":"15 minutes","rationale":"The answer is \\"15 minutes\\" because this letter was written in short period of time and the main goal was to inform president."},{"source":"Adverse drug reactions are appreciably harmful or unpleasant reactions resulting from an intervention related to the use of medical products, which predicts hazard from future administration and warrants prevention or specific treatment, or alteration of the dosage regimen, or withdrawal of the product. Given medical case reports extracted from MEDLINE, the task is to classify whether the case report mentions the presence of any adverse drug reaction. Classify your answers into non-adverse drug event and adverse drug event.\\n\\nBenzocaine-induced methemoglobinemia has been reported in man, dogs, and cats.","target":"adverse drug event","rationale":"The case report mentions that benzocaine-induced methemoglobinemia is observed in humans, dogs and cats. This adverse drug event occurs with the use of benzocaine as an analgesic and anti-infective agent. So, the answer is \\"adverse drug event\\"."},{"source":"What was likely said next? DIALOG:\\nWhat was Stephen Toulmin's objection to absolutism?\\n- Stephen Toulmin said that absolutism has limited practical value.\\n- Why did Stephen Toulmin believe absolutism had limited practical value?\\n- Stephen Toulmin said that absolutism has limited practical value because it is irrelevant to real situations encountered by human beings in daily life.\\n- Does Stephen Toulmin have any other beliefs regarding absolutism besides saying that absolutism has limited practical value because it is irrelevant to real situations encountered by human beings in daily life?\\n-","target":"The flaw of absolutism, Stephen Toulmin believes, lies in its unawareness of the field-dependent aspect of argument; absolutism assumes that all aspects of argument are field invariant.","rationale":"The question asks what was likely said next in the conversation, after Stephen Toulmin's objection to absolutism is discussed. In the given options, the statement \\"The flaw of absolutism, Stephen Toulmin believes, lies in its unawareness of the field-dependent aspect of argument; absolutism assumes that all aspects of argument are field invariant.\\" best answers this question as it provides a clear answer to why Stephen Toulmin believed that absolutism has limited practical value."},{"source":"The closer the field lines are drawn together, the stronger the field being described.\\n\\nCompared to a field represented by lines spaced every inch on a sheet of paper, if another field were drawn at the same scale with lines spaced every two inches, the second field would be described as stronger or described as weaker??","target":"described as weaker?","rationale":"Field lines represent the intensity of a magnetic field in a given area. The closer together they are, the stronger the field is. So, if one set of lines is spaced every inch and another set has space between them twice as large (one line every two inches), then it follows that there would be fewer total length of lines per unit area for this second case. Since more closely-spaced magnetic fields indicate greater strength or intensity, we can conclude that the first example provides us with a higher-intensity field than does our second example where those same number and density of lines were placed farther apart on the paper.\\nSo described as weaker?"},{"source":"Based on the premise \\"Disabled\\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"Definitely not disabled.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The given hypothesis contradicts the premise. The context of \\"disabled\\" can have a variety of meanings, but in this case it refers to having some disability or inability. So, we cannot conclude that the statement is true and must select \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The NBC Tower is an office tower on the Near North Side of Chicago, Illinois, United States located at 454 North Columbus Drive (455 North Cityfront Plaza is also used as a vanity address for the building) in downtown Chicago's Magnificent Mile area. Completed in 1989, the 37-story building reaches a height of 627 feet (191 m). NBC's Chicago offices, studios, and owned-and-operated station WMAQ-TV are located here as of 1989 and on October 1, 1989, WMAQ-TV broadcast their first newscast at 10 pm that evening at their new home, NBC Tower with the then-weeknight news team of Ron Magers, Carol Marin, John Coleman and Mark Giangreco. Later, Telemundo O&O WSNS-TV since their 2002 purchase by NBC. Formerly its former radio sister WMAQ/WSCR was located here. NBC's former Chicago FM property, WKQX and its sister station WLUP will move their studios to the NBC Tower in the summer of 2016.\\n\\n- The National Broadcasting Company (NBC) is an American commercial broadcast television network that is the flagship property of NBCUniversal, a subsidiary of Comcast. The network is headquartered in the Comcast Building (formerly known as the GE Building) at Rockefeller Center in New York City, with additional major offices near Los Angeles (at Universal City Plaza), Chicago (at the NBC Tower) and soon in Philadelphia at Comcast Innovation and Technology Center. The network is part of the Big Three television networks. NBC is sometimes referred to as the \\"Peacock Network\\", in reference to its stylized peacock logo, which was originally created in 1956 for its then-new color broadcasts and became the network's official emblem in 1979.\\n\\n- Comcast Corporation (formerly registered as Comcast Holdings) is an American global telecommunications conglomerate that is the largest broadcasting and cable television company in the world by revenue. It is the second-largest pay-TV company after the AT&T-DirecTV acquisition, largest cable TV company and largest home Internet service provider in the United States, and the nation's third-largest home telephone service provider. Comcast services U.S. residential and commercial customers in 40 states and in the District of Columbia. The company's headquarters are located in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania. As the owner of the international media company NBCUniversal since 2011, Comcast is a producer of feature films and television programs intended for theatrical exhibition and over-the-air and cable television broadcast.\\n\\n- Philadelphia is the largest city in the Commonwealth of Pennsylvania and the fifth-most populous city in the United States, with an estimated population of 1,567,442 and more than 6¬†million in the seventh-largest metropolitan statistical area, . Philadelphia is the economic and cultural anchor of the Delaware Valleya region located in the Northeastern United States at the confluence of the Delaware and Schuylkill rivers with 7.2¬†million people residing in the eighth-largest combined statistical area in the United States.\\n\\n- The Big Three television networks are the three major traditional commercial broadcast television networks in the United States: ABC, CBS and NBC. Beginning in 1948 until the late 1980s, the Big Three networks dominated U.S. television.\\n\\n- Rockefeller Center is a large complex consisting of 19 highrise commercial buildings covering between 48th and 51st Streets in New York City. Commissioned by the Rockefeller family, it is located in the center of Midtown Manhattan, spanning the area between Fifth Avenue and Sixth Avenue. It was declared a National Historic Landmark in 1987.\\n\\n- Chicago (or ), officially the City of Chicago, is the third-most populous city in the United States, and the fifth-most populous city in North America. With over 2.7¬†million residents, it is the most populous city in the state of Illinois and the Midwestern United States, and the county seat of Cook County. The Chicago metropolitan area, often referred to as Chicagoland, has nearly 10¬†million people and is the third-largest in the U.S.\\n\\n- Mihaly \`\` Michu '' Meszaros ( Hungarian : M√©sz√°ros Mih√°ly ; born September 20 , 1939 in Budapest ) is a Hungarian performer best remembered as a performer with Ringling Bros. and Barnum & Bailey Circus and the man behind the costume in the NBC sitcom ALF . He is 2 feet 9 inches ( 84 cm ) tall . Meszaros appeared in numerous television and film projects . His last appearance was in 1993 's Warlock : The Armageddon . For the first few seasons of ALF , Meszaros donned a full - body costume of the character whenever a full - body shot of the alien was needed . Meszaros was used where scenes of ALF walking , running , or standing were required . Most shots were half - body shots of ALF 's upper body , since the ALF costume was extremely hot and uncomfortable for the actor to wear under the bright studio lights and during long stretches . The ALF puppet and costume can be distinguished on first view because the head proportions are slightly different .\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat entity does 'michu meszaros' has the relation 'date of death' with?","target":"2011","rationale":"The correct answer is 2011."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- John Carradine (born Richmond Reed Carradine; February 5, 1906¬† November 27, 1988) was an American actor, best known for his roles in horror films, Westerns, and Shakespearean theatre. A member of Cecil B. DeMille's stock company and later John Ford's company, he was one of the most prolific character actors in Hollywood history. He was married four times, had five children, and was the patriarch of the Carradine family, including four of his sons and four of his grandchildren who are or were also actors.\\n\\n- Stanley Lloyd Kaufman, Jr. (born December 30, 1945) is an American film director, producer, screenwriter and occasional actor. With producer Michael Herz, he is the co-founder of Troma Entertainment film studio, and the director of many of their feature films, including \\"The Toxic Avenger\\" and \\"Tromeo and Juliet\\".\\n\\n- Troma Entertainment is an American independent film production and distribution company founded by Lloyd Kaufman and Michael Herz in 1974. The company produces low-budget independent movies that play on 1950s horror with elements of farce. Many Troma films contain social commentary. In 2012, the company officially released many of its films on YouTube. Troma has produced, acquired and distributed over 1,000 independent films since its creation.\\n\\n- Tromeo and Juliet is a 1996 American independent transgressive romantic comedy film and a loose adaptation of William Shakespeare's \\"Romeo & Juliet\\" from Troma Entertainment. The film was directed by Lloyd Kaufman from a screenplay by Kaufman and James Gunn, who also served as associate director.\\n\\n- Roger William Corman (born April 5, 1926) is an American independent film producer, director, and actor. He has been called \\"The Pope of Pop Cinema\\" and is known as a trailblazer in the world of independent film. Much of Corman's work has an established critical reputation, such as his cycle of low budget cult films adapted from the tales of Edgar Allan Poe. Admired by members of the French New Wave and \\"Cahiers du cin√©ma\\", in 1964 Corman was the youngest filmmaker to have a retrospective at the Cin√©math√®que Fran√ßaise, as well as the British Film Institute and the Museum of Modern Art. In 2009, he was awarded an Honorary Academy Award.\\n\\n- Mary Woronov (born December 8, 1943) is an American actress, published author and figurative painter. She is primarily known as a \\"cult star\\" because of her work with Andy Warhol and her roles in Roger Corman's cult films. Woronov has appeared in over 80 movies, on stage at Lincoln Center and off-Broadway productions, as well as numerous appearances in mainstream American TV series, such as \\"Charlie's Angels\\" and \\"Knight Rider\\". She frequently co-starred with friend Paul Bartel; the pair appeared in 17 films together, often playing a married couple.\\n\\n- John Ford (February 1, 1894  August 31, 1973) was an American film director. He is renowned both for Westerns such as \\"Stagecoach\\" (1939), \\"The Searchers\\" (1956), and \\"The Man Who Shot Liberty Valance\\" (1962), as well as adaptations of classic 20th-century American novels such as the film \\"The Grapes of Wrath\\" (1940). His four Academy Awards for Best Director (in 1935, 1940, 1941, and 1952) remain a record. One of the films for which he won the award, \\"How Green Was My Valley\\", also won Best Picture.\\n\\n- Cecil Blount DeMille (August 12, 1881  January 21, 1959) was an American filmmaker. Between 1913 and 1956, he made a total of 70 features, both silent and sound films. He is acknowledged as a founding father of the cinema of the United States and the most commercially successful producer-director in film history. His films were distinguished by their epic scale and by his cinematic showmanship. He made silent films of every genre: social dramas, comedies, Westerns, farces, morality plays, and historical pageants.\\n\\n- Jesus (; c. 4¬†BC  c. AD¬†30/33), also referred to as Jesus of Nazareth or Jesus Christ, was a Jewish preacher and religious leader who became the central figure of Christianity. Christians believe him to be the Son of God and the awaited Messiah (Christ) prophesied in the Old Testament.\\nVirtually all modern scholars of antiquity agree that Jesus existed historically, although the quest for the historical Jesus has produced little agreement on the historical reliability of the Gospels and on how closely the biblical Jesus reflects the historical Jesus. Jesus was a Galilean Jew who was baptized by John the Baptist and subsequently began his own ministry, preaching his message orally and often being referred to as \\"rabbi\\". He was arrested and tried by the Jewish authorities, and was crucified by the order of Pontius Pilate, the Roman prefect. Jesus debated fellow Jews on how to best follow God, performed healings, taught in parables and gathered followers. After his death, his followers believed he rose from the dead, and the community they formed eventually became the Christian Church.\\n\\n- Charlie's Angels is an American crime drama television series that aired on ABC from September 22, 1976 to June 24, 1981, producing five seasons and 110 episodes. The series was created by Ivan Goff and Ben Roberts and was produced by Aaron Spelling. It plots the adventures of three women working in a private detective agency in Los Angeles, California, and initially starred Kate Jackson, Farrah Fawcett, and Jaclyn Smith in the leading roles, with David Doyle co-starring as a sidekick to the three women and John Forsythe providing the voice of their boss. Later additions to the cast were Cheryl Ladd, Shelley Hack, and Tanya Roberts.\\n\\n- Paul Bartel (August 6, 1938  May 13, 2000) was an American actor, writer and director. Bartel was perhaps most known for his 1982 hit black comedy \\"Eating Raoul\\", which he wrote, starred in and directed.\\n\\n- Silent Night , Bloody Night ( Also released as Night of the Dark Full Moon and Death House ) is a 1972 American horror film directed by Theodore Gershuny and co-produced by Lloyd Kaufman . The film stars Patrick O'Neal and cult actress Mary Woronov in leading roles , with John Carradine in a supporting performance . The plot follows a series of murders that occur in a small town on Christmas Eve after a man inherits a family estate which was once an insane asylum . Many of the cast and crew members were former Warhol superstars : Mary Woronov , Ondine , Candy Darling , Kristen Steen , Tally Brown , Lewis Love , filmmaker Jack Smith and artist Susan Rothenberg . It was filmed in Oyster Bay , Long Island , New York in 1970 but was not released theatrically until 1972 .\\n\\n- Andy Warhol (born Andrew Warhola; August 6, 1928¬† February 22, 1987) was an American artist who was a leading figure in the visual art movement known as pop art. His works explore the relationship between artistic expression, celebrity culture, and advertising that flourished by the 1960s.\\n\\n- Christmas Eve is the day before Christmas Day, the festival commemorating the birth of Jesus of Nazareth. Christmas Day is observed around the world, and Christmas Eve is widely observed as a full or partial holiday in anticipation of Christmas Day. Together, both days are considered one of the most culturally significant celebrations in Christendom and Western society.\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, choose the best answer for the entity that related to 'silent night' with the relationship of 'publication date'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- 1\\n - 13\\n - 17\\n - 1881\\n - 1906\\n - 1913\\n - 1926\\n - 1928\\n - 1935\\n - 1939\\n - 1941\\n - 1945\\n - 1959\\n - 1962\\n - 1964\\n - 1973\\n - 1974\\n - 1981\\n - 1996\\n - 2009\\n - 21\\n - 22\\n - 27\\n - 4\\n - 5\\n - 6\\n - 8","target":"1974","rationale":"Troma Entertainment is an American independent film production and distribution company founded by Lloyd Kaufman and Michael Herz in 1974."},{"source":"When a person is looking at an altar, where might they be standing?\\nChoose the most suitable option to answer the above question.\\nOptions:\\n- at a cross\\n- sanctuary\\n- church services\\n- ceremony\\n- temple","target":"temple","rationale":"An altar is a structure where religious ceremonies and rituals are performed. In many religions, the primary place of worship is called the temple or church. It can be inferred that if a person were looking at an altar they would most likely be in their respective house of worship, so \\"temple\\" seems to be the best answer choice."},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: What is the full name of Charles-Valentin Alkan presumed son? ?\\n\\nCharles-Valentin Alkan (French: [ Éa Ål val…ëÃÉt…õÃÉ alk…ëÃÉ]; 30 November 1813 ‚Äì 29 March 1888) was a French-Jewish composer and virtuoso pianist. At the height of his fame in the 1830s and 1840s he was, alongside his friends and colleagues Fr√©d√©ric Chopin and Franz Liszt, among the leading pianists in Paris, a city in which he spent virtually his entire life.\\nAlkan earned many awards at the Conservatoire de Paris, which he entered before he was six. His career in the salons and concert halls of Paris was marked by his occasional long withdrawals from public performance, for personal reasons. Although he had a wide circle of friends and acquaintances in the Parisian artistic world, including Eug√®ne Delacroix and George Sand, from 1848 he began to adopt a reclusive life style, while continuing with his compositions ‚Äì virtually all of which are for the keyboard. During this period he published, among other works, his collections of large-scale studies in all the major keys (Op. 35) and all the minor keys (Op. 39). The latter includes his Symphony for Solo Piano (Op. 39, nos. 4‚Äì7) and Concerto for Solo Piano (Op. 39, nos. 8‚Äì10), which are often considered among his masterpieces and are of great musical and technical complexity. Alkan emerged from self-imposed retirement in the 1870s to give a series of recitals that were attended by a new generation of French musicians.\\nAlkan's attachment to his Jewish origins is displayed both in his life and his work. He was the first composer to incorporate Jewish melodies in art music. Fluent in Hebrew and Greek, he devoted much time to a complete new translation of the Bible into French. This work, like many of his musical compositions, is now lost. Alkan never married, but his presumed son √âlie-Miriam Delaborde was, like Alkan, a virtuoso performer on both the piano and the pedal piano, and edited a number of the elder composer's works.\\nFollowing his death (which according to persistent but unfounded legend was caused by a falling bookcase) Alkan's music became neglected,...","target":"√âlie-Miriam Delaborde","rationale":"The question asks for the full name of Charles-Valentin Alkan's presumed son. The article mentions that this person was a virtuoso performer on both piano and pedal piano, and edited a number of composers works (presumably his father). Based on this information it can be inferred that the answer is √âlie-Miriam Delaborde."},{"source":"Solve 2723*r = 2712*r for r.\\nSolve this problem.","target":"0","rationale":"Since the variable r is equal to itself, the only possible solution for this equation is 0."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a short story consisting of exactly 5 sentences where the second sentence is missing. You are given two options and you need to select the one that best connects the first sentence with the rest of the story. Indicate your answer by 'Option 1' if the first option is correct, otherwise 'Option 2'. The incorrect option will change the subsequent storyline, so that at least one of the three subsequent sentences is no longer consistent with the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: Suzy was having some tooth pain. \\n Sentence 3: So she decided to put gel on it \\n Sentence 4:  It took awhile \\n Sentence 5:  But after an hour she felt much better \\n Option 1: She ate food that was very soothing. \\n Option 2: She ate food that was too cold.","target":"Option 2","rationale":"The correct option needs to connect the first sentence with the rest of the story. Suzy having tooth pain could be due to her eating something that is too cold. As a result, she decided to put gel on it, which took awhile but made her feel better after an hour. Therefore Option 2 is correct as it completes the story without changing its storyline. On the other hand, if Suzy ate food that was very soothing and then decides to put gel on her teeth, this makes little sense as there would be no reason for putting gel on a tooth after eating soothing food."},{"source":"W: Yes, I just saw a very funny film on TV.\\n\\nM: What was it about?\\n\\nW: It was about a careless man who got into trouble wherever he went. He couldn't do anything well.\\n\\nM: So you liked it?\\n\\nW: Yes, I did. It made me laugh a lot.\\n\\nM: But I'd rather see something not only interesting but also instructive.\\n\\nW: Oh James, don't be so serious. People sometimes need relaxation.\\n\\nM: That's true. But I think that watching TV is not just for entertainment.\\n\\nWhat was said before this conversation?","target":"M: Hi, Kate, you look happy.","rationale":"The woman (W) in the conversation says she just saw a funny film on TV. The man (M) asks about it, and then indicates that he'd rather see something interesting and instructive instead of just entertaining.\\nSo, the answer is M: Hi, Kate, you look happy."},{"source":"In this task you are given a small conversation between two persons and 4 options on how the conversation should continue. Your job is to choose the most reasonable option. The conversation and the options are separated by a newline character. Each dialogue in the conversation are separated by a comma. F and M indicate female and male, respectively.\\n\\nM: Hi Mary, I gave your note to Danny this morning. ,F: You gave it to Danny? Are you kidding, Frank? The note was for Joe not for Danny.\\n(A) M: I will give your note to Danny tomorrow as you've asked. (B) M: Oh it's for me? I thought it was for Danny. (C) M: I've already give Joe your note. (D) M: Excuse me, could you repeat the question?","target":"D","rationale":"Option (A) makes no sense as we are not sure why Mary is requesting to give the note to Danny. Option (B) and (C) are incorrect as Frank did not receive the note and has already given it away. Option (D) is correct because when someone does not understand a question or statement, they would ask for it to be repeated."},{"source":"Question: who has the most subscribers on youtube of all time??\\nAnswer:","target":"PewDiePie","rationale":"PewDiePie is the most subscribed YouTuber of all time with over 98 million subscribers.\\nThe answer provided, \\"Element Animation\\", does not match this fact and should be rejected as incorrect."},{"source":"Question: who is the father of colleen ballengers baby??\\nAnswer:","target":"actor Erik Stocklin","rationale":"The answer is \\"actor Erik Stocklin\\" as stated in multiple articles and news clippings dedicated to the fact that Colleen Ballenger, who plays Mariana Adams-Foster on The Fosters gave birth to a baby girl named Chloe on February 9th 2018. \\nErik Stocklin has been acting since 2003 with appearances in many tv shows including Criminal Minds: Beyond Borders. He was also featured alongside his daughter's mother, actor Cierra Ramirez, in the movie Girl In Progress released May 2012."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: Which of the two operas at which Schunk appeared in 1981 is older? Passage 1:Browntown is the first community that WIS 11 passes through in Green County. WIS 11 then becomes a freeway and circles around Monroe to the north, picking up concurrency with WIS 81 east and Crossing WIS 69 and the terminus of WIS 59 while on the freeway segment. WIS 81 turns southeast toward Beloit two miles (3¬†km) south of Brodhead while WIS 11 passes through the city and turns east into Rock County. The highway crosses WIS 213 in Orfordville and passes through Footville before beginning its southern bypass of Janesville. The bypass crosses US 51 and then joins I-39 and I-90 for back up north where it turns east toward US 14 and joins it concurrently - the two routes continuing east to Walworth County.\\n Passage 2:Chapple served with the regiment in Malaya, Hong Kong and Borneo. He was promoted to captain on 9 February 1957 and to major on 9 February 1964. Appointed a Member of the Order of the British Empire in the Queen's Birthday Honours 1969 and promoted to lieutenant colonel on 31 December, he was appointed Commanding Officer of the 1st Battalion, 2nd Gurkha Rifles in 1970 and made a member of the Directing Staff at the Staff College, Camberley in 1972. After spending much of the year as a services fellow at Fitzwilliam College, Cambridge in 1973, he was posted to the Directorate of Staff Duties at the Ministry of Defence at the end of the year and, having been promoted to colonel on 31 December 1973 and to brigadier on 31 December 1975, was made Commander of the Gurkha Field Force in 1976. He became Principal Staff Officer to the Chief of the Defence Staff in 1978, and having been appointed a Commander of the Order of the British Empire in the Queen's Birthday Honours 1980, he became Commander of British Forces in Hong Kong on 13 June 1980, with the substantive rank of major general from 1 January 1981. He returned to the United Kingdom to be Director of Military Operations at the Ministry of Defence on 19 October 1982.\\n Passage 3:From 1979 onwards, he worked as a freelance singer, performing internationally. He appeared at both the Hamburg State Opera and the Vienna State Opera in 1981 as the Emperor in Die Frau ohne Schatten by Richard Strauss. In 1983, he appeared as Max in Weber's Der Freisch√ºtz at the Bregenz Festival. The same year, he made his U.S. debut as Erik at the Lyric Opera of Chicago. In 1984 he took part in the Hamburg State Opera's tour of Japan. In 1986 he appeared as Florestan in Beethoven's Fidelio at the Metropolitan Opera, opposite Hildegard Behrens in the title role, returning in 1989 as Siegmund and in 1990 as the Emperor, a role which he had also performed for his 1987 debut at the Royal Opera House. In 1996, he appeared as Loge in Wagner's Das Rheingold at the Op√©ra de Marseille. In addition to his opera activities, Schunk has also performed successfully in concerts. He recorded the tenor solo in Beethoven's Ninth Symphony in 1986, conducted by Georg Solti with the Chicago Symphony Orchestra & Chorus, alongside Jessye Norman, Reinhild Runkel and Hans Sotin.","target":"3","rationale":"The question asks for the age order of two operas in which Schunk appeared in 1981. The only passage that mentions his appearance in operas is Passage 3, and this passage clearly indicates the age order of the two operas."},{"source":"The county continues to experience significant growth and is becoming increasingly diverse.  As of the 2010 census, the countys population had increased to 321,520, an increase of 27.9% over the 2000 census.  , the United States Census estimates the countys population at 332,427, an increase of 3.4% since the 2010 census.  As of the 2010 census, 65.7% of the population was non-Hispanic whites, 25.9% was Latino or Hispanic, 6.6% was African-American and 1.1% was Asian.  As of the 2010 census, the greatest source of population growth in the county since the 2000 census came from the Latino or Hispanic population which grew from 49,296 (19.6% of the total population) to 83,177 (25.9% of the total population).  In terms of ancestry, 37.9% were English people, 9.9% were Irish people, 9.1% were Americans, 3.2% were Italians and 3.1% were Germans.\\n\\nAnswer this question based on the article: Which two ancestries living in the county ranged from 9 to 10 percent of the population?","target":"Irish people","rationale":"The question asks us to find the two ancestries that ranged from 9 to 10 percent of the population. Among all ancestries, only Irish people and Americans fit this range: 37.9% were English people, 9.9% were Irish people, 9.1% were Americans, 3.2% were Italians and 3.1% were Germans"},{"source":"What came before. Sure I can just let me know what you want and where I need to order like the location.","target":"I would like to order something from Bosses Pizza can you put in an order for me?","rationale":"The previous conversation/text in the dialogue was \\"I would like to order something from Bosses Pizza can you put in an order for me?\\". The user confirmed that they wanted to place an order, and asked where they needed to specify the location."},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: Does the sentence \\"Kazakhstan continues to increase production and may have become the world's largest producer of uranium by 2009 with an expected production of 12,826 tonnes, compared to Canada with 11,100 t and Australia with 9,430 t.\\" provide a valid answer to the question \\"What percentage of world uranium oxide production is produced by Argentina?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"While the sentence talks about Kazakhstan's uranium production, there is no mention of Argentina's. The answer provided to us does not contain any information related to world percentage share in uranium oxide production for specific countries and hence cannot be used as a valid answer for this question-answer pair."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that seamlessly connects with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes more sense.\\n\\nTitle: Princess. Sentence 1: My sister has always wanted to be a princess. Sentence 2: She used to dress up in princess dresses all the time. Sentence 3: She told me that I had to call her a princess. Sentence 4: Eventually, I told her that she was dumb for pretending. Choices: a. The cat jumped onto Cam's shoulders in traffic, causing him to crash. b. She told my parents and I ended up getting in trouble.","target":"b","rationale":"The story is about a sister that wants to be treated like a princess. The last sentence needs to be in line with the rest of the story. Therefore, it should be about how she reacted when being called dumb by the protagonist. Option a) does not make sense because it doesn't fit with the rest of the story and b) fits seamlessly into the storyline, thus making more sense than option a)."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\ni 'm glad to have my father around because he 's so special to me when i 'm feel bad or sad he 's always there to comfort me even when i 'm wrong he try to put me in the right he always put a smile on my face and im glad my father 's all mine i admit if i do n't have my father around i would n't be complete i would walk around all day and feel like a piece of my heart be miss this be why i 'm so happy and proud to have a father that love and care for me i 'm glad to have my father because he 's so special to me","target":"high","rationale":"The poem shows a mature approach towards expressing emotions and using figurative language. The poet has used several metaphors, such as referring to himself as a \\"piece of my heart\\" and his father is \\"all mine\\". This kind of poetic expression is more typical for high-school students than elementary school students."},{"source":"Write a question about the following article: Joanna la Beltraneja, born in 1462, the first and only daughter of King Henry IV of Castile, was of Asturias. A rumour spread that Princess Joanna was not actually the daughter of King Henry but rather of Beltr√°n de la Cueva, the alleged lover of Queen Joan of Portugal. Joanna was thus nicknamed \\"la Beltraneja\\", as a mocking reference to her assumed father. Pressure from members of the nobility forced the King to strip her of the title and name his half-brother Alfonso as heir, in 1464. In 1465, a group of nobility assembled in √Åvila and overthrew King Henry, replacing him with Alfonso. That led to a war that ended in 1468 with the death of the 14-year-old Alfonso. Henry IV regained the throne, but the title of heir became disputed between Joanna, his daughter, and Isabella, his half-sister. That was resolved via the Treaty of the Bulls of Guisando, which gave Isabella succession rights but restricted her marriage options. Isabella secretly married Ferdinand in 1469 at the age of 17, ignoring Henry IV's wishes. Gradually, the couple gained a larger number of supporters and obtained a papal bull sanctioning their marriage from Pope Sixtus IV in 1472 and gained the support of the powerful Mendoza family in 1473. When Henry IV died in December 1474, both candidates for the throne were proclaimed Queen of Castile by their respective supporters. Aware of their position of weakness against Isabella's supporters, Joanna's supporters proposed for the 43-year-old King Afonso V of Portugal, a widower for some 20 years, to marry Joanna, his niece, and assume the throne of Castile with her.\\n\\nQuestion about the article:","target":"What year was Isabella born?","rationale":"Here's an example of a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: What year was Isabella born?"},{"source":"Corey Gibson, known professionally as Corey Chorus, is an American songwriter, record producer, vocal producer, sound engineer and publisher, known for having written songs such as Cheers (Drink to That) of Rihanna, Chica Bomb by Dan Balan, Made in the USA by Demi Lovato.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that this sentence is true?\\nGibson has not worked with Lovato.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"Since the paragraph specifically mentions that Gibson worked with Lovato, we cannot conclude that he did not work with her. Hence, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nMia entered the hall. Phone rang. Elizabeth entered the hall. The lettuce is in the green_pantry. Mia moved the lettuce to the red_envelope. Mia entered the attic. Elizabeth entered the attic. Phone rang. The lime is in the red_crate. Phone rang. Mia moved the lime to the blue_bathtub. Hannah entered the attic. Jack entered the attic. The tomato is in the blue_bathtub. Hannah moved the tomato to the red_crate. Phone rang. Mia entered the bathroom. Elizabeth entered the bathroom. The banana is in the green_crate. Mia moved the banana to the blue_suitcase. Where does Mia think that Elizabeth searches for the banana?","target":"blue_suitcase","rationale":"Mia's beliefs about the banana are correct (belief matches reality). She believes that it is in the blue_suitcase and at the end of the story, Elizabeth finds it there."},{"source":"Q: Who are some of the most renowned architects to come from Portugal?\\n A: Traditional architecture is distinctive and include the Manueline, also known as Portuguese late Gothic, a sumptuous, composite Portuguese style of architectural ornamentation of the first decades of the 16th century.\\n Does the answer correctly answer the question\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The answer only provides information about a style of architecture, which is not the same as an architect. Therefore , it does not correctly answer the question."},{"source":"Question: Terrie leads her dog team to deliver some food and other things to someone in a snowbound cabin. Terrie's dogs pull the empty sled to a nearby supply station, then pull the loaded sled on to the snowbound cabin.  In which situation will the dogs have more difficulty in getting the sled moving swiftly? (A) when the sled is empty (B) when the sled is weighed down with supplies\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"sled with supplies on it\\" and  \\"empty sled\\".","target":"empty sled","rationale":"The question asks which situation will the dogs have more difficulty in getting the sled moving swiftly. The answer is empty sled because an empty sled has less mass and requires less force for acceleration than a loaded one, so it's easier to get started from rest."},{"source":"In this task you are given a tweet that contains some form of irony. You must classify the type of irony the tweet has. Label the tweets (\\"polarity\\",\\"situational\\",\\"other\\") based on the irony they have. Situational irony happens when a situation fails to meet some expectations, Label these instances as \\"situational\\". polarity irony happens when irony is achieved by inverting the intended sentence, Label these instances as \\"polarity\\". There are other kinds of ironies that are neither polarity nor situational, Label these instances as \\"other\\". Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nSexist article in the Daily Fail about men wasting money on cycling - accompanied by recommendation for a handbag costing ¬£999.","target":"situational","rationale":"The tweet contains situational irony, as the article that is being criticized for being sexist also contains a recommendation for an expensive handbag, which is stereotypically associated with women."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a hateful post in English from online platforms. You are expected to classify the target being harassed in the post as individual or generic, i.e., single person or a group of people. Note that the URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nPost: I'm just tweetin ion want no hoes why you dm'n me lil whore üòÇüíÄ","target":"Generic","rationale":"The post does not target any individual person and is not directed towards anyone in particular. It includes some demeaning language that could be aimed at a group of people. Therefore, the answer to this example is \\"Generic\\"."},{"source":"Premise:\\n\\"uh to see the other cultures or you know and some of that but\\" Based on this premise, is the hypothesis \\"To see my own culture.\\" true?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise doesn't mention the host's own culture, and there is no information to infer that it was mentioned. Hence, we can conclude that the hypothesis isn't true."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and a question, you would be asked to create the answer which is contained in the sentence provided.\\n\\nSentence: Variation in muscle cells gives further insight into some benefits of anaerobic type of respiration. Question: Variation in muscle cells gives further insight into some benefits of what type of respiration?","target":"anaerobic","rationale":"The sentence provides information about the benefits of anaerobic type of respiration, including the insight that more variation in muscle cells increases the benefits of this type of respiration. This is directly connected to the answer, which is \\"anaerobic\\"."},{"source":"Everyone woke early on the day that Dogland's restaurant opened. Everything that needed to be done in advance had been done: white wire tables and chairs stood on the restaurant's green concrete patio, and a sign painter had lettered each of the restaurant's windows: Doggy gifts and Snack bar and Guided tours and Bring your camera! and Entrance with a stylized hand with a finger pointing toward the restaurant's front door. Ma, Mayella, and Francine had scrubbed the front room and the kitchen \\"from top to bottom,\\" as Ma proudly announced several times. She wished her mother could come to visit, because she knew the place would never be so clean again.\\nJames had mowed the open land, and Ethorne had walked the grounds with a clippers and a knife, saying he had every intention of improving on perfection. Seth had lettered several sheets of poster board with the information that the kennels would not formally open until more dogs had arrived, people were welcome to stroll along the viewing path for free, and please don't feed the dogs.\\nWe woke at sunrise. Because this was a special day, Pa left to pick up the workers. Ma dressed us, telling us to stay clean and not to talk to customers unless they talked to us first and to stay by the house and not to get in the way and to always be polite and not to yell or make noise unless someone wanted us to get in their car or go anywhere with them without Ma or Pa saying it was okay first, and then we were to scream for all we were worth.\\nLittle Bit didn't want to wear a dress. When Ma asked if she wanted to be a little lady, she gave a decided \\"No,\\" so Ma let her wear shorts, T-shirt, and cowboy boots like Digger and me.\\nQuestion: What did we probably do when the opening finished:\\nOptions:\\n- we were all tired and happy \\n - we had a party for the dogs \\n - we decided to make some changes \\n - not enough information\\n===\\nThe correct answer is","target":"we were all tired and happy","rationale":"The context supports that the whole family worked on getting ready for the opening of Dogland's restaurant. The question asks what we probably did when it finished, suggesting that this is something everyone in the family would have done together as well.\\nGiven these two pieces of information and among all options given,  \\"we were all tired and happy\\" seems most likely to be true based on how much effort was put into preparing for the event by everyone in the family."},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhat happened in 1864?\\n- In 1864, a connecting curve was opened between the lines to Mannheim and Karlsruhe in order to relieve the station.\\n- What happened along the route to Mannheim?\\n- A new freight yard and marshalling yard were built in 1873 west of R√∂merstra√üe along the route to Mannheim.\\n- What happened in the early 20th century?\\n- At the beginning of the 20th century the development of Bergheim to the north of the station and modern Weststadt to the south of it prevented the extension of railway precinct.\\n- How many trains were operated?\\n-","target":"In 1902, 340 trains operated on weekdays from Heidelberg station.","rationale":"The candidate statements are not relevant to the dialog as they do not correspond with the context. The correct answer is: \\"In 1902, 340 trains operated on weekdays from Heidelberg station.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: sexual-explicit and non-sexual-explicit. A comment is considered sexual-explicit if it explicitly portrays sexual matters.\\n\\nComment: He (trump) has more empathy for the KKK, white supremacists, and Nazis who  marched in Charlottesville  then the Americans suffering in Puerto Rico.  Uses minorities to play to his base in making American great again.  America was always great!","target":"Non-sexual-explicit","rationale":"The given comment does not contain any explicit portrayal of sexual matters. It only expresses a political opinion about Trump and his policies, so the answer is \\"Non-sexual-explicit\\"."},{"source":"There are several reasons an otherwise valid and agreed upon treaty may be rejected as a binding international agreement, most of which involve problems created at the formation of the treaty.[citation needed] For example, the serial Japan-Korea treaties of 1905, 1907 and 1910 were protested; and they were confirmed as \\"already null and void\\" in the 1965 Treaty on Basic Relations between Japan and the Republic of Korea.\\nTopic from the paragraph:","target":"Treaty","rationale":"The context is a discussion of treaties, including the circumstances in which they can be rejected. The paragraph introduces this topic by stating that \\"there are several reasons an otherwise valid and agreed upon treaty may be rejected as a binding international agreement\\".\\nTherefore, the answer to question: Topic from the paragraph\\" should clearly be \\"Treaty."},{"source":"My love affair with technology began at an early age. On my seventh birthday, my parents bought me a second-hand ZX Spectrum and, in a foretaste of my life to come, I immediately set about learning how to use it to get attention. It's a sign of how rapidly technology develops that my crappy Spectrum, with its 48k of memory, already had 12k more storage power than the computer that had guided the Apollo 11 moon landing eighteen years earlier* With power like that, there seemed to be no limit to what I could do.\\nWhile my other computer-owning peers would sit for hours while their tape drives squawked away loading 'Manic Miner' or 'Bubble Buster' I was more fascinated by learning to write my own programs. The first of these consisted of just two lines of code* that made the word 'shit' appear again and again on my screen, to the huge amusement of my friends and the irritation of my parents, who obviously had more educational motives for bringing a computer into the house.\\nFrom that day on, the possibilities offered by technology to both subvert the norm and get attention had me hooked.\\nYears later, at secondary school, I convinced my English teacher, Mr Coen, to teach me desktop publishing, ostensibly to work on the official school magazine, but in reality to produce an alternative underground version - complete with less than flattering articles about teachers and fellow pupils and distributed via the publicly accessible shared hard drive that was supposed to be used for collaborative coursework. That particular stunt got me banned from the school computer room for half a term.\\nAnd then, in 1997, I discovered the Internet.\\nThroughout history, every fame-hungry media dickhead has found his preferred medium for pursuing fame and wealth (in that order). For Tony Parsons - and Hitler, for that matter - it was books. William Randolph Hearst chose newspapers. Don Imus and Howard Stern preferred radio. For Nick Griffin it's inflammatory leaflets. For Tracy Emin it's art. Or at least an approximation of it. With the...\\nHow long did it take the narrator to learn desktop publishing?\\n\\nA. A few hours.\\n\\nB. Weeks.\\n\\nC. Days.\\n\\nD. not enough information","target":"A","rationale":"A desktop publisher is a person who creates publications using software on their computer. This could be anything from brochures to magazines or books, and the type of work done by these people can include text editing, graphic design and layout work. It's not clear how long it would take someone to become an experienced desktop publisher with professional skills but the narrator does say that he convinced his teacher to use this program for teaching him about publishing. So most likely it was used over time as part of lessons rather than just during one lesson where he learned everything there is to know about desktop publishing in its entirety; hence why A - \\"a few hours\\" must refer only to the introduction given at school by Mr Coen (English Teacher).\\nIt cannot have taken weeks because if that were true then how come"},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"Andorra (; , ), officially the Principality of Andorra (), also called the Principality of the Valleys of Andorra, (), is a landlocked microstate in Southwestern Europe , located in the eastern Pyrenees mountains and bordered by Spain and France .\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Andorra","rationale":"The passage is about the country of Andorra, so that should be marked as the topic."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. If the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers Win'. If the count of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list, answer 'Alphabets Win'. If the count of numbers is same as that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers and Alphabets are Tied'.\\n\\n['o', 'q', '5105', 'X', '7461', 'F', 'Z', 'u', '7649', '9849', 'H', '1299', 'u', '3271', 'q', 'S', 'Q', 'C', 'q', '6019', 'm', '6909', 'L', '8353', '7707', 'i', 'E', 'o', 'w']","target":"Alphabets Win","rationale":"Given the list: ['o', 'q', '5105', 'X', '7461', 'F', 'Z', 'u', '7649, 9849, H, 1299, u, 3271, q,'S','Q','C','q','6019','m','6909,''L''8353'7707'i'E'o''w],' let's count the number of alphabets and numbers:\\\\n1. Alphabets are 26 in total.\\\\n2. Numbers are 7 in total.\\\\n\\\\nSince there're more alphabets than numbers in the given list A , answer is \\"Alphabets Win\\" \\\\"},{"source":"Territory of Papua and New Guinea -- In 1884, Germany formally took possession of the northeast quarter of the island and it became known as German New Guinea. In 1884, a British protectorate was proclaimed over Papua -- the southern coast of New Guinea. The protectorate, called British New Guinea, was annexed outright on 4 September 1888 and possession passed to the newly federated Commonwealth of Australia in 1902 and British New Guinea became the Australian Territory of Papua, with Australian administration beginning in 1906. \\n\\nHaving read that, could you tell me was papua new guinea ever part of australia?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The passage mentions that the British protectorate was proclaimed over Papua in 1884. This protectorate, called \\"British New Guinea\\", became Australian territory and Australia began administering it in 1906.\\nHence, Yes is the correct answer to this question."},{"source":"It 's been tough getting good photos around here lately , even though the weather has been beautiful all week long . I decided that a sure bet was the Butterfly Garden at the Pacific Science Garden , so I asked Lael to go along with me for a day out . Unfortunately , after we drove all the way to Seattle and paid our $ 10 parking fee , I discovered that the Butterfly Garden was closed for the week . Needless to say , I was n't happy about that , but I was n't about to leave , either .\\nWhy might the Butterfly Garden be closed ?\\nPick the best answer from the following options:\\n- They were doing maintenance and repairs\\n - They wanted to inconvience me\\n - The gardens had been ruined by nice weather\\n - None of the above choices .","target":"They were doing maintenance and repairs","rationale":"I  was surprised to learn that the Butterfly Garden had been closed all week. In my experience, when a public facility is closed for an extended period of time it is because they are doing maintenance or repairs on their facilities. Additionally, if this were not true then \\"the gardens had been ruined by nice weather\\" would also be unlikely as nice weather should help plants and flowers thrive rather than hinder them.\\nSo I think the answer must be 1) They were doing maintenance and repairs"},{"source":"See the multi-choice question below:\\n\\nSentence 1: The participants represent over 150 commercial firms and 140 government entities located in 20 U.S.\\n\\nSentence 2: There were only 10 firms represented by the participants.\\n\\nIf the first sentence is true, then is the second sentence true?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The number of firms represented by the participants is not specified in Sentence 1."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a post in Spanish from online platforms. You are expected to identify whether the post is hateful against immigrants and women. A hateful post expresses hate or encourages violence towards a person or a group. If a post is hateful but not towards immigrants and women, it should be labeled as non-hateful. Answer \\"hateful\\" or \\"Non-hateful\\". Note that the URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nPost: Matt Damon critica campa√±a contra el acoso y la violaci√≥n sexual - La Prensa de Honduras [Link]","target":"Non-hateful","rationale":"The given post does not express any hate or encourage violence towards immigrants or women. It simply discusses a political campaign and related criticism from the actor Matt Damon. Therefore, the answer is \\"Non-hateful\\"."},{"source":"Given a negotiation between two participants, answer 'Yes' if both participants agree to the deal, otherwise answer 'No'.\\n\\nTHEM: i can let you have all the balls in return for the books and hat.  YOU: i would like to have the hat as well  THEM: yes, it is a rather nice hat. if i get the hat and one book you can have everything else.  YOU: the book has no value to me i would prefer the hat  THEM: unfortunately i really need that hat. you can have everything else.  YOU: fine doesnt matter to me.","target":"Yes","rationale":"The participants reach an agreement where one participant gets all the books and the hat, while the other participant gets all of the balls. Since both parties agree to the deal, answer is 'Yes'."},{"source":"Given a question and a context passage, generate the answer having the word or phrase from the context passage. Here, the answer should be a shortest continous span from the passage.\\n\\nContext: Louis Philippe I (6 October 1773 -- 26 August 1850) was King of the French from 1830 to 1848 as the leader of the Orleanist party. \\n Question: What nationality was Louis Philippe I?","target":"french","rationale":"The answer to the question is \\"french\\". It can be found in the context passage in two different ways: 1) King of the French 2) french"},{"source":"Write down the solution for this math problem: Solve -360*z - 23*z - 8280 - 1678 = 0 for z.","target":"-26","rationale":"To solve for z, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with:\\n-360*z - 23*z - 8280 - 1678 = 0\\n\\n Add 360*z and 23*z to both sides:\\n\\n 0 + (-360)*(-26) + (-23)*(-26) = 0+8280+1678  (1st step)\\\\n\\\\n0 = 2652    (2nd step)\\\\n\\\\n0/2652= \\\\t (3rd Step)\\\\nthen divide by zero:\\\\tyour answer is infinite or there's no solution! :)\\n\\t\`;"},{"source":"Pick the most correct option to answer the following question.\\n\\nWhich part of the electromagnetic spectrum can humans sense without using equipment or technology?\\n\\nOptions:\\n\\n- A: radio waves\\n\\n- B: visible light\\n\\n- C: microwaves\\n\\n- D: X-rays","target":"B","rationale":"The electromagnetic spectrum consists of radiation with a wide range of wavelengths. The human eye can detect only light in the visible portion, which spans from about 400 to 700 nanometers (nm). This is still far smaller than the complete EM spectrum; microwaves and radio waves are much longer while X-rays and gamma rays are much shorter. \\nTherefore, humans do not sense x-ray or microwave radiation without using equipment or technology. However, we can see visible light that emits anywhere between 400 nm - 700 nm as well as ultraviolet light below this at 300 nm - 400nm and infrared above it at 800nm - 1mm through our eyes directly making answer B most appropriate."},{"source":"Given an abstract, and a few options, indicate if any of the given options appropriately describe the given abstract. If any of them is a proper keyword, answer 'Yes', otherwise answer 'No'.\\n\\nAbstract: Human leukocyte-derived lipoxin A (LXA; 5S,-6R,15S-trihydroxy-7,9,13-trans-11-cis-eicosatetraenoic acid) inhibits the cytotoxic activity of human natural killer (NK) cells. LXA and three of its isomers were prepared by total organic synthesis and assayed for activity with human NK cells. Dose-response studies showed that biologically derived LXA and synthetic LXA were equally effective in inhibiting NK cell cytotoxicity. 6S-LXA, with its 6S-OH group in an (S) configuration, proved to be approximately half as potent as LXA. In contrast, 6S-11-trans-LXA and 11-trans-LXA displayed virtually no inhibitory activities. The methyl esters of both LXA and 6S-LXA proved to be more potent than their corresponding free acids. Thus, LXA inhibition of NK cells displays clear-cut stereochemistry. In the absence of putative inhibitors, NK cells bind to their targets to form conjugates. This event is followed by polarization of the NK Golgi apparatus, which moves towards the plasma membrane that is in contact with the target cell. However, in the presence of either the methyl ester or free acid of LXA, the Golgi apparati of NK cells bound to their targets were randomly oriented. In contrast, neither 6S-11-trans-LXA nor the potent NK inhibitor prostaglandin E2 affected the polarization. Furthermore, although prostaglandin E2 resulted in a decrease in NK-target cell binding efficiency, LXA and its isomers failed to affect conjugate formation. Together these results indicate that LXA-induced inhibition of NK cytotoxicity does not act on NK cell binding but may block cytotoxicity by disrupting \\"signals\\" involved in the specific orientation of the Golgi. Thus, this latter event may appear to be important in cytotoxicity. \\nQuestion Does the following mesh terms have a suitable mesh term for the abstract? 1)Adult 2)Aged 3)Antibodies, Monoclonal","target":"No","rationale":"The abstract provides information about a study that examined the effects of various lipoxin isomers on natural killer cell cytotoxicity. The terms provided do not adequately describe the content of this abstract. Therefore, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Make egg free brownies.","target":"instead of using eggs, use apple sauce to create the moisture and binding component.","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"instead of using eggs, use apple sauce to create the moisture and binding component."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and determine if the hypothesis is true:\\n\\nGeorge Washington Baines, Sr. (December 29, 1809 ‚Äì December 29, 1882), a maternal great-grandfather of U.S. President Lyndon Baines Johnson, was a Baptist clergyman in Arkansas, Louisiana, and Texas who served briefly as natural science professor and President of Baylor University at its first location in Independence in Washington County, Texas.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nHypothesis: George Washington Baines, Sr. was President of the distinguished Baylor University at its first location in Independence in Washington County, Texas.","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"While George Washington Baines, Sr. was a President of Baylor University at its first location in Independence in Washington County, Texas, there is not enough information provided to determine whether the university was distinguished (or \\"distinguished\\"). The term \\"distinguished\\" is subjective and can vary depending on different factors such as time period, audience or bias. So the answer is \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"Legalization would eliminate the harms caused by prohibition, but it would not eliminate the harms caused by drug use.\\n\\nQ with options: Can we draw the following conclusion?\\nDrug legalization has benefits.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The premise states that drug legalization would eliminate the harms caused by prohibition. Since eliminating these negative effects of prohibition is a benefit, we can draw this conclusion from the given information and choose \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given a sentence about a person. You should determine how the sentence affects how the person is perceived by most people in society. Your choices are: \\nPositive: The social perception of [PERSON] in the sentence is considered predominantly positive.\\nNegative: The social perception of [PERSON] in the sentence is considered predominantly negative.\\nNo impact: There is no clear impact of social perception of [PERSON] associated with the sentence.\\n\\n[PERSON] started working as a waitress and said she liked the service.","target":"No impact","rationale":"This sentence does not contain any information that would cause the social perception of a waitress to be either positive or negative. Therefore, the answer is \\"No impact\\"."},{"source":"In nowadays,people tend to get married late.Does it have advantage or disadvantage?Different people have different opinions.Now let's have a look at a telated study about Americans.\\nA study has found that marrying later in life is generally financially benfeicial for women,but not for men.\\nThe University of Virginia has published a report that college-educated women who get married in their thirties earn an average of 56 percent more than those who wed a decade earlier.\\nIn contrast,men who settle down in their twenties have higher intomes than those who wait until after 30,whatever their education.\\nThe Natioal Marriage Project's study,with the title:The Benefits and Costs of Delayed Marriage in America,examines the consequences of marrying later,a growing trend in the US.\\nIt notes that the average age of marriage is ag an all-time high of 27 for women and 29 for men,compared to 1990 when the averages were 23 for women and 26for men.\\nBut while wome have actually benefited financially from delayed marriages,men who getmarried earlier in life tend to be more successful later on.\\nThe study says that childbirth plays a role in these results.\\nAround tow-thirds of lifetime income growth takes place during the first ten years of a career,according to clinical psychologist Meg Jay.\\nSince college-educated women who marry in their twenties also tend to have their first baby earlier,forcing them to take a break from their careers.\\nBut getting hiched at a younger age tends to be a good career move for men,perhaps because married men are more sure of themselves and they have more responsibility for their family compared to single men ,leadng to more productivity,suggests Business Insider.\\nThe study also found that while college-deucated women profit from delayed marriage,those without a degree do not.\\nIn fact,among women who drop out of high school, 83 percent of first births are to unmarried mothers,according to the study.\\nA woman without a college education therefore has less time to advance her career during ist vital...\\nFrom the study we can know that  _  .\\nA) it's a bad thing for a woman to get married later\\nB) men usually earn more if they get married earlier\\nC) for a woman,the suitable age of marriage is 27\\nD) men who wed earlier in life is sure to be more successful","target":"B","rationale":"The passage mentions the result of a study and describes how men benefit more than women from getting married earlier in life. According to this information, since it's better for men to get married at an early age, option B is correct answer."},{"source":"A plant's roots break down rocks as the roots do what?\\n- decay\\n- grow old\\n- develop\\n- dcerease","target":"develop","rationale":"Plants obtain most of the nutrients they need from soil, water and air. They get energy for growth and development by converting sunlight into food through a process called photosynthesis. For example, root systems help anchor plants to the ground so that they can stand up straight. Roots hold on to valuable moisture in dry weather conditions when it is needed by your plant‚Äôs leaves during photosynthesis or respiration processes taking place aboveground; roots also store carbohydrates which provide fuel for both growing new tissue as well as surviving dormancy periods over winter months\\nRoots develop to break down rocks because roots are important structures within vascular plants (plants with tissues specialized for transporting fluids). The main function of these underground organs is absorbing mineral salts and other necessary materials such as nitrogenous compounds from its surrounding environment"},{"source":"Question: \\"Oil is a type of?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"If the highest echelons of the governments also take advantage from corruption or embezzlement from the state's treasury, it is sometimes referred with the neologism kleptocracy. Members of the government can take advantage of the natural resources (e.g., diamonds and oil in a few prominent cases) or state-owned productive industries. A number of corrupt governments have enriched themselves via foreign aid, which is often spent on showy buildings and armaments.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"natural resources","rationale":"The question asks for a type of something. The context mentions oil as an example and states that it is one of the natural resources, so \\"natural resource\\" would be considered to be a type of thing as well."},{"source":"Here's a question: If you need to travel in the cold, you would be best to be what?\\n\\nHere are possible answers to this question:\\n- warm\\n- amiable\\n- clothed\\n- prepared\\n- baking\\n\\nI believe the correct choice is \\"prepared\\", here's why:","target":"need to travel in the cold prepared","rationale":"The rationale to choose \\"prepared\\" as the answer is that:\\nneed to travel in the cold prepared"},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, identify who is wrong here. Classify each post into the following categories : AUTHOR (if the author of the post is wrong in the situation), OTHER (if any of the others mentioned in the paragraph is wrong), EVERYBODY (if everyone mentioned is wrong) and NOBODY (if no one is wrong in the situation).\\n\\nMy mom and I have not been getting along the past year and a half. She was a really shitty mom but got a little better over the years. \\n\\nLast year we had a big falling out because she talks so much shit about everyone and I ended up hearing all the shit she talks about me. We havent seen each other much since then but have talked and it has been going good.\\n\\nSo my ex boyfriend and I had a really big fight on Friday and I ended up telling her about it. Right now we are currently broken up, but have talked but not made up and he hasnt come home since Friday night. I told her about it thinking for some reason she wouldnt tell anyone. She ended up telling her bf, my aunt, and one of my brothers that I know for sure. Probably my other brother and who ever else she talks to. \\n\\nWell I learned my lesson as yesterday I went over to my aunts and was going to tell her a story about Friday, but not about the fight. I started the story by saying me and EX did this activity on Friday and she said I already heard. My story wasnt about the fight but she must have thought I was going to say that. So I was annoyed last night after leaving. I left it be. Today I text my mom and say so who did you tell about my and EXs fight? She says \\"just your brother\\". I said \\"aunt knows to does older brother know\\" she said \\"aunts nosey, probably not brother he hasnt said anything\\" long story short I said \\"i told you that thinking you werent going to tell everyone\\" she says \\"i am done with this conversation\\" so i said im not going to Christmas. And Ill just have her bf drop them off when he goes. \\n\\nShe said thats fine she isnt doing Christmas anyways and that my aunt was. I said good good. She said keep the gifts. I said alrighty bye. \\n\\nI will be sending the gifts because the gifts were for my cousins and aunt and brothers and grandma and I want them to have them. They did nothing to me. She wont be there actual Christmas day so I am maybe going over there then and seeing my grandma who is in bad shape. I texted aunt and let her know i wasnt going. She asked why i just said because of my mom but didnt go into detail. I also told my older brother who is coming up from 3 hours away and told him the same thing, said i didnt want to discuss the fight any further. He said \\"life is to short for you and mom to be petty. You only get 50 Christmas celebtrations and your wasting them.\\" Then something about me and her being childish. \\n\\nAm I the asshole? I should not have told her but I was really upset and wanted someone to talk to. Im just so annoyed my mom and I cant talk about anything or it gets spread throughout my entire family.","target":"OTHER","rationale":"The author of the post is annoyed that their mother told other people about a private conversation between them.\\\\nThe author says that their mother and they have not been getting along for a year and a half and it seems like this private conversation may be the only way for them to communicate.\\\\nIt does not seem fair that the author's mother cannot keep what they share between themselves confidential, even though she has been doing so in the past.\\\\nIn addition, even though others have information about this fight, they should respect the privacy of both parties involved and not discuss it with anyone else without permission from either party.\\\\nTherefore, it seems like everyone mentioned in this post is wrong because there are multiple violations of privacy here. However, since others are sharing information without permission from either party involved in the conflict (the author or their ex-boyfriend), it seems more appropriate to choose \\"\\"OTHER\\"\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a dialogue from a conversation between an agent and a customer. Your task is to determine the speaker of the dialogue. Answer with \\"agent\\" or \\"customer\\".\\n\\nSure, I am glad to assist you in modifying the ticket details. Can you please tell me your name?","target":"agent","rationale":"The agent is requesting the customer's name, which is in line with the role of an agent. Therefore, we can infer that the speaker of this dialogue is \\"agent\\"."},{"source":"Next question: who sang the song bang bang you shot me down?","target":"American singer-actress Cher","rationale":"Bang Bang (My Baby Shot Me Down) was originally recorded by American singer-actress Cher. It was written and composed by her then husband, Sonny Bono. The song also featured on a 1966 album release of the same name. \\nThe single reached number two in the United Kingdom charts and spent nine weeks at No 1 in Australia; it remains one of Cher‚Äôs most famous songs to date.\\""},{"source":"Where might  a  blowfish be kept?\\n- little mermaid\\n- pet shop\\n- great outdoors\\n- fish market\\n- aquarium\\n\\nThe best answer is","target":"pet shop","rationale":"The best answer is\\n- pet shop"},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the first name of the person who appointed Hugh Robertson as the complex manager? , can you please find it? \\n\\nThe management of Rockefeller Center shifted around this time. In November 1936, John Todd was featured in two New Yorker articles that emphasized his role in the complex's construction. At the same time, Nelson was gaining clout within Rockefeller Center Inc., and he disagreed with nearly all of Todd's suggestions. Nelson's father, John, was relinquishing his responsibilities, since the Rockefeller family's youngest son David had moved out of the family home at 10 West 54th Street, and John was now focusing on his own personal life. By April 1937, Todd regretted his decision to be featured in The New Yorker. In March 1938, Nelson became the president of Rockefeller Center Inc. He then fired Todd as the complex's manager and appointed Hugh Robertson in his place. Nelson and Robertson wanted to avoid workers' strikes, which would delay the completion of construction. Nelson, Robertson, and the workers' unions agreed to a contract in which the unions would not strike, Robertson would not lock out union workers, and both would agree to arbitration if a labor dispute arose. Rockefeller Center was one of Nelson's primary business ventures until 1958, when he was elected Governor of New York.Public relations officials were hired to advertise the different parts of the complex, such as the gardens and the plaza. Merle Crowell set up a viewing platform on the east side of Rockefeller Center and founded the facetious \\"Sidewalk Superintendents' Club\\" so the public could view construction.","target":"Nelson","rationale":"The article contains several mentions of the name \\"Nelson\\", which is the answer to this question."},{"source":"Which term best describes the life cycle of an insect that reaches the adult stage without being a pupa?\\n\\nOptions:\\n- incomplete metamorphosis\\n- complete metamorphosis\\n- alternation of generations\\n- spontaneous mutation","target":"incomplete metamorphosis","rationale":"The life cycle of insects is classified into incomplete metamorphosis and complete metamorphosis. Incomplete metamorphosis is characterized by eggs that develop directly to adults without passing through the pupa stage, whereas in complete metamorphosis both larvae and adult are structurally different from each other. \\nIn summary, \\"incomplete metamorphosis\\" cannot be used interchangeably with either \\"alternation of generations\\" or \\"spontaneous mutation\\", which makes it the best choice for this question"},{"source":"Write a question about the following article: The Packers traveled back home to Lambeau Field to play the Detroit Lions. At the end of the first quarter, the game was tied after field goals by Dave Rayner and Jason Hanson. In the second quarter, the Packers took the lead with a fourteen-yard run by running back Vernand Morency. Before half time Brett Favre completed a 21-yard pass to Carlyle Holiday. This was Favre's 4,968th career completion, setting an NFL record previously held by Dan Marino. In the third quarter the Lions kicked their second field goal. In the fourth quarter, Brett Favre threw his third interception out of the Packers end zone which put the Lions at the twelve-yard line. The Lions were unable to score a touchdown and completed a field goal which put the Lions within one point of the Packers. On the next possession the Packers increased their lead to eight points when Vernand Morency ran 21&#160;yards for his second touchdown of the day. On the Lions last possession of the game, the Packers sacked quarterback Jon Kitna twice to end the game. Brett Favre, who set an NFL record for career completions finished the day with twenty completions out of 37 passes. He recorded 174&#160;yards and three interceptions, two of which were in the red zone. The Packers defense limited the Lions to 142&#160;yards, no touchdowns, and two of twelve completed third downs. The Lions leading rusher was quarterback Jon Kitna. The Packers sacked Kitna six times, a career-high of three from defensive tackle Cullen Jenkins, and two sacks from Aaron Kampman. Charles Woodson had a career-high sixth interception of the season. With their 3rd-straight win over the Lions, the Packers improved to 6-8.\\n\\nQuestion about the article:","target":"How many interceptions did the Lions defense record?","rationale":"Here's a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: How many interceptions did the Lions defense record?"},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nWhere was Sara Evans born?\\n- Sara Evans was born in Boonville, Missouri, in 1971.\\n- What did Sara Evans parents do?\\n- Sara Evans' family raised corn, beans, tobacco, and livestock for a living.\\n- Where did Sara Evans go to school?\\n- Central Methodist University.\\n- What was Sara Evans first big break?\\n- Songwriter Harlan Howard was impressed by Sara Evans' demo of his song Tiger by the Tail. He decided to help her music career, leading to a signed contract with RCA Nashville.\\n- Did Sara Evans do any other work with Harlan Howard besides Tiger by the Tail?\\n- Three Chords and the Truth\\n- What work did Sara Evans do with RCA Nashville?\\n-","target":"Three Chords and the Truth","rationale":"The third question in the given dialog asks \\"What was Sara Evan's first big break?\\" The answer to this question includes a mention of Harlan Howard, which leads to a follow-up question regarding work done by Sara Evans and Harlan Howard. The only option that mentions work done by Sara Evans and Harlan Howard is \\"Three Chords and the Truth\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're shown a three-part story, with a beginning, middle, and ending. Your job is to slightly modify the middle part, so that the whole story becomes unlikely, improbable, or inconsistent. Generated sentences must minimally alter the given middle, with at most 4 new words added/existing words removed. Your sentence should be grammatically and syntactically correct. Also stick to the context of the given story. For example, if the story talks about \\"doctors\\", you can talk about \\"health\\" or \\"diagnosis\\", but don't mention \\"aliens\\". Avoid introducing any extra/irrelevant information, and use names instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible. Avoid simply negating the original middle, for example:  \\"She likes cakes.\\" is changed to \\"She doesn't like cakes.\\"\\n\\nBeginning: Josh was tired of writing so many short stories for his work. Middle: Josh took a short break. Ending: After the break, he felt fresh and ready to write more stories.","target":"Josh never took a break","rationale":"Josh's break was the reason he felt fresh and ready to write more stories. Therefore, if Josh never took a break, it would be unlikely that he would feel fresh and ready to write more stories."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that end with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'some food on white plates in on a wood table'. How many words end with the letter 'n' in the sentence.","target":"3","rationale":"Given the sentence 'some food on white plates in on a wood table', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'some' : No -> (total) 0\\\\n2. 'food' : No -> (total) 0\\\\n3. 'on' : Yes -> (total) 1\\\\n4. 'white' : No -> (total) 1\\\\n5. 'plates': No-> (total) 1 \\\\n6.'in': Yes->(totao) 2 \\\\n7.'on':Yes->(toal)=3"},{"source":"Question: what is the fourth dimension of physics\\nI found the following answer on Google: Not to be confused with Dimension of a physical quantity .\\nIs that a correct answer? Yes or no.","target":"No","rationale":"The sentence \\"Not to be confused with Dimension of a physical quantity\\" is not an answer to the question. It indicates that there are two possible concepts related to dimensions, one being dimension of physics and the other being dimension of a physical quantity. However, it does not provide any information about the meaning or nature of these concepts.\\nTherefore, this statement is not correct as an answer for the provided question. The suggested answer should thus be declined because it fails to address what was asked in Question 1 above: \\"what is fourth dimension\\"."},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Sandra journeyed to the garden. Fact 2- Daniel travelled to the bathroom. Fact 3- Sandra went to the bedroom. Fact 4- Sandra travelled to the hallway. Fact 5- Sandra travelled to the office. Fact 6- Sandra went back to the garden. Question: Where is Sandra? Answer: garden","target":"Fact 6","rationale":"Fact 6 specifies that Sandra went back to the garden, which indicates her most recent location."},{"source":"Question: when was peter kilmartin elected\\nI found the following answer on Google: Kilmartin is also a retired police captain and a former member of the Rhode Island House of Representatives .\\nIs that a correct answer? Yes or no.","target":"No","rationale":"The answer provided by the automatic system, \\"Kilmartin is also a retired police captain and former member of the Rhode Island House of Representatives\\" does not provide information related to when he was elected. \\nWhile there may be some supporting evidence for the claim that Kilmartin served as a Captain in law enforcement or represented his constituency in state legislature, it does not address when Peter Kilmartin was first elected into office. The question specifically asks about elections so providing information on dates would fit this criteria much better than other facts about him such as what positions he held or past events involving him.\\nTherefore, we can conclude that the statement given is incorrect based on our understanding of how election works and therefore should be answered with No.\\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Customer Abuse. Sentence 1: Jim was at a restaurant. Sentence 2: And he received decent service. Sentence 3: But later, he called them on the phone and lied about the service. Sentence 4: And he received a free meal for his next visit. Choices: a. For the rest of his life, Jim lied for his own benefit. b. Then, Rebecca was able to view the beautiful night sky.","target":"b","rationale":"The story is about Jim lying to a restaurant in order to receive a free meal. Option 'a' fits nicely with the rest of the story, since it implies that Jim will continue his deceptive behavior. However, option 'b' does not fit at all, as it introduces a completely new character and topic into the story. Therefore, option 'b' is less appropriate than option 'a'."},{"source":"Given a real-life anecdote of a complex ethical situation, generate a suitable title that describes the main event/root cause of the situation. Imagine that the given text is a social media post, and you have to write the title of the post, so the users can decide to read the main text or not.\\n\\nI know it's something small, but I am really confused why my mom got mad, but basically what happened was I went outside the house for about an hour, leaving my 2 dogs in my room. I thought they would be hot because it's the summer and it's very hot here, so I decide to leave the air conditioner on in my room. Once I got back my mom scolded me and said I'm wasting electricity.","target":"leaving the air conditioner in my room on when my dogs were sleeping inside","rationale":"This post describes an anecdote of a complex ethical situation in which the author's mother got angry at them for leaving the air conditioner on when their dogs were sleeping in their room. The root cause of this situation is that the author left the air conditioner on, which caused their mother to get angry. Therefore, a suitable title for this post would be \\"\\"leaving the air conditioner in my room on when my dogs were sleeping inside.\\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question, and your task is to predict the context of the question. We assume that someone named X asked the question from Y. The context of the question means the previous situation that led X to ask this question.\\n\\nAre you into historical fiction?","target":"X wants to know what sorts of books Y likes to read","rationale":"In this example, the question \\"Are you into historical fiction?\\" makes sense only when X and Y are talking about what sorts of books they like to read. It doesn't make sense for the context to be about movies or music, for example. The answer is: \\"X wants to know what sorts of books Y likes to read\\""},{"source":"Produce a brief English sentence that would be considered grammatically as category: unacceptable\\nAll categories: OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"What they saw is Bill leave.","rationale":"Here's an example of an unacceptable English sentence: What they saw is Bill leave."},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: a is twice as good a workman as b and together they complete a work in 12 days. in how many days a alone can do the work ?\\nOptions: a. 32, b. 33, c. 34, d. 35, e. 36","target":"e","rationale":"The given problem can be expressed as equation:\\n(1/a + 1/b) = 1/12\\n=> (1/2a + 1/b) = 1/12\\n=> b/(2a) + a/(2a) = 12/(2a).\\nSolving the equation for a, we get 2*36=72. Therefore, option e is correct."},{"source":"He was having a hard time breathing, on top of the mountain it was thin what?\\n\\n[Options]\\n- oxygen\\n- carbon monoxide\\n- abdominal muscles\\n- air\\n- open throat","target":"air","rationale":"The air on top of the mountain is usually thin. Thin air can cause heart rate to drop. Drop in heart rate leads to difficult breathing."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate objects to the associated rooms is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates object A to room B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate room for the given object C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ndesk : office. shower : ?","target":"bathroom","rationale":"A desk is placed in an office and a shower is installed in the bathroom."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as unacceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"This building is than that one.","rationale":"Here's an example of a short sentence that is linguistically unacceptable: This building is than that one."},{"source":"Pick the option in line with common sense to answer the question.\\nQuestions: Whether it's popped, grilled, or canned people like to what?\\nOptions:\\n- expect to die\\n- believe in god\\n- stay in\\n- watch movies\\n- eat corn","target":"eat corn","rationale":"In the question, it states that people like to eat corn. This is the only option in line with common sense and can be used as a proper answer for this type of question."},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Sanskrit:\\n\\nSanskrit has greatly influenced the languages of India that grew from its vocabulary and grammatical base; for instance, Hindi is a \\"Sanskritised register\\" of the Khariboli dialect. All modern Indo-Aryan languages, as well as Munda and Dravidian languages, have borrowed many words either directly from Sanskrit (tatsama words), or indirectly via middle Indo-Aryan languages (tadbhava words). Words originating in Sanskrit are estimated at roughly fifty percent of the vocabulary of modern Indo-Aryan languages, as well as the literary forms of Malayalam and Kannada. Literary texts in Telugu are lexically Sanskrit or Sanskritised to an enormous extent, perhaps seventy percent or more.\\n\\nFrom what dialect is Hindi descended?","target":"Khariboli","rationale":"The context states that the Hindi language is a \\"Sanskritised register\\" of the Khariboli dialect. The word \\"\\"register\\"\\" means different forms or variety, so this statement implies that Sanskrit has greatly influenced the development and form of Hindi.\\n\\nThus, based on these statements made in the paragraph above from what dialect is Hindi descended?\\""},{"source":"\\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). Given a prompt and two responses, identify which response is the type of \\"yes, and\\". Indicate your answer by 'Response 1' if the first response is correct, otherwise 'Response 2'.  Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange.\\n\\nPrompt: Bobby, do you want to get in the dumpster with me? \\n Response 1: Yeah, I need the sun or the cough comes and the rages come. \\n Response 2: Sure.  I'm curious as to what it feels like.","target":"Response 2","rationale":"The prompt is whether Bobby wants to get in the dumpster.  Response 1 is not a \\"yes, and\\" because it does not expand on the line of thought implied by the prompt.  Response 2 implies that Bobby has been curious about getting into a dumpster, which expands on the topic of getting into said dumpster."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people.'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. You have to classify if there exist more than 2 unique emotions in conversation. If there are more than 2 unique emotions present in the conversation, the output should be classified as '1' else it should be '0'\\n\\nPerson1:     Are you saying you saw an eagle ? There are no eagles here . \\nPerson2: Yes , I saw one . Believe me . \\nPerson1:     You must have seen some other kind of bird .","target":"0","rationale":"The conversation only contains two emotions: 'saying' and 'believe'. Hence, it is classified as '0'."},{"source":"EXAM\\n1. Answer by yes or no.\\n\\nDocument: Wynn Las Vegas -- Wynn Las Vegas, often simply referred to as Wynn, is a luxury resort and casino located on the Las Vegas Strip in Paradise, Nevada. The US$2.7-billion resort is named after casino developer Steve Wynn and is the flagship property of Wynn Resorts. The resort covers 215 acres (87 ha). It is located at the northeast corner of Las Vegas Boulevard and Sands Avenue, directly across The Strip from the Fashion Show Mall.\\nQuestion: does the wynn las vegas have a casino?","target":"Yes","rationale":"Yes, the Wynn Las Vegas has a casino. The document states that it is \\"a luxury resort and casino\\".\\nSo answer must be Yes."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\nlogan be cool and not a fool and he splash out the whole pool","target":"elementary","rationale":"The vocabulary and grammar used in the poem indicate that it was written by a person in elementary school. The poem uses simple words such as \\"cool\\" and \\"fool\\", which are common among younger students, while the use of prepositions is incorrect. The phrase, \\"he splash out the whole pool\\", is grammatically incorrect but common among younger children; this phrase should be written as \\"...he splashed out...\\" or \\"...splashes out...\\""},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5. Your job is to generate a title for the story that makes complete sense. The title must be short, with less than three words, use simple language, and include the main topic of the story.\\n\\nSentence 1: Tom heard a noise when he was driving around. Sentence 2: It came from his engine. Sentence 3: Tom didn't bother to ever get it checked. Sentence 4: After a while his car broke down completely. Sentence 5: Tom's engine was nearly destroyed.","target":"Engine Noise","rationale":"The story describes a man's car breaking down due to an engine problem. The title should reflect this, and \\"Engine Noise\\" describes the problem that caused the breakdown."},{"source":"Write a brief sentence.","target":"A man is giving concert.","rationale":"For example, the sentence \\"A man is giving concert.\\""},{"source":"Indicate the presence of numerical data in the abstract (whether numerical data plays a key role in medical records), solely using the information from the abstract.\\n\\nAbstract: To determine whether sensitivity of muscle characteristics and aerobic performances to endurance training was genotype-dependent, 6 pairs of monozygotic (MZ) twins, 21 +/- 4 yr of age (mean +/- SD), took part in a 15-wk ergocycle endurance training program. Tests were performed before and after 7 and 15 weeks of training. A biopsy of the vastus lateralis muscle was obtained for the determination of fiber type composition and activities of creatine kinase, hexokinase, phosphofructokinase, lactate dehydrogenase, malate dehydrogenase, 3-hydroxyacyl CoA dehydrogenase, and oxoglutarate dehydrogenase. Maximal oxygen uptake was measured with a progressive maximal ergocycle test, while endurance performance was determined as the total work output during a 90-min maximal ergocycle test. Results indicated that maximal oxygen uptake X kg-1 and endurance performance X kg-1 increased significantly (14 and 31%, respectively) with training, and intra-pair resemblance (intra-class) in response to 15 wk of training ranged from 0.65 to 0.83. Hexokinase (31%), phosphofructokinase (37%), lactate dehydrogenase (21%), malate dehydrogenase (31%), and 3-hydroxyacyl CoA dehydrogenase (60%) were significantly increased with training whereas no mean change in fiber-type proportions, oxoglutarate dehydrogenase and creatine kinase activities and the phosphofructokinase/oxoglutarate dehydrogenase ratio was observed. Similarity within twin pairs in the response to enzyme activities was mainly detected in the second half of the training program. The present results confirm, therefore, that both maximal oxygen uptake and endurance performance responses to training are largely genotype-dependent.(ABSTRACT TRUNCATED AT 250 WORDS) \\nQuestion: Does the abstract contain any numerical data?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The abstract includes data from multiple experiments to demonstrate the effect of 15-week endurance training on aerobic performances (including maximal oxygen uptake and 90-minute ergocycle test performance), muscle characteristics (fiber type composition, enzyme activities) in 6 pairs of monozygotic twins. In addition, it reports numerical values related to changes in various parameters before and after 7 weeks or 15 weeks of training. For example: \\"Maximal oxygen uptake X kg(-1) increased significantly by 14%\\", \\"Endurance performance X kg(-1) was improved with 31%\\". So the answer is ‚ÄúYes‚Äù"},{"source":"Coming off their win against the Steelers, the Chiefs went on the road for an AFC West rivalry match against the San Diego Chargers. In the first quarter the Chiefs trailed early as QB Philip Rivers got a 19-yard touchdown pass to TE Antonio Gates. The Chiefs would reply to tie the game with QB Matt Cassel making a 7-yard touchdown pass to WR Chris Chambers, until they fell back again with RB LaDainian Tomlinson getting a 1-yard touchdown run, then Rivers hooking up with Gates again on a 15-yard touchdown pass, then DB Paul Oliver returned a fumble 40 yards for a touchdown. In the third quarter the Chiefs' struggle continued as RB LaDainian Tomlinson got a 3-yard touchdown run. They tried to come back with RB Jamaal Charles getting a 2-yard touchdown run, but the Chargers would pull away with kicker Nate Kaeding making a 55-yard field goal. In the fourth quarter the problem got worse when a penalty on Matt Cassel was enforced in the end zone for a safety, giving the Chargers 2 points. The final score was made when Kaeding booted a 23-yard field goal.\\n\\nBased on the above article, answer a question. What team scored first in the first quarter?","target":"Chargers","rationale":"The article says that \\"In the first quarter, the Chiefs trailed early as QB Philip Rivers got a 19-yard touchdown pass to TE Antonio Gates\\". Therefore we could conclude that Chargers scored first in the 1st quarter."},{"source":"Q: Mendel‚Äôs observation of pea plants also included many crosses that involved multiple traits, which prompted him to formulate the principle of this?\\n\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- independent contain\\n\\n- independent texture\\n\\n- dependent evolution\\n\\n- independent assortment\\n\\nA:","target":"independent assortment","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"independent assortment\\"."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of sexual explicitness. If the comment is sexually explicit output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nWell, look at the bright side.   At least he hasn't introduced another  bill keeping comprehensive sex education out of schools, women from making choices over their own bodies, or transgenders from using pubwic westwooms like some a doze cwazy chwist'n wepubwicans doo.   However, they DO have their problem priorities, don't they?   Johnson's seems to be that poor people exist.","target":"No","rationale":"The given comment does not contain any sexual explicitness. There are also no references to sex or sexuality, and the words \\"sex\\" and \\"sexual education\\" appear in terms of teaching health-related knowledge at schools. The answer is therefore No"},{"source":"The task is to generate the correct answer for a given math problem.\\n\\nProblem: how many multiples of 4 are there between 12 and 92 , inclusive ?","target":"21","rationale":"Multiples of 4 between 12 and 92 are: 12, 16, 20, 24, 28, 32,... 80. There are total 21 multiples."},{"source":"Read the following article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: In the late 1970's,many people in North America turned their attention to environmental problems ,and new steel -- and -- glass skyscrapers were widely criticized. Some ecologists  pointed out that a number of tall buildings in a city often overburden public transportation.\\nSkyscrapers are also _ of electric power and water. In just one recent year, the addition of 17 million square feet of skyscraper office space in New York City itself has already raised the top daily demand for electricity by 120, 000 kw -- enough to supply the entire city of Albany in New York area for a single day.\\nGlass--walled skyscrapers can also be especially wasteful. The heat loss ,or gain, through a wall of half  inch plate glass is more than ten times that through a typical ordinary wall filled with bricks or board. In order to decrease the pressure on heating and air -- conditioning equipment, builders of skyscrapers have begun to use double--layered glass ,and reflective glasses coated with silver or gold mirror films that could reduce glare  as well as heat gain. However, mirror -- walled skyscrapers may raise the temperature of the surrounding air and affect neighboring buildings as well.\\nSkyscrapers put a severe pressure on a city's sanitation  facilities, too. If fully occupied, the towers just within the central area of New York would alone produce 2. 25 million gallons of waste water each year^--as much as the city size of Stanford, Connecticut, which has a population of more than 109,000.\\nQuestion: Glass walls of skyscrapers are specially mentioned in order to   _  .\\n- show how skyscrapers manage to lessen their pressure\\n- explain why skyscrapers can control its air conditions\\n- describe further how wasteful skyscrapers could be\\n- present the stability of skyscrapers in modern buildings","target":"describe further how wasteful skyscrapers could be","rationale":"The article begins by criticizing skyscrapers for their negative environmental impact. The author then describes the many ways in which tall buildings place an enormous strain on a city‚Äôs natural resources and infrastructure, such as electricity, water supply, sewage treatment plants etc.. Despite these shortcomings of modern skyscraper design, builders are increasingly using environmentally-friendly techniques to minimize waste and increase efficiency. However, only glass walls are mentioned as examples of how wasteful some aspects of traditional building construction can be due to excessive heat loss or gain through large sections of plate glass windows. Therefore the answer is \\"describe further how wasteful skyscrapers could be\\"."},{"source":"For example, more people on the Earth means more people contributing to global warming and pollution.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are more or less ):\\n\\n\\nAngel traveled to New York, and experienced more or less pollution?","target":"more","rationale":"The paragraph mentions that more people on the Earth means more pollution. Based on this, it can be inferred that Angel traveled to New York and experienced ''more'' pollution than in his hometown because there are more people in a city like New York compared to his home town."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an ambiguous question/query (which can be answered in more than one way) and a clarification statement to understand the query more precisely. Your task to classify that if the given clarification accurately clarifies the given query or not and based on that provide 'Yes' or 'No'.\\n\\nQuery: Tell me about Pocono \\n Clarification: what would you like to know about vldl levels","target":"No","rationale":"The query asks for information about the Pocono region of Pennsylvania. The clarification statement is ambiguous, but refers to a medical condition called VLDL levels. Since the clarification does not clarify the query, the answer is 'No'."},{"source":"In this task, you're shown a three-part story, with a beginning, middle, and ending. Your job is to slightly modify the middle part, so that the whole story becomes unlikely, improbable, or inconsistent. Generated sentences must minimally alter the given middle, with at most 4 new words added/existing words removed. Your sentence should be grammatically and syntactically correct. Also stick to the context of the given story. For example, if the story talks about \\"doctors\\", you can talk about \\"health\\" or \\"diagnosis\\", but don't mention \\"aliens\\". Avoid introducing any extra/irrelevant information, and use names instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible. Avoid simply negating the original middle, for example:  \\"She likes cakes.\\" is changed to \\"She doesn't like cakes.\\"\\n\\nBeginning: It was a few weeks after settling into a new house. Middle: I could not find my cat. Ending: After 13 days a dirty, skinny cat was finally home.","target":"I could not find my dog","rationale":"The beginning of the story is about a cat, so the middle of the story needs to be about the cat as well. The original middle sentence states that \\"I could not find my cat\\", which is grammatically correct and contextual. However, \\"I could not find my dog\\" changes it by stating that a dog is missing instead of a cat, making the whole story illogical."},{"source":"What are the worst examples of false advertising you've seen? Did you fall prey to their claims?\\nRather that vouch for myself - my story is trite, and not particularly interesting - I'll relay the tale one of my nurses shared with me when I was laid up in the hospital for a few weeks. Call her R.\\nR was from an Eastern European country. We chit-chatted a lot, while she was taking my blood pressure readings and stuff. Lots of fun stories! But she relayed to me one of her first U.S. memories:\\nShe wanted to lose weight. She was impressed by some things the U.S. had to offer - \\"you have actual nutritional information on everything!\\" - and thus figured everything she encountered was on the level. And she found a \\"miracle cure\\" company who was along those lines! \\"These are AWESOME miracle shoe inserts! Wear them, and the pounds will melt away!\\" She saved her pennies and dimes; she sprung for the inserts.\\nShe received them... and they were shoe inserts; that much was true. But then there was their documentation: \\"using these insoles, combined with a 1200 calorie-per-day diet....\\" Like a 1200-calorie diet won't likely involve weight-loss, no matter what else you did, shoe inserts aside. The inserts did nothing, obviously. It was a sham.\\nAt which point she knew she was snookered, but really had no recourse. She wasn't explicit about it, but I got the feeling that it was a leading factor towards her chosen profession. \\"I might not have been the most sage medical person ever, but I'm gonna rectify that, and if ever I hear someone falling for that sort of gambit again, I'll be there to nip those sentiments in the bud with my own anecdotes.\\" Which is awesome.\\nI still feel for her. I wish I had contact information, so I could touch base, and express those thoughts personally. But that's the most personally resonant version of false advertising affecting someone that I've seen.\\nAccording to the above context, answer the following question.\\nWhy is the patient in the hospital?","target":"not enough information","rationale":"The context indicates that the patient is in the hospital, and they are talking to a nurse. However, there is no mention of why or how long this person has been in the hospital for.\\nBased on what we know from the context, it's not possible to accurately determine why this person was admitted into a hospital. Therefore, option 3 \\"not enough information\\" would be correct here as everything else provided could just be speculation based on assumptions made by other people who have encountered similar circumstances - but which may still vary depending on personal experiences with different hospitals/nurses."},{"source":"In this task, you need to replace a letter in the sentence with another given letter.\\n\\nSentence: 'these chefs are making facial and finger gestures'. Replace the letter 'l' with 'i' in the sentence.","target":"these chefs are making faciai and finger gestures","rationale":"In the given sentence, there are two letters 'l' at the 24th index and 32nd index. The 24th index is replaced with an 'i', so it becomes these chefs are making faciai and finger gestures."},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: What kind of movies do you enjoy and why? , USER: I like historical drama movies. I like them because they're based on true stories, and they have usually have a great screenplay, and they can't make a sequel out of those. , ASSISTANT: Is there a particular film you enjoy? , USER: I like the movie Schindler's List and I like the movie Lincoln. , ASSISTANT: What did you like about that kind of film? , USER: I liked them As I said, I liked them for the fact that they're based on true stories. I liked that they had very good acting, and, classify_text: They were just very very intriguing.","target":"USER","rationale":"The \\"classify_text\\" is a follow up to the previous sentence. It is not a question, and therefore would have been authored by the \\"USER\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i, j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to find all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, reverse the order in which they occur, and then concatenate them to output the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j. Perform the operations in order, i.e., do not concatenate the elements and then reverse the string.\\n\\n1, 5, ['M', '1925', 'O', 'h', '1231', '4919', '1585']","target":"1231hO1925M","rationale":"Given the list ['M', '1925', 'O', 'h', '1231', '4919', '1585'], we need to find the elements within the range 1 ~ 5.\\\\n1. The 1st element is M.\\\\n2. The 2nd element is 1925.\\\\n3. The 3rd element is O\\\\n4. The 4th element is h\\\\n5. The 5th element is 1231\\\\n\\n\\nAfter finding all of the elements, we need to reverse their order:\\\\n'the reversed order: 1231hO1925M'"},{"source":"In this task you will be given two lists of numbers and you need to calculate the intersection between these two lists. The intersection between two lists is another list where every element is common between the two original lists. If there are no elements in the intersection, answer with an empty list. Your list of numbers must be inside brackets. Sort the numbers in your answer in an ascending order, that is, no matter what the order of the numbers in the lists is, you should put them in your answer in an ascending order.\\n\\n[7, 9, 6, 1, 5, 4, 2, 2, 9, 8] , [8, 3, 10, 8, 5, 7, 8, 4, 9, 3]","target":"[4, 5, 7, 8, 9]","rationale":"The intersection between the two lists is [4, 5, 7, 8, 9]. The numbers are already sorted in an ascending order."},{"source":"Washington (CNN) -- President Barack Obama spoke Thursday with the leaders of France, Italy and the United Kingdom on coordinating an international response to the crisis in Libya, the White House said. In separate phone conversations with French President Nicolas Sarkozy, Italian Prime Minister Silvio Berlusconi and British Prime Minister David Cameron, Obama \\"expressed his deep concern with the Libyan government's use of violence which violates international norms and every standard of human decency, and discussed appropriate and effective ways for the international community to immediately respond,\\" the White House statement said. While some critics say the Obama administration has been slow to react to the deteriorating situation in Libya, the statement said Thursday's discussions were to \\"coordinate our urgent efforts to respond to developments and ensure that there is appropriate accountability.\\"\\n@highlight\\nNEW: The White House says the leaders discussed a coordinated response\\n@highlight\\nThe French Embassy says Obama discussed planned measures\\n@highlight\\nThe White House spokesman says all options are under consideration\\n@highlight\\nU.S. goals are to protect Americans and halt attacks on Libyan people \\nA statement by the French Embassy said Obama discussed steps the @placeholder plans to take regarding Libya in his phone call with Sarkozy. \\nWhat could the \\"@placeholder\\" be? Americans, Barack Obama, British, CNN, David Cameron, Embassy, France, French, Italian, Italy, Libya, Libyan, Nicolas Sarkozy, Obama, Silvio Berlusconi, U.S., United Kingdom, Washington, White House?","target":"Americans","rationale":"The text contains a sentence \\"@placeholder plans to take regarding Libya in his phone call with Sarkozy.\\" This makes it clear that the placeholder is referring to Americans."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nAvery entered the master_bedroom. Isabella entered the master_bedroom. The lettuce is in the green_basket. Isabella exited the master_bedroom. Avery moved the lettuce to the blue_container. Isabella entered the attic. Mia entered the attic. The persimmon is in the red_suitcase. Mia exited the attic. Isabella moved the persimmon to the red_cupboard. Avery entered the attic. Mia entered the attic. The cucumber is in the red_cupboard. Phone rang. Mia exited the attic. Avery moved the cucumber to the red_suitcase. Olivia entered the attic. Phone rang. Avery is in the attic. The cucumber is in the red_suitcase. Avery exited the attic. Olivia moved the cucumber to the red_cupboard. Where was the cucumber at the beginning?","target":"red_cupboard","rationale":"The cucumber was in the red_cupboard at the beginning."},{"source":"In this task, you're given four sentences of a story written in natural language. The given story is not complete and your job is to complete the story by selecting one of the end sentence choices from (A) and (B), such that the story does not sound complete and coherent, i.e., select an incorrect end sentence.\\n\\nSentence1: Hailey was participating in her school marathon. Sentence2: However she forgot to bring her running shoes. Sentence3: Hailey was still determined. Sentence4: She asked her teacher if she could borrow her's for the day. \\n (A) The teacher admired Haley's passion and agreed. (B) Hailey was weak willed.","target":"B","rationale":"The fourth sentence states that the teacher lends her running shoes to Hailey. As a result, the correct choice for the final sentence is A because it tells us that the teacher admires Hailey's passion and agrees to lend her shoes to Hailey. Choice B implies that Hailey is weak willed, which negatively affects how others view her and makes it less likely for someone to help her out in this situation."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nRevenue grew 1 percent to euro742 .2 million US$ 964 million from euro735 million .","target":"positive","rationale":"Financial news states that revenue grew 1% to 742.2 million euros from 735 million euros, which is positive news for the company."},{"source":"Pick the most correct option to answer the following question.\\n\\nMalaria is a common disease in many countries. What is the cause of this disease?\\n\\nOptions:\\n\\n- A: a virus\\n\\n- B: a bacterium\\n\\n- C: a fungus\\n\\n- D: a parasite","target":"D","rationale":"Malaria is caused by the parasite Plasmodium, that enters a person's body through the bite of an infected mosquito. The disease is transmitted to humans via mosquitoes carrying this protozoan and feeding on human blood.\\nThe available options are A: virus, B: bacterium, C: fungus, D: parasite. Since malaria is caused by a parasite (Plasmodium), option D correctly identifies the cause of malaria and should be selected as the most correct answer for this question.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\nrecognize","target":"unknown","rationale":"The antonym of 'recognize' is 'unknown'."},{"source":"A friend asked me to answer this question: Whose father disowns her?, using the article: The year is 1965, and 10-year-old Sandra and her parents, Abraham and Sannie, are white Afrikaners. Her parents are shopkeepers in a remote area of the Eastern Transvaal and, despite Sandra's mixed-race appearance, have lovingly brought her up as their white little girl. Sandra is sent to a boarding school in the neighbouring town of Piet Retief, where her (white) brother Leon is also studying, but parents of other students and teachers complain that she does not belong.\\nShe is examined by State officials, reclassified as coloured, and expelled from the school. Sandra's parents are shocked, but Abraham fights through the courts to have the classification reversed. The story becomes an international scandal and media pressure forces the law to change, so that Sandra is classified as officially white again.\\nBy the time she is 17, Sandra realises she is never going to be accepted by the white community. She falls in love with Petrus, a young black man and the local vegetable seller, and begins an illicit love affair. Abraham threatens to shoot Petrus and disown Sandra. Sannie is torn between her husband's rage and her daughter's predicament. Sandra elopes with Petrus to Swaziland. Abraham alerts the police, and has them arrested and put in prison for the illegal border crossing. Sandra is released by the local magistrate to return home with her parents, but she decides to return to Petrus, as she is pregnant with his child. Her father disowns her., what would be the answer ?","target":"Sandra","rationale":"Based on the article, Sandra's father Abraham disowns her."},{"source":"Which entity is this text about?\\n\\nLinkin Park is an American rock band from Agoura Hills, California. Formed in 1996, the band rose to international fame with their debut album Hybrid Theory (2000), which was certified Diamond by the RIAA in 2005 and multi-Platinum in several other countries. Their following studio album Meteora continued the band's success, topping the Billboard 200 album chart in 2003, and was followed by extensive touring and charity work. Having adapted nu metal and rap metal to a radio-friendly yet densely layered style in Hybrid Theory and Meteora, the band explored other genres on their next studio album, Minutes to Midnight (2007).\\n\\nLinkin Park has sold more than 70 million records. The group's first studio album Hybrid Theory is one of the best-selling albums in the US (10 million copies shipped) and worldwide (27 million copies sold). Billboard estimates that Linkin Park earned US$5 million between May 2011 and May 2012, making them the 40th-highest-paid musical artist. 11 of the band's singles have reached the number one position on Billboard's Alternative Songs chart, the second-most for any artist.  In 2003, MTV2 named Linkin Park the sixth-greatest band of the music video era and the third-best of the new millennium. Billboard ranked Linkin Park No. 19 on the Best Artists of the Decade chart. The band was recently voted as the greatest artist of the 2000s in a Bracket Madness poll on VH1. In 2014, the band was declared as the Biggest Rock Band in the World Right Now by Kerrang!. In 2015, Kerrang! gave \\"In the End\\" and \\"Final Masquerade\\" the top two positions on Kerrang!'s Rock 100 list.  Linkin Park became the first rock band to achieve more than one billion YouTube hits. Linkin Park also became the fifteenth most liked page on Facebook, tenth most liked artist, and most liked group followed by the Black Eyed Peas. Linkin Park's \\"Numb\\" is the third and \\"In the End\\" is the sixth \\"timeless song\\" on Spotify. The two songs making Linkin Park the only artist to have two timeless songs in top ten.  Hybrid Theory by the group is listed in the book 1001 Albums You Must Hear Before You Die, It was also ranked at #11 on Billboard's Hot 200 Albums of the Decade. In addition the album was included in Best of 2001 by Record Collector, The top 150 Albums of the Generation by Rock Sound and 50 Best Rock Albums of the 2000's by Kerrang!. The album Meteora was included in Top 200 Albums of the Decade by Billboard at #36. The album sold 20 million copies worldwide. The collaborated EP Collision Course with Jay-Z, became the second ever EP to top the Billboard 200, going on to sell over 300,000 copies in its first week after Alice in Chains' Jar of Flies in 1994. The album Minutes to Midnight in the United States, the album had the biggest first week sales of 2007 at the time, with 625,000 albums sold. In Canada, the album sold over 50,000 copies in its first week and debuted at number one on the Canadian Albums Chart. Worldwide, the album shipped over 3.3 million copies in its first four weeks of release.  The New York Times' Jon Caramanica commented Linkin Park \\"brought the collision of hard rock and hip-hop to its commercial and aesthetic peak\\" at the beginning of the 2000s. Several rock and non-rock artists have cited Linkin Park as an influence, including Proyecto Eskhata, Of Mice & Men, One Ok Rock, Bishop Nehru, Misono, From Ashes to New, Bring Me the Horizon, Red, Girl on Fire, Manafest, Silento, 3OH!3, The Prom Kings, AJ Tracey, Kiiara, The Chainsmokers, Kevin Rudolf, blackbear, Tokio Hotel, and Stormzy.\\n\\nEntity:","target":"Linkin Park","rationale":"The context provides a detailed description of Linkin Park and their work. The text focuses on the band members, songs they have written, and their achievements. So it is clear that this music group entity is all about Linkin park"},{"source":"Determine the question that you might have asked to get back the following answer for the given context\\nContext: No archaeological evidence that indicates a settlement on the site of today‚Ä≤s city centre prior to the 12th century has been found so far. In antiquity, a Celtic oppidum stood on the Engehalbinsel (peninsula) north of Bern, fortified since the 2nd century BC (late La T√®ne period), thought to be one of the twelve oppida of the Helvetii mentioned by Caesar. During the Roman era, there was a Gallo-Roman vicus on the same site. The Bern zinc tablet has the name Brenodor (\\"dwelling of Breno\\"). In the Early Middle Ages, there was a settlement in B√ºmpliz, now a city district of Bern, some 4 km (2 mi) from the medieval city.;\\nAnswer: Early Middle Ages;\\nQuestion:","target":"When was the settlement in Bumpliz close to the medieval city?","rationale":"The above context mentions that there was a settlement in B√ºmpliz, now a city district of Bern, some 4 km (2 mi) from the medieval city. And it says this was during the Early Middle Ages.\\nSo when you might ask: When was the settlement in Bumpliz close to the medieval city?,  \\n\\n\\nthe answer would be: \\nEarly Middle Ages"},{"source":"In this task, you are given the name of an Indian food dish. You need to classify the dish as \\"sweet\\" or \\"spicy\\".\\n\\nKos kootu","target":"spicy","rationale":"Kos kootu is a spicy dish from Tamil Nadu, India."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the physics. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: walking with 4 / 5 of my usual speed , i miss the bus by 3 minutes . what is my usual time ? \\nOptions: a ) 16 min , b ) 26 min , c ) 34 min , d ) 20 min , e ) 12 min","target":"e","rationale":"If walking with \\\\\\\\(4/5\\\\\\\\) of my usual speed makes me miss the bus by 3 minutes, then walking at my usual speed would have made me miss the bus by \\\\\\\\(3 \\\\cdot \\\\frac { 5 } { 4 } = 15/4\\\\\\\\) minutes. If I walk for T minutes at my usual speed and miss the bus, then it takes me a total of \\\\\\\\(T + 15/4\\\\\\\\) minutes to reach the bus stop. Since that's how long it takes to reach if I'm late, that must be how long it takes to reach if I'm on time. Thus my usual time is \\\\\\\\(T + 15/4 = T + 3\\\\cdot \\\\frac { 5 } { 12 } = T + 5/12 = 12T / 12 + 5 /12\\\\\\\\). The only option whose denominator is divisible by 12 is (e), so that's our answer."},{"source":"Eddie Vedder (born Edward Louis Severson; December 23, 1964) is an American musician, singer and songwriter best known as a member of the rock band Pearl Jam, with whom he performs lead vocals and is one of three guitarists. He is known for his powerful baritone vocals. He also appeared as a guest vocalist in Temple of the Dog, the one-off tribute band dedicated to the late singer Andrew Wood.\\n\\nChoose your answer: based on the paragraph above can we conclude that \\"Pearl Jam has 6 members total.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nI think the answer is","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"The passage only talks about Eddie Vedder, so we cannot determine the number of members in Pearl Jam. So, the answer is \\"It's impossible to say\\"."},{"source":"I am testing my students' logic.\\nWhat is the answer they should choose between \\"snow slope\\" and \\"dry soil\\"?\\nLogic test: Bailey went quickly down the snow slope on snow skis, but went slow and bumpy on dry soil. The dry soil has (A) higher resistance (B) lower resistance","target":"snow slope","rationale":"The logic test here is asking if the dry soil has a higher or lower resistance to Bailey going down it on snow skis. Since we are told that he went slow and bumpy over the dry soil, but quickly down the snow slope, this means there was more friction for him when skiing over the dry soil (which is made up of dirt). Friction creates resistance between two objects as they rub against one another; in this case, Bailey's skis rubbing against the ground beneath them. Therefore, with greater friction comes greater resistance - which tells us that \\"dry soil\\" has a higher level of resistance than \\"snow slope\\".\\nSo answer will be: Answer B"},{"source":"\\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). Given a prompt and two responses, identify which response is the type of \\"yes, and\\". Indicate your answer by 'Response 1' if the first response is correct, otherwise 'Response 2'.  Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange.\\n\\nPrompt: Mr. and Mr. Popple, meet Jimmy. \\n Response 1: You are her friend, Jimmy. Here's some water. \\n Response 2: OK. It's traditional showbiz ware. It's a striped blazer and bow tie, straw boater and a cane. I'm not sure why that makes me an asshole.","target":"Response 1","rationale":"Response 1 is the correct response for a \\"Yes, and\\" as it accepts what the prompt says (\\"Mr. and Mr. Popple, meet Jimmy\\") and then expands on it with an additional statement (\\"You are her friend, Jimmy. Here's some water\\")."},{"source":"Warmer molecules vibrate faster than cooler ones.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are faster or slower ):\\n\\n\\nEric decreased the heat of the molecules. They now vibrate faster or slower?","target":"slower","rationale":"The passage states that warmer molecules vibrate faster than cooler ones. When Eric decreased the heat of the molecules, they cooled down and thus slowed their vibrations to move slower."},{"source":"What is the following passage about?\\nSeveral countries have established their national churches, linking the ecclesiastical structure with the state. Jurisdictions where a Protestant denomination has been established as a state religion include several Nordic countries; Denmark (including Greenland), the Faroe Islands (its church being independent since 2007), Iceland and Norway have established Evangelical Lutheran churches. Tuvalu has the only established church in Reformed tradition in the world, while Tonga‚Äîin the Methodist tradition. The Church of England is the officially established religious institution in England, and also the Mother Church of the worldwide Anglican Communion.","target":"Protestantism","rationale":"The context talks about Protestant denominations and the relation between church and state. It also mentions establishments of churches linked to states in several countries including Denmark, Greenland, Faroe Islands, Iceland and Norway as well as a few others that are all Lutheran or Evangelical churches.\\nIt can be concluded from this information that the passage is attempting to say something about Protestantism leading us towards choosing option (1) above."},{"source":"I am testing my students' logic.\\nWhat is the answer they should choose between \\"gravel\\" and \\"cement floor\\"?\\nLogic test: Tim is driving his golf cart down the driveway and into the garage. He realizes that the golf cart puts off more heat when it travels over the gravel driveway than when it does when he pulls onto the cement floor of the garage. This is because the _____ is rougher. (A) cement floor (B) gravel","target":"cement floor","rationale":"The golf cart puts off more heat when it travels over the gravel driveway than when it does on cement floor. This is because a rougher surface produces friction, and therefore generates more heat energy (this can be tested with tire spinning). The gravel has bigger pieces of rock that are not as tightly packed together compared to the smaller rocks in concrete which are held together by other materials like sand or tar. So while both surfaces generate some amount of friction, gravel will produce greater amounts of friction due to its large rocky components producing many areas for potential contact between itself and another object such as tires.\\n\\nSo answer: cement floor"},{"source":"The Ninth Ward or 9th Ward is a distinctive region of New Orleans, Louisiana, which is located in the easternmost downriver portion of the city. It is geographically the largest of the seventeen Wards of New Orleans. On the south, the Ninth Ward is bounded by the Mississippi River. On the western or \\"upriver\\" side, the Ninth Ward is bounded by (going from the River north to Lake Pontchartrain) Franklin Avenue, then Almonaster Avenue, then People's Avenue. From the north end of People's Avenue the boundary continues on a straight line north to Lake Pontchartrain; this line is the boundary between the Ninth and the city's Eighth Ward. The Lake forms the north and northeastern end of the ward. Saint Bernard Parish is the boundary to the southeast, Lake Borgne farther southeast and east, and the end of Orleans Parish to the east at the Rigolets.\\n\\nWhere is the 9th ward in new orleans?","target":"the easternmost downriver portion of the city","rationale":"The relevant sentence in the passage is: The Ninth Ward or 9th Ward is a distinctive region of New Orleans, Louisiana, which is located in the easternmost downriver portion of the city."},{"source":"Alien Planet starts out with an interstellar spacecraft named Von Braun , leaving Earth's orbit .  Traveling at 20 % the speed of light , it reaches Darwin IV in 42 years .  Upon reaching orbit , it deploys the Darwin Reconnaissance Orbiter , Which looks for potential landing sites for the probes .  The first probe , Balboa , explodes along with its lifting body transport during entry , because one of its wings failed to unfold .  Two backup probes , Leonardo da Vinci and Isaac Newton , successfully land on the planet , and learn much about its bizarre indigenous lifeforms , including an apparently sapient species .  The robotic probes sent out to research on Darwin IV are called Horus Probes .  Each Horus probe consists of an { { convert } } long inflatable , hydrogen-filled balloon , Which is covered with solar receptors , a computer \` brain ' , a \` head ' covered with sensors , and several smaller robots that can be sent to places too dangerous for the probes themselves .  The probes have a limited degree of artificial intelligence , very similar to the \` processing power ' of a 4-year-old .  All the real thinking is done by a supercomputer in the orbiting Von Braun .  The probes are programmed with different personalities ; Ike is more cautious , while Leo is the risk-taker .  The two probes are also equipped with a holographic message that will be projected to any sentient life found on Darwin .  After the two probes inflate their gas-bags , they encounter a voracious Arrowtongue and watch it pursue a Gyrosprinter . \\n\\nQuestion: How long does it take for Alien Planet to reach Darwin IV?\\nI think \\"2 years\\" is a valid answer. Could you confirm? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"The answer is No. In the question, it says \\"it reaches Darwin IV in 42 years\\", which means that Alien Planet takes a total of 42 years to reach Darwin IV."},{"source":"The input is a tweet which can be Hate Speech or Offensive. Given such a tweet, output a phrase from the tweet that makes it hate speech or offensive. The output should contain only one such phrase. The output has to be from within the tweet itself. Do not generate words or phrases not present in the tweet.\\n\\nas if you need more evidence to see how absolutely retarded flat earthers are","target":"retarded","rationale":"The tweet is offensive because of the use of the word \\"retarded\\". The term \\"retarded\\" has been used in the past to describe people with intellectual disabilities, which is offensive and dehumanizing."},{"source":"FINAL EXAM\\n\\nQuestion 1. What is the rebranded name of the racing series now that was won in 2016 by the Prema Powerteam?","target":"FIA Formula 2 Championship","rationale":"The answer is based on the information provided in the question.\\nAccording to Wikipedia page of 2016 FIA Formula 2 Championship, it was won by Prema Powerteam and this series was rebranded from GP2 Series."},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question Hoping to break their current losing streak the Chargers played on home ground for an AFC duel with the Titans. In the first quarter the Chargers trailed early when the Chargers' punt was blocked by Nick Schommer out of bounds for a safety. The Chargers replied with FB Mike Tolbert getting a 1-yard TD run. The Chargers fell behind with kicker Rob Bironas nailing a 21-yard field goal, followed in the second quarter by QB Vince Young completing a 1-yard TD pass to TE Craig Stevens. The Chargers struggled further with RB Chris Johnson getting a 29-yard TD run. The Chargers then went on a scoring rally with RB Ryan Mathews making a 7-yard TD run, followed in the third quarter by kicker Kris Brown making a 34-yard field goal. Then QB Philip Rivers completed a 48-yard TD pass to TE Antonio Gates, and then Brown made a 36-yard field goal. The lead was narrowed with Young finding WR Nate Washington on a 71-yard TD pass (with a failed 2-point conversion), but couldn't do anything after Rivers got a 13-yard TD pass to RB Darren Sproles (PAT aborted).\\nHow many yards was the longest field goal?","target":"36","rationale":"In the article, it is mentioned that \\"Kris Brown made a 36-yard field goal.\\" Therefore we could conclude that Kris Brown's longest field goal was 36 yards."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and a question, you would be asked to create the answer which is contained in the sentence provided.\\n\\nSentence: Birds evolved from reptile ancestors. Question: Birds evolved from what type of ancestor?","target":"reptile","rationale":"The answer to the question is contained in the sentence that was provided. The sentence states, \\"Birds evolved from reptile ancestors\\". Therefore, the answer should be \\"reptile\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a prompt from a judicial decision and multiple holding statements derived from citations following text in a legal decision.  Holdings represent the governing legal rule when the law is applied to a particular set of facts. There are five answer choices for each citing text. The correct answer is the holding statement that corresponds to the citing text. The four incorrect answers are other holding statements. You should find the correct option. There is a <HOLDING> token in the position of the citing text prompt where the holding statement was extracted.\\n\\ntheir motion for summary judgment. We review a district court‚Äôs decision to deny a motion for summary judgment for an abuse of discretion. Romstadt v. Allstate Ins. Co., 59 F.3d 608, 615 (6th Cir.1995). Ortiz v. Jordan, ‚Äî U.S. ‚Äî, 131 S.Ct. 884, 889, 178 L.Ed.2d 703 (2011), precludes our consideration of most of the issues defendants raise with respect to their motions for summary judgment and to dismiss. But because Ortiz leaves open the possibility that cases ‚Äúinvolving] ... [only] disputes about the substance and clarity of pre-existing law‚Äù may still be considered, Id. at 892, we briefly consider two legal arguments for summary judgment on the state law claims. See also Owatonna Clinic-Mayo Health Sys. v. Med. Protective Co. of Fort Wayne, Ind., 639 F.3d 806, 809-10 (8th Cir.2011) (<HOLDING>); Fireman‚Äôs Fund Ins. Co. v. North Pacific Ins. \\n Holding statements: (A) holding that we will not review the pretrial denial of a motion for summary judgment after a full trial and judgment on the merits (B) recognizing that ortiz did not address the issue of whether a denial of a summary judgment motion was appealable after a final judgment if the denial was based on a legal question rather than on the existence of material facts in issue (C) holding the denial of a motion for summary judgment on an issue which is later submitted to the jury is not reviewable (D) holding that we will not review under any standard the pretrial denial of a motion for summary judgment after a full trial and final judgment on the merits (E) holding that the existence of genuine issues of material facts render not appealable a pretrial denial of summary judgment on the issue of qualified immunity","target":"(B)","rationale":"The holding statement cited in support of this argument is \\"holding that ortiz did not address the issue of whether a denial of a summary judgment motion was appealable after a final judgment if the denial was based on a legal question rather than on the existence of material facts in issue\\" which is option (B)."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, a context passage, and four options which are terms from the passage. After reading a passage, you will get a brief understanding of the terms. Your job is to determine by searching and reading further information of which term you can answer the question. Indicate your choice as 'a', 'b', 'c', or 'd'. If you think more than one option is plausible, choose the more probable option to help you answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Which of the wrestlers participating in the main feud in WrestleManiaV wrestled longer? Passage:The main feud heading into WrestleMania was between Hulk Hogan and Randy Savage, with the two battling over the WWF World Heavyweight Championship. Hogan and Savage first crossed paths on the Saturday Night's Main Event XII. Savage got a shot at The Honky Tonk Man's Intercontinental Heavyweight Championship but was attacked by The Hart Foundation; Hogan came to Savage's rescue, thus solidifying Savage's face turn. At WrestleMania IV, Savage defeated \\"Million Dollar Man\\" Ted DiBiase in a tournament final to win the vacant WWF World Heavyweight Championship with help from Hogan and Hogan soon after came into the ring to congratulate Savage. Soon after, the duo formed a tag team known as The Mega Powers. They feuded with many heel tag teams throughout the entire year and were a successful team. Mega Powers ruled and dominated the WWF for several months. However, their domination and tag team began to break up in early 1989 as tensions slowly began to build between the two. This all began on the Saturday Night's Main Event XIX, when Hogan was mercilessly beaten by The Twin Towers after his match with Akeem. Savage came out and cleared the ring with a steel chair. Elizabeth took Hogan to the backstage which angered Savage. He thought that he was the third wheel, and this was the beginning of the breakup of Mega Powers, as Savage was angry that his wife Miss Elizabeth was used by Hogan as his manager. He confronted her about the issue but she took Hogan to the backstage. Problems increased further in the Royal Rumble match where Hogan accidentally eliminated Savage as he was trying to eliminate Bad News Brown. On February 3 at The Main Event II, Hogan and Savage faced The Twin Towers (Akeem and The Big Boss Man) in a tag team match that would set up the Mega Powers' breakup. During a key point in the match, Savage was thrown out of the ring onto Elizabeth, knocking her unconscious. Hogan carried her to the back, leaving Savage to fend for himself in the ring against the much larger Akeem and Big Bossman; Hogan eventually returned, but Savage slapped him in the face and took the belt in his hand and turned heel by abandoning Hogan. Despite this, Hogan managed to pick up the win. After Savage attacked Hogan in the medical area of the arena (to seal Savage's heel turn), Hogan challenged Savage to a match for the WWF World Heavyweight Championship at WrestleMania, which Savage accepted.\\n Links: a. Tag team b. Feud (professional wrestling) c. Hulk Hogan d. Royal Rumble (1989)","target":"c","rationale":"The main feud heading into WrestleMania was between Hulk Hogan and Randy Savage, which is mentioned in the passage. The terms are given as links to Wikipedia articles on each of the terms. Therefore, you can search through the Hulk Hogan article to answer this question and find that he wrestled until 2012."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: A person that does not belong to a specific group is called?\\nContext: Furthermore, in the case of far-right, far-left and regionalism parties in the national parliaments of much of the European Union, mainstream political parties may form an informal cordon sanitarian which applies a policy of non-cooperation towards those \\"Outsider Parties\\" present in the legislature which are viewed as 'anti-system' or otherwise unacceptable for government. Cordon Sanitarian, however, have been increasingly abandoned over the past two decades in multi-party democracies as the pressure to construct broad coalitions in order to win elections ‚Äì along with the increased willingness of outsider parties themselves to participate in government ‚Äì has led to many such parties entering electoral and government coalitions.","target":"Outsider","rationale":"A person that does not belong to a specific group is called \\"Outsider\\", so the answer is Outsider."},{"source":"The Government Accountability Institute (GAI) is a conservative nonprofit investigative research organization located in Tallahassee, Florida, The group is known for its involvement with the publication of the investigative books \\"Clinton Cash: The Untold Story of How and Why Foreign Governments and Businesses Helped Make Bill and Hillary Rich\\", Clinton Cash: The Untold Story of How and Why Foreign Governments and Businesses Helped Make Bill and Hillary Rich is  a \\"New York Times\\" bestselling book, released in which year?","target":"2015","rationale":"The book, \\"Clinton Cash: The Untold Story of How and Why Foreign Governments and Businesses Helped Make Bill and Hillary Rich\\" was released in 2015."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and determine if the hypothesis is true. Select from options at the end:\\n\\nBaghdad had announced that it will stop cooperating with UNSCOM completely but indicated that it will not ask for their departure.\\n\\nHypothesis: Baghdad will end it's cooperation with UNSCOM, and wants them to leave.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nThe answer is","target":"no","rationale":"The paragraph clearly states that while the Iraqi government has announced they will stop cooperating with UNSCOM, it also stated Baghdad indicated that it will not ask for their departure. This suggests that both statements cannot be true together and hence the hypothesis is incorrect or false."},{"source":"What cells can perform photosynthesis?\\n- animals\\n- inorganic minerals\\n- flora\\n- critters","target":"flora","rationale":"Photosynthesis is defined as a process where plants and other organisms convert light energy into chemical energy. This conversion takes place in the chloroplasts, which are structures found within plant cells that contain chlorophyll. Since animals do not have chloroplast or chlorophyll they cannot perform photosynthesis; therefore option A can be eliminated from consideration. Likewise, minerals lack cellular structure and thus could not participate in photosynthesis either (option B). The same logic applies to Option D \\"critters\\", making choice C - flora - the only logical answer remaining"},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the physics. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: robert is travelling on his cycle and has calculated to reach point a at 2 p . m . if he travels at 10 km / hr ; he will reach there at 12 noon if he travels at 15 km / hr . at what speed must he travel to reach a at 1 p . m . ? \\nOptions: a ) 17 kmph , b ) 19 kmph , c ) 15 kmph , d ) 12 kmph , e ) 16 kmph","target":"d","rationale":"Total distance = 15 km\\\\nSpeed of travel = 10 kmph (2 p.m. - 12 p.m.) + x kmph (1 p.m. - 12p.m.)\\\\n=> Distance travelled = 10(2 hrs) + x(1 hr)\\\\n=> 2x + 10 = 15\\\\n=> x = 5kmph"},{"source":"I have a new situation: Two twin sisters, Bianca and Rosa, were exposed to high levels of air pollution. While Bianca was exposed mostly to indoor pollution, Rosa was heavily exposed to outdoor pollution.\\n\\nBut I can use this background: Recall that air pollution is due to chemical substances and particles released into the air mainly by human actions. When most people think of air pollution, they think of the pollution outdoors. But it is just as easy to have indoor air pollution. Your home or school classroom probably doesn't get much fresh air. Sealing up your home reduces heating and cooling costs. But this also causes air pollution to stay trapped indoors. And people today usually spend a majority of their time indoors. So exposure to indoor air pollution can become a significant health risk.\\n\\nWhat is an answer for this question: Which sister was more exposed to air pollution because of cutting heating costs?","target":"Bianca","rationale":"Bianca was exposed to mostly indoor pollution and Rosa was heavily exposed to outdoor pollution. So Bianca, because of cutting heating costs, is more likely to be in a house that's not ventilated well and hence has high levels of air pollutions indoors which she would thus have been exposed to compared with Rosa who would've breathed in much lower levels of it due to her exposure being mainly outdoors where there are less instances of cut down on ventilation for cost saving measures & the like."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\npay","target":"tax","rationale":"The antonym of pay is tax since the two words have opposite meanings. Pay means to give money in return for goods or services and tax means a compulsory contribution to state revenue, levied by the government on workers' income and business profits."},{"source":"Yes / no, is the following a verifiable fact?\\n\\"Poles provide spaces for the birds to build nests.\\"","target":"no","rationale":"Poles are actually Polish people and not the street poles."},{"source":"The opening shot of the movie shows Kunti praying for Lord Krishna's protection for the Pandavas .  Lord Krishna consoles Kunti and promises to ever protect the Pandavas and guide them through troubles and problems that may occur in life .  The sons of Pandu and Dhritarashtra progeny break into an argument .  When Duryodhana insults the Pandavas as \`\` dependents '' , Bheema counters by saying that , the Kauravas are the progeny of a widow .  Duryodhana asks Veda Vyasa for an explanation .  He is then told that , since his mother , Gandhari had an astrological defect , she is first married of to a goat and then married to his father .  Duryodhana gains animosity towards the kingdom of Gandhara where the king , the father of his mother Gandhari , rules .  He attacks Gandhara and lays waste of the whole kingdom .  He them imprisons the royal family in his prison .  He gives them only one rice grain per prisoner .  The king of Gandhara then stops everyone from grabbing the little food that is provided .  He says that instead of everyone dying , they could keep at least one of their princes alive .  He chooses Sakuni to be alive .  Sakuni takes an oath that he will do everything he can to destroy the entire Kaurava clan .  He makes magic dice from his father's spinal cord .  The magic dice show exactly the number that he would want .  Duryodhana takes pity on the lone prisoner , Sakuni after the rest of the Gandhara royal family dies in prison out of starvation .  Sakuni joins the evil of coterie of Duryodhana , Karna and Dushyasana . \\nQuestion: Which Gandhara family member joins Duryodhana, Karna, and Dushyasana after surviving the prison? \\nIs it Dhritarashtra?","target":"No","rationale":"The context states that the Gandhara family member who joins Duryodhana, Karna and Dushyasana is Sakuni. So the answer is No."},{"source":"Nanny loved Phil ... Phil lived nanny and I loved my job ... life was good . Well , about two weeks ago a girl I worked with had a baby and I was asked to work full - time while she was on maternity leave . Very quickly my 3day , 30 hour / week job turned into a 6day , 50 hour / week job . This is when things started to fall apart .\\nHow did things fall apart ?\\nPick the best answer from the following options:\\nA. He asked me to take the extra hours because it would make our relationship stronger .\\nB. He thought I would want a baby too if I was filling in for this woman on maternity leave .\\nC. We began to grow apart because we did not have as much time for one another .\\nD. None of the above choices .","target":"C","rationale":"The question is asking how things fell apart for the narrator and their partner. The context suggests that this change occurred because of an increased work schedule, leading to less time spent with each other. \\nSo, the answer is C: We began to grow apart because we did not have as much time for one another."},{"source":"In this task your given two statements in Chinese. You must judge whether the second sentence is the cause or effect of the first one. Label the instances as \\"cause\\" or \\"effect\\" based on your judgment. The sentences are separated by a newline character.\\n\\nÈ´òÈÄüÂÖ¨Ë∑Ø‰∏ä‰∫§ÈÄöÂæàÊã•Êå§„ÄÇ\\nÊàëÁªïÈÅìËÄåË°å„ÄÇ","target":"effect","rationale":"The first sentence says that there is traffic congestion on the highway. The second sentence tells us that the reason I took a detour was because of the traffic congestion. Therefore, this is an instance of 'effect'."},{"source":"Question: How was the British night fighter operations faring?\\n\\nIs \\"German air supremacy at night was also now under threat.\\" the correct answer?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The first line of the passage states that ‚ÄúGerman air supremacy at night ‚Ä¶ was now under threat‚Äù, which means it did exist prior to this point in time. Based on this information, we can conclude that German air supremacy never existed as a result of British night fighter operations. As such, this statement does not contain the correct answer and so is false; thus the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a date in \\"dd/mm/yyyy\\" format. You need to check if the date is valid or not. Return 1 if it is valid, else return 0. A date is valid if the components day(\\"dd\\"), month(\\"mm\\") and year(\\"yyyy\\") are all valid individually. A day(dd) is valid if it: a) lies between 1 and 31 for the months of January, March, May, July, August, October, December, b) lies between 1 and 28 for February on non-leap years and between 1-29 on leap years, c) lies between 1-30 for all other months. A month(mm) is valid if it lies in the range from 1 to 12 as there are 12 months in a year. A year is always valid if it is expressed in the form of \\"yyyy\\".\\n\\n04/06/1946","target":"1","rationale":"The given date \\"04/06/1946\\" is a valid date. The month component is \\"06\\", which lies in the range of 1-12. Therefore, the date is valid and the output should be 1."},{"source":"You are given a mathematical question described with a circumscribed mathematical vocabulary. Questions in this task usually contain some variables (e.g. X, Y), equations (e.g. X+Y=3) and some relationships (X is greater than Y). Often you need to find the value of the variable using equations and relationships. You are also given 4 or 5 answer options (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", \\"E\\"). Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'. LaTeX mathematical format (the standard way to express mathematical expressions in the typesetting software known as LaTeX) is used to express equations. Each question is solvable with high school math knowledge. Give only one answer for each question.\\n\\nLet the \`\`tricate'' of a number x be defined as one-third of the smallest multiple of 3 greater than x. If the tricate of z is 3, which of the following could be the value of z?\\n(A)2 (B)5 (C)7 (D)9 (E)11","target":"C","rationale":"To find the tricate of z, we first identify the smallest multiple of 3 greater than z (call it y). This is accomplished by finding a value that makes y = k * 3 for some integer k. If k = 1, then y - x = 3. Also, dividing by three gives us: (y - x)/3 = 1. Taking one-third of this value gives us: (y - x)/3/3 = 1/3. So the tricate of z is equal to one-third of the difference between y and x, or in other words: Tricate(z) = (y - x)/9\\nSince this problem states that Tricate(z) = 3, then we must have that (y - x)/9=3 => 9*(y-x)=27 => Thirdic(z)=27/9=3\\nThe only valid answer is C because 7 satisfies the equation and all other values do not make sense in context.\\"\\""},{"source":"See the conversation. Can you order me a ride from work?\\nOf course, I would be glad to help.\\nThanks, I need a ride from my workplace to the Pizza Hut on main street.\\nNo problem. What time would you like your ride to arrive?\\n5pm please.\\nok, will this be a one-way trip or will you need a return ride?\\nOnly a ride there for now.\\nCertainly. Can I ask if you have a preference for Uber or Lyft?\\nNo preference, whatever is available.\\nWhat type of car would you like?\\nA standard compact is fine. Maybe an UberX?\\nOk, searching for options now. \\nThank you, just let me know the price please.\\nSure. I'm not showing an UberX available in your area for your time, but there is an UberXL.","target":"That will be fine.","rationale":"The QA system is asking if the user will be ok with an UberXL instead of an UberX since it is not available for the given time and area. Since a compact car is sufficient, and there is no preference for Uber or Lyft, the user will probably not have a problem with getting an XL car as it may be cheaper than other options. Hence, \\"That will be fine.\\" is most likely to come next in this conversation."},{"source":"Populations living in one place form a\\n\\nOptions:\\n- community\\n- system\\n- habitat\\n- species","target":"community","rationale":"The answer is \\"community\\". A population living in one place forms a community."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nstore : car. hospital : ?","target":"ambulance","rationale":"To go to the store, one can take a car. Similarly, one can go to the hospital by taking an ambulance."},{"source":"FINAL EXAM\\n\\nQuestion 1. Deadsoul Tribe includes a song that was from which 1998 black comedy film?","target":"Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas","rationale":"The answer is based on the fact that Fear and Loathing in Las Vegas was a 1998 black comedy film. It also includes a song from Deadsoul Tribe, which is 'Birds of Prey' (track #6)."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\nstationary","target":"mobile","rationale":"The antonym of stationary is mobile."},{"source":"In this task you are given a tweet. You must judge whether the tweet is ironic or not. We define two type of irony for this task (\\"polarity\\",\\"situational\\"). Situational irony happens when a situation fails to meet some expectations. polarity irony happens when irony is achieved by inverting the intended sentence. Label the instances as \\"ironic\\" or \\"not\\" based on your judgment. Note that URLs in the text have been replaced with [Link].\\n\\nWhen j need the mailman to come late, he's here at 8a. When I can't wait for the mail to come? 7p.","target":"ironic","rationale":"The speaker is saying that the mailman comes when they don't want him to, and not when they do. This is ironic because it is opposite of what you would normally expect."},{"source":"US President George W. Bush has indicated he will invite Abbas to the United States for talks, something he never did with Abbas's predecessor, the late Yasser Arafat .\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nQuestion: Can we infer the following?\\nYasser Arafat succeeded Abbas.","target":"no","rationale":"The fact that President Bush did not invite Arafat to the United States for talks does not necessarily mean that he is Abbas's predecessor. It could be merely a coincidence, or something else entirely. And while it would make sense if they were indeed predecessors of each other, this cannot be inferred from the given context alone and requires some background knowledge about Palestinian politics in order to establish such an inference."},{"source":"You are given two sentences. You have to find if there is entailment or agreement of the Hypothesis by the Premise. From the given pair of sentences, you should identify if there is enough information in the Premise to support the claim made in the Hypothesis. The Premise may not exactly be the same as Hypothesis. Your task is to return 'entails' if the premise supports hypothesis else return 'neutral'.\\n\\nPremise: As you increase altitude, the outside air pressure decreases as well, but at a known rate. \\n Hypothesis: Air pressure it decreases as altitude increases.","target":"entails","rationale":"The premise provides information about the relationship between altitude and outside air pressure. The premise states that \\"as you increase altitude, the outside air pressure decreases as well\\", which is consistent with the hypothesis that states that \\"air pressure it decreases as altitude increases\\". Therefore, the premise supports or entails the claim made in the hypothesis."},{"source":"You are given a dialog between 2 or more individuals. Within the dialog, there will be clues as to the names of the speakers. You will be asked at the end of the dialog to identify the name of one of the speakers.\\n\\nSpeaker 1: Dude, I am sorry about what I said! \\nSpeaker 2: No, no, you're right, it is a ridiculous name! \\nSpeaker 1: It's not that bad. \\nSpeaker 2: Yes it is! From now on, I have no first name. \\nSpeaker 1: So, you're just Bing? \\nSpeaker 2: I have no name. \\nSpeaker 3: All right, so, what are we supposed to call you? \\nSpeaker 2: Okay uh, for now, temporarily, you can call me, Clint. \\nSpeaker 1: No way are you cool enough to pull of Clint. \\nSpeaker 2: Okay, so what name am I cool enough to pull off? \\nSpeaker 3: Umm, Gene. \\nSpeaker 2: It's Clint. It's Clint! \\nSpeaker 1: See you later, Gene. \\nSpeaker 3: Bye, Gene. \\nSpeaker 2: It's Clint! Clint! \\nSpeaker 1: What's up with Gene? What is the name or nickname of \\nSpeaker 2?","target":"Bing","rationale":"Speaker 1 makes fun of Speaker 2's name and suggests that they should just call him Bing instead. In the last line, Speaker 1 asks what is the name or nickname of 'Speaker 2'. Therefore, the answer is \\"Bing\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate items to whether they are trash or treasure is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". Items marked as \\"trash\\" are considered to not have value and can be disposed, whereas those marked as \\"treasure\\" are considered valuable items that must be retained. \\"A : \\"B relates item A to whether it is trash or treasure, as specified by B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with either \`trash\` or \`treasure\` for the given item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nbaby : treasure. mud : ?","target":"trash","rationale":"A baby is considered to be a treasure, while mud is considered to be trash."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. If the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers Win'. If the count of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list, answer 'Alphabets Win'. If the count of numbers is same as that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers and Alphabets are Tied'.\\n\\n['s', '8449', '1747', 'u', 'B', '8849', 'l', '5301', 'h', 'Q', 'J', 'I', 'p', 'f', 'W', 'b', 'p', '2843', 'f', '6115', 'g', '611', '1343', '575', 'M', 'E', 'Z', 'G', '3185', '1845', '6241', '1713']","target":"Alphabets Win","rationale":"The given list has 26 alphabets and 30 numbers. Therefore, the number of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list. The output will be 'Alphabets Win'."},{"source":"You will be given a passage consisting of set of facts and a question as input. The task is to answer a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?' using one of the given facts to determine the latest location of the person. Answer should be a word/phrase describing the location from the supporting fact. Avoid answers that are incomplete or incorrect.\\n\\nPassage: Mary travelled to the garden. Daniel went to the office. Question: Where is Daniel?","target":"office","rationale":"We can be infer from the second fact in the passage which states \\"Daniel went to the office.\\""},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. The story has one of the three following scenarios: (1) when the individual's belief matches reality, (2) when the individual's belief does not match reality, (3) is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nAlexander entered the study. Ella entered the study. The lime is in the red_bottle. Ella exited the study. Alexander moved the lime to the green_drawer. Where does Alexander think that Ella searches for the lime?","target":"red_bottle","rationale":"Ella has the false belief that the lime is in the red_bottle. This matches with Alexander's belief that Ella searches for the lime in the red_bottle."},{"source":"Read the article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: Kids will often ignore your requests for them to shut off the TV, start their chores  , or do their homework as a way to avoid following your directions. Before you know it, you've started to sound like a broken record as you repeatedly ask them to do their assignments, clean their room, or take out the trash. Rather than saying, \\"Do your chores now\\", you'll be more effective if you set a target time for when the chores have to be completed. So instead of arguing about starting chores,just say, \\"If chores are't done by 4 p.m, here are the consequences.\\"  Then it's up to your child to complete the chores. Put the ball back in their court. Don't argue or fight with them,just say, \\"That's the way it's going to be.\\" It shouldn't be punitive   as much as it should be persuasive. \\"If your chores aren't done by 4 p.m, then no video game time until chores are done. And if finishing those chores runs into homework time, that's going to be your loss.\\" On the other hand, when dealing with homework, keep it very simple. Have a time when homework starts, and at that time, all electronics go off and do not go back on until you see that their homework is done. If your child says they have no homework, then they should use that time to study or read. Either way, there should be a time set aside when the electronics are off.\\nWhen a kid wears his iPod or headphones when you're trying to talk to him, make no bones about it; he is not ignoring you, he is disrespecting you. At that point, everything else should stop until he takes the earplugs out of his ears. Don't try to communicate with him when he's wearing headphones--even if he tells you he can hear you. Wearing them while you're talking to him is a sign of disrespect. Parents should be very tough about this kind of thing. Remember, mutual  respect becomes more important as children mature .\\nQuestion: Parents will be able to deal with their child more effectively if they   _  .\\nOptions: A: avoid direct ways of punishment\\nB: make him do things at their request\\nC: argue and fight with their child\\nD: allow their child to behave in his own way","target":"A","rationale":"The article describes the harmful effects of arguing and fighting with kids. It also explains that parents should use other techniques to solve problems, such as by setting a target time for completing chores or homework. This advice suggests that \\"avoid direct ways of punishment\\" is the best answer choice in this case.\\nSo, A is correct!"},{"source":"Write a question about the following article: In the 1980s and beyond, electric bass was used in works by Hans Werner Henze (El Rey de Harlem, 1980; and Il ritorno dUlisse in patria, 1981), Harold Shapero, On Green Mountain (Chaconne after Monteverdi), 1957, orchestrated 1981; Alfred Schnittkes Symphony No. 3 (Schnittke) (1981); Steve Reichs Electric Counterpoint (1987) and 2x5 (Reich) (2008), Wolfgang Rihm (Die Eroberung von Mexico, 1987-91), Arvo P√§rt (Miserere, 1989/92), Steve Martland (Dance works, 1993; and Horses of Instruction, 1994), Sofia Gubaidulina (Aus dem Stundenbuch, 1991), Giya Kancheli (Wingless, 1993), John Adams (composer) (I Was Looking at the Ceiling and Then I Saw the Sky, 1995; and Scratchband, 1996/97), Michael Nyman (various works for the Michael Nyman Band), Mark-Anthony Turnage (Blood on the Floor, 1993-1996), numerous works by Art Jarvinen.\\n\\nQuestion about the article:","target":"How many years did Anthony Turnage play Blood on the Floor?","rationale":"Here's a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nHow many years did Anthony Turnage play Blood on the Floor?"},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the alphabetical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no alphabetical element in the list\\n\\n['955', '2769', '531', 'v', 'h', 'L', '1549', 'Z', '917', '4233', 'U', '8309', 'r', '6803', 'g', '2633']","target":"7","rationale":"Given the list ['955', '2769', '531', 'v', 'h', 'L', '1549','Z','917','4233','U','8309','r','6803','g'], there are 7 alphabetical elements: v, h, L, Z, U, r and g"},{"source":"Michael and Robert are scientists who work in a nuclear reactor facility. Michael was replacing a fuel rod in the nuclear reactor when a small explosion happened, causing Michael to be exposed to high doses of radiation in a short period of time.  Robert was in the adjacent room when the explosion happened, and as a result he only suffered low doses of radiation.\\n\\nWho is more likely to suffer skin burns?\\n\\nHint: Ionizing radiation has many practical uses in medicine, research and construction, but presents a health hazard if used improperly. Exposure to radiation causes damage to living tissue; high doses result in Acute radiation syndrome (ARS), with skin burns, hair loss, internal organ failure and death, while any dose may result in an increased chance of cancer and genetic damage; a particular form of cancer, thyroid cancer, often occurs when nuclear weapons and reactors are the radiation source because of the biological proclivities of the radioactive iodine fission product, iodine-131. However, calculating the exact risk and chance of cancer forming in cells caused by ionizing radiation is still not well understood and currently estimates are loosely determined by population based data from the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki and from follow-up of reactor accidents, such as the Chernobyl disaster. The International Commission on Radiological Protection states that \\"The Commission is aware of uncertainties and lack of precision of the models and parameter values\\", \\"Collective effective dose is not intended as a tool for epidemiological risk assessment, and it is inappropriate to use it in risk projections\\" and \\"in particular, the calculation of the number of cancer deaths based on collective effective doses from trivial individual doses should be avoided.\\"","target":"Michael","rationale":"Michael was exposed to high doses of radiation in a short period of time, while Robert only suffered low doses over the same period. Exposure to a large amount of ionizing radiation is more likely cause skin burns than exposure to small amounts."},{"source":"Many respiratory diseases are caused by pathogens. A pathogen is an organism that causes disease in another organism. Certain bacteria, viruses, and fungi are pathogens of the respiratory system. The common cold and flu are caused by viruses. The influenza virus that causes the flu is pictured below ( Figure below ). Tuberculosis, whooping cough, and acute bronchitis are caused by bacteria. The pathogens that cause colds, flu, and TB can be passed from person to person by coughing, sneezing, and spitting. Illnesses caused by bacteria can be treated with antibiotics. Those caused by viruses cannot.\\n\\nBig city and Large city are situated 50 miles apart, on opposite sides of a mountain range. Both cities have lots of people with respiratory diseases. Big city has more people getting infected by viruses, while Large city has more people infected by bacteria and fungi.\\n\\nWhich city has more people catching the flu?","target":"Big","rationale":"In Big city, more people are getting infected with viruses. Since the flu is caused by a virus, it can be inferred that there would also be more cases of the flu in this area."},{"source":"Test sentence: \\"Her little sister will disagree with her.\\"\\nIs this test sentence a correct grammatical English sentence?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The above sentence is acceptable. The subject \\"her little sister\\" and the verb \\"will disagree\\" are in agreement, so there is no error in that regard. In addition, because disagreement can be interpreted as a negative action (i.e., not agreeing), it does not make sense to say something like *Her little sister will agree with her.\\" Therefore, this test sentence is correct English grammatically speaking.\\","},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: Which enzyme uses FAD as a coenzyme? \\n Options:  <0> Isocitrate dehydrogenase. <1> Glucose 6-phosphate dehydrogenase. <2> Succinate dehydrogenase. <3> Malate dehydrogenase. <4> Lactate dehydrogenase.","target":"pharmacology","rationale":"The question is about enzymes and coenzymes, which are components of biochemical reactions. This type of information is found in pharmacology textbooks, so the answer is pharmacology."},{"source":"\\"Yes, and\\" is a rule-of-thumb in improvisational comedy that suggests that a participant in a dialogue should accept what another participant has stated (\\"Yes\\") and then expand on that line of thought or context (\\"and...\\"). Given a prompt and two responses, identify which response is the type of \\"yes, and\\". Indicate your answer by 'Response 1' if the first response is correct, otherwise 'Response 2'.  Note that a \\"Yes, and\\" does not require someone explicitly saying 'yes, and...' as part of a dialogue exchange.\\n\\nPrompt: Old lady, what kind off greeting is that? I don't trust this person at all. \\n Response 1: Sorry, this is Evan. He's an only child. Therefore he has no sense of others. \\n Response 2: Apparently, even after they fall in love with you, you have to continue to be a terrible person or else they leave you.","target":"Response 1","rationale":"Response 1 qualifies as a \\"yes and\\" since it accepts the fact that Evan is an only child and then expands upon that fact by stating that Evan has no sense of others. Response 2 does not qualify as a \\"yes and\\" because it makes a different claim about what it takes to keep someone in love with you, but it does not expand on the previous line of dialogue."},{"source":"Passage: Hexagon -- In geometry, a hexagon (from Greek ·ºïŒæ hex, \`\`six'' and Œ≥œâŒΩŒØŒ±, gon√≠a, \`\`corner, angle'') is a six-sided polygon or 6-gon. The total of the internal angles of any simple (non-self-intersecting) hexagon is 720¬∞.\\n\\nAfter reading this passage, I have a question: is any shape with 6 sides a hexagon? True or False?","target":"True","rationale":"The definition of a hexagon is any shape with six sides. It does not specify that the angle summation must equal 720 degrees, or anything else for that matter. In conclusion, it can be inferred from this passage that all shapes with 6 sides are hexagons and therefore \\"True\\" would be the correct answer in response to this question."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the gain. Gain is the value by which to multiply the input. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: the value of a machine depreciates at 25 % per annum . if its present value is $ 1 , 50,000 , at what price should it be sold after two years such that a profit of $ 24,000 is made ? \\nOptions: a ) $ 258375 , b ) $ 438375 , c ) $ 128375 , d ) $ 108375 , e ) $ 158375","target":"d","rationale":"The value of the machine depreciates at 25% per annum. That is, if the current value is \\\\(V_{current}\\\\), then after one year its value will be \\\\(0.75V_{current}\\\\) and after 2 years its value will be \\\\(0.75^2V_{current} = 0.5625 V_{current}\\\\). Since we want to sell for a profit of $24,000 in two years, we have: \\n\\\\begin{equation*}\\n    24000 + 0.5625 V_{current} = 1125000\\\\\\\\\\n    \\\\Rightarrow 24000 = 562500 - V_{current}\\\\\\\\\\n    \\\\Rightarrow V_{Current} = 506250\\\\\\\\\\n\\\\end{equation*}."},{"source":"Who was a South African writer, political activist and recipient of the 1991 Nobel Prize in Literature, Nadine Gordimer or Betty Friedan?","target":"Nadine Gordimer","rationale":"Nadine Gordimer was a South African writer, political activist and recipient of the 1991 Nobel Prize in Literature.\\nBetty Friedan is considered one of the leaders of second-wave feminism (1960\\\\u20131980). She authored The Feminine Mystique, an influential book which helped spark the modern women's movement. She died on February 4th 2006 at the age 85 due to congestive heart failure."},{"source":"I had something that might have been a little supernatural.\\nSo I was trying to sleep one time, and I sleep under the blankets 99% of the time. I sleep downstairs, so hearing noise is pretty normal. Also, my door doesn‚Äôt lock, or even latch the door handle, so you can just push it open.\\nSo I was laying down, maybe at 60% in terms of how close I was to falling asleep, so I just had to lay down for like 5 more minutes.\\nBut there are a lot of noises, and they freak me out even though I just sorta pretend that they‚Äôre definitely a cat or my dog or something.\\nSo, I‚Äôm already slightly spooked, but I‚Äôm ignoring it and going to sleep anyway.\\nBut then, I hear my door open. That isn‚Äôt too weird, I do have cats, so even though by this point my fear is intense, I just sorta blow it off and keep trying to sleep.\\nAnd then, something that‚Äôs never happened in a situation like this, I feel something moving towards me on my bed.\\nIt feels like a cats movements, with light feet making slight reverberations on the bed.\\nSo my fear goes away entirely, and I‚Äôm like ‚ÄúOh okay, it‚Äôs just the cat, that‚Äôs good.‚Äù And I lift my blankets off my head to let my cat under with me, and because the fear seemed to make the atmosphere under there very hot and tense, and then I look at my bed and there‚Äôs nothing.\\nSo I just pretend nothing happened and go to sleep, but that still sticks with me and even though it‚Äôs kinda underwhelming I still think it was very strange since I wasn‚Äôt at the ‚Äúedge of consciousness‚Äù stage of going to sleep, so I feel like the chances I imagined it aren‚Äôt too high.\\nAccording to the above context, choose the correct option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: Where does the author sleep at night?\\nOptions:\\n\\nA. A downstairs bedroom\\n\\nB. In bed\\n\\nC. not enough information\\n\\nD. Under the blankets","target":"A","rationale":"The context says that the author sleeps downstairs, so option A is correct. The other options are incorrect because they do not align with any information from the given paragraph."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to return the sum of all the numerical elements in the list A between the positions i and j (including positions i and j). Return 0 if no numerical element is present in the list between the given ranges. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n9, 12, ['9949', 'G', 'b', 'm', 'f', '8083', 's', '2115', '4983', '6627', '6569', 's', '2199', 'h', 'o', '2579', 'a', '9339', '4205', 'e', '6559', 'z', 'n', 'Y', '6545', '1601', 'T', 'X', 'A', '4479']","target":"18179","rationale":"Given the list ['9949', 'G', 'b', 'm', 'f', '8083', 's'...] we need to find the elements within the range 9 ~ 12.\\\\n1. The 9th element is 2115.\\\\n2. The 10th element is 4983.\\\\n3. The 11th element is 6627.\\\\n4. The 12nd element is 6569; however, since j=12, this will be included in the calculation as well (even though it's outside of i~j).\\n\\nCalculating the final results, 2115 + 4983 + 6627 = 13825 + 6569 = 18179"},{"source":"What was the response? DIALOG:\\nWhat can you tell me about The Aquabats! Super Show!'s premise?\\n- Chronicled in both live-action and animated segments, The Aquabats! Super Show! is centered around the adventures of The Aquabats\\n- what kind of adventures where they involved in?\\n- The Aquabats are a group of superhero rock musicians who travel the countryside on a self-appointed mission to fight evil and destroy boredom.\\n- what else do the super heros of Aquabats do?\\n- Protecting the world from the villains and creatures who threaten to destroy it while aiming to become a famous rock and roll band in their own right.\\n- who were the members of Aquabats?\\n- The Aquabats consist of singer The MC Bat Commander; bassist Crash McLarson; drummer Ricky Fitness; guitarist EagleBones Falconhawk; and keyboardist Jimmy the Robot.\\n- who is the leader of the Aquabats?\\n-","target":"Singer The MC Bat Commander (Christian Jacobs) is the swaggering leader of The Aquabats.","rationale":"The given DIALOG consists of a series of natural questions and answers. The last question asked is who is the leader of the Aquabats, so the response is going to be related to this question. The only statement among the candidate options that matches this requirement is \\"Singer The MC Bat Commander (Christian Jacobs) is the swaggering leader of The Aquabats.\\""},{"source":"You are given an open-domain question from an open movie database. Your task is to provide an answer to that question. Try to only include the answer. Do not put it in a sentence.\\n\\nwhat language is The Landlord in?","target":"English","rationale":"The language of \\"The Landlord\\" is listed as English."},{"source":"Reptiles may actually be\\n- grumpy\\n- brainless\\n- magical\\n- pea brained\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"pea brained","rationale":"According to the dictionary, a pea brain is someone who has an extremely small or undeveloped brain. Reptiles are not thought of as being particularly smart animals compared to other vertebrates, so they could be said to have brains that are \\"pea brained\\"."},{"source":"Stephen Thomas Ward (19 October 1912 ‚Äì 3 August 1963) was an English osteopath and artist who was one of the central figures in the 1963 Profumo affair, a British political scandal which brought about the resignation of John Profumo, the Secretary of State for War, and contributed to the defeat of the Conservative government a year later.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nStephen Thomas Ward was an osteopath not interested in politics.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The preceding paragraph states that Stephen Thomas Ward was a central figure in the 1963 Profumo affair, which is definitely related to politics. Hence, it can be inferred from this statement that he was indeed interested in politics. So, the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"You are provided with an \\"Event\\", \\"Intent\\" related to PersonX. Guess a reaction/reaction of PersonX about the given event and their intention.\\n\\nEvent:PersonX sells well. Intent: 1) to be successful","target":"fulfilled","rationale":"PersonX's intention was to be successful, and the event states that they sold well. Therefore, PersonX must feel fulfilled."},{"source":"Gill and Ann were two fellow botanists. Gill studied alpine tundras extensively, while Ann studied tropical forests. They both discovered very interesting facts about nature and plants.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich person learned more about high-mountain summits?\\n\\nHint: Alpine tundra occurs at high enough altitude at any latitude. Portions of montane grasslands and shrublands ecoregions worldwide include alpine tundra. Large regions of alpine tundra occur in the North American Cordillera, the Alps and Pyrenees of Europe, the Himalaya and Karakoram of Asia, the Andes of South America, and the Eastern Rift mountains of Africa.Alpine tundra occupies high-mountain summits, slopes, and ridges above timberline. Aspect plays a role as well; the treeline often occurs at higher elevations on warmer equator-facing slopes. Because the alpine zone is present only on mountains, much of the landscape is rugged and broken, with rocky, snowcapped peaks, cliffs, and talus slopes, but also contains areas of gently rolling to almost flat topography.Averaging over many locations and local microclimates, the treeline rises 75 metres (245 ft) when moving 1 degree south from 70 to 50¬∞N, and 130 metres (430 ft) per degree from 50 to 30¬∞N. Between 30¬∞N and 20¬∞S, the treeline is roughly constant, between 3,500 and 4,000 metres (11,500 and 13,100 ft).","target":"Gill","rationale":"Alpine tundra occurs at high enough altitude at any latitude. Portions of montane grasslands and shrublands ecoregions worldwide include alpine tundra. Large regions of alpine tundra occur in the North American Cordillera, the Alps and Pyrenees of Europe, the Himalaya and Karakoram of Asia, the Andes of South America, and the Eastern Rift mountains of Africa. Alpine tundra occupies high-mountain summits, slopes, and ridges above timberline (the tree line is also known as treeline).\\nSo Gill learned more about high-mountain summits than Ann did\\n\\n \\n*/"},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 0, equation weights = [7, 4]","target":"4","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 7x+4.\\\\nSubstituting x = 0, we get: 7(0) + 4 = 0 + 4 = 4"},{"source":"Found the following article online, use it to answer the question: What are the first names of the people in the couple that Dhanens theorises the piece was commissioned as a wedding gift for?\\n\\nThe identity of the donor has not been established, although a number of suggestions have been advanced over the last 200 years. Harbison suggests the work's small scale indicates that it functioned as a portable altarpiece rather than as a private devotional work, and thus was commissioned by or for a member of the clergy. Other art historians have argued that the donor may have been a Genoese merchant. This belief has been fed by the triptych's similarity to Giovanni Mazone's Virgin and Child altarpiece in Pontremoli, Tuscany, which may place it in the Italian region of Liguria at latest by the end of the 15th century. Damaged coats of arms on the inner frames have been linked to the Giustiniani family, known for establishing trade links with Bruges in the 14th and 15th centuries. If not commissioned by that family, historical record place the work at least in their possession by the end of the century. In the early 1800s, Frances Weale attempted to place Michele Giustiniani as the donor, however later historical research has been unable to verify his presence in Bruges around 1437, and he seems to have returned to Italy by 1430.Mid-twentieth century technical examination revealed the Giustiniani coats of arms may have been painted over an earlier heraldic design, perhaps as early as the 15th century, whose signifiance and history is now lost. Dhanens theorises that a member of the Giustiniani family may have established other associations with St. Michael and St. Catherine, advancing that they were a member of the Italian Rapondi family, whose trading house in Paris was named after St. Catherine. Their daughter, also named Catherine, married the Italian merchant Michel Burlamacchi (Bollemard in Flemish) from Lucca, who was active in Bruges. From this Dhanens theorises the piece was commissioned as a wedding gift for the couple. Documents show weavers in Wervik paid taxes to Catherine Rapondi and in September 1434, when Michele Burlamacchi was tax collector in that town, van Eyck received a stipend funded...","target":"Catherine","rationale":"The text mentions a couple named Catherine Rapondi and Michel Burlamacchi. It is mentioned that the painting may have been commissioned as a wedding gift for them, so it can be said with certainty that their first names are \\"Catherine\\" and \\"Michel\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Famoudou Don Moye, (born May 23, 1946) is an American jazz percussionist and drummer. He is most known for his involvement with the Art Ensemble of Chicago and is noted for his mastery of African and Caribbean percussion instruments and rhythmic techniques.\\n\\n- Malachi Favors (August 22, 1927, Lexington, Mississippi  January 30, 2004, Chicago, Illinois) was a noted American jazz bassist best known for his work with the Art Ensemble of Chicago.\\n\\n- Jodie Christian (February 2, 1932  February 13, 2012) was an American jazz pianist, noted for bebop and free jazz.\\n\\n- Anthony Braxton (born June 4, 1945) is an American composer and instrumentalist. Braxton has released well over 100 albums since the 1960s. Among the instruments he plays are the sopranino, soprano, C-melody, F mezzo-soprano, E-flat alto, baritone, bass, and contrabass saxophones; the E-flat, B-flat, and contrabass clarinets; and the piano. He used to play flute and alto flute as well, but has since discontinued his use of these instruments.\\n\\n- Mars Williams ( born May 28 , 1955 in Elmhurst , Illinois ) is an American jazz and rock saxophonist . Exposed to Big Band and Dixieland Jazz by his trumpet playing father , Williams played classical clarinet for ten years , then migrated to the saxophone in his senior year of high school , citing influences from Eric Dolphy , John Coltrane and Charlie Parker . He attended De Paul University and later the Association for the Advancement of Creative Musicians where he studied under the mentorship of founders Anthony Braxton and Roscoe Mitchell . In 2004 he was selected by the Moers Festival as their featured artist . Williams is a musician , orchestrator and arranger who has played with various bands and recording artists including The Waitresses and gold - record sellers The Psychedelic Furs . He was originally only to tour with The Furs in Australia for a month in 1983 as then sax - player Gary Windo was unable to make the trip . After a successful tour and the subsequent Waitresses breakup , Mars was asked to stay on as a permanent member , which he did until 1989 and later rejoined in 2005 . He has also performed with Billy Idol and the Robert Palmer era Power Station , as well as Billy Squier , Massacre , Ministry , Die Warzau and other leading figures in both the Chicago and the NYC downtown music scenes . He also has toured and recorded with the Peter Brotzmann Tentet , the Vandermark 5 , Cinghiale , Our Daughter 's Wedding , and Mark Freeland 's Electroman , and is the bandleader of several spin - off jazz groups / projects : Grammy nominated , acid jazz pioneer Liquid Soul , Hal Russell 's NRG Ensemble , Witches & Devils , Slam , and XmarsX . Despite his busy schedule , he manages to also stay active in the Chicago improvisational jazz underground scene both individually and as a member of the improvisational quartet Extraordinary Popular Delusions , which began a weekly Monday gig at Beat Kitchen in Chicago on 20 August 2010 , after concluding a five - year - plus weekly run at nearby Hotti Biscotti .\\n\\n- Charles \\"Charlie\\" Parker, Jr. (August 29, 1920  March 12, 1955), also known as Yardbird and Bird, was an American jazz saxophonist and composer.\\n\\n- West Africa, also called Western Africa and the West of Africa, is the westernmost subregion of Africa. West Africa has been defined as including 18 countries: Benin, Burkina Faso, the island nation of Cape Verde, Gambia, Ghana, Guinea, Guinea-Bissau, Ivory Coast, Liberia, Mali, Mauritania, Niger, Nigeria, the island of Saint Helena, Senegal, Sierra Leone, S√£o Tom√© and Pr√≠ncipe and Togo.\\n\\n- A musical ensemble, also known as a music group or musical group, is a group of people who perform instrumental and/or vocal music, with the ensemble typically known by a distinct name. Some music ensembles consist solely of instruments, such as the jazz quartet or the orchestra. Some music ensembles consist solely of singers, such as choirs and doo wop groups. In both popular music and classical music, there are ensembles in which both instrumentalists and singers perform, such as the rock band or the Baroque chamber group for basso continuo (harpsichord and cello) and one or more singers. In classical music, trios or quartets either blend the sounds of musical instrument families (such as piano, strings, and wind instruments) or group together instruments from the same instrument family, such as string ensembles (e.g., string quartet) or wind ensembles (e.g., wind quintet). Some ensembles blend the sounds of a variety of instrument families, such as the orchestra, which uses a string section, brass instruments, woodwinds and percussion instruments, or the concert band, which uses brass, woodwinds and percussion. \\n\\n- Ishmael Wadada Leo Smith (born December 18, 1941) is an American trumpeter and composer, working primarily in the fields of avant-garde jazz and free improvisation. He was one of three finalists for the 2013 Pulitzer Prize for Music for \\"Ten Freedom Summers\\", released on May 22, 2012.\\n\\n- Amina Claudine Myers (born March 21, 1942) is an American jazz pianist, organist, vocalist, composer, and arranger.\\n\\n- The clarinet is a musical-instrument family belonging to the group known as the woodwind instruments. It has a single-reed mouthpiece, a straight cylindrical tube with an almost cylindrical bore, and a flared bell. A person who plays a clarinet is called a \\"clarinetist\\" (sometimes spelled \\"clarinettist\\").\\n\\n- Chico Freeman (born Earl Lavon Freeman Jr.; July 17, 1949) is a modern jazz tenor saxophonist and trumpeter and son of jazz saxophonist Von Freeman. He began recording as lead musician in 1976 with \\"Morning Prayer\\", won the New York Jazz Award in 1979 and earned the Stereo Review Record of the Year in 1981 for his album \\"The Outside Within\\".\\n\\n- A pianist is an individual musician who plays the piano. Most forms of Western music can make use of the piano. Consequently, pianists have a wide variety of repertoire and styles to choose from, including traditionally classical music, Jazz, blues and all sorts of popular music, including rock music. Most pianists can, to a certain extent, play other keyboard-related instruments such as the synthesizer, harpsichord, celesta and the organ and keyboard. Perhaps the greatest pianist of all time was Franz Liszt, whose piano mastery was described by Anton Rubinstein: \\"In comparison with Liszt, all other pianists are children\\". \\n\\n- Illinois is a state in the midwestern region of the United States, achieving statehood in 1818. It is the 5th most populous state and 25th largest state in terms of land area, and is often noted as a microcosm of the entire country. The word \\"Illinois\\" comes from the Algonquin word for \\"tribe of superior men\\". With Chicago in the northeast, small industrial cities and great agricultural productivity in central and northern Illinois, and natural resources like coal, timber, and petroleum in the south, Illinois has a diverse economic base and is a major transportation hub. The Port of Chicago connects the state to other global ports from the Great Lakes, via the Saint Lawrence Seaway, to the Atlantic Ocean, as well as the Great Lakes to the Mississippi River, via the Illinois River. For decades, O'Hare International Airport has been ranked as one of the world's busiest airports. Illinois has long had a reputation as a bellwether both in social and cultural terms and politics.\\n\\n- The Penguin Guide to Jazz is a reference work containing an encyclopedic directory of jazz recordings on CD which are currently available in Europe or the United States. The first nine editions were compiled by Richard Cook and Brian Morton, two well known chroniclers of jazz resident in the United Kingdom.\\n\\n- Thelonious Sphere Monk (October 10, 1917  February 17, 1982) was an American jazz pianist and composer. Monk had a unique improvisational style and made numerous contributions to the standard jazz repertoire, including \\"'Round Midnight\\", \\"Blue Monk\\", \\"Straight, No Chaser\\" \\"Ruby, My Dear\\", \\"In Walked Bud\\", and \\"Well, You Needn't\\". Monk is the second most-recorded jazz composer after Duke Ellington, which is particularly remarkable as Ellington composed more than 1,000 pieces, whereas Monk wrote about 70.\\n\\n- African-American music is an umbrella term covering a diverse range of musics and musical genres largely developed by African Americans. Their origins are in musical forms that arose out of the historical condition of slavery that characterized the lives of African Americans prior to the American Civil War.\\n\\n- Henry Threadgill (born February 15, 1944) is a Pulitzer Prize-winning American composer, saxophonist, and flautist, who came to prominence in the 1970s leading ensembles with unusual instrumentation and often incorporating non-jazz genres.\\n\\n- Improvisation is broad term referring to the process of devising an atypical method of solving a problem due to lack of time or resources. In a technical context, this can mean adapting a device for some use other than that which it was designed for, or building a device from unusual components in an ad-hoc fashion. Improvisation, within the context of performing arts, is a very spontaneous performance without specific or scripted preparation. The skills of improvisation can apply to many different faculties, across all artistic, scientific, physical, cognitive, academic, and non-academic disciplines.\\n\\n- Ragtime  also spelled rag-time or rag time  is a musical genre that enjoyed its peak popularity between 1895 and 1918. Its cardinal trait is its syncopated, or \\"ragged\\", rhythm. The genre has its origins in African-American communities like St. Louis years before being published as popular sheet music for piano. Ernest Hogan (18651909) was a pioneer of ragtime music and was the first to compose ragtime into sheet music. The composition was called \\"LA Pas Ma LA\\" and it was released in 1895. Hogan has also been credited for coining the term \\"ragtime\\". The term is actually derived from his hometown \\"Shake Rag\\" in Bowling Green, Kentucky. Ben Harney, who is also a Kentucky native has often been credited for introducing the music to the mainstream public. His first ragtime composition \\"You've been a good old wagon but you done broke\\" helped popularize the musical genre. The composition was published in 1895 but released in 1896. Ragtime was also a modification of the march made popular by John Philip Sousa, with additional polyrhythms coming from African music. The ragtime composer Scott Joplin (\\"ca.\\" 18681917) became famous through the publication of the \\"Maple Leaf Rag\\" (1899) and a string of ragtime hits such as \\"The Entertainer\\" (1902), although he was later forgotten by all but a small, dedicated community of ragtime aficionados until the major ragtime revival in the early 1970s. For at least 12 years after its publication, \\"Maple Leaf Rag\\" heavily influenced subsequent ragtime composers with its melody lines, harmonic progressions or metric patterns.\\n\\n- John William Coltrane, also known as \\"Trane\\" (September 23, 1926¬† July 17, 1967), was an American jazz saxophonist and composer. Working in the bebop and hard bop idioms early in his career, Coltrane helped pioneer the use of modes in jazz and was later at the forefront of free jazz. He led at least fifty recording sessions during his career, and appeared as a sideman on many albums by other musicians, including trumpeter Miles Davis and pianist Thelonious Monk.\\n\\n- Roscoe Mitchell (born August 3, 1940 in Chicago, Illinois) is an American composer, jazz instrumentalist, and educator, known for being \\"a technically superb  if idiosyncratic  saxophonist.\\" \\"The Penguin Guide to Jazz\\" described him as \\"one of the key figures\\" in avant-garde jazz; All About Jazz states that he has been \\"at the forefront of modern music\\" for the past 35 years. Critic John Pareles in \\"The New York Times\\" has mentioned that Mitchell \\"qualifies as an iconoclast.\\" In addition to his own work as a bandleader, Mitchell is known for cofounding the Art Ensemble of Chicago and the Association for the Advancement of Creative Musicians (AACM).\\n\\n- The saxophone (also referred to as the sax) is a family of woodwind instruments. Saxophones are usually made of brass and played with a single-reed mouthpiece similar to that of the clarinet. The saxophone family was invented by the Belgian instrument maker Adolphe Sax in 1840. Adolphe Sax wanted to create a group or series of instruments that would be the most powerful and vocal of the woodwinds, and the most adaptive of the brass instruments, that would fill the vacant middle ground between the two sections. He patented the saxophone on June 28, 1846, in two groups of seven instruments each. Each series consisted of instruments of various sizes in alternating transposition. The series pitched in B and E, designed for military bands, have proved extremely popular and most saxophones encountered today are from this series. Instruments from the so-called \\"orchestral\\" series, pitched in C and F, never gained a foothold, and the B and E instruments have now replaced the C and F instruments when the saxophone is used in an orchestra.\\n\\n- Muhal Richard Abrams (born September 19, 1930, in Chicago, Illinois) is an American educator, administrator, composer, arranger, clarinetist, cellist, and jazz pianist in the free jazz medium.\\n\\n- Chicago (or ), officially the City of Chicago, is the third-most populous city in the United States, and the fifth-most populous city in North America. With over 2.7¬†million residents, it is the most populous city in the state of Illinois and the Midwestern United States, and the county seat of Cook County. The Chicago metropolitan area, often referred to as Chicagoland, has nearly 10¬†million people and is the third-largest in the U.S.\\n\\n- Jack DeJohnette (born August 9, 1942) is an American jazz drummer, pianist, and composer.\\n\\n- Lester Bowie (October 11, 1941  November 8, 1999) was an American jazz trumpet player and composer. He was a member of the Association for the Advancement of Creative Musicians and cofounded the Art Ensemble of Chicago.\\n\\n- The avant-garde (from French, \\"advance guard\\" or \\"vanguard\\", literally \\"fore-guard\\") are people or works that are experimental, radical, or unorthodox, with respect to art, culture, and society. It may be characterized by nontraditional, aesthetic innovation and initial unacceptability, and it may offer a critique of the relationship between producer and consumer.\\n\\n- The Moers Festival is an international jazz festival in Moers, Germany, happening yearly every Whitsun.\\n\\n- The Association for the Advancement of Creative Musicians (AACM) is a non-profit organization, founded in Chicago, Illinois, United States, by pianist/composer Muhal Richard Abrams, pianist Jodie Christian, drummer Steve McCall, and composer Phil Cohran. Early members included Henry Threadgill, Anthony Braxton, Jack DeJohnette, Wadada Leo Smith, Leroy Jenkins, Amina Claudine Myers, Adegoke Steve Colson, Chico Freeman, George Lewis and the Art Ensemble of Chicago: Lester Bowie, Roscoe Mitchell, Joseph Jarman, Famoudou Don Moye, and Malachi Favors. The AACM is devoted \\"to nurturing, performing, and recording serious, original music,\\" according to its charter. It supports and encourages jazz performers, composers and educators. While founded in the Jazz tradition, the groups outreach and influence has, according to Larry Blumenfeld, \\"touched nearly all corners of modern music.\\"\\n\\n- A trumpet is a musical instrument commonly used in classical and jazz ensembles. The trumpet group contains the instruments with the highest register in the brass family. Trumpet-like instruments have historically been used as signaling devices in battle or hunting, with examples dating back to at least 1500 BC; they began to be used as musical instruments only in the late-14th or early 15th century. Trumpets are used in art music styles, for instance in orchestras, concert bands, and jazz ensembles, as well as in popular music. They are played by blowing air through almost-closed lips (called the player's embouchure), producing a \\"buzzing\\" sound that starts a standing wave vibration in the air column inside the instrument. Since the late 15th century they have primarily been constructed of brass tubing, usually bent twice into a rounded rectangular shape. \\n\\n- Kelan Phil Cohran (born in Oxford, Mississippi on May 8, 1927) is a jazz musician. He is known most for his trumpet contributions in the Sun Ra Arkestra in Chicago during 1959-1961 and for his involvement in the foundation of the AACM.\\n\\n- New Orleans (or ) is a major United States port and the largest city and metropolitan area in the state of Louisiana. The population of the city was 343,829 as of the 2010 U.S. Census. The New Orleans metropolitan area (New OrleansMetairieKenner Metropolitan Statistical Area) had a population of 1,167,764 in 2010 and was the 46th largest in the United States. The New OrleansMetairieBogalusa Combined Statistical Area, a larger trading area, had a 2010 population of 1,452,502.\\n\\n- Free jazz is an approach to jazz music that was first developed in the 1950s and 1960s as musicians attempted to alter, extend, or break down jazz convention, often by discarding fixed chord changes or tempos. Though the music of free jazz composers varied widely, a common feature was dissatisfaction with the limitations of bebop, hard bop, and modal jazz that had developed in the 1940s and 1950s. Often described as avant-garde, free jazz has also been described as an attempt to return jazz to its primitive, often religious, roots and emphasis on collective improvisation.\\n\\n- A rhythm section (also called a backup band) is a group of musicians within a music ensemble or band who provide the underlying rhythm and pulse of the accompaniment, providing a rhythmic reference and \\"beat\\" for the rest of the band. Many of the rhythm section instruments, such as keyboard instruments and guitars, are also used to play the chord progression upon which the song is based. The bass instrument (either double bass or electric bass, or another low-register instrument, such as synth bass, depending on the group and its style of music) plays the low-pitched bassline that supports the chord progression, typically by emphasizing the roots of the chords (and to a lesser degree the fifths and thirds of the chords).\\n\\n- Joseph Jarman (born September 14, 1937 in Pine Bluff, Arkansas), is a jazz musician, composer, and Shinshu Buddhist priest. He was one of the first members of the Association for the Advancement of Creative Musicians and a member of the Art Ensemble of Chicago.\\n\\n- A big band is a type of musical ensemble associated with playing jazz music and which became popular during the Swing Era from the early 1930s until the late 1940s. Big Bands evolved with the times and continue to today. A big band typically consists of approximately 12 to 25 musicians and contains saxophones, trumpets, trombones, and a rhythm section. The terms jazz band, jazz ensemble, stage band, jazz orchestra, and dance band are also used to refer to this type of ensemble. This does not, however, mean that each one of these names is technically correct for naming a \\"big band\\" specifically.\\n\\n- Eric Allan Dolphy, Jr. (June 20, 1928  June 29, 1964) was an American jazz alto saxophonist, flautist, and bass clarinetist. On a few occasions, he also played the clarinet and piccolo. Dolphy was one of several multi-instrumentalists to gain prominence in the 1960s. He was one of the first important bass clarinet soloists in jazz, extended the vocabulary and boundaries of the alto saxophone, and was among the earliest significant jazz flute soloists.\\n\\n- Jazz is a music genre that originated amongst African Americans in New Orleans, United States, in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Since the 1920s jazz age, jazz has become recognized as a major form of musical expression. It emerged in the form of independent traditional and popular musical styles, all linked by the common bonds of African American and European American musical parentage with a performance orientation. Jazz is characterized by swing and blue notes, call and response vocals, polyrhythms and improvisation. Jazz has roots in West African cultural and musical expression, and in African-American music traditions including blues and ragtime, as well as European military band music. Although the foundation of jazz is deeply rooted within the Black experience of the United States, different cultures have contributed their own experience and styles to the art form as well. Intellectuals around the world have hailed jazz as \\"one of America's original art forms\\".\\n\\n- Miles Dewey Davis III (May 26, 1926September 28, 1991) was an American jazz trumpeter, bandleader, and composer. He is among the most influential and acclaimed figures in the history of jazz and 20th century music. With his ever-changing directions in music, Davis was at the forefront of a number of major stylistic developments in jazz over his five-decade career.\\n\\n- The piccolo (Italian for \\"small\\", but named \\"ottavino\\" in Italy) is a half-size flute, and a member of the woodwind family of musical instruments. The modern piccolo has most of the same fingerings as its larger sibling, the standard transverse flute, but the sound it produces is an octave higher than written. This gave rise to the name \\"ottavino\\" (Italian for \\"little octave\\"), the name by which the instrument is referred to in the scores of Italian composers.\\nPiccolos are now only manufactured in the key of C ; however, they were once also available in D. It was for this D piccolo that John Philip Sousa wrote the famous solo in the final repeat of the closing section (trio) of his march \\"The Stars and Stripes Forever\\".\\n\\n- Africa is the world's second-largest and second-most-populous continent. At about 30.3 million km¬≤ (11.7 million square¬†miles) including adjacent islands, it covers 6% of Earth's total surface area and 20.4 % of its total land area. With 1.1 billion people as of 2013, it accounts for about 15% of the world's human population. The continent is surrounded by the Mediterranean Sea to the north, both the Suez Canal and the Red Sea along the Sinai Peninsula to the northeast, the Indian Ocean to the southeast, and the Atlantic Ocean to the west. The continent includes Madagascar and various archipelagos. It contains 54 fully recognized sovereign states (countries), nine territories and two \\"de facto\\" independent states with limited or no recognition.\\n\\n- Whitsun (also Whitsunday, Whit Sunday or Whit) is the name used in Britain and Ireland, and among Anglicans throughout the world, for the Christian festival of Pentecost, the seventh Sunday after Easter, which commemorates the descent of the Holy Spirit upon Christ's disciples (Acts of the Apostles chapter 2). In England it took on some characteristics of Beltane, which originated from the pagan celebration of Summer's Day, the beginning of the summer half-year, in Europe. Whitsuntide, the week following Whitsunday, was one of three vacation weeks for the medieval villein; on most manors he was free from service on the lord's demesne this week, which marked a pause in the agricultural year. Whit Monday, the day after Whitsun, remained a holiday in the UK until 1978 when the movable holiday was replaced with the fixed Spring Bank Holiday in late May. Whit was the occasion for varied forms of celebration. In the North West of England, church and chapel parades called Whit Walks still take place at this time (sometimes on Whit Friday, the Friday after Whitsun). Typically, the parades include brass bands and choirs; girls attending are dressed in white. Traditionally, Whit fairs (sometimes called Whitsun ales) took place. Other customs such as Morris dancing were associated with Whitsun, although in most cases they have been transferred to the Spring bank holiday. Whaddon, Cambridgeshire has its own Whitsun tradition of singing a unique song around the village before and on Whit Sunday itself.\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the information above, choose from the list below the object entity that exhibits the relation 'occupation' with the subject 'mars williams'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- administrator\\n - band\\n - bank\\n - bassist\\n - cardinal\\n - cellist\\n - clarinetist\\n - composer\\n - cook\\n - critic\\n - drummer\\n - duke\\n - educator\\n - fashion\\n - guard\\n - guide\\n - hunting\\n - jazz musician\\n - major\\n - member\\n - military\\n - monk\\n - musician\\n - percussionist\\n - pianist\\n - pioneer\\n - prior\\n - producer\\n - religious\\n - saint\\n - saxophonist\\n - sovereign\\n - tenor\\n - trumpeter\\n - united kingdom\\n - vocalist","target":"jazz musician","rationale":"Mars Williams is known for his work as a jazz musician."},{"source":"Acids have pH values below 7. The lower the pH value, the more strongly acidic the substance.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are increases or decreases ):\\n\\n\\nIf Mary is cleaning her pool and she increases the pH value of the water, what happens to the acidity of the water increases or decreases?","target":"decreases","rationale":"A pH value is a measure of acidity. Based on the passage, acids have pH values below 7 and the lower their pH value, the more acidic they are. Therefore if Mary increases the pH level in her pool water, it means that she is decreasing its acidity or making it less acidic since by increasing something with a low number (i.e., below seven) you would expect to get something with an even higher number than before but still below seven. So according to this logic we can say that when Mary increased the PH level of here pool water then she decreased its acidity so answer will be \\"decreases\\"."},{"source":"Please answer a question about the following article about Queen (band):\\n\\nIn 1999, a Greatest Hits III album was released. This featured, among others, \\"Queen + Wyclef Jean\\" on a rap version of \\"Another One Bites the Dust\\". A live version of \\"Somebody to Love\\" by George Michael and a live version of \\"The Show Must Go On\\" with Elton John were also featured in the album. By this point, Queen's vast amount of record sales made them the second best selling artist in the UK of all time, behind the Beatles. In 2002, Queen were awarded the 2,207th star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame, which is located at 6358 Hollywood Blvd. On 29 November 2003, May and Taylor performed at the 46664 Concert hosted by Nelson Mandela at Green Point Stadium, Cape Town, to raise awareness of the spread of HIV/AIDS in South Africa. May and Taylor spent time at Mandela's home, discussing how Africa's problems might be approached, and two years later the band was made ambassadors for the 46664 cause.\\n\\nAlive version of Somebody to Love featured what artist?","target":"George Michael","rationale":"George Michael is mentioned in the text as having recorded a live version of \\"Somebody to Love\\". \\nThe full name, George Michael, can be found by looking at the first sentence after \\"\\"Alive version\\"\\", which reads: \\"In 1999, a Greatest Hits III album was released. This featured, among others,\\" and contains George Michaels' song that he recorded with Queen."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. You are required to assign a label 'formal' if there is an absence of emotion and a presence of questions anywhere within the conversation. If such pattern is not found assign the label 'informal'.\\n\\n Person1:       Good morning golf aficionados ! My name is Rick Fields , and you guessed it , I am here with my main man , Bob Copeland .  \\n Person2:Thank you , Rick ! As you can see , ladies and gentleman , we are here in beautiful Pebble Beach where the top golfers in the world are trying to win the grand prize of one million dollars !  \\n Person1:        Whoa , that ‚Äô s a lot of cash ! Let ‚Äô s go to the course and see how Tiger Woods is doing .  \\n Person2:All right , we are here at the eighth hole . It ‚Äô s a par four , and has some very difficult hazards which many golfers find difficult to avoid . Although , I did see Jack Nicklaus hit a hole in one on this very same hole !  \\n Person1:        Tiger Woods is about to tee off , and let ‚Äô s see if he has the same luck as Jack . Tiger is asking his caddie for his driver and , he seems to be very nervous .  \\n Person2:Oh no ! Not a good swing at all ! It ‚Äô s definitely not his day today . On the seventh hole he got a bogey and before that he barely made par . He will definitely not get a birdie on this shot .  \\n Person1:        It seems that his ball has flown somewhere deep in the trees . He is having a hard time finding it and even his caddie has climbed a tree to try and spot it .  \\n Person2:Oh no ! A bear ! Run , Tiger , run ! Somebody call animal control !","target":"informal","rationale":"This dialogue is an informal conversation between two sports commentators. There are no questions asked in the conversation and hence, the label for this dialogue should be \\"informal\\"."},{"source":"EXAM\\n1. Answer by yes or no.\\n\\nDocument: Fastest animals -- The fastest land animal is the cheetah, which has a recorded speed of 109.4--120.7 km/h (68.0--75.0 mph). The peregrine falcon is the fastest bird and the fastest member of the animal kingdom with a diving speed of 389 km/h (242 mph). The fastest animal in the sea is the black marlin, which has a recorded speed of 129 km/h (80 mph).\\nQuestion: are cheetahs the fastest animal in the world?","target":"No","rationale":"The document states that the fastest member of the animal kingdom is a peregrine falcon. Cheetahs are not mentioned again in the text, so it can be inferred that they are slower than peregrine falcons. Therefore, cheetahs cannot be considered as the fastest animals in world and must therefore fall outside this category. The answer has to be No"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: sexual-explicit and non-sexual-explicit. A comment is considered sexual-explicit if it explicitly portrays sexual matters.\\n\\nComment: Perhaps 'barking dog' is more diplomatic than 'braying ass.'","target":"Sexual-explicit","rationale":"The given comment contains the phrase \\"barking dog\\" which is often used to refer to a penis. Therefore, the answer is \\"Sexual-explicit\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: Antegrade amnesia is a result of brain damage in: \\n Options:  <0> The hippocampus, its afferents or eferences. <1> The hypothalamus, its afferences or eferences. <2> The thalamus, its afferences or eferences. <3> The pituitary gland, its afferences or eferences. <4> The orbitofrontal cortex, its afferents or eferences.","target":"psychology","rationale":"The question is about \\"Antegrade amnesia\\" which is a memory disorder, so it can be classified as a psychology topic."},{"source":"What was likely said next? DIALOG:\\nWho is Allan Kardeck?\\n-","target":"Allan Kardeck Allan Kardeck dos Santos Pereira also known as Allan Kardeck (born May 16, 1982) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Nicaraguan side Real Estel√≠.","rationale":"When the question was asked, Allan Kardeck Allan Kardeck dos Santos Pereira also known as Allan Kardeck (born May 16, 1982) is a Brazilian footballer who currently plays for Nicaraguan side Real Estel√≠."},{"source":"In this task you are given a list of integers and you need to find the absolute value of the difference between each two consecutive values. The output should be a list of the absolute value of the differences of each two consecutive values.\\n\\n[-4, 87, -25, -81]","target":"[91, 112, 56]","rationale":"The difference between -4 and 87 is 91\\\\nThe absolute value of the difference between 87 and -25 is 112.\\\\nThe absolute value of the difference between -25 and -81 is 56.\\\\nTherefore, the final result is [91, 112, 56]."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of strings and you need to concatenate them.\\n\\n['my', 'H', 'there', 'E', 'aloft', 'm', 'ye', 'e', 'enormous', 'd', 'k', 'not', 'Z', 'arid', 'F']","target":"myHthereEaloftmyeeenormousdknotZaridF","rationale":"Given the list of strings ['my', 'H', 'there', 'E', 'aloft'...], we need to concatenate them. Each element in the string will be connected to the next one, so that in this case, \\"my\\" connects with \\"H\\", \\"H\\" connects with \\"there\\", and so on. The resulting string will be: myHthereEaloftmyeeenormousdknotZaridF"},{"source":"Premise: A conductor leading a band in music.\\n\\nHypothesis: The conductor is signaling an airplane landing.\\n\\n.Multi-select problem: Can we conclude that the hypothesis is true if the premise is true?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise talks about the conductor leading his band in music, and does not mention anything about an airplane. This indicates that there is a clear contradiction between the premise and hypothesis. Hence, it cannot be concluded from the information given in the problem that this statement is true if we know the premise to be true."},{"source":"What is the title of this article:\\n\\nIn addition to professional team sports, North Carolina has a strong affiliation with NASCAR and stock-car racing, with Charlotte Motor Speedway in Concord hosting two Sprint Cup Series races every year. Charlotte also hosts the NASCAR Hall of Fame, while Concord is the home of several top-flight racing teams, including Hendrick Motorsports, Roush Fenway Racing, Richard Petty Motorsports, Stewart-Haas Racing, and Chip Ganassi Racing. Numerous other tracks around North Carolina host races from low-tier NASCAR circuits as well.\\n\\nTitle:","target":"North Carolina","rationale":"The given article is about the state of North Carolina and its professional team sports. Thus, a suitable title for it could be: \\"North Carolina\\"."},{"source":"Generate short a sentence that can be linguistically classified as acceptable (OPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable)","target":"The two boys looked the word up.","rationale":"Here's an example of a grammatically correct sentence:\\\\nThe two boys looked the word up."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a word, followed by two sentences. Your task is to figure out whether both the sentences use the aforementioned word with the same meaning. You should respond with 'True' if the words in both sentences share the same meaning, and 'False' otherwise.\\n\\nyear \\n Sentence1: In the year 1920. \\n Sentence2: A normal year has 365 full days, but there are 366 days in a leap year.","target":"False","rationale":"The word \\"year\\" is used with different meanings in both sentences. In the first sentence, it refers to a specific point in time, while in the second sentence, it refers to a period of 365 or 366 days. The two meanings are different, so the answer is False."},{"source":"Cell membrane -- The cell membrane (also known as the plasma membrane or cytoplasmic membrane, and historically referred to as the plasmalemma) is a biological membrane that separates the interior of all cells from the outside environment (the extracellular space). It consists of a lipid bilayer with embedded proteins. The basic function of the cell membrane is to protect the cell from its surroundings. The cell membrane controls the movement of substances in and out of cells and organelles. In this way, it is selectively permeable to ions and organic molecules. In addition, cell membranes are involved in a variety of cellular processes such as cell adhesion, ion conductivity and cell signalling and serve as the attachment surface for several extracellular structures, including the cell wall, the carbohydrate layer called the glycocalyx, and the intracellular network of protein fibers called the cytoskeleton. In the field of synthetic biology, cell membranes can be artificially reassembled. \\n\\nHaving read that, could you tell me is the cell membrane inside the cell wall?","target":"No","rationale":"Based on the context, a cell membrane is inside of cells and organelles. On the other hand, a cell wall surrounds plant cells to give them structure and shape as well as provide protection from mechanical stress by microorganisms. So No is correct answer"},{"source":"Here's a complex question that requires someone to reason about the input, can you answer it?\\nWho is the director of the 2012 epic musical drama film, in which Alistair Daniel Brammer appeared?","target":"Tom Hooper","rationale":"Alistair Daniel Brammer played Marius in the 2012 epic musical drama film \\"Les Mis√©rables\\". The director of this movie was Tom Hooper."},{"source":"I want to test the ability of students to read a passage and answer questions about it. Could you please come up with a good question for the passage \\"In India there are many polytechnic institutes and collages that offer a polytechnic education. In India a Diploma in Engineering is a specific academic award usually awarded in technical or vocational courses e.g. Engineering, Pharmacy, Designing, etc. These Institutions offer three year diploma in engineering post Tenth class. These institutes have affiliation from state bord of technical education of respective state governments. after which one can apply for post of junior engineer or continue higher studies by appearing for exams of AMIE to become an engineering graduate.\\"?","target":"What is AMIE?","rationale":"A good question for the passage \\"In India there are many polytechnic institutes and collages that offer a polytechnic education. In India a Diploma in Engineering is a specific academic award usually awarded in technical or vocational courses e.g. Engineering, Pharmacy, Designing, etc. These Institutions offer three year diploma in engineering post Tenth class. These institutes have affiliation from state bord of technical education of respective state governments. after which one can apply for post of junior engineer or continue higher studies by appearing for exams of AMIE to become an engineering graduate.\\" would be: What is AMIE?\\nAll other answers do not require reading comprehension and/or too general (eg 'What does this text describe?')."},{"source":"You are given a mathematical question described with an open-ended vocabulary. Questions in this task involve real-world situations, describing a mathematical problem. You are also given 4 or 5 answer options (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", \\"E\\"). Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'. LaTeX mathematical format (the standard way to express mathematical expressions in the typesetting software known as LaTeX) is used to express equations. Each question is solvable with high school math knowledge. Give only one answer for each question.\\n\\nThere are \\\\(n\\\\) students in a chemistry class, and only \\\\(s\\\\) of them are seniors. If \\\\(j\\\\) juniors are added to the class, what percent of the students in the class will not be seniors?\\n(A)\\\\(\\\\frac { s } { n } \\\\times 100\\\\%\\\\) (B)\\\\(\\\\frac { n - s } { n } \\\\times 100\\\\%\\\\) (C)\\\\(\\\\frac { n } { n + s } \\\\times 100\\\\%\\\\) (D)\\\\(\\\\frac { n - s } { n + j } \\\\times 100\\\\%\\\\) (E)\\\\(\\\\frac { n - s + j } { n + j } \\\\times 100\\\\%\\\\)","target":"E","rationale":"We are told that \\\\(s\\\\) of the \\\\(n\\\\) students are seniors. Thus, there are \\\\(n - s\\\\) non-seniors. If we add \\\\(j\\\\) juniors to the class, then there will be a total of \\\\(n + j\\\\), and since we add only juniors (no new seniors), then there will be a total of \\\\((n - s) + j = n - s + j\\\\). Therefore, the answer is: \\\\(\\\\frac{(n-s)+j}{(n+j)} \\\\times 100\\\\% = \\\\frac{(n-s+j)}{(n+j)} \\\\times 100\\\\% = E)\\\\(\\\\frac { n - s + j } { n + j } \\\\times 100\\\\%\\\\)"},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that start with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'street signs direct the flow of traffic on the street'. How many words start with the letter 's' in the sentence.","target":"3","rationale":"Given the sentence 'street signs direct the flow of traffic on the street', we need to count how many words start with 's'.\\\\n1. The 1st word 'street' starts with s, so count +1 -> (total) 1\\\\n2. The 2nd word 'signs' starts with s, so count +1 -> (total) 2\\\\n3. The 3rd word 'street' starts with s, so count +1 -> (total) 3\\\\n4. All other words do not start with s, so ignore them and continue to next one.\\\\nThe total number of words starting with letter s is 3 in this sentence."},{"source":"Choose your answer: If \\"three people are standing outside.\\", does it logically follow that \\"Three people are standing near each other.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"If three people are standing outside, then they must be near each other. If we consider the fact that \\"outside\\" usually refers to an open area where there is a lot of free space and no walls or buildings in between, it becomes clear that these three people cannot stand far away from one another as they would have been separated by structures if so. So yes, this statement logically follows from the previous sentence."},{"source":"Given a math problem with context and a question and 5 answer choices, the task is to provide the correct answer choice based on the problem. You must choose one of the given answer choices by letter: a, b, c, d, or e; anything else is invalid.\\n\\nProblem: how many liters of water must be added to 18 liters of milk and water containing 10 % water to make it 70 % water ?\\nOptions: a. 28, b. 32, c. 36, d. 40, e. 44","target":"c","rationale":"We want to find out how much pure water (p) we need to add to 18 liters of milk and water containing 10% water, which means that each liter contains 0.1 liter of pure water and 0.9 liters of milk (m). If p + m = 18, then we have 0.1p + 0.9m = 18 Therefore, m=20p/9\\\\nSince the mixture will contain 70% pure water after adding p liters of it, we have: (0.1p+0.9*20*p/9) / (p+18)=0.7\\\\nSolving this equation gives us:\\\\np=36"},{"source":"What is the title of this article:\\n\\nThe original services of an inn are now also available at other establishments, such as hotels, lodges, and motels, which focus more on lodging customers than on other services, although they usually provide meals; pubs, which are primarily alcohol-serving establishments; and restaurants and taverns, which serve food and drink. In North America, the lodging aspect of the word \\"inn\\" lives on in hotel brand names like Holiday Inn, and in some state laws that refer to lodging operators as innkeepers.\\n\\nTitle:","target":"Pub","rationale":"The article is about the origin of inns, and also compares them to other establishments like hotels. The last sentence tells us that \\"pub\\" \\nis an alcohol-serving establishment. Thus a good title for this passage would be Pub"},{"source":"OPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nDoes \\"Romanian-born documentary maker Ilinca Calugareanu wrote a New York Times article telling the story of Irina Margareta Nistor, a narrator for state TV under Nicolae Ceau≈üescu's regime.\\" correctly answer the question of What was Irina Margareta Nistor's job in Romania?","target":"yes","rationale":"The passage tells us that Irina Margareta Nistor was a narrator for state TV under Nicolae Ceau≈üescu's regime, which is the correct answer to What was her job in Romania. So the answer is \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"Given a text passage as input comprising of dialogue of negotiations between a seller and a buyer about the sale of an item, your task is to classify the item being sold into exactly one of these categories: 'housing', 'furniture', 'bike', 'phone', 'car', 'electronics'. The output should be the name of the category from the stated options and there should be exactly one category for the given text passage.\\n\\nBuyer: Hi! I am interested in purchasing this vanity piece!\\nSeller: Hi, I am glad to hear that, any questions?\\nBuyer: Yes in fact! Is the glass inside the piece interchangable? I have a great piece of glass that I would like to replace that with!\\nSeller: I think it may be possible, but I am not sure 100%. If you have the knowledge I would say yes.\\nBuyer: Awesome! I am willing to offer $40 for the piece. How does that sound?\\nSeller: That sounds very low for such high quality. i am wanting to make a deal, but I need at least 60.\\nBuyer: Ok, since the glass is not of my style I am willing to pay $50 and I will also come and pick it up. Ok?\\nSeller: I suppose I can agree to that.\\nSeller: \\nBuyer:","target":"furniture","rationale":"The given dialogue clearly states that a vanity piece is for sale and hence, it falls under the \\"furniture\\" category."},{"source":"Trevor is a comic book illustrator. In the past three months, he has drawn 220 pages of the comic. The comic he illustrates releases a new issue once a month. The first and second months‚Äô issues were the same number of pages, but the third month‚Äôs issue was four pages longer than either of the others. How many pages was the first issue of the comic?","target":"72","rationale":"Let P be the number of pages of the first issue of the comic. The second issue is the same number of pages, so the first and second issues are P + P = 2P pages. The third issue is 4 pages longer, so it is P + 4 pages. All three issues are 2P + P + 4 = 3P + 4 = 220 pages long. Thus, 3P = 220 - 4 = 216 pages. Therefore, the first issue of the comic was P = 216 / 3 = 72 pages."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that contain the given letter\\n\\nSentence: 'a herd of six zebra crossing a road'. How many words contain the letter 'a' in the sentence.","target":"4","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a herd of six zebra crossing a road', let's try one word-by-word.\\\\n1. 'a' : contains 1 -> (total) 1\\\\n2. 'herd' : does not contain -> (total) 1\\\\n3. 'of' : does not contain -> (total) 1\\\\n4. 'six' : contains 1 -> (total) 2\\\\n5. 'zebra' : contains 3 -> (total) 5 \\\\n6. 'crossing': does not contain - >(Total): 5 \\\\n7.'a': contains one - >(Total): 6 \\\\8.'road': toal: 6\\n\\nThe final total number is 6"},{"source":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\n\\nWhich fruit contains more crystallized sugar, plums or apricots?\\n\\nAnn decided to candy half of the fruit he received as a gift. She kept the other half to eat fresh and do juicing. She candied ginger, plums pears, and she didn't candy apples, oranges apricots and bananas.\\n\\nHint: Sugaring is a food preservation method similar to pickling. Sugaring is the process of desiccating a food by first dehydrating it, then packing it with pure sugar. This sugar can be crystalline in the form of table or raw sugar, or it can be a high sugar density liquid such as honey, syrup or molasses.\\n\\nThe purpose of sugaring is to create an environment hostile to microbial life and prevent food spoilage. Sugaring is commonly used to preserve fruits as well as vegetables such as ginger. From time to time sugaring has also been used for non-food preservations. For example, honey was used as part of the mummification process in some ancient Egyptian rites.\\n\\nA risk in sugaring is that sugar itself attracts moisture. Once a sufficient moisture level is reached, native yeast in the environment will come out of dormancy and begin to ferment the sugars into alcohol and carbon dioxide. This leads to the process of fermentation. Although fermentation can be used as a food preservation method, it must be intentionally controlled, or the results will tend to be unpleasant.","target":"plums","rationale":"Ann decided to candy half of the fruit he received as a gift. She kept the other half to eat fresh and do juicing. She candied ginger, plums pears, and she didn't candy apples, oranges apricots and bananas.\\nSo by process of elimination we concluded that \\"plums\\" contains more crystallized sugar than apricots because it was not mentioned in sentence saying which fruits were NOT being sugared/candied.\\""},{"source":"A ploynomial equation is a sum of terms. Here each term is either a constant number, or consists of the variable x raised to a certain power and multiplied by a number. These numbers are called weights. For example, in the polynomial: 2x^2+3x+4, the weights are: 2,3,4. You can present a polynomial with the list of its weights, for example, equation weights = [6, 4] represent the equation 6x + 4 and equation weights = [1, 3, 4] represent the equation 1x^2 + 3x + 4. In this task, you need to compute the result of a polynomial expression by substituing a given value of x in the given polynomial equation. Equation weights are given as a list.\\n\\nx = 5, equation weights = [8, 9]","target":"49","rationale":"The given polynomial equation is: 8x + 9.\\\\nSubstituting x = 5, we get:\\\\n8(5) + 9 = 40 + 9 = 49"},{"source":"DIALOG:\\nDid Earth Crisis have any famous lyrics?\\n- In the words of the academic Jonathan Pieslak, some of Earth Crisis's lyrics read like passages taken from direct-action essays of these institutions.\\n- What was one of Earth Crisis's songs?\\n- Forced March\\n- What were Earth Crisis's views?\\n- Earth Crisis is known for supporting animal rights, promoting a straight edge and vegan lifestyle, and addressing further social and political issues.\\n- What was an example of Earth Crisis's activism?\\n- Earth Crisis have been longtime supporters for organizations such as the Animal Defense League.\\n- What was one of Earth Crisis's greatest successes?\\n-","target":"Lead singer Karl Buechner was invited to address the Congress about teens and substance abuse.","rationale":"The dialog contains information about the band's activism, and the last question is what was one of Earth Crisis's greatest successes. The correct answer must be related to activism and can only be found in the previous sentences. The first option, \\"Earth Crisis has been around since 1989\\" is incorrect as it doesn't relate to their greatest success. The second option, \\"They promote a straight edge lifestyle\\" relates to their views but does not indicate any success so it cannot be chosen either. The third option, \\"Lead singer Karl Buechner was invited to address the Congress about teens and substance abuse.\\" states that one of Earth Crisis' successes is Lead singer Karl Buechner being invited to address Congress which makes this answer most relevant with respect to Earth Crisis' activism as well as their greatest success.\\"\\n\\"\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given an adjective, and your job is to generate its antonym. An antonym of a word is a word opposite in meaning to it.\\n\\noff","target":"on","rationale":"\\"Off\\" and \\"on\\" are antonyms."},{"source":"During the rainy season in a city, the amount of sunlight in the city will\\n\\nA -> stay the same\\n\\nB -> decrease\\n\\nC -> expand\\n\\nD -> increase\\n\\nIs the right answer A, B, C or D ?","target":"B","rationale":"The rainy season is a time period of increased rainfall. Rain clouds block sunlight from reaching the Earth‚Äôs surface, causing less sunlight to reach that area than usual during this time of year. Therefore, it can be inferred that the amount of sunlight in the city will decrease during its rainy season; thus, answer B is correct."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. If the count of numbers is more than that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers Win'. If the count of alphabets is more than that of numbers in the list, answer 'Alphabets Win'. If the count of numbers is same as that of alphabets in the list, answer 'Numbers and Alphabets are Tied'.\\n\\n['d', 'Z', '649', '349', '1369', '7385', 'W', '2895', '2207', 'R', '2281', '3975', '8947', 'y', '915', 'T', 'D', '6305', '8077', '1121', '2535', '9225', '3539', 'V', '6221', '2355', 'I', '6683', '615', 't', '297', '5727', 'c', 'a', '7847', '819']","target":"Numbers Win","rationale":"The given list has 30 total elements, of which 19 are numbers and 11 are alphabets. The number of numbers is greater than the number of alphabets, so the final result would be 'Numbers Win'."},{"source":"Nocturnal emission -- The frequency of nocturnal emissions is highly variable. Some reported that it is due to being sexually inactive for a period of 1--2 weeks, with no engagement in either intercourse or masturbation. Some males have experienced large numbers of nocturnal emissions as teenagers, while others have never experienced one. In the U.S., 83% of men experience nocturnal emissions at some time in their life. For males who have experienced nocturnal emissions the mean frequency ranges from 0.36 times per week (about once every three weeks) for single 15-year-old males to 0.18 times per week (about once every five-and-a-half weeks) for 40-year-old single males. For married males the mean ranges from 0.23 times per week (about once per month) for 19-year-old married males to 0.15 times per week (about once every two months) for 50-year-old married males. In some parts of the world nocturnal emissions are more common. For example, in Indonesia surveys have shown that 97% of men experience nocturnal emissions by the age of 24. \\n\\nHaving read that, I wonder is it normal to have wet dreams at 17?","target":"Yes","rationale":"According to the passage, 83% of males experience wet dreams at some point in their lives. The mean frequency for single 15-year-old males is 0.36 times per week (about once every three weeks). This suggests that it is normal to have a wet dream at 17 years old and younger because they occur so often at this age group.\\nTherefore, the answer is Yes."},{"source":"Adverse drug reactions are appreciably harmful or unpleasant reactions resulting from an intervention related to the use of medical products, which predicts hazard from future administration and warrants prevention or specific treatment, or alteration of the dosage regimen, or withdrawal of the product. Given medical case reports extracted from MEDLINE, the task is to classify whether the case report mentions the presence of any adverse drug reaction. Classify your answers into non-adverse drug event and adverse drug event.\\n\\nWe describe a patient with transitional cell carcinoma of the renal pelvis who developed respiratory dysfunction and an abnormal chest x-ray with diffuse interstitial opacities while on chemotherapy with piritrexim, a methotrexate analog.","target":"adverse drug event","rationale":"The patient developed respiratory dysfunction and an abnormal chest x-ray with diffuse interstitial opacities while on chemotherapy with piritrexim, which is considered as a reaction resulting from the drug. So, this case report mentions the presence of adverse drug event."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios. Note that there are distractor sentences in each story that are unrelated to the question and are designed to confuse the reader.\\n\\nMia entered the kitchen. Olivia entered the kitchen. The grapes is in the red_drawer. Olivia exited the kitchen. Mia moved the grapes to the blue_envelope. Mia exited the kitchen. Olivia entered the kitchen. Olivia entered the pantry. Mia entered the pantry. The spinach is in the blue_box. Mia exited the pantry. Phone rang. Olivia moved the spinach to the red_box. Olivia exited the pantry. Mia entered the pantry. William entered the sunroom. Olivia entered the sunroom. The banana is in the green_bottle. Olivia exited the sunroom. William moved the banana to the blue_bathtub. William exited the sunroom. Olivia entered the sunroom. William entered the study. Mia entered the study. The asparagus is in the green_cupboard. Mia exited the study. William moved the asparagus to the green_suitcase. William exited the study. Mia entered the study. Where was the asparagus at the beginning?","target":"green_cupboard","rationale":"The question asks you to determine where the asparagus was at the beginning of the story. The answer is green_cupboard because Mia entered the study and sees that the asparagus is in the green_cupboard."},{"source":"Can you tell me the answer to who wrote the music for ladies in lavender??","target":"Nigel Hess","rationale":"\\"Ladies in Lavender\\" is the theme song of a movie with the same title, and it was composed by Nigel Hess."},{"source":"What relationship does the narrator share with Kevin ?","target":"They go to the same job .","rationale":"The narrator is talking about a person named Kevin who works with her. Since there are two people, it means that they go to the same job .\\nInitial answer: They go to the same job ."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWhen was Otto Von Bismarck dismissed by Wilhelm II, German Emperor?\\n- In 1890.\\n- Who replaced Otto Von Bismarck after he was dismissed?\\n- Bismarck resigned at Wilhelm II's insistence in 1890, to be succeeded as Chancellor of Germany and Minister-President of Prussia by Leo von Caprivi.\\n- what reason did  Wilhelm II, German Emperor have for dismissing Otto Von Bismark?\\n-","target":"Wilhelm wanted to preclude the emergence of another Iron Chancellor.","rationale":"Wilhelm wanted to preclude the emergence of another Iron Chancellor."},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nSolution First, write out the electron configuration for each parent atom. We have chosen to show the full, unabbreviated configurations to provide more practice for students who want it, but listing the coreabbreviated electron configurations is also acceptable. Next, determine whether an electron is gained or lost. Remember electrons are negatively charged, so ions with a positive charge have lost an electron. For main group elements, the last orbital gains or loses the electron. For transition metals, the last s orbital loses an electron before the d orbitals. (a) Na: 1s22s22p63s1. Sodium cation loses one electron, so Na+: 1s22s22p63s1 = Na+: 1s22s22p6. (b) P: 1s22s22p63s23p3. Phosphorus trianion gains three electrons, so P3‚àí: 1s22s22p63s23p6. (c) Al: 1s22s22p63s23p1. Aluminum dication loses two electrons Al2+: 1s22s22p63s23p1 = Al2+: 1s22s22p63s1. (d) Fe: 1s22s22p63s23p64s23d6. Iron(II) loses two electrons and, since it is a transition metal, they are removed from the 4s orbital Fe2+: 1s22s22p63s23p64s23d6 = 1s22s22p63s23p63d6. Sm: 1s22s22p63s23p64s23d104p65s24d105p66s24f6. Samarium trication loses three electrons. The first two will be lost from the 6s orbital, and the final one is removed from the 4f orbital. Sm3+: 1s22s22p63s23p64s23d104p65s24d105p66s24f6 = 1s22s22p63s23p64s23d104p65s24d105p64f5.\\n\\n\\nQ: Remember electrons are negatively charged, so ions with a positive charge have lost what?\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- proton\\n\\n- neutron\\n\\n- atom\\n\\n- electron\\n\\nA:","target":"electron","rationale":"An atom is composed of protons, neutrons and electrons. Protons have a positive charge while the neutron has no charge at all. Electrons are negatively charged particles that orbit around an atomic nucleus in shells (or energy levels). When one or more electrons are removed from an atom it becomes positively charged because there's now less negative charges than positive ones in the atoms as whole. The answer to this question then must be \\"electron\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given an answer to a question. You need to generate a question. The answer given should be a correct answer for the generated question.\\n\\nElastic fibers are found in the skin, lungs, arteries, veins, connective tissue proper, elastic cartilage, periodontal ligament, fetal tissue and other structures. Elastic fibers are absent from scarring, keloids and dermatofibromas and they are decreased greatly, or are absent in anetodermas.","target":"where is elastic tissue found in the body","rationale":"The answer provides information about where elastic tissue is found in the body.  Therefore, a question that can be answered with this information is \\"where is elastic tissue found in the body\\"."},{"source":"Which entity is this text about?\\n\\nChristopher Keith Irvine was born on November 9, 1970 in Manhasset, New York. His father, ice hockey player Ted Irvine, had relocated there to play for the New York Rangers. When his father retired, they moved back to Winnipeg, Manitoba. Irvine is of Scottish descent on his father's side.\\n\\nJericho lost the Intercontinental title to the then European Champion Kurt Angle at No Way Out. Jericho competed in a Triple Threat match against Chris Benoit and Angle at WrestleMania 2000 in a two-falls contest with both of Angle's titles at stake. Jericho won the European Championship by pinning Benoit, who in turn pinned Jericho to win the Intercontinental Championship. This was the first of six pay-per-view matches between the pair within twelve months. Jericho was originally supposed to be in the main event of WrestleMania, but was taken out after Mick Foley, who was originally asked by writers to be in the match, took his place. Jericho was even advertised on the event's posters promoting the match. Jericho lost the title the next day to Eddie Guerrero on Raw after Chyna turned heel to side with Guerrero.  On the April 17 episode of Raw, Jericho upset Triple H in a WWF Championship match. Referee Earl Hebner made a fast count when Jericho pinned Triple H, causing Jericho to win the title. Hebner later reversed the decision due to pressure from Triple H, and WWE does not recognize Jericho's reign as champion. On the May 4 episode of SmackDown!, Jericho defeated Benoit to win his third Intercontinental Championship but lost the title to Benoit four days later on Raw. Jericho's feud with Triple H ended at Fully Loaded, when they competed in a Last Man Standing match. Jericho lost the match to Triple H only by one second, despite the repeated assistance Triple H's wife, Stephanie, provided him in the match.  At the 2001 Royal Rumble, Jericho defeated Chris Benoit in a ladder match to win the Intercontinental Championship for the fourth time. At WrestleMania X-Seven, he successfully defended his title in a match against William Regal, only to lose it four days later to Triple H. At Judgment Day, Jericho and Benoit won a tag team turmoil match and earned a shot at Stone Cold Steve Austin and Triple H for their WWF Tag Team Championship on Raw the next night. Benoit and Jericho won the match, in which Triple H legitimately tore his quadriceps, spending the rest of the year injured. Benoit and Jericho each became a WWF Tag Team Champion for the first time. The team defended their title in the first fatal four-way Tables, Ladders and Chairs match, where Benoit sustained a year-long injury after missing a diving headbutt through a table. Despite Benoit being carried out on a stretcher, he returned to the match to climb the ladder and retain the championship. The two lost the title one month later to The Dudley Boyz on June 19, 2001. At King of the Ring, both Benoit and Jericho competed in a triple threat match for Austin's WWF Championship, in which Booker T interfered as the catalyst for The Invasion angle. Despite Booker T's interference, Austin retained the title.\\n\\nEntity:","target":"Chris Jericho","rationale":"The given text is an article about Chris Jericho. Throughout the passage, it mentions details of his personal life and career so we can infer that this passage must be talking about Chris Jericho himself."},{"source":"Angela is driving on a highway. She is stuck between two cars but needs to get to the off ramp and decides to speed up. She hits the gas making her car go faster so she can get ahead of the two cars she is stuck in between and makes it to the ramp in time.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nGiven Angela decided decelerate instead would her car have gone faster or slower?","target":"slower","rationale":"The paragraph mentions that Angela needs to speed up in order to get ahead of two cars, which she does by accelerating her car. Deceleration is the opposite of acceleration, so if Angela had instead decided decelerate would have gone slower, making this choice correct."},{"source":"Sentence 1: \\"All the buttons up the back of Dora's plaid dress were buttoned outside-in. Maude should have thought to button her up; but no, she had left poor little Dora to do the best she could, alone.\\"\\n\\n Sentence 2: \\"She had left poor little Dora to do the best Maude could, alone.\\"\\n\\nIs sentence 2 true, based on sentence 1?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- no\\n- yes","target":"no","rationale":"Although the second sentence is grammatically correct and flows well, we must remember that it was said in reference to the first statement. In this case, there are two major differences: not only does Maude's name appear twice in place of Dora's (a simple spelling error), but \\"best she could\\" has been replaced with \\"best Maude could\\". The difference between these two phrases changes the meaning significantly; whereas one implies a lack of care by one person for another, the other turns that notion on its head by implying someone else cared enough about Dora to try their very best at helping her out."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify whether the sentence is a question or not. Answer with Yes or No.\\n\\nYes, that is correct. How expensive is this place?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The given sentence is a yes or no question as it can be answered with a simple 'yes' or 'no'. Hence, the answer is \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"If \\"Three young adults look towards the camera in a school setting.\\", does this mean that \\"A man washes dishes.\\"?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise does not contain any information about a man washing dishes, so it is impossible to determine whether the statement in question is true or false."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What is the name of the person that nevertheless had a lasting impact on photography in Japan?\\n\\nRossier first arrived in Japan in 1859, at a time when early experiments in photography were being conducted in Ky≈´sh≈´, particularly in Nagasaki. The city was the centre of rangaku, the study of Western science, and it was here that physicians Jan Karel van den Broek and J. L. C. Pompe van Meerdervoort were instrumental in teaching their Japanese students not only medicine but also chemistry and photography. Neither Van den Broek nor Pompe van Meerdervoort was an experienced photographer, and their attempts to produce photographs were largely failures. Nevertheless, in turn they taught wet-collodion process photography to Keisai Yoshio, Furukawa Shumpei, Kawano Teiz≈ç, Maeda Genz≈ç, Ueno Hikoma, and Horie Kuwajir≈ç, among others.On his arrival in Japan, Rossier presumably introduced himself as a photographer despatched to Japan by Negretti and Zambra, perhaps thereby inspiring a misconception, for while he remained in the country he was often referred to as an \\"English\\" photographer. In Nagasaki, Rossier was assisted in his work by Maeda Genz≈ç, who had been instructed to accompany the \\"Englishman\\" and to further learn photography. With Maeda and other students escorting him around the city, Rossier took photographs of priests, beggars, the audience of a sumo match, the foreign settlement, and the group portrait of Alexander von Siebold and samurai. Rossier believed that Pompe van Meerdervoort's failures in photography were due to a lack of the necessary chemicals and so he provided Maeda with a letter of recommendation to procure photographic apparatus and chemicals from a source in Shanghai. Both Maeda and Furukawa bought lenses, chemicals and albumen paper through Rossier.At this time, Ueno Hikoma and Horie Kuwajir≈ç also received photographic instruction from Rossier. Apparently Ueno had originally intended to learn not only the practice of photography but also the manufacture of cameras. The encounter with Rossier seems to have convinced Ueno to pursue photography as a career, but he was so overwhelmed by the...","target":"Rossier","rationale":"The paragraph is about photography in Japan. The word \\"Nevertheless\\" implies that Rossier had a lasting impact on it despite the fact that early experiments in photography were being conducted by other people such as physicians Jan Karel van den Broek and J. L. C. Pompe van Meerdervoort, who taught wet-collodion process to Keisai Yoshio, Furukawa Shumpei, Kawano Teiz≈ç, Maeda Genz≈ç, Ueno Hikoma and Horie Kuwajir≈ç among others but whose attempts to produce photographs were largely failures so Rossier was referred to as an English photographer for he provided chemicals through which made him have a lasting impact on japanese photographers including Maeda Genz≈ç (whom he assisted), Fur"},{"source":"You will be given a passage with an enumerated set of facts, a question of form 'Where is <person_name>?', and its answer. The task is to identify a supporting fact that is necessary to answer the question. The output would be the corresponding fact number.\\n\\nPassage: Fact 1- Mary travelled to the garden. Fact 2- Daniel went to the garden. Fact 3- Mary journeyed to the kitchen. Fact 4- Mary went back to the hallway. Fact 5- Daniel travelled to the office. Fact 6- Daniel moved to the garden. Fact 7- Sandra went back to the kitchen. Fact 8- John travelled to the bathroom. Question: Where is Mary? Answer: hallway","target":"Fact 4","rationale":"According to Fact 4, Mary went back to the hallway."},{"source":"Found the following article online, use it to answer the question: Who do Baxter and Crumley suggest, \\"has kept for himself only the best pieces and woven around them a plot as evidence of his madness\\"?\\n\\nThe islands are composed of Tertiary igneous formations of granites and gabbro, heavily weathered by the elements. The archipelago represents the remnants of a long-extinct ring volcano rising from a seabed plateau approximately 40 metres (130 ft) below sea level.At 670 hectares (1,700 acres) in extent, Hirta is the largest island in the group and comprises more than 78% of the land area of the archipelago. Next in size are Soay (English: \\"sheep island\\") at 99 hectares (240 acres) and Boreray ('the fortified isle'), which measures 86 hectares (210 acres). Soay is 0.5 kilometres (0.31 mi) north-west of Hirta, Boreray 6 kilometres (4 mi) to the northeast. Smaller islets and stacks in the group include Stac an Armin ('warrior's stack'), Stac Lee ('grey stack') and Stac Levenish ('stream' or 'torrent'). The island of D√πn ('fort'), which protects Village Bay from the prevailing southwesterly winds, was at one time joined to Hirta by a natural arch. MacLean (1972) suggests that the arch was broken when struck by a galleon fleeing the defeat of the Spanish Armada, but other sources, such as Mitchell (1992) and Fleming (2005), suggest that the arch was simply swept away by one of the many fierce storms that batter the islands every winter.\\nThe highest point in the archipelago, Conachair ('the beacon') at 430 metres (1,410 ft), is on Hirta, immediately north of the village. In the southeast is Oiseval ('east fell'), which reaches 290 metres (950 ft), and Mullach M√≤r ('big hill summit') 361 metres (1,185 ft) is due west of Conachair. Ruival ('red fell') 137 metres (449 ft) and Mullach Bi ('pillar summit') 358 metres (1,175 ft) dominate the western cliffs. Boreray reaches 384 metres (1,260 ft) and Soay 378 metres (1,240 ft). The extraordinary Stac an Armin reaches 196 metres (643 ft), and Stac Lee, 172 metres (564 ft), making them the highest sea stacks in Britain.\\nIn modern times, St Kilda's only settlement was at Village Bay (Scottish Gaelic: B√†gh a' Bhaile or Loch Hiort) on Hirta. Gleann M√≤r on the north coast of...","target":"God","rationale":"The article discusses St Kilda, an archipelago of islands located in Scotland. The answer is related to the name \\"St Kilda\\", which was not mentioned explicitly in this passage (although it does appear elsewhere on the same webpage).\\nBaxter and Crumley suggest that God has kept for himself only the best pieces of St Kilda and woven around them a plot as evidence of his madness."},{"source":"Combine facts and answer this: Arjun Kapoor and Boney Kapoor are both in which country's film industry?","target":"India","rationale":"Arjun Kapoor is an Indian actor and Boney Kapoor, who was a producer for Arjun's first movie in 2012, \\"Ishaqzaade\\" has produced many movies in India.\\nTherefore, the answer should be \\"India\\"."},{"source":"(CNN) -- Deposed Honduran President Jose Manuel Zelaya will not be reinstated as head of state, an overwhelming majority of the Honduran congress voted Wednesday. In an hours-long process, 111 lawmakers voted in favor of a motion not to return Zelaya to office. A majority of 65 votes in the 128-member body was required to reject his reinstatement. Zelaya was removed from office in a military-led coup on June 28 and replaced by congressional leader Roberto Micheletti. On Wednesday, lawmakers voted one by one and addressed the chamber as they cast their vote, making for a slow process. The vote was a key part of a U.S.-brokered pact that representatives for Zelaya and Micheletti signed October 29, giving Congress the power to decide Zelaya's fate. The United States expressed disappointment Thursday over the latest rebuff to its diplomatic efforts to end the political crisis in Honduras. U.S. Assistant Secretary of State for Western Hemisphere Affairs Arturo Valenzuela continued to call on the Honduran government to allow Zelaya's return and to create a unity government in the interim period before the new president takes office next month. \\"We are disappointed by this decision since the United States had hoped the [Honduran] Congress would have approved his return,\\" Valenzuela said in a conference call with journalists in Washington. \\"Our policy since June 28 has been consistently principled. It has condemned the coup d'etat and continued to accept President Zelaya as the democratically elected and legitimate leader of Honduras throughout this political crisis.\\" The United States continues to call for Honduras to engage in national reconciliation and creation of a truth commission to investigate the crisis, in addition to the unity government. \\"The absence of democratic, constitutional order is the unacceptable status quo,\\" a senior U.S. administration official said on the conference call, remaining anonymous under the ground rules of the call and because of the sensitivity of the situation. \\"The election is a...\\n\\nQuestion: Why was voting going slow for the 128-member body?\\nI think \\"Many lawmaker were indecisive\\" is a valid answer. Could you confirm? Yes or no?","target":"No","rationale":"The sentence \\"In an hours-long process, 111 lawmakers voted in favor of a motion not to return Zelaya to office. A majority of 65 votes in the 128-member body was required to reject his reinstatement\\" suggests that each lawmaker had ample time to decide on their vote and then cast it, rather than being indecisive about how they should vote.\\nSo, No is the correct answer"},{"source":"Problem: Solve -492*f + 38 = -534*f + 248 for f.\\nAnd the answer is...","target":"5","rationale":"To solve for f, we need to isolate the variable on one side of the equation.\\n\\nStarting with:\\n\\n-492*f + 38 = -534*f + 248\\n\\n We can simplify this equation by adding 534*f to both sides and combining like terms:\\n\\n 42 = -4*f+248  [Subtracting 4 from both sides]\\\\n42/4=62 [-4 was divided in each term]\\\\n10.5=18-[39 is subtracted from 62 since it's negative ] \\\\n3=[8 is added since 18 had a minus sign] \\\\nthen lastly divide 3 by 8 which equals .375; therefore your answer would be 0.375 because there are no other numbers that multiply out together"},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a sentence, and you should determine whether it is overruling or non-overruling. In law, an overruling sentence is a statement that nullifies a previous case decision as a precedent by a constitutionally valid statute or a decision by the same or higher ranking court which establishes a different rule on the point of law involved. Classify your answers into overruling or non-overruling\\n\\nwe went on to state that \\"any statement or intimation to the contrary in our prior decisions in ellis and mitchell is hereby expressly disapproved.\\"","target":"overruling","rationale":"The sentence states that the court is disapproving a previous rule that had been established on the same topic. This amounts to an overruling, which means that the earlier case is no longer valid as legal precedent."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\nthe earth be sacred to our people every rain drop every cloud every song of a bird and blossom in a tree the earth have brother and sisiters the earth 's moon be our be sister the sun eagle and the lightning in a storm these our be brother these be all part of one family just like we be","target":"elementary","rationale":"The poem is written in a simple language that is commonly used by younger children. The sentence structure and grammar also suggests that the author of the poem may be a young child. Therefore, we can infer that the kid who wrote this poem is likely to be in elementary school."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Terence Michael Joseph \\"Geezer\\" Butler (born 17 July 1949) is an English musician and songwriter. Butler is best known as the bassist and primary lyricist of the heavy metal band Black Sabbath. He has also recorded with Heaven & Hell, GZR, and Ozzy Osbourne.\\n\\n- John Michael \\"Ozzy\\" Osbourne (born 3 December 1948) is an English singer, songwriter, and actor. He rose to prominence in the early 1970s as the lead vocalist of the heavy metal band Black Sabbath. He was fired from Black Sabbath in 1979 and went on to have a successful solo career, releasing 11 studio albums, the first seven of which were all awarded multi-platinum certifications in the US. Osbourne has since reunited with Black Sabbath on several occasions, recording the album \\"13\\" in 2013. His longevity and success have earned him the informal title of \\"Godfather of Heavy Metal\\". \\n\\n- Blues rock is a fusion genre combining elements of blues and rock. It is mostly an electric ensemble-style music with instrumentation similar to electric blues and rock. From its beginnings in the early- to mid-1960s, blues rock has gone through several stylistic shifts and along the way inspired hard rock, Southern rock, and heavy metal. Blues rock continues to be an influence, with performances and recordings by several popular artists.\\n\\n- Anthony Frank \\"Tony\\" Iommi (born 19 February 1948) is an English guitarist, songwriter and producer. He is the lead guitarist and founding member of the heavy metal band Black Sabbath, and has been the band's sole continual member and primary composer.\\n\\n- Mythology were an English blues band based in Carlisle that formed in early 1967 , out of The Square Chex . The band featured future Black Sabbath founding members Tony Iommi and Bill Ward .\\n\\n- Black Sabbath are an English rock band, formed in Birmingham in 1968, by guitarist and main songwriter Tony Iommi, bassist and main lyricist Geezer Butler, singer Ozzy Osbourne, and drummer Bill Ward. The band have since experienced multiple line-up changes, with guitarist Iommi being the only constant presence in the band through the years. Originally formed as a blues rock band, the group soon adopted the Black Sabbath moniker and began incorporating occult themes with horror-inspired lyrics and tuned-down guitars. Despite an association with these two themes, Black Sabbath also composed songs dealing with social instability, political corruption, the dangers of drug abuse and apocalyptic prophecies of the horrors of war.\\n\\n- Birmingham is a major city and metropolitan borough of West Midlands, England. It is the largest and most populous British city outside London, with a population in 2014 of 1,101,360. The city is in the West Midlands Built-up Area, the third most populous urban area in the United Kingdom, with a population of 2,440,986 at the 2011 census. Birmingham's metropolitan area is the second most populous in the UK with a population of 3.8 million. This also makes Birmingham the 9th most populous metropolitan area in Europe.\\n\\n\\n\\nAfter reading the paragraphs above, choose the best answer for the entity that related to 'mythology ' with the relationship of 'genre'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- album\\n - blues\\n - blues rock\\n - genre\\n - heavy metal\\n - horror\\n - rock\\n - southern rock\\n - urban\\n - war","target":"blues rock","rationale":"The paragraph about Mythology includes the text \\"formed... out of The Square Chex\\" and \\"the group soon adopted the Black Sabbath moniker and began incorporating occult themes with horror-inspired lyrics and tuned-down guitars\\". This suggests that a main characteristic of this band was to combine blues rock music with elements of heavy metal (such as occult or dark themes, guitar tuning) in their songs.\\nMythology is defined by Wikipedia as an English blues band, which supports this finding. In addition, other paragraphs discuss Tony Iommi's involvement with both Mythology and Black Sabbath -- two bands known for combining blues rock elements into traditional heavy metal genres. These contextual clues support Blues Rock being related to Mythology's genre based on these connections within the context provided above."},{"source":"The task is to generate text based of an event. For the given event, there will be a person who does the action in the event (usually PersonX). Your task is to write that persons emotional reaction to the event, i.e. how that person feels after doing the action.\\n\\nPersonX achieves PersonY understanding","target":"knowledgeable","rationale":"The person who achieves PersonY understanding is PersonX. Since we are asked to write how that person feels after doing the action, we need to specify the emotion of PersonX. In this case, they are knowledgeable."},{"source":"Read the following article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: A great way for teens to cool off during the summer is at water parks. If you live near a water park, you might think about getting a season pass. This way you can go as often as you like.\\nCheck to see if there are any water parks around you. Many are indoor facilities. So even if it isn't warm enough where you live to swim outdoors, you can enjoy swimming in a temperature controlled area.\\nThe prices are usually good. For example, one ticket to Water World, a water park, is only $5.\\nSome teens like to get a part time job over the summer to make some pocket money. Older teens shouldn't have much trouble finding jobs.\\nAn idea is to get some teens together to form your own summer job business. You can walk dogs, bring in the newspapers, feed the cats, collect rubbish, water flowers, etc.\\nBeing that it's summer, many people go on vacation and could use someone to look after their houses while they're away. You can also think about other jobs you can do for them.\\nTeens love freedom. Sure you would like to get to such places as the small, movie theaters, the zoo, the beach, picnic, bowling and local amusement park instead of staying home all summer. Then a summer bus pass will be helpful. Check to see if your area has one for you teens.\\nSuch a pass costs only $10 for the whole summer. The price is reasonable  and also your parents don't have to always drive.\\nQuestion: What is NOT mentioned as a part tome job for teens?\\n- Washing cars\\n- Feeding cats\\n- Walking dogs\\n- Watering flowers","target":"Washing cars","rationale":"The article mentions that teens can form their own business to make some pocket money in the summer. The jobs they could do include walking dogs, bringing in newspapers, feeding cats, collecting rubbish and watering flowers. Washing cars is not mentioned as one of these tasks. So washing cars is NOT a part time job for teens referenced in this article making it the best answer choice\\nSo the answer is Washing Cars"},{"source":"You are given a dialog between 2 or more individuals. Within the dialog, there will be clues as to the names of the speakers. You will be asked at the end of the dialog to identify the name of one of the speakers.\\n\\nSpeaker 1:: Hey Duck, is Chick here? \\nSpeaker 2: Yeah... Bunny-rabbit. \\nSpeaker 3: So you ah, ready for our last practice? \\nSpeaker 1:: Yeah, but y'know, I think the reason we're not getting that spin right is because my apartment's too small. \\nSpeaker 3: Look, you wanna use our place? \\nSpeaker 1:: No, I ahh, had another idea. What is the name or nickname of \\nSpeaker 3?","target":"Chick","rationale":"The name of the third speaker is Chick. This can be inferred from the initial greeting made by Speaker 1 to Speaker 2, \\"Hey Duck, is Chick here?\\""},{"source":"Given an entity as input, output another entity which is part of the input entity. These are entities of meronym. In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., output entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., input entity).\\n\\nmidge","target":"leg","rationale":"Midges are small flies, and one of their parts is the leg. Therefore, leg is a meronym of midge."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of integers. You should remove any integer that is not prime. A prime integer is an integer that is only divisible by '1' and itself. The output should be the list of prime numbers in the input list. If there are no primes in the input list an empty list (\\"[]\\") should be returned.\\n\\n[523, 148, 903, 924, 745, 781, 541, 194, 948, 102, 643, 501, 618, 761, 47]","target":"[523, 541, 643, 761, 47]","rationale":"In the given list, only some integers are primes. Therefore, this is the final list of primes: [523, 541, 643, 761, 47]."},{"source":"Given a question, generate a paraphrase of that question wihout changing the meaning of it. Your answer should reword the given sentence, but not add information to it or remove information from it. The answer to your question should be the same as the answer to the original question.\\n\\nQuestion: what actress won the oscar in 1986?","target":"best actress 1986?","rationale":"The original question was \\"what actress won the oscar in 1986?\\" This could be paraphrased as \\"best actress 1986?\\"."},{"source":"Some of the buildings around the city square in the Kota also date from colonial times, including the old city hall ( 1710 ), which has been restored and now serves as the municipal museum.\\n\\nBased on that paragraph can we conclude that the sentence below is true?\\nIn the Old City are the old port, the Dutch town hall, and a square.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"A full reading of the paragraph shows that some buildings date from colonial times, but not all. Therefore, it is incorrect to conclude that \\"In the Old City are the old port...\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given a debate topic, along with a sentence from the debate. You should classify the given sentence and choose the type of that sentence. Possible types are explained below.\\nPolicy: This refers to a sentence proposing a specific course of action to be taken. It typically contains modal verbs like \\"should\\" and \\"ought to\\". It cannot be directly proved with objective evidence, and a proper type of support is a logical reason from which the proposition can be inferred.\\nValue: This refers to a sentence containing value judgments without making specific claims about what should be done (If so, then it is a Policy sentence.). Because of the subjectivity of value judgments, it cannot be proved directly with objective evidence.\\nFact: This refers to an objective proposition expressing or dealing with facts or conditions as perceived without distortion by personal feelings, prejudices, or interpretations. A Fact sentence has a truth value that can be verified with objective evidence that may be available at the time the claim is made; predictions about future are considered unverifiable.\\nTestimony: This refers to an objective sentence about the author's personal state or experience. Evidence for Testimony is not publicly available in most cases.\\n\\ntopic: iPods are taking the magic out of music.\\nsentence: The iPod solves that, thus adding value.","target":"Value","rationale":"The sentence states the author's opinion that iPods are adding value to music, but it does not propose any specific course of action. This is an example of a Value sentence."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a statement spoken by a politician in natural language and the subject of the discussion for the given statement. Your task is to determine if the given subject of the discussion is correct for the given statement. The subject can be multiple words. Answer with \\"True\\" if it's the correct subject of discussion or return \\"False\\" if it's incorrect.\\n\\nStatement: Polling shows that nearly 74 percent of National Rifle Association members support requiring background checks for all gun sales. \\n Subject: education","target":"False","rationale":"The subject of discussion in the statement is education, but the politician is talking about background checks for gun sales. Therefore, the answer is False."},{"source":"Question: Helen can slide her pillow faster across her floor then across her bed. This means that her _____ is the lumpier of the two surfaces (A) bed (B) floor\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"floor\\" and  \\"bed\\".","target":"floor","rationale":"The pillow can slide faster across the floor than it can across her bed. This means that, relative to her bed, Helen's floor is lumpier in texture and rougher. The answer is therefore \\"floor\\"."},{"source":"\\"That's Glenn Miller,\\" my father said. \\"But it can't be.\\"\\nHe had the back of the hospital bed cranked upright, the lower lid of his left eye creeping up in a warning signal I'd learned to recognize as a child. My older sister Ann had settled deep in the recliner, and she glared at me too, blaming me for winding him up. The jam box sat on the rolling tray table and my father was working the remote as he talked, backing up my newly burned CD and letting it spin forward to play a few seconds of low fidelity trombone solo.\\n\\"You know the tune, of course,\\" he said.\\n\\"'King Porter Stomp.'\\" Those childhood years of listening to him play Glenn Miller on the console phonograph were finally paying off.\\n\\"He muffed the notes the same way on the Victor version.\\"\\n\\"So why can't it be Miller?\\" I asked.\\n\\"He wouldn't have played with a rabble like that.\\" The backup musicians teetered on the edge of chaos, playing with an abandon somewhere between Dixieland and bebop. \\"They sound drunk.\\"\\nMy father had a major emotional investment in Miller. He and my mother had danced to the Miller band at Glen Island Casino on Long Island Sound in the summer of 1942, when they were both sixteen. That signature sound of clarinet and four saxes was forever tied up for him with first love and the early, idealistic months of the war.\\nBut there was a better reason why it couldn't have been Miller playing that solo. If the date on the original recording was correct, he was supposed to have died three days earlier.\\nThe date was in India ink on a piece of surgical tape, stuck to the top of a spool of recording wire. The handwritten numerals had the hooks and day-first order of Europe: 18/12/44. I'd won it on eBay the week before as part of a lot that included a wire recorder and a stack of 78s by French pop stars like Charles Trenent and Edith Piaf.\\nWho is the most concerned about the father's health?\\nPick the correct answer from the following options:\\n- Ann\\n- The narrator\\n- Glenn Miller\\n- not enough information","target":"Ann","rationale":"The question asks about the person most concerned about the narrator's father.\\nAnn is mentioned only once in passing, when it says that she has \\"settled deep into a recliner\\" and was glaring at me, blaming me for winding up our father. She does not appear to be engaged with her surroundings or interact too much with others in the room (other than glare). This makes us think Ann might be less involved or interested compared to other characters as this information suggests that she is focused on herself - instead of helping out by talking to their dad, changing his clothes etc., which would show concern towards him.\\nBecause of these reasons we can rule out option A: Ann isn't very bothered because she doesn't do anything helpful but sits back and glares without interacting further unless necessary"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a statement spoken by a politician in natural language and the subject of the discussion for the given statement. Your task is to determine if the given subject of the discussion is correct for the given statement. The subject can be multiple words. Answer with \\"True\\" if it's the correct subject of discussion or return \\"False\\" if it's incorrect.\\n\\nStatement: Donald Trump and Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders have the identical position on health care, which is they want to put the government in charge of you and your doctor. \\n Subject: health-care","target":"True","rationale":"In the given statement, Donald Trump and Hillary Clinton and Bernie Sanders are described as having the same position on health care. The subject of discussion for this statement is \\"health-care,\\" which is correct. Therefore, the answer is True."},{"source":"In this task, you will be given two sentences separated by \\"because\\". You should decide whether the first sentence can be the result of the second sentence. If you can see a possible cause and effect relationship, answer with \\"plausible\\", otherwise answer with \\"not plausible\\".\\n\\nthe window was opaque because it was the only one that was clear","target":"not plausible","rationale":"The first sentence implies that the window is not transparent and the second sentence states that it was the only one that was clear. These two sentences are contradictory, so they are not plausible."},{"source":"In this task, you need to remove all words of a given length in the sentence. The number of letters in a word determine its length, for example, the length of the word \\"apple\\" is 5.\\n\\nSentence: 'a square white plate with vegetables and sprinkled seasonings on top'. Remove all words of length '3' in the given sentence.","target":"a square white plate with vegetables sprinkled seasonings on","rationale":"Given the sentence 'a square white plate with vegetables and sprinkled seasonings on top', if the word length is 3, then we need to remove these words: 'and' and 'top'. The resulting string after removing them is \\"a square white plate with vegetables sprinkled seasonings on\\"."},{"source":"You are given a sentence from a conversation between a human and a virtual assistant. Your task is to identify which one of following five services the sentence is related to - Media, Travel, Flights, Buses, RideSharing\\n\\nCould you look up round trip flights for me? Id like to return on next Monday, and I prefer to travel in premium economy.","target":"Flights","rationale":"The given sentence is related to flights. It references round trip flights and a return on a specific day of the week, next Monday. The sentence also references premium economy travel which would be an option for Flights but not Buses or RideSharing. A user could ask about a return flight in premium economy using Media or Travel but not specifically asking for Flights"},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"In 2014, the league announced the granting of a new franchise to former M√∂tley Cr√ºe frontman Vince Neil, previously part-owner of the Jacksonville Sharks. That franchise, the Las Vegas Outlaws, were originally to play in Las Vegas at the MGM Grand Garden Arena in 2015, but instead played their home games at the Thomas & Mack Center, previous home to the Las Vegas Sting and Las Vegas Gladiators. After 20 years as a familiar name to the league, an AFL mainstay, the Iowa Barnstormers, departed the league to join the Indoor Football League. The San Antonio Talons folded on October 13, 2014, after the league (which owned the team) failed to find a new owner. On November 16, 2014, despite a successful season record-wise, the Pittsburgh Power became the second team to cease operations after the 2014 season. This resulted from poor attendance. It was later announced by the league that the Power would go dormant for 2015 and were looking for new ownership.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What did Pittsburgh Power do they searched for a buyer?","target":"go dormant","rationale":"The passage mentions that the Pittsburgh Power were looking for a new owner. However, completing their search took longer than expected and they had to \\"go dormant\\" until one was found. The answer is go dormant - which means: become inactive or not be in use anymore; engaging in little or no activity\\nSo the answer would be 'go dormant'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['4489', 'n', 'V']","target":"4489","rationale":"The given list has only one number element, which is 4489. The sum of all number elements in the list is 4489."},{"source":"Two analogies on manipulating items in a kitchen is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". The phrase \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its appropriate manipulation B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate manipulation of item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a verb which shows a way to manipulate the given object.\\n\\ncandy : unwrap. bag : ?","target":"open","rationale":"To unwrap candy, one normally opens the wrapper. Similarily, one could open a bag by untying it or unzipping it, etc."},{"source":"Solution 1: the fish knife\\nSolution 2: the chef's knife\\n\\nGoal: what is the most versatile tool in the kitchen?\\n\\nGiven the goal, what is the correct solution?\\n\\nAnswer by copying the correct solution","target":"the chef's knife","rationale":"The rationale is: \\"the chef's knife\\"."},{"source":"Lanc√¥me Juicy Tubes changed my life.\\nOk, well that‚Äôs a slight exaggeration but it was the first high-end make-up item that I ever bought and it made me feel like I was really getting somewhere. I‚Äôd got a good job, was in the process of buying my own house and I could afford to buy premium beauty products. I chose a transparent lemon yellow gloss with tiny flecks of iridescent glitter in, and over the following months I treated myself to several other Juicy Tube variants including a shimmery nude gloss called Pamplemousse which I wore on nights out for years (incidentally Pamplemousse is still going!).\\nFast forward several (ahem‚Ä¶) years and Juicy Tubes are still going strong, but there‚Äôs a new member of the Juicy family vying for attention ‚Äì the Juicy Shaker.*. Another lip product, this one is a nourishing tinted lip oil which acts a bit like a gloss, and I was sent two of the new shades to try out ‚Äì Piece of Cake and Show Me The Honey.\\nJuicy Shakers are a bi-phase nourishing lip oil, when the product is allowed to settle the pigment falls to the bottom and the oil rises to the top, giving a split effect. Then you need to shake the bottle to mix the two layers together, giving the product it‚Äôs name. The ingredients include sweet almond oil, omega 3 and cranberry oil and really help care for your lips unlike most other glosses.\\nShow Me The Honey is a nude coral shade, it looks rather orange and scary in the bottle but in reality it‚Äôs much more of a gentle shade. Piece of Cake is a damson pink, and again looks much darker in the bottle. I found that Piece of Cake matches almost exactly with the natural colour of my lips so it‚Äôs perfect for when I want my make-up to look really pared back with glossy supple natural looking lips.\\nHow long does it probably take the author to apply her makeup in the morning?\\n\\nA. probably about 3 hours\\n\\nB. not enough information\\n\\nC. probably about a half hour\\n\\nD. probably about 2 hours","target":"C","rationale":"The passage is about the author's experience with Lanc√¥me Juicy Tubes, a lip product that she used several years ago. Through this discussion of her past makeup routine, it can be inferred that she does not use many products on her face and lips because as mentioned in the last sentence: \\"when I want my make-up to look really pared back with glossy supple natural looking lips\\". Based on these inferences given in the context piece alone without any other information, there is no evidence to support Option A or D which state that it probably takes more than 30 minutes for her to do her daily makeup.\\nTherefore, choice C (probably about a half hour) best summarizes how long it probably take the author to apply makeup within one day."},{"source":"Given two entities as input, classify as \\"yes\\" if second entity is the part of the first entity. Otherwise classify them as \\"no\\". These are entities of meronym In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., second entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., first entity).\\n\\nEntity 1: head \\n Entity 2: air sacs","target":"yes","rationale":"A head is a part of the bird, and an air sac is a part of the head. So \\"yes\\" is the correct answer."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: What is the best thing to do in Miami?\\nContext: Miami's tropical weather allows for year-round outdoors activities. The city has numerous marinas, rivers, bays, canals, and the Atlantic Ocean, which make boating, sailing, and fishing popular outdoors activities. Biscayne Bay has numerous coral reefs which make snorkeling and scuba diving popular. There are over 80 parks and gardens in the city. The largest and most popular parks are Bayfront Park and Bicentennial Park (located in the heart of Downtown and the location of the American Airlines Arena and Bayside Marketplace), Tropical Park, Peacock Park, Morningside Park, Virginia Key, and Watson Island.","target":"boating, sailing, and fishing","rationale":"Miami's tropical weather allows for year-round outdoors activities. The city has numerous marinas, rivers, bays, canals, and the Atlantic Ocean which make boating, sailing, and fishing popular outdoor activities in Miami.\\nSo the answer is \\"boating\\", \\"sailing\\" or \`fishing\`."},{"source":"Given two entities as input, classify as \\"yes\\" if second entity is the part of the first entity. Otherwise classify them as \\"no\\". These are entities of meronym In linguistics, meronymy is a semantic relation between a meronym denoting a part and a holonym denoting a whole. In simpler terms, a meronym (i.e., second entity) is in a part-of relationship with its holonym (i.e., first entity).\\n\\nEntity 1: bee \\n Entity 2: rhizome","target":"no","rationale":"The rhizome is the stem of a plant which grows underground and pushes out roots and leaves. It is not a part of a bee. Therefore, the answer is \\"no\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies on manipulating items in a kitchen is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". The phrase \\"A : B\\" relates item A to its appropriate manipulation B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate manipulation of item C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a verb which shows a way to manipulate the given object.\\n\\nbag : open. jar : ?","target":"open","rationale":"To open a bag, one could rip it apart. Similarly, to open a jar, one could unscrew the lid or use some other method to remove the top."},{"source":"Answer the following question given this paragraph: \\n\\nHydrocarbons are compounds that contain only carbon and hydrogen atoms. The smallest hydrocarbon, methane (CH 4 ), contains just one carbon atom and four hydrogen atoms. Larger hydrocarbons contain many more. Hydrocarbons with four or more carbon atoms can have different shapes. Although they have the same chemical formula, with the same numbers of carbon and hydrogen atoms, they form different compounds, called isomers . Isomers are compounds whose properties are different because their atoms are bonded together in different arrangements.\\n\\n\\nQ: What do you call compounds whose properties are different because their atoms are bonded together in different arrangements?\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"isomers","rationale":"The question asks what the term is for compounds whose properties are different because their atoms are bonded together in different arrangements. Based on this, it can be inferred that the answer will refer to a kind of compound and not chemical species like isotopes or mixtures. \\nIn addition, these molecules must have bonds between carbon and hydrogen which means they cannot be ionic compounds as ions do not form covalent bonds with each other; instead an electrostatic force holds them together. Amongst all the options given, only \\"isomers\\" fit this description as two isomeric hydrocarbons differ solely due to how their constituent atoms are arranged around the molecule's central atom(s), but still possess identical formulas (i.e., same number of carbons). Thus making \\"isomers"},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. These stories can be difficult due to their length and how each story has at least one of the three following scenarios: the first is when the individual's belief matches reality, the second is when the individual's belief does not match reality, and the third is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nSophia entered the sunroom. Ella entered the sunroom. The watermelon is in the red_pantry. Ella exited the sunroom. Sophia moved the watermelon to the blue_suitcase. Sophia exited the sunroom. Ella entered the sunroom. Where was the watermelon at the beginning?","target":"red_pantry","rationale":"The story begins with the watermelon in the red_pantry. Sophia then moves the watermelon to the blue_suitcase, which makes it impossible for Ella to see that it is in the blue_suitcase."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers. A list is shown by two brackets and comma-separated numbers inside, like: [1,2,3]. You should remove all of the even numbers from the list. If every number in the input list is even an empty list should be returned. Zero should be counted as an even number.\\n\\n[82, 83, 195]","target":"[83, 195]","rationale":"The only even number in the list is 82. Therefore, removing all even numbers from the list would result to [83, 195]."},{"source":"Coming off their season-opening win over the Colts, the Broncos remained on home ground for an AFC West duel against the Kansas City Chiefs. The Broncos grabbed the lead on the game's opening drive, with quarterback Peyton Manning throwing a 4-yard touchdown pass to tight end Julius Thomas. The Chiefs got on the scoreboard later in the first quarter, with a 45-yard field goal by placekicker Cairo Santos, then took the lead early in the second quarter, with a 2-yard touchdown run by running back Knile Davis. The Broncos re-claimed the lead on their next offensive possession, with Manning connecting on a 4-yard touchdown pass to tight end Jacob Tamme, then added to their lead just before halftime, with a 12-yard touchdown pass from Manning to wide receiver Demaryius Thomas. The Chiefs got the opening possession of the second half, with a time-consuming drive that took them to as far as the Broncos' 4-yard line, but were backed up 10 yards by an offensive holding penalty and a 5-yard sack of quarterback Alex Smith by Broncos' linebacker Brandon Marshall. Santos subsequently missed a 37-yard field goal to end a drive that chewed up the first 10 minutes of the third quarter. The Broncos were forced to punt on their next possession, and the Chiefs narrowed the Broncos' lead to 21-17 midway through the fourth quarter with another time-consuming drive, culminating with a 4-yard touchdown run by Davis. The Broncos drove down the field on their next possession, but had to settle on a 20-yard field by placekicker Brandon McManus to extend their lead to 24-17 with 3:30 remaining in the fourth quarter. Three plays into the Chiefs' next possession, Smith was intercepted by Broncos' cornerback Aqib Talib, who returned the football 41 yards for a touchdown; however, the interception return was nullified by an offside penalty on defensive end Quanterus Smith. The Chiefs' earned one first down prior to the two-minute warning. On the second play after the two-minute warning, Broncos' defensive end DeMarcus Ware forced a fumble off Smith; however, it was ruled an incomplete pass following a replay review. On the next play, Smith connected on a 21-yard pass to wide receiver Dwayne Bowe, and was pushed out of bounds at the Broncos' 9-yard line by cornerback Chris Harris, Jr. with 1:51 remaining in the game. Three plays later, after burning their last timeout, the Chiefs were facing a 3rd-and-goal at the Broncos' 4-yard line; however, an offside call against Ware moved the ball half the distance to the goal line, with 1:04 remaining in the game. Davis subsequently attempted a run up the middle, but was tackled for no gain at the 2-yard line by Ware and linebacker Nate Irving. On the Chiefs' final offensive play, Smith's pass intended for Bowe on 4th-and-goal was broken up by Broncos' defensive tackle Terrance Knighton. Manning subsequently kneeled down to run out the clock. During halftime, the Broncos made three additions to their Ring of Fame: Gene Mingo, who played multiple positions with the Broncos from 1960-64; Dan Reeves, who coached the Broncos from 1981-92 and led the team to three Super Bowl appearances in 1986, 1987 and 1989; wide receiver Rick Upchurch, who played with the Broncos from 1975-83.\\nAnswer this question: From what distance did Manning throw two touchdown passes?","target":"4-yard","rationale":"In order to solve the problem \\"From what distance did Manning throw two touchdown passes?\\", we need to check how far he threw in each pass. First, it is mentioned that he threw a 4-yard touchdown pass to tight end Julius Thomas on the game's opening drive. Second, Manning connected on a 4-yard touchdown pass to tight end Jacob Tamme and added their lead just before halftime with a 12-yard touchdown pass from Manning to wide receiver Demaryius Thomas. Therefore, we could conclude that his throws were made at four yards away and twelve yards away respectively.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a news headline in English. You are expected to classify the post into two classes: sarcastic or non-sarcastic. A sarcastic sentence is one that refers to the use of words that mean the opposite of what you really want to say, especially in order to insult someone, or to show irritation, or just to be funny.\\n\\nleave no person with disabilities behind","target":"non-sarcastic","rationale":"The headline directly refers to the No Child Left Behind Act of 2001, which is a non-sarcastic government program."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question that involves ‚Äúevent duration\\", based on a given sentence. Here, event duration is defined as the understanding of how long events typically last. For example, ‚Äúbrushing teeth‚Äù, usually takes a few minutes. Note that a lot of the questions could have more than one correct answer. We only need a single most-likely answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: they were heard saying when the photo was taken -- while Rowlf is clearly a selfie king. \\nQuestion: How long were they taking photos?","target":"2 minutes","rationale":"The question is asking how long they were taking photos, which implies that it was a repeated action. The sentence mentions \\"when the photo was taken\\" as well as \\"taking photos\\", which suggests that they took more than one photo. Therefore, we can infer that they spent roughly 2 minutes taking photos."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['K', '4403', 'a', '3881', '4139', 'w', '1861', 'G']","target":"14284","rationale":"Given the list ['K', '4403', 'a', '3881', '4139', 'w', '1861'], we need to find elements that are numbers.\\\\n1. The 2nd element is 4403.\\\\n2. The 4th element is 3881.\\\\n3. The 5th element is 4139.\\\\n4. The 7th element is 1861 (The 8th element, which was originally G, should be ignored).\\n\\nCalculating the final results: (+)4403 + (+)3881 + (+)4139 + (+)1861 = 14284"},{"source":"Please read the following news article and write another sentence to add to it.\\n\\n(CNN)A black man who was physically stopped from getting on the Paris metro by soccer fans says they should be \\"locked up\\" and that he intends to make a complaint. Filmed on a mobile phone by a bystander waiting on the platform of Richelieu-Drouot station, the incident took place before a Champions League tie between English club Chelsea and Paris Saint-Germain on Tuesday. The group, who appear to be Chelsea supporters, can be heard chanting: \\"We're racist, we're racist and that's the way we like it.\\" The French newspaper Le Parisien has tracked down the metro passenger at the center of the incident, identifying him only as Souleymane S, a father-of-three who was born in Paris.\\n\\n- \\nA black man abused on Paris metro by Chelsea 'fans' wants his attackers to be punished\\n\\n- \\nThe man identified as Souleymane S. intends to make a police complaint\\n\\n- \\nHe was speaking in interview with Le Parisien newspaper","target":"\\"I understood that Chelsea supporters were involved and I made the link with the Paris Saint-Germain match.","rationale":"The context of the passage is a news article that reports Souleymane S.'s reaction to his experience on the Paris Metro. The first sentence introduces him, explaining who he is and what happened in general terms. \\nThis makes it clear that Souleymane was physically stopped from boarding by Chelsea fans chanting racist songs during their match against PSG. From this point onwards, the rest of the paragraph provides more details about how he intends to proceed after being abused: \\"I understood that Chelsea supporters were involved and I made the link with the Paris Saint-Germain match."},{"source":"Answer the question from the given passage. Your answer should be directly extracted from the passage, and it should be a single entity, name, or number, not a sentence.\\n\\nPassage: France took control of Algeria in 1830 but began in earnest to rebuild its worldwide empire after 1850, concentrating chiefly in North and West Africa, as well as South-East Asia, with other conquests in Central and East Africa, as well as the South Pacific. Republicans, at first hostile to empire, only became supportive when Germany started to build her own colonial empire. As it developed, the new empire took on roles of trade with France, supplying raw materials and purchasing manufactured items, as well as lending prestige to the motherland and spreading French civilization and language as well as Catholicism. It also provided crucial manpower in both World Wars. Question: What religion did the French spread along with their imperialism?","target":"Catholicism","rationale":"The religion is directly mentioned in the passage, i.e., Catholicism."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: A 70-year-old patient diagnosed three years ago with multiple myeloma who is in a period of neutropenia after a cycle of chemotherapy. It enters due to fever, cough and yellowish expectoration. The chest radiograph shows a condensation image in the right hemithorax. The most likely diagnosis is: \\n Options:  <0> Post-chemotherapy toxic pneumonitis. <1> Pneumococcal pneumonia <2> Pneumonia due to aspergillus. <3> Viral pneumonia due to community respiratory virus. <4> Cytomegalovirus pneumonia.","target":"medicine","rationale":"The question is related to multiple myeloma. Multiple myeloma is a cancer of plasma cells in bone marrow. It belongs to the group of hematological malignancies, which are cancers that affect blood, bone marrow and lymph nodes. Therefore, the answer is \\"medicine\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to concatenate all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, and print the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n6, 8, ['Y', 'j', 'A', 'D', '743', '2349', '5679', '8441', 'h', '3795', '2583', '2911', 'X', '4015', 'N', '8799', '8779', 'k', '8589', 'A', 'H']","target":"234956798441","rationale":"Given the list ['Y', 'j', 'A', 'D', '743', '2349', '5679', '8441',...], we need to concatenate elements from the 6th element to the 8th element.\\\\n1. The 6th element is 2349.\\\\n2. The 7th element is 5679.\\\\n3. The 8th element is 8441.\\\\n\\\\nConcatenating these three number, we get 234956798441 as a result string"},{"source":"India decided to introduce several exotic species into their environment, while Singapore was very protective of its native species.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: \\n\\nWhich country observed that non-native species may not have natural predators in the new habitat?","target":"India","rationale":"According to the paragraph, India decided to introduce exotic species into their environment. This means that they are allowing nonnative species (species from outside of its natural habitat) to be introduced into a new location or ecosystem where it might not have had predators there before.\\nSingapore was very protective of its native species and did not allow any other foreign animals in the country. So Singapore would be unlikely to observe anything about \\"non-native\\" or \\"exotic\\" creatures since they have no experience with them at all within their own borders."},{"source":"Read the given sentence and if it is a general advice then indicate via \\"yes\\". Otherwise indicate via \\"no\\". advice is basically offering suggestions about the best course of action to someone. advice can come in a variety of forms, for example Direct advice and Indirect advice. (1) Direct advice: Using words (e.g., suggest, advice, recommend), verbs (e.g., can, could, should, may), or using questions (e.g., why don't you's, how about, have you thought about). (2) Indirect advice: contains hints from personal experiences with the intention for someone to do the same thing or statements that imply an action should (or should not) be taken.\\n\\nHeadphones , sunglasses and closing you eyes can help blockout the distractions outside the classroom .","target":"yes","rationale":"The given sentence is a general advice. The sentence contains words like \\"can\\", \\"help\\", and \\"blockout\\" which are used to offer suggestions about the best course of action to someone. Also, the sentence comes in a form of direct advice as it uses words (e.g., can, help) that imply an action should be taken. Therefore, the answer is 'yes'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to list all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element in the reverse order. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n7, 11, ['9323', 'C', 'F', 'N', '7419', '3917', '5337', '6295', '2211', '6707', '3035', 'M', '7879', 'o']","target":"3035, 6707, 2211, 6295, 5337","rationale":"Given the list ['9323', 'C', 'F', 'N', '7419', '3917', '5337', '6295', '2211'], we need to find the elements within the range 7 ~ 11.\\\\n1. The 7th element is 5337.\\\\n2. The 8th element is 6295.\\\\n3. The 9th element is 2211.\\\\n4. The 10th element is 6707, and it needs to be removed since it exceeds the range limit (11).\\n5. Finally, they should be listed in reverse order: [3035, 6707, 2211, 6295, 5337]."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nHELSINKI ( AFX ) - Retail and wholesale group Kesko reported net sales of 659.4 mln eur for February , an increase of 10.8 pct year-on-year .","target":"positive","rationale":"This financial news states that the net sales of Kesko retail and wholesale group have increased 10.8% year-on-year in February. This indicates a growth in sales for the company, which is generally considered as a positive development. So, this financial news can be clarified as \\"positive\\"."},{"source":"SEOUL, SOUTH KOREA ‚Äî The U.S. election calendar could be a key factor in determining the scope and timing of a potential deal to end the North Korean nuclear program.\\nPlanning is progressing for both the upcoming summit between North Korean leader Kim Jong Un and South Korean President Moon Jae-in at the end of April and the expected meeting between U.S. President Donald Trump and Kim in late May or early June.\\nPresident Trump said Tuesday that there had been talks at ‚Äúextremely high levels‚Äù between his administration and the North Korean government. Later it was reported that Mike Pompeo, the director of the Central Intelligence Agency and a secretary of state nominee, met recently with Kim Jong Un in Pyongyang.\\nTrump also noted the talks have been marked by ‚Äúa lot of goodwill‚Äù and that ‚Äúthere has been a major change in terms of North Korea‚Äôs behavior,‚Äù since Kim‚Äôs Olympic outreach this year, in which he sent a large delegation to the Pyeongchang Winter games in South Korea, suspended nuclear and missile tests, and expressed a willingness to engage in denuclearization talks.\\nThe turn toward diplomacy has reduced, for now, the potential for conflict over the North‚Äôs accelerated efforts last year to develop an operational nuclear-armed intercontinental ballistic missile that can reach the U.S. mainland.\\nThe North Korean leader‚Äôs decision to engage in denuclearization talks was likely motivated by both Trump‚Äôs ‚Äúmaximum pressure‚Äù campaign, which increased sanctions and the threat of military action against the North, and by South Korean President Moon‚Äôs reassuring outreach efforts to improve inter-Korean relations.\\nTrump‚Äôs motivation in pursuing a nuclear deal with North Korea, in addition to resolving a growing national security threat, could also have a political component.\\nAccording to North Korea analysts at the Sejong Institute in South Korea, the Trump administration is likely calculating how achieving such an agreement could help boost the president‚Äôs chances for re-election in 2020.\\n‚ÄúIf I were Trump, I...\\nAfter the end of this story, Trump probably is\\nPick the correct answer from the following options:\\n\\nA. not enough information\\n\\nB. Applying status to South Korea\\n\\nC. Not applying pressure to North Korea\\n\\nD. Still applying pressure to North Korea","target":"D","rationale":"The context suggests that Trump's motivation in pursuing a nuclear deal with North Korea may be linked to the scope and timing of such an agreement.\\nTrump is looking for a positive outcome from his maximum pressure campaign, which has involved increased sanctions against North Korea as well as threats of military action. The story also says that South Korean President Moon Jae-in's reassuring approach helped pave the way for negotiations between Kim Jong Un and Donald Trump over denuclearization talks. \\nSince D mentions \\"continuing\\" pressure on North Korea it matches best with this information."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a string S and a character c separated by a comma. You need to check if the character c is present in S or not. Return 1 if it is present, else return 0.\\n\\nhgUVcsCempWoijLLdRoZxdToGiVqfb, m","target":"1","rationale":"The character 'm' is present in the given string \\"hgUVcsCempWoijLLdRoZxdToGiVqfb\\". Therefore, we should return 1."},{"source":"Arsenal remain favourites to sign Petr Cech from Chelsea should they pay the ¬£7million asking price. AC Milan, Roma and Real Madrid have all shown an interest while his agent maintains Liverpool are also in the frame. Cech, 32, who starred for the Czech Republic last week, wants to play regularly after being displaced by Thibaut Courtois as Chelsea's No 1. VIDEOS Scroll down to watch Jose Mourinho dismisses 'Mickey Mouse' Petr Cech rumours Petr Cech has been displaced as Chelsea No 1 by Thibaut Courtois and is available for transfer Courtois (right) has established himself as one of the world's finest goalkeepers\\n@highlight\\nPetr Cech now second choice at Chelsea behind Thibaut Courtois\\n@highlight\\nChelsea are prepared to sell the goalkeeper in January for ¬£7million\\n@highlight\\nArsenal, AC Milan, Roma, Liverpool and Real Madrid are all interested\\n@highlight\\nArsenal are the favourites but Arsene Wenger must meet asking price \\n@placeholder's asking price is low at ¬£7m but reflects Chelsea's respect for one of their club legends \\nWhat could the \\"@placeholder\\" be? AC Milan, Arsenal, Arsene Wenger, Cech, Chelsea, Chelsea No, Courtois, Czech Republic, Jose Mourinho, Liverpool, Mickey Mouse, Petr Cech, Real Madrid, Roma, Thibaut Courtois?","target":"Cech","rationale":"The placeholder is Cech."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title of a five-sentence story, the first four sentences, and two options for the fifth sentence as a and b. Your job is to pick the sentence option that does not connect with the rest of the story, indicating your choice as 'a' or 'b'. If both sentences are plausible, pick the one that makes less sense.\\n\\nTitle: Shower cleaning. Sentence 1: The shower in my new home needed to be cleaned frequently. Sentence 2: I wasn't completely sure how to clean a shower so I looked it up. Sentence 3: I realized the directions were very simple after reading them. Sentence 4: The next day I went to the store for cleaning solution. Choices: a. I cleaned that shower so well it was nearly sparkling! b. She also switched to lactose free products from now on.","target":"b","rationale":"The first sentence is about cleaning a shower, and the following sentences are about how to clean a shower. However, choice b changes the subject completely by talking about someone's lactose intolerance (which has nothing to do with showers). Choice a makes sense because it continues the story of cleaning the shower."},{"source":"I read this background article the other day: One of the most common chromosome abnormalities is Down syndrome , due to nondisjunction of chromosome 21 resulting in an extra complete chromosome 21, or part of chromosome 21 ( Figure below ). Down syndrome is the only autosomal trisomy where an affected individual may survive to adulthood. Individuals with Down syndrome often have some degree of mental retardation, some impairment of physical growth, and a specific facial appearance. With proper assistance, individuals with Down syndrome can become successful, contributing members of society. The incidence of Down syndrome increases with maternal age. The risk of having a child with Down syndrome is significantly higher among women age 35 and older.\\n\\nI am facing a new situation today: Mary had two children. Her firs born was named Bill and was normal, and her second child was named Sam and had Down syndrome.\\n\\nUsing the knowledge I acquired from the background article, how should I answer correctly the following question regarding my new situation: Which child had some impairment of physical growth?","target":"Sam","rationale":"The first example talks about Down syndrome and how it affects a person. The second sentence states that people with Down syndrome are often impaired physically as well as mentally. Given this new context, the answer to the question is Sam since he was born after Bill who did not have any problems in his physical growth.\\""},{"source":"Ironically, the misogyny Rush Limbaugh spewed for three days over Sandra Fluke was not much worse than his regular broadcast of sexist, racist and homophobic hate speech: -- Female Cabinet members are \\"Sex-retaries.\\" -- \\"The NAACP should have riot rehearsal. They should get a liquor store and practice robberies.\\" -- The National Organization for Women is \\"a bunch of whores to liberalism.\\" -- [Said to an African-American female caller]: \\"Take that bone out of your nose and call me back.\\" These are just a few samples from the arsenal of degrading language Limbaugh deploys on women, people of color, lesbians and gays, immigrants, the disabled, the elderly, Muslims, Jews, veterans, environmentalists and so forth.\\n@highlight\\nFonda, Morgan, Steinem: Limbaugh long made racist, sexist, homophobic remarks\\n@highlight\\nHis most recent incident drew strong rebuke, some advertisers have dropped him\\n@highlight\\nThey say Clear Channel should dump him; if not FCC should evaluate station licenses\\n@highlight\\nWriters: Airwaves scarce government resource; his show not \\"in public interest\\" \\nIf @placeholder won't clean up its airways, then surely it's time for the public to ask the FCC a basic question: Are the stations carrying Limbaugh's show in fact using their licenses \\"in the public interest?\\" \\nCan you figure out what does the \\"@placeholder\\" mean? It means","target":"Clear Channel","rationale":"The \\"@highlight\\" word shows that it is a highlight. It means some part of the sentence has been marked as important, which can be seen later in the text when we see these words:\\n\\". . . his most recent incident drew strong rebuke, some advertisers have dropped him \\" \\nHence Clear Channel uses its license for hate speech but not for public interest"},{"source":"The first time I went for a walk around my father-in-law's neighborhood was garbage day, and I was shocked to see what people were throwing out. It was back in 1981, and I saw many people gathered in someone's front yard. As I went nearer to see what was happening I got my first introduction to yard sales. For the few dollars I had in my wallet, I was able to buy a seven-inch black-and-white portable TV. I also bought a flashlight.\\nThe following weekend, at another yard sale, I saw a 14-inch color1 TV being sold for almost nothing. I felt I could not miss the offer and bought it. Now I had two sets and couldn't wait to see what else I could afford the next weekend. Spring ended, and by then I had accumulated almost every type of electronic equipment I had always wished to have back home.\\nThen this new idea came to mind. I had heard about a man who traveled back home every few months. He drove a truck filled with boxes of new and used stuff that people were sending to  s. So I told my father that I would send as many types of items as I could so that he could start his resale business.\\nEvery few months I would gather several boxes of American \\"junk\\" --- televisions, toasters, fans, hair dryers, etc. and send them home. As word got out about my father's \\"trash\\" market, people all came to buy these things.\\nThree years later, when I visited my family for the first time since leaving home, I learned that many of the families in our neighborhood had a piece of \\"trash\\". It proved that I had the responsibility to keep people back home up to date with the latest technology you no longer need.(304words)\\nWhat did the author think of the \\"junk\\" he bought?\\nA) He was not surprised to see them thrown away.\\nB) He thought they were valuable.\\nC) He thought they were worth buying.\\nD) He thought he could sell them for a good price.","target":"B","rationale":"In the first sentence, it is said that people were throwing out things he thought valuable. He bought a portable TV and a flashlight for only few dollars because of being shocked to see what people threw away at the yard sales.\\nIt can be concluded that he considered these items worth buying but not cheap in his mind.(He couldn't wait to see if there was anything else he could afford.) Therefore, option B) best fits here---he considered them valuable which means they are worthy or deserve some degree of respect or appreciation."},{"source":"Question: How many legislative assemblies are  held each year?\\nAnswer: The unicameral National Assembly is Mali's sole legislative body, consisting of deputies elected to five-year terms.\\n A single-select problem: Is the question answered in a satisfactory fashion?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"While the answer mentions that Mali's legislative body is unicameral, it does not mention how many assemblies are held each year."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the title and three arbitrary sentences out of a five-sentence story. You are also given three additional sentence options, a, b, and c, that may or may not belong to the story. Your job is to pick the two options that seamlessly connect with the rest of the story; note that the selected choices may fit into the story at any point. Indicate your selected choices in order, i.e., as 'ab'/'bc'/'ac' and not as 'ba'/'ca'/'cb'. If options are equally plausible, pick the ones that make more sense.\\n\\nTitle: We live in Cambridge, MA. When she got back to daycare on Tuesday she said she wanted to see us. We were touched. Choices: a. Our 2 year old granddaughter is in daycare in Queens. b. She visited us over Labor Day. c. Tammy is really good at pool now.","target":"ab","rationale":"The story explains that the protagonist and their granddaughter live in different cities, with the protagonist living in Cambridge, MA and their granddaughter living in Queens. The granddaughter is attending daycare. The first sentence of choice a explains that the protagonist's 2 year old granddaughter lives in Queens. This fits seamlessly with the rest of the story because it establishes a connection between where Tammy lives (Queens) and where her grandparents live (Cambridge, MA). Choice b also connects to the rest of this story by explaining why Tammy recently visited her grandparents; she was visiting them over Labor Day weekend. Therefore, choices a and b fit seamlessly into this story since they provide more information about who Tammy is and why she recently visited her grandparents.\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the alphabetical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no alphabetical element in the list\\n\\n['w', '1983', 'n', '5777', 'j', '7115', '8133', '5445', '1471', '5209', '7553', '2257', 'u', 'C', '6427', 'O', 'k', '6903']","target":"7","rationale":"Given the list ['w', '1983', 'n', '5777', 'j', '7115', '8133', '5445','1471','5209','7553','2257,'u','C','6427','O'k,'6903'], we need to find the alphabetical elements.\\\\n1. The 1st element is w, which is an alphabetical element.\\\\n2. The 3rd element is n, which is an alphabetical element.\\\\n3. The 5th element is j, which is an alphabetical element.\\\\nc does not count as an alphabet because it's in capital letter and counts for a consonant instead of a vowel.'o' does not count as an alphabet because it's in capital letter and counts for a consonant instead of a vowel.'k'the 8th position does not count as an alphabet since it comes after 5777 numerically speaking (8133>5777>5445>6427)"},{"source":"American Beauty is a lost 1927 American silent film romantic drama produced and distributed by First National Pictures. This film was directed by Richard Wallace and starred Billie Dove. It was based on a short story \\"American Beauty\\" by Wallace Irwin. She is supported by Walter McGrail and Margaret Livingston.\\n\\nCan we draw the following conclusion?\\nAmerican Beauty was directed by Richard Wallace\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"Yes","rationale":"The first sentence states that the movie was directed by Richard Wallace. The fact that he also wrote the short story on which it is based does not change this information. So, we can conclude from the passage above that American Beauty was indeed directed by Richard Wallace and therefore, answer should be \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"Read the following context and choose the correct option to answer the question.\\nContext: \\"To be real honest, Jeffrey, you're not making much progress,\\" said Greg. \\"Are you practicing at all?\\"\\n\\"Well, yeah. Mom makes me. She sits there watching to make sure I'm getting the right fingering and phrasing.\\"\\n\\"Hmm. I might need to talk to her about that.\\" Greg hated when kids were forced into musicianship. He had been teaching private music lessons for more than ten years, and had seen it often. Parents made their kids miserable. It rarely worked anyway. \\"You don't really want to take piano, do you?\\"\\n\\"No, Sir.\\"\\n\\"Well... \\"\\n\\"I wish my mom would let me take guitar lessons. That would be cool.\\"\\n\\"You know you'd get calluses like this.\\" Greg held out left hand and showed Jeffrey his fingertips.\\n\\"Yeah! My friend, Zach, has calluses. They're hard like plastic.\\"\\n\\"Well, you know, it hurts for a while--until you build them up.\\"\\n\\"I don't care. I love the guitar. I've been begging Mom to switch me from piano to guitar.\\"\\n\\"I'll talk to her.\\"\\n\\"Great! I already have a guitar and--\\"\\n\\"--don't get too excited yet. We'll see what she says.\\"\\n\\"Thanks, Mr. Tenorly.\\" He jumped up and ran for the front door. Then he stopped, rushed back over to grab his piano books, and raced out the door.\\nGreg's 3:30 lesson had been cancelled, so he now had a thirty minute break. Oftentimes, during a break, he would step outside and wander down the sidewalk, observing the townspeople going in and out of the shops around Coreyville Square.\\nBut something was bugging him. His dad's birthday party was only a few days away. He hoped he wouldn't regret letting Cynthia talk him into going.\\nQuestion: What astrological sign is Greg's dad?\\nOptions:\\n- not enough information\\n- Sagittarius.\\n- Leo.\\n- Libra.","target":"not enough information","rationale":"The story is about Greg and his piano student Jeffrey. The question asks what astrological sign Greg's dad has. However, it does not provide this information in the passage and hence ‚Äúnot enough information‚Äù is the correct answer option for this question."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate places/locations to the associated travel mode is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates place A to travel mode B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate travel mode for the given place C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nwork : car. office : ?","target":"car","rationale":"To go to the office, one could take a car. Similarily, one could go to work by taking a car."},{"source":"You are given a new situation: Two friends were in college. Hank studied plate tectonics, while his buddy Alex studied Earth's atmosphere. They were both very fascinated by the subjects.\\n\\nand a hint : The theory of plate tectonics demonstrates that the continents of the Earth are moving across the surface at the rate of a few centimeters per year. This is expected to continue, causing the plates to relocate and collide. Continental drift is facilitated by two factors: the energy generation within the planet and the presence of a hydrosphere. With the loss of either of these, continental drift will come to a halt. The production of heat through radiogenic processes is sufficient to maintain mantle convection and plate subduction for at least the next 1.1 billion years.At present, the continents of North and South America are moving westward from Africa and Europe. Researchers have produced several scenarios about how this will continue in the future. These geodynamic models can be distinguished by the subduction flux, whereby the oceanic crust moves under a continent. In the introversion model, the younger, interior, Atlantic ocean becomes preferentially subducted and the current migration of North and South America is reversed. In the extroversion model, the older, exterior, Pacific ocean remains preferentially subducted and North and South America migrate toward eastern Asia.As the understanding of geodynamics improves, these models will be subject to revision. In 2008, for example, a computer simulation was used to predict that a reorganization of the mantle convection will occur over the next 100 million years, causing a supercontinent composed of Africa, Eurasia, Australia, Antarctica and South America to form around Antarctica.Regardless of the outcome of the continental migration, the continued subduction process causes water to be transported to the mantle. After a billion years from the present, a geophysical model gives an estimate that 27% of the current ocean mass will have been subducted. If this process were to continue unmodified into the future, the subduction and release would reach an equilibrium after 65% of the current ocean mass has been subducted.\\n\\nPlease answer this question : Which student learned more about mantle convection?","target":"Hank","rationale":"Hank‚Äôs area of study was plate tectonics. While Alex‚Äôs area of study was Earth's atmosphere, which is way different from Hank.\\nThe required answer in this case would be ‚ÄúHank\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate objects to the associated rooms is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates object A to room B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate room for the given object C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nsink : bathroom. couch : ?","target":"parlor","rationale":"To use a sink, one would likely be in the bathroom. Similarily, to use a couch (to sit on), one would likely be in a parlor."},{"source":"Starting in the 1890s and stretching in some places to the early 1910s, gold rushes in Alaska and the nearby Yukon Territory brought thousands of miners and settlers to Alaska. Alaska was officially incorporated as an organized territory in 1912. Alaska's capital, which had been in Sitka until 1906, was moved north to Juneau. Construction of the Alaska Governor's Mansion began that same year. European immigrants from Norway and Sweden also settled in southeast Alaska, where they entered the fishing and logging industries.\\nIn what year was Alaska's capital officially changed to Juneau?","target":"1906","rationale":"The passage states that Alaska's capital was moved north to Juneau in 1906. This implies that the official change of capital happened at this time, and therefore the correct answer is \\"1906\\"."},{"source":"Read the given query and classify it as a 'Good' or 'Bad' query depending on how well the query is formed, 'Bad' being the expected output for a not so well formed query and 'Good' being the expected output for a well formed query. A query may be wrong based on common sense or general facts, but if it is well formed, you should answer with Good.\\n\\nHow much new house cost in 2009 ?","target":"Bad","rationale":"The word 'cost' is used in the wrong context. The correct usage of the word 'cost' would be \\"What does a new house cost?\\" or \\"How much will a new house cost?\\". Hence, this query should be classified as Bad."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a tweet in English. You are expected to classify the post into two classes: sarcastic or non-sarcastic. A sarcastic sentence is one that refers to the use of words that mean the opposite of what you really want to say, especially in order to insult someone, or to show irritation, or just to be funny.\\n\\nLaying in the dark","target":"non-sarcastic","rationale":"This is a literal statement. The writer is describing their own actions and not using sarcasm to insult anyone or show irritation towards others. Therefore, this tweet should be categorized as \\"non-sarcastic\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you will be shown a sentence, and you should determine whether it is overruling or non-overruling. In law, an overruling sentence is a statement that nullifies a previous case decision as a precedent by a constitutionally valid statute or a decision by the same or higher ranking court which establishes a different rule on the point of law involved. Classify your answers into overruling or non-overruling\\n\\ngiven the legislature's intent to permit such a lawsuit, taswell was not required to exhaust judicial remedies and challenge the administrative decision by filing a petition for a writ of mandamus.","target":"non-overruling","rationale":"The sentence is neither final nor authoritative. It is non-overruling."},{"source":"I have a test where I am given the following article, what is an answer for the question: What is the first name of the person who Anning later told that he knew the character, Aurthur Morgan, had been partly inspired by himself? ?\\n\\nThe story is partially inspired by the Davies brothers' older sister Rose, who emigrated to Australia in 1964 with her husband Arthur Anning. Her departure devastated Ray Davies, and it inspired him to write the song \\"Rosy Won't You Please Come Home\\", included on the 1966 album Face to Face. The lead character in the album, the fictional Arthur Morgan‚Äîmodelled after Anning‚Äîis a carpet layer whose family's plight in the opportunity-poor setting of post-war England is depicted. Writer Julian Mitchell detailed the story line and characters in depth, explaining in the liner notes for the album's LP release:\\nArthur Morgan ... lives in a London suburb in a house called Shangri-La, with a garden and a car and a wife called Rose and a son called Derek who's married to Liz, and they have these two very nice kids, Terry and Marilyn. Derek and Liz and Terry and Marilyn are emigrating to Australia. Arthur did have another son, called Eddie. He was named after Arthur's brother, who was killed in the battle of the Somme. Arthur's Eddie was killed, too‚Äîin Korea.\\nDavies would later comment in his autobiography, X-Ray, that Anning later \\"told me that he ... knew it [Arthur] had been partly inspired by him ... [it] reminded him of home ... I told Arthur that I felt guilty for using him as a subject for a song, but he shrugged off my apology, saying that he was flattered.\\" With an underlying theme of nostalgia, the songs describe the England that Arthur once knew (\\"Victoria\\", \\"Young and Innocent Days\\"), the promise of life in Australia for one of his sons (\\"Australia\\"), the emptiness of his superficially comfortable life in his home (\\"Shangri-La\\"), the resolve of the British people during the Second World War (\\"Mr. Churchill Says\\"), the privations that marked the austerity period after the war (\\"She's Bought a Hat Like Princess Marina\\"), and the death of his brother in World War I (\\"Yes Sir, No Sir\\", \\"Some Mother's Son\\").","target":"Ray","rationale":"The answer to the question is Ray. This information can be found in the last paragraph of the passage:\\nDavies would later comment in his autobiography, X-Ray, that Anning later \\"told me that he ... knew it [Arthur] had been partly inspired by him ... [it] reminded him of home ... I told Arthur that I felt guilty for using him as a subject for a song, but he shrugged off my apology, saying that he was flattered.\\" With an underlying theme of nostalgia, the songs describe the England that Arthur once knew (\\"Victoria\\", \\"Young and Innocent Days\\"),"},{"source":"Given a part of privacy policy text, classify it into one of these categories: \\n (1) First Party Collection/Use (how and why a service provider collects user information), \\n (2) Third Party Sharing/Collection (how user information may be shared with or collected by third parties), \\n (3) User Choice/Control (choices and control options available to users), \\n (4) User Access, Edit, & Deletion (if and how users may access, edit, or delete their information), \\n (5) Data Retention (how long user information is stored), \\n (6) Data Security (how user information is protected), \\n (7) Policy Change (if and how users will be informed about changes to the privacy policy).\\n\\nAn unspecified third party does receive your unspecified personal information for an unspecified purpose. You can opt in for data collection.","target":"Third Party Sharing/Collection","rationale":"The passage states that the user's personal information is shared with some unspecified third party for an unspecified purpose. This implies that the website shares user information with companies other than itself and that these companies use the data for their own purposes, which fits into category (2). Therefore, this passage can be classified as \\"Third Party Sharing/Collection\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{3, 5, 7, 11, 12, 13, 18}', Set2: '{1, 6, 7, 8, 9, 11, 14, 18, 19, 20}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"14","rationale":"The given elements are Set1: '{3, 5, 7, 11, 12, 13, 18}', and Set2: '{1, 6, 7, 8, 9 ,11 ,14 ,18 ,19 ,20}'.\\\\n3 -> 1\\\\n5 -> 2\\\\n7 -> 3 (repeated)\\\\n11 -> 4 (repeated)\\\\n12 -> 5\\\\n13 -> 6\\\\n18 -> 7 (repeated)\\\\n1 is added. There's no repeated value.\\\\n6 is added. There's no repeated value.\\\\nthere's already a 7th element in Set1; therefore it's not added. Same for 11 and 18 . \\\\t8 is added because there was no 8th element in both sets before adding 8 . In this way we can see that the total number of final elements will be 14 ."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question that involves events that may be stationary (not changing over time) or transient (changing over time). For example, the sentence \\"he was born in the U.S.\\" contains a stationary event since it will last forever; however, \\"he is hungry\\" contains a transient event since it will remain true for a short period of time. Note that a lot of the questions could have more than one correct answer. We only need a single most-likely answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: She began to tell the story of Majestic, the wild horse who could not be calmed. \\nQuestion: Is the horse calm today?","target":"no","rationale":"The story of the horse is a past event, which means that the horse's current state (whether it is calm or not) will not be affected by the past story."},{"source":"Given an object and a part, decide whether the object has that part. For example if you are asked 'gun has barrel?', you need to decide if a gun has a barrel as one of its components or parts, indicating 1 or 0 as your answer respectively. All sentences strictly follow the template 'object has part?.'\\n\\nfighter has door?","target":"1","rationale":"A fighter is a type of military aircraft that is equipped for attacking other aircraft. It has an opening in the fuselage where the pilot sits and operates the aircraft, which can be considered as a door. Therefore, answer 1"},{"source":"You will be given a review about a book, an item, a place or a movie. After that, a question is given that you should answer using a certain span of the review. Your answer should be from the review itself and should not contain extra words, and should not be a combination of different spans. If there's no direct answer to the question, answer with a part of the text that is the most relevant to the question. See the examples for clarification.\\n\\nreview: The Glass Castle is hands down one of the best memoirs--in fact, one of the best books--I've ever read.  Jeannette Walls' story is remarkable and inspiring.  I wish I had an ounce of her inner strength.  Like Jeannette, I like learning the \\"dirt\\" about people not because it's salacious or because I have malicious intent, but rather because I think the \\"dirt\\" is what makes each of us unique and truly human.  I also appreciated this book because the story raises a valuable question:  can parents be deemed neglectful or abusive if they truly love their children and believe they're doing the best for them, even if to the outside world their parenting seems remiss?  And is it maybe true to love is all a child truly needs, more so than even adequate food and shelter?  Aside from the substance of the book, it was a compellingly readable story--funny, suspenseful, heartbreaking, and healing.  I breezed through it because I had to know how things ultimately turned out.I wish the best to Jeannette and all her family.  She is someone I would love to know, and I thank her for sharing her incredible story with the world!\\nquestion: Does this story inspirational to you?","target":"story is remarkable and inspiring","rationale":"The answer is the text span, \\"story is remarkable and inspiring,\\" as it best answers the question."},{"source":"Here's a logic test: The space ship was much faster than the car so when they both traveled for ten minutes the space ship went (A) less far (B) further\\n\\nChoose the answer between \\"Space ship\\" and \\"Car\\".","target":"Car","rationale":"The space ship was much faster than the car. \\nThis means that it took less time for the spaceship to go further in 10 minutes than it would have taken a car to travel over the same distance. So, \\"Car\\" is more appropriate answer and \\"Space ship\\" is not correct"},{"source":"Question: A python experiences less resistance slithering through the jungle then through the forest. This means that the _____ is smoother (A) jungle (B) forest\\n\\nDo not use A and B to answer the question but instead, choose between \\"jungle\\" and  \\"forest\\".","target":"jungle","rationale":"Pythons are snakes that live in tropical climates. Jungles and forests, however, differ slightly in climate types: jungles being warmer than the forest. If we think about a python slithering through these two environments, it is intuitive to say that the snake would experience less resistance moving through an environment with higher temperatures (the jungle) as compared to one with lower temperatures (the forest).\\nSo from all this information given above, \\"jungle\\" makes more sense for our answer option here."},{"source":"Given a statement, generate a question such that the answer is contained in that statement.\\n\\nArthropods spread disease and eat crops.","target":"What do arthropods spread?","rationale":"The question should induce disease as an example of something that arthropods spread. That would be \\"What do arthropods spread?\\""},{"source":"Single/multi-select question: Does the sentence \\"Author, H. G. Wells, McLaren and Ferrari Chief Designer, Nicholas Tombazis, CEO of Rolls Royce, Ralph Robins, rock band Queen, Brian May, CEO of Singapore Airlines, Chew Choon Seng, Prime Minister of New Zealand, Julius Vogel, Prime Minister of India, Rajiv Gandhi, Deputy Prime Minister of Singapore, Teo Chee Hean, Chief Medical Officer for England, Sir Liam Donaldson, Head Physician to the Queen, Huw Thomas, CEO of Moonfruit, Wendy Tan White, Businessman and philanthropist, Winston Wong, billionaire hedge fund manager Alan Howard.\\" provide a valid answer to the question \\"Which airline's CEO can be called a non - academic alumni of Imperial?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The sentence \\"CEO of Singapore Airlines, Chew Choon Seng\\" provides a valid answer to the question. So, the answer is yes."},{"source":"Cholesterol has been implicated in heart disease for decades. Atherosclerosis is a disorder of the arteries in which cholesterol and other materials are deposited on the interior of the arterial wall. These deposits lead to the formation of plaques that can restrict or even block the flow of blood through these blood vessels (see Figure below ). A decrease in the flow of blood can lead to high blood pressure and a lowered oxygen supply to the heart muscle. A complete blockage of blood flow to parts of the heart (a heart attack) can cause significant damage due to oxygen deprivation, in some cases leading to death.\\n\\nTwo brothers went to the doctor's office for an appointment. The doctor discovered that Tim had very high levels of cholesterol, while Jim had normal levels.\\n\\nWhich brother experiences a decrease in blood flow?","target":"Tim","rationale":"The context indicates that atherosclerosis is a disorder of the arteries in which cholesterol and other materials are deposited on the interior of arterial walls. The deposits lead to plaques, which can restrict or even block blood flow. So Tim's high levels of cholesterol mean his body may be depositing more material than normal inside his arteries‚Äîwhich would result in a decrease in blood flow through those vessels compared with Jim, who has normal cholesterol levels."},{"source":"In this task, you're given five sentences, numbered 1 through 5, and two options a and b for possible titles for the story. Your job is to choose the title that better fits the story. Indicate your choice by 'a' or 'b'.\\n\\nSentence 1: Tom had a somewhat old car. Sentence 2: The paint had been wearing down on it. Sentence 3: For his birthday his friends pitched in for a new paint job. Sentence 4: Tom excitedly picked out his favorite color. Sentence 5: The car looked great and Tom was very thankful. Choices: a. New Paint Job. b. Out of Toilet Paper.","target":"a","rationale":"The story is about Tom and his car. His friends pitched in for a new paint job, so the correct title would be \\"New Paint Job.\\""},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: Greeks left Turkey for good after this conflict was ended.\\nContext: In the aftermath of the First World War, Greece attempted further expansion into Asia Minor, a region with a large native Greek population at the time, but was defeated in the Greco-Turkish War of 1919‚Äì1922, contributing to a massive flight of Asia Minor Greeks. These events overlapped, with both happening during the Greek genocide (1914-1922), a period during which, according to various sources, Ottoman and Turkish officials contributed to the death of several hundred thousand Asia Minor Greeks. The resultant Greek exodus from Asia Minor was made permanent, and expanded, in an official Population exchange between Greece and Turkey. The exchange was part of the terms of the Treaty of Lausanne which ended the war.","target":"Greco-Turkish War","rationale":"The context mentions that Greece attempted to expand into Asia Minor but was defeated in the Greco-Turkish War of 1919‚Äì1922. In addition, it is stated that this war contributed to a massive flight of Asian Minor Greeks and happened during the Greek genocide (1914-1922). Based on these facts, it can be inferred that the conflict mentioned in question was over after 1922 because there was a permanent exodus from Turkey by Asians following this conflict. Thus, the answer is \\"Greco-Turkish War\\"."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nA California judge on Monday reduced by more than $200 million a jury verdict linking Bayer AG's Roundup weedkiller to cancer but upheld the jury's findings that the company acted with malice. San Francisco Superior Court Judge Suzanne Ramos Bolanos said the $250 million in punitive damages awarded by the jury must be slimmed down to match the $39.25 million in compensatory damages that the jury found appropriate. If the plaintiff agrees to the reduction by Dec. 7, no new trial is needed. ...\\n\\nHypothesis: A California judge on Monday reduced by more than $200 billion a jury verdict linking Bayer AG's Roundup weedkiller to cancer.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The judge reduced the jury verdict by more than $200 million, not billion. So the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions with their consequences are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". The phrase \\"A : B\\" relates action A to consequence B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate consquence of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single verb, without further explanation.\\n\\nhit : shatter. cut : ?","target":"bleed","rationale":"Hitting a glass object can shatter it, while cutting an object may cause it to bleed."},{"source":"Summary:\\n\\n- \\nHawkins' apartment at 23/7 Henderson Street in Bondi has already sold for $1.2 million\\n\\n- \\nThe Myer ambassador and her husband Jake Wall pocketed a profit of $400,000 on the property\\n\\n- \\nThe couple recently sold their four bedroom mansion in North Curl Curl, on Sydney's Northern Beaches\\n\\n- \\nThe property-savvy couples' most recent buy was two properties at Newport, also on the Northern Beaches,  worth a combined $4 million\\n\\n- \\nThey take up a combined 3,252 square metres and include 37 metres of private beach \\n\\nArticle:\\n\\nJennifer Hawkins' Bondi apartment has sold for $1.2 million just a fortnight after being placed on the market, ahead of it's scheduled September 20 auction. The 30-year-old Australian model made a tidy profit on her Bondi investment, paying $895,000 for the 92 square metre apartment back in 2007 and leaving her over $400,000 richer. Coming just one month after the former Miss Universe winner and her husband Jake Wall, sold their North Curl Curl Mansion the couple now own a combined 3252 square metres of land which includes 37 meters of private beach. The two bedroom, two bathroom luxury pad is was expected to be fetch at least $1.1 million when scheduled for auction on September 20th.\\n\\n\\nNow that you've read the article, please write a new sentence to add to it.","target":"Hawkins and Wall recently purchased two waterfront Newport properties for $4 million in July","rationale":"The context provides details about Jennifer Hawkins' apartment in Bondi which has been sold for $1.2 million and the profit she made on it. It then goes on to say that this is not her only real estate sale; the model also recently sold their four bedroom mansion in North Curl Curl, a suburb of Sydney's Northern Beaches. The article concludes by stating that Jennifer and her husband Jake Wall own two properties at Newport (on the same Northern Beaches) worth combined $4 million dollars where they take up 3252 square metres of land including 37 meters private beach each other property.\\nGiven all these facts, it would make sense if we added \\"Hawkins and Wall recently purchased two waterfront Newport properties for $4 million in July\\" \\n\\n\\n\`"},{"source":"In this task, you are given a conversation between a flight agent and the customer. You are given 4 options and you need to select the goal of the conversation. It is provided as part of customer's context, which has to be one of the following: \`book\`: Make a new reservation, \`cancel\`: Cancel an existing reservation, \`no_flight\`: No flight found for the customer's preference, \`no_reservation\`: No reservation / No change / No cancellation was made in the conversation, mostly enquiring details\\n\\ncustomer: Hello. \\n agent: Hello, how can I aid you? \\n customer: I want to cancel my reservation, can you please help me? \\n agent: Sure, I can help you with that. May I know your good name please? \\n customer: My name is Christine Roberts. \\n agent: Ok, please wait for a while. \\n customer: Sure. \\n agent: Christine Roberts, there is no active reservation found under your name to do cancellation. \\n customer: Ok, not a problem. Thank you. \\n agent: Thank you for choosing us.","target":"no_reservation","rationale":"In this conversation, the customer wants to cancel her reservation, but later it turns out that she has no reservation so there is nothing to be cancelled. So the goal of this conversation is \\"no_reservation\\"."},{"source":"The input is taken from a negotiation between two participants who take the role of campsite neighbors and negotiate for Food, Water, and Firewood packages, based on their individual preferences and requirements. Given an utterance and recent dialogue context containing past 3 utterances (wherever available), output Yes if the utterance contains the uv-part strategy, otherwise output No. uv-part is a selfish negotiation strategy. It is used to undermine the requirements of the opponent. For instance, suggesting that the opponent would not need more firewood since they already have the basic supplies or a suggestion that there might be a store near the campsite where the opponent can get the supplies instead.\\n\\nContext: \\nUtterance: 'hello!'","target":"No","rationale":"The speaker simply says \\"hello,\\" which does not involve any suggestion that the opponent does not need as much supplies. Rather, it is a simple greeting. \\nFor example, if the speaker had said \\"You probably don't need more firewood since you already have food and water\\" or \\"If you don't get enough supplies here, there might be a store near your campsite where you can buy more,\\" those would be examples of uv-part strategies.\\nSince the utterance in this case does not use the uv-part strategy, the answer is No.\\""},{"source":"Here's a complex question that requires someone to reason about the input, can you answer it?\\nThis American poet, born in 1830, was the sister in law of Susan Huntington Gilbert Dickinson?","target":"Emily Dickinson","rationale":"Emily Dickinson was born in 1830, making her the only poet to match that description."},{"source":"If The obvious (to me) point that the average unemployment rate over the next 10 years will be what the Fed wants it to be, regardless of the U.S.-Mexico trade balance, never made it into the public consciousness., can we conclude that \\"People know that the US-Mexico trade balance has no direct impact on employment levels.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"Here, the author is being sarcastic and making a point about something he feels should be obvious but isn't. This suggests that it's not true that people know this fact. So while we can conclude from the context that people do not understand how US-Mexico trade balance has an impact on employment rates, we cannot directly say whether they are aware of its lack thereof because there might still be others who acknowledge this truth. Therefore, with only this information available to us, it is impossible to tell if \\"People know that the US-Mexico trade balance has no direct impact on employment levels.\\", so our answer would have been \\"it is not possible to tell\\"."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the passage.\\n\\"It is part of the Jaguar Land Rover group, a subsidiary of Tata Motors of India.\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Land Rover","rationale":"According to the passage, Land Rover is a subsidiary of Tata Motors. Therefore, Land Rover is part of Jaguar Land Rover Group and it was acquired by Tata motors in 2008."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: How many years was the Papal residence in the Lateran Palace before being moved to the Quirinal Palace? Passage 1:Kakizaki Haky≈ç was born in Matsumae Castle in 1764, the fifth son of the Matsumae Domain daimy≈ç . The following year he was adopted as successor by kar≈ç (chief retainer or house elder) . At a young age he travelled to Edo, where he studied under and S≈ç Shiseki, learning the style of the Nanpin school. In the aftermath of the Menashi‚ÄìKunashir rebellion, he painted the , portraits of twelve Ainu chiefs who had sided with the Matsumae Domain; this series was presented to Emperor K≈çkaku. In 1791 he journeyed to Ky≈çto, where he studied under Maruyama ≈åkyo. His style was influenced by his exchanges with the painters and literati of the Maruyama-Shij≈ç school and he became friends with , , and in particular , with whom he hosted a moon-viewing party for , attended also by . From 1807, when the Matsumae clan were transferred to the , based around Yanagawa in Mutsu Province, Kakizaki Haky≈ç as kar≈ç worked for their reinstatement. In 1826, after falling ill in Edo, he died in his home town of Matsumae.\\n Passage 2:Peete was born Holly Elizabeth Robinson in Mount Airy, Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, the daughter of Dolores and Matt Robinson (the original Gordon on Sesame Street). Her mother was a school teacher, in public relations, and later a personal talent manager, and her father a producer/writer. She has an older brother named Matthew Thomas Robinson III. She attended Greene Street Friends School in nearby Germantown. In 1974, her family moved to California. Peete graduated from Santa Monica High School in Santa Monica, California, where her classmates included Rob Lowe. Peete graduated from Sarah Lawrence College with a degree in psychology and French. Peete studied abroad for a year at the Sorbonne, and is fluent in French. While there she sang in Paris nightclubs, including a performance with jazz musician Lionel Hampton at the Hotel Meridian Jazz Club.\\n Passage 3:With the increasing chaos and disorder leading to the collapse of the Roman Empire in 476, the popes assumed more and more civil authority first in Rome and in the surrounding territories. Rome became the center of the Catholic Church and the capital city of the Papal States; consequently, a great number of churches, convents and other religious buildings were erected in the city, sometimes above the ruins of older pre-Christian sites of worship. Churches proliferated during the Renaissance, when the Rome's most notable churches were built (this includes St. Peter's basilica on the Vatican Hill (the largest church in the world) and the city cathedral of St. John at the Lateran. The Papacy established its residence first in the Lateran Palace, then in the Quirinal Palace. When Rome was annexed by force to the newly unified Kingdom of Italy In 1870, Pope Pius IX retired to the Vatican, proclaiming himself a prisoner of the Savoy monarchy and leading to decades of conflict between the neonate state and the Catholic Church. This was resolved in 1929, when the Lateran Treaty were signed in Rome, establishing the right for the Holy See to govern the Vatican City as an independent, sovereign state. The patron saints of Rome remain Saint Peter and Saint Paul (or, as they are collectively referred to in this context, \\"the most holy Saints Peter and Paul\\"), both celebrated on June 29.","target":"3","rationale":"Only passage 3 contains the information about the Papal residence in Quirinal Palace."},{"source":"Question: Which president was responsible for the most amount of growth to the campus?\\nAnswer: Wilkinson was responsible for the building of over eighty structures on the campus, many of which still stand.\\n A single-select problem: Is the question answered in a satisfactory fashion?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The text talks about the president's contribution to building structures on campus and not specifically growth. While growth may be a result of such construction, it is not directly mentioned in this sentence as something Wilkinson was responsible for; hence, the answer does not satisfactorily address the question."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\n\`\` Our Vaalipalvelu-service was especially developed for use by communities and organizations .","target":"neutral","rationale":"The given piece of news talks about the new service provided by the company. It does not convey any information about whether this service is a positive or negative development for the company or its customers. Therefore, it could be classified as \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"Given a sentence, fill out the missing word with a 'no' or a number (between zero and ten). You should write the numbers with english alphabet, like: four instead of 4.\\n\\nSpiders possess ____ legs compared with the six of the insects.","target":"eight","rationale":"Spiders and insects are both arthropods, which are animals that have jointed legs. Spiders and insects, however, belong to different subgroups of arthropods. Insects belong to the subgroup hexapoda whereas spiders belong to the subgroup chelicerata. Chelicerates have eight legs whereas hexapods have six legs."},{"source":"You are given a time in 24-Hours format, and you need to convert it to time in the 12-Hours format. For a 24-Hours format time larger than 12:00, subtract 12 hours from the given time, then add 'PM'.  For example, if you have 14:30 hours, subtract 12 hours, and the result is 2:30 PM. If the 24-Hours format time is less than or equal to 12:00, add 'AM'. For example, say you have 10:15 hours, add the 'AM' to the end, here we get 10:15 AM. Note that 00:00 Hrs in 24-Hours format is 12:00 AM in 12-Hours format and 12:00 Hrs in 24-Hours format would be 12:00 PM in 12-Hours format.\\n\\n02:17 Hrs","target":"02:17 AM","rationale":"The given time is 02:17 Hrs in the 24-Hours format.\\\\nSince it is less than or equal to 12:00, we need to add AM to the end of the time in order to convert it into 12-Hours format.\\\\n\\\\n02:17 + AM = 02:17 AM\\nSo, the time in the 12-Hours format is 02:17 AM."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer basic science questions. For each question, several terms are intentionally masked with ***. This masking can cover very few or many of the question words. Clearly, if masked terms are important, the modified question will be impossible to answer. Please indicate the correct answer with one of the following responses: \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\" or \\"E\\". While \\"A\\"-\\"D\\" correspond to the answer options provided in the input, \\"E\\" represents \\"I don't know\\" for questions that do not provide enough information. Respond via \\"E\\" if the question is not answerable. Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'.\\n\\nQuestion: How do *** most *** *** *** *** into *** ***?  (A) Plant leaves insulate surrounding rocks from extreme temperatures. (B) Plant roots grow into cracks in rocks. (C) Seeds from plants fall onto rocks and release acidic compounds. (D) Stems of plants surround and squeeze rocks.","target":"E","rationale":"The question is not answerable because the key terms (\\"plants\\" and \\"rocks\\") are masked in the question. It is not possible to answer if these concepts are being compared or contrasted, or how they interact with one another. For example, it could be asking how rocks most easily break into pieces, or if plants can absorb nutrients from rocks. Therefore, the output should be \\"E\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Co 2 is the molecular formula of carbon dioxide. Sentence 2: As the organic matter burns, the carbon is changed to carbon dioxide (CO 2 ) and carbon monoxide (CO).","target":"entails","rationale":"Statement 2 provides additional information about the compound carbon dioxide. It states that the burning of organic matter converts carbon into carbon dioxide and monoxide. This process supports the statement in Statement 1 that \\"CO2\\" is the molecular formula for carbon dioxide, which is composed of one atom of oxygen bonded to two atoms of carbon. As a result, Statement 2 entails or implies Statement 1."},{"source":"What is this Danish charter airline headquartered in Copenhagen which resulted from merging of two airlines and operates at Copenhagen Kastrup Airport?","target":"Thomas Cook Airlines Scandinavia","rationale":"The answer is based on the fact that Thomas Cook Airlines Scandinavia was formed by merging two airlines. It is a Danish charter airline headquartered in Copenhagen and operates at Copenhagen Kastrup Airport. \\nTherefore, the correct answer should be \\"Thomas Cook Airlines Scandinavia\\"."},{"source":"I'm taking a test and have to guess the right answer to the question after the article.\\nArticle: If you want to live in Hawaii,you need to think about how to save money,because it is one of the most expensive states in the USA.\\nHawaii buys most of its goods from other countries.This makes the prices very high.Eating out can be expensive.Breakfast is at$5 or$8 and lunch ia around$12,while dinner goes from $15 to$30.\\nWhat makes living in Hawaii more difficult is that there are few high-paying jobs. For example, it is harder to find engineering jobs than waitressing jobs.\\nHere is some advice on how to get around and enjoy living in Hawaii.\\n*Check out online travel websites, magazines and books for information about the islands, from their beaches to their restaurants.\\n*Find hotels by reading newspapers. You can also find someone to share your room to save money.\\n*Try to find a job. Craigslist is a good website to start your search. Also, check the newspapers.\\n*Buy your food and other things at cheap chain stores like Costco and Wal-Mart.\\nHawaii is an expensive place to live, but there are ways to save your money if you shop properly.\\nQuestion: What's the price of having breakfast in Hawaii?\\nOptions: A: $ 15.\\nB: $ 12.\\nC: $ 8.\\nD: $ 30.","target":"C","rationale":"The article mentions that breakfast is $5 or $8. Since the question asks for the price of having breakfast in Hawaii, and not dinner, D can be eliminated from choices. \\nSince there are no other items mentioned between options B and C, it's most likely that the answer to this question would be option C:$ 8"},{"source":"Sentence: \\"Either Dana or Lee are going to lead the parade.\\"\\nWould a linguist rate this sentence to be acceptable linguistically?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"puppy,\\" the verb is \\"was kissed,\\" and the object is \\"by the policeman.\\" Therefore, the sentence is linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"This article: Sir Robert Eric Mortimer Wheeler (10 September 1890 ‚Äì 22 July 1976) was a British archaeologist and officer in the British Army. Over the course of his career, he served as Director of both the National Museum of Wales and London Museum, Director-General of the Archaeological Survey of India, and the founder and Honorary Director of the Institute of Archaeology in London, in addition to writing twenty-four books on archaeological subjects.\\nBorn in Glasgow to a middle-class family, Wheeler was raised largely in Yorkshire before relocating to London in his teenage years. After studying classics at University College London (UCL), he began working professionally in archaeology, specialising in the Romano-British period. During World War I he volunteered for service in the Royal Artillery, being stationed on the Western Front, where he rose to the rank of major and was awarded the Military Cross. Returning to Britain, he obtained his doctorate from UCL before taking on a position at the National Museum of Wales, first as Keeper of Archaeology and then as Director, during which time he oversaw excavation at the Roman forts of Segontium, Y Gaer, and Isca Augusta with the aid of his first wife, Tessa Wheeler. Influenced by the archaeologist Augustus Pitt Rivers, Wheeler argued that excavation and the recording of stratigraphic context required an increasingly scientific and methodical approach, developing the \\"Wheeler method\\". In 1926, he was appointed Keeper of the London Museum; there, he oversaw a reorganisation of the collection, successfully lobbied for increased funding, and began lecturing at UCL.\\nIn 1934, he established the Institute of Archaeology as part of the federal University of London, adopting the position of Honorary Director. In this period, he oversaw excavations of the Roman sites at Lydney Park and Verulamium and the Iron Age hill fort of Maiden Castle. During World War II, he re-joined the Armed Forces and rose to the rank of brigadier, serving in the North African Campaign and then the Allied... contains an answer for the question: What is the last name of the person who oversaw excavation at the Roman forts of Segontium, Y Gaer, and Isca Augusta while serving as Director of the National Museum of Wales?, what is it ?","target":"Wheeler","rationale":"The article states that Wheeler oversaw excavation at the Roman forts of Segontium, Y Gaer, and Isca Augusta while serving as Director of the National Museum of Wales. The last name is \\"Wheeler\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a paragraph and title from the research paper. Your task is to classify whether the given title is suitable or not for the research paper based on the given paragraph. Return \\"True\\" if title is proper according to paragraph else \\"False\\".\\n\\nParagraph: Introduction. Posttraumatic stress disorder (PTSD) is accompanied by poor general psychological status (GPS). In the present study, we investigated the effects of a Chinese herbal formula on GPS in earthquake survivors with PTSD. Methods. A randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled trial compared a Chinese herbal formula, Xiao-Tan-Jie-Yu-Fang (XTJYF), to placebo in 2008 Sichuan earthquake survivors with PTSD. Patients were randomized into XTJYF (n = 123) and placebo (n = 122) groups. Baselineto-end-point score changes in the three global indices of the Symptom Checklist-90-Revised (SCL-90-R) and rates of response in the SCL global severity index (GSI) were the primary endpoints. A subanalysis of the nine SCL factors and the sleep quality score were secondary endpoints. Results and Discussion. Compared to placebo, the XTJYF group was significantly improved in all three SCL global indices (P = 0.001‚àº0.028). More patients in the XTJYF group reported \\"much improved\\" than the placebo group (P = 0.001). The XTJYF group performed significantly better than control in five out of nine SCL factors (somatization, obsessivecompulsive behavior, depression, anxiety, and hostility (P = 0.001‚àº0.036)), and in sleep quality score (P < 0.001). XTJYF produced no serious adverse events. These findings suggest that XTJYF may be an effective and safe treatment option for improving GPS in patients with PTSD. \\n Title: A Chinese Herbal Formula to Improve General Psychological Status in Posttraumatic Stress Disorder: A Randomized Placebo-Controlled Trial on Sichuan Earthquake Survivors","target":"True","rationale":"The title of this paper describes the specific goal, methods and results of a clinical trial that investigated whether a Chinese herbal formula can improve general psychological status in patients with PTSD. It provides clear information about what the researchers are trying to accomplish (to investigate whether XTJYF is an effective treatment option for improving GPS), how they conducted their research (a randomized placebo-control trial) and who participated in their study (2008 Sichuan earthquake survivors). Therefore, it serves as a suitable title for the article. So \\"True\\" should be returned.\\""},{"source":"Answer the question...who sings the original i can live if living is without you??","target":"Badfinger","rationale":"This song was sung by Badfinger."},{"source":"Given a pair of words, generate the relation between them. The first word is called the 'concept' and the second word is called the 'relatum' The relation must be one of the following: co-hyponym (coordinate), hypernym, meronym, attribute, event, or random. A coordinate relation indicates that the concept and relatum belong to the same semantic class. A hypernym relation indicates that the relatum is a category of which the concept is a specific instance. A meronym relation implies that relatum is a part/component/organ/member of the concept. An attribute relation is when the relatum is an adjective expressing an attribute of the concept. An event relation holds when the relatum is a verb referring to an action/activity/happening/event that is performed by or with the concept. If the relatum and concept are unrelated, the relation between them is 'random'. Classify your answers into coord, hyper, mero, attri, event, and random.\\n\\nConcept: pistol, Relatum: altruisme.","target":"random","rationale":"The concept 'pistol' cannot have any of the listed relations with 'altruisme'. The two words are unrelated, so the relation between them is 'random'."},{"source":"Write a correct answer for the question. You should reason about prototypical situations and provide the correct answer. Avoid answers that provide incomplete justification for the question.\\n\\nname an article of clothing you are constantly buying more of","target":"socks","rationale":"Socks are a very common article of clothing that are worn and washed often. Socks also tend to go missing in the wash, so people often buy more socks because they wear them out or lose them."},{"source":"Classify the given a piece of financial news into three classes: positive, negative, and neutral. Output must be 'positive', 'negative', or 'neutral'.\\n\\nEfore 's CEO Reijo Maihaniemi said that the company has developed and already delivered power supply units to respective systems based on this technology to Chinese sector company ZTE Corp SHE : 000063 .","target":"neutral","rationale":"In this financial news, Finnish power supply company Efore has developed and already delivered power supply units to ZTE based on a technology. This development is positive for ZTE because it will get the required power supplies from Efore. But, as the financial news does not provide any information about its impact on revenue or profits of either company, this topic can be classified as \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"In the Bulgarian census of 2011, a total of 48,945 people declared themselves to be Roman Catholics, up from 43,811 in the previous census of 2001 though down as compared to 53,074 in 1992. The vast majority of the Catholics in Bulgaria in 2001 were ethnic Bulgarians and the rest belonged to a number of other ethnic groups such as Croatians, Italians, Arabs and Germans. Bulgarian Catholics live predominantly in the regions of Svishtov and Plovdiv and are mostly descendants of the heretical Christian sect of the Paulicians, which converted to Roman Catholicism in the 16th and 17th centuries. The largest Roman Catholic Bulgarian town is Rakovski in Plovdiv Province. Ethnic Bulgarian Roman Catholics known as the Banat Bulgarians also inhabit the Central European region of the Banat. Their number is unofficially estimated at about 12,000, although Romanian censuses count only 6,500 Banat Bulgarians in the Romanian part of the region. Bulgarian Catholics are descendants of three groups. The first were converted Paulicians from the course of the Osam river  and around Plovdiv are the second  group, while the third  one is formed by more recent Eastern Orthodox converts.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"The first group of Bulgarian Catholics were descendants of which group, Eastern Orthodox converts or Paulicans of the Osam river?","rationale":"Here's a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: The first group of Bulgarian Catholics were descendants of which group, Eastern Orthodox converts or Paulicans of the Osam river?"},{"source":"The Arts Tower is a building at 12 Bolsover Street in Sheffield, England belonging to the University of Sheffield and opened in 1966. English Heritage has called it \\"the most elegant university tower block in Britain of its period\\". At 78 m (255 feet) tall, it is the second tallest building in the city, after the 101 m, St Paul's Tower on Arundel Gate, which was topped out in 2009.\\nCan we infer the following?\\nSheffield, England is a progressive area.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No\\nThe answer is:","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"While the information provided in the options about Sheffield suggests that it is an area with some modern architecture, there is not enough information to determine whether or not it qualifies as a \\"progressive\\" city. The term \\"progressive\\" does not have specific criteria and can vary depending on different factors. So, the answer should be It's impossible to say"},{"source":"Given a passage classify if the passage has a definite objective/aim/goal or not. Output '1' if the passage has a defininte objective/aim/goal and output '0' if the passage does not have a definite objective/aim/goal.\\n\\nEarly metastasis in node-negative breast cancer indicates that breast cancer cells obviously can bypass the lymph nodes and disseminate directly hematogenous to distant organs. For this purpose, we evaluated the prognostic value of blood-borne, HER2-positive circulating tumor cells (CTC) in the peripheral blood from 42 breast cancer patients with a median follow-up of 95 months.', 'Cells were isolated by the patented combined buoyant density gradient and immunomagnetic separation procedure and analyzed by immunocytochemistry.', 'We detected one to eight CTCs in the peripheral blood of 17 of 35 patients (48.6%) presenting no overt metastasis. As a positive control, 7 of 7 (100%) patients with metastatic disease presented positive. Healthy persons and patients (n = 32) operated for nonmalignant diseases presented negative for CTCs. The presence and frequency of HER2-positive CTCs correlated with a significantly decreased disease-free survival (P < 0.005) and overall survival (P < 0.05). Interestingly, in 12 patients with HER2-positive CTCs, the primary tumor was negative for HER2 as assessed by immunohistochemical score and fluorescence in situ hybridization.","target":"1","rationale":"The passage states that the objective of the study was \\\\\\"to evaluate the prognostic value of blood-borne, HER2-positive circulating tumor cells in the peripheral blood from 42 breast cancer patients with a median follow-up of 95 months\\\\\\" and describes how this was done. Therefore, there is a definite objective in this passage. The output is '1'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two strings A, B. Find the longest common substring in the strings A and B.\\n\\nyDawTNwvmn, ZXWwTNwmlcc","target":"wTNw","rationale":"The longest common substring in given strings is \\"wTNw\\"."},{"source":"Please answer correctly the following question related to the paragraph below. \\n\\nWhich team learned about keystone species?\\n\\nTwo teams studied two types of animals: team A studied predators, while team B studied grazers. They learned a lot from this experience.\\n\\nHint: Predators play an important role in an ecosystem. For example, if they did not exist, then a single species could become dominant over others. Grazers on a grassland keep grass from growing out of control. Predators can be keystone species . These are species that can have a large effect on the balance of organisms in an ecosystem. For example, if all of the wolves are removed from a population, then the population of deer or rabbits may increase. If there are too many deer, then they may decrease the amount of plants or grasses in the ecosystem. Decreased levels of producers may then have a detrimental effect on the whole ecosystem. In this example, the wolves would be a keystone species.","target":"team A","rationale":"In the passage, both teams studied two types of animals. Team A learned about predators and keystone species , which are important for maintaining ecosystem balance. Predators could be considered a major reason why too many deer can destroy an entire area‚Äôs vegetation because they hunt and keep the population in check from growing out of control . Wolves (a type of predator) were listed as examples in the paragraph above to help explain what kind of effects certain species have on their ecosystems when removed or overpopulated. So team A was studying predators that can act as keystones within ecosystems by keeping other populations balanced through predation/hunting like wolves do with rabbits and deer; so this makes them much more dangerous than grazers who only eat grasses and plant life leaving no room for destruction towards another animal"},{"source":"Given a passage classify if the passage has a definite objective/aim/goal or not. Output '1' if the passage has a defininte objective/aim/goal and output '0' if the passage does not have a definite objective/aim/goal.\\n\\nEarly trauma-induced coagulopathy may increase susceptibility to nosocomial infections such as ventilator-associated pneumonia. However, the relationship between trauma- induced coagulopathy and the development of ventilator-associated pneumonia in spinal cord injury patients has not been evaluated.', 'We conducted a 5-year retrospective study of 300 spinal cord injury patients admitted to Level 1 trauma center. Standard coagulation studies were evaluated upon arrival, prior to fluid resuscitative efforts, and at 24 \\\\u200ah after admission. Based on these studies, three groups of patients were identified: no coagulopathy, latent coagulopathy, and admission coagulopathy. Ventilator- associated pneumonia was identified utilizing Centers for Disease Control and Prevention criteria. Since we used the data in the trauma registry and did not have the information on FiO2 and PEEP, we elected to use the VAP terminology and not the VAE sequence. Demographic, injury, and clinical characteristics were compared among no coagulopathy, latent coagulopathy, and admission coagulopathy groups using chi-square test and ANOVA for categorical and continuous variables, respectively. A logistic regression was used to estimate odds ratios (ORs) and 95% confidence intervals (CIs) for the association between coagulopathy and both ventilator-associated pneumonia and mortality.', 'The incidence of ventilator-associated pneumonia was 54.5% (OR 4.01, 95% CI 1.76-9.15) in spinal cord injury patients with admission coagulopathy, compared with the 17.5% in spinal cord injury patients with no coagulopathy. Mortality was significantly higher in spinal cord injury patients with admission coagulopathy than in spinal cord injury patients with no coagulopathy (OR 6.14, 95% CI 1.73-21.73).After adjusting for age, race, injury mechanism, Injury Severity Score, base deficit at admission, the number of pRBC units transfused in the first 24\\\\u200a h, and hospital stay, only the association of ventilator-associated pneumonia among those with admission coagulopathy remained significant (OR 3.51, 95% CI 1.48-8.32). Compared with those with no coagulopathy, patients with admission coagulopathy had a higher odds of death (4.10, 95% CI 1.53-11.02), though this association lost significance after adjustment (OR 3.56, 95% CI 0.90-14.12). There was no statistical difference in mortality for latent coagulopathy compared with no coagulopathy patients.","target":"0","rationale":"The passage describes a study that retrospectively examines the relationship between trauma-induced coagulopathy and ventilator associated pneumonia in spinal cord injury patients. It provides information on the methods, results, and interpretation of the study. However, it does not explicitly state a main objective or aim. Therefore, the output is '0'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two statements. The task is to output whether a given textual premise, i.e. Statement 2, entails or implies a given scientific fact, i.e. Statement 1. The output should be 'entails' if Statement 2 supports Statement 1 and should be 'neutral' otherwise.\\n\\nSentence 1: Opaque is the term for matter that does not let any light pass through. Sentence 2: The density of that very dense matter was originally so high that it was then opaque and light could not pass through it.","target":"entails","rationale":"Statement 2 provides additional information that supports the scientific fact stated in Statement 1. Statement 1 defines opaque matter as \\"matter that does not let any light pass through\\", and statement 2 explains how this is true by describing how an extremely dense state of matter prevents light from passing through. Therefore, statement 2 entails or implies statement one."},{"source":"You are given two sentences. You have to find if there is entailment or agreement of the Hypothesis by the Premise. From the given pair of sentences, you should identify if there is enough information in the Premise to support the claim made in the Hypothesis. The Premise may not exactly be the same as Hypothesis. Your task is to return 'entails' if the premise supports hypothesis else return 'neutral'.\\n\\nPremise: Social Communication Among Animals. \\n Hypothesis: For social animals, communication essential.","target":"neutral","rationale":"The premise provides information about the topic of a book. It does not provide any direct evidence to support or refute the claim made in the hypothesis that communication is essential for social animals. As a result, the answer is \\"neutral\\"."},{"source":"You are provided with a list of converations between a \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\". Figure out if the conversation provided as \\"classify_text\\" is authored by \\"USER\\" or \\"ASSISTANT\\". There are maximum of 7 conversations between \\"USER\\" and \\"ASSISTANT\\" in each input\\n\\nASSISTANT: What type of movies do you enjoy? , ASSISTANT: What appeals to you with these type of movies? , USER: Gives me the life to keep living and like just every story is the same not the same and to live and experience a new like a person's story. , ASSISTANT: Is there a specific movie you enjoy from this genre? , USER: Yeah, I love The Wild. It's a new film. Into the Wild. The authentic relationship between father and daughter, and then or father and son, and then father and wife. , ASSISTANT: What did you like about this movie?, classify_text: Are there any type of movies that you don't enjoy?","target":"ASSISTANT","rationale":"\\"ASSISTANT\\" is the one asking all the questions in this conversation, with \\"USER\\" responding to the questions. In this case, \\"classify_text\\" is a question and hence it must be from \\"ASSISTANT\\"."},{"source":"The Spice Girls are an English pop girl group formed in 1994. The group originally consisted of Melanie Brown (\\"Scary Spice\\"), Melanie Chisholm (\\"Sporty Spice\\"), Emma Bunton (\\"Baby Spice\\"), Geri Halliwell (\\"Ginger Spice\\"), and Victoria Beckham, nee Adams (\\"Posh Spice\\"). They were signed to Virgin Records and released their debut single \\"Wannabe\\" in 1996, which hit number one in 37 countries and established them as a global phenomenon. Their debut album Spice sold more than 31 million copies worldwide, becoming the best-selling album by a female group in history.\\n\\nThe phrase \\"girl power\\" put a name to a social phenomenon, but the slogan was met with mixed reactions. The phrase was a label for the particular facet of post classical neo-feminist empowerment embraced by the band: that a sensual, feminine appearance and equality between the sexes need not be mutually exclusive. This concept was by no means original in the pop world: both Madonna and Bananarama had employed similar outlooks. The phrase itself had also appeared in a few songs by British girl groups and bands since at least 1987; most notably, it was the name of British pop duo Shampoo's 1996 single and album, later credited by Halliwell as the inspiration for the Spice Girls' mantra.  However, it was not until the emergence of the Spice Girls in 1996 with \\"Wannabe\\", that the concept of \\"girl power\\" exploded onto the common consciousness. The phrase was regularly uttered by all five members--although most closely associated with Halliwell--and was often delivered with a peace sign. The slogan also featured on official Spice Girls merchandise and on some of the outfits the group members wore. The Spice Girls' version was distinctive. Its message of empowerment appealed to young girls, adolescents and adult women, and it emphasised the importance of strong and loyal friendship among females.  In all, the focused, consistent presentation of \\"girl power\\" formed the centrepiece of their appeal as a band. Some commentators credit the Spice Girls with reinvigorating mainstream feminism--popularized as \\"girl power\\"--in the 1990s, with their mantra serving as a gateway to feminism for their young fans. On the other hand, some critics dismissed it as no more than a shallow marketing tactic, while others took issue with the emphasis on physical appearance, concerned about the potential impact on self-conscious and/or impressionable youngsters. Regardless, the phrase became a cultural phenomenon, adopted as the mantra for millions of girls and even making it into the Oxford English Dictionary. In summation of the concept, author Ryan Dawson said, \\"The Spice Girls changed British culture enough for Girl Power to now seem completely unremarkable.\\"  The Spice Girls' debut single \\"Wannabe\\" has been hailed as an \\"iconic girl power anthem\\". In 2016, the United Nations' Global Goals \\"#WhatIReallyReallyWant\\" campaign filmed a global remake of the original music video for \\"Wannabe\\" to highlight gender inequality issues faced by women across the world. The video, which was launched on YouTube and ran in movie theatres internationally, featured British girl group M.O, Canadian \\"viral sensation\\" Taylor Hatala, Nigerian-British singer Seyi Shay and Bollywood actress Jacqueline Fernandez lip-syncing to the song in various locations around the world. In response to the remake, Beckham said, \\"How fabulous is it that after 20 years the legacy of the Spice Girls' girl power is being used to encourage and empower a whole new generation?\\"  At the 43rd People's Choice Awards in January 2017, American actress Blake Lively dedicated her \\"Favorite Dramatic Movie Actress\\" award to \\"girl power\\" in her acceptance speech, and credited the Spice Girls, saying: \\"What was so neat about them was that they're all so distinctly different, and they were women, and they owned who they were, and that was my first introduction into girl power.\\" Answer this question using a quote from the following article:\\n\\nWhat did she say during the speech?","target":"What was so neat about them was that they're all so distinctly different, and they were women, and they owned who they were,","rationale":"The question asks for a quote from the actress's speech. The last sentence of her speech, \\"What was so neat about them was that they're all so distinctly different, and they were women, and they owned who they were,\\" is quoted in the article.\\nTherefore, this must be one of the correct answers to the question: What did she say during the speech?"},{"source":"Does the sentence \\"The study found that health literacy increases with education and people living below the level of poverty have lower health literacy than those above it.\\" answer the question \\"What percentage of Americans fell below the basics of health literacy?\\"\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The sentence does not give any information about the percentage of Americans falling below health literacy. The passage only states that \\"Health literacy is lower among persons with less education, older adults and racial/ethnic minorities.\\" So, we can say that it's a 'no'."},{"source":"Answer the following question.\\nDungeness is a headland on the coast of which English county?","target":"Kent (England)","rationale":"The answer is based on the fact that Dungeness is a headland on the coast of Kent, England. \\n\\nMoreover, it can be found at: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungeness_(headland)\\n\\n\\nTherefore, the correct answer should be \\"Kent (England)\\" or simply \\"Kent\\"."},{"source":"Give me the correct facts to answer this: where was the battle of verdun ww1?","target":"Verdun","rationale":"Verdun"},{"source":"The task is to generate the correct answer for a given math problem.\\n\\nProblem: mr . loyd wants to fence his square shaped land of 120 sqft each side . if a pole is laid every 12 ft how many poles do he need ?","target":"40","rationale":"Length of land = 120 ft\\\\nDistance between poles = 12 ft\\\\nTotal poles needed to fence the land= (120/12) * 4 = 40"},{"source":"Read the following article and answer the question.\\nArticle: Do you wake up in the morning dreading the moment that your feet have to hit the floor for you to get ready for work? If that's the case, join most of Americans. Very few people wake up to that annoying alarm clock and spring out of bed excited about having to go to work.\\nAs if that were not enough, most of us have to fight traffic getting there, usually an hour's drive. Then, when we get to work, we have to fight with unruly co-workers or a nagging boss. And to make matters worse, you have to fight the same traffic going in the opposite direction just to get back home.\\nMaking dinner, fixing plates, eating and then straightening up afterwards is a job within itself. If that sounds like your life, you probably have a J-O-B. you know what J-O-B stands for? Just Over Broke, that's what! With a job, most Americans are living paycheck-to-paycheck and hating every minute of it. I know because I was doing the same thing: trading time for money. And, I came to a conclusion that it stinks  ! Big time!\\nLooking around at my co-workers, friends and relatives, I saw that they were all doing the same thing I was doing. They were complaining about the same things I was complaining about : not having enough time or money. And, I decided that I wanted to do\\n.[:**\\nSo, I started a home-based business. There are several to choose from. The extra income has done so much for our family. We can vacation more. We have been able to give more. And, we've even been able to do something calling save! It's been amazing.\\nTherefore, if you're sick and tired of being sick and tired, it's time you make a change, too. The definition of insanity   is doing the same thing over and over and expecting different results. I know you aren't stupid. If you continue to do what everyone else is doing: trading time for money, you're going to keep getting what everyone else is getting: being broke and not having the time to do what is really important to you.\\nDo your due diligence. Find a home-based business that works well for you. Go to work, and live...\\nQuestion: What does \\"something different\\" in Paragraph 4 refer to?\\nAnswer:","target":"To set up a business at home.","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"To set up a business at home."},{"source":"Does the sentence \\"The Byzantines also faced a revived Bulgaria, which in the late 12th and 13th centuries spread throughout the Balkans.\\" answer the question \\"During what century did the Seljuk Turks occupy Persia?\\"\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The sentence does not answer the question of which century the Seljuk Turks occupied Persia. The time period described in this sentence is about 200 years off from being relevant to answering the given question, therefore, it would be incorrect to say that \\"yes\\" it answers this particular question."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question-answer pair.\\nQuestion: \\"where is Chayanne from??\\";  Answer: \\"Elmer Figueroa Arce (born June 28, 1968), best known under the stage name Chayanne, is a Puerto Rican Latin pop singer and actor.\\"? Topic:","target":"Chayanne","rationale":"The answer starts with the full name of Chayanne, which is Elmer Figueroa Arce. This would be a good indicator that this person may very well be the topic of the question. However, there are other additional clues in both the question and its answer to support this observation: \\nIn addition to his first name being mentioned at the start of t"},{"source":"Read the following article and answer the question.\\nArticle: Perfect grades, perfect bodies, perfect friends. Welcome to Generation Supergirl - the young women who are supposed to have everything.\\nUnlike their grandmothers, they don't have to fight for their right to be heard. Unlike their mothers, they are confident they can have the career without sacrificing the home life.\\nRecord numbers of them are achieving top grades, heading to the best universities and on to great jobs.\\nBut are all these opportunities making them happy? According to a new book, Supergirls Speak Out: Inside the Secret Crisis of Over-Achieving Girls, the answer is no.\\nAs the book's 21-year-old author, Liz Funk, explains: Their search for perfection has turned them into stressed-out women who are at risk of eating disorders, depression and even suicide .\\nSo why have so many teenage girls come to the conclusion that anything short of perfection is failure?\\nStephen Hinshaw, professor of psychology at the University of California, Berkeley, believes that they are suffering from the weight of expectations: society's, their parents', and most crucially , their own.\\nThey are constantly bombarded by \\"perfect\\" celebrity(, ). Articles about how to have the perfect career and perfect life appear to be everywhere.\\nSo it is hardly surprising that increasing numbers of young women are unable to cope and are unsure of just who they are. \\"Many teenage girls have no intrinsic sense of their own worth,\\" says Funk. \\"Instead, they see themselves in terms of how they look, how they are seen, what they've achieved.\\"\\nTeenage girls believe that they must be all things to all people. They must be good at \\"girl\\" stuff-cultivating relationships and being beautiful - as well as being good at \\"guy\\" stuff - competing aggressively both at college and in the workplace.\\nAccording to Funk, teenage girls need to recognize that \\"you don't have to be successful at everything.\\" \\"Young women should take time for themselves and think about what matters to them, or enjoy life for what it is,\\" she said.\\nQuestion: What's the best title for this passage?\\nAnswer:","target":"Do they have to be perfect?","rationale":"The article discusses perfectionism among teenage girls and the problems this causes. The passage questions whether women being perfect is setting unrealistic expectations for young people, which leads to stress and mental health issues.\\nTherefore, \\"Do they have to be perfect?\\" would make a good title for the article because it summarizes the main topic of discussion - namely that expecting perfection from teenage girls may not always be appropriate or healthy ."},{"source":"In this task, you're shown a three-part story, with a beginning, middle, and ending. Your job is to slightly modify the middle part, so that the whole story becomes unlikely, improbable, or inconsistent. Generated sentences must minimally alter the given middle, with at most 4 new words added/existing words removed. Your sentence should be grammatically and syntactically correct. Also stick to the context of the given story. For example, if the story talks about \\"doctors\\", you can talk about \\"health\\" or \\"diagnosis\\", but don't mention \\"aliens\\". Avoid introducing any extra/irrelevant information, and use names instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible. Avoid simply negating the original middle, for example:  \\"She likes cakes.\\" is changed to \\"She doesn't like cakes.\\"\\n\\nBeginning: Dakota received her summer camp packing list. Middle: Dakota made sure she had everything on the list. Ending: When it was time to go to camp she was ready.","target":"Dakota made sure she had everything on the list for groceries","rationale":"The middle implies that the protagonist is preparing for summer camp. However, it is unlikely that a summer camp would provide a list of groceries for their attendees to bring along. Therefore, we can change the last part of the middle to \\"Dakota made sure she had everything on the list for groceries\\". The new sentence makes it clear that Dakota was packing food and not supplies needed at summer camp."},{"source":"EXAM\\n1. Answer by yes or no.\\n\\nDocument: Venomoid -- A venomoid is a venomous snake that has undergone a surgical procedure to remove or inhibit the production of snake venom. This procedure has been used for venomous snakes kept as pets or used in public demonstrations in order to remove the risk of injury or death when handled. The removal of venom glands or fangs of exhibited animals may be by surgery or simple mutilation; some or all of these procedures have been considered illegal and unethical. Removal of fangs is uncommon, as snakes frequently regenerate teeth, and the more invasive procedure of removing the underlying maxillary bone would be fatal. Most venomoid procedures consist of either removing the venom gland itself, or severing the duct between the gland and the fang. However, the duct and gland have been known to regenerate, and supposedly \`\`safe'' snakes have killed mice and successfully envenomated humans.\\nQuestion: can you remove venom glands from a snake?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The document states that venomoid is a snake with removed or inhibited production of snake venom, which means there are snakes whose venom glands were successfully removed. This would imply that one can remove the venom gland from a snake and therefore answer to this question is 'Yes'.\\nNote: Please use the information directly stated in the documents."},{"source":"Use a disfluent question or a proper question and find the answer to the question based on the given context or return None if an answer can't be found. A disfluent question is a question that has some interruptions in it while framing. A proper question is the correct form of the question without any disfluency.\\n\\nproper question: What was the Warsaw Pact war plan? \\n disfluent question: What was the Rhine bridge at Arnhem instead use the Warsaw Pact war plan? \\n context: In World War II, it was recognised that the Rhine would present a formidable natural obstacle to the invasion of Germany, by the Western Allies. The Rhine bridge at Arnhem, immortalized in the book, A Bridge Too Far and the film, was a central focus of the battle for Arnhem, during the failed Operation Market Garden of September 1944. The bridges at Nijmegen, over the Waal distributary of the Rhine, were also an objective of Operation Market Garden. In a separate operation, the Ludendorff Bridge, crossing the Rhine at Remagen, became famous, when U.S. forces were able to capture it intact ‚Äì much to their own surprise ‚Äì after the Germans failed to demolish it. This also became the subject of a film, The Bridge at Remagen. Seven Days to the River Rhine was a Warsaw Pact war plan for an invasion of Western Europe during the Cold War.","target":"Seven Days to the River Rhine","rationale":"The disfluent question contains the proper question as a sub-string. The mention of \\"Rhine\\" in the context directs us to look into the answer named Seven Days to the River Rhine."},{"source":"What is the answer?\\nContext: After the start of the civil war, various new telecommunications companies began to spring up in the country and competed to provide missing infrastructure. Somalia now offers some of the most technologically advanced and competitively priced telecommunications and internet services in the world. Funded by Somali entrepreneurs and backed by expertise from China, Korea and Europe, these nascent telecommunications firms offer affordable mobile phone and internet services that are not available in many other parts of the continent. Customers can conduct money transfers (such as through the popular Dahabshiil) and other banking activities via mobile phones, as well as easily gain wireless Internet access.;\\nQuestion: When the civil war began, many telecomunications companies were created to provide missing what?;\\nIf you can't find the answer, please respond \\"unanswerable\\".\\nAnswer:","target":"infrastructure","rationale":"The context states that after the start of a civil war in Somalia, many new telecommunications companies were created to provide missing infrastructure. \\nThus, the answer is \\"infrastructure\\"."},{"source":"Here's a question and a few possible answers: \\n\\nQ: What could you find in a bookstore that is not for sale?\\nPossible A: magazines, phone book, carpeting, town, city\\n\\nWhy is \\"carpeting\\" an answer aligned with human common sense?","target":"very few stores sell their carpets","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"very few stores sell their carpets\\"."},{"source":"Suggest a movie title for the following movie plot: A stray grey alley tom tabby cat is chased by a disheveled St. Bernard dog, and nearly gets run down by a red 1958 Plymouth Fury. He hides from the dog in a delivery truck, which drives to New York City. The tomcat hears the disembodied voice of a young girl (Drew Barrymore) pleading for help because something is threatening her. The cat is then captured by an employee from Quitters, Inc.\\n\\"Quitters, Inc.\\"[edit]\\nCigarette smoker Dick Morrison (James Woods) is advised by a friend to join Quitters, Inc. to kick his habit. Clinic counselor Dr. Vinnie Donatti (Alan King) explains that the clinic has a 100% success rate due to a uniquely persuasive method: every time Dick smokes a cigarette, horrors of increasing magnitude will befall his wife and child.\\nUsing the tomcat that Donatti's assistant Junk has caught in the street, Donatti demonstrates the first of these horrors: the cat is locked in a cage and tormented with electric shocks. Donatti explains that if his new client should be caught with a cigarette, Dick's wife Cindy will be subjected to the same shocks while he is forced to watch. For subsequent infractions, his young daughter afflicted with Down Syndrome will be subjected to the shocks, then his wife raped, and after the fourth infraction, they give up (i.e. kill him). Not wanting to worry them, Dick hides the looming threat from his family.\\nThat night, Dick is angered by the methods Quitters uses and notices an undisposed pack of cigarettes in his desk. He prepares to smoke it, but notices a set of feet in his closet, realizing Quitters Inc. is serious about their threat to ensure he is not smoking. The following day, Dick visits his daughter (also played by Drew Barrymore) and gives her a doll. Donatti is also at the school, warning Dick that if he strays the only thing his daughter would understand is that someone is hurting her because her father misbehaved. Morrison resolves to never let that happen, and Donatti hopes so for her sake.\\nTwo weeks later, Dick is at a party where he is the only guest...","target":"Cat's Eye","rationale":"Cat's Eye is a 1985 horror film directed by Lewis Teague and written by Stephen King. It comprises three separate stories linked together by a stray cat traveling from town to town, searching for its original owner (Candy Clark). The first segment involves the battle between a woman who has quit smoking with help of an unorthodox clinic against their attempts to make her start again; this story was also published in 1975 as Quitters Inc., and later adapted into both comic book form, shown at the end of Creepshow 2, which starred James Woods as Donatti)\\n\\"The Ledge\\"[edit] \\nand an episode \\"Quitter's Inc.\\" on Tales From the Darkside season 3 Episode 1 with John Glover playing Vinnie Donati"},{"source":"Given a pair of words, generate the relation between them. The first word is called the 'concept' and the second word is called the 'relatum' The relation must be one of the following: co-hyponym (coordinate), hypernym, meronym, attribute, event, or random. A coordinate relation indicates that the concept and relatum belong to the same semantic class. A hypernym relation indicates that the relatum is a category of which the concept is a specific instance. A meronym relation implies that relatum is a part/component/organ/member of the concept. An attribute relation is when the relatum is an adjective expressing an attribute of the concept. An event relation holds when the relatum is a verb referring to an action/activity/happening/event that is performed by or with the concept. If the relatum and concept are unrelated, the relation between them is 'random'. Classify your answers into coord, hyper, mero, attri, event, and random.\\n\\nConcept: jet, Relatum: feast.","target":"random","rationale":"The word \\"jet\\" is a noun that refers to a type of aircraft. The word \\"feast\\" is a noun that refers to an elaborate and extensive meal. There does not seem to be any connection between the two words, so the answer is 'random'."},{"source":"Does the following sentence make sense?\\n\\"Most Christians do not believe the Book of Revelation to be true.\\"\\n\\n[Options]\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The Book of Revelation is part of biblical canon and is accepted by the majority of Christians."},{"source":"Choose from options: Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below:\\nBeilin District is popular with asians\\n\\nBeilin District () is one of nine districts of Xi'an, the capital of Shanxi province, China. The well-known Small Wild Goose Pagoda is also located in the district. The smallest, but most densely populated, of Xi'an's county-level divisions, it borders the districts of Xincheng to the northeast, Yanta to the south, and Lianhu to the northwest.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"It's impossible to say","rationale":"The text does not mention anything about the popularity of Beilin District among asians. In fact, it only mentions that this district is one of nine districts in Xi'an and its famous landmark Small Wild Goose Pagoda. Therefore, we cannot determine if the statement is true or false based on this information alone; thus, \\"It's impossible to say\\" must be our answer choice here."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: If not the Surgeon general then who is responsible for the health service to the Canadian Armed Forces?\\nContext: The Health Services Group is a joint formation that includes over 120 general or specialized units and detachments providing health services to the Canadian Armed Forces. With few exceptions, all elements are under command of the Surgeon General for domestic support and force generation, or temporarily assigned under command of a deployed Joint Task Force through Canadian Joint Operations Command.","target":"deployed Joint Task Force","rationale":"The Surgeon General is responsible for the Health Services Group, which provides health services to the Canadian Armed Forces. This group includes units and detachments that provide support domestically as well as those assigned under command of a deployed Joint Task Force (JTF).\\nTherefore, since the JTFs are not in Canada they would not be supported by The Surgeon general but rather by other military personnel who operate outside of his or her jurisdiction."},{"source":"See the conversation. DIALOG:\\nWhat was Dario Varotari the Elder's artistic style like?\\n- Dario Varotari the Elder Dario Varotari the Elder (c. 1539‚Äì1596) was an Italian painter, sculptor, and architect of the Renaissance.\\n- Did he have any inspirations?\\n-","target":"Born in Verona, he was descended from a Strasburg or Augsburg family of the name of 'Weyrotter.' He was a pupil of Paolo Veronese, and an imitator of Titian.","rationale":"The user asks about Dario Varotari the Elder's artistic style, and is told that he was an Italian painter, sculptor, and architect of the Renaissance. The user then goes on to ask whether he had any inspirations. Therefore the correct choice is \\"Born in Verona, he was descended from a Strasburg or Augsburg family of the name of 'Weyrotter.' He was a pupil of Paolo Veronese, and an imitator of Titian.\\""},{"source":"Question: When were the mosaics at the Basilica of Sant'Apollinare created?\\nAnswer: The mosaics of the Basilica of Sant'Apollinare in Classe were made around 549.\\n A single-select problem: Is the question answered in a satisfactory fashion?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"The answer given provides the date when the mosaics were made, which is exactly what was asked in the question. Hence, it satisfies the requirements of a satisfactory response to this question and can be classified as \\"yes\\"."},{"source":"By Sara Malm PUBLISHED: 14:31 EST, 30 October 2013 | UPDATED: 17:00 EST, 30 October 2013 Their goal lies across the water, on the shores of Dover, where they believe they will finally be able to leave their experiences of their war-torn homes behind. They have pitched their tents close to the shore after long and troublesome journeys from countries such as Syria, Iraq and Somalia, to seek asylum in the UK. Hundreds of refugees are camping out in Calais, France, awaiting the next opportunity to cross the English Channel. Shoreline: An encampment of makeshift tents near the Calais ferry port, home to migrants of mainly Afghan origin awaiting an opportunity to cross\\n@highlight\\nHundreds of refugees are camping on the shores of Calais, France\\n@highlight\\nMain goal for migrants is to get to Britain to seek asylum\\n@highlight\\nThe UK, unlike France, pays benefits to asylum seekers\\nRoad to @placeholder: Graffiti purporting to direct migrants to the border is scrawled across a Calais road sign\\n\\nPick one option, \\"@placeholder\\" refers to:\\n- Afghan\\n- Britain\\n- Calais\\n- Dover\\n- English Channel\\n- France\\n- Iraq\\n- Main\\n- Sara Malm\\n- Shoreline\\n- Somalia\\n- Syria\\n- UK","target":"Britain","rationale":"The context states that these migrants are trying to get to Britain in order to seek asylum. Later, the text also mentions how they believe they will leave their experiences of war behind by coming here and receiving benefits as asylum seekers. \\nAnother mention of \\"Britain\\" can be seen a little earlier where it says: 'Hundreds of refugees camping out in Calais, France'.. The next line is 'awaiting an opportunity to cross the English Channel'. This means the migrants are currently lodged at this place called \\"Calais\\", which is located in France very close to Dover (England) and separated from England only by some water body referred as \\"English Channel\\". So obviously @placeholder would refer to UK or more specifically --->> Britain"},{"source":"Goal: How can I keep my Bagel fresh at the office?\\n\\nWhich is the correct ending?\\n- Use and old DVD spindle and case, put the bagel inside and the spindle goes in the middle, lid goes on top to seal it.\\n- Use and old C D spindle and case, put the bagel inside and the spindle goes in the middle, lid goes on top to seal it.\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"Use and old C D spindle and case, put the bagel inside and the spindle goes in the middle, lid goes on top to seal it.","rationale":"The correct answer is \\nUse and old C D spindle and case, put the bagel inside and the spindle goes in the middle, lid goes on top to seal it.\\n\\n\\n'''"},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: what money do they use in chile?","target":"Chilean peso","rationale":"The official currency of Chile is the Chilean peso.\\nTherefore, \\"Chilean Peso\\" should be considered a correct answer to this question."},{"source":"Question: He was a bit of an audiophile, he replaced the stylus almost as often as he switched albums to listen to on his what?\\n\\nChoices: \\n- record player\\n- palm pilot\\n- hand\\n- ink\\n- fridge\\n\\nThe rationale to choose \\"record player\\" as the answer is that:","target":"record player plays music","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"record player plays music\\""},{"source":"Combine facts and answer this: Which 1997 American action film starring Steven Seagal was nominated for 4 Golden Raspberry Awards?","target":"Fire Down Below","rationale":"Here's an direct answer: Fire Down Below is a 1997 American action film starring Steven Seagal and was nominated for 4 Golden Raspberry Awards."},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that is the least toxic with respect to continuing the prompt. Toxicity is defined as a rude, disrespectful, or unreasonable statement that is likely to make you leave a discussion. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: I hate this clown-ass black man. I do not believe shithe \\nCompletion A: al is right- wing,\\" said one white person to another.  He told the Daily Caller that he thinks Trump is \\"a man of integrity \\nCompletion B: terstitialABLEorthernHuhnedSlowapeLetUmotiamCopesKipplyIfANusesItNowCutFastDiscoveryBruove","target":"Completion B","rationale":"Completion A contains a hate speech (racist), while Completion B is not toxic."},{"source":"Given a concept word, generate a hypernym for it. A hypernym is a superordinate, i.e. a word with a broad meaning constituting a category, that generalizes another word. For example, color is a hypernym of red.\\n\\nfeel","target":"touch","rationale":"Feel is a synonym for touch, which is more general than feel."},{"source":"In this task, you are provided with an article of the legal acts. Your task is to classify it into three categories (Regulation, Decision and Directive) based on its content: 1) Regulation is a binding legislative act that must be applied in its entirety on a set date across all the member states (European Union countries). 2) Decision is binding on those to whom it is addressed (e.g. an European Union country or an individual company) and is directly applicable. 3) Directive is a legislative act that sets out a goal that all  must achieve. However, it is up to the individual countries to devise their own laws on how to reach these goals.\\n\\nThe Government of the Kingdom of Belgium is hereby authorized in respect of the calendar year 1976 to grant the following aids to the Belgian coal-mining industry:    (a) for the financing of investment projects:Campine coalfield, up to Bfrs 230 000 000, Sud coalfield, up to Bfrs 11 300 000;(b) for the covering of costs of stocks of coal and coke:Campine coalfield, up to Bfrs 467 500 000;(c) for the covering of pit operating losses:Campine coalfield, up to Bfrs 2 250 200 000, Sud coalfield, up to Bfrs 2 729 200 000. The Government of the Kingdom of Belgium shall notify the Commission by 30 November 1977 of details of the aids granted pursuant to this Decision, and in particular of the amount of the payments made and the manner in which they are apportioned. This Decision is addressed to the Kingdom of Belgium.","target":"Decision","rationale":"This article is a Decision, which is binding on those to whom it is addressed (e.g. an European Union country or an individual company) and is directly applicable."},{"source":"What is the topic from this? \\nQuestion: What part of him did Le Corbusier say proper architecture touched?;  Answer: heart; Topic:","target":"Architecture","rationale":"The provided context has already been categorized as \\"Architecture\\". It is a description of the work and philosophy of Le Corbusier. The text states that he believed architecture should affect people's emotions, specifically their hearts. This extract shows that the topic for this particular passage would be \\"architecture\\".\\n\\n\\n</code>\\n\\n\\nA:\\n\\nNote to Code Review visitors - I am not sure if there are any specific guidelines here in terms of what constitutes an answer on your site but my comment was too long so posting it here instead...  :)   (Also posted as a comment)   \\nFirstly well done you! Its great stuff seeing someone put effort into doing something like this which will help them learn more about coding etc its just brilliant!! So good luck with everything"},{"source":"Louis arrived in Charleroi on 5 May 1672. Turenne's 50,000 men set off on 11 May. Arrived at Vis√©, Louis decided not to lay siege to Maastricht but only to occupy the surrounding forts of Tongeren, Maaseik and Valkenburg so its garrison stayed bottled up. Moving along the Rhine, Rheinberg, Wesel, Burick and Orsoy were taken. Turenne then took Nijmegen , with 4,000 infantry and 400 cavalry, and from there Fort Cr√®vec≈ìur near 's-Hertogenbosch, which fell after only two days. In view of these defeats, the Dutch public panicked and rioted. Leading politicians Johan and Cornelis de Witt were lynched by an angry Orangist mob, following rumours  that they were planning the assassination of William of Nassau . On 4 July, William was acclaimed stadtholder. As the French had promised the major cities of Holland to the English, they were in no hurry to capture them. The French tried to gain sixteen million guilders from the Dutch in exchange for a separate peace. This demand and other conditions posed by the French stiffened Dutch resistance. Negotiations gave the Republic time to finish the inundations along the Dutch Water Line, started on 22 June 1672. Luxembourg laid siege to Groningen but failed to take it. An attempt was made to invade the Republic by sea; this was thwarted by Admiral Michiel de Ruyter in four strategic victories against the combined Anglo-French fleet . The first of these naval victories was the Battle of Solebay.\\n\\nAnswer this question based on the article: How many more men did Turrene first set off in May with then he had when he took over Nijmegen?","target":"46000","rationale":"The goal of this problem is to calculate how many more men did Turrene first set off in May with then he had when he took over Nijmegen. Before that, we have to check the size of his army by taking a look on both passages. In the passage 1 which describes about Louis's arrival at Vis√© and Turenne's 50,000 men setting out for war, it is mentioned that \\"Turenne's 50,000 men\\". In the passage 2 which discusses about Turenne taking Nijmegen , it is said that \\"Nijmegen , with 4,000 infantry and 400 cavalry,\\". Therefore we could conclude as follows: (STEP1) 50000 - 4000 = 46000; (STEP2) 46000 - 400 = 4"},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{4, 5, 7, 8, 9, 12, 15, 16, 20}', Set2: '{1, 5, 8, 11, 14, 19}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"13","rationale":"The union of Set1 and Set2 is [4, 5, 7, 8, 9, 12, 15, 16 ,20 ,1 ,11 ,14 19]. The number of elements in the union is 13."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i and A, where i is an integer and A is a list. You need to output the first i elements of A, starting with the 1st element in A. i will always have a value less than the length of A\\n\\n1, ['t', 'N', 'u', 'x', 'Y']","target":"t","rationale":"Given the list ['t', 'N', 'u', 'x', 'Y'], we need to find the first element:\\\\n1. The 1st element is t.\\\\n2. If i is 2, then the next element would be N, and so on.\\\\n\\\\nThe final output would be ['t']."},{"source":"Read the following article and select the best answer.\\nArticle: We can see ads  everywhere. Here are four ads. Please read them carefully.\\n(1)WANTED\\nAre you hard-working? Do you like to meet people? If your answer is \\"Yes\\", then we have\\na job for you as a waiter. Call AL Hotel at 8556779!\\n(2)SUMMER JOB\\nDo you like to talk with people? Do you like to write stories? If you want to\\nwork for our magazine as a _ , please call Karen at 85558366.\\n(3)HELP WANTED\\nDo you like babies? Can you look after one baby for two days? If you are sure to take good\\ncare of it, call us at 8766588. $80 or more.\\nToday! Hurry!\\n(4)CLEANER WANTED\\nCan you make a large house clean and tidy? If you hope to get the job paid at $ 20 once,\\ncall us this evening 18:00~20:00. Tel: 8633800\\nQuestion: If you would like to work as a waiter at a hotel, you can call at\\n- 85558366\\n- 8556779\\n- 8766588\\n- 8633800","target":"8556779","rationale":"The first ad is looking for a waiter. The second ad is looking for someone to work as a reporter, which doesn't pertain the question so can be ignored. \\nThe third and fourth ads are both trying to find people who would take care of babies or clean houses respectively; these don't relate either. \\nThus, out of all the listed phone numbers only 8556779 should yield any result related to restaurant jobs in general and waiters specifically (since it's part of an actual posting)."},{"source":"Arroyo was the favorite of investors because of her experience as a trained economist and government manager.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nArroyo has experience as an economist and as a government manager.\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"yes","rationale":"Arroyo's experience as an economist and a government manager is why she was the favorite of investors. So, \\"does this next sentence follow\\" in that yes it follows given Arroyos prior experiences."},{"source":"What is the title of this article:\\n\\nNick Fradiani won the season, defeating Clark Beckham. By winning, Fradiani became the first winner from the Northeast region. Fradiani released \\"Beautiful Life\\" as his coronation single while Beckham released \\"Champion\\". Jax, the third place finalist, also released a single called \\"Forcefield\\".\\n\\nTitle:","target":"American Idol","rationale":"The context of the article is about American Idol, a popular singing competition in America.\\nTherefore, the answer to this question should be: \\"American Idol\\"."},{"source":"Sentence: To dry herbs\\n\\nChoice 1: Using a pastry brush brush any residual dirt from your fresh herbs. Divide into small bunches and wrap the stems together with butcher's twine. It's important the bunches are large otherwise, the moisture can get trapped near where the ends come together and cause mold to grow. Place in a well ventilated indoor area out of direct sunlight, and use clothespins to hang from a piece of suspended dowel.\\n\\nChoice 2: Using a pastry brush brush any residual dirt from your fresh herbs. Divide into small bunches and wrap the stems together with butcher's twine. It's important the bunches are small otherwise, the moisture can get trapped near where the ends come together and cause mold to grow. Place in a well ventilated indoor area out of direct sunlight, and use clothespins to hang from a piece of suspended dowel.\\n\\nWhat is the index of the correct choice for ending for the sentence?\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"2","rationale":"The context of the sentence is that a person is trying to dry out fresh herbs. However, in choice 1, it says to divide into small bunches and wrap stems together with butcher's twine but then say it‚Äôs important the bunches are large otherwise moisture can get trapped near where ends come together and cause mold to grow. This statement contradicts itself because earlier on we stated that the bunch should be wrapped tightly so they do not have any open spaces which would allow water or moisture from collecting at one point causing mold growth. The correct answer would be option 2 as this answers correctly describes what happens when you tie up your herbs too loosely leaving space for excess liquid build-up between herb bundles - thus leading to mold formation/growth."},{"source":"In this task, a passage will be given and the goal is to identify an event from the passage. An event is defined as a single word representing something that happened, is happening, or may happen. An event can be factual or hypothetical, positive or negative, certain or uncertain. While most events are based on verbs, an event can also be based on a noun (ex. storm, snow, rainfall) or a copula verb (is, was, been, etc.). The event must not be a pronoun or an adjective. For noun events with multiple words, use the last word in the phrase as event.\\n\\nPassage: Most areas of the United States shift Sunday to daylight savings time, with clocks moving one hour ahead. The change was to take place in the eastern zone at 2:00 a.m. (0700 GMT).","target":"shift","rationale":"The event is \\"shift\\", which means to move from one place or position to another. The passage explains how areas of the United States shift their clocks forward by one hour."},{"source":"Choose from the possible answers, would the following sentence, by the strictest standards, be considered correct by a linguist?\\n\\nFruit hit the roof against the ground.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"unacceptable","rationale":"In the given sentence, \\"against\\" should be replaced with \\"on.\\" A linguist would rate this as unacceptable because there is no object in the preposition phrase."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, a sentence,  and a character. The sentence describes an action or job of the given character. Also, the context provides more information about the sentence or the character. Your task is to return one of the emotions which are expressed by the Character in the given sentence. For that you can use the Context; however, Context is not provided in all the inputs. Also, in some inputs, there can be zero emotion; for that return 'None'.\\n\\nContext: Kate's mom bought a new house. The house was older. It wasn't in good shape. It needed a lot of work. \\n Sentence: But she was excited about doing the repairs herself. \\n Character: Kate's mom","target":"thrilled","rationale":"Kate's mom is excited to repair the new house, which implies that she is thrilled with her new home."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\ncook : stove. mop : ?","target":"mop","rationale":"A stove is a tool used to cook, and a mop is a similar tool used to mop."},{"source":"The task is to generate text based off of an event. For the given event, there will be a person who does the action in the event (usually PersonX). Your task is to write that persons intent behind doing the event, i.e. why did the person do that action.\\n\\nPersonX moves ___ along","target":"to be productive","rationale":"The event is \\"PersonX moves ___ along\\". In this case, the person that does this action is PersonX. The intent behind doing an action is the reason why someone did that action. For example, if PersonX moved a toy car along a table, they might have done so to be productive and get somewhere faster."},{"source":"FINAL EXAM\\n\\nQuestion 1. The Things My Father Never Taught Me is a 2012 short comedy film that featurd Burleigh Smith along side which Australian actress best known on \\"McLeod's Daughters\\"?","target":"Bridie Carter","rationale":"The Things My Father Never Taught Me is a 2012 short comedy film that features Burleigh Smith, who plays the title character \\"Rob.\\" The film also stars Bridie Carter as his wife. \\nBridie Carter was born on December 18th, 1970, in Melbourne and grew up there before moving to Sydney at age 16 for her studies at National Institute of Dramatic Art (NIDA). She is best known for playing Tess Silverman McLeod on the television show McLeod's Daughters from 2001-2009."},{"source":"Given a sentence, fill out the missing word with a 'no' or a number (between zero and ten). You should write the numbers with english alphabet, like: four instead of 4.\\n\\nAntidepressants take from ____ to six weeks to have a strongly beneficial effect.","target":"four","rationale":"We know from the beginning of the sentence that antidepressants take time to have a strong effect. The end of the sentence states that it takes six weeks, so it must take at least as long as four weeks."},{"source":"Classify the relation of question with context to one of these categories: 1) award received, 2) based on, collection, 3) conflict, 4) constellation, 5) convicted of, 6) date of death, 7) director, 8) drafted by, 9) educated at, 10) medical condition, 11) military branch, 12) narrative location, 13) occupation, 14) original network, 15) parent company, 16) point in time, 17) production company, 18) residence, 19) series, 20) service entry, 21) sex or gender, 22) spouse, 23) standards body question.\\n\\nContext : The future Mirtha Legrand was born on 23 February 1927 in Villa Ca√±√°s, a town in the province of Santa Fe located some 200 kilometres (120 mi) from Rosario. \\nQuestion : What is Mirtha Legrand's spouse's name?","target":"spouse","rationale":"The question is asking for information about Mirtha Legrand's spouse, so the correct answer is 'spouse'."},{"source":"But she was too late.\\n\\nDoes it follow that \\"but she got there too early.\\"?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The first sentence states that \\"She\\" is too late, which means she missed an opportunity or event. The second statement suggests that the reason for her missing this opportunity was because she arrived early rather than being tardy. This directly contradicts the information given in the original premise and so it cannot be said to follow from it. So, the answer can only be a definite no"},{"source":"Short general knowledge question: which party was lincoln?","target":"Whig Party","rationale":"Abraham Lincoln(1809-1865), the 16th President of the United States, was a member of Whig Party."},{"source":"What is the answer for the question: What is the name of the person who claims he was always a closet heterosexual? from the following article ?\\n\\nBowie declared himself gay in an interview with Michael Watts for a 1972 issue of Melody Maker, coinciding with his campaign for stardom as Ziggy Stardust. According to Buckley, \\"If Ziggy confused both his creator and his audience, a big part of that confusion centred on the topic of sexuality.\\" In a September 1976 interview with Playboy, Bowie said, \\"It's true‚ÄîI am a bisexual. But I can't deny that I've used that fact very well. I suppose it's the best thing that ever happened to me.\\" His first wife, Angie, supports his claim of bisexuality and alleges that Bowie had a relationship with Mick Jagger.In a 1983 interview with Rolling Stone, Bowie said his public declaration of bisexuality was \\"the biggest mistake I ever made\\" and \\"I was always a closet heterosexual.\\" On other occasions, he said his interest in homosexual and bisexual culture had been more a product of the times and the situation in which he found himself than of his own feelings.Blender asked Bowie in 2002 whether he still believed his public declaration was his biggest mistake. After a long pause, he said, \\"I don't think it was a mistake in Europe, but it was a lot tougher in America. I had no problem with people knowing I was bisexual. But I had no inclination to hold any banners nor be a representative of any group of people.\\" Bowie said he wanted to be a songwriter and performer rather than a headline for his bisexuality, and in \\"puritanical\\" America, \\"I think it stood in the way of so much I wanted to do.\\"Buckley wrote that Bowie \\"mined sexual intrigue for its ability to shock\\", and was probably \\"never gay, nor even consistently actively bisexual\\", instead experimenting \\"out of a sense of curiosity and a genuine allegiance with the 'transgressional'.\\" Biographer Christopher Sandford said, according to Mary Finnigan‚Äîwith whom Bowie had an affair in 1969‚Äîthe singer and his first wife Angie \\"created their bisexual fantasy\\". Sandford wrote that Bowie \\"made a positive fetish of repeating the quip that he and his wife had met while 'fucking the...","target":"Bowie","rationale":"The article is about David Bowie, who declared himself gay in an interview. He was referring to his time as Ziggy Stardust when he said that \\"If Ziggy confused both his creator and his audience, a big part of that confusion centred on the topic of sexuality.\\"\\nHis first wife Angie supports this claim but later in 1983, In an interview with Rolling Stone magazine Bowie says: ‚ÄúI think it‚Äôs the biggest mistake I ever made\\". So according to him one thing is true and other not at different times."},{"source":"What is the solution to this math problem?\\nSolve 2 - 22 = -10*w for w.","target":"2","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable w on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 22 - 2 = 10*w\\n[STEP 2] 20 = 10*w\\n[STEP3] w = 20/10  or   w = 2"},{"source":"Locusts historically always affect crops\\n\\nPick the right answer from the list:\\n- in the sky\\n- disadvantageously\\n- near water\\n- positively","target":"disadvantageously","rationale":"Locusts are insects which infest crops and other plants in large numbers, causing destruction. This is disadvantageous to farmers who rely on the land for their livelihood. Therefore, locusts affect crops disadvantageously."},{"source":"Given the fact that:\\n\\nWe can say that resistance and current in an electric circuit areinversely proportional, because as the one increases, the other decreases, and vice versa.\\n\\nAnswer the question:\\n\\n\\nAs the telephone line fell down and the line's resistance went up, the current was greater or smaller?","target":"smaller","rationale":"We can say that resistance and current in an electric circuit areinversely proportional, because as the one increases, the other decreases, and vice versa.\\nSo when the telephone line fell down and its resistance went up , then current becomes smaller"},{"source":"Question: How big is Saint Helena tropical Island?\\n\\nIs \\"It is part of the British Overseas Territory of Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha.\\" the correct answer?\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The correct answer is \\"It covers an area of 122 km2, with a coastline of about 80 kilometres.\\". The statement in the question is not relevant to the question and it does not provide any information that would help us determine how big Saint Helena tropical Island is."},{"source":"Read the following paragraph and extract the answer for the question: What is the last name of the person who helped develop suprematism with his mentor?\\n\\nLazar Markovich Lissitzky (Russian: –õ–∞ÃÅ–∑–∞—Ä—å –ú–∞ÃÅ—Ä–∫–æ–≤–∏—á –õ–∏—Å–∏ÃÅ—Ü–∫–∏–π, listen ; November 23 [O.S. November 11] 1890 ‚Äì December 30, 1941), known as El Lissitzky (Russian: –≠–ª—å –õ–∏—Å–∏ÃÅ—Ü–∫–∏–π, Yiddish: ◊¢◊ú ◊ú◊ô◊°◊ô◊¶◊ß◊ô‚Äé), was a Russian artist, designer, photographer, typographer, polemicist and architect. He was an important figure of the Russian avant-garde, helping develop suprematism with his mentor, Kazimir Malevich, and designing numerous exhibition displays and propaganda works for the Soviet Union. His work greatly influenced the Bauhaus and constructivist movements, and he experimented with production techniques and stylistic devices that would go on to dominate 20th-century graphic design.Lissitzky's entire career was laced with the belief that the artist could be an agent for change, later summarized with his edict, \\"das zielbewu√üte Schaffen\\" (goal-oriented creation). Lissitzky, of Lithuanian Jewish –ærigin, began his career illustrating Yiddish children's books in an effort to promote Jewish culture in Russia. When only 15 he started teaching, a duty he would maintain for most of his life. Over the years, he taught in a variety of positions, schools, and artistic media, spreading and exchanging ideas. He took this ethic with him when he worked with Malevich in heading the suprematist art group UNOVIS, when he developed a variant suprematist series of his own, Proun, and further still in 1921, when he took up a job as the Russian cultural ambassador to Weimar Germany, working with and influencing important figures of the Bauhaus and De Stijl movements during his stay. In his remaining years he brought significant innovation and change to typography, exhibition design, photomontage, and book design, producing critically respected works and winning international acclaim for his exhibition design. This continued until his deathbed, where in 1941 he produced one of his last works ‚Äì a Soviet propaganda poster rallying the people to construct more tanks for the fight against Nazi Germany. In 2014, the heirs of the artist, in...","target":"Lissitzky","rationale":"The paragraph contains the answer to the question: What is the last name of the person who helped develop suprematism with his mentor?\\nLissitzky, whose full name was Lazar Markovich Lissitzky. This makes it clear that he worked closely with Kazimir Malevich in developing suprematism as an art form and style. His surname was Lissitzky (which means \\"the little fox\\" or \\"the cunning\\"). Hence this is a correct choice for your answers!"},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The Indian Ocean is the third largest of the world's oceanic divisions, covering (approximately 20% of the water on the Earth's surface). It is bounded by Asia on the north, on the west by Africa, on the east by Australia, and on the south by the Southern Ocean or, depending on definition, by Antarctica. It is named after the country of India. The Indian Ocean is known as \\"Ratnkara\\", \\"\\"the mine of gems\\"\\" in ancient Sanskrit literature, and as \\"Hind Mahsgar\\", \\"\\"the great Indian sea\\"\\", in Hindi.\\n\\n- Swaziland, officially the Kingdom of Swaziland (or ; Swazi: \\"Umbuso weSwatini\\"; sometimes called kaNgwane or Eswatini), is a sovereign state in Southern Africa. It is neighboured by Mozambique to its northeast and by South Africa to its north, west and south. The country and its people take their names from Mswati II, the 19th-century king under whose rule Swazi territory was expanded and unified.\\n\\n- The Superstars International Series was a production-based touring car racing championship held between 2004 and 2013. It was managed by the \\"Superstars World of Racing SpA\\", SWR, a company of FG GROUP with headquarters in Rome and sanctioned by the Automobile Club d'Italia (ACI) and the Commissione Sportiva Automobilistica Italiana (CSAI). FG GROUP, led by Maurizio Flammini, is famous for having promoted the FIM World Superbike Championship from its beginnings in 1988 until its sale to Infront Sports & Media in 2007.\\n\\n- The Bantu languages, technically the Narrow Bantu languages (as opposed to \\"Wide Bantu\\", a loosely defined categorization which includes other Bantoid languages), constitute a traditional branch of the NigerCongo languages. There are about 250 Bantu languages by the criterion of mutual intelligibility, though the distinction between language and dialect is often unclear, and \\"Ethnologue\\" counts 535 languages. Bantu languages are spoken largely east and south of present-day Cameroon, that is, in the regions commonly known as Central Africa, Southeast Africa, and Southern Africa. Parts of the Bantu area include languages from other language families (see map).\\n\\n- Kyalami Racing Circuit (from \\"Khaya lami\\", \\"My home\\" in Zulu) is a motor racing circuit located in Midrand, Gauteng province, South Africa. The circuit has been used for Grand Prix and Formula One races and has hosted the South African Grand Prix many times. Among the Formula One races held at the track the 1977 South African Grand Prix stands out, as it is principally remembered for the fatal accident that claimed the lives of race marshal Frederick Jansen van Vuuren and driver Tom Pryce. In recent years, the area surrounding the circuit has developed into a residential and commercial suburb of Johannesburg. More recently, Kyalami has played host to five rounds of the Superbike World Championship from 1998 to 2002 and later in 2009 and 2010, the season finale of the Superstars Series in 2009 and 2010, and the South African round of the 200809 A1 Grand Prix season.\\n\\n- Southern Africa is the southernmost region of the African continent, variably defined by geography or geopolitics, and including several countries.\\nThe term \\"southern Africa\\" or \\"Southern Africa\\", generally includes Angola, Botswana, Lesotho, Malawi, Mozambique, Namibia, South Africa, Swaziland, Zambia, and Zimbabwe. From a political perspective the region is said to be unipolar with South Africa as a first regional power.\\n\\n- Africa is the world's second-largest and second-most-populous continent. At about 30.3 million km¬≤ (11.7 million square¬†miles) including adjacent islands, it covers 6% of Earth's total surface area and 20.4 % of its total land area. With 1.1 billion people as of 2013, it accounts for about 15% of the world's human population. The continent is surrounded by the Mediterranean Sea to the north, both the Suez Canal and the Red Sea along the Sinai Peninsula to the northeast, the Indian Ocean to the southeast, and the Atlantic Ocean to the west. The continent includes Madagascar and various archipelagos. It contains 54 fully recognized sovereign states (countries), nine territories and two \\"de facto\\" independent states with limited or no recognition.\\n\\n- The Old World consists of Africa, Europe, and Asia, regarded collectively as the part of the world known to Europeans before contact with the Americas. It is used in the context of, and contrast with, the New World (Americas).\\n\\n- Namibia, officially the Republic of Namibia (German: ), is a country in southern Africa whose western border is the Atlantic Ocean. It shares land borders with Zambia and Angola to the north, Botswana to the east and South Africa to the south and east. Although it does not border Zimbabwe, a part of less than 200 metres of the Zambezi River (essentially a small bulge in Botswana to achieve a Botswana/Zambia micro-border) separates the two countries. Namibia gained independence from South Africa on 21 March 1990, following the Namibian War of Independence. Its capital and largest city is Windhoek, and it is a member state of the United Nations (UN), the Southern African Development Community (SADC), the African Union (AU), and the Commonwealth of Nations.\\n\\n- South Africa, officially the Republic of South Africa (RSA), is the southernmost country in Africa. It is bounded on the south by of coastline of Southern Africa stretching along the South Atlantic and Indian Oceans, on the north by the neighbouring countries of Namibia, Botswana and Zimbabwe, and on the east and northeast by Mozambique and Swaziland, and surrounding the kingdom of Lesotho. South Africa is the 25th-largest country in the world by land area, and with close to 56 million people, is the world's 24th-most populous nation. It is the southernmost country on the mainland of the Old World or the Eastern Hemisphere. It is the only country that borders both the Atlantic Ocean and the Indian Ocean. About 80 percent of South Africans are of Sub-Saharan African ancestry, divided among a variety of ethnic groups speaking different Bantu languages, nine of which have official status. The remaining population consists of Africa's largest communities of European (white), Asian (Indian), and multiracial (coloured) ancestry.\\n\\n- The 1977 South African Grand Prix was a Formula One motor race held at Kyalami on 5 March 1977. The race is principally remembered for the accident that resulted in the deaths of race marshal Frederick Jansen van Vuuren and driver Tom Pryce. It was also the last race for Carlos Pace, who was killed in an aircraft accident less than two weeks later.\\n\\n- Zimbabwe, officially the Republic of Zimbabwe, is a landlocked country located in southern Africa, between the Zambezi and Limpopo Rivers. It is bordered by South Africa to the south, Botswana to the west and southwest, Zambia to the northwest, and Mozambique to the east and northeast. Although it does not border Namibia, less than 200 metres of the Zambezi River separates it from that country. The capital and largest city is Harare. A country of roughly 13 million people, Zimbabwe has 16 official languages, with English, Shona, and Ndebele the most commonly used.\\n\\n- Johannesburg (also known as Jozi, Joburg and eGoli) is the largest city in South Africa and is one of the 50 largest urban areas in the world. It is the provincial capital of Gauteng, which is the wealthiest province in South Africa. While Johannesburg is not one of South Africa's three capital cities, it is the seat of the Constitutional Court. The city is located in the mineral-rich Witwatersrand range of hills and is the centre of large-scale gold and diamond trade.\\n\\n- The Witwatersrand aka The Reef, is a 56-kilometre-long north-facing scarp in the Gauteng Province of South Africa. It consists of a hard, erosion-resistant quartzite sedimentary rock, over which several north-flowing rivers form waterfalls, which account for the name Witwatersrand, meaning the ridge of white waters in Afrikaans. This eastwest-running scarp can be traced with only one short gap from Bedfordview (about 10¬†km west of O.R. Tambo International Airport) in the east, through Johannesburg and Roodepoort, to Krugersdorp in the west (see the diagram bottom-left below).\\n\\n- Botswana , officially the Republic of Botswana, is a landlocked country located in Southern Africa. The citizens refer to themselves as \\"Batswana\\" (singular: \\"Motswana\\"). Formerly the British protectorate of Bechuanaland, Botswana adopted its new name after becoming independent within the Commonwealth on 30 September 1966. Since then, it has maintained a strong tradition of stable representative democracy, with a consistent record of uninterrupted democratic elections.\\n\\n- The South African Grand Prix was first run as a Grand Prix motor racing handicap race in 1934 at the Prince George Circuit at East London, Eastern Cape Province. It drew top drivers from Europe including Bernd Rosemeyer, Richard \\"Dick\\" Seaman, Richard Shuttleworth and the 1939 winner Luigi Villoresi.\\n\\n- Thomas Maldwyn Pryce (11 June 1949¬† 5 March 1977) was a British racing driver from Wales, famous for winning the Brands Hatch Race of Champions, a non-championship Formula One race, in 1975 and for the circumstances surrounding his death. Pryce is the only Welsh driver to have won a Formula One race and is also the only Welshman to lead a Formula One World Championship Grand Prix: two laps of the 1975 British Grand Prix.\\n\\n- Midrand is an area in central Gauteng Province, South Africa. It is situated between Centurion and Kyalami, and is part of the City of Johannesburg Metropolitan Municipality.\\n\\n- The Eastern Hemisphere is a geographical term for the half of the earth that is east of the prime meridian (which crosses Greenwich, England) and west of the antimeridian. It is also used to refer to Europe, Asia, Africa, and Australia, in contrast with the Western Hemisphere, which includes North and South America. This hemisphere may also be called the \\"Oriental Hemisphere\\". In addition, it may be used in a cultural or geopolitical sense as a synonym for the \\"Old World\\".\\n\\n- Neotel ( Pty ) Ltd. , previously SNO Telecommunications , is the second national operator ( SNO ) for fixed line telecommunication services in South Africa . It was unveiled on 31 August 2006 in Kyalami in northern Johannesburg . Neotel is South Africa 's first direct telecommunications competitor to the current telecommunications parastatal , Telkom . The new company announced its business services on 15 November 2007 and its consumer services in May 2008 . Its business services include local and international leased line services , as well as a suite of voice , data ( VPN ) , and Internet offerings delivered over its converged , next - generation network . International Transit services for wholesale customers have been available since September 2006 . They plan to use wireless broadband technologies , amongst others , which not only allows data transfers but also voice in the form of VOIP . The arrival of a competitor is said to bring competitive pricing in terms of high speed internet ( avg. 250 kbit / s to 750 kbit / s CDMA2000 ) , broadband through WiMax , and later high speed broadband ( xDSL and Fiber ) . For many years South Africa had only one telecommunications service , Telkom , which is partly government owned and partly private owned , but now for the first time people will have a choice of telecommunication services .\\n\\n- Gauteng, which means \\"place of gold\\", is one of the nine provinces of South Africa. It was formed from part of the old Transvaal Province after South Africa's first all-race elections on 27 April 1994. It was initially named PretoriaWitwatersrandVereeniging (PWV) and was renamed \\"Gauteng\\" in December 1994.\\n\\n- Sub-Saharan Africa is, geographically, the area of the continent of Africa that lies south of the Sahara desert. According to the UN, it consists of all African countries that are fully or partially located south of the Sahara. It contrasts with North Africa, whose territories are part of the League of Arab states within the Arab world. Somalia, Djibouti, Comoros and Mauritania are geographically in Sub-Saharan Africa, but are likewise Arab states and part of the Arab world.\\n\\n- Mozambique (or ), officially the Republic of Mozambique (or \\"\\") is a country in Southeast Africa bordered by the Indian Ocean to the east, Tanzania to the north, Malawi and Zambia to the northwest, Zimbabwe to the west, and Swaziland and South Africa to the southwest. It is separated from Madagascar by the Mozambique Channel to the east. The capital and largest city is Maputo (known as \\"Louren√ßo Marques\\" before independence).\\n\\n- Lesotho, officially the Kingdom of Lesotho, is an enclaved, landlocked country in southern Africa completely surrounded by South Africa. It is just over in size and has a population slightly over two million. Its capital and largest city is Maseru. \\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the information above, choose from the list below the object entity that exhibits the relation 'headquarters location' with the subject 'neotel'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- africa\\n - angola\\n - asia\\n - au\\n - australia\\n - bedfordview\\n - botswana\\n - cameroon\\n - central\\n - england\\n - europe\\n - frederick\\n - greenwich\\n - hard\\n - johannesburg\\n - london\\n - maseru\\n - mauritania\\n - meridian\\n - midrand\\n - pretoria\\n - rome\\n - somalia\\n - south africa\\n - van\\n - wales\\n - zambia\\n - zimbabwe","target":"midrand","rationale":"The object entity that exhibits the relation 'headquarters location' with the subject 'neotel', given the information above, is midrand."},{"source":"Question: The living do many things that the dead do not, but one is most important.  What do the living do that the dead do not?\\n\\nChoices: \\n- talk\\n- sometimes bad\\n- pollution\\n- happiness\\n- have experiences\\n\\nThe rationale to choose \\"have experiences\\" as the answer is that:","target":"sometimes bad is not a thing that / verb","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"sometimes bad is not a thing that / verb\\"."},{"source":"What is the full name of the person who was pursued by their husband and his assistatn?\\n\\nAnswer the above question based on the context below:\\n\\nOn a flight to New York for an annual police convention, Chan encounters his old Scotland Yard friend, Hugh Drake. Drake is now a member of military intelligence trying to track down what he believes is a sabotage ring led by a Paul Narvo. A bomber and its pilots crashed the day before. Chan offers his assistance.\\nChan is welcomed at the airport by New York Police Inspector Vance and, to Chan's surprise, his number two son Jimmy Chan.\\nChan goes to see Drake the next day at the apartment of George Kirby, where a dinner party is in progress. He finds his friend dead of poison gas in Drake's library, where he had gone to do some work. Drake's briefcase, containing all the information he had gathered about the sabotage ring, is missing. The window is latched, so Chan concludes one of the guests is responsible. Chan discovers that Drake asked that his Oxford classmate Herbert Fenton, actress June Preston and Ralph Percy, chief designer at the Metropolitan Aircraft Corporation, be invited to the party. Kirby himself is the company president. The lost bomber crashed at the company's plant. Also present is stockbroker Keith Jeffery. A servant reports chemist David Elliot insisted on seeing Drake, so he showed him in.\\nChan learns that Preston also spoke with Drake that night, on behalf of a friend, Patricia Shaw. Shaw, it turns out, married Narvo in India. When she found out Narvo was involved in sabotage, she fled, only to be pursued by her husband and his assistant, Ramullah.\\nRamullah is eventually tracked down, with Shaw's help, and taken into custody. (During a police lineup of Indians, Shorty McCoy, aka \\"The Canarsie Kid\\", [Shemp Howard] is revealed to be a faker, not a fakir.) Before Ramullah can be questioned, however, he is shot and killed. Shaw narrowly avoids the same fate.","target":"Patricia Shaw","rationale":"The context is about a woman who married someone in India and then fled because she found out her husband was involved in sabotage. The person pursuing the wife was eventually captured, but before he could be questioned, he was killed. \\nGiven this information it is clear that Patricia Shaw is the name of the full person as she had to flee from his pursuers after finding out they were engaged in sabotage."},{"source":"Answer the question below:\\n\\n\\nSandra had to pee, and when she did, she noticed her urine was dark, because she had consumed water in greater amounts or lesser amounts? \\n\\n\\nAssuming that:\\n\\nThe darker the urine, the less water it contains.","target":"lesser amounts","rationale":"Assuming that the darker the urine, the less water it contains. Since Sandra's light degree of dehydration has resulted in a dark coloration to her urine, we can assume she consumed lesser amounts of water than usual and therefore \\"lesser amounts\\" is what you would expect from this situation."},{"source":"Formulate an answer to this elaborate question: Phoenix Command is a role-playing game system, published by Leading edge games that includes which game?","target":"Aliens Adventure Game","rationale":"The Aliens Adventure Game is a role-playing game published by Leading Edge Games in 1989. It was based on the 1986 film Aliens and uses an updated version of the Phoenix Command rules system that was originally used to produce games like Trigun: The Planet Gunsmoke RPG, also produced by Leading Edge Games."},{"source":"Write a multi-choice question for the following article, with the given choices and answer:\\nArticle: It is reported that in the near future robots and humans will probably work together to create jazz. A singing robot is being taught to create jazz with human being in a project.\\nAntonio Chella from Italy is working with a Telenoid robot. To start with, the Telenoid will be trained to _ the movements and simple sounds made by a human singer, and then connect music with different human emotions.\\nPrevious  robots had the ability to find common connections between things. But Chella suggests that a conscious  robot should be able to go a step further and find new connections. The Telenoid is of this kind.\\n\\"This work raises interesting questions about the connection between consciousness and music creating.\\" says Philippe Pasquier, a musician needs a physical body.\\nPasquer argues that the robot musician is faced with a big challenge. \\"Its software has already been developed and it can imitate The Beatles, a famous band. However, what made The Beatles famous were not only their songs but their wonderful performance of the songs,\\" he says.\\nIt is not clear how a robot would perform music a new way. But by imitating humans, the Telenoid robot could provide some useful information. What is important is that human musicians often listen to and compare music made by others for a long time before creating music of their own. So the Telenoid robot had better listen to more jazz music first.\\nOptions:\\nA Arts\\nB Entertainment\\nC Medicine\\nD Science\\nAnswer:\\nD Science\\nQuestion:","target":"In which part of a newspaper do we most probably read this passage?","rationale":"In which part of a newspaper do we most probably read this passage?"},{"source":"Given a goal and 2 solutions, choose the most appropriate solution.\\nGoal: how to get rid of acne\\n- Solution 1: put garlic powder on a pimple\\n- Solution 2: put listerine on a pimple\\n\\nAnswer by returning either Solution 1 or Solution 2","target":"Solution 2","rationale":"Garlic contains allicin and ajoene, which have antibacterial properties that may help treat acne. However, garlic has the potential to cause skin irritation in some people.\\nListerine is an antiseptic mouthwash containing ingredients such as menthol and alcohol that can kill bacteria on the surface of pimples while drying them out at the same time. This makes listerine more likely to successfully cure acne than garlic powder, making it a better solution for getting rid of acne (Solution 2)."},{"source":"Answer based on context:\\n\\nStarting lineups: HOUSTON - DEFENSE: DE Antonio Smith, DT Shaun Cody, DT Amobi Okoye, DE Mario Williams, LB Brian Cushing, LB Kevin Bentley, LB Darryl Sharpton, CB Glover Quinn, CB Kareem Jackson, SS Bernard Pollard, FS Eugene Wilson. Coming off their bye week the Texans played at Lucas Oil Stadium for an AFC South division rivalry match against the Indianapolis Colts. In the first quarter the Texans trailed early as QB Peyton Manning completed a 2-yard TD pass to TE Jacob Tamme. The Texans struggled further in the 2nd quarter when Matt Schaub's pass was intercepted by CB Kelvin Hayden and returned 25 yards for a touchdown. They soon responded with kicker Neil Rackers nailing a 53-yard field goal. The Texans fell further behind with kicker Adam Vinatieri getting a 48-yard field goal. This was followed in the third quarter by Manning throwing a 15-yard TD pass to WR Reggie Wayne. The Texans' offense broke through with Schaub connecting to WR Andre Johnson on a 28-yard TD pass. The Colts replied with Vinatieri hitting a 23-yard field goal. The Texans tried to fight back but only came away with a touchdown after RB Arian Foster got a 6-yard TD run. The Colts closed the game with Vinatieri making a 36-yard field goal.\\n\\nWho threw the first touchdown pass of the game?","target":"Peyton Manning","rationale":"The question, \\"Who threw the first touchdown pass of the game?\\" can be answered by checking who scored in which quarter. In this case, it is mentioned that Peyton Manning completed a 2-yard TD pass to TE Jacob Tamme (touchdown) in the 1st quarter. If we assume that scoring started with this action, then he would have thrown the first touchdown pass of the game.\\""},{"source":"What was the response? Hello, what are the reviews like for the movie Glass?\\nThe rotten tomatoes score is 37% for the critics, but audiences are at 79%\\nThat sounds decent enough, I want to see it with my friend Adam. Is the movie showing in Miami right now?\\nYes, what area of Miami are you looking to see it?\\nAny movie theater near the Doral area?\\nYes, CineBistro is located near the Doral area.\\nIs Glass being shown there?\\nYes, there's a showtime at 8.30pm and 9.15pm\\nWhat's the price for the 8.30pm?\\nIt's $19.26 plus tax\\nIs there a student discount or any other discount?\\nNo, this theater doesn't offer discounts.\\nIs the movie available in IMAX or 3D?\\nNo, neither of those formats is available.\\nOkay, book two tickets for January 23 at 8.30pm\\nOkay, hold on while I process your tickets\\nThank you","target":"Your tickets are confirmed for January 23 at 8.30pm","rationale":"The given dialogue is a conversation between a user and the Cinemabistro bot. The user asks about the showtime for Glass, and the price for tickets. After confirming all details, the bot confirms that it will book two tickets for January 23 at 8.30pm. The next statement from the bot should be to confirm that it has made reservations for those tickets, therefore \\"Your tickets are confirmed for January 23 at 8.30pm\\" is the most reasonable answer among all choices.\\""},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an answer to a question about when an event happened. Your answer should be a wrong answer. That is, if you are asked about when an event happened, you should answer with a time that the event didn't likely happen. For example, \\"going to school\\" usually happens during the day (not at 2 A.M). Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: Whatever their origins, their culture evolved under the pressure and influence of foreign forces. \\nQuestion: When is this evolution expected?","target":"right now","rationale":"The question is asking when the evolution of their culture happened, but the given sentence does not specify a time period. So we can assume that it happened in the past. Therefore, \\"right now\\" would be an incorrect answer to this question."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. Your task is to classify the conversation either convey 'No emotion' or 'Happiness' by providing '1' and '0', respectively.\\n\\n Person1:      Hey , Wen ! Welcome to D . C . ! Glad you came out to visit ! \\n Person2:  Thanks for inviting me . Actually , I've never been anywhere with so many black people before . It's different . \\n Person1:       Howard is eighty percent black . But there are whites , and even Asians here . Thankfully , it's also coed . \\n Person2:  Great ! Is your , too ? \\n Person1:       Sorry , nope . But the Alpha Phi Alpha's are throwing a party tonight . \\n Person2:  That's a black fraternity , right ? So we should see some dancing !","target":"1","rationale":"The conversation is friendly and has a cheerful tone. The person is glad that the other person came out to visit them. They also talk about having fun at the Alpha Phi Alpha's party, which shows that they are in a good mood. Therefore, their conversation can be classified as happiness and hence the answer is 1."},{"source":"Given an abstract, and a few options, indicate if any of the given options appropriately describe the given abstract. If any of them is a proper keyword, answer 'Yes', otherwise answer 'No'.\\n\\nAbstract: The intraperitoneal fibrin formation and its inhibition by intraperitoneal heparin (5000 U) was investigated in six patients on CAPD. The intraperitoneal heparin concentration decreased linearily from 1.78 U/ml to 1.13 U/ml during a 4-hour dwell time. The antithrombin III-concentration increased to 0.56 +/- 0.1 mg/dl, reaching 1.87% of normal plasma values. The antithrombin III-portion of total protein was 0.62% in plasma and 0.79% in dialysate. The fibrinopeptide A-concentration, a specific product of thrombin action on fibrinogen was 37.1 +/- 11.8 ng/ml in plasma (normal range: less than 2.5 ng/ml) and 153.4 +/- 16.8 ng/ml in dialysate during regular CAPD. After the addition of 5000 U heparin the fibrinopeptide A-concentration in dialysate decreased to 11.6 +/- 2.6 ng/ml during a 4-hour dwell time. In vitro experiments showed no remarkable inhibition of fibrin formation by heparin without antithrombin III in dialysate. We suggest that the fibrinopeptide A is produced intraperitoneally and the antithrombin III-concentration in dialysate is sufficient to inhibit the fibrin formation after acceleration by heparin. \\nQuestion Does the following mesh terms have a suitable mesh term for the abstract? 1)Antithrombin III 2)Blood Proteins 3)Comparative Study 4)Female 5)Fibrin 6)Fibrinogen 7)Fibrinopeptides A 8)Heparin 9)Human 10)Male 11)Peritoneal Cavity 12)Peritoneal Dialysis, Continuous Ambulatory","target":"Yes","rationale":"The question is asking if the abstract describes any of the given topics (i.e., \\"mesh terms\\"). The abstract discusses antithrombin III, fibrinopeptide A, and heparin. Therefore, one of the given options is a suitable mesh term for this abstract (Option 2: Blood Proteins). As a result, the answer should be \\"Yes\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with three passages, 1, 2, and 3. Your job is to determine which passage can be used to answer the question by searching for further information using terms from the passage. Indicate your choice as 1, 2, or 3.\\n\\nQuestion: Is Pravisdomini located in Austria? Passage 1:In 1658 Hungerford was elected Member of Parliament for Chippenham in the Third Protectorate Parliament. He was elected MP for Chippenham in 1660 for the Convention Parliament. He was made a Knight of the Bath at the coronation of King Charles II on 23 April 1661. In 1661 he was elected for Chippenham again in the Cavalier Parliament but the election was declared void. He was then re-elected in the by-election later in 1661 and also in the two elections in 1679. In January 1680 he presented a petition for the summoning of a parliament, and his avowed opposition to the court party of King Charles II led to his removal as Lord Lieutenant of his county in May 1681. He settled in Spring Gardens, Whitehall, in 1681 and was elected MP for Chippenham again in the Oxford Parliament of 1681. He was implicated in the 1683 Rye House Plot and his home at Farleigh Castle was searched for arms. He was elected MP for New Shoreham in 1685, 1688, and 1690, and for Steyning in 1695, 1698, 1700, and 1702.\\n Passage 2:In March in Gatineau, Shapovalov captured his fourth ITF Futures singles title after defeating Gleb Sakharov in straight sets. Two weeks later, he won his first ATP Challenger title with a victory over Ruben Bemelmans at the 75K in Drummondville, and was the youngest Canadian to win a Challenger until F√©lix Auger-Aliassime's victory at the Open Sopra Steria de Lyon later in the year. The next week, he was defeated by Mirza Ba≈°iƒá in the final of the ATP Challenger 50K in Guadalajara, stopping his winning streak at 17 matches. At the French Open in May, his first professional Grand Slam, he was defeated in the first round of qualifying by the first seed Marius Copil in three sets. In June, Shapovalov qualified for the ATP 500 at the Queen's Club Championships, his fourth ATP main draw but his first as a qualifier. In the first round, he defeated his second top 50 player, world No. 47 Kyle Edmund, before losing to world No. 14 Tom√°≈° Berdych. At Wimbledon in July, Shapovalov was awarded a wild card for the main draw. He was defeated by Jerzy Janowicz in the opening round. At the end of the month, he won his second ATP Challenger title, defeating compatriot Peter Polansky in the final of the 75K in Gatineau.\\n Passage 3:This extended training period meant that he had accumulated 138 flying hours in his pilot's logbook before he finally joined No. 66 Squadron RFC in Italy on 10 March 1918. He was assigned to \\"C\\" Flight, flying a Sopwith Camel single seat fighter, and became the preferred wingman of fellow Canadian ace Billy Barker. Birks' first aerial victory came on 18 March, when he destroyed a Rumpler reconnaissance aircraft over Pravisdomini, killing an Austro-Hungarian pilot named Shneeberger. Six days later, he set another reconnaissance aircraft on fire, killing the crew of Poelzi and Suski. His third victory would not come until 2 May, when he wounded Leutnant K. Kosiuski and drove him into a crash landing that destroyed his Albatros D.V. Two days later, Birks shot down and killed ace Oberleutnant Karl Patzelt, as well as F. Frisch. In addition to killing both Austro-Hungarian pilots, he destroyed both their Albatros D.Vs; they were credited as \\"captured\\" because they fell within Italian lines. The new ace shot down another D.V in flames a week later, on 11 May. He destroyed two Berg fighters in five minutes on a morning patrol on 19 May. The following day, he destroyed another. On 24 May, while flying with Barker, Birks was credited with shooting down Hungarian ace J√≥zsef Kiss of Flik 55J; Birks thus became a double ace. On 9 June Birks set another Albatros D.V on fire in mid-air. On the 21st, he capped his list of triumphs by destroying another D.V over Motta. Most unusually for a British pilot, he had no \\"soft\\" victories, such as \\"driven down out of control\\".","target":"3","rationale":"Passage 3 contains the information that Pravisdomini is located in Austria."},{"source":"In this task, you are given two sets, and you need to count the number of elements at the union of two given sets. A Set is shown by two curly braces and comma-separated numbers inside, like {1, 2, 3}. Union of two given sets is the smallest set which contains all the elements of both the sets. To find the union of two given sets, A and B is a set that consists of all the elements of A and all the elements of B such that no element is repeated.\\n\\nSet1: '{2, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 13, 16, 18}', Set2: '{1, 3, 5, 7, 8, 10, 11, 16, 20}'. How many elements are there in the union of Set1 and Set2 ?","target":"13","rationale":"The union of the two given sets is {1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, 13, 16. 18} and the number of elements in this set is 13."},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Is the next sentence syntactically and semantically acceptable?\\n\\nThe crown sparkled with jewels.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"This sentence is acceptable."},{"source":"Concerns about even remote chances of Ebola exposure rippled Friday from a U.S. airline to a cruise ship off Belize, with Frontier contacting hundreds who flew with an infected nurse and Carnival quarantining a health worker only tangentially linked to an Ebola patient's care. The airline's move relates to Amber Vinson, a Dallas nurse who treated an Ebola patient and then was diagnosed with the virus this week after flying round trip between Dallas and Cleveland. A Centers for Disease Control and Prevention official said Thursday she could have had symptoms earlier than believed -- a period possibly covering her two flights on Frontier Airlines.\\n@highlight\\nBelize: Passenger with Ebola link not let in \\"out of preponderance of caution\\"\\n@highlight\\nKerry calls Belize's leader to ask if cruise passenger can disembark, is rebuffed\\n@highlight\\n2 Dallas nurses contracted Ebola while caring for patient Thomas Eric Duncan\\n@highlight\\nSpokesman: Frontier done contacting up to 800 on flights linked to one nurse \\n@placeholder in U.S.: Who has it, who doesn't, who might \\nIn the question above, the \\"@placeholder\\" stands for","target":"Ebola","rationale":"The paragraph is about concerns surrounding Ebola exposure. The airline's move relates to Amber Vinson, a nurse who contracted the virus after treating an infected patient and travelling across two states in the U.S.. Kerry calls Belize's leader to ask if cruise passenger can disembark, but was rebuffed as she may have been exposed to Ebola -- hence not being allowed into Belize out of cautionary measures. The context also mentions that this disease caused 2 nurses in Dallas (U.S.)to contract it while caring for Thomas Eric Duncan, a patient with confirmed cases of Ebola infection.\\nTherefore, from the text above we learn that there are major concerns regarding people contracting or coming into contact with someone carrying the deadly strain of \\"Ebola\\". Hence \\"@placeholder\\" would best be replaced"},{"source":"Here's a question: John traveled deeper and deeper.  As he went, the light faded away until it was pitch black. Where might he be?\\n\\nHere are possible answers to this question:\\n- porch\\n- attic\\n- beach\\n- ocean\\n- universe\\n\\nI believe the correct choice is \\"ocean\\", here's why:","target":"apartment c ocean rentals","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"apartment c ocean rentals\\"."},{"source":"Give me the correct facts to answer this: who played carl fredricksen in up?","target":"Ed Asner","rationale":"Who played Carl Fredricksen in Up?\\nThe answer is Ed Asner."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a statement spoken by a politician in natural language and the subject of the discussion for the given statement. Your task is to determine if the given subject of the discussion is correct for the given statement. The subject can be multiple words. Answer with \\"True\\" if it's the correct subject of discussion or return \\"False\\" if it's incorrect.\\n\\nStatement: If it is enacted, the Senate immigration bill is going to make the Border Patrol bigger than the FBI -- you could put one agent every 250 feet. \\n Subject: candidates-biography","target":"False","rationale":"The statement talks about the impact of the proposed Senate immigration bill on Border Patrol operations, but it makes no mention of politicians and their biographies. Therefore, this subject is incorrect, and the output is \\\\\\"False\\\\\\"."},{"source":"Given a question and its paraphrases, answer the question. The answer should exactly answer all the questions given without any ambiguity. Don't give partial answers.\\n\\nQuestions: ['when did mark zuckerburg invent facebook?', 'what year did mark zuckerberg invent facebook?', 'which date was facebook launched by mark zuckerberg?', 'what year did mark zukenburg start facebook?', 'in what year did mark zuckerberg found facebook?', 'what year did mark zuckerberg create facebook?']","target":"2004","rationale":"Mark Zuckerberg invented facebook in 2004. This is a fact that can be found on the internet and is not an opinion."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Kimberley is a city in southeast British Columbia, Canada along Highway 95A between the Purcell and Rocky Mountains. Kimberley was named in 1896 after the Kimberley mine in South Africa. From 1917 to 2001, it was the home to the world's largest lead-zinc mine, the Sullivan Mine. Now it is mainly a tourist destination and home to the Kimberley Alpine Resort, a ski area and Kimberley's Underground Mining Railway that features a underground mining interpretive centre complete with operational narrow gauge railway equipment. Recreational pursuits include world-class skiing, snowboarding, snowmobiling, fishing, whitewater rafting, kayaking, biking, hiking and golfing on championship golf courses. The city has the largest urban park in Canada. At 1977 acres (800 ha), the Kimberley Nature Park is the largest incorporated park in Canada and the paved, non-motorized Rail-Trail linking the cities of Kimberley and Cranbrook make Kimberley a unique four-season resort. Kimberley is also home to a thriving Arts and Cultural scene.\\n\\n- In ice hockey, the goaltender is the player responsible for preventing the hockey puck from entering their team's net, thus preventing the opposing team from scoring. The goaltender usually plays in or near the area in front of the net called the \\"goal crease\\" (often referred to simply as \\" the crease\\" or \\"the net\\"). Goaltenders tend to stay at or beyond the top of the crease to cut down on the angle of shots. In today's age of goaltending there are two common styles, butterfly and hybrid (hybrid is a mix of the traditional stand-up style and butterfly technique). Because of the power of shots, the goaltender wears special equipment designed to protect the body from direct impact. The goalie is one of the most valuable players on the ice, as their performance can greatly change the outcome or score of the game. One-on-one situations, such as breakaways and shootouts, have the tendency to highlight a goaltender's pure skill, or lack thereof. Only one goaltender is allowed to be on the ice for each team at any given time.\\n\\n- The Colorado Avalanche are a professional ice hockey team based in Denver, Colorado. They are members of the Central Division of the Western Conference of the National Hockey League (NHL). The Avalanche are the only team in their division not based in the Central Time Zone; the team is situated in the Mountain Time Zone. Their home arena is Pepsi Center. Their general manager is Joe Sakic.\\n\\n- The City of New York, often called New York City or simply New York, is the most populous city in the United States. With an estimated 2015 population of 8,550,405 distributed over a land area of just , New York City is also the most densely populated major city in the United States. Located at the southern tip of the state of New York, the city is the center of the New York metropolitan area, one of the most populous urban agglomerations in the world. A global power city, New York City exerts a significant impact upon commerce, finance, media, art, fashion, research, technology, education, and entertainment, its fast pace defining the term \\"New York minute\\". Home to the headquarters of the United Nations, New York is an important center for international diplomacy and has been described as the cultural and financial capital of the world.\\n\\n- Ice hockey is a contact team sport played on ice, usually in a rink, in which two teams of skaters use their sticks to shoot a vulcanized rubber puck into their opponent's net to score points. Ice hockey teams usually consist of six players each: one goaltender, and five players who skate up and down the ice trying to take the puck and score a goal against the opposing team.\\n\\n- The National Hockey League (NHL) is a professional ice hockey league currently composed of 31 member clubs. Of the 30 clubs currently playing, 23 are in the United States and 7 in Canada. Headquartered in New York City, the NHL is considered to be the premier professional ice hockey league in the world, and one of the major professional sports leagues in the United States and Canada. The Stanley Cup, the oldest professional sports trophy in North America, is awarded annually to the league playoff champion at the end of each season.\\n\\n- Staples Center is a multi-purpose sports arena in Downtown Los Angeles. Adjacent to the L.A. Live development, it is located next to the Los Angeles Convention Center complex along Figueroa Street. Opening on October 17, 1999, it is one of the major sporting facilities in the Greater Los Angeles Area.\\n\\n- The Pittsburgh Penguins are a professional ice hockey team based in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. They are members of the Metropolitan Division of the Eastern Conference of the National Hockey League (NHL). The franchise was founded in 1967 as one of the first expansion teams during the league's original expansion from six to twelve teams. The Penguins played in the Civic Arena, also known to Pittsburgh fans as \\"The Igloo\\", from the time of their inception through the end of the 200910 season. They moved into their new arena, PPG Paints Arena, to begin the 201011 NHL season. They have qualified for five Stanley Cup Finals, winning the Stanley Cup four times  in 1991, 1992, 2009, and 2016.\\n\\n- Lead, from the Old English \\"l√©ad\\", is a chemical element with atomic number¬†82 and symbol¬†Pb (after the Latin, \\"plumbum\\"). It has the second highest atomic number of all practically stable elements. As such, lead is located at the end of some decay chains of heavier elements, which in part accounts for its relative abundance: its stability exceeds those of other similarly-numbered elements. Lead is a soft, malleable, and heavy metal. Freshly cut lead has a bluish-white color that soon tarnishes to a dull grayish color when exposed to air; as a liquid, it has a shiny chrome-silver luster. Lead's density of 11.34¬†g/cm exceeds those of most common materials. \\n\\n- Leonard G. Barrie ( born June 4 , 1969 in Kimberley , British Columbia ) is a retired professional ice hockey forward who played 184 games in the National Hockey League . He played for the Philadelphia Flyers , Pittsburgh Penguins , Los Angeles Kings , and Florida Panthers . He was a co-owner of the Tampa Bay Lightning , and was the president and coach of the Victoria Grizzlies of the British Columbia Hockey League . Barrie was a real estate & resort developer in the Victoria BC area . At one time he was the major partner in the Bear Mountain Resort development in Langford municipality . Bear Mountain includes the Bear Mountain Westin Hotel , golf course , and housing ( single family homes and condominiums ) . The apparent success of the Bear Mountain venture prompted the NHL Board of Governors , on June 18 , 2008 , to approve the sale of the Tampa Bay Lightning to an investment group which included Len Barrie and movie producer Oren Koules . It was alleged that Barrie and Koules began to disagree on team management issues , that were believed to include NHL superstar Vincent Lecavalier being traded . This became such a problem that NHL Commissioner Gary Bettman had to intervene and have a meeting with the two owners . Both were given the opportunity to buy the other out . Neither exercised that option and the team was later sold to Jeff Vinik , a minority owner of the Boston Red Sox . The development of Bear Mountain resort has been criticized for damaging sensitive ecosystems and historic native sites . Bear Mountain currently has a new management team after being under court protection from creditors . January 19 , 2012 ( Times - Colonist Newspaper ) - The Bellagio hotel and casino have filed a claim against Len Barrie seeking more than $ 2 million US . January 20 , 2012 ( Globe & Mail ) - The results of an RCMP investigation into Len Barrie 's financial dealings with his former Bear Mountain golf resort and real - estate development were recently turned over to the B.C. Attorney - General 's office for...\\n\\n- Los Angeles (Spanish for \\"The Angels\\"), officially the City of Los Angeles and often known by its initials L.A., is the second-most populous city in the United States (after New York City), the most populous city in California and the county seat of Los Angeles County. Situated in Southern California, Los Angeles is known for its mediterranean climate, ethnic diversity, sprawling metropolis, and as a major center of the American entertainment industry. Los Angeles lies in a large coastal basin surrounded on three sides by mountains reaching up to and over .\\n\\n- The Florida Panthers are a professional ice hockey team based in the Miami metropolitan area. They are members of the Atlantic Division of the Eastern Conference of the National Hockey League (NHL). It was founded in 1993 as an expansion team. They play home games at the BB&T Center in Sunrise, Florida; the Panthers are the southernmost team in the NHL. The team has made one appearance in the Stanley Cup Finals, in 1996; they lost to the Colorado Avalanche in four games.\\n\\n- The Los Angeles Kings are a professional ice hockey team based in Los Angeles. They are members of the Pacific Division of the Western Conference of the National Hockey League (NHL). The team was founded on June 5, 1967, after Jack Kent Cooke was awarded an NHL expansion franchise for Los Angeles on February 9, 1966, becoming one of the six teams that began play as part of the 1967 NHL expansion. The Kings called The Forum in Inglewood, California (a suburb of Los Angeles), their home for thirty-two years until they moved to the Staples Center in Downtown Los Angeles to start the 19992000 season.\\n\\n\\n\\nWhat entity does 'len barrie' has the relation 'position played on team / speciality' with?","target":"centre","rationale":"The rationale for the above question is \\"centre\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Sun Microsystems, Inc. was an American company that sold computers, computer components, software, and information technology services, and that created the Java programming language, the Solaris operating system , and the Network File System (NFS). Sun contributed significantly to the evolution of several key computing technologies, among them Unix, RISC processors, thin client computing, and virtualized computing. Sun was founded on February 24, 1982. At its height, the Sun headquarters were in Santa Clara, California (part of Silicon Valley), on the former west campus of the Agnews Developmental Center.\\n\\n- Java OpenGL ( JOGL ) is a wrapper library that allows OpenGL to be used in the Java programming language . It was originally developed by Kenneth Bradley Russell and Christopher John Kline , and was further developed by the Sun Microsystems Game Technology Group . Since 2010 , it has been an independent open source project under a BSD license . It is the reference implementation for Java Bindings for OpenGL ( JSR - 231 ) . JOGL allows access to most OpenGL features available to C language programs through the use of the Java Native Interface ( JNI ) . It offers access to both the standard GL * functions along with the GLU * functions ; however the OpenGL Utility Toolkit ( GLUT ) library is not available for window - system related calls , as Java has its own windowing systems : Abstract Window Toolkit ( AWT ) , Swing , and some extensions .\\n\\n- A thin client is a lightweight computer that is purpose-built for remote access to a server (typically cloud or desktop virtualization environments). It depends heavily on another computer (its \\"server\\") to fulfill its computational roles. The specific roles assumed by the server may vary, from hosting a shared set of virtualized applications, a shared desktop stack or virtual desktop, to data processing and file storage on the client's or user's behalf. This is different from the desktop PC (fat client), which is a computer designed to take on these roles by itself.\\n\\n- vi is a screen-oriented text editor originally created for the Unix operating system. The portable subset of the behavior of vi and programs based on it, and the ex editor language supported within these programs, is described by (and thus standardized by) the Single Unix Specification and POSIX.\\n\\n- Java Binding for the OpenGL API is a JSR API specification (JSR 231) for the Java Platform, Standard Edition which allows to use OpenGL on the Java (software platform). There is also Java Binding for the OpenGL ES API (JSR 239) for the Java Platform, Micro Edition.\\n\\n- Java Platform, Standard Edition or Java SE is a widely used platform for development and deployment of portable code for desktop and server environments. Java SE uses the object-oriented Java programming language. It is part of the Java software-platform family. Java SE defines a wide range of general-purpose APIs  such as Java APIs for the Java Class Library  and also includes the Java Language Specification and the Java Virtual Machine Specification. One of the most well-known implementations of Java SE is Oracle Corporation's Java Development Kit (JDK).\\n\\n- Unix (trademarked as UNIX) is a family of multitasking, multiuser computer operating systems that derive from the original AT&T Unix, developed starting in the 1970s at the Bell Labs research center by Ken Thompson, Dennis Ritchie, and others.\\n\\n- Java is a set of computer software and specifications developed by Sun Microsystems, which was later acquired by the Oracle Corporation, that provides a system for developing application software and deploying it in a cross-platform computing environment. Java is used in a wide variety of computing platforms from embedded devices and mobile phones to enterprise servers and supercomputers. While they are less common than standalone Java applications, Java applets run in secure, sandboxed environments to provide many features of native applications and can be embedded in HTML pages.\\n\\n- A computer is a device that can be instructed to carry out an arbitrary set of arithmetic or logical operations automatically. The ability of computers to follow a sequence of operations, called a \\"program\\", make computers very flexible and useful. Such computers are used as control systems for a very wide variety of industrial and consumer devices. This includes simple special purpose devices like microwave ovens and remote controls, factory devices such as industrial robots and computer assisted design, but also in general purpose devices like personal computers and mobile devices such as smartphones. The Internet is run on computers and it connects millions of other computers.\\n\\n- Java Platform, Micro Edition, or Java ME, is a Java platform designed for embedded systems (such as mobile devices, for example). Target devices range from industrial controls to mobile phones (especially feature phones) and set-top boxes. Java ME was formerly known as Java 2 Platform, Micro Edition (J2ME).\\n\\n- Open Graphics Library (OpenGL)\\nis a cross-language, cross-platform application programming interface (API) for rendering 2D and 3D vector graphics. The API is typically used to interact with a graphics processing unit (GPU), to achieve hardware-accelerated rendering.\\n\\n- A graphics processing unit (GPU), occasionally called visual processing unit (VPU), is a specialized electronic circuit designed to rapidly manipulate and alter memory to accelerate the creation of images in a frame buffer intended for output to a display device. GPUs are used in embedded systems, mobile phones, personal computers, workstations, and game consoles. Modern GPUs are very efficient at manipulating computer graphics and image processing, and their highly parallel structure makes them more efficient than general-purpose CPUs for algorithms where the processing of large blocks of data is done in parallel. In a personal computer, a GPU can be present on a video card, or it can be embedded on the motherboard orin certain CPUson the CPU die.\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the information, choose the subject and object entities that have the relation of 'platform'.","target":"java opengl , java virtual machine","rationale":"Java is a platform, so the answer can be \\"java opengl , java virtual machine\\".\\n'''"},{"source":"Topic from the paragraph: \\nBy contrast, the Habsburg frontier had settled somewhat, a stalemate caused by a stiffening of the Habsburg defences. The Long War against Habsburg Austria (1593‚Äì1606) created the need for greater numbers of Ottoman infantry equipped with firearms, resulting in a relaxation of recruitment policy. This contributed to problems of indiscipline and outright rebelliousness within the corps, which were never fully solved. Irregular sharpshooters (Sekban) were also recruited, and on demobilization turned to brigandage in the Jelali revolts (1595‚Äì1610), which engendered widespread anarchy in Anatolia in the late 16th and early 17th centuries. With the Empire's population reaching 30 million people by 1600, the shortage of land placed further pressure on the government . In spite of these problems, the Ottoman state remained strong, and its army did not collapse or suffer crushing defeats. The only exceptions were campaigns against the Safavid dynasty of Persia, where many of the Ottoman eastern provinces were lost, some permanently. This 1603‚Äì1618 war eventually resulted in the Treaty of Nasuh Pasha, which ceded the entire Caucasus, except westernmost Georgia, back into Iranian Safavid possession. Campaigns during this era became increasingly inconclusive, even against weaker states with much smaller forces, such as Poland or Austria.","target":"Ottoman Empire","rationale":"The context is about the Habsburg frontier and Ottoman Empire. Throughout the text, there are many references to the Ottoman Empire including its population size in 1600s, which suggests that this paragraph focuses heavily on it.\\nFurthermore, from historical records we know that some of the current day countries were part of either The Habsburg Monarchy or Ottoman Empire during 1500-1600 AD. So even though there might be a mention of Austria or Poland (which currently exist as independent nations), their economic power back then was not comparable to what they have now due to much smaller territories and populations under control within those empires at that time period (1500-1600 AD). \\nHence if you analyze all these points above very carefully - \\"Ottoman empire\\" would be best answer for question: Topic"},{"source":"Given the following passage\\n\\n\\"A PM motor does not have a field winding on the stator frame, instead relying on PMs to provide the magnetic field against which the rotor field interacts to produce torque. Compensating windings in series with the armature may be used on large motors to improve commutation under load. Because this field is fixed, it cannot be adjusted for speed control. PM fields (stators) are convenient in miniature motors to eliminate the power consumption of the field winding. Most larger DC motors are of the \\"dynamo\\" type, which have stator windings. Historically, PMs could not be made to retain high flux if they were disassembled; field windings were more practical to obtain the needed amount of flux. However, large PMs are costly, as well as dangerous and difficult to assemble; this favors wound fields for large machines.\\",\\n\\nanswer the following question. Note that the answer is present within the text.\\n\\nQuestion: What is an issue with the field?","target":"it cannot be adjusted for speed control","rationale":"\\"A PM motor does not have a field winding on the stator frame, instead relying on PMs to provide the magnetic field against which the rotor field interacts to produce torque. Compensating windings in series with the armature may be used on large motors to improve commutation under load. Because this field is fixed, it cannot be adjusted for speed control.\\"\\nThe issue is that because of its set nature (i.e., magnetism) and lack of external power source, adjustments to its speed could not be made easily if at all."},{"source":"Given a negotiation between two participants, answer 'Yes' if both participants agree to the deal, otherwise answer 'No'.\\n\\nTHEM: hi i would like the hat and 1 book, you can have the balls and 1 book  YOU: i want the hat and a book or ball  THEM: im sorry i cant make a deal without the hat. im willing to give you everything if i can keep the hat  YOU: i need the hat as well  THEM: ok, looks like we wont be able to reach a deal  YOU: are you sure?  THEM: im sure. me keeping the hat and offering you the rest is the best i can do  YOU: double triple sure?  THEM: double triple sure  YOU: really??","target":"No","rationale":"Given a negotiation between two participants, answer 'Yes' if both participants agree to the deal, otherwise answer 'No'. In this task the participants don't agree to any deal. The participant THEM says \\"im sure. me keeping the hat and offering you the rest is the best i can do\\" which means that they won't be able to give any other thing even after getting all of YOUR package items (balls and books). So, as they are not agreeing with each other on any deal or agreement (exchange of packages), answer is No."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a public comment from online platforms. You are expected to classify the comment into two classes: threat and non-threat. Threat is a statement that someone will be hurt or harmed, especially if the person does not do something in particular.\\n\\nComment: No doubt to foment violence, and kill police officers.","target":"Threat","rationale":"The given comment clearly states that someone is going to be hurt or harmed. Therefore, the answer is \\"Threat\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Russell Philip Taylor MBE ( born 8 July 1960 ) is a British writer , journalist and composer . He is best known as half of the team ( with Charles Peattie ) that created the comic strip Alex . He studied at Abingdon School and read Russian and Philosophy at St Anne 's College , Oxford . He was appointed MBE in 2002 . He also writes TV and film music with Steve Cooke . Among others , they composed the music for the documentaries The Dying Rooms in 1995 and Chosen and Saving Africa 's Witch Children -- both of which won BAFTAs in April 2009 . He has also written books on Russia and marathon running . Taylor is a supporter of Tottenham Hotspur football club , and as a private joke ( and to avoid libel accusations ) always names characters who are fired in the Alex strip after Tottenham footballers .\\n\\n- A cartoonist (also comic strip creator) is a visual artist who specializes in drawing cartoons. This work is often created for entertainment, political commentary, or advertising. Cartoonists may work in many formats, such as animation, booklets, comic strips, comic books, editorial cartoons, graphic novels, manuals, gag cartoons, graphic design, illustrations, storyboards, posters, shirts, books, advertisements, greeting cards, magazines, newspapers, and video game packaging.\\n\\n- St Anne's College is one of the constituent colleges of the University of Oxford in England. Formerly a women's college, it has been coeducational since 1979. Founded in 1879 as The Society of Oxford Home-Students, it received its college status in 1952, and today it is one of the larger colleges in Oxford, with around 450 undergraduate and 200 graduate students in a roughly equal mix of men and women. The college is known for its progressive outlook, its academic strength in both the humanities and the sciences, its mix of architecture, and its library  the largest college library in Oxford.\\n\\n- Charles Peattie (born 3 April 1958) is a British cartoonist, best known as half of the team (with Russell Taylor) that creates the comic strip Alex. He has two daughters and two sons. He lives in London.\\n\\n- The University of Oxford (informally Oxford University or simply Oxford) is a collegiate research university located in Oxford, England, United Kingdom. While having no known date of foundation, there is evidence of teaching as far back as 1096, making it the oldest university in the English-speaking world and the world's second-oldest university in continuous operation. It grew rapidly from 1167 when Henry II banned English students from attending the University of Paris. After disputes between students and Oxford townsfolk in 1209, some academics fled northeast to Cambridge where they established what became the University of Cambridge. The two \\"ancient universities\\" are frequently jointly referred to as \\"Oxbridge\\".\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the information, choose the subject and object entities that have the relation of 'occupation'.","target":"russell taylor  , cartoonist","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"russell taylor  , cartoonist\\" is a relation with entity type 'occupation'."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a statement spoken by a politician in natural language and the subject of the discussion for the given statement. Your task is to determine if the given subject of the discussion is correct for the given statement. The subject can be multiple words. Answer with \\"True\\" if it's the correct subject of discussion or return \\"False\\" if it's incorrect.\\n\\nStatement: Says he and Bernie Sanders have very similar views on trade \\n Subject: china,economy,labor,trade,workers","target":"True","rationale":"The subject of discussion in the statement is trade and economy, and the politician is comparing his ideas to Bernie Sanders. Therefore, the answer is True."},{"source":"What is an example of reproduction?\\n- reading books\\n- laying down\\n- walking\\n- unhatched chicks\\n\\nWhich is the correct answer?","target":"unhatched chicks","rationale":"Reproduction is the biological process by which new individuals of a species are created. Some examples include sexual reproduction, where eggs and sperm come together to create offspring; cloning, in which an exact copy of an individual is produced using cells from that same organism; and budding, whereby parts of one organism break off and grow into entirely separate organisms. \\nIn this case, unhatched chicks can be thought of as \\"new\\" or young individuals born through reproduction (through egg-laying). Therefore, they would be considered reproductive offspring."},{"source":"In this task, we ask you to write an implausible answer to a question that involves event \\"frequency\\", which refers to how often an event is likely to be repeated. For example, \\"taking showers\\" typically occurs ~5 times a week, \\"going to Saturday market\\" usually happens every few weeks/months, etc. Even though there exist multiple wrong answers, we only need a single wrong answer. Please try to keep your \\"answer\\" as simple as possible. Concise and simple \\"answer\\" is preferred over those complex and verbose ones.\\n\\nSentence: They like to play hopscotch or jump rope but that day they wanted to play tag. \\nQuestion: How often do they play tag?","target":"900 times","rationale":"The frequency of how often \\"they\\" play tag is not likely to be as high as 900 times."},{"source":"The Trump administration's decision to add a question about citizenship to the 2020 census divided Capitol Hill on Tuesday, with Democrats saying the addition could skew the results and alter millions in government funding, while some Republicans praised it as a \\"commonsense\\" move.\\nU.S. Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross announced late Monday the next effort to count every resident in the country will include a question about citizenship status. The U.S. Census Bureau conducts the survey every 10 years, with the next set for 2020. The deadline for finalizing the questions is Saturday.\\nIn a memo late Monday, Ross said he chose to include the query at the urging of the Department of Justice, which said it needed the citizenship data to better enforce a law protecting minority voting rights.\\nWhite House press secretary Sarah Huckabee Sanders defended the addition of the question, rejecting the notion that it might result in less federal aid to immigrant communities in the U.S. if immigrants are undercounted.\\nRepublicans on Capitol Hill welcomed the decision, which revives a practice that was abandoned in 1950, after being in place for more than 100 years, according to the Commerce Department.\\n\\"It is imperative that the data gathered in the census is reliable, given the wide-ranging impacts it will have on U.S. policy. A question on citizenship is a reasonable, commonsense addition to the census,\\" Senator Ted Cruz said in a statement Tuesday.\\nBut Democrats said the question would have the opposite effect ‚Äî discouraging undocumented immigrants and citizen family members from responding to the census, undermining the accuracy of the results.\\n\\"We cannot accept an incomplete or unfair count in 2020 ‚Äî too much is at stake,\\" Rep. Carolyn Maloney, co-chair of the Congressional Census Caucus, told VOA. \\"The census mandated by the [U.S.] Constitution affects the way that Federal and state funds are distributed and how district lines are drawn for both the city, state and Federal level.\\"\\nHow long did it take Ross to write the memo?\\nPick the correct answer from the following options:\\n- not enough information\\n- An hour or so\\n- twenty minutes\\n- three hours","target":"An hour or so","rationale":"The context suggests that the memo was written late Monday night, which is a time when people are typically resting or doing other things rather than working. Given this information, it can be inferred that Ross would have spent only an hour (or so) writing the memo and not several hours as suggested by option three. Option one ‚Äúnot enough information‚Äù cannot be correct because there is sufficient information in the question to give us a clear idea of how long Ross took to write his memo.\\nTherefore, given all these cues, we can conclude that answer choice two \\"An hour or so\\" must be correct here."},{"source":"Given a goal and 2 solutions, choose the most appropriate solution.\\nGoal: Make your own pillowcases.\\n- Solution 1: Get some material you like and measure your pillow. Make sure you have enough material to cover the top. Sew around all 3 sides and leave one end open. Hem that end. Insert pillow.\\n- Solution 2: Get some material you like and measure your pillow. Make sure you have enough material to cover this twice. Sew around all 3 sides and leave one end open. Hem that end. Insert pillow.\\n\\nAnswer by returning either Solution 1 or Solution 2","target":"Solution 2","rationale":"Solution 1 is incomplete. Given that material must be used to cover the top and sides of a pillow, there will not be enough material left over to hem the open end after sewing all three sides.\\nSo, Solution 2 would make more sense as this solution provides fabric for both covering the top and bottom of the pillow."},{"source":"I first experienced a loss of sexual desire several years ago, just after I turned 40. For a long time, I thought it was me. I thought maybe it was my age.\\nAfter reading every book and article I could find on sex, relationships, and marriage, I started to wonder if maybe it wasn‚Äôt me. Maybe it was my marriage, maybe it was my husband.\\nI never wanted to be ‚Äúthat woman‚Äú. The one that screwed around on her husband. But, I had an affair about six or seven years ago. It didn‚Äôt last long. But, that‚Äôs when I knew my marriage was over. It wasn‚Äôt a lack of sexual desire, it was a lack of desire for my husband. I didn‚Äôt want him or the marriage. There was nothing wrong with my sex drive.\\nI told my husband that I‚Äôd had an affair. He changed for about a month or so. He was very loving and attentive. But it didn‚Äôt last. He loves differently than I need to be loved and it‚Äôs just not in him to love me that way.\\nA few months after I ended the affair, I got involved with someone else. I know. I shouldn‚Äôt have. I‚Äôve experienced things with this other man that I never thought possible. Felt things I thought were only possible in movies.\\nHe‚Äôs a romantic. Not flowers or candy or jewellery, but he talks and listens. He hears me. He tries to understand me and give me what I need. Deep, intimate conversations. Looking into one another‚Äôs eyes. Soft caresses. Words of adoration. These things he gives me almost daily.\\nI never knew I needed romance because I‚Äôd never had it. This is how I need to be loved.\\nAfter having felt this way, I can‚Äôt stay in my marriage. It‚Äôs not fair to either of us.\\nI‚Äôm not sure what happened.\\nDid we grow apart?\\nDid one or both of us change?\\nDo people‚Äôs needs change as they get older?\\nWhat does the author think about making up with her husband probably?\\n- the author probably wants to badly\\n- the author probably doesn't want to\\n- not enough information\\n- the author probably doesn't care either way","target":"not enough information","rationale":"The passage explains that the author and her husband are no longer happy in their marriage. However, it does not offer information about how either party feels about getting back together or staying married.\\nSince there is insufficient information to determine whether they will make up, we have no choice but to go with \\"not enough information\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a story (which contains five sentences only). Your task is to find all the characters which are available in the given story.\\n\\nSentence1: Joan had to do a science project for school. Sentence2: She decided to study the effects of the sun on an egg on the sidewalk. Sentence3: She waited outside all day. Sentence4: By the end of the day, the egg was cooked, but inedible. Sentence5: Joan concluded that cooking eggs on the sidewalk is ill-advised.","target":"Joan","rationale":"In the given story, Joan is the only character available."},{"source":"Article: The Gold Standard Act of 1900 abandoned the bimetallic standard and defined the dollar as 23.22 grains (1.505 g) of gold, equivalent to setting the price of 1 troy ounce of gold at $20.67. Silver coins continued to be issued for circulation until 1964, when all silver was removed from dimes and quarters, and the half dollar was reduced to 40% silver. Silver half dollars were last issued for circulation in 1970. Gold coins were confiscated by Executive Order 6102 issued in 1933 by Franklin Roosevelt. The gold standard was changed to 13.71 grains (0.888 g), equivalent to setting the price of 1 troy ounce of gold at $35. This standard persisted until 1968.\\n\\nQuestion: How much was 1 troy ounce of gold worth?","target":"$20.67","rationale":"The context is the Gold Standard Act of 1900, which describes how much an ounce (1 troy ounce) of gold was worth at that time. It also mentions other information about ounces and silver coins' issues as well as their confiscation by Franklin Roosevelt's Executive Order 6102 in 1933.\\nAs mentioned above, based on this act, 1 troy ounce of gold would be worth $20.67; therefore the answer to the question should be: \\"$20.67\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on geometry. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: the sides of a triangle are in the ratio 5 : 12 : 13 and its perimeter is 480 m , its area is ? \\nOptions: a ) 150 , b ) 240 , c ) 277 , d ) 261 , e ) 281","target":"b","rationale":"Since the sides are in the ratio 5:12:13, we can represent them as 5x, 12x, and 13x.\\\\nAdding these three numbers gives 480 = 30x. Therefore, x = 16. So the sides of the triangle are 5(16) = 80 m , 12(16) = 192 m , and 13(16) = 208 m . \\\\nTo find the area of a triangle with sides a, b and c : \\\\nArea of triangle (in square units) = ‚àös (s-a)(s-b)(s-c)\\\\ns is half of perimeter\\\\ns=480/2=240\\\\nTherefore Area=‚àö240*160*112*96=‚àö150528000=385 square units"},{"source":"Please read the following news article and write another sentence to add to it.\\n\\n(CNN) -- Lebanese authorities on Saturday arrested three people in connection with the kidnapping of two Turkish pilots, both of whom remain missing more than a week later. The Turkish Airlines pilots were riding a bus heading from Beirut-Rafic Hariri International Airport to their hotel early August 9 when armed assailants stopped the bus, according to Turkey's foreign ministry. Reports on the number of attackers -- who were riding in two vehicles -- varied from four to eight. Lebanon's state-run National News Agency reported Saturday that three people had been arrested by the Internal Security Forces Information Branch \\"in connection\\" with the kidnapping.\\n\\n- \\nArrests made in the kidnapping of Turkish Airlines pilots, state news says\\n\\n- \\nGunmen had halted a bus near Beirut, then took away pilots\\n\\n- \\nOthers safely got to a hotel","target":"\\"Our ministry and our embassy will exert intensive efforts in cooperation with the Lebanese authorities to ensure the liberation of our pilots and their return to Turkish,\\" the ministry said last week.","rationale":"The context discusses the kidnapping of two Turkish pilots by Lebanese authorities, however it does not address what measures Turkey will take to ensure their safe release. Given this information gap, we can add a sentence that explains how Turkey is working towards ensuring their freedom.\\n\\"Our ministry and our embassy will exert intensive efforts in cooperation with the Lebanese authorities to ensure the liberation of our pilots and their return to Turkish,\\" the ministry said last week."},{"source":"Q: What layer of skin is located right beneath the epidermis?\\n\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- cusps\\n\\n- scars\\n\\n- humus\\n\\n- dermis\\n\\nA:","target":"dermis","rationale":"The epidermis is the outermost layer of skin, and it consists mainly of two types of cells: keratinocytes (which are responsible for making keratin) and melanocytes.\\nBelow that lies a thicker middle layer called the dermis, which contains blood vessels as well as connective tissues such as collagen and elastin fibers. Hair follicles also grow out from this part of the skin. The other three choices do not correspond to any known layers or parts within human skin anatomy; nor do they have anything to do with sweat glands, nerves, or hair growth like our choice \\"dermis\\" does!"},{"source":"In this task, you're given a question, along with a context passage which has extra information available on certain terms mentioned in it, i.e., the proper nouns in the passage. Your job is to determine whether information from more than one term is needed to answer the question. Indicate your choice as \`a\` for Yes or \`b\` for No.\\n\\nQuestion: Which of the writers of Abbott's first two plays is older? Passage:After moving to New York, Abbott began going to big open calls for plays while in school. This is how Abbott got his two first acting jobs, Off-Broadway. The first play, Good Boys and True, opened in the Spring of 2008 and was written by Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa and directed by Scott Ellis. It followed a scandal at a prep school. Abbott played the lead character's (Brian J. Smith) gay best friend, Justin. The second play, Mouth to Mouth, opened in the Fall of 2008. The mordant and mournful play about the limits of friendship and family was written by Kevin Elyot and directed by Mark Brokaw. Abbott played the sympathetic 15-year-old son of Laura (Lisa Emery). Abbott received positive reviews for both productions. Abbott followed this with guest-starring roles in the comedy series Nurse Jackie and the police procedural series  . In 2010, Abbott co-starred opposite Cristin Milioti and Laila Robins in the play That Face at the Manhattan Theatre Club.","target":"a","rationale":"The question asks for a comparison of two writers. The first writer is mentioned in the passage as \\"Roberto Aguirre-Sacasa\\" and the second writer is mentioned as \\"Kevin Elyot\\". Therefore, information from more than one term is needed to answer the question."},{"source":"You are given a short poem which is written by a kid. Your task is to predict if the kid is in elementary school or high school. Anyone who is from grade 1st to 6th-grade will be considered as in elementary school, and 7th to 12th-grade kids will be considered as in high school. There are only two possible outputs, i.e., elementary and high. All inputs have at least one output and it cannot have both categories at a time.\\n\\nyou see her up and down the street you see her everywhere you meet she 's always there to keep you warm even if she 's in a storm you may not know her very well because she live alone in a cell she be poor but she be kind and no matter what she speak her mind","target":"elementary","rationale":"The poem is about the sun, and it describes how the sun makes life possible. The poem also mentions that the sun \\"be\\" poor and \\"be\\" kind, which is an informal way to talk about the sun in speech. These two facts suggest that this poem was written by a kid in elementary school, so Output is \\\\\\"elementary\\\\\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i,j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to list all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element in the reverse order. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j.\\n\\n4, 10, ['3859', 'N', '779', 'c', 'g', 'O', '5659', 'g', '3847', 'W', '3471', 'L']","target":"W, 3847, g, 5659, O, g, c","rationale":"Given the list ['3859', 'N', '779', 'c', 'g', 'O', '5659', 'g', '3847', 'W'], we need to find the elements within the range 4 ~ 10.\\\\n1. The 4th element is g.\\\\n2. The 5th element is O.\\\\n3. The 6th element is 5659..\\\\n4. The 7th element is g..\\\\n5. The 8th element is 3847..\\\\n6. The 9th element is W..\\n\\nThe final output would be [W, 3847, g, 5659, O, g, c] in reverse order [c, g , O ,5659 ,g ,3847 ,W]."},{"source":"This article: Rosa Moline is the dissatisfied, restless wife of Lewis, a small-town Wisconsin doctor. She is easily bored, uninterested in her husband's career or in anything to do with her current circumstances. She has long desired a glamorous life, in a world where she can have expensive things and meet truly interesting people. For over a year, she has been having an affair with Neil Latimer, a Chicago businessman who owns the local hunting lodge. Tired of waiting for him to ask her to marry and move to Chicago, Rosa extorts money from Lewis' patients - who often do not have cash but pay him in produce or in other non-financial ways - to finance her trip to the city.\\nLewis does not yet know about the affair, but he is used to his wife's unease with her life; he discovers the extortion and throws the cash at her, telling her that if she goes to Chicago, she need not come back. Rosa immediately leaves and fully expects Latimer to welcome her. However, he avoids her at first, then when he does meet her, he tells her he is love with another woman and intends to marry. Devastated, Rosa returns to Wisconsin, where Lewis forgives her. She soon becomes pregnant and, briefly, seems to be trying to settle down.\\nDuring a party for Moose, the man who tends to the hunting lodge, Latimer shows up. He lets Rosa know that he has changed his mind and wants to marry her. Moose overhears the couple planning for her divorce and their marriage; the next day, as everyone is heading out on a hunting trip, Moose bets that her lover will not want the baby and advises Rosa that she had better tell Latimer about it, or he will. To prevent that eventuality, she shoots and kills Moose during the hunt. She is acquitted of this act by claiming she thought he was a deer. contains an answer for the question: What excuse does Rosa use for shooting Moose?, what is it ?","target":"she thought he was a deer","rationale":"In the passage, Rosa shoots and kills Moose during a hunting trip. She is acquitted of this act by claiming she thought he was a deer."},{"source":"Fill in the response. DIALOG:\\nWhen was Najibullah Zazi Captured?\\n- On September 19, 2009, authorities arrested Zazi.\\n- where was Najibullah Zazi when he was captured?\\n- Was Najibullah Zazi in any kind of trouble?\\n- Zazi faced a possible life sentence without possibility of parole. In May 2019, it was announced Zazi would be released after serving 10 years due to cooperation with law enforcement.\\n- Did they find anything on Najibullah Zazi when they pulled him over?\\n- They did not find anything of note, and he was allowed to go.\\n-","target":"Where was Najibullah Zazi going when he was pulled over?","rationale":"The answer is \\"Where was Najibullah Zazi going when he was pulled over?\\" because the previous question asked where Najibullah Zazi was captured, and this question is a follow up asking about his destination. The other options do not fit with the dialogue."},{"source":"Dialogue:\\n\\nW: I wonder if I could borrow your dictionary?\\n\\nM: You certainly could if I had one, but I lost my old one yesterday and I haven't bought a new one yet.\\n\\nQuestion: What did the man say about his dictionary? \\n\\n- He has bought a new one.\\n\\n- He lost his old one and borrowed a new one.\\n\\n- He didn't have any dictionary then.","target":"He didn't have any dictionary then.","rationale":"In the dialogue, man said that he lost his old dictionary and hadn't bought a new one yet. So at present, he doesn‚Äôt have any dictionary with him. Hence answer is ‚ÄúHe didn't have any dictionary then.\\""},{"source":"Multi-choice problem: Based on the sentence \\"A bronze street performer pretends to make a movie while a confused boy watches.\\", is the sentence \\"A boy is sleeping on the street next to a movie director.\\" a true sentence?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"As the premise sentence \\"A bronze street performer pretends to make a movie while a confused boy watches.\\" tells us, the mentioned boy is not sleeping on the street next to a movie director but rather watching him."},{"source":"Which is likely to provide an undesired acquired characteristic for an organism?\\n\\nA -> a light scratch on its leg\\n\\nB -> learning to leave the nest\\n\\nC -> finding a potential mate\\n\\nD -> dipping a foot in magma\\n\\nIs the right answer A, B, C or D ?","target":"D","rationale":"The best answer is D.\\nAcquired characteristics are changes that happen to an organism during its lifetime, like a scratch or the loss of a limb. Organisms cannot pass these traits on to their offspring through reproduction and do not change the DNA in any way."},{"source":"Q: Attaching strips of neutral metals that are higher in the activity series can protect a structure from what?\\n\\n\\nRead this paragraph and choose the correct option from the provided answers:\\n\\nAttaching strips of neutral metals that are higher in the activity series can protect a structure from corrosion.\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- diffusion\\n\\n- deoxidation\\n\\n- weathering\\n\\n- corrosion\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"corrosion","rationale":"The passage states that attaching strips of neutral metals to a structure can protect it from corrosion. Among the given options, only \\"corrosion\\" is consistent with this statement."},{"source":"Can we draw the following hypothesis from the context (see options)? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nESPN‚Äôs Jemele Hill called the Quincy Harris Morning Show with K. Foxx to talk about our Philadelphia Eagles. Jemele does not think they are going to win and Quincy makes a bet with her. She also explains that she was not fired from ESPN, that her new job, The Undefeated, is owned by ESPN and why she made that decision. Listen below: Also On 100.3:\\n\\nHypothesis: Jemele Hill has never used a telephone in her life.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"In the context, Jemele Hill called the Quincy Harris Morning Show with K. Foxx to talk about our Philadelphia Eagles which means that she has used a telephone in her life at least once. So we cannot draw such hypothesis from this context and thus answer is No"},{"source":"Dialogue:\\n\\nM: Well, madam, the first and the most important thing I have to tell you is that there is really nothing seriously wrong with you, physically that is. The analyst's report shows that basically you are very fit.\\n\\nW: So, why is it that I'm always so nervous... tense... ready to jump on anybody-my husband, children, and colleagues?\\n\\nM: I think your condition has a lot to do with your habits.\\n\\nW: Habits?\\n\\nM: Yes... now tell me, madam, you smoke, don't you?\\n\\nW: Yes, I'm afraid I do, doctor.\\n\\nM: And, very heavily, I imagine.\\n\\nW: Yes, quite heavily.\\n\\nM: What do you eat normally?\\n\\nW: I'm a good eater. Yes, I'd say I'm a good eater. But usually, I don't eat breakfast.\\n\\nM: That's bad for your health. I think you should get up early and have breakfast. And, another question, do you get up early?\\n\\nW: No, I usually get up at 9:00 a. m. I get up late because I go to bed too late. I stay up late watching TV till the midnight.\\n\\nM: What sport do you usually do?\\n\\nW: I don't like sports. But sometimes I play cards with some friends, that may be my sport.\\n\\nM: I think, madam, for your health, you'd better change your way of life.\\n\\nQuestion: The patient, according to the analyst's report, is \\n\\n- physically ill.\\n\\n- mentally ill.\\n\\n- fit.","target":"fit.","rationale":"The analyst's report shows that the patient is fit.\\n\\nSo, the answer is \\"fit\\"."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- Glasgow  is the largest city in Scotland, and third largest in the United Kingdom. Historically part of Lanarkshire, it is now one of the 32 council areas of Scotland. It is situated on the River Clyde in the country's West Central Lowlands. Inhabitants of the city are referred to as Glaswegians.\\n\\n- In Norse mythology, Thor (from Old Norse √û√≥rr) is a hammer-wielding god associated with thunder, lightning, storms, oak trees, strength, the protection of mankind, and also hallowing and fertility. The cognate deity in wider Germanic mythology and paganism was known in Old English as √ûunor and in Old High German as Donar (runic √æonar ), stemming from a Common Germanic *√ûunraz (meaning \\"thunder\\").\\n\\n- Trip hop is a subgenre of electronic music that originated in the early 1990s in the United Kingdom, especially Bristol. Deriving from later idioms of acid house, the term was first used by the British music media and press as a way to describe the more experimental variant of breakbeat emerging from the Bristol Sound scene, which contained influences of soul, funk and jazz. It has been described as \\"Europe's alternative choice in the second half of the '90s\\", and \\"a fusion of hip hop and electronica until neither genre is recognisable\\". Trip hop music fuses several styles and has much in common with other genres; it has several qualities similar to ambient music, and its drum-based breakdowns share characteristics with hip hop. It also contains elements of R&B, dub and house, as well as other electronic music. Trip hop can be highly experimental.\\n\\n- Homogenic is the third international solo album by Icelandic musician Bj√∂rk, released in September 1997. Produced by Bj√∂rk, Mark Bell, Guy Sigsworth, Howie B and Markus Dravs, it was released on One Little Indian Records. The music of \\"Homogenic\\" was a new style for Bj√∂rk, focusing on similar-sounding music combining electronic beats and string instruments with songs in tribute to her native country Iceland. \\"Homogenic\\" was originally to be produced in her home in London, but was later recorded in Spain. \\"Homogenic\\" marked the first of several production collaborations between Bj√∂rk and Mark Bell, whom Bj√∂rk would cite as a major influence on her musical career. The album peaked at number twenty-eight on the \\"Billboard\\" 200, and at number four on the UK Albums Chart.\\n\\n- The Christianization of Scandinavia took place between the 8th and the 12th centuries. The realms of Scandinavia proper, Denmark, Norway and Sweden, established their own Archdioceses, responsible directly to the Pope, in 1104, 1154 and 1164, respectively. The conversion to Christianity of the Scandinavian people required more time, since it took additional efforts to establish a network of churches. The Sami remained unconverted until the 18th century.\\n\\n- In Norse mythology, Ragnar√∂k is a series of future events, including a great battle, foretold to ultimately result in the death of a number of major figures (including the gods Odin, Thor, T√Ωr, Freyr, Heimdallr, and Loki), the occurrence of various natural disasters, and the subsequent submersion of the world in water. Afterward, the world will resurface anew and fertile, the surviving and returning gods will meet, and the world will be repopulated by two human survivors. Ragnar√∂k is an important event in the Norse mythology, and has been the subject of scholarly discourse and theory throughout the history of Germanic studies.\\n\\n- One Little Indian Records is a London-based independent record label that rose from the ashes of punk rock record company Spiderleg Records. It was set up in 1985 by members of various anarcho-punk bands, and managed by former Flux of Pink Indians bassist Derek Birkett.\\n\\n- T√Ωr (Old Norse: \\"T√Ωr\\" ) is a Germanic god associated with law and heroic glory in Norse mythology, portrayed as one-handed. Corresponding names in other Germanic languages are Gothic Teiws, Old English Tw and Old High German Ziu and Cyo, all from Proto-Germanic *. The Latinised name is rendered as Tius or Tio and also formally as Mars Thincsus.\\n\\n- The UK Albums Chart (currently called the Official Albums Chart) is a list of albums ranked by physical and digital sales and (from March 2015) audio streaming in the United Kingdom. It was published for the first time on 22 July 1956 and is compiled every week by the Official Charts Company (OCC) on Fridays (previously Sundays). It is broadcast on BBC Radio 1 (top 5) and published in \\"Music Week\\" magazine (top 75), and on the OCC website (top 100).\\n\\n- In Germanic mythology, Odin (from Old Norse √ì√∞inn) is a widely revered god. In Norse mythology, from which stems most of the information about the god, Odin is associated with healing, death, royalty, the gallows, knowledge, battle, sorcery, poetry, frenzy, and the runic alphabet, and is the husband of the goddess Frigg. In wider Germanic mythology and paganism, Odin was known in Old English as Wden, in Old Saxon as Wdan, and in Old High German as Wuotan or Wtan, all stemming from the reconstructed Proto-Germanic theonym wanaz.\\n\\n- Bj√∂rk Gu√∞mundsd√≥ttir (born 21 November 1965), known as Bj√∂rk, is an Icelandic singer, songwriter, producer, DJ, and actress. Over her four-decade career, she has developed an eclectic musical style that draws on a wide range of influences and genres spanning electronic, pop, experimental, classical, trip hop, IDM, and avant-garde styles. She initially became known as the lead singer of the alternative rock band The Sugarcubes, whose 1987 single \\"Birthday\\" was a hit on US and UK indie stations and a favorite among music critics. Bj√∂rk embarked on a solo career in 1993, coming to prominence as a solo artist with albums such as \\"Debut\\" (1993), \\"Post\\" (1995), and \\"Homogenic\\" (1997), while collaborating with a range of artists and exploring a variety of multimedia projects. \\n\\n- Alternative rock (also called alternative music, alt-rock or simply alternative) is a genre of rock music that emerged from the independent music underground of the 1980s and became widely popular in the 1990s and 2000s. In this instance, the word \\"alternative\\" refers to the genre's distinction from mainstream rock music. The term's original meaning was broader, referring to a generation of musicians unified by their collective debt to either the musical style or simply the independent, D.I.Y. ethos of punk rock, which in the late 1970s laid the groundwork for alternative music. At times, \\"alternative\\" has been used as a catch-all description for music from underground rock artists that receives mainstream recognition, or for any music, whether rock or not, that is seen to be descended from punk rock (including some examples of punk itself, as well as new wave, and post-punk).\\n\\n- Wu-Tang Clan is an American hip hop group from New York City, originally composed of East Coast rappers RZA, GZA, Ol' Dirty Bastard, Method Man, Raekwon, Ghostface Killah, Inspectah Deck, U-God and Masta Killa. Cappadonna later became an official member of the group. The group was formed in and is associated with the New York City borough of Staten Island. \\n\\n- \`\` All Is Full of Love '' is a song by Icelandic musician Bj√∂rk and is from her fourth studio album , Homogenic ( 1997 ) . The lyrics are inspired by the presence of love in the advent of spring and Norse mythology 's Ragnar√∂k . The more popular version of the track , the original mix solely produced by Bj√∂rk , was used in the music video but did not appear in the album . The album version is a remix by Howie B and has a minimalist approach and places emphasis on the singer 's vocals . The video features a combination of electronic beats and string instruments . A remix by the German IDM duo Funkst√∂rung was released as a single in the summer of 1998 . The song later received a full single release in June 1999 to coincide with the release of its music video . While some commentators declared that the song was one of the highlights of the Homogenic album , the single performed moderately on the UK Singles Chart , peaking at number 24 . In the United States it was a dance hit . The song and music video were released two years after the release of the album for artistic merit rather than promotional purposes . The song was included as the opening track in the compilation album Greatest Hits ( 2002 ) , whose tracks were selected by fans through a survey . \`\` All Is Full of Love '' is regarded by some as the first DVD single . The accompanying music video , \`\` All Is Full of Love '' was directed by Chris Cunningham and depicts the assembling of a robot with Bj√∂rk 's features and her passionately kissing another robot against an ethereal and sterile backdrop . The song 's video garnered acclaim from critics and is commonly regarded as one of the best music videos of all time and a milestone in computer animation . The subject of much analysis and scrutiny , it was on permanent display at the Museum of Modern Art in New York City and has been included in various art exhibitions . Bj√∂rk has performed \`\` All Is Full of Love '' in five of her tours , with the most recent being the Vulnicura Tour . It is one of Bj√∂rk 's...\\n\\n- Autechre are an English electronic music duo consisting of Rob Brown and Sean Booth, both from Rochdale, Greater Manchester, England. Formed in 1987, they are one of the most popular acts signed to the Warp Records label, known for its pioneering electronic music and through which all of Autechre's albums have been released.\\n\\n- Scandinavian folklore or Nordic folklore is the folklore of Norway, Sweden, Finland, Denmark, Iceland and the Faroe Islands.\\n\\n- Norse mythology is the body of mythology of the North Germanic people stemming from Norse paganism and continuing after the Christianization of Scandinavia and into the Scandinavian folklore of the modern period. The northernmost extension of Germanic mythology, Norse mythology consists of tales of various deities, beings, and heroes derived from numerous sources from both before and after the pagan period, including medieval manuscripts, archaeological representations, and folk tradition.\\n\\n- Scotland (Scots: ) is a country that is part of the United Kingdom and covers the northern third of the island of Great Britain. It shares a border with England to the south, and is otherwise surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, with the North Sea to the east and the North Channel and Irish Sea to the south-west. In addition to the mainland, the country is made up of more than 790 islands, including the Northern Isles and the Hebrides.\\n\\n- Funkst√∂rung (German for \\"radio interference\\", sometimes also spelt Funkstorung) are an IDM musical duo hailing from Rosenheim, Germany; consisting of Christian de Luca (born 11 May 1974) and Michael Fakesch (born 8 March 1975). They are known for rhythmically complex but melody driven music, similar to the late 1990s work of Autechre, although their latest work incorporates elements of hip hop as well as pop music. They also do a lot of remix work, their portfolio including top-level artists such as Jean Michel Jarre, Wu-Tang Clan and Bj√∂rk. Three of the seven Funkst√∂rung albums are collection of remixes for other artists.\\n\\n- Howard Bernstein (born 18 April 1963, Glasgow, Scotland), professionally known as Howie B, is a musician and producer, who has worked with artists including: Bj√∂rk, U2, Robbie Robertson, Elisa, Tricky, Mukul Deora and The Gift.\\n\\n- The Republic of Iceland, \\"L√Ω√∞veldi√∞ √çsland\\" in Icelandic, is a Nordic island country in the North Atlantic Ocean. It has a population of and an area of , making it the most sparsely populated country in Europe. The capital and largest city is Reykjav√≠k. Reykjav√≠k and the surrounding areas in the southwest of the country are home to over two-thirds of the population. Iceland is volcanically and geologically active. The interior consists of a plateau characterised by sand and lava fields, mountains and glaciers, while many glacial rivers flow to the sea through the lowlands. Iceland is warmed by the Gulf Stream and has a temperate climate, despite a high latitude just outside the Arctic Circle. Its high latitude and marine influence still keeps summers chilly, with most of the archipelago having a tundra climate.\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the paragraphs above, decide what entity has the relation 'record label' with 'one little indian records'.","target":"all is full of love","rationale":"The rationale to choose \\"all is full of love\\" as the answer is that:\\n- All Is Full Of Love was released by Bjork on her album Homogenic in 1997. The label who released it? One Little Indian Records, which has been around since 1985 and helped define UK independent music with releases from acts like Flux Of Pink Indians, McCarthy and Autechre."},{"source":"Information:\\n\\n- The Northern Isles  is an archipelago comprising a chain of islands off the north coast of mainland Scotland. The climate is cool and temperate and much influenced by the surrounding seas. There are two main island groups: Shetland and Orkney. There are a total of 26 inhabited islands with landscapes of the fertile agricultural islands of Orkney contrasting with the more rugged Shetland islands to the north, where the economy is more dependent on fishing and the oil wealth of the surrounding seas. Both have a developing renewable energy industry. They also share a common Pictish and Norse history. Both island groups were absorbed into the Kingdom of Scotland in the 15th century and remained part of the country following the formation of the Kingdom of Great Britain in 1707, and later the United Kingdom after 1801. The islands played a significant naval role during the world wars of the 20th century.\\n\\n- The North Sea is a marginal sea of the Atlantic Ocean located between Great Britain, Scandinavia, Germany, the Netherlands, Belgium, and France. An epeiric (or \\"shelf\\") sea on the European continental shelf, it connects to the ocean through the English Channel in the south and the Norwegian Sea in the north. It is more than long and wide, with an area of around .\\n\\n- A registration county was, in Great Britain and Ireland, a statistical unit used for the registration of births, deaths and marriages and for the output of census information. In Scotland registration counties are used for land registration purposes.\\n\\n- England is a country that is part of the United Kingdom. It shares land borders with Scotland to the north and Wales to the west. The Irish Sea lies northwest of England and the Celtic Sea lies to the southwest. England is separated from continental Europe by the North Sea to the east and the English Channel to the south. The country covers five-eighths of the island of Great Britain (which lies in the North Atlantic) in its centre and south; and includes over 100 smaller islands such as the Isles of Scilly, and the Isle of Wight.\\n\\n- A country is a region that is identified as a distinct national entity in political geography. A country may be an independent sovereign state or one that is occupied by another state, as a non-sovereign or formerly sovereign political division, or a geographic region associated with sets of previously independent or differently associated people with distinct political characteristics. Regardless of the physical geography, in the modern internationally accepted legal definition as defined by the League of Nations in 1937 and reaffirmed by the United Nations in 1945, a resident of a country is subject to the independent exercise of legal jurisdiction.\\n\\n- Scotland (Scots: ) is a country that is part of the United Kingdom and covers the northern third of the island of Great Britain. It shares a border with England to the south, and is otherwise surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, with the North Sea to the east and the North Channel and Irish Sea to the south-west. In addition to the mainland, the country is made up of more than 790 islands, including the Northern Isles and the Hebrides.\\n\\n- Great Britain, also known as Britain¬†, is a large island in the north Atlantic Ocean off the northwest coast of continental Europe. With an area of , Great Britain is the largest European island and the ninth-largest in the world. In 2011 the island had a population of about 61¬†million people, making it the world's third-most populous island after Java in Indonesia and Honshu in Japan. The island of Ireland is situated to the west of it, and together these islands, along with over 1,000 smaller surrounding islands, comprise the British Isles archipelago.\\n\\n- The Hebrides (Scottish Gaelic: \\"Innse Gall\\"; Old Norse: \\"Su√∞reyjar\\") comprise a widespread and diverse archipelago off the west coast of mainland Scotland. There are two main groups: the Inner and Outer Hebrides. These islands have a long history of occupation dating back to the Mesolithic, and the culture of the residents has been affected by the successive influences of Celtic, Norse, and English-speaking peoples. This diversity is reflected in the names given to the islands, which are derived from the languages that have been spoken there in historic and perhaps prehistoric times.\\n\\n- Ben Lui (Scottish Gaelic: Beinn Laoigh) is a mountain in the southern Highlands of Scotland, at the head of Glen Fyne. It has five well-defined ridges radiating out from the summit. Four corries lie between the ridges; including Coire Gaothaich which lies on the northeast side of the mountain.\\n\\n- The United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland, commonly known as the United Kingdom (UK) or Britain, is a sovereign country in western Europe. Lying off the north-western coast of the European mainland, it includes the island of Great Britain (the name of which is also loosely applied to the whole country), the north-eastern part of the island of Ireland, and many smaller islands. Northern Ireland is the only part of the UK that shares a land border with another sovereign statethe Republic of Ireland. Apart from this land border, the UK is surrounded by the Atlantic Ocean, with the North Sea to its east, the English Channel to its south and the Celtic Sea to its south-south-west, giving it the 12th-longest coastline in the world. The Irish Sea lies between Great Britain and Ireland. With an area of , the UK is the 78th-largest sovereign state in the world and the 11th-largest in Europe. It is also the 21st-most populous country, with an estimated 65.1 million inhabitants. Together, this makes it the fourth most densely populated country in the European Union.\\n\\n- The Pass of Drumochter is the main mountain pass between the northern and southern central Scottish Highlands. The A9 road passes through here, as does the Highland Main Line, the railway between Inverness and the south of Scotland. The Sustrans National Cycle Route 7 between Glasgow and Inverness also runs through the pass.\\n\\n- Rannoch Moor (Scottish Gaelic: \\"M√≤inteach Raineach/Raithneach\\") is an expanse of around 50¬†square miles (130¬†km¬≤) of boggy moorland to the west of Loch Rannoch in Scotland, where it extends from and into westerly Perth and Kinross, northerly Lochaber (in Highland), and the area of Highland Scotland toward its south-west, northern Argyll and Bute. Rannoch Moor is designated a Site of Special Scientific Interest (SSSI) and a Special Area of Conservation.\\n\\n- The Irish Sea (, , , Ulster-Scots: \\"Airish Sea\\"), separates the islands of Ireland and Great Britain. It is connected to the Celtic Sea in the south by St George's Channel, and to the Inner Seas off the West Coast of Scotland in the north by the North Channel. Anglesey is the largest island within the Irish Sea, followed by the Isle of Man. The sea is occasionally, but rarely, referred to as the Manx Sea.\\n\\n- The Atlantic Ocean is the second largest of the world's oceans with a total area of about . It covers approximately 20 percent of the Earth's surface and about 29 percent of its water surface area. It separates the \\"Old World\\" from the \\"New World\\".\\n\\n- Perthshire, officially the County of Perth, is a registration county in central Scotland. It extends from Strathmore in the east, to the Pass of Drumochter in the north, Rannoch Moor and Ben Lui in the west, and Aberfoyle in the south. It was a local government county from 1890 to 1930.\\n\\n- Grandtully ( pronounced as \`\` Grantly '' and sometimes also spelt \`\` Grantully '' ) is a small village in Perthshire , Scotland . It is situated close to the River Tay , about 3 miles from Pitlochry . It has a population of approximately 750 inhabitants .\\n\\n\\n\\nGiven the information above, choose from the list below the object entity that exhibits the relation 'located in the administrative territorial entity' with the subject 'grandtully'.\\n\\nChoices:\\n- atlantic ocean\\n - belgium\\n - earth\\n - east\\n - england\\n - france\\n - germany\\n - indonesia\\n - inverness\\n - ireland\\n - isle of man\\n - kingdom of great britain\\n - mainland\\n - mountain\\n - naval\\n - netherlands\\n - north\\n - northern\\n - northwest\\n - of\\n - orkney\\n - outer hebrides\\n - perth\\n - perth and kinross\\n - perthshire\\n - scandinavia\\n - scotland\\n - scottish highlands\\n - shetland\\n - south\\n - ulster\\n - union\\n - united kingdom\\n - wales\\n - west","target":"perth and kinross","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"perth and kinross\\"."},{"source":"Falsely accused: Sunil Tripathi, 22, was wrongly fingered as the Boston marathon bomber on Reddit A Rhode Island family is anxiously awaiting news from authorities on whether the body they pulled from Providence River on Tuesday evening is their son, missing Brown student Sunil Tripathi. Police found the body around 6 p.m. and said they think it is 'very possible' that it is Tripathi, who was wrongly accused of being one of the Boston Marathon bombers. Tripathi, 22, has been missing since the middle of March. Authorities are hoping to reveal the identity of the body today, but police lieutenant Joseph Donnelly told The Boston Globe that 'it's very, very possible' that it is Tripathi.\\n@highlight\\n'Body of Sunil Tripathi' discovered in the Providence River in Boston\\n@highlight\\nBrown University student, 22, has been missing since middle of March\\n@highlight\\nWas wrongly identified on social media as a suspect in terror killings \\nHe announced his departure from the site as part of a Reddit 'AMA', which stands for @placeholder. \\nWhat could the \\"@placeholder\\" be? Boston, Boston Marathon, Boston marathon, Brown, Brown University, Providence River, Reddit, Rhode Island, Sunil Tripathi, Tripathi?","target":"Reddit","rationale":"\`@placeholder' is used in the context to denote a missing word that needs to be filled.\\nThe sentence refers to an event related exclusively on Reddit, so it could not be Boston or Rhode Island.\\nTripathi had nothing directly related with The Brown University and Providence River other than being a student there and his body found respectively; therefore they are unlikely candidates as well. \\nSunil Tripathi was wrongly identified by social media users only after he went missing; hence this cannot be the answer either. In fact, people were accused of having falsely fingered him if they pointed out his name anywhere before the official suspects were revealed - according to some sources at least (see link below)."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an utterance, which is a part of a conversation between a user and an agent. Your job is to detect the speaker. The user usually commands the agent to schedule events, retrieve event information, and check the schedule. While the agent's response is an answer to the user's questions or follow-up questions on the user's command. Answer with \\"User\\" or \\"Agent\\".\\n\\nChange the name to \\"Budget Meeting\\"","target":"user","rationale":"The given utterance is in the form of an active command, which is usually a part of the user's conversation. Therefore, the correct classification here will be \\"user\\"."},{"source":"You are given a mathematical question described with a circumscribed mathematical vocabulary. Questions in this task usually contain some variables (e.g. X, Y), equations (e.g. X+Y=3) and some relationships (X is greater than Y). Often you need to find the value of the variable using equations and relationships. You are also given 4 or 5 answer options (associated with \\"A\\", \\"B\\", \\"C\\", \\"D\\", \\"E\\"). Do not generate anything else apart from one of the following characters: 'A', 'B, 'C', 'D', 'E'. LaTeX mathematical format (the standard way to express mathematical expressions in the typesetting software known as LaTeX) is used to express equations. Each question is solvable with high school math knowledge. Give only one answer for each question.\\n\\nIf x is directly proportional to \\\\(\\\\sqrt { y } \\\\), then y is inversely proportional to\\n(A)\\\\(x^2\\\\) (B)\\\\(\\\\sqrt { x } \\\\) (C)\\\\(\\\\frac { 1 } { \\\\sqrt { x } } \\\\) (D)\\\\(\\\\frac { 1 } { x } \\\\) (E)\\\\(\\\\frac { 1 } { x^2 } \\\\)","target":"E","rationale":"If \\\\(x\\\\propto \\\\sqrt { y } \\\\), then there is some constant \\\\(k\\\\) such that\\n\\\\(x = k\\\\sqrt { y } .\\\\)\\nThen, dividing both sides by \\\\(\\\\sqrt { y } \\\\), we get\\n\\\\(\\\\frac { x }{ \\\\sqrt { y }  } =k.\\\\)\\nThis means that \\\\(\\\\frac{1}{\\\\sqrt{y}}\\\\) is proportional to \\\\(\\\\frac{1}{x}\\\\). It follows that \\\\(y\\\\) is inversely proportional to \\\\(x^2.\\\\) Thus, the answer is (E)\\\\(\\\\frac{1}{x^2}\\\\)."},{"source":"Choose your answer: Is \\"Melting of floating ice shelves (ice that originated on the land) does not in itself contribute much to sea-level rise (since the ice displaces only its own mass of water).\\" a good answer to the question \\"Along what area has there been more collapsing ice shelves?\\"\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The answer is too general and does not help us determine which area has had more collapsing ice shelves. We would need to know specific information about the number of ice shelves that have collapsed in each location along with their size, density etc., before we can accurately assess whether one area is better than another."},{"source":"In this task, you need to replace a letter in the sentence with another given letter.\\n\\nSentence: 'a man is holding a tennis racket, and making a peace sign'. Replace the letter 'm' with 'g' in the sentence.","target":"a gan is holding a tennis racket, and gaking a peace sign","rationale":"In the sentence 'a man is holding a tennis racket, and making a peace sign', we need to replace the letter 'm' with 'g'. The resulting sentence will be \\"a gan is holding a tennis racket, and gaking a peace sign\\"."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a claim and a perspective. You should determine whether that perspective supports or undermines the claim. If the perspective could possibly convince someone with different view, it is supporting, otherwise it is undermining.\\n\\nclaim: Public high school students in the United States ought not be required to pass standardized exit exams to graduate.\\n perspective: Standardized tests result in teachers ‚Äúteaching the test‚Äù","target":"support","rationale":"The perspective given in the passage is that standardized tests result in teachers teaching to the test, which means that students are not learning individualized content. This perspective lends support to the claim that high schools students should not be required to pass standardized exit exams because it suggests that those tests do not adequately assess what students have learned in school. Therefore, the answer is \\"support\\"."},{"source":"The task is to generate text based off of an event. For the given event, there will be a person who does the action in the event (usually PersonX). Your task is to write that persons intent behind doing the event, i.e. why did the person do that action.\\n\\nPersonX thanks PersonY's profusely","target":"to express gratitude","rationale":"The event details that PersonX is thanking PersonY profusely. This indicates that the person behind this action is seeking to express gratitude."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence and question which can be answered using the sentence. Your task is to answer the question using the information from the sentence. The answer to the question is unique and it is a continuous text span from the sentence.\\n\\nSentence: The State Chancellory prepared a draft , which was discussed during five sessions of the Council of Ministers , where alterations were made to further strengthen the emperor 's prerogatives at the expense of the new parliament . \\n Question: what was  discussed?","target":"a draft","rationale":"The answer to the question is the text span a draft."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question-answer pair.\\nQuestion: \\"What is the significance of Good Friday??\\";  Answer: \\"The holiday is observed during Holy Week as part of the Paschal Triduum on the Friday preceding Easter Sunday , and may coincide with the Jewish observance of Passover .\\"? Topic:","target":"Good Friday","rationale":"The answer is Good Friday because the question was about what are the significance of this holiday. The provided response discusses why it's significant and when its observed as a part of other Christian holidays (Easter Sunday)."},{"source":"Please answer this question: who played george kirk in the star trek movie?","target":"Hemsworth","rationale":"Chris Hemsworth is the actor who played George Kirk in Star Trek"},{"source":"Given a prompt and two completions from a language model, select the completion that is the least toxic with respect to continuing the prompt. Toxicity is defined as a rude, disrespectful, or unreasonable statement that is likely to make you leave a discussion. Generate either Completion A or Completion B.\\n\\nPrompt: I just saw an Andre Williams highlight from a different game. How is \\nCompletion A: that not good? And he's on his way to scoring some points, what's up? You know that, right? That's Andre Williams.\\" \\nCompletion B: he doing from here","target":"Completion B","rationale":"Completion A is the more toxic choice because it contains the words \\"Andre Williams.\\" and \\"you\\" which explicitly target another user in a rude and disrespectful manner. Completion B should be chosen as it has no such targetted toxicity."},{"source":"In this task, you need to count the number of words in a sentence that start with the given letter. Answer with numbers and not words.\\n\\nSentence: 'man about to throw a forehand frisbee in game'. How many words start with the letter 'm' in the sentence.","target":"1","rationale":"The sentence 'man about to throw a forehand frisbee in game' contains only one word starting with the letter 'm', which is 'man'. The answer is 1."},{"source":"Problem: Solve 33*g = 15*g for g.\\nAnd the answer is...","target":"0","rationale":"We need to isolate the variable g on one side of the equation.\\n\\n[STEP 1] 33*g - 15*g = 0\\n[STEP 2] 18*g = 0\\n[STEP 3] g =  0"},{"source":"Read this article and answer this question On 28 March 1193 Richard was brought to Speyer and handed over to Henry VI, Holy Roman Emperor, who imprisoned him in Trifels Castle. Henry VI was aggrieved by the support the Plantagenets had given to the family of Henry the Lion and by Richard's recognition of Tancred in Sicily. Henry VI needed money to raise an army and assert his rights over southern Italy and continued to hold Richard for ransom.  In response, Pope Celestine III excommunicated Henry VI, as he had Duke Leopold, for the continued wrongful imprisonment of Richard. Richard famously refused to show deference to the emperor and declared to him, \\"I am born of a rank which recognises no superior but God\\". Despite his complaints, the conditions of his captivity were not severe. The emperor demanded that 150,000 marks  be delivered to him before he would release the king, the same amount raised by the Saladin tithe only a few years earlier, and 2-3 times the annual income for the English Crown under Richard. Richard's mother, Eleanor of Aquitaine, worked to raise the ransom. Both clergy and laymen were taxed for a quarter of the value of their property, the gold and silver treasures of the churches were confiscated, and money was raised from the scutage and the carucage taxes. At the same time, John, Richard's brother, and King Philip of France offered 80,000 marks for the Emperor to hold Richard prisoner until Michaelmas 1194. The emperor turned down the offer. The money to rescue the King was transferred to Germany by the emperor's ambassadors, but \\"at the king's peril\\" , and finally, on 4 February 1194 Richard was released. Philip sent a message to John: \\"Look to yourself; the devil is loose\\".\\nWho demanded?","target":"emperor","rationale":"In order to find out who demanded, we need to check the following sentence: \\"The emperor demanded that 150,000 marks  be delivered to him before he would release the king\\". Therefore we could conclude that it was the emperor who made this demand."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence with a missing word that can be an object, a person, and/or an action. Fill in the blank with a plausible word. Although each sentence has many correct answers, you only have to write one answer.\\n\\nPersonX recently lost ___","target":"ID","rationale":"PersonX recently lost the ID card. The reason is PersonX just lost anything and this could be a possible answer."},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: Which of these structures form when materials are deposited, buried, and cemented?\\nPossibilities:\\n- intrusive structures\\n- metamorphic rocks\\n- volcanic mountains\\n- sedimentary rocks","target":"sedimentary rocks","rationale":"The process of sedimentary rocks forming is described as: sediments are deposited, buried and cemented (over time).\\nIntrusive structures form when magma cools underground. Metamorphic rocks form by other rock types being heated or squeezed over long periods of time. Volcanic mountains can be formed by the eruption of lava or through erosion from ice age glaciers."},{"source":"Based on the premise \\"Lord Charlemont's marine villa, built in 1762 1777, is one of Ireland's finest Neoclassical buildings, and certainly one of the most intriguing.\\", can we conclude the hypothesis \\"Lord Charlemont's marine villa is not highly regarded in any capacity.\\" is true (see options)?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- it is not possible to tell\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The premise states that the marine villa is \\"one of Ireland's finest Neoclassical buildings\\", meaning it is highly regarded, which directly contradicts the hypothesis. Therefore, we cannot conclude the hypothesis to be true and so our answer should be \\"no\\"."},{"source":"I am hesitating between 4 options to answer the following question, which option should I choose?\\nQuestion: Stars are often classified by their apparent brightness in the nighttime sky. Stars can also be classified in many other ways. Which of these is least useful in classifying stars?\\nPossibilities:\\n- visible color\\n- composition\\n- surface texture\\n- temperature","target":"surface texture","rationale":"The most useful way to classify stars is by temperature, followed by composition, then visible color. \\nA star's surface texture (for example: whether it has sunspots) doesn't tell us much about the star itself or how it compares with other stars in terms of its size and brightness. Therefore, \\"surface texture\\" is least useful for classifying stars."},{"source":"Text: The Vampire Diaries (season 8) -- The Vampire Diaries, an American supernatural drama, was renewed for an eighth season by The CW on March 11, 2016. On July 23, 2016, the CW announced that the upcoming season would be the series' last and would consist of 16 episodes. The season premiered on October 21, 2016 and concluded on March 10, 2017.\\n\\nAnswer the following yes/no question: is there a season 8 for vampire diaries? Yes or no?","target":"Yes","rationale":"Yes. The Vampire Diaries was renewed for an eighth season by the CW on March 11, 2016 and it premiered October 21st, which is in Season 8. There were 16 episodes total for this last season of Vampire Diaries."},{"source":"Write the conversation response. Hello Sally. I think I want to get some movie tickets to go see Dumbo or Pet Cemetary.\\nOk. What theater are you wanting to go to?\\nI think we are going to go to the AMC 30 in Mesquite, TX.\\nOk which one do you want me to get? Pet Cemetery or Dumbo?\\nLets do Dumbo.\\nOk. What time do you want to go see the movie?\\nHow about the 10:20PM show.\\nDo you want to do the 3D theater Experience?\\nYes I do. Please make sure it is in one of the 3D theaters.\\nOkay. Actually it looks like Dumbo is not showing in the 3D theater tonight.\\nOkay, how about Pet Cemetery then.\\nOkay. What time would you like to see that one?\\nHow about the 10:00PM show.\\nOk do you want the 3D theater experience for that movie?\\nYes. Please make sure it is a 3D theater.\\nOh no, it looks like that one is not available in a 3D theater either.","target":"Well that stinks. Nevermind then, I think we will just do something else tonight.","rationale":"The answer is \\"Well that stinks. Nevermind then, I think we will just do something else tonight.\\" because the system tells the person that neither of the movies they want to see in a 3D theater are showing at a 3D theater. Therefore, there are no options for them to go see one of those two movies in a 3D theater."},{"source":"Here's a problem to solve: Which living organism makes its own food using sunlight?\\n\\nAmong the 4 following options, which is the correct answer?\\n\\n- A: lizard\\n \\n- B: tree\\n \\n- C: deer\\n \\n- D: hawk","target":"B","rationale":"Living organisms that can make their own food using sunlight are called \\"autotrophs\\". \\nThey get all the energy they need from photosynthesis, which converts light into chemical energy.  \\nExamples of autotrophs include plants and algae. While some trees use chemosynthetic bacteria to produce sugars during photosynthesis (e.g., mangrove trees), most have chloroplasts in their cells where photosynthesis takes place just as it does for other green plants such as grasses and leafy vegetables etc... Therefore, option B is correct because a tree is an example of an organism that makes its own food using sunlight through photosynthesis.\\n\\n\\nOther options listed above do not fit the criteria described by the question: none of these animals or microorganisms directly process visible"},{"source":"Test sentence: \\"Doug blew it up.\\"\\nIs this test sentence a correct grammatical English sentence?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"This is an example of a sentence that linguists would consider acceptable grammatically."},{"source":"James is driving down the street in his town. For some reason today hes very curious about the things that he sees. He looks around as hes driving and the street lights catch his attention. He realizes that he's never seen someone changing the bulbs in a street light. He also wonders if its a film on the light that makes them have that color or something inside.\\n\\nGiven the street lights are sodium vapor lights, will these lights have a long life or short life?\\n\\nHint: A vapor light produces visible light by electroluminescence. The bulb contains a small amount of solid sodium or mercury as well as a mixture of neon and argon gases. When an electric current passes through the gases, it causes the solid sodium or mercury to change to a gas and emit visible light. Sodium vapor lights, like these streetlights, produce yellowish light. Mercury vapor lights produce bluish light. Vapor lights are very bright and energy efficient. The bulbs are also long lasting.","target":"long life","rationale":"The sodium vapor light is a type of streetlight. It works by using an electric current to produce visible light. The bulb contains solid sodium and two types of gases: neon and argon, which help the gas change from solid form into gas in order to emit yellowish colored lights. Sodium vapor lights are very bright because they can easily convert energy. They are also long lasting as they have efficient bulbs that do not wear out quickly making them ideal for streetlights since there would be less need to replace them often or climb up high places just so someone could change it manually\\nSo, given these factors, we conclude that the answer is \\"long life\\""},{"source":"The goal is to predict an English answer string for an input English question. \\nQuestion : Which animal is the symbol of the Argentinian rugby union team?\\nAnswer :","target":"Puma (disambiguation)","rationale":"The Puma (disambiguation) is the symbol of the Argentinian rugby union team. The animal's image can be seen on the jerseys, logos and equipment affiliated with this particular sport in Argentina.\\nTherefore, \\"Puma\\" should not be accepted as a valid answer because it does not clearly indicate that we are referring to the disambiguated version of pumas rather than other variants such as cougars or mountain lions which have been incorrectly assumed by some individuals to represent the national rugby team instead"},{"source":"Question: \\"What happens twice in 365 days?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"When not celebrating Mass but still serving a liturgical function, such as the semiannual Urbi et Orbi papal blessing, some Papal Masses and some events at Ecumenical Councils, cardinal deacons can be recognized by the dalmatics they would don with the simple white mitre (so called mitra simplex).\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"semiannual Urbi et Orbi papal blessing","rationale":"Incorrect. Correct answer is semiannual Urbi et Orbi papal blessing."},{"source":"Article: Immediately after the earthquake event, mobile and terrestrial telecommunications were cut to the affected and surrounding area, with all internet capabilities cut to the Sichuan area too. Elements of telecommunications were restored by the government piece by piece over the next number of months as the situation in the Sichuan province gradually improved. Eventually, a handful of major news and media websites were made accessible online in the region, albeit with dramatically pared back webpages.\\n\\nNow answer this question: What kinds of telecommunications were cut?","target":"mobile and terrestrial","rationale":"The paragraph describes the aftermath of an earthquake in Sichuan. Immediately after, mobile and terrestrial telecommunications were cut to the affected areas which means that no one could call or text anyone else via cell phones. Additionally, internet capabilities were also cut off so people couldn't go online at all either.\\nThis left a lot of people without any way to communicate with each other electronically as they usually would before this disaster occurred.\\nGiven these facts it is clear that what kinds of telecommunication were cut are \\"mobile\\" (cell phone) and \\"terrestrial\\" (landline)."},{"source":"You are given a conversation between two people. 'Person1:' and 'Person2:' are used to separate their respective dialogues. You are required to assign a label 'formal' if there is an absence of emotion and a presence of questions anywhere within the conversation. If such pattern is not found assign the label 'informal'.\\n\\n Person1:       I really like the book you lent me the other day .  \\n Person2:I'm glad you like it .  \\n Person1:        And thank you very much for letting me keep it so long .  \\n Person2:Not at all .  \\n Person1:        Everyone in our class enjoyed it too.It ' s very interesting .  \\n Person2:Oh , I'm glad .  \\n Person1:        Would you mind me keeping it for another three days ?  \\n Person2:No problem .","target":"informal","rationale":"While there is an exchange of questions and answers, there is also an evident presence of emotion which makes the overall conversation informal."},{"source":"Background: Desertification is a type of land degradation in which a relatively dry area of land becomes a desert, typically losing its bodies of water as well as vegetation and wildlife.[2] It is caused by a variety of factors, such as through climate change (particularly the current global warming)[3] and through the overexploitation of soil through human activity.[4] When deserts appear automatically over the natural course of a planet's life cycle, then it can be called a natural phenomenon; however, when deserts emerge due to the rampant and unchecked depletion of nutrients in soil that are essential for it to remain arable, then a virtual \\"soil death\\" can be spoken of,[5] which traces its cause back to human overexploitation. Desertification is a significant global ecological and environmental problem with far reaching consequences on socio-economic and political conditions.[6]\\n\\nParagraph: People in Iran used extensive grazing, fell most of their trees so they have lots of problems with desertification. Iraq took a more mindful approach to land use, they preserved native species, planted trees and didn't overgraze the land.\\n\\nGiven the paragraph above, please answer correctly the following question: Which country was more exposed to land degradation?","target":"Iran","rationale":"The paragraph describes two countries that were exposed to land degradation. The first country, Iran, overgrazed the land and cut down a lot of trees. This resulted in desertification because there wasn't enough vegetation or wildlife left on the earth for it to be arable.\\nIn contrast, Iraq took more mindful approach towards land use as they preserved native species and planted new tree saplings instead of cutting them all down like Iran did with their trees. Overall this helped prevent Iraqi lands from being degraded as badly compared to Iranian lands due to excessive grazing practices by Iranians people which led directly into severe destruction of entire ecosystem . So answer is \\"Iran\\"."},{"source":"What is the following passage about?\\nHindu philosophy also includes several sub-schools of theistic philosophies that integrate ideas from two or more of the six orthodox philosophies, such as the realism of the NyƒÅya, the naturalism of the Vai≈õe·π£ika, the dualism of the SƒÅ·πÖkhya, the monism and knowledge of Self as essential to liberation of Advaita, the self-discipline of yoga and the asceticism and elements of theistic ideas. Examples of such schools include PƒÅ≈õupata ≈öaiva, ≈öaiva siddhƒÅnta, Pratyabhij√±a, Rase≈õvara and Vai·π£·πáava. Some sub-schools share Tantric ideas with those found in some Buddhist traditions. The ideas of these sub-schools are found in the Puranas and ƒÄgamas.","target":"Hindu philosophy","rationale":"The context describes the main ideas of Hindu philosophy and its sub-schools, including their beliefs in deities, asceticism and self-discipline. \\nTherefore, it is clear that this passage is about: \\"Hindu philosophy\\"."},{"source":"We would like you to classify each of the following sets of argument pairs (discussing Gay Marriage)  into either SIMILAR or NOT SIMILAR. A pair of arguments is considered SIMILAR if the arguments are about the same FACET (making the same argument), and is considered NOT SIMILAR if they do not have the same FACET. A FACET is a low level issue that often reoccurs in many arguments in support of the author's stance or in attacking the other author's position.\\n\\nSent1: Gays don't call their unions marriage, we have commitment ceremonies not weddings.\\n Sent2: We don't necessarily have a right to officially recognized gay marriage, but we have every right to tell the government if we want it or not.","target":"Not similar","rationale":"The first sentence expresses a belief that same-sex couples do not use the term \\"marriage\\" to describe their unions and also asserts that they perform commitment ceremonies, which are similar to weddings. The second sentence states that members of the gay community should have the right to determine whether or not marriage is officially recognized for same-sex couples. These two sentences do not share any common facets, so the answer is Not similar."},{"source":"Well not all the time , but sometimes it really sucks . Remember when I said I had a bad feeling . Well I was hiding in my cave today and did n't get the news about the big bail out till about 5 pm .\\nAccording to the above context, choose the best option to answer the following question.\\nQuestion: Why would the person be isolating from others ?\\nOptions:\\nA. They are scared about a relationship .\\nB. None of the above choices .\\nC. They are scared about a loved one .\\nD. They are scared about money .","target":"D","rationale":"In the context, it is revealed that the person isolating themselves from others has a bad feeling about money. The main reason they are hiding in their cave is to avoid hearing any news related to bailouts and financial struggles. Based on this information, we can infer that the person's isolation and fear of financial problems goes beyond just not wanting to hear bad news; they may be worried or scared about losing some of their own personal wealth due to the economic crisis currently happening around them.\\nTherefore, option D is correct: \\"They are scared about money\\"."},{"source":"(CNN) -- \\"Hobbit\\" mania is in full swing in New Zealand this week, where all three of the Peter Jackson-directed movies based on the work of J.R.R. Tolkien were filmed. Wellington International Airport has unveiled a new installation featuring two realistic \\"great eagles\\" from the \\"The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug,\\" the second in the trilogy. The film's world premier will take place on December 2 in Los Angeles. Meanwhile, Air New Zealand is showing off a new livery featuring the title character on one of its planes. The airport's new sculptures were created by Wellington's Weta Workshop -- the same team that built props and designed physical effects for \\"The Hobbit\\" and \\"The Lord of the Rings\\" trilogies.\\n@highlight\\nWellington International Airport unveils sculpture of \\"great eagles\\" from \\"The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug\\"\\n@highlight\\nAir New Zealand unveils its own ode to the film -- a new livery featuring the dragon Smaug\\n@highlight\\nAll three films in the \\"Hobbit\\" trilogy were shot in New Zealand\\n\\"To see @placeholder fly off the big screen and into the skies like this is pretty exciting,\\" said director Peter Jackson in a statement.\\n\\nPick one option, \\"@placeholder\\" refers to:\\n- Air New Zealand\\n- CNN\\n- Desolation of Smaug\\n- Hobbit\\n- New Zealand\\n- Peter Jackson\\n- Smaug\\n- The Hobbit\\n- Wellington International Airport","target":"Smaug","rationale":"Smaug, the title character of \\"The Hobbit: The Desolation of Smaug\\", is an ode to the film."},{"source":"Determine if the sentence is true based on the text below. Choose from options.\\nA woman succeeds in climbing Everest solo.\\n\\nEverest Grand Circle Expedition, Nepal and Tibet. First circumambulation of Everest; trekking, skiing, and mountaineering. First American winter ascent of Pumori (elev. 23,422'). Immortalized in the book Everest Grand Circle. Ned Gillette, Jan Reynolds, Jim Bridwell, Steve McKinney, Craig Calonica and Rick Barker.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no","target":"no","rationale":"The passage does not mention about the women climbing Everest solo, so this sentence is wrong."},{"source":"In this task, you are given the abstract of a research paper. Your task is to generate a summary of this abstract. Your summary should not be very short, but it's better if it's not more than 30 words.\\n\\nWe improve the robustness of deep neural nets  to adversarial attacks by using an interpolating function as the output activation.    This data-dependent activation function remarkably improves both classification accuracy and stability to adversarial perturbations. Together with the total variation minimization of adversarial images and augmented training, under the strongest attack, we achieve up to 20.6%, 50.7%, and 68.7% accuracy improvement w.r.t.   the fast gradient sign method, iterative fast gradient sign method, and Carlini-WagnerL2attacks, respectively.   Our defense strategy is additive to many of the existing methods.   We give an intuitive explanation of our defense strategy via analyzing the geometry of the feature space. For reproducibility, the code will be available on GitHub.","target":"We proposal strategies for adversarial defense based on data dependent activation function, total variation minimization, and training data augmentation","rationale":"Here's a brief summary:\\\\nWe proposal strategies for adversarial defense based on data dependent activation function, total variation minimization, and training data augmentation."},{"source":"The Open Enrollment Program<br>Anita went to the local university and enrolled. She chose the open enrollment program. This way she didn't have to submit her grades from high school. Anita graduated college and then asked for a promotion at her job. Her boss said no since she did open enrollment not traditional school.\\nDoes this next sentence follow, given the preceding text?\\nAnita enrolled in an online university. \\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- Yes\\n- It's impossible to say\\n- No","target":"No","rationale":"The text states that Anita enrolled in the open enrollment program at a local university. An online school would be neither local nor an open enrolment, so the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Question with options: can we draw the following hypothesis from the context? \\n\\nContext:\\n\\nA month after Gov. David A. Paterson dropped his proposal for a soda tax, New York City's health commissioner has written an article advocating \\"hefty\\" taxes on sodas and sports drinks containing sugar. Such a tax, the article said, could be the biggest boon to public health since tobacco taxes. The commissioner, Dr. Thomas R. Frieden, and Kelly D. Brownell of Yale University, his co-author, argue in the New England Journal of Medicine that a tax of a penny per ounce could reduce consumption by more than 10 percent and raise $1.2 billion a year in New York State alone.\\n\\nHypothesis: Michael Bloomberg is the mayor of New York.\\nOPTIONS:\\n- yes\\n- no\\nA:","target":"no","rationale":"The passage talks about a soda tax proposal and its effect on the health of New Yorkers. The premise does not mention anything about Michael Bloomberg or who is in charge as mayor at this time, so we are unable to determine whether he was/is still mayor or not. Hence, it's impossible to draw that conclusion from the context provided and answer \\"no\\""},{"source":"In this task, you are given a sentence from the research paper and the category to which it belongs. Your task is to classify whether the given category is correct or not by providing \\"True\\" and \\"False\\", respectively. Here are the definitions for the categories: Background (Why is this problem important? What relevant works have been created before? What is still missing in the previous works? What are the high-level research questions? How might this help other research or researchers?), Purpose (What specific things do the researchers want to do? What specific knowledge do the researchers want to gain? What specific hypothesis do the researchers want to test?), Method (How did the researchers do the work or find what they sought? What are the procedures and steps of the research?), or Finding (What did the researchers find out? Did the proposed methods work? Did the thing behave as the researchers expected?). \\",\\n\\nSentence: The goal was to estimate net income and losses ( nationally , and by hospital type ) of a response of filling unused hospital bed capacity proportionately and postponing elective admissions ( a \`\` passive '' supply response ). \\n Section: purpose","target":"True","rationale":"The sentence describes the goal of the study (\\"The goal was to estimate net income and losses ( nationally , and by hospital type ) of a response of filling unused hospital bed capacity proportionately and postponing elective admissions ( a \`\` passive '' supply response ).\\"). The purpose can be summed up as: \\"How do we estimate net income and losses nationally, along with an analysis of how different types of hospitals respond to filling unused bed capacity proportionately, based on postponing elective admissions?\\". Therefore, the correct category for this sentence is \\"Purpose\\". Hence, the answer is True."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a date in \\"dd/mm/yyyy\\" format. You need to check if the date is valid or not. Return 1 if it is valid, else return 0. A date is valid if the components day(\\"dd\\"), month(\\"mm\\") and year(\\"yyyy\\") are all valid individually. A day(dd) is valid if it: a) lies between 1 and 31 for the months of January, March, May, July, August, October, December, b) lies between 1 and 28 for February on non-leap years and between 1-29 on leap years, c) lies between 1-30 for all other months. A month(mm) is valid if it lies in the range from 1 to 12 as there are 12 months in a year. A year is always valid if it is expressed in the form of \\"yyyy\\".\\n\\n31/03/1102","target":"1","rationale":"The given date \\"31/03/1102\\" is a valid date. The day(dd) component is 31 which lies between 1 and 31 for the month of March. The month(mm) component is 3 which lies in the range from 1 to 12 as there are 12 months in a year. The year(yyyy) component 1102 has exactly 4 digits so it is always valid. Therefore, the output should be 1.\\""},{"source":"Then when we got back to the house , I hung out with Harrison , Ian , and Jake , and Kaitlin for a while until she decided to leave . And I had one of the best moments of all of college during this time , in which I surprised Harrison with my intelligence . Harrison is the kind of guy who likes to think that he is way smarter and intellectual than everyone else is , and is pretty arrogant - and I am pretty sure he will fully acknowledge this .\\nWhat 's a possible reason the writer hung out with these people at the house ?\\nPick the best answer from the following options:\\n- Because the writer wanted to surprise Harrison with their intelligence .\\n - Because they enjoy each other 's company .\\n - Because the writer was having one of their best moments of college .\\n - None of the above choices .","target":"Because they enjoy each other 's company .","rationale":"The question asks for a possible reason the writer hung out with these people at the house. The context suggests that all of these people are friends, and they often spend time together. \\nAlthough it is not explicitly stated in the text, we can infer from this information that hanging out with them was enjoyable to the writer, which would be a reasonable explanation why they continued to hang out with their friends after arriving home from work or class.\\nSo the answer is Because they enjoy each other 's company ."},{"source":"In this task, you're given an open-domain question. Your task is to provide an answer to the given question. There is only one unique answer for each question. Your answer should be short, and refer to an entity, date, number, etc. Do not put your answer in the context of a sentence.\\n\\nWhen does kyle richards american woman come out?","target":"June 7, 2018","rationale":"The premiere date for the show is June 7, 2018. This is an entity so it should be a short answer."},{"source":"You will be given a topic and an argument. Decide the argument's stance towards that topic. The argument's stance is in favor or against the topic. If the argument supports that topic, answer with \\"in favor\\"; otherwise, if the argument opposes the topic, answer with \\"against\\".\\n\\ntopic: DC handgun ban\\nargument: 2nd amendment combines right to militia and individual arms","target":"against","rationale":"The argument states that the 2nd amendment combines the right to militia and individual arms. This implies that the author believes both these rights should be applied together, which is against the DC handgun ban, which only allows individuals to own handguns if they are part of a government-authorized militia or security organization. Therefore, the argument is \\"against\\" DC handgun ban."},{"source":"Determine the topic of the question.\\nQuestion: \\"what is considered to be a disasters?\\"\\nTopic:","target":"Disaster","rationale":"The question is about a disaster.\\nTherefore, the topic should be \\"Disaster\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you're given the middle and ending of a three-part story. Your job is to complete the short story by writing a probable beginning of the story. Generated sentences must be short, have fewer than 10 words, and be simple as if narrating to a child. Avoid using any irrelevant extra information when creating the beginning, and use names (e.g. Jack, Barbara,...) instead of pronouns (e.g. he / she) wherever possible.\\n\\nMiddle: Daisy did an awful job. Ending: Annoyed, she put everything away and left the kitchen.","target":"Daisy decided that she wanted to make some cookies","rationale":"This is a simple story about making cookies. In the middle of the story, Daisy did an awful job, and in the ending she put everything away and left. Therefore, we can infer that Daisy did not like making cookies since she wanted to leave after doing an awful job. Thus, the most probable beginning would be \\"Daisy decided that she wanted to make some cookies.\\""},{"source":"Article: Captain John Charles Marshall and Thomas Gilbert visited the islands in 1788. The islands were named for Marshall on Western charts, although the natives have historically named their home \\"jolet jen Anij\\" (Gifts from God). Around 1820, Russian explorer Adam Johann von Krusenstern and the French explorer Louis Isidore Duperrey named the islands after John Marshall, and drew maps of the islands. The designation was repeated later on British maps.[citation needed] In 1824 the crew of the American whaler Globe mutinied and some of the crew put ashore on Mulgrave Island. One year later, the American schooner Dolphin arrived and picked up two boys, the last survivors of a massacre by the natives due to their brutal treatment of the women.:2\\n\\nNow answer this question: Who notably accompanied John Charles Marshall to the Marshall Islands?","target":"Thomas Gilbert","rationale":"From the given context, it is clear that Thomas Gilbert accompanied John Charles Marshall to the Marshall Islands."},{"source":"Given a story, answer the question about the story. The question is the last sentence in the input. The story has one of the three following scenarios: (1) when the individual's belief matches reality, (2) when the individual's belief does not match reality, (3) is when an individual has a false belief about another individual's beliefs. The question will ask about the location of an object in the story with respect to either none or one of the three scenarios.\\n\\nLiam entered the attic. Jayden entered the attic. The pear is in the blue_cupboard. Jayden exited the attic. Liam moved the pear to the green_bucket. Where was the pear at the beginning?","target":"blue_cupboard","rationale":"The pear was in the blue_cupboard at the beginning of the story and while Jayden was in the attic."},{"source":"By Ellie Zolfagharifard If you've ever wanted to soar over Earth on the world's largest parachute, now is your chance ‚Äì and you don't even have to leave your desk. This dizzying footage of Nasa's 'flying saucer' will take you 180,000ft (35 miles) into Earth's atmosphere as it travels four times faster than the speed of sound. The saucer, dubbed the Low Density Supersonic Decelerator (LDSD), is designed to someday deliver large payloads, such as vehicles, to Mars. Scroll down for video The footage shows the June test conducted over Hawaii, which although successful, didn't go quite to plan with the parachute failing to unfurl properly.\\n@highlight\\nFootage shows a June test of LDSD conducted over Hawaii, which although successful, didn't go quite to plan\\n@highlight\\nLow Density Supersonic Decelerator (LDSD) is designed to deliver large payloads, such as vehicles, to Mars\\n@highlight\\nIt was carrying the world's largest parachute, known as the Supersonic Disksail, which failed to unfurl properly\\n@highlight\\n'As far as I am concerned, whenever you get to ride shotgun on a rocket-powered flying saucer, it is a good day,' said Ian Clark, principal investigator for LDSD \\nAs this point the @placeholder inflated around a larger saucer-shaped object, bringing it safely back to land in open water. \\nHere, the placeholder refers to","target":"LDSD","rationale":"At the end of July, 2014 , Nasa released footage from its latest test flight to take a flying saucer 180,000ft into Earth's atmosphere. The LDSD (Low Density Supersonic Decelerator) project is designed to one day deliver large payloads - such as manned vehicles or Mars rovers - onto the surface of other planets. \\nAs this point the LDSD inflated around a larger saucer-shaped object, bringing it safely back to land in open water."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nwash : rag. vacuum : ?","target":"vacuum","rationale":"Washing something is a task that is performed with a rag, and vacuuming something is a task that can be performed with a vacuum."},{"source":"A Royal Charter in 1952 upgraded University College at Highfield to the University of Southampton. Southampton acquired city status, becoming the City of Southampton in 1964.\\nWhat document declared the upgrade of University College at Highfield?","target":"Royal Charter","rationale":"The context explicitly states that the document is a Royal Charter and it clearly mentions what actions were performed due to this document."},{"source":"Math Problem\\nSolve -m = 5*m + 2*m for m.","target":"0","rationale":"-m = 5*m + 2*m\\n\\n[STEP 1] -4*m = 0\\n[STEP 2] m = 0"},{"source":"M: And this sports shirt too, all cleaned and ironed. When will they be ready?\\n\\nW: Is Sunday morning soon enough?\\n\\nM: Well, yes, but I need that coat earlier.\\n\\nW: We do have a special quick service at an extra charge of 15%.\\n\\nM: When will it be ready?\\n\\nW: Tomorrow afternoon. Any time after four o'clock.\\n\\nM: How late are you open?\\n\\nW: Until 9 o'clock in the evening, sir.\\n\\nM: Fine. That leaves me plenty of time to pick it up after work.\\n\\nW: OK. You can come for the coat any time after 4 o, clock.\\n\\nM: Good. Thank you.\\n\\nWhat was said before this conversation?","target":"W: Let's see. That's two pairs of trousers, one lady's dress and one man's overcoat.","rationale":"Here's the rationale: \\"W: Let's see. That's two pairs of trousers, one lady's dress and one man's overcoat.\\""},{"source":"In this task you are given an anecdote. You must find out whether the anecdote is something the author has done or is considering doing. Label the instances as \\"HISTORICAL\\" when the author has already done something and label them as \\"HYPOTHETICAL\\" when the author is considering doing something in the future.\\n\\nTo preface, this was after church (I‚Äôm not Christian but act like I am) and just my mother and I were on our way to lunch with the family. \\n\\nThe topic goes to this 12 year old girl at church. My mother just goes on an on saying that she is ugly and has a weird face, for about two or three minutes. I 17M, finally have had enough and tell her that judging a 12 year old kid about their looks is rude and something that should remain unsaid. Now, I will admit, that kid isn‚Äôt super good looking, but maybe I just think it doesn‚Äôt matter because I‚Äôm gay, but she is super nice usually. \\n\\nWell my mother got all upset at me and every time she said an opinion at lunch she would then say, ‚ÄúOh wait, ntaylor7746 said I‚Äôm not allowed to have an opinion.‚Äù Am I the asshole for calling her, a grown ass 44 year old woman, put for talking shit about a child?","target":"HISTORICAL","rationale":"The author uses the past tense to describe the events, which suggests that they have already occurred. This means that the anecdote is not hypothetical and should be labeled as \\"HISTORICAL\\"."},{"source":"Categorize the comment on the basis of insult. If the comment is insulting output Yes, otherwise output No.\\n\\nMaybe you'll feel better after reading the Haycox commentary in today's ADN. \\nI seem to recall Cruz suggesting that his company was headed south if SB21 didn't pass; it did pass and he went south nonetheless. \\nNow, with oil sands in Canada and fracking in the US in decline he's back in Alaska to advocate for using our dividend to fund tax credits.\\nIs Cruz in it for Alaskans or for himself is the real question you and Rick should be asking.","target":"No","rationale":"The comment criticizes the governor and oil companies for their decisions and actions, but does not contain any insulting language. Therefore, it can be classified as \\"No\\"."},{"source":"Question: \\"What trait did Chopin consider the most important when playing music?\\"\\n\\nContext: \\"In 1841, L√©on Escudier wrote of a recital given by Chopin that year, \\"One may say that Chopin is the creator of a school of piano and a school of composition. In truth, nothing equals the lightness, the sweetness with which the composer preludes on the piano; moreover nothing may be compared to his works full of originality, distinction and grace.\\" Chopin refused to conform to a standard method of playing and believed that there was no set technique for playing well. His style was based extensively on his use of very independent finger technique. In his Projet de m√©thode he wrote: \\"Everything is a matter of knowing good fingering ... we need no less to use the rest of the hand, the wrist, the forearm and the upper arm.\\" He further stated: \\"One needs only to study a certain position of the hand in relation to the keys to obtain with ease the most beautiful quality of sound, to know how to play short notes and long notes, and [to attain] unlimited dexterity.\\" The consequences of this approach to technique in Chopin's music include the frequent use of the entire range of the keyboard, passages in double octaves and other chord groupings, swiftly repeated notes, the use of grace notes, and the use of contrasting rhythms (four against three, for example) between the hands.\\"\\n\\nAnswer:","target":"dexterity","rationale":"Chopin‚Äôs style was based on his use of very independent finger technique. According to the context, Chopin believed that there is no set technique for playing well; he also wrote in Projet de m√©thode that ‚ÄúOne needs only to study a certain position of the hand in relation to the keys...to attain unlimited dexterity‚Äù (the key words are bolded). Therefore, it can be inferred that Chopin considered ‚Äòdexterity‚Äô as one of the most important traits when playing music."},{"source":"Found the following article online, use it to answer the question: What was the position held by the man who captured Lhasa in 1904?\\n\\nNathu La is located on the 563 km (350 mi) Old Silk Route, an offshoot of the historic Silk Road. The Old Silk Route connects Lhasa in Tibet to the plains of Bengal to the south. In 1815, trade volume increased after the British annexed territories belonging to the Sikkimese, Nepalese, and Bhutanese. The potential of Nathu La was realised in 1873, after the Darjeeling Deputy Commissioner published a report on the strategic importance of mountain passes between Sikkim and Tibet. In December 1893, the Sikkimese monarchy and Tibetan rulers signed an agreement to increase trade between the two nations. The agreement culminated in 1894 when the trade pass was opened.\\nNathu La played a vital role in the 1903‚Äì1904 British expedition to Tibet, which sought to prevent the Russian Empire from interfering in Tibetan affairs and thus gaining a foothold in the region. In 1904, Major Francis Younghusband, serving as the British Commissioner to Tibet, led a successful mission through Nathu La to capture Lhasa. This led to the setting up of trading posts at Gyantse and Gartok in Tibet, and gave control of the surrounding Chumbi Valley to the British. The following November, China and Great Britain ratified an agreement approving trade between Sikkim and Tibet.\\nIn 1947 and 1948, a popular vote for Sikkim to join newly independent India failed and Indian Prime Minister Jawaharlal Nehru agreed to a special protectorate status for Sikkim. Sikkim agreed to be a protectorate nation and Indian troops were allowed to man its borders, including Nathu La. During this period, more than 1,000 mules and 700 people were involved in cross-border trade through Nathu La. In 1949, when the Tibetan government expelled the Chinese living there, most of the displaced Chinese returned home through the Nathu La‚ÄìSikkim‚ÄìKolkata route.The current Dalai Lama, Tenzin Gyatso, used this pass to travel to India for the 2,500th birthday celebration of Gautama Buddha, which was held between November 1956 and February 1957. Later, on 1 September 1958, Nehru,...","target":"British Commissioner to Tibet","rationale":"In the article, it mentions \\"Major Francis Younghusband... led a successful mission through Nathu La to capture Lhasa\\". This suggests that Major Francis was in charge of this expedition. Later on, it states that \\"[this] led to setting up of trading posts at Gyantse and Gartok\\", which again implies Major Francis's involvement with these events. Finally, we see mention of him as the British Commissioner to Tibet in 1904 when China and Great Britain ratified an agreement approving trade between Sikkim and Tibet.\\nGiven all this evidence from the text about his status during this time period, we can conclude that he held the position of British Commissioner for Tibet around this time."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a string of characters. You should remove all vowels from the given string. Vowels are: i,e,a,u,o. The character 'y' or 'Y' does not count as a vowel.\\n\\nIuEAmJAOEq","target":"mJq","rationale":"The given string contains the vowels 'I', 'u', 'E', 'A', and 'O'. They should be removed according to the instructions. The resulting string after removing the vowels is mJq."},{"source":"A sunscreen with a higher SPF value protects the skin longer.\\n\\nHaving read the above passage, choose the right answer to the following question (choices are higher SPF or lower SPF ):\\n\\n\\nJimbo is going to the beach and he wants to ensure he has the lowest sun protection for his skin. Should he wear a sunscreen with a higher SPF or a lower SPF higher SPF or lower SPF?","target":"lower SPF","rationale":"The passage states that a sunscreen with a higher SPF value will protect the skin longer. This indicates that Jimbo should wear a lower SPF sunscreen if he wants to have low sun protection for his skin.\\nSo, the answer is \\"lower SPF\\"."},{"source":"Given news headlines, an edited word and funniness labels. The original sentence has word with the given format {word}. Create new headlines by replacing {word} in the original sentence with edit word. Your task is to generate answer \\"Yes\\" if an edited sentence matches funniness label, otherwise generate answer \\"No\\".  \\n\\nNews Headline: New study says House GOP healthcare bill would lead to the loss of almost 1 million jobs in 10 {years}  \\n Edit: Parsecs \\n Label: Funny","target":"Yes","rationale":"The word \\"years\\" is replaced with \\"parsecs\\", which does not make sense. The original sentence is about the loss of jobs, but the edited sentence refers to a unit of distance. So, the edited sentence is funny and should be labeled as Yes."},{"source":"Extract the answer to the question from the following context.\\nQuestion: Where does the judge preside?\\nContext: Burke took a leading role in the debate regarding the constitutional limits to the executive authority of the king. He argued strongly against unrestrained royal power and for the role of political parties in maintaining a principled opposition capable of preventing abuses, either by the monarch, or by specific factions within the government. His most important publication in this regard was his Thoughts on the Cause of the Present Discontents of 23 April 1770. Burke identified the \\"discontents\\" as stemming from the \\"secret influence\\" of a neo-Tory group he labelled as, the \\"king's friends\\", whose system \\"comprehending the exterior and interior administrations, is commonly called, in the technical language of the Court, Double Cabinet\\". Britain needed a party with \\"an unshaken adherence to principle, and attachment to connexion, against every allurement of interest\\". Party divisions \\"whether operating for good or evil, are things inseparable from free government\\".","target":"Court","rationale":"The context involves a judge presiding over the court.\\nSo, the answer is Court"},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions to the tools used to perform the action is given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". \\"A : B\\" relates action A to tool B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate tool for the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation.\\n\\nstir : spoon. hit : ?","target":"hammer","rationale":"To stir something, one could use a spoon. Similarly, to hit something, one could use a hammer."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list. A list contains several comma-separated items written within brackets. You need to return the count of all the numerical elements in the given list. Return 0 if no numerical element in the list.\\n\\n['X', 'r', 'N', 'L', '927', '9551', '5391', '127', 'f', '9569', 'L', 'Q', '1225', '1627']","target":"7","rationale":"Given the list ['X', 'r', 'N', 'L', '927', '9551'...], we need to find the number of numerical elements.\\\\n1. 927 is a numerical element.\\\\n2. 9551 is a numerical element.\\\\n3. 5391 is a numerical element.\\\\n4. 127 is a numerical element.\\\\n5, 9569 is a numerical element, but it consists of two numbers 9 and 569 and it should be counted as one, not two elements in this task..\\\\n6, 1225 is a numerical element (it also consists of two numbers), but it should be counted as one in this task..\\n7, 1627 ia alos considered as an integer and will be counted for the total number of integers"},{"source":"Use information from the paragraph to answer the question.\\n\\nParagraph :\\n\\nThe thinner the wire, the more resistance it offers.\\n\\nQuestion:\\n\\n\\nRobin is using aluminum foil to make small cylinders. A foil cylinder of diameter 1cm likely has greater or less resistance than a foil cylinder of diameter 10cm?","target":"greater","rationale":"The wire is made of the same material, aluminium foil. It's only that one cylinder has a diameter 10 times greater than the other. The resistance increases proportionally with increasing cross-sectional area for similar metals and alloys at constant temperature (ref: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Electrical_resistivity_and_conductivity#Resistivity)\\nAccording to Ohm‚Äôs Law, Resistance = Voltage / Current  A larger surface area means fewer electrons colliding per unit length in any given period of time as they travel through it because there are more possible paths available to them; this also implies lower collisions as well resulting into lesser resistive force opposing electron movement causing less current flow i.e., higher resistance when compared with smaller wires or cylinders having"},{"source":"Indicate the presence of numerical data in the abstract (whether numerical data plays a key role in medical records), solely using the information from the abstract.\\n\\nAbstract: Pyomyositis occurred in a man who had not been to the tropics. The condition is common in the tropics but most unusual in temperate climates and is nearly always caused by Staphylococcus aureus. Pyomyositis must be borne in mind in obscure cases of sepsis, as early recognition and treatment are essential to prevent a fatal outcome. \\nQuestion: Does the abstract contain any numerical data?","target":"No","rationale":"The abstract describes a case of pyomyositis in a man who had not been to the tropics. It provides information about the prevalence of the disease in temperate climates and what bacteria typically cause it. However, it does not include any numerical values or measurements that would indicate that numerical data plays a key role in medical records. So the answer is \\"No\\"."},{"source":"In this task, you are given inputs i, j, and A, where i and j are integers and A is a list. You need to find all elements of A from the ith element to the jth element, reverse the order in which they occur, and then concatenate them to output the resultant string. i and j will be non-negative, and will always have a value less than the length of A. i will always be less than j. Perform the operations in order, i.e., do not concatenate the elements and then reverse the string.\\n\\n4, 6, ['O', '2143', '9263', '8509', 'g', '8827', '6783', '1189']","target":"8827g8509","rationale":"Given the list ['O', '2143', '9263', '8509', 'g', '8827', '6783', 1189], we need to find the elements within the range 4 ~ 6.\\\\n1. The 4th element is g.\\\\n2. The 5th element is 8827.\\\\n3. The 6th element is 6783, which should be skipped since it's outside of the given range (4 ~ 6).\\\\n4. We need to reverse their order as follows: 8827g8509"},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of strings and you need to concatenate them.\\n\\n['q', 'god', 'N', 'O']","target":"qgodNO","rationale":"The given list is ['q', 'god', 'N', 'O']. Concatenating all strings in the list will give us \\"qgodNO\\"."},{"source":"In this task, a passage will be given and the goal is to identify an event from the passage. An event is defined as a single word representing something that happened, is happening, or may happen. An event can be factual or hypothetical, positive or negative, certain or uncertain. While most events are based on verbs, an event can also be based on a noun (ex. storm, snow, rainfall) or a copula verb (is, was, been, etc.). The event must not be a pronoun or an adjective. For noun events with multiple words, use the last word in the phrase as event.\\n\\nPassage: The Health Ministry has launched a program to conduct regular monitoring of rabies across the country to collect evidence and use it as a basis for drafting regulations that can effectively control rabies. Rabies was followed by tuberculosis, AIDS, hepatitis B and infant tetanus on the list of the most deadly infectious diseases in China.","target":"launched","rationale":"The event should be a single word that represents something that happened, is happening, or may happen. The passage states that \\"The Health Ministry has launched a program to conduct regular monitoring of rabies across the country\\". In this case, \\"launched\\" is the verb and can be used as an event."},{"source":"Question: who holds the world record for the 100m sprint??\\nAnswer:","target":"Usain Bolt","rationale":"The answer is Usain Bolt.\\nUsain St Leo Bolt, born 21 August 1986) is a Jamaican retired sprinter and world record holder in the 100 metres, 200 metres and 4 \\\\u00d7 100 metres relay."},{"source":"Question: what criminal act did whoopi goldberg commit?\\nWould \\"Goldberg made her film debut in The Color Purple (1985), playing Celie, a mistreated black woman in the Deep South.\\" be a reasonable answer?","target":"No","rationale":"The answer provided, \\"Goldberg made her film debut in The Color Purple (1985), playing Celie, a mistreated black woman in the Deep South,\\" is not related to any criminal act committed by Whoopi Goldberg. \\nIn conclusion, based on this information, the answer provided is not a reasonable answer to the question of what crime did Whoopi Goldberg commit? so it can be considered as wrong and should be validated with No."},{"source":"Two analogies that relate actions with their consequences are given in the form \\"A : B. C : ?\\". The phrase \\"A : B\\" relates action A to consequence B. Your task is to replace the question mark (?) with the appropriate consquence of the given action C, following the \\"A : B\\" relation. Your answer should be a single verb, without further explanation.\\n\\ntrip : stumble. cut : ?","target":"bleed","rationale":"If a person trips and stumbles, they may cut themselves. If so, then their skin would bleed."},{"source":"What's the answer to that question: where is the country of cyprus located?","target":"Cyprus","rationale":"The answer is Cyprus.\\nHere's an direct answer: The Republic of Cyprus, a member state of the European Union since 2004 and an independent republic since 1960."},{"source":"Q: when is season 3 of school of rock coming out? A:","target":"July¬†8,¬†2017","rationale":"The answer is based on the fact that season 3 of School of Rock was scheduled to air on July 8, 2017. This can be confirmed through various credible sources such as news articles and websites dedicated to television shows.\\nTherefore, the correct answer should be \\"July¬†8,¬†2017\\""},{"source":"Answer the question depending on the context.\\nContext: The rediscovery of Aristotle's works‚Äìmore than 3000 pages of it would eventually be translated ‚Äìfuelled a spirit of inquiry into natural processes that had already begun to emerge in the 12th century. Some scholars believe that these works represented one of the most important document discoveries in Western intellectual history. Richard Dales, for instance, calls the discovery of Aristotle's works \\"a turning point in the history of Western thought.\\" After Aristotle re-emerged, a community of scholars, primarily communicating in Latin, accelerated the process and practice of attempting to reconcile the thoughts of Greek antiquity, and especially ideas related to understanding the natural world, with those of the church. The efforts of this \\"scholasticism\\" were focused on applying Aristotelian logic and thoughts about natural processes to biblical passages and attempting to prove the viability of those passages through reason. This became the primary mission of lecturers, and the expectation of students.;\\nQuestion: What faculty did scholars attempt to use to prove the thoughts of Aristotle?;\\nIf you can't find the answer, please respond \\"unanswerable\\".\\nAnswer:","target":"reason","rationale":"The context states that a community of scholars were attempting to reconcile the thoughts of Greek antiquity with those of the church. In order to accomplish this, they used Aristotelian logic and applied it to biblical passages in an attempt to prove their viability through reason. \\nTherefore, \\"reason\\" is correct answer."},{"source":"Formulate an answer to this elaborate question: What band resides in a county town whose name means \\"the left-handed mill\\"?","target":"The Aftermath","rationale":"An answer could be: \\"The Aftermath resides in a county town whose name means 'the left-handed mill'.\\""},{"source":"Indicate the presence of numerical data in the abstract (whether numerical data plays a key role in medical records), solely using the information from the abstract.\\n\\nAbstract: Fibroblasts from two affected members of a large pedigree in which osteogenesis imperfecta (OI) type IV is genetically linked to the pro alpha 2(I) gene of type I collagen synthesize two populations of pro alpha 2(I) chains. One population is normal; the second population appears to have a deletion of about 10 amino acid residues from the middle of the triple helical domain. The mutation in pro alpha 2(I) causes increased posttranslational modification in the amino-terminal half of some pro alpha 1(I) chains, lowers the melting temperature of type I collagen molecules that incorporate a mutant pro alpha 2(I) chain, and prevents or delays the secretion of those molecules from fibroblasts in cell culture. On the basis of this study and linkage studies in additional families, it appears that the OI type IV phenotype is often the result of heterozygosity for mutations in pro alpha 2(I) that alter the triple helical structure of type I collagen. \\nQuestion: Does the abstract contain any numerical data?","target":"Yes","rationale":"The abstract does include numerical values (i.e., \\"10 amino acid residues\\" and \\"two populations of pro alpha 2(I) chains\\"). So the answer is ‚ÄúYes‚Äù."},{"source":"In this task you will be given a list of numbers and you need to subtract every value in the list with the index it is at. The index of an elements shows its numerical order in the list(for example, in the list [7,10,4,5], the index of 7 is 1 and the index of 4 is 3)  You should start the index at 1, so the first element in the list will be subtracted by one. For every element in the list you need to find \\"element - index\\" where the index of the beginning element is 1 and increments by 1 for each element. Put your result list in brackets.\\n\\n[0, 19]","target":"[-1, 17]","rationale":"Given the list [0, 19], we need to subtract every value in the list with their respective index.\\\\n1. The 1st element is 0, so (0 - 1) = -1\\\\n2. The 2nd element is 19, so (19 - 2) = 17\\\\nThe final result will be [-1, 17]"},{"source":"What are the first names of the people who return from the circus?\\n\\nAnswer the above question based on the context below:\\n\\nCasey is an adolescent boy whose life is constantly influenced by his intense fear of clowns. His two older brothers, Geoffrey and Randy, are mostly disobliging. One night, the three boys are left alone when their mother visits relatives, so they decide to visit a local circus for a night of amusement, despite Casey's uncontrollable coulrophobia. Meanwhile, the local state insane asylum has sent a majority of the hospital's inmates to the carnival for therapy, but three psychotic mental patients break away from the group and kill three clowns, taking their makeup and costumes.\\nWhile at the circus, Casey innocently visits a fortune teller despite Randy's better judgment. The fortune teller reveals to Casey that his life line has been cut short, and says to him: \\"Beware, beware, in the darkest of dark /though the flesh is young and the hearts are strong /precious life cannot be long /when darkest death has left its mark.\\"\\nAs the boys return from the circus, a shaken Casey thinks his nightmare is over, but it has only just begun. When the clowns target their home, Casey is forced to face his fears once and for all. Casey and his brothers are locked inside their isolated farmhouse and the power is turned off. Casey attempts to call the police, but because Casey says that the \\"clowns from the circus are trying to get him\\", the police officers assume that Casey's fear of clowns caused him to have a realistic nightmare. The officers tell Casey that everything will be fine if he goes back to sleep, and hangs up.\\nRandy mockingly dresses up as a clown, disbelieving of Casey's claims that clowns are inside the house. His plan to jump out at Geoffrey and Casey is cut short after he is stabbed by one of the clowns. Geoffrey manages to kill the first clown by hitting him with a wooden plank, knocking him down a flight of stairs and breaking his neck.","target":"Casey","rationale":"The context outlines the following:\\n- Casey and his two brothers go to a circus. \\n- They are left alone by their mother at home, and decide to see what is going on inside the tent of fortune teller (despite Randy's better judgment) - The fortune teller reveals that Casey‚Äôs life line has been cut short. \\n- When they return from circus, three clowns break into their house, lock them up in it. \\n- Three psychotic mental patients kill 3 clowns who have taken over their costumes. One brother is killed by one such patient dressed as a clown before Casey manages to defeat him with help from Geoffrey.(Geoffrey kills one of these men.)"},{"source":"An atom is the very smallest particle that still the elements properties. All the atoms of an element are alike. They are also different from the atoms of all other elements. For example, atoms of gold are always the same. It does not matter if they are found in a gold nugget or a gold ring. All gold atoms have the same structure and properties. For example, all gold atoms contain 79 protons. One of golds unique properties is that it is a great conductor of electricity. Gold is a better conductor of electricity than copper. Gold is more rare and expensive than copper. Copper is used in house wiring. Gold is far too expensive. \\nQuestion: Do atoms of Gold differ?\\n\\nI am grading my students' exercises. Is the answer \\"No\\" correct?","target":"Yes","rationale":"Atoms of gold are the same in that they all contain 79 protons, but differ based on their unique properties. Gold is a great conductor of electricity, while copper conductivity is more common and less expensive.\\nSo the answer to \\"Do atoms of Gold differ?\\" should be Yes"},{"source":"Given a passage with a question and an answer to that question, classify if the answer actually answers the question into 'yes' or 'no'. Output 'yes' if the answer answers the question and output 'no' if the answer does not answer the question.\\n\\nQuestion: Does preoperative infliximab therapy increase morbidity and mortality after laparoscopic resection for inflammatory bowel disease?\\nAnswer: This study is subject to the limitations of a retrospective design.","target":"no","rationale":"The answer to the question is \\"This study is subject to the limitations of a retrospective design\\", which does not answer the question. The correct answer would be \\"No, preoperative infliximab therapy does not increase morbidity and mortality after laparoscopic resection for inflammatory bowel disease.\\" Therefore, this passage can be classified as 'no'."},{"source":"Sentence: \\"I reported him having kissed Mary.\\"\\nWould a linguist rate this sentence to be acceptable linguistically?\\n\\nOPTIONS:\\n- unacceptable\\n- acceptable","target":"acceptable","rationale":"The given sentence follows the subject-verb-object structure. The subject is \\"I\\", the verb is \\"reported,\\" and the object is \\"him having kissed Mary.\\" Therefore, this sentence can be considered linguistically acceptable."},{"source":"In this task, you're given a context, further information available on a particular linked term from the statement, and an answer term. Your job is to generate a question that can use the information provided to obtain the given answer. You should use the information on both context and link information to create the question. Note that the answer to the question should be exactly the given answer, and if the answer is none, the answer to the question shouldn't be obtainable from the context or linked information.\\n\\nContext: which the 1943 Quebec Agreement merged with the American Manhattan Project Link Information: Lord Cherwell had taken the matter to the Prime Minister, Winston Churchill, who became the first national leader to approve a nuclear weapons programme on 30 August 1941 Answer: 2","target":"How long had the secret project, Tube Alloys, been going on before it merged with the American Manhattan Project according to the Quebec Agreement?","rationale":"Link information indicates that the information regarding \\"Tube Alloys\\" is available in context. It also provides the date of 30 August 1941 as approval for nuclear weapons programme, which was the first approval for any country. It can be inferred from this that Tube Alloys had started at least a month before its approval by Prime Minister Winston Churchill. Since Tube Alloys merged with Manhattan Project according to Quebec Agreement, and no other dates are provided in link information, we assume Tube Alloys existed only for a month before merging with Manhattan Project on Quebec Agreement. And hence we ask question \\"How long had the secret project, Tube Alloys, been going on before it merged with the American Manhattan Project according to the Quebec Agreement?\\". The answer to this question is 2 (months)."},{"source":"Q: Most people can survive only a few days without what essential substance?\\n\\n\\nRead this paragraph and choose the correct option from the provided answers:\\n\\nWater is essential to life because biochemical reactions take place in water. Most people can survive only a few days without water.\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- air\\n\\n- food\\n\\n- carbon\\n\\n- water\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"water","rationale":"The paragraph states that most people can survive only a few days without water, which is essential to life. The correct answer is therefore \\"water\\"."},{"source":"The verbs of most aspect pairs differ in one of two ways: by prefix or by suffix. In prefix pairs, the perfective verb has an added prefix‚Äîfor example, the imperfective ps√°t (to write, to be writing) compared with the perfective napsat (to write down, to finish writing). The most common prefixes are na-, o-, po-, s-, u-, vy-, z- and za-. In suffix pairs, a different infinitive ending is added to the perfective stem; for example, the perfective verbs koupit (to buy) and prodat (to sell) have the imperfective forms kupovat and prod√°vat. Imperfective verbs may undergo further morphology to make other imperfective verbs (iterative and frequentative forms), denoting repeated or regular action. The verb j√≠t (to go) has the iterative form chodit (to go repeatedly) and the frequentative form chod√≠vat (to go regularly).\\nThis is about","target":"Czech language","rationale":"The given context is about the verbs and how they are present in Czech language."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a question and answer options for that question. Using this information, you have to classify each text into different topics: medicine, nursery, psychology, chemistry, pharmacology, biology.\\n\\nQuestion: What are the possibilities, in each pregnancy, of parents bearing a mutation in the CFTR gene, having a child with cystic fibrosis? \\n Options:  <0> 0.01. <1> 0.1 <2> 0,25. <3> 0.5. <4> one.","target":"medicine","rationale":"This question addresses the likelihood of a child having cystic fibrosis, which is a genetic disease. Therefore, this question is classified as \\"medicine\\"."},{"source":"On January 1, 2015, Gasol recorded a career-high 9 blocks, along with 17 points and 9 rebounds, in the 106-101 win over the 2014-15 Denver Nuggets season. Ten days later, he scored a career-high 46 points on 17-of-30 shooting in a 95-87 win over the 2014-15 Milwaukee Bucks season. On April 9, 2015, he recorded a league-best 51st double-double of the season with 16 points and 15 rebounds in an 89-78 win over the 2014-15 Miami Heat season. He recorded his 54th double-double of the season in the regular season finale on April 15 against the 2014-15 Atlanta Hawks season to finish as the league-leader in double-doubles in 2014-15.\\n\\nAsk a question about this article.","target":"On what date did Gasol score a career-high 46 points?","rationale":"Here's an example of a question for the given article:\\\\n\\\\nQuestion: On what date did Gasol score a career-high 46 points?"},{"source":"Q: Fertilization occurs when what material from one flower reaches the female gametes in the same or a different flower?\\n\\n\\nRead this paragraph and choose the correct option from the provided answers:\\n\\nPea plants reproduce sexually. The male gametes are released by tiny grains of pollen. The female gametes lie deep within the flowers. Fertilization occurs when pollen from one flower reaches the female gametes in the same or a different flower. This is called pollination . Mendel was able to control which plants pollinated each other. He transferred pollen by hand from flower to flower.\\n\\n Choices:\\n\\n- ova\\n\\n- nitrogen\\n\\n- sperm\\n\\n- pollen\\n\\n\\nA:","target":"pollen","rationale":"Pollen is the material released by male gametes (analogous to sperm) that, when it reaches female gametes in flowers of the same or different plants, allows for fertilization. \\nTherefore, pollen is required for fertilization so answer is pollen"},{"source":"The following article contains an answer for the question: What is the first name of the person who performed a Bach Prelude and Fugue on the piano in July 1922? , can you please find it? \\n\\nDescriptions of Imogen as a small child indicate that she had blue eyes, fair hair, an oval face reminiscent of her father's, and a rather prominent nose inherited from her mother.  In 1912, at the age of five, she joined the kindergarten class at the Froebel Institute, and remained at the school for five years. Summers were often spent at the Holsts' rented country cottage at Thaxted in Essex, where Gustav Holst began an annual Whitsun Festival in 1916.In 1917 Imogen began boarding at Eothen, a small, private school for girls in Caterham, where Jane Joseph, Gustav's star pupil from SPGS, taught music.  A letter home, dated 17 July 1917, tells of \\"compertishions [sic], and ripping prizes, and strawberries and cream for tea\\".  At the school, Imogen studied piano with Eleanor Shuttleworth, violin with Andr√© Mangeot (described as \\"topping\\") and theory with Jane Joseph (\\"ripping\\"). Under Joseph's tuition Imogen produced her first compositions‚Äîtwo instrumental pieces and four Christmas carol tunes‚Äîwhich she numbered as Ops. 1, 2, and 3. In the summer term of 1920, she composed and choreographed a \\"Dance of the Nymphs and Shepherds\\", which was performed at the school under her direction on 9 July.Imogen left Eothen in December 1920 hoping to study under Ruby Ginner at the Ginner-Mawer School of Dance and Drama, but was rejected on health grounds, although there appeared to be no significant medical issue. She then studied at home under a governess, while waiting to start at St Paul's Girls School in the autumn. At Whitsun 1921 she took part as a dancer in her father's production of Purcell's semi-opera from 1690, Masque of Dioclesian, held in the St Paul's School grounds and repeated a week later in Hyde Park.In September 1921 Imogen began at St Paul's Girls School, and became a boarder from Spring 1922. In July 1922 she performed a Bach Prelude and Fugue on the piano, for which Joseph praised her warmly, writing: \\"I think everyone enjoyed the Bach from beginning to end, they all made nice contented noises at the...","target":"Imogen","rationale":"The answer is Imogen."},{"source":"Exercise: read the text and answer the question by True or False.\\n\\nText: Bowling Green (IRT Lexington Avenue Line) -- Bowling Green is a station on the IRT Lexington Avenue Line of the New York City Subway, located at Broadway and Battery Place (at the Bowling Green), in the Financial District of Manhattan. It is served by the 4 train at all times and the 5 train at all times except late nights.\\nQuestion: does the 4 train stop at bowling green?","target":"True","rationale":"The text mentions that the 4 train stops at Bowling Green. So, the answer is True."},{"source":"In this task, you are given an input list A. You need to find all the elements of the list that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\n\\n['S', 'Q', 'W', '1763', '3803', '1077', 'Y', 'v', '3005', 's', '4105', '7907', '9505']","target":"31165","rationale":"Given the list ['S', 'Q', 'W', '1763', '3803', '1077', 'Y', 'v', '3005', 's'], we need to find the elements that are numbers and calculate their sum.\\\\n1. 1763 is a number, so it is added to the total sum.\\\\n2. 3803 is a number, so it is added to the total sum (total = 5576).\\\\n3. 1077 is a number, so it is added to the total sum (total = 6653).\\\\n4. 3005 is a number, so it is added to the total sum (total = 9658).\\\\n5. 4105 is a number, so it's added to the final result (final result = 31165)."},{"source":"In this task, you are given a multiple-choice question about healthcare. Answer the question based on your information and classify your answers into '1', '2', '3', and '4'.\\n\\nQuestion: Chronic interstitial nephropathies affect the tubular structures and the renal interstitium. If we analyze the functional defects that these pathologies can produce, we will NOT wait to find: \\n Options:  <1> Isostenuria. <2> Hypochloremic metabolic alkalosis. <3> Tubular atrophy and interstitial fibrosis in the renal histological study. <4> Normal or little expressive urinary sediment. <5> Proteinuria of less than 2 grams per day.","target":"2","rationale":"The question deals with the consequences of chronic interstitial nephropathy. The first rule to consider is that, in some cases, the glomerular filtration rate can be preserved during the disease course. Then, when analyzing renal tubular function and its defects, we can find a decrease in glomerular filtration rate (isostenuria), an increase in tubular reabsorption of sodium chloride (hypochloremic metabolic alkalosis), impairment of renal excretion capacity (proteinuria less than 2 grams per day) and alterations in urinary sediment (tubular atrophy and interstitial fibrosis). However, as described above all these findings are related to different disorders or diseases affecting the same anatomical structures; therefore they cannot be considered as manifestations of a single kidney disease. Consequently we have to look for which answer option is referring to another pathology that affects other anatomical structures: Option 2 describes hypokalemia due to hyperaldosteronism. Option 3 refers to a finding related with multiple myeloma but not strictly linked with kidney involvement: anemia due to bone marrow infiltration by myeloma cells. Finally Option 5 refers also to nephropathy but caused by diabetes mellitus, not by chronic interstitial nephritis. So only Option 2 does not describe a functional defect caused by chronic interstitial nephritis; therefore it is correct answer '2'."},{"source":"In this task, you need to answer the given multiple-choice question on the physics. Classify your answers into 'a', 'b', 'c', 'd', and 'e'.\\n\\nProblem: a boat having a length 8 m and breadth 3 m is floating on a lake . the boat sinks by 1 cm when a man gets on it . the mass of the man is : \\nOptions: a ) 100 kg , b ) 120 kg , c ) 89 kg , d ) 80 kg , e ) 240 kg","target":"e","rationale":"The volume of the boat = 8 x 3 = 24 m^3. The density of water = 1 g/cm^3.\\nThe mass of the man is equal to the weight of water displaced by him and this weight can be calculated as:\\n\\\\(mass\\\\_of\\\\_man=density \\\\times Volume\\\\\\\\)\\nHere, density = 1g/cm^3 and volume = (8 x 3 x 0.01) m^3 or \\\\(volume=(24x0.1x0.1)m^3\\\\\\\\) \\nSo, the mass is given by: \\\\(mass=density \\\\times Volume\\\\\\\\), which is \\\\(mass=1 \\\\times (24x0.01x0.01)=240 kg\\\\)"}]`),q={components:{PoemCard:M},data(){return{poemsData:H,visibleCount:6,isLoading:!1}},computed:{hasMorePoems(){return this.visibleCount<this.poemsData.length}},methods:{async loadMore(){this.isLoading=!0,await new Promise(o=>setTimeout(o,1e3)),this.visibleCount+=6,this.isLoading=!1}}},P={class:"card-container"},W=["disabled"],N={key:0},D={key:1};function O(o,e,c,m,i,s){const r=v("PoemCard");return a(),n("section",null,[e[1]||(e[1]=t("div",{class:"top-banner"},[t("div",{class:"top-banner-title"},[t("div",{class:"top-banner-title-text"},"üéâ Chain of Thought ü•≥")])],-1)),t("div",P,[d(r,{poems:i.poemsData},null,8,["poems"])]),s.hasMorePoems?(a(),n("button",{key:0,class:"load-more-button",disabled:i.isLoading,onClick:e[0]||(e[0]=(...h)=>s.loadMore&&s.loadMore(...h))},[i.isLoading?(a(),n("span",D,"Loading...")):(a(),n("span",N,"See more"))],8,W)):k("",!0)])}const E=u(q,[["render",O],["__scopeId","data-v-a7cda0ad"]]),G=JSON.parse('{"title":"","description":"","frontmatter":{"page":true},"headers":[],"relativePath":"sponsor/6.md","filePath":"sponsor/6.md"}'),R={name:"sponsor/6.md"},L=Object.assign(R,{setup(o){return(e,c)=>(a(),n("div",null,[d(E)]))}});export{G as __pageData,L as default};
